WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.579
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:17.579 --> 00:00:22.500
Book Five, The Brightest Night, by 2ET

00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:25.859
Sutherland, read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:46.619
The Dragonette Prophecy.

00:00:46.679 --> 00:00:50.759
When the war has lasted 20 years, the

00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:51.719
dragonettes will come.

00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:54.899
When the land is soaked in blood and

00:00:54.899 --> 00:00:57.780
tears, the dragonettes will come.

00:00:57.840 --> 00:01:01.740
Find the sea wing egg of deepest blue

00:01:01.740 --> 00:01:04.319
wings of night shall come to you.

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:08.339
The largest egg in mountain high will

00:01:08.339 --> 00:01:09.959
give to you the wings of sky.

00:01:10.019 --> 00:01:13.560
For wings of earth, search through the

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:16.260
mud, for an egg the color of dragon

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:16.859
blood.

00:01:16.920 --> 00:01:20.700
And hidden alone from the rival queens.

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:23.640
The sand wing egg awaits unseen.

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:28.079
Of 3 queens who blister and blaze and

00:01:28.079 --> 00:01:28.620
burn.

00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:33.239
Two shall die, and one shall learn, If

00:01:33.239 --> 00:01:35.340
she bows to a fate that is stronger and

00:01:35.340 --> 00:01:38.519
higher, She'll have the power of wings of

00:01:38.519 --> 00:01:38.879
fire.

00:01:38.939 --> 00:01:43.019
Five eggs to hatch on brightest night.

00:01:43.079 --> 00:01:46.319
Five dragons born to end the fight.

00:01:46.379 --> 00:01:49.620
Darkness will rise to bring the light.

00:01:49.680 --> 00:02:11.400
The dragonettes are coming. 20 years

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:11.639
ago.

00:02:11.699 --> 00:02:15.240
It is nearly impossible to steal from a

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:18.539
dragon, particularly a royal one with a

00:02:18.539 --> 00:02:20.879
palace and guards and very high walls.

00:02:20.939 --> 00:02:24.780
At least, that's what Queen Oasis kept

00:02:24.780 --> 00:02:26.580
telling herself as she hurried along the

00:02:26.580 --> 00:02:28.919
dark halls, breathing fire to light her

00:02:28.919 --> 00:02:32.520
way, Nearly impossible, and decidedly

00:02:32.520 --> 00:02:32.939
stupid.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.599
And yet, she had this terrible feeling.

00:02:36.659 --> 00:02:38.639
Something was wrong.

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:42.180
There was something scrabbling around in

00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:42.780
her palace.

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:45.599
With her exceptionally sharp, sandwing

00:02:45.599 --> 00:02:46.020
hearing.

00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:48.360
She was sure she could hear squeaking

00:02:48.360 --> 00:02:51.659
like faraway mice, and perhaps the

00:02:51.659 --> 00:02:52.860
clinking of coins.

00:02:52.919 --> 00:02:55.259
But mice didn't steal treasure.

00:02:55.319 --> 00:02:57.419
So what was it?

00:02:57.479 --> 00:02:58.919
Was she imagining it?

00:02:58.979 --> 00:03:01.259
She'd woken from a deep sleep with a

00:03:01.259 --> 00:03:03.300
start, as if someone had stabbed her in

00:03:03.300 --> 00:03:04.800
the chest with his venomous tail.

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:08.939
It seemed unlikely, but she was going to

00:03:08.939 --> 00:03:09.960
check on her treasure anyway.

00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:13.139
The sand wing queen whirled around a

00:03:13.139 --> 00:03:14.939
corner and collided with 2 of her

00:03:14.939 --> 00:03:17.039
daughters, Blaze, and Blister.

00:03:17.099 --> 00:03:21.479
Ow, Blaise complained, hopping backward

00:03:21.479 --> 00:03:22.199
with a grimace.

00:03:22.259 --> 00:03:24.419
Mother, you stepped on my foot.

00:03:24.479 --> 00:03:28.139
Blister said nothing, but side stepped

00:03:28.139 --> 00:03:29.580
into a corner to get out of the queen's

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:29.819
way.

00:03:29.879 --> 00:03:32.400
Her dark eyes were fixed on every move

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:35.699
Oasis made, in that unsettling way she

00:03:35.699 --> 00:03:35.939
had.

00:03:36.060 --> 00:03:38.939
Oasis had had a feeling from the moment

00:03:38.939 --> 00:03:39.960
blister hatched.

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:42.419
This was the daughter who was going to

00:03:42.419 --> 00:03:42.840
kill her.

00:03:42.900 --> 00:03:46.199
Her oldest daughter, Bern, was bigger and

00:03:46.199 --> 00:03:46.740
stronger.

00:03:46.800 --> 00:03:49.199
But Oasis and Bern actually got along in

00:03:49.199 --> 00:03:49.500
a way.

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:51.479
They understood each other.

00:03:51.539 --> 00:03:53.759
Apart from burns obsession with

00:03:53.759 --> 00:03:56.400
mutilating animals, and it was easy to

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:57.360
distract burn.

00:03:57.419 --> 00:03:59.639
Give her something creepy looking, and

00:03:59.639 --> 00:04:01.979
she'd disappear into her rooms for days.

00:04:02.039 --> 00:04:05.460
Blister, on the other talon, always

00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:07.020
seemed to be calculating the moments

00:04:07.020 --> 00:04:09.960
until her mother's demise, and she'd been

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:11.340
like that ever since she was a small

00:04:11.340 --> 00:04:12.240
dragonette.

00:04:12.300 --> 00:04:15.060
Ever since she'd 1st realized that

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:17.399
killing her mother would make her queen.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:19.439
Go ahead and challenge me.

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:22.680
Oasis thought scornfully, glaring down at

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:23.100
blister.

00:04:23.220 --> 00:04:25.439
I'd squash you like a bug and you know

00:04:25.439 --> 00:04:25.620
it.

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:27.480
What's the hurry?

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:30.480
Blister asked smoothly, as if she

00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:31.920
couldn't sense the malevolence in her

00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:32.759
mother's gaze.

00:04:32.819 --> 00:04:34.560
Is there a royal crisis?

00:04:34.620 --> 00:04:35.519
Let me guess.

00:04:35.579 --> 00:04:37.319
Smolder tried to run off with his

00:04:37.319 --> 00:04:37.800
girlfriend again?

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:41.699
No, I took care of her, Oasis said.

00:04:41.759 --> 00:04:43.199
I'm just going to check the treasury.

00:04:43.259 --> 00:04:46.500
Ew, sparkly things.

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:47.939
Blaze yawned.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:48.839
Good night, mother.

00:04:48.899 --> 00:04:50.879
Dizzy Blaze.

00:04:50.939 --> 00:04:53.040
Oasis thought, as she hurried on.

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:55.860
She'd be a terrible queen, but she's an

00:04:55.860 --> 00:04:56.399
acceptable daughter.

00:04:56.519 --> 00:04:58.439
I don't have to worry about what she'll

00:04:58.439 --> 00:04:58.860
do to me.

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:01.860
She heard Claus click on the stone behind

00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:03.420
her and whirled around.

00:05:03.480 --> 00:05:06.000
Blister held up her talons and flared her

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:08.160
wings, filling the narrow passageway.

00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:10.199
Sorry to startle you.

00:05:10.259 --> 00:05:12.060
She said unconvincingly.

00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:13.920
I just wondered if I could come with

00:05:13.920 --> 00:05:14.100
you.

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:16.379
Oasis hesitated.

00:05:16.439 --> 00:05:18.600
But she knew if she said no.

00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:20.459
Blister would find a way to sneak along

00:05:20.459 --> 00:05:20.819
anyway.

00:05:20.879 --> 00:05:23.160
It was always better to keep her where

00:05:23.160 --> 00:05:23.759
you could see her.

00:05:23.879 --> 00:05:26.759
Fine, but don't touch anything.

00:05:26.819 --> 00:05:29.100
I know what you want to see.

00:05:29.160 --> 00:05:30.720
You conniving fiber.

00:05:30.779 --> 00:05:32.879
It won't do you any good until I'm dead

00:05:32.879 --> 00:05:33.240
though.

00:05:33.300 --> 00:05:36.540
They whisked down the long passage that

00:05:36.540 --> 00:05:38.100
led to the 4 treasure rooms.

00:05:38.160 --> 00:05:39.779
Everything looked in order.

00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:42.000
The torches flickered peacefully.

00:05:42.060 --> 00:05:43.680
The doors were closed and locked.

00:05:43.740 --> 00:05:46.379
But there was a strange smell.

00:05:46.439 --> 00:05:50.459
Something hairy, and woodsy, and flowery

00:05:50.459 --> 00:05:51.120
at the same time.

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:53.819
Something had definitely been here.

00:05:53.879 --> 00:05:57.300
Oasis crouched to peer under the doors.

00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:59.939
There was a large gap between the doors

00:05:59.939 --> 00:06:02.279
and the floor, not large enough for a

00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:05.100
dragon, of course, but do you smell

00:06:05.100 --> 00:06:06.060
scavenger?

00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:07.740
She asked blister.

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:09.660
I wouldn't know what those smell like

00:06:09.660 --> 00:06:11.699
blister said, wrinkling her nose.

00:06:11.759 --> 00:06:13.980
They're too bulky and squishy for my

00:06:13.980 --> 00:06:14.279
taste.

00:06:14.339 --> 00:06:17.699
Queen Oasis selected the right keys from

00:06:17.699 --> 00:06:19.860
around her neck and unlocked all the

00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:22.199
doors, then did a sweep through each room

00:06:22.199 --> 00:06:23.819
leaving the doors open.

00:06:23.819 --> 00:06:27.180
She came back out, glowering with rage.

00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:31.019
That looks ominous, Blister remarked.

00:06:31.079 --> 00:06:34.680
Scavengers, spat the queen.

00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:36.120
Robbed me.

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:37.740
How dare they?

00:06:37.860 --> 00:06:40.259
She lashed her tail, hissing.

00:06:40.319 --> 00:06:41.939
They can't have gone far.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.980
Wake up, burn and tell her to meet me

00:06:43.980 --> 00:06:44.279
outside.

00:06:44.339 --> 00:06:46.319
Burn?

00:06:46.439 --> 00:06:48.839
Blister echoed, glancing over her

00:06:48.839 --> 00:06:50.819
mother's shoulder at the treasure rooms.

00:06:50.939 --> 00:06:53.399
Just in case there are a lot of them and

00:06:53.399 --> 00:06:54.000
we need to fight.

00:06:54.060 --> 00:06:55.500
Oasis said.

00:06:55.560 --> 00:06:57.720
I've seen what their tiny swords can do.

00:06:57.779 --> 00:06:59.819
I'm not such a fool as to go out there

00:06:59.819 --> 00:07:00.060
alone.

00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:04.139
Oh no, of course not, Blister said.

00:07:04.199 --> 00:07:05.699
But why burn?

00:07:05.819 --> 00:07:06.480
When I'm here.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:09.060
Oasis gave her a withering look.

00:07:09.120 --> 00:07:12.000
I need a real fighter, she said.

00:07:12.060 --> 00:07:13.980
Not someone who thinks she can use her

00:07:13.980 --> 00:07:16.019
brain to get herself out of anything and

00:07:16.019 --> 00:07:17.579
isn't even as smart as she thinks she

00:07:17.579 --> 00:07:17.879
is.

00:07:17.939 --> 00:07:21.240
I see, Blister said coldly.

00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:22.980
I'll wake her at once.

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:26.040
She took a step up the corridor, then

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:26.459
turned back.

00:07:26.519 --> 00:07:28.259
What did they take?

00:07:28.319 --> 00:07:30.839
Small things for the most part.

00:07:30.899 --> 00:07:34.019
Oasis growled, but they also took the eye

00:07:34.019 --> 00:07:34.800
of onyx.

00:07:34.860 --> 00:07:38.100
That actually made blisters face twitch

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:41.579
as if a hint of a real emotion, worry

00:07:41.579 --> 00:07:43.800
surprise, was trying to come through.

00:07:43.860 --> 00:07:47.819
We'll get it back, Oasis promised, and

00:07:47.819 --> 00:07:49.319
we'll have roasted scavenger for

00:07:49.319 --> 00:07:49.740
breakfast.

00:07:49.800 --> 00:07:52.980
She pushed past blister and stormed

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:54.420
toward the nearest route to the sky.

00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:57.300
I'm going out there, wake burn, and

00:07:57.300 --> 00:07:57.720
hurry.

00:07:57.779 --> 00:07:59.279
Oh yes.

00:07:59.339 --> 00:08:01.860
Right away, Blister said.

00:08:01.920 --> 00:08:05.279
As Oasis charged into the courtyard

00:08:05.279 --> 00:08:07.860
spread her wings and lifted into the sky

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:10.379
she thought for a moment that she saw a

00:08:10.379 --> 00:08:12.060
blister turn to look back at the treasure

00:08:12.060 --> 00:08:12.660
rooms instead.

00:08:12.779 --> 00:08:15.480
I forgot to lock them up again.

00:08:15.540 --> 00:08:17.339
Oasis thought uneasily.

00:08:17.459 --> 00:08:19.500
But this will only take a minute.

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:21.660
And if she's stupid enough to take

00:08:21.660 --> 00:08:22.079
anything.

00:08:22.139 --> 00:08:24.000
I'll have a good excuse to kill her.

00:08:24.060 --> 00:08:25.620
She's smarter than that.

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:29.040
She wheeled toward the outer walls

00:08:29.040 --> 00:08:30.600
scanning the sands.

00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:32.639
A disturbing thought occurred to her.

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:35.220
What if she doesn't wake burn?

00:08:35.279 --> 00:08:37.440
What if I'm going to face the thieves

00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:39.059
alone with no backup?

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.340
Then she spotted them.

00:08:41.399 --> 00:08:44.519
Three scavengers, 2 of them waiting on

00:08:44.519 --> 00:08:46.740
the sand, the other climbing down from a

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:48.960
window, none of them watching the sky.

00:08:49.019 --> 00:08:52.080
Scab infested idiot monkeys.

00:08:52.139 --> 00:08:55.679
Oasis growled, and folded her wings to

00:08:55.679 --> 00:08:57.659
drop down silently behind them.

00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:59.639
Maybe she could scare them to death.

00:08:59.700 --> 00:09:02.159
Prey always tasted better when it died

00:09:02.159 --> 00:09:02.519
like that.

00:09:02.639 --> 00:09:04.679
Only 3 of them.

00:09:04.740 --> 00:09:05.759
She thought.

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:08.340
I don't need to wait for burn, if

00:09:08.340 --> 00:09:09.480
blisters even getting her.

00:09:09.539 --> 00:09:11.879
I can certainly handle 3 annoying

00:09:11.879 --> 00:09:13.379
scavengers by myself.

00:09:13.440 --> 00:09:17.039
She narrowed her eyes, advancing up the

00:09:17.039 --> 00:09:19.740
dunes toward the sound of squeaking, after

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:20.039
all.

00:09:20.100 --> 00:09:21.899
What's the worst that could happen?

00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:28.320
Part one, The Shifting Sands.

00:09:28.379 --> 00:09:31.019
Chapter one.

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:34.559
Sunny had always known that she was the

00:09:34.559 --> 00:09:36.960
right dragon for a big heroic destiny.

00:09:37.019 --> 00:09:39.600
She was going to save the world.

00:09:39.659 --> 00:09:42.360
She and her friends were going to swoop

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:44.940
in on wings of fire, whatever that meant

00:09:44.940 --> 00:09:47.159
and bring peace to every dragon and

00:09:47.159 --> 00:09:47.759
pyrea.

00:09:47.820 --> 00:09:50.519
It was right there in the prophecy. 5

00:09:50.519 --> 00:09:52.440
dragons born to end the fight.

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:54.179
That was her fate.

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:55.919
That was her purpose.

00:09:56.039 --> 00:09:59.220
Besides, it explained everything.

00:09:59.279 --> 00:10:01.320
Why else was she so small and weird

00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:01.740
looking?

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:04.200
She wasn't a normal sandwing.

00:10:04.259 --> 00:10:06.779
Her scales and eyes were the wrong color

00:10:06.779 --> 00:10:09.000
and she had no venomous bar by the end of

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:10.980
her tail, but that didn't matter.

00:10:11.039 --> 00:10:12.899
In fact, it made sense.

00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:16.080
Of course, a dragon hero with an epic

00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:18.000
noble quest would be a little different

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:18.840
from everyone else.

00:10:18.899 --> 00:10:21.539
And who would care how strange she looked

00:10:21.539 --> 00:10:22.799
once she stopped the war.

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:26.159
Then there were her parents, the

00:10:26.159 --> 00:10:28.019
mysterious dragon who had left her egg

00:10:28.019 --> 00:10:30.600
buried in the sand in the desert, alone

00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:31.740
and unguarded.

00:10:31.799 --> 00:10:33.779
It didn't matter that they obviously

00:10:33.779 --> 00:10:34.620
didn't want her.

00:10:34.679 --> 00:10:37.740
It didn't bother Sonny at all, because it

00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:38.639
was part of the prophecy.

00:10:38.700 --> 00:10:42.659
Hidden alone from the rival queens, the

00:10:42.659 --> 00:10:45.179
sand wing egg awaits unseen.

00:10:45.240 --> 00:10:46.559
That was all right.

00:10:46.620 --> 00:10:49.019
Heroes and the scrolls often had no

00:10:49.019 --> 00:10:49.320
parents.

00:10:49.379 --> 00:10:51.539
Their heroic destiny was more important

00:10:51.539 --> 00:10:52.860
than any family.

00:10:52.919 --> 00:10:55.740
And her destiny was important.

00:10:55.799 --> 00:10:58.500
There was nothing more important than

00:10:58.500 --> 00:11:00.240
stopping the war between the dragon

00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:00.840
tribes.

00:11:00.899 --> 00:11:03.960
All her life, especially whenever she

00:11:03.960 --> 00:11:06.539
felt trapped or sad or worried about

00:11:06.539 --> 00:11:06.899
anything.

00:11:06.960 --> 00:11:09.419
Sonny had imagined fulfilling the

00:11:09.419 --> 00:11:10.019
prophecy.

00:11:10.080 --> 00:11:13.500
How many lives they would save, and all

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:16.379
the happy reunited families, and all the

00:11:16.379 --> 00:11:18.600
future dragonettes, who could grow up in

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:20.940
peace, without the constant fear of war.

00:11:21.059 --> 00:11:23.820
That was the entire point of her life.

00:11:23.879 --> 00:11:25.980
And it was a lie.

00:11:26.039 --> 00:11:30.000
Rock walls scraped against her wings as

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:31.679
she scrambled away from the night wing

00:11:31.679 --> 00:11:32.039
island.

00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:34.799
She could feel the rumbles of the volcano

00:11:34.799 --> 00:11:36.360
all the way through her claws.

00:11:36.419 --> 00:11:39.299
Her friends were behind her, still facing

00:11:39.299 --> 00:11:41.519
Morrow Seer, but she had to get away from

00:11:41.519 --> 00:11:44.159
them, from him, from everything.

00:11:44.220 --> 00:11:46.919
He made up the prophecy.

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:48.299
It was all a trick.

00:11:48.360 --> 00:11:50.700
No, I don't believe it.

00:11:50.759 --> 00:11:53.399
He's a vindictive, cruel dragon, who's

00:11:53.399 --> 00:11:55.379
always manipulated us and everyone around

00:11:55.379 --> 00:11:55.679
him.

00:11:55.740 --> 00:11:57.779
He would say anything to hurt us.

00:11:57.779 --> 00:11:59.820
The prophecy is real.

00:11:59.879 --> 00:12:01.620
It has to be.

00:12:01.679 --> 00:12:04.740
She burst out of the tunnel into the

00:12:04.740 --> 00:12:07.139
rainforest, and immediately slammed into

00:12:07.139 --> 00:12:09.659
the side of a skinny black dragon.

00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:11.460
The night wind grunted with surprise and

00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:12.299
glared at her.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:14.820
So he tried to turn and fly the other way

00:12:14.820 --> 00:12:17.639
but a floundering wall of black wings and

00:12:17.639 --> 00:12:19.559
talons and tails drove her back.

00:12:19.679 --> 00:12:23.340
In the moonlight, the entire rainforest

00:12:23.340 --> 00:12:26.519
seemed to be seething with dragons, roars

00:12:26.519 --> 00:12:29.460
and hisses and growls, drowned out the

00:12:29.460 --> 00:12:31.320
sound of their raindrops pattering on the

00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:32.700
leaves all around them.

00:12:32.759 --> 00:12:34.980
It didn't help that half of the dragons

00:12:34.980 --> 00:12:37.320
were dark as the shadows, and the other

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:40.019
half were camouflaged, so claws and

00:12:40.019 --> 00:12:42.179
corners of wings seemed to suddenly poke

00:12:42.179 --> 00:12:42.779
out of nowhere.

00:12:42.899 --> 00:12:46.500
Sunny narrowly avoided a tail in her ear

00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:48.600
when 2 night wings got caught in a

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:50.519
dangling vine, and whipped around

00:12:50.519 --> 00:12:52.139
violently, as if they were being

00:12:52.139 --> 00:12:52.500
attacked.

00:12:52.559 --> 00:12:55.320
Everyone calmed down.

00:12:55.799 --> 00:12:57.000
Glory's voice shouted.

00:12:57.059 --> 00:13:01.080
Listen, bellowed grandeur, the old royal

00:13:01.080 --> 00:13:01.799
rain wing.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:03.659
Your new queen is speaking.

00:13:03.779 --> 00:13:06.360
Several night wings muttered under their

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:06.659
breath.

00:13:06.779 --> 00:13:09.720
But none loud enough to be heard, and

00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:11.700
even they fell silent as others hissed at

00:13:11.700 --> 00:13:11.879
them.

00:13:11.940 --> 00:13:14.759
Sonny ducked and wriggled through the

00:13:14.759 --> 00:13:16.860
crowd, but she couldn't get any farther

00:13:16.860 --> 00:13:17.460
than the stream.

00:13:17.519 --> 00:13:20.879
Several rain wings stood by the water, in

00:13:20.879 --> 00:13:23.100
shades of blue and purple, holding night

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:23.820
wing spears.

00:13:23.879 --> 00:13:26.700
Most of them were ruining the effect by

00:13:26.700 --> 00:13:28.440
peering at the spears with mystified

00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:30.659
expressions, or holding them upside

00:13:30.659 --> 00:13:30.899
down.

00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:34.440
Still, Sonny decided not to try pushing

00:13:34.440 --> 00:13:34.919
past them.

00:13:34.980 --> 00:13:37.679
Those spears would hurt just as much if

00:13:37.679 --> 00:13:39.179
they poked her by accident as on

00:13:39.179 --> 00:13:39.539
purpose.

00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:43.080
What she really wanted to do was crash

00:13:43.080 --> 00:13:44.879
away into the rainforest and not come

00:13:44.879 --> 00:13:45.240
back.

00:13:45.299 --> 00:13:47.879
She wasn't sure she could face her

00:13:47.879 --> 00:13:50.340
friends, who acted as if they didn't care

00:13:50.340 --> 00:13:51.539
about the prophecy at all.

00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:53.820
And she couldn't even look the night

00:13:53.820 --> 00:13:54.299
wings.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:57.779
Tsunami wants to believe Marosir.

00:13:57.840 --> 00:13:59.879
She's never wanted to fulfill the

00:13:59.879 --> 00:14:00.360
prophecy.

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:03.000
She doesn't understand how important it

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:03.240
is.

00:14:03.299 --> 00:14:06.299
Clay would be just as happy if nobody

00:14:06.299 --> 00:14:08.399
ever noticed how wonderful he is.

00:14:08.460 --> 00:14:11.399
Then he could sleep and eat and take care

00:14:11.399 --> 00:14:12.720
of us instead of fighting.

00:14:12.779 --> 00:14:15.720
Starflight would love to stop worrying

00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:16.620
about the prophecy.

00:14:16.679 --> 00:14:19.740
And glory has enough to do here, now that

00:14:19.740 --> 00:14:20.399
she's queen.

00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:22.620
None of them will fight for our destiny.

00:14:22.679 --> 00:14:25.740
They certainly won't listen to me if I

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:28.080
try to explain that Morrow seer must have

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:28.500
been lying.

00:14:28.559 --> 00:14:31.799
They'll give me that look I always get

00:14:31.799 --> 00:14:34.440
the one that says, oh, silly little Sonny

00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:35.820
and her crazy dreams.

00:14:35.879 --> 00:14:37.740
Isn't she cute and harmless?

00:14:37.799 --> 00:14:41.039
She gazed up at the mass of dark trees

00:14:41.039 --> 00:14:43.500
overhead, where the moonbeams and

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:46.559
raindrops skittered in the wind, even if

00:14:46.559 --> 00:14:48.840
she tried to run off, she'd probably get

00:14:48.840 --> 00:14:51.059
her tail stuck in a tree branch and need

00:14:51.059 --> 00:14:53.220
to be rescued, and then her friends would

00:14:53.220 --> 00:14:55.080
get to roll their eyes and pat her on the

00:14:55.080 --> 00:14:55.379
head again.

00:14:55.440 --> 00:14:58.200
It wouldn't be like this in the desert

00:14:58.259 --> 00:14:59.159
she thought.

00:14:59.220 --> 00:15:01.860
She looked across the stream at the other

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.080
tunnel, the one that led to the kingdom

00:15:04.080 --> 00:15:04.620
of sand.

00:15:04.679 --> 00:15:09.000
There, I could fly and fly and fly all

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:11.159
the way to the horizon without ever

00:15:11.159 --> 00:15:12.000
stopping to think.

00:15:12.059 --> 00:15:15.720
Not thinking, sounded pretty appealing

00:15:15.720 --> 00:15:16.080
right now.

00:15:16.139 --> 00:15:20.220
You're just as ordinary as any other

00:15:20.220 --> 00:15:21.000
dragon.

00:15:21.059 --> 00:15:24.299
Morrisier's spiteful words kept going

00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:26.039
around and around in her head.

00:15:26.100 --> 00:15:29.399
I made up the whole prophecy.

00:15:29.460 --> 00:15:33.299
Now the war will drag on endlessly, and

00:15:33.299 --> 00:15:36.059
more dragons will die every day, probably

00:15:36.059 --> 00:15:38.940
for generations, all of them wondering

00:15:38.940 --> 00:15:41.940
what happened to the amazing dragonettes

00:15:41.940 --> 00:15:43.500
who were supposed to save them.

00:15:43.559 --> 00:15:45.779
But obviously failed.

00:15:45.899 --> 00:15:49.620
Sonny clenched her talons and crouched

00:15:49.620 --> 00:15:50.399
low to the ground.

00:15:50.460 --> 00:15:51.779
He was lying.

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:53.039
He was lying.

00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:54.720
He was lying.

00:15:54.779 --> 00:15:57.419
She wouldn't let these night wings see

00:15:57.419 --> 00:15:57.779
her cry.

00:15:57.840 --> 00:16:01.139
Glory climbed onto a boulder and flapped

00:16:01.139 --> 00:16:04.379
her wings loudly, even up there, and even

00:16:04.379 --> 00:16:07.139
with her queenliest face on, Glory still

00:16:07.139 --> 00:16:09.600
looked like a dragonette, smaller than

00:16:09.600 --> 00:16:11.399
almost all the night wings surrounding

00:16:11.399 --> 00:16:11.639
her.

00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:13.919
If the prophecy is fake.

00:16:13.980 --> 00:16:16.799
Then why was everyone so awful to glory

00:16:16.799 --> 00:16:17.879
about not being in it?

00:16:17.940 --> 00:16:21.240
Sonny thought, feeling another surge of

00:16:21.240 --> 00:16:22.620
fury at Morrow Seer.

00:16:22.679 --> 00:16:26.220
Why make her feel so useless if we're all

00:16:26.220 --> 00:16:26.940
useless?

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:28.740
Because it is real.

00:16:28.799 --> 00:16:30.000
It has to be.

00:16:30.059 --> 00:16:32.279
But how can I prove it?

00:16:32.340 --> 00:16:36.779
Night Wings, Glory said firmly, speaking

00:16:36.779 --> 00:16:38.940
up to be heard over the shuffling dragons

00:16:38.940 --> 00:16:39.840
and the rainstorm.

00:16:39.899 --> 00:16:42.299
Your home is gone.

00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:45.360
Your queen is dead, but this is your

00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:46.440
chance to start over.

00:16:46.500 --> 00:16:49.620
If you mess it up, you'll lose this home

00:16:49.620 --> 00:16:50.159
too.

00:16:50.220 --> 00:16:52.379
She pointed to the rain wings.

00:16:52.440 --> 00:16:55.559
You will treat these dragons with respect

00:16:55.559 --> 00:16:58.320
and in return, because that's the kind of

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:00.539
dragons they are, they will be much

00:17:00.539 --> 00:17:02.039
kinder to you than you deserve.

00:17:02.100 --> 00:17:05.099
The rain wing across the stream from

00:17:05.099 --> 00:17:07.319
sunny, mustered an expression that looked

00:17:07.319 --> 00:17:08.519
almost fierce.

00:17:08.700 --> 00:17:12.299
Rain splattered across Sonny's snout and

00:17:12.299 --> 00:17:12.839
wings.

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:15.660
The storm was picking up strength, ripping

00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:17.099
through the treetops way over their

00:17:17.099 --> 00:17:17.279
heads.

00:17:17.339 --> 00:17:21.359
Tonight, you'll stay right here, Glory

00:17:21.359 --> 00:17:21.719
went on.

00:17:21.839 --> 00:17:24.299
I don't want any night wings wandering

00:17:24.299 --> 00:17:26.279
off until we can count you and write you

00:17:26.279 --> 00:17:26.699
all down.

00:17:26.759 --> 00:17:29.759
You will each be assigned 2 rain wings to

00:17:29.759 --> 00:17:30.599
keep an eye on you.

00:17:30.660 --> 00:17:33.480
And yes, if you're feeling like perhaps

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:35.759
we don't trust you very much, it's

00:17:35.759 --> 00:17:36.420
because we don't.

00:17:36.480 --> 00:17:39.119
None of you are welcome in the rain wing

00:17:39.119 --> 00:17:41.460
village until you earn that trust.

00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:44.160
We will find you somewhere else to live.

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:46.559
We'll get wet out here.

00:17:46.619 --> 00:17:48.779
One of the burlier night wings

00:17:48.779 --> 00:17:49.259
complained.

00:17:49.319 --> 00:17:52.079
Glory gave him a steely glare.

00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:54.539
Feel free to go back and sleep on your

00:17:54.539 --> 00:17:57.119
nice dry island instead, she snapped.

00:17:57.180 --> 00:17:59.099
I hear it's quite warm there.

00:17:59.160 --> 00:18:01.980
Sunny glanced around at the night wings.

00:18:02.099 --> 00:18:04.740
Even in the moonlight, she could see that

00:18:04.740 --> 00:18:06.779
most of them looked badly shaken and

00:18:06.779 --> 00:18:07.200
subdued.

00:18:07.259 --> 00:18:10.619
Seeing their home buried by the volcano

00:18:10.619 --> 00:18:11.880
even if they knew it would happen

00:18:11.880 --> 00:18:14.099
eventually, and even though the island

00:18:14.099 --> 00:18:16.799
had been a terrible place to live, it

00:18:16.799 --> 00:18:18.420
still must have been an awful shock.

00:18:18.539 --> 00:18:21.539
Something like being told your whole life

00:18:21.539 --> 00:18:22.799
is a lie, I imagine.

00:18:22.859 --> 00:18:26.039
A roar suddenly erupted from the crowd

00:18:26.039 --> 00:18:26.339
behind her.

00:18:26.400 --> 00:18:30.059
Black dragons surged toward Sunny

00:18:30.059 --> 00:18:33.000
flapping their wings in alarm, as 2 deep

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:36.000
red rain wings dove into their midst, and

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:38.460
dragged a yowling, petrified night wing

00:18:38.460 --> 00:18:39.539
in front of Queen Glory.

00:18:39.599 --> 00:18:43.200
This one, growled one of the rain wings.

00:18:43.259 --> 00:18:44.819
He can't stay here.

00:18:44.880 --> 00:18:46.740
He's the worst of all of them.

00:18:46.799 --> 00:18:49.500
He's the one who did all the venom

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:51.599
experiments on us, said the other.

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:54.299
She lashed her tail and hissed at him.

00:18:54.359 --> 00:18:57.359
Sonny had never seen any rain wings look

00:18:57.359 --> 00:18:58.019
so angry before.

00:18:58.079 --> 00:18:59.759
Besides glory.

00:18:59.819 --> 00:19:02.039
She craned her neck to peer at the night

00:19:02.039 --> 00:19:04.859
wing, and realized it was Starflight's

00:19:04.859 --> 00:19:07.980
father, mastermind, the head scientist of

00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:08.940
the night wing tribe.

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:11.940
From the look on glory's face, the queen

00:19:11.940 --> 00:19:13.859
was probably guessing exactly who it was

00:19:13.859 --> 00:19:14.160
too.

00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:17.519
The night wings had been kidnapping rain

00:19:17.519 --> 00:19:20.339
wings for the last year, imprisoning them

00:19:20.339 --> 00:19:22.920
and doing experiments to understand their

00:19:22.920 --> 00:19:24.180
venom shooting abilities.

00:19:24.240 --> 00:19:26.400
They'd been planning to invade the

00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:28.200
rainforest to steal it from the rain

00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:31.619
wings, either by killing or enslaving all

00:19:31.619 --> 00:19:33.539
the peaceful rainforest dragons who

00:19:33.539 --> 00:19:34.140
already lived here.

00:19:34.259 --> 00:19:37.980
Sunny had seen the lava riddled wasteland

00:19:37.980 --> 00:19:39.420
of an island where the night wings

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:39.720
lived.

00:19:39.779 --> 00:19:42.059
She knew they were desperate for a new

00:19:42.059 --> 00:19:45.240
home, and at 1st, she thought Starflight

00:19:45.240 --> 00:19:46.920
was brilliant for offering to let them

00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:49.259
come through to the rainforest, as long

00:19:49.259 --> 00:19:51.059
as they pledged their loyalty to Queen

00:19:51.059 --> 00:19:53.579
Glory, along with a promise to behave

00:19:53.579 --> 00:19:54.299
peacefully.

00:19:54.359 --> 00:19:56.700
She liked the idea of dragons from

00:19:56.700 --> 00:19:58.500
different tribes, learning to live

00:19:58.500 --> 00:19:58.799
together.

00:19:58.859 --> 00:20:01.680
She felt sorry for the sick and starving

00:20:01.680 --> 00:20:04.440
black dragons, and she loved the poetic

00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:07.019
justice of a rain wing becoming the new

00:20:07.019 --> 00:20:08.279
queen of the night wings.

00:20:08.339 --> 00:20:11.039
But looking at the muttering dragons

00:20:11.039 --> 00:20:13.259
around her, the night wings who didn't

00:20:13.259 --> 00:20:15.420
look as sorry as they should, and the

00:20:15.420 --> 00:20:17.579
hissing rain wings, who were only

00:20:17.579 --> 00:20:19.200
beginning to realize what their friends

00:20:19.200 --> 00:20:21.839
had been through, Sonny wondered if this

00:20:21.839 --> 00:20:22.859
had been a huge mistake.

00:20:22.980 --> 00:20:25.319
Maybe they should have let the night

00:20:25.319 --> 00:20:27.180
wings be swallowed up by the volcano.

00:20:27.240 --> 00:20:29.460
Maybe it wasn't possible to forgive

00:20:29.460 --> 00:20:29.700
them.

00:20:29.759 --> 00:20:31.259
Maybe.

00:20:31.319 --> 00:20:32.759
We shouldn't even try.

00:20:32.819 --> 00:20:36.000
If they could lie about something as huge

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:38.759
and important as the prophecy and

00:20:38.759 --> 00:20:39.599
stopping the war.

00:20:39.660 --> 00:20:41.279
What else would they lie about?

00:20:41.339 --> 00:20:44.220
How could glory ever trust them?

00:20:44.279 --> 00:20:45.960
Ah, I'm sorry.

00:20:46.019 --> 00:20:48.359
Mastermind croaked weekly.

00:20:48.420 --> 00:20:53.039
It was, I was just, for science.

00:20:53.099 --> 00:20:56.339
His voice sputtered out, and he cringed

00:20:56.339 --> 00:20:57.900
away from the rain wings beside him.

00:20:57.960 --> 00:21:01.319
Glory flared her wings, and several

00:21:01.319 --> 00:21:03.000
colors rippled quickly through her

00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:03.599
scales.

00:21:03.660 --> 00:21:05.099
Tie him up.

00:21:05.160 --> 00:21:07.619
We'll figure out what to look out.

00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:09.539
A dragon by the tunnel roared.

00:21:09.599 --> 00:21:10.859
Stand clear.

00:21:10.920 --> 00:21:14.460
Fate speaker shot out of the hole, and a

00:21:14.460 --> 00:21:16.619
moment later, tsunami hurtled after her.

00:21:16.680 --> 00:21:18.779
Everyone, get down.

00:21:18.839 --> 00:21:20.160
The Sea Wing yelled.

00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:23.220
The night wings by the tunnel all threw

00:21:23.220 --> 00:21:24.240
themselves to the ground.

00:21:24.299 --> 00:21:27.240
A blast of scorching heat crackled out of

00:21:27.240 --> 00:21:29.759
the hole, turning the raindrops around it

00:21:29.759 --> 00:21:30.720
to hissing steam.

00:21:30.839 --> 00:21:34.140
Sunny was one of the few still standing

00:21:34.140 --> 00:21:36.180
looking at the tunnel, when 2 more

00:21:36.180 --> 00:21:37.980
dragons burst out of it.

00:21:38.039 --> 00:21:41.339
It was clay, with his wings shielding

00:21:41.339 --> 00:21:42.119
Starflight.

00:21:42.180 --> 00:21:44.819
Starflight's front talons recovering his

00:21:44.819 --> 00:21:47.460
eyes, and long burns were blistering

00:21:47.460 --> 00:21:48.240
along his scales.

00:21:48.299 --> 00:21:51.119
As soon as they reached the open air, he

00:21:51.119 --> 00:21:52.140
collapsed to the ground.

00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:54.299
Stay back!

00:21:54.359 --> 00:21:56.940
tsunami shouted ferociously at the

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.319
dragons who were flapping around them.

00:21:58.380 --> 00:22:02.460
Starflight, Sonny cried, feeling a stab

00:22:02.460 --> 00:22:02.940
of guilt.

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:04.140
He's hurt.

00:22:04.200 --> 00:22:06.240
I never should have left my friends with

00:22:06.240 --> 00:22:07.079
Maro seer.

00:22:07.140 --> 00:22:09.839
She jumped forward, trying to squeeze

00:22:09.839 --> 00:22:11.759
through the crowd of frantic dragons to

00:22:11.759 --> 00:22:12.539
get to him.

00:22:12.599 --> 00:22:15.599
But suddenly, talons wrapped around her

00:22:15.599 --> 00:22:17.880
snout and shoulders, and she was yanked

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:19.440
backward into the dark trees.

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:23.819
Chapter 2.

00:22:24.180 --> 00:22:28.019
Sonny thrashed furiously against the huge

00:22:28.019 --> 00:22:29.279
wings that wrapped around her.

00:22:29.339 --> 00:22:32.400
Quick, while they're all distracted.

00:22:32.519 --> 00:22:33.900
She heard a voice hiss.

00:22:33.960 --> 00:22:36.420
A shower of raindrops pattered down on

00:22:36.420 --> 00:22:38.640
Sonny's head, as the dragon holding her

00:22:38.640 --> 00:22:39.599
ducked through the leaves.

00:22:39.660 --> 00:22:41.940
It was hard to see much more than black

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:44.819
scales, but Sunny realized she was being

00:22:44.819 --> 00:22:47.279
dragged into the forest, away from the

00:22:47.279 --> 00:22:48.779
tunnels and a crowd of dragons.

00:22:48.839 --> 00:22:51.720
But I have to make sure Starflight is all

00:22:51.720 --> 00:22:51.960
right.

00:22:52.019 --> 00:22:54.839
She clawed the arm that pinned her wings

00:22:54.839 --> 00:22:57.119
down, but the night wing only grunted and

00:22:57.119 --> 00:22:57.779
held her tighter.

00:22:57.900 --> 00:23:01.440
Wet leaves squelched and slithered under

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:02.339
their talons.

00:23:02.460 --> 00:23:05.220
From the sounds around her, Sonny guessed

00:23:05.220 --> 00:23:07.319
there were 3 night wings, including her

00:23:07.319 --> 00:23:10.140
attacker, sneaking away from the scene

00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:11.759
while everyone was focused on starflight

00:23:11.759 --> 00:23:12.240
and clay.

00:23:12.299 --> 00:23:15.240
That's ominous.

00:23:15.299 --> 00:23:17.819
Maybe she should try to find out what

00:23:17.819 --> 00:23:18.299
they were up to.

00:23:18.420 --> 00:23:21.059
She stopped struggling and listened.

00:23:21.119 --> 00:23:24.119
The dragons were moving fast and quietly

00:23:24.119 --> 00:23:25.619
even without flying.

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:28.500
In just a few heartbeats, Sonny couldn't

00:23:28.500 --> 00:23:30.359
hear what glory and tsunami were shouting

00:23:30.359 --> 00:23:30.660
anymore.

00:23:30.720 --> 00:23:33.960
They also moved purposefully, as if they

00:23:33.960 --> 00:23:34.740
knew the forest well.

00:23:34.799 --> 00:23:38.519
A hunting party, Sonny thought with a

00:23:38.519 --> 00:23:38.819
shiver.

00:23:38.880 --> 00:23:41.279
These are probably some of the dragons

00:23:41.279 --> 00:23:42.960
who came through the tunnel to kidnap

00:23:42.960 --> 00:23:43.619
rain wings.

00:23:43.680 --> 00:23:45.779
What do they want with me?

00:23:45.839 --> 00:23:47.460
Here.

00:23:47.519 --> 00:23:50.099
One of the dragons said after a while, and

00:23:50.099 --> 00:23:50.700
they all stopped.

00:23:50.819 --> 00:23:53.759
Even with Sonny's sharp hearing, the

00:23:53.759 --> 00:23:56.400
dragons roaring behind them sounded like

00:23:56.400 --> 00:23:58.440
distant thunder muttering on the horizon

00:23:58.440 --> 00:24:01.799
rain poured down harder and harder, and

00:24:01.799 --> 00:24:03.779
the ever present insect noises of the

00:24:03.779 --> 00:24:05.579
rainforest had gone into hiding.

00:24:05.640 --> 00:24:09.299
Sunny was dumped onto the ground, mud

00:24:09.299 --> 00:24:11.279
squishing between her claws and

00:24:11.279 --> 00:24:12.180
splattering her tail.

00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:14.819
She sprang up and hissed at the dragon

00:24:14.819 --> 00:24:15.720
who'd been carrying her.

00:24:15.779 --> 00:24:18.299
He barely glanced down at her before

00:24:18.299 --> 00:24:19.380
turning to the other two.

00:24:19.440 --> 00:24:21.299
Now what?

00:24:21.359 --> 00:24:22.319
He demanded.

00:24:22.380 --> 00:24:24.180
The whole plan is ruined.

00:24:24.299 --> 00:24:27.000
I'm not staying here to kowtow to a rain

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:27.839
wing dragonet.

00:24:27.960 --> 00:24:31.740
Me neither, said one of the others, a

00:24:31.740 --> 00:24:33.359
female, who was little more than a

00:24:33.359 --> 00:24:34.619
dragonette herself.

00:24:34.680 --> 00:24:36.539
Then he guessed she was about 9 years

00:24:36.539 --> 00:24:36.839
old.

00:24:36.900 --> 00:24:40.619
She was bedraggled, wet, bony, and

00:24:40.619 --> 00:24:43.259
hunched over, and yet when she snorted a

00:24:43.259 --> 00:24:45.420
burst of flame, Sonny could see her eyes

00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:47.279
gleaming with stubborn ferocity.

00:24:47.339 --> 00:24:51.599
Plus, they'll probably kill me, said the

00:24:51.599 --> 00:24:52.140
big dragon.

00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:54.539
You saw how they were about mastermind.

00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:56.339
If they remember that I was his

00:24:56.339 --> 00:24:56.880
assistant.

00:24:56.940 --> 00:24:59.940
I mean, I was the one who locked them up

00:24:59.940 --> 00:25:01.859
or stuck them to the walls for him.

00:25:01.920 --> 00:25:03.900
They'll be after my blood if we stick

00:25:03.900 --> 00:25:04.380
around here.

00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:06.660
Where are we supposed to go?

00:25:06.660 --> 00:25:10.500
hissed the last dragon, another male, much

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:11.940
less brawny than the one who'd been

00:25:11.940 --> 00:25:13.019
carrying sunny.

00:25:13.079 --> 00:25:15.359
He had a few missing teeth, and his tail

00:25:15.359 --> 00:25:17.640
was bent to the end, as if it had once

00:25:17.640 --> 00:25:19.440
been broken and then fixed incorrectly.

00:25:19.500 --> 00:25:22.259
We were promised the rainforest.

00:25:22.319 --> 00:25:24.119
This is where I want to live.

00:25:24.180 --> 00:25:26.940
But not as 2nd class dragons.

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:29.700
Imagine, rain wings telling us what to

00:25:29.700 --> 00:25:29.880
do.

00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:33.599
Well, we've got her, like you suggested.

00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:36.240
The big male said to the dragonette

00:25:36.240 --> 00:25:37.980
flipping one wing towards Sonny.

00:25:38.039 --> 00:25:40.619
So, what do we do with her?

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:43.440
The Nightwing Dragonette lashed her tail

00:25:43.440 --> 00:25:45.180
and narrowed her eyes at Sonny.

00:25:45.240 --> 00:25:48.059
We use her as a bargaining chip.

00:25:48.119 --> 00:25:50.640
We can hold her hostage until they take

00:25:50.640 --> 00:25:52.319
our whole tribe to the rain wing village

00:25:52.319 --> 00:25:54.000
and make one of us queen.

00:25:54.119 --> 00:25:56.339
Like who?

00:25:56.339 --> 00:25:57.480
said the other male.

00:25:57.599 --> 00:25:59.940
He spat a small flame with a branch that

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:00.720
was dripping on his head.

00:26:00.779 --> 00:26:03.539
Greatness is weak and won't fight for

00:26:03.539 --> 00:26:03.779
it.

00:26:03.839 --> 00:26:06.960
Queen Battle winner had no brothers or

00:26:06.960 --> 00:26:08.640
sisters, and no other daughters.

00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:10.980
There's no one else to claim the throne.

00:26:11.039 --> 00:26:14.099
I'll take it, said the dragonette.

00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:16.680
That'd be even better than being in a

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:17.160
prophecy.

00:26:17.279 --> 00:26:20.039
If that rain wing can be queen, why not

00:26:20.039 --> 00:26:20.339
me?

00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:21.900
I'm bigger than her.

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:25.680
True, growled the big one behind Sonny.

00:26:25.740 --> 00:26:28.799
Well, I have bad news.

00:26:28.859 --> 00:26:30.299
Sonny spoke up.

00:26:30.359 --> 00:26:32.519
They won't give you anything in exchange

00:26:32.519 --> 00:26:32.819
for me.

00:26:32.880 --> 00:26:34.200
I'm nobody.

00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:36.839
Just a weird looking sandwing with a

00:26:36.839 --> 00:26:37.619
useless tail.

00:26:37.680 --> 00:26:40.680
She snapped her mouth shut before her

00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:41.759
voice could start wavering.

00:26:41.819 --> 00:26:44.160
She'd been saying things like that her

00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:46.500
whole life, but she'd never felt awful

00:26:46.500 --> 00:26:47.460
about it until today.

00:26:47.519 --> 00:26:51.000
If there were no prophecy, then that

00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:53.579
meant she really was just weird looking

00:26:53.579 --> 00:26:54.240
and useless.

00:26:54.299 --> 00:26:57.299
No, that's not how it works.

00:26:57.359 --> 00:27:00.119
I'm weird looking because I have a

00:27:00.119 --> 00:27:00.779
destiny.

00:27:00.839 --> 00:27:02.400
There's a reason I'm like this.

00:27:02.460 --> 00:27:03.900
There has to be.

00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:06.539
The Nightwings regarded her with

00:27:06.539 --> 00:27:07.680
skeptical expressions.

00:27:07.740 --> 00:27:12.180
That would be annoying, said the big

00:27:12.180 --> 00:27:12.420
one.

00:27:12.480 --> 00:27:15.059
I'd be pretty angry if I carry this

00:27:15.059 --> 00:27:16.920
little thing through the forest and got

00:27:16.920 --> 00:27:18.660
my scale scratched up for no reason.

00:27:18.720 --> 00:27:20.519
Fierce teeth.

00:27:20.579 --> 00:27:21.839
I thought you said she'd be worth

00:27:21.839 --> 00:27:22.140
something.

00:27:22.200 --> 00:27:24.420
Fierce teeth.

00:27:24.480 --> 00:27:27.480
Sonny remembered what Starflight had told

00:27:27.480 --> 00:27:28.980
them about the dragonettes in the

00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:31.740
Nightwing Kingdom wasn't fierce teeth, his

00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:32.220
half sister.

00:27:32.279 --> 00:27:35.220
We can use her if she's who I think she

00:27:35.220 --> 00:27:36.960
is, said Fierce Teeth.

00:27:37.019 --> 00:27:39.420
She jabbed Sonny painfully in the ribs.

00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:41.220
Aren't you sunny?

00:27:41.279 --> 00:27:43.799
Starflight yapped on and on about his

00:27:43.799 --> 00:27:45.000
sonny whenever he was asleep.

00:27:45.059 --> 00:27:48.000
Sonny blinked at her, too startled to

00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:48.240
answer.

00:27:48.299 --> 00:27:50.160
Yeah.

00:27:50.220 --> 00:27:53.519
This is her, fierce teeth said, answering

00:27:53.519 --> 00:27:54.299
her own question.

00:27:54.359 --> 00:27:56.700
My brother's totally in love with her.

00:27:56.759 --> 00:27:58.619
He'll agree to anything to get her back.

00:27:58.680 --> 00:28:01.200
That might actually be true.

00:28:01.259 --> 00:28:03.000
Sonny thought with alarm.

00:28:03.059 --> 00:28:05.339
Does he really talk about me in his

00:28:05.339 --> 00:28:05.700
sleep?

00:28:05.759 --> 00:28:09.900
Only a few hours had passed, since she'd

00:28:09.900 --> 00:28:12.119
stood in the rainforest clearing, in the

00:28:12.119 --> 00:28:14.220
middle of dragons preparing to invade the

00:28:14.220 --> 00:28:17.339
Nightwing Island, and Starflight had told

00:28:17.339 --> 00:28:19.559
her he loved her, that he'd always loved

00:28:19.559 --> 00:28:19.859
her.

00:28:19.920 --> 00:28:22.500
She still didn't know how she felt about

00:28:22.500 --> 00:28:22.740
that.

00:28:22.799 --> 00:28:25.319
She didn't know what this feeling was.

00:28:25.380 --> 00:28:27.960
The strange ripples of surprise every

00:28:27.960 --> 00:28:29.519
time she remembered his expression.

00:28:29.579 --> 00:28:33.119
It was, I don't know what to do, and

00:28:33.119 --> 00:28:34.859
somebody loves me.

00:28:34.920 --> 00:28:37.200
And don't hurt him.

00:28:37.259 --> 00:28:39.480
And really, right now?

00:28:39.599 --> 00:28:42.900
And imagine how happy you could make him

00:28:42.900 --> 00:28:44.759
and why me?

00:28:44.819 --> 00:28:45.539
Really?

00:28:45.599 --> 00:28:46.019
Me?

00:28:46.079 --> 00:28:49.619
And But it's Starflight.

00:28:49.680 --> 00:28:53.099
Her sweet, smart, anxious friend.

00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:55.079
She'd never thought of him like that.

00:28:55.140 --> 00:28:56.279
Not once.

00:28:56.339 --> 00:28:59.099
It was still hard for her to believe that

00:28:59.099 --> 00:28:59.759
he meant it.

00:28:59.819 --> 00:29:01.980
None of the other dragonettes took her

00:29:01.980 --> 00:29:02.400
seriously.

00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:04.920
She'd always assumed he was the same way

00:29:04.920 --> 00:29:07.319
that he thought she was too little and

00:29:07.319 --> 00:29:08.759
cheerful to be worth listening to.

00:29:08.819 --> 00:29:10.380
Focus.

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:12.359
Don't let them use you to hurt your

00:29:12.359 --> 00:29:12.660
friends.

00:29:12.720 --> 00:29:15.539
Didn't you see Starflight's injuries?

00:29:15.599 --> 00:29:16.259
She said.

00:29:16.319 --> 00:29:18.660
He's too wounded to have any say in what

00:29:18.660 --> 00:29:19.200
happens next?

00:29:19.319 --> 00:29:21.480
And glory couldn't care less about me?

00:29:21.539 --> 00:29:23.819
Face it, you can't use me.

00:29:23.880 --> 00:29:26.519
You should go back and rejoin the other

00:29:26.519 --> 00:29:27.059
night wings.

00:29:27.119 --> 00:29:29.759
Nice try.

00:29:29.819 --> 00:29:31.500
Fierce teeth said.

00:29:31.559 --> 00:29:34.259
What if she's right?

00:29:34.259 --> 00:29:35.880
said the night wing with the missing

00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:36.119
teeth.

00:29:36.180 --> 00:29:37.980
What if they don't want her?

00:29:38.039 --> 00:29:40.319
What if we expose ourselves, and then

00:29:40.319 --> 00:29:41.160
they just kill us?

00:29:41.220 --> 00:29:44.279
Strong wings won't let them do that.

00:29:44.400 --> 00:29:47.279
Fierce teeth said, stepping closer to the

00:29:47.279 --> 00:29:48.119
burly dragon.

00:29:48.180 --> 00:29:51.779
They're a couple, Sonny realized.

00:29:51.839 --> 00:29:54.180
A really strange couple.

00:29:54.240 --> 00:29:57.900
Strong Wings was nearly twice the size of

00:29:57.900 --> 00:30:00.000
fierce teeth, but he kept turning toward

00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:02.460
her, and ducking his head, as though he

00:30:02.460 --> 00:30:03.900
was waiting for her to order him around.

00:30:03.960 --> 00:30:08.220
I know how we could find out, said the

00:30:08.220 --> 00:30:08.819
other male.

00:30:08.880 --> 00:30:12.119
He drew something flat and shiny and oval

00:30:12.119 --> 00:30:13.559
shaped from under his wing.

00:30:13.619 --> 00:30:16.859
In the moonlight, it shone like polished

00:30:16.859 --> 00:30:19.500
black glass, and fit neatly between his

00:30:19.500 --> 00:30:21.779
front talons, and it stayed perfectly

00:30:21.779 --> 00:30:22.019
dry.

00:30:22.079 --> 00:30:25.380
The raindrops seemed to swerve to avoid

00:30:25.380 --> 00:30:26.039
raining on it.

00:30:26.099 --> 00:30:30.839
The obsidian mirror, said strong wings

00:30:30.839 --> 00:30:32.339
with a hiss of admiration.

00:30:32.400 --> 00:30:34.619
Nice work, prey hunter.

00:30:34.680 --> 00:30:36.720
I wondered if someone would think to save

00:30:36.720 --> 00:30:36.900
it.

00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:39.779
He leaned in and touched the smooth

00:30:39.779 --> 00:30:41.160
surface with one claw.

00:30:41.279 --> 00:30:44.039
No surprise that it wasn't greatness.

00:30:44.099 --> 00:30:46.319
She was more worried about saving her own

00:30:46.319 --> 00:30:47.099
scales.

00:30:47.160 --> 00:30:50.460
She never used it anyway, snorted Prey

00:30:50.460 --> 00:30:50.819
Hunter.

00:30:50.880 --> 00:30:53.160
Even when we needed to know what the rain

00:30:53.160 --> 00:30:53.940
wings were up to.

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.400
She said she didn't trust anything that

00:30:56.400 --> 00:30:57.900
was enchanted by an animus.

00:30:57.960 --> 00:30:59.039
Coward.

00:30:59.099 --> 00:31:01.079
I don't think the queen knew she wasn't

00:31:01.079 --> 00:31:01.500
checking it.

00:31:01.559 --> 00:31:04.140
It doesn't work as well as it used to

00:31:04.140 --> 00:31:06.299
Strongwing said.

00:31:06.359 --> 00:31:08.579
Everyone thinks Stone Mover did something

00:31:08.579 --> 00:31:09.839
to it before he disappeared.

00:31:09.900 --> 00:31:11.880
What is it?

00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:13.319
Fierce teeth asked.

00:31:13.380 --> 00:31:16.980
A really old animus touched piece of

00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:17.579
treasure.

00:31:17.640 --> 00:31:19.319
Strong wings explained.

00:31:19.380 --> 00:31:22.259
This was one of the most important things

00:31:22.259 --> 00:31:24.000
we had to save from the treasure room

00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:26.880
when the volcano erupted, and buried that

00:31:26.880 --> 00:31:29.640
part of the fortress, back when I was a

00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:30.539
small dragonette.

00:31:30.599 --> 00:31:34.019
We use it for he stopped and glanced at

00:31:34.019 --> 00:31:34.500
Sonny.

00:31:34.559 --> 00:31:35.460
Hmm.

00:31:35.519 --> 00:31:38.400
Don't worry, we'll kill her before she

00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:40.859
can tell anyone anything important, said

00:31:40.859 --> 00:31:41.460
Pray Hunter.

00:31:41.519 --> 00:31:44.700
Go ahead and try, Sonny thought

00:31:44.700 --> 00:31:45.180
fiercely.

00:31:45.240 --> 00:31:47.099
No one else has managed it yet.

00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:50.039
He tilted the mirror so it caught the

00:31:50.039 --> 00:31:52.140
light of the 2 moons glowing through the

00:31:52.140 --> 00:31:52.859
clouds above them.

00:31:52.920 --> 00:31:56.220
The 3rd moon was just a thin crescent

00:31:56.220 --> 00:31:57.900
barely cresting the tops of the trees.

00:31:57.960 --> 00:32:00.779
The rain had slowed to a misty drizzle.

00:32:00.839 --> 00:32:03.000
Show me how it works.

00:32:03.119 --> 00:32:04.799
Fierce teeth demanded.

00:32:04.859 --> 00:32:07.019
She snapped a branch off the nearest tree

00:32:07.019 --> 00:32:10.200
and set the end on fire, leaves crackling

00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:11.579
wetly in the flames.

00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:15.599
We just need a name, said Strong Wings.

00:32:15.660 --> 00:32:17.579
Ah, someone important.

00:32:17.640 --> 00:32:21.539
That rain wing queen, obviously, fierce

00:32:21.539 --> 00:32:22.200
teeth snapped.

00:32:22.259 --> 00:32:24.960
He looked blank, and she hissed at him

00:32:24.960 --> 00:32:26.220
glory.

00:32:26.279 --> 00:32:30.359
Glory, whispered the dragon holding the

00:32:30.359 --> 00:32:31.200
obsidian mirror.

00:32:31.319 --> 00:32:33.960
He breathed a plume of smoke across the

00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:34.740
dark glass.

00:32:34.799 --> 00:32:38.160
The smoke coiled and twisted, winding

00:32:38.160 --> 00:32:40.259
like a thin snake around the outer rim of

00:32:40.259 --> 00:32:41.700
the mirror for a few heartbeats.

00:32:41.759 --> 00:32:45.299
All at once, the smoke vanished as if it

00:32:45.299 --> 00:32:47.579
had been sucked into the mirror, and a

00:32:47.579 --> 00:32:50.400
moment later, one tendril curled up from

00:32:50.400 --> 00:32:52.980
the center of the glass, white, tinted

00:32:52.980 --> 00:32:55.440
with purple, curving like a dragon's

00:32:55.440 --> 00:32:55.680
neck.

00:32:55.740 --> 00:32:57.839
Mangrove!

00:32:57.900 --> 00:33:00.180
The tendril barked abruptly in Glory's

00:33:00.180 --> 00:33:00.539
voice.

00:33:00.539 --> 00:33:02.579
Make sure none of them have any more of

00:33:02.579 --> 00:33:03.180
those spears.

00:33:03.240 --> 00:33:06.119
Jambu, you and Grandeur start counting

00:33:06.119 --> 00:33:07.980
them, the night wings, just to be clear

00:33:07.980 --> 00:33:09.059
not the spears.

00:33:09.180 --> 00:33:12.420
Fierce teeth grinned, her teeth gleaming

00:33:12.420 --> 00:33:13.380
whitely in the moonlight.

00:33:13.440 --> 00:33:16.980
This is happening right now, she

00:33:16.980 --> 00:33:19.079
whispered, and strong wings nodded.

00:33:19.140 --> 00:33:20.700
Brilliant.

00:33:20.759 --> 00:33:21.960
Yes.

00:33:22.019 --> 00:33:24.000
I can see how that would be a useful

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:27.240
trick, Sonny thought bitterly, especially

00:33:27.240 --> 00:33:29.460
for convincing other dragons that you

00:33:29.460 --> 00:33:31.200
have mystical mind reading abilities.

00:33:31.319 --> 00:33:34.799
A pinkish wisp of smoke curled up on the

00:33:34.799 --> 00:33:36.119
mirror next to the 1st one.

00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:37.859
You bet.

00:33:37.920 --> 00:33:41.400
No problem, Your Majesty, it said, except

00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:43.500
uh, so counting.

00:33:43.559 --> 00:33:45.359
Um, don't get me wrong.

00:33:45.420 --> 00:33:49.859
I'm really good at it up to like 20?

00:33:49.920 --> 00:33:51.779
That's a pretty big number, right?

00:33:51.839 --> 00:33:54.119
There probably aren't more night wings

00:33:54.119 --> 00:33:54.660
here than that.

00:33:54.720 --> 00:33:58.500
Jambu, there are at least 200 night wings

00:33:58.500 --> 00:33:58.740
here.

00:33:58.799 --> 00:33:59.940
Glory snapped.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:02.279
Hum, he said.

00:34:02.339 --> 00:34:05.579
That's like 220s?

00:34:05.640 --> 00:34:06.779
Maybe three?

00:34:06.839 --> 00:34:09.300
I cannot even roll my eyes at you right

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:09.539
now.

00:34:09.599 --> 00:34:10.800
Glory said.

00:34:10.860 --> 00:34:12.719
Find me a rain wing who can count.

00:34:12.780 --> 00:34:14.219
I'll do it.

00:34:14.280 --> 00:34:17.639
A darker coil of smoke appeared, right

00:34:17.639 --> 00:34:18.480
next to the first.

00:34:18.539 --> 00:34:20.880
It took Sonny a moment to recognize the

00:34:20.880 --> 00:34:23.280
voice of Deathbringer, the assassin who

00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:25.260
had been ordered to kill glory, but

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:26.579
instead helped her escape the night

00:34:26.579 --> 00:34:27.000
wings.

00:34:27.059 --> 00:34:28.860
Funny.

00:34:28.920 --> 00:34:31.079
Glory said, tell me another.

00:34:31.139 --> 00:34:33.299
I love jokes about trusting night wings.

00:34:33.360 --> 00:34:36.719
You exasperating creature, Deathbringer

00:34:36.719 --> 00:34:36.960
said.

00:34:37.019 --> 00:34:39.300
Haven't I not killed you multiple times

00:34:39.300 --> 00:34:39.719
already?

00:34:39.780 --> 00:34:44.460
I knew it, snarled Prey Hunter, curling

00:34:44.460 --> 00:34:45.539
his claws around the mirror.

00:34:45.599 --> 00:34:48.239
I knew vengeance was right about him.

00:34:48.239 --> 00:34:50.219
Death bringer is a traitor.

00:34:50.280 --> 00:34:53.639
We'll take care of him when the

00:34:53.639 --> 00:34:56.820
rainforest is ours, hissed Strongwings.

00:34:56.880 --> 00:34:59.760
Fine, Glory's voice said.

00:34:59.820 --> 00:35:01.380
Go count Nightwings.

00:35:01.440 --> 00:35:02.940
I'll have Starflight check your numbers

00:35:02.940 --> 00:35:03.719
when he wakes up.

00:35:03.780 --> 00:35:06.780
A ringing vote of confidence.

00:35:06.840 --> 00:35:09.420
Death bringer answered, sounding amused.

00:35:09.539 --> 00:35:12.659
The dark wisp of smoke coiled back into

00:35:12.659 --> 00:35:14.699
the mirror, as did the pinkish one.

00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:17.400
Glory's tendril of smoke twisted for a

00:35:17.400 --> 00:35:19.739
moment, alone on the glass.

00:35:19.800 --> 00:35:21.599
He will wake up.

00:35:21.659 --> 00:35:22.559
Right?

00:35:22.619 --> 00:35:24.539
She finally said quietly.

00:35:24.599 --> 00:35:26.340
I think so.

00:35:26.400 --> 00:35:30.000
A new spiral of mud colored smoke wound

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:32.099
its way up from the mirror, and Sonny

00:35:32.099 --> 00:35:33.960
felt her heart jump hopefully at the

00:35:33.960 --> 00:35:35.159
sound of Clay's voice.

00:35:35.219 --> 00:35:37.980
He always made her feel better, even from

00:35:37.980 --> 00:35:39.420
the other side of the rainforest.

00:35:39.480 --> 00:35:42.119
But he was burned pretty badly.

00:35:42.179 --> 00:35:45.599
We should use the darts, to make him keep

00:35:45.599 --> 00:35:47.460
sleeping until he's healed as much as

00:35:47.460 --> 00:35:48.119
possible, I think.

00:35:48.239 --> 00:35:50.820
It'll hurt a lot when he wakes up.

00:35:50.880 --> 00:35:54.480
Oh, poor Starfight.

00:35:54.539 --> 00:35:57.239
Sonny curled her tail around her talons.

00:35:57.360 --> 00:35:58.980
And his eyes?

00:35:59.039 --> 00:36:00.059
Glory asked.

00:36:00.119 --> 00:36:01.739
Will they be all right?

00:36:01.800 --> 00:36:04.739
I don't know, Clay said.

00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:07.679
All right, I did a perimeter sweep.

00:36:07.739 --> 00:36:10.320
Tsunami's voice said bossily, as a blue

00:36:10.320 --> 00:36:11.940
twist of smoke appeared on the mirror.

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:14.400
I made sure any gaps were filled with

00:36:14.400 --> 00:36:16.679
rain wings, holding spears and blow guns

00:36:16.679 --> 00:36:18.300
and I added a few more guards on the

00:36:18.300 --> 00:36:18.659
tunnels.

00:36:18.719 --> 00:36:21.300
I don't think they look very scary, but

00:36:21.300 --> 00:36:22.380
hopefully the night wings will.

00:36:22.440 --> 00:36:25.559
The blue smoke whisked around the other 2

00:36:25.559 --> 00:36:28.559
tendrils, as if tsunami was circling them

00:36:28.559 --> 00:36:28.980
to land.

00:36:29.039 --> 00:36:31.679
That's why I need you to here.

00:36:31.739 --> 00:36:33.059
Glory said.

00:36:33.119 --> 00:36:35.280
The healers who took Starflight back to

00:36:35.280 --> 00:36:37.260
the village can look after him until we

00:36:37.260 --> 00:36:37.619
get there.

00:36:37.679 --> 00:36:39.719
But for corralling night wings.

00:36:39.780 --> 00:36:42.000
You're the most intimidating dragons I

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:42.239
have.

00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:44.460
Waha!

00:36:44.579 --> 00:36:45.420
Clay said.

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:46.440
That's me.

00:36:46.500 --> 00:36:48.719
Intimidating roar.

00:36:48.780 --> 00:36:53.099
Well, you are until you do that, tsunami

00:36:53.099 --> 00:36:53.340
said.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:56.280
Hey, at least you're not bright pink

00:36:56.280 --> 00:36:57.300
Glory said.

00:36:57.360 --> 00:36:59.639
That's extremely helpful right now.

00:36:59.699 --> 00:37:02.400
It's all right, Clay said.

00:37:02.460 --> 00:37:04.559
Sonny's probably at the village already.

00:37:04.619 --> 00:37:07.380
She'll look after Starflight, no matter

00:37:07.380 --> 00:37:08.340
how upset she is.

00:37:08.400 --> 00:37:12.119
Sunny winced, and fierce teeth gave her a

00:37:12.119 --> 00:37:12.599
sharp look.

00:37:12.659 --> 00:37:14.940
Why is she upset?

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:15.840
Glory asked.

00:37:15.900 --> 00:37:18.539
That slime lizard, Marosier?

00:37:18.599 --> 00:37:19.800
Tsunami answered.

00:37:19.860 --> 00:37:21.840
He told us that the prophecy is fake.

00:37:21.900 --> 00:37:24.300
He made it all up as part of the plan for

00:37:24.300 --> 00:37:25.679
the night wings to take over the

00:37:25.679 --> 00:37:26.519
rainforest.

00:37:26.579 --> 00:37:28.500
There was a long pause.

00:37:28.559 --> 00:37:31.199
The 3 dragons around the mirror all

00:37:31.199 --> 00:37:32.159
glanced at Sonny.

00:37:32.219 --> 00:37:34.320
She stared down at her claws.

00:37:34.380 --> 00:37:35.880
What?

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:37.739
Glory exploded.

00:37:37.800 --> 00:37:40.320
Her curl of smoke shot up to twice its

00:37:40.320 --> 00:37:41.400
previous size.

00:37:41.400 --> 00:37:45.659
Yeah, Clay said, isn't that crazy?

00:37:45.719 --> 00:37:48.420
I guess that's why Marosier wanted us to

00:37:48.420 --> 00:37:50.099
choose blister as the next queen.

00:37:50.159 --> 00:37:53.699
He had this whole I am going to bite thy

00:37:53.699 --> 00:37:55.860
dragon's head off and stuff him in a

00:37:55.860 --> 00:37:57.179
volcano.

00:37:57.239 --> 00:37:58.019
Glory roared.

00:37:58.139 --> 00:38:01.980
Too late, tsunami said. since that's kind

00:38:01.980 --> 00:38:02.699
of already happened.

00:38:02.760 --> 00:38:05.519
The volcano part, I mean, he's a pile of

00:38:05.519 --> 00:38:06.059
ashes now.

00:38:06.119 --> 00:38:08.699
Are you serious?

00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:10.619
Glory demanded, talking over her.

00:38:10.679 --> 00:38:12.659
The whole thing was made up.

00:38:12.780 --> 00:38:14.159
There's no destiny.

00:38:14.219 --> 00:38:15.420
No wings of fire?

00:38:15.480 --> 00:38:17.760
No reason for us to be trapped in a cave

00:38:17.760 --> 00:38:21.480
our whole lives, no amazing mythical sky

00:38:21.480 --> 00:38:23.400
wing is infinitely better than me.

00:38:23.460 --> 00:38:26.460
Absolutely no need for any of us after

00:38:26.460 --> 00:38:26.760
all.

00:38:26.820 --> 00:38:32.519
Hey, I'm mad too, tsunami said, but let's

00:38:32.519 --> 00:38:34.019
go back and kill him again.

00:38:34.079 --> 00:38:37.079
At least we don't have to worry about it

00:38:37.079 --> 00:38:39.420
anymore, Tsunami pointed out.

00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:42.179
No destiny means we can do whatever we

00:38:42.179 --> 00:38:42.480
want.

00:38:42.539 --> 00:38:45.719
The talons of peace can go shove a puffer

00:38:45.719 --> 00:38:47.099
fish up their noses.

00:38:47.159 --> 00:38:49.679
But Sonny was really upset.

00:38:49.739 --> 00:38:51.300
Clay said.

00:38:51.420 --> 00:38:53.820
She was always kind of excited about the

00:38:53.820 --> 00:38:54.599
prophecy.

00:38:54.659 --> 00:38:56.639
Kind of excited?

00:38:56.699 --> 00:38:58.980
Sonny lashed her tail.

00:38:59.039 --> 00:39:02.280
It wasn't just some fun adventure I was

00:39:02.280 --> 00:39:03.480
looking forward to, Clay.

00:39:03.599 --> 00:39:07.320
Oh, Sunny will be fine. said tsunami.

00:39:07.380 --> 00:39:08.219
You know her?

00:39:08.280 --> 00:39:10.139
She's always happy about everything.

00:39:10.199 --> 00:39:12.179
By tomorrow, she'll be smiling again.

00:39:12.239 --> 00:39:14.699
And by next week, she probably won't even

00:39:14.699 --> 00:39:15.840
remember the prophecy.

00:39:15.900 --> 00:39:18.000
She just needs something new to care

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.039
about, like making Starflight better.

00:39:20.099 --> 00:39:23.159
Well, I can think of lots of ways to keep

00:39:23.159 --> 00:39:26.519
her busy, Glory said, for one, she can

00:39:26.519 --> 00:39:29.460
find me someone to yell at, I seriously

00:39:29.460 --> 00:39:30.840
cannot believe this.

00:39:30.900 --> 00:39:33.539
If I didn't have to act like a queen

00:39:33.539 --> 00:39:35.699
right now...

00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:38.340
Her voice trailed off into muffled

00:39:38.340 --> 00:39:38.880
growling.

00:39:38.940 --> 00:39:42.000
Sonny glared at the obsidian mirror.

00:39:42.119 --> 00:39:44.880
This was exactly what she hated most

00:39:44.880 --> 00:39:46.980
about the way her friends saw her

00:39:46.980 --> 00:39:49.920
although hearing them say it so bluntly

00:39:49.920 --> 00:39:52.860
made it much worse, as if acting happy

00:39:52.860 --> 00:39:55.139
means I don't really care about anything

00:39:55.139 --> 00:39:59.460
as if I just need to be distracted, and

00:39:59.460 --> 00:40:01.139
I'll forget about the whole point of our

00:40:01.139 --> 00:40:03.659
existence, and all the dragon to are

00:40:03.659 --> 00:40:06.780
counting on us, as if my brain were the

00:40:06.780 --> 00:40:09.659
size of a blueberry, 3 moons.

00:40:09.719 --> 00:40:12.659
She caught fierce teeth looking at her

00:40:12.659 --> 00:40:13.800
with a wry smirk.

00:40:13.860 --> 00:40:16.619
Not too impressed with your intelligence

00:40:16.619 --> 00:40:17.519
are they?

00:40:17.639 --> 00:40:19.260
Said the night wing.

00:40:19.320 --> 00:40:21.599
Sonny scowled back at her.

00:40:21.659 --> 00:40:26.039
It sounds like they like her, said strong

00:40:26.039 --> 00:40:29.219
wings dubiously, but not like they think

00:40:29.219 --> 00:40:31.559
she's particularly useful or important.

00:40:31.619 --> 00:40:33.960
I'm not sure they will give us the

00:40:33.960 --> 00:40:35.519
rainforest in exchange for her.

00:40:35.579 --> 00:40:37.559
I'm not either.

00:40:37.619 --> 00:40:38.940
Sonny thought.

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:43.260
Not that they should, but what would they

00:40:43.260 --> 00:40:44.039
do to get me back?

00:40:44.099 --> 00:40:45.420
Anything?

00:40:45.480 --> 00:40:48.960
Or will they figure, hey, she'll be fine

00:40:48.960 --> 00:40:49.980
as a hostage.

00:40:50.039 --> 00:40:50.579
Remember?

00:40:50.639 --> 00:40:53.099
She's always happy about everything, and

00:40:53.099 --> 00:40:54.780
that should be pretty distracting for

00:40:54.780 --> 00:40:55.019
her.

00:40:55.079 --> 00:40:56.039
Perfect.

00:40:56.099 --> 00:40:59.099
Perhaps I'll just rescue myself then.

00:40:59.159 --> 00:41:00.420
That'll show them.

00:41:00.480 --> 00:41:03.000
And then I'll fulfill the prophecy all by

00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:05.159
myself too, and then they'll see that it

00:41:05.159 --> 00:41:06.179
was real all along.

00:41:06.239 --> 00:41:09.360
She knew that was exactly the kind of

00:41:09.360 --> 00:41:10.980
thing her friends would roll their eyes

00:41:10.980 --> 00:41:11.940
at her for saying.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:13.980
But if no one else cared about their

00:41:13.980 --> 00:41:14.880
destiny anymore.

00:41:14.940 --> 00:41:17.760
If she was the only dragonette who still

00:41:17.760 --> 00:41:20.099
believed in it, what was she supposed to

00:41:20.099 --> 00:41:20.699
do?

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:23.400
The night wing holding the mirror tilted

00:41:23.400 --> 00:41:26.099
the glass, so the smoke tendrils swirled

00:41:26.099 --> 00:41:28.500
together, and then he shot a small burst

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:29.699
of fire across the surface.

00:41:29.760 --> 00:41:32.760
The smoke vanished, and the black glass

00:41:32.760 --> 00:41:33.360
went still.

00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:37.679
There is another option, Pray Hunter said

00:41:37.679 --> 00:41:39.480
regarding the others with a sly

00:41:39.480 --> 00:41:42.480
expression, someone else, who definitely

00:41:42.480 --> 00:41:44.460
does want this stunted sandwing.

00:41:44.579 --> 00:41:46.139
Pretty badly, I'd guess.

00:41:46.199 --> 00:41:49.139
Fierce teeth inhaled sharply.

00:41:49.199 --> 00:41:50.579
You're right.

00:41:50.639 --> 00:41:52.199
Three some ones.

00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:54.239
We could sell her to the highest bidder.

00:41:54.300 --> 00:41:56.519
Whoever's willing to raise an army and

00:41:56.519 --> 00:41:57.900
take back the rainforest for us.

00:41:57.960 --> 00:41:59.699
Uh-oh.

00:41:59.760 --> 00:42:02.940
Sunny was not about to be handed over to

00:42:02.940 --> 00:42:04.380
one of the sand wing queens.

00:42:04.440 --> 00:42:06.840
She'd spent enough time in cages and

00:42:06.840 --> 00:42:08.219
prisons already, thanks very much.

00:42:08.280 --> 00:42:11.219
She snuck a look at the leaning trees and

00:42:11.219 --> 00:42:13.619
tangled vines around them, searching for

00:42:13.619 --> 00:42:15.119
the closest gaps in the foliage.

00:42:15.179 --> 00:42:17.400
Start with blister.

00:42:17.460 --> 00:42:20.579
Strongwing said, his dark eyes glinting

00:42:20.579 --> 00:42:21.179
in the moonlight.

00:42:21.239 --> 00:42:24.599
She always pays her informants well, and

00:42:24.599 --> 00:42:25.559
she needs us the most.

00:42:25.679 --> 00:42:28.079
What does she pay them with?

00:42:28.139 --> 00:42:29.880
Sonny wondered.

00:42:29.940 --> 00:42:32.940
All the sandwing royal treasure was

00:42:32.940 --> 00:42:34.800
stolen by the scavenger who killed Queen

00:42:34.800 --> 00:42:35.940
Oasis, wasn't it?

00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:39.000
And if there's any left, it would be in

00:42:39.000 --> 00:42:41.400
the sand wing stronghold, which burn

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:41.940
controls.

00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:45.239
But burn, would love to have this

00:42:45.239 --> 00:42:47.760
weirdling in her collection, argued Prey

00:42:47.760 --> 00:42:48.119
Hunter.

00:42:48.179 --> 00:42:50.940
From what I hear, a deformed dragonette

00:42:50.940 --> 00:42:52.920
would fit right in with the 2 headed

00:42:52.920 --> 00:42:54.420
creatures and stuffed scavengers.

00:42:54.480 --> 00:42:59.639
I am not deformed, Sonny said hotly, but

00:42:59.639 --> 00:43:01.019
none of them paid any attention to her.

00:43:01.079 --> 00:43:03.900
Queen Scarlet had been planning to hand

00:43:03.900 --> 00:43:06.480
Sonny over to burn for this ominous

00:43:06.480 --> 00:43:07.320
collection as well.

00:43:07.380 --> 00:43:10.139
Sonny was quite sure she never wanted to

00:43:10.139 --> 00:43:12.059
see what else Bern had collected.

00:43:12.119 --> 00:43:14.519
Who has the strongest army?

00:43:14.519 --> 00:43:16.139
Pierced he asked.

00:43:16.199 --> 00:43:17.280
Burn, right?

00:43:17.340 --> 00:43:19.860
And it would only take us a few days to

00:43:19.860 --> 00:43:20.219
get to her.

00:43:20.340 --> 00:43:22.860
If we fly straight over the mountains and

00:43:22.860 --> 00:43:23.579
don't stop.

00:43:23.639 --> 00:43:26.400
She flicked strong wings in the snout as

00:43:26.400 --> 00:43:27.420
he opened it to speak.

00:43:27.480 --> 00:43:29.219
Don't ask stupid questions.

00:43:29.280 --> 00:43:31.739
We can't use the tunnel to the kingdom of

00:43:31.739 --> 00:43:32.159
sand.

00:43:32.219 --> 00:43:34.679
That'll be guarding...

00:43:34.739 --> 00:43:37.860
Fierce teeth's howl of pain, send

00:43:37.860 --> 00:43:39.659
raindrops flying off the leaves around

00:43:39.659 --> 00:43:42.059
them as Sonny sank her teeth into the

00:43:42.059 --> 00:43:43.559
vulnerable spot on her tail.

00:43:43.619 --> 00:43:47.460
Strong wings, lunged to grab Sonny, pried

00:43:47.460 --> 00:43:49.019
her jaws loose and threw her aside.

00:43:49.079 --> 00:43:51.360
Fierce teeth!

00:43:51.480 --> 00:43:53.880
he cried, bending over the night wing

00:43:53.880 --> 00:43:54.599
dragonhead.

00:43:54.659 --> 00:43:55.559
Are you all right?

00:43:55.619 --> 00:43:59.039
Behind him, Sonny hit the ground rolling

00:43:59.039 --> 00:44:01.619
sprang up with her wings spread and shot

00:44:01.619 --> 00:44:02.340
into the trees.

00:44:02.460 --> 00:44:04.920
Don't let her get away.

00:44:04.980 --> 00:44:06.719
Fierce teeth shrieked.

00:44:06.780 --> 00:44:08.460
Strong wings, catch her.

00:44:08.519 --> 00:44:09.780
Kill her if you have to.

00:44:09.840 --> 00:44:13.920
Chapter 3.

00:44:14.159 --> 00:44:17.760
Dangling wet vines smacked against

00:44:17.760 --> 00:44:20.340
Sonny's snout as she flew up into the

00:44:20.340 --> 00:44:21.179
treetops.

00:44:21.239 --> 00:44:23.159
She remembered what she'd learned from

00:44:23.159 --> 00:44:25.440
the rain wings about rainforest flying

00:44:25.440 --> 00:44:27.300
and kept her wings tucked close.

00:44:27.420 --> 00:44:29.820
She couldn't use her tail to swing from

00:44:29.820 --> 00:44:31.920
the trees like they did, but she was

00:44:31.920 --> 00:44:33.599
small enough to maneuver through narrow

00:44:33.599 --> 00:44:35.159
gaps and swerve quickly.

00:44:35.219 --> 00:44:38.039
But the 3 night wings were right behind

00:44:38.039 --> 00:44:40.139
her, roaring angrily.

00:44:40.199 --> 00:44:42.480
I should lead them back to the tunnels

00:44:42.480 --> 00:44:43.199
and the others.

00:44:43.199 --> 00:44:45.239
Glory needs to know that they're not

00:44:45.239 --> 00:44:45.719
loyal.

00:44:45.780 --> 00:44:48.059
She needs to lock them up and keep an eye

00:44:48.059 --> 00:44:48.360
on them.

00:44:48.420 --> 00:44:50.159
For how long?

00:44:50.219 --> 00:44:51.659
Sonny wondered.

00:44:51.719 --> 00:44:52.679
Forever?

00:44:52.739 --> 00:44:54.539
They'll never be trustworthy.

00:44:54.599 --> 00:44:56.579
They'll always be plotting to overthrow

00:44:56.579 --> 00:44:56.820
her.

00:44:56.880 --> 00:44:59.099
What do you do with dragons like that?

00:44:59.159 --> 00:45:02.219
One of her wings hit a branch as she flew

00:45:02.219 --> 00:45:04.559
past, and a family of monkeys went

00:45:04.559 --> 00:45:07.260
leaping off into the trees, howling and

00:45:07.260 --> 00:45:08.039
chattering with alarm.

00:45:08.099 --> 00:45:11.099
She twisted to glance back, and saw a

00:45:11.099 --> 00:45:13.679
bolt of fire engulf one of the monkeys as

00:45:13.679 --> 00:45:15.420
the night wings attacked them, thinking

00:45:15.420 --> 00:45:15.960
it was her.

00:45:16.019 --> 00:45:18.960
They won't be foolish enough to follow me

00:45:18.960 --> 00:45:21.119
all the way back, Sonny realized.

00:45:21.179 --> 00:45:23.340
Even if I can't keep ahead of them for

00:45:23.340 --> 00:45:25.739
that long, they won't let themselves be

00:45:25.739 --> 00:45:26.460
caught.

00:45:26.519 --> 00:45:28.079
What will they do instead?

00:45:28.199 --> 00:45:31.440
She narrowly missed knocking herself out

00:45:31.440 --> 00:45:34.320
with a giant tree branch, ducking to

00:45:34.320 --> 00:45:35.519
avoid it at the last second.

00:45:35.579 --> 00:45:38.760
The same plan, just without me.

00:45:38.820 --> 00:45:41.639
They'll go to burn and tell her we're in

00:45:41.639 --> 00:45:43.860
the rainforest, where her army can find

00:45:43.860 --> 00:45:44.460
us easily.

00:45:44.519 --> 00:45:46.679
I need to hide.

00:45:46.739 --> 00:45:48.000
I need to think.

00:45:48.059 --> 00:45:51.420
She curled into a ball and threw herself

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:53.699
into one of the dragon fruit trees, where

00:45:53.699 --> 00:45:56.039
the leaves were huge and overlapped one

00:45:56.039 --> 00:45:57.239
another like scales.

00:45:57.300 --> 00:45:59.519
Her momentum nearly carried her out the

00:45:59.519 --> 00:46:02.039
other side, but she was able to fling her

00:46:02.039 --> 00:46:04.860
talons out and hook onto the trunk

00:46:04.860 --> 00:46:06.000
slamming her body into it.

00:46:06.059 --> 00:46:09.119
She froze in place, clinging to the rough

00:46:09.119 --> 00:46:11.280
bark, hoping the night wings had lost

00:46:11.280 --> 00:46:12.539
sight of her in the dark.

00:46:12.599 --> 00:46:16.440
By all the moon's strong wings, fierce

00:46:16.440 --> 00:46:18.059
teeth swore from somewhere to Sonny's

00:46:18.059 --> 00:46:18.300
left.

00:46:18.360 --> 00:46:19.980
How could you let her escape?

00:46:20.039 --> 00:46:22.980
Sorry, his voice mumbled.

00:46:23.099 --> 00:46:25.860
She's gone, said Pray Hunter.

00:46:25.920 --> 00:46:27.719
We'll never find her now.

00:46:27.780 --> 00:46:29.639
Not without running the risk of a rain

00:46:29.639 --> 00:46:30.599
wing spotting us.

00:46:30.659 --> 00:46:34.199
Let's get out of here, said Strongwings

00:46:34.199 --> 00:46:36.239
before she brings back reinforcements.

00:46:36.300 --> 00:46:40.139
Talents and tales, fierce teeth hissed.

00:46:40.199 --> 00:46:41.099
We needed her.

00:46:41.159 --> 00:46:44.219
We still have useful information for the

00:46:44.219 --> 00:46:47.280
next Sandwing queen, said Preyhunter.

00:46:47.340 --> 00:46:49.019
They all want to know where the

00:46:49.019 --> 00:46:49.920
dragonettes are.

00:46:49.980 --> 00:46:52.260
If we hurry, we'll be the only one

00:46:52.260 --> 00:46:54.480
selling that information, and we don't

00:46:54.480 --> 00:46:55.739
need the sand wing as proof.

00:46:55.800 --> 00:46:57.119
We're night wings.

00:46:57.179 --> 00:46:58.619
Everyone believes us.

00:46:58.679 --> 00:47:00.300
Makes sense.

00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:01.260
Let's go.

00:47:01.320 --> 00:47:03.000
Strong Wing said.

00:47:03.059 --> 00:47:05.639
And with a flurry of wing beats.

00:47:05.699 --> 00:47:07.860
The dragon's headed for the dark open sky

00:47:07.860 --> 00:47:08.639
above the trees.

00:47:08.699 --> 00:47:12.059
Sonny's claws were trembling with the

00:47:12.059 --> 00:47:12.960
effort to stay still.

00:47:13.079 --> 00:47:14.820
She took a deep breath.

00:47:14.880 --> 00:47:18.659
If I go back until the others, we can

00:47:18.659 --> 00:47:19.079
follow them.

00:47:19.139 --> 00:47:22.860
But by the time they listen to me, if

00:47:22.860 --> 00:47:25.199
they listen to me at all, the night wings

00:47:25.199 --> 00:47:25.920
will be long gone.

00:47:25.980 --> 00:47:28.800
Sonny was used to the way her friends

00:47:28.800 --> 00:47:30.300
talked over her all the time.

00:47:30.360 --> 00:47:33.179
If she really wanted to be heard.

00:47:33.239 --> 00:47:34.920
She usually had to get Clay's attention

00:47:34.920 --> 00:47:37.559
and have him make her suggestions for her

00:47:37.559 --> 00:47:38.940
which wasn't fair.

00:47:39.000 --> 00:47:42.179
She had good ideas, but her friends never

00:47:42.179 --> 00:47:43.920
expected her to have anything useful to

00:47:43.920 --> 00:47:44.340
say.

00:47:44.340 --> 00:47:46.320
They also didn't trust her to keep

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:46.800
secrets.

00:47:46.860 --> 00:47:49.019
They hadn't even told her about it when

00:47:49.019 --> 00:47:50.340
they were all planning to escape their

00:47:50.340 --> 00:47:50.940
guardians.

00:47:51.000 --> 00:47:53.039
All they wanted was for her to be

00:47:53.039 --> 00:47:55.260
cheerful and supportive, and agree with

00:47:55.260 --> 00:47:56.340
everything they wanted to do.

00:47:56.400 --> 00:47:58.500
Would Glory even listen?

00:47:58.619 --> 00:48:00.480
If Sonny tried to tell her about the

00:48:00.480 --> 00:48:02.940
rogue night wings, wouldn't she be too

00:48:02.940 --> 00:48:03.360
busy?

00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:06.059
What if she just rolled her eyes at Sonny

00:48:06.059 --> 00:48:07.500
the way she often did?

00:48:07.559 --> 00:48:10.440
I don't want to be distracted from

00:48:10.440 --> 00:48:12.659
worrying about the prophecy, Sonny

00:48:12.659 --> 00:48:14.400
muttered, I want to do something.

00:48:14.460 --> 00:48:17.280
Like stopping the night wings.

00:48:17.400 --> 00:48:19.440
I could follow them right now.

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:22.139
I might be the only dragon who can stop

00:48:22.139 --> 00:48:23.940
them before they tell Bern where we are.

00:48:24.000 --> 00:48:26.039
Maybe if I do.

00:48:26.099 --> 00:48:28.199
My friends will see that I can do

00:48:28.199 --> 00:48:28.980
important things.

00:48:29.039 --> 00:48:31.260
And then maybe they'll listen to me about

00:48:31.260 --> 00:48:31.920
the prophecy.

00:48:31.980 --> 00:48:35.460
She thought guiltily of Starflight, and

00:48:35.460 --> 00:48:37.139
what he would think when he finally woke

00:48:37.139 --> 00:48:39.960
up and realized she wasn't there, taking

00:48:39.960 --> 00:48:40.500
care of him.

00:48:40.559 --> 00:48:43.139
Then she thought of what her friends had

00:48:43.139 --> 00:48:45.780
said about her in the obsidian mirror, and

00:48:45.780 --> 00:48:48.300
she thought about Maru Sears' smug, evil

00:48:48.300 --> 00:48:50.760
face, and she thought of all the dragons

00:48:50.760 --> 00:48:53.280
in Pyrea, waiting for the dragonettes of

00:48:53.280 --> 00:48:54.239
destiny to save them.

00:48:54.300 --> 00:48:56.159
I'm doing this.

00:48:56.219 --> 00:48:58.800
Even if I have to fulfill the prophecy

00:48:58.800 --> 00:49:00.239
alone, I will.

00:49:00.300 --> 00:49:03.059
Sonny clambered up through the branches

00:49:03.059 --> 00:49:03.900
and lifted off.

00:49:03.960 --> 00:49:06.360
Following the black dragons into the

00:49:06.360 --> 00:49:07.019
night sky.

00:49:07.079 --> 00:49:11.039
It was easier to follow the night wings

00:49:11.039 --> 00:49:12.119
than Sonny would have expected.

00:49:12.179 --> 00:49:14.940
Her sharp eyes could catch the movement

00:49:14.940 --> 00:49:17.280
of their small silver underwing scales

00:49:17.280 --> 00:49:19.679
flashing against the sky, and they

00:49:19.679 --> 00:49:21.000
weren't making much effort to be quiet

00:49:21.000 --> 00:49:21.420
either.

00:49:21.480 --> 00:49:24.239
Or maybe loud and flappy was how night

00:49:24.239 --> 00:49:25.320
wings always flew.

00:49:25.380 --> 00:49:28.739
They also were slower than Sonny, and got

00:49:28.739 --> 00:49:29.579
tired more quickly.

00:49:29.639 --> 00:49:31.980
So she had to be careful not to pass them

00:49:31.980 --> 00:49:34.079
accidentally, especially during their

00:49:34.079 --> 00:49:36.059
frequent rest stops.

00:49:36.119 --> 00:49:38.460
The sun was rising behind them when they

00:49:38.460 --> 00:49:40.320
reached the far edge of the rainforest

00:49:40.320 --> 00:49:42.659
where the jungles shifted into sparser

00:49:42.659 --> 00:49:45.300
forest and more marshes, the outskirts of

00:49:45.300 --> 00:49:46.260
mudwing territory.

00:49:46.320 --> 00:49:49.559
The claws of the Clouds Mountains stood

00:49:49.559 --> 00:49:51.659
out sharply up ahead in the growing light

00:49:51.659 --> 00:49:53.880
like a line of jagged, broken teeth.

00:49:53.940 --> 00:49:56.159
Most of the mountains in the southern

00:49:56.159 --> 00:49:58.440
part of the range were not as tall as the

00:49:58.440 --> 00:50:00.420
ones in the north, where the Sky Wings

00:50:00.420 --> 00:50:00.719
lived.

00:50:00.780 --> 00:50:03.900
But there was one exception, Jade

00:50:03.900 --> 00:50:04.380
Mountain.

00:50:04.440 --> 00:50:06.659
The tallest mountain on the continent was

00:50:06.659 --> 00:50:08.699
easy to spot, and not just for its

00:50:08.699 --> 00:50:09.599
towering size.

00:50:09.659 --> 00:50:12.179
Sonny remembered the picture on the map

00:50:12.179 --> 00:50:14.460
of Pyria they'd had underground.

00:50:14.519 --> 00:50:17.579
In reality, the 2 crags at the top looked

00:50:17.579 --> 00:50:19.980
even more like sharp fangs sticking up

00:50:19.980 --> 00:50:20.400
into the air.

00:50:20.460 --> 00:50:23.280
One of the scrolls had said that from

00:50:23.280 --> 00:50:25.199
certain approaches, the tip of the

00:50:25.199 --> 00:50:27.059
mountain looked exactly like the head of

00:50:27.059 --> 00:50:29.579
a snake, lunging out of the ground to

00:50:29.579 --> 00:50:30.420
attack the clouds.

00:50:30.480 --> 00:50:32.639
Jade Mountain.

00:50:32.699 --> 00:50:34.320
Sonny frowned.

00:50:34.440 --> 00:50:36.420
Someone had said something recently about

00:50:36.420 --> 00:50:39.000
Jade Mountain, something she needed to

00:50:39.000 --> 00:50:39.300
remember.

00:50:39.420 --> 00:50:41.219
What was it?

00:50:41.340 --> 00:50:44.760
Nothing came to her, as the sun slowly

00:50:44.760 --> 00:50:46.139
lit up the mountain's fangs.

00:50:46.199 --> 00:50:49.559
Sunny had been worrying all night about

00:50:49.559 --> 00:50:51.360
how she would hide from the night wings

00:50:51.360 --> 00:50:52.079
in the daylight.

00:50:52.079 --> 00:50:54.119
They didn't seem to be watching behind

00:50:54.119 --> 00:50:56.340
them, but it would be hard to miss her

00:50:56.340 --> 00:50:58.559
golden scales once the sun was reflecting

00:50:58.559 --> 00:50:58.920
off them.

00:50:58.980 --> 00:51:01.860
She wished she had glorious camouflage

00:51:01.860 --> 00:51:02.340
scales.

00:51:02.400 --> 00:51:03.119
Really?

00:51:03.239 --> 00:51:05.340
Any of her friend's skills would be

00:51:05.340 --> 00:51:07.860
helpful, instead of her own total lack of

00:51:07.860 --> 00:51:08.340
powers.

00:51:08.400 --> 00:51:11.579
But as the sky grew pinker and brighter

00:51:11.579 --> 00:51:13.679
and then started shading from gray to

00:51:13.679 --> 00:51:16.800
blue, the 3 night wings flew lower, their

00:51:16.800 --> 00:51:19.440
wings drooping, until finally they landed

00:51:19.440 --> 00:51:20.280
beside a small river.

00:51:20.400 --> 00:51:24.119
Sunny kept her distance, choosing the

00:51:24.119 --> 00:51:26.280
tallest tree she could find and tucking

00:51:26.280 --> 00:51:28.260
herself among the branches, close to the

00:51:28.260 --> 00:51:28.500
trunk.

00:51:28.559 --> 00:51:31.019
She fixed her eyes on where the night

00:51:31.019 --> 00:51:32.940
wings had gone down and pricked her

00:51:32.940 --> 00:51:33.179
ears.

00:51:33.239 --> 00:51:35.760
She could hear their distant muttering

00:51:35.760 --> 00:51:37.920
with fierce teeth the most distinct.

00:51:37.980 --> 00:51:40.320
It sounded as if they were planning to

00:51:40.320 --> 00:51:41.820
sleep for as much of the day as they

00:51:41.820 --> 00:51:43.860
could, and then fly on at dusk.

00:51:43.920 --> 00:51:47.639
They've been breathing volcanic ash, and

00:51:47.639 --> 00:51:50.579
living on dying rotting scraps, probably

00:51:50.579 --> 00:51:52.860
for their whole lives, Sonny thought.

00:51:52.920 --> 00:51:54.840
No wonder they're not exactly in great

00:51:54.840 --> 00:51:55.199
shape.

00:51:55.260 --> 00:51:59.280
After a while, the trees stopped rustling

00:51:59.280 --> 00:52:01.980
and the dragon voices fell silent.

00:52:02.039 --> 00:52:04.500
A few minutes later, one of them, sunny

00:52:04.500 --> 00:52:07.199
guest, strong wings, started snoring like

00:52:07.199 --> 00:52:08.880
a herd of congested hippos.

00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:10.920
Now what do I do?

00:52:10.980 --> 00:52:12.360
Sonny wondered.

00:52:12.420 --> 00:52:14.880
This was a perfect opportunity to wreck

00:52:14.880 --> 00:52:17.340
their plans if she could figure out how.

00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:20.280
Could I fly to the rain wing village and

00:52:20.280 --> 00:52:21.960
get back with reinforcements before they

00:52:21.960 --> 00:52:22.320
wake up?

00:52:22.380 --> 00:52:26.099
No, it would take me all day just to get

00:52:26.099 --> 00:52:27.179
someone to pay attention to me.

00:52:27.239 --> 00:52:29.280
I can do this myself.

00:52:29.340 --> 00:52:30.420
I have to.

00:52:30.480 --> 00:52:32.699
What would tsunami do?

00:52:32.760 --> 00:52:34.440
Would she go down there and kill them?

00:52:34.500 --> 00:52:38.039
I don't think I could do that, even if I

00:52:38.039 --> 00:52:38.760
could do that.

00:52:38.820 --> 00:52:41.159
Sunny sighed.

00:52:41.219 --> 00:52:44.219
A breeze whispered through the trees

00:52:44.219 --> 00:52:45.960
curling under her wings as if inviting

00:52:45.960 --> 00:52:46.559
her to fly.

00:52:46.619 --> 00:52:49.679
Yesterday, I wouldn't have worried about

00:52:49.679 --> 00:52:51.599
what was going to happen next with fierce

00:52:51.599 --> 00:52:52.440
teeth and the others.

00:52:52.500 --> 00:52:54.960
I'd be able to follow them, knowing for

00:52:54.960 --> 00:52:57.300
sure that whatever I did would turn out

00:52:57.300 --> 00:52:57.719
all right.

00:52:57.780 --> 00:53:01.320
She hated Marosia for making her feel

00:53:01.320 --> 00:53:01.800
this way.

00:53:01.860 --> 00:53:04.860
This awful, doubting feeling.

00:53:04.920 --> 00:53:08.159
He'd planted this worry, which she'd

00:53:08.159 --> 00:53:10.260
never had before, that maybe things

00:53:10.260 --> 00:53:13.679
wouldn't be all right, that in fact, she

00:53:13.679 --> 00:53:14.219
could die.

00:53:14.280 --> 00:53:17.519
And the war might go on endlessly, and

00:53:17.519 --> 00:53:19.500
perhaps there wasn't a happy ending all

00:53:19.500 --> 00:53:20.760
planned out by the universe.

00:53:20.820 --> 00:53:24.179
She had to stop thinking about Marosir

00:53:24.179 --> 00:53:24.900
and the prophecy.

00:53:24.960 --> 00:53:27.599
It was like stabbing icicle sharp claws

00:53:27.599 --> 00:53:28.679
between her scales.

00:53:28.739 --> 00:53:31.199
Every time she pictured the haughty black

00:53:31.199 --> 00:53:34.139
dragon, sneering about his great lies.

00:53:34.199 --> 00:53:37.980
Stupid night wings, and their deceitful

00:53:37.980 --> 00:53:40.800
all knowing, high and mighty, Sonny sat

00:53:40.800 --> 00:53:43.139
up so fast, she nearly fell off her tree

00:53:43.139 --> 00:53:45.659
branch, all knowing.

00:53:45.719 --> 00:53:48.420
There was one thing she could do to slow

00:53:48.420 --> 00:53:49.500
the night wings down.

00:53:49.559 --> 00:53:51.900
She could steal the obsidian mirror.

00:53:51.960 --> 00:53:56.039
Chapter 4.

00:53:56.280 --> 00:54:00.360
This was one of those ideas that Sonny's

00:54:00.360 --> 00:54:01.860
friends would totally ignore if she

00:54:01.860 --> 00:54:04.139
suggested it, but would love like crazy

00:54:04.139 --> 00:54:06.000
if it came from clay or tsunami.

00:54:06.059 --> 00:54:08.699
It was also something they would never

00:54:08.699 --> 00:54:12.000
ever let her do herself. too dangerous

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:12.900
too risky.

00:54:12.960 --> 00:54:15.480
Send a dragon with fighting skills or

00:54:15.480 --> 00:54:16.800
camouflage scales.

00:54:16.860 --> 00:54:19.619
Not their undersized, cheerful, silly

00:54:19.619 --> 00:54:20.280
little sister.

00:54:20.340 --> 00:54:23.340
Well, I'm the only one here.

00:54:23.400 --> 00:54:25.199
And I know I can do it.

00:54:25.260 --> 00:54:28.619
She waited until the sun was halfway up

00:54:28.619 --> 00:54:30.960
the sky, and then she carefully worked

00:54:30.960 --> 00:54:33.659
her way closer, hopping from tree to tree

00:54:33.659 --> 00:54:35.820
and giving herself as much cover as she

00:54:35.820 --> 00:54:36.000
could.

00:54:36.059 --> 00:54:38.340
There were a few spots where she was

00:54:38.340 --> 00:54:40.920
exposed, and her golden scales caught the

00:54:40.920 --> 00:54:43.260
light, but when she finally came to rest

00:54:43.260 --> 00:54:44.820
on a branch within sight of the night

00:54:44.820 --> 00:54:47.219
wings, all 3 of them were sleeping

00:54:47.219 --> 00:54:47.579
soundly.

00:54:47.699 --> 00:54:51.059
Starflight said, there were never any

00:54:51.059 --> 00:54:52.500
night wing guards posted in their

00:54:52.500 --> 00:54:52.980
fortress.

00:54:53.039 --> 00:54:56.039
They're used to being so isolated that no

00:54:56.039 --> 00:54:57.300
one could find them to attack them.

00:54:57.360 --> 00:54:59.579
It didn't even occur to them to leave

00:54:59.579 --> 00:55:00.960
someone awake to keep watch.

00:55:01.019 --> 00:55:03.179
She snorted.

00:55:03.239 --> 00:55:06.360
They probably also figured no one would

00:55:06.360 --> 00:55:08.280
dare attack a group of amazing all

00:55:08.280 --> 00:55:10.139
powerful night wings.

00:55:10.199 --> 00:55:12.719
Fierce teeth was curled in the curve of

00:55:12.719 --> 00:55:15.000
strong wings underbelly, with her tail

00:55:15.000 --> 00:55:17.340
draped over his, and her head resting on

00:55:17.340 --> 00:55:17.880
his shoulder.

00:55:17.940 --> 00:55:21.000
Sonny had no idea how fierce teeth could

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:22.980
sleep. through those tree rattling

00:55:22.980 --> 00:55:23.460
snores.

00:55:23.519 --> 00:55:26.340
Prey hunter lay closer to the river

00:55:26.340 --> 00:55:29.460
scrunched into a tight, tense ball with

00:55:29.460 --> 00:55:30.900
his wings tucked close to him.

00:55:30.960 --> 00:55:32.400
In the daylight.

00:55:32.460 --> 00:55:34.980
Sonny could see how dull his scales were

00:55:34.980 --> 00:55:38.039
and how ill they all looked, even

00:55:38.039 --> 00:55:40.260
Strongwings, who was built large and

00:55:40.260 --> 00:55:43.500
burly, looked underfed, and his snores

00:55:43.500 --> 00:55:45.840
rasped heavily, as if his lungs and

00:55:45.840 --> 00:55:48.539
throat and nose were lined with claws.

00:55:48.599 --> 00:55:51.000
Sunny studied the ground around prey

00:55:51.000 --> 00:55:53.400
hunter, until she spotted a corner of

00:55:53.400 --> 00:55:55.500
black glass sticking out from under one

00:55:55.500 --> 00:55:56.280
of his wings.

00:55:56.340 --> 00:55:58.860
He was keeping the obsidian mirror very

00:55:58.860 --> 00:55:59.099
close.

00:55:59.219 --> 00:56:02.639
How can I get it without waking him up?

00:56:02.699 --> 00:56:06.000
She glanced at the other 2 again, then

00:56:06.000 --> 00:56:08.219
quietly slid down her tree, until her

00:56:08.219 --> 00:56:09.539
talon touched the grass.

00:56:09.599 --> 00:56:12.659
The river bubbled over smooth gray rocks

00:56:12.659 --> 00:56:14.280
not much more than a stream.

00:56:14.340 --> 00:56:17.519
Small purple wildflowers bent under her

00:56:17.519 --> 00:56:19.980
claws, as sunny tiptoed over to the

00:56:19.980 --> 00:56:20.820
sleeping night wing.

00:56:20.880 --> 00:56:24.119
He looked miserable, even in his sleep.

00:56:24.179 --> 00:56:26.039
His jaw was clenched.

00:56:26.099 --> 00:56:29.400
His talons twitched defensively, and his

00:56:29.400 --> 00:56:31.440
forked black tongue flickered in and out

00:56:31.440 --> 00:56:33.239
as he muttered something to himself.

00:56:33.300 --> 00:56:36.599
When Sonny crouched beside him, she

00:56:36.599 --> 00:56:38.460
realized he was shivering.

00:56:38.519 --> 00:56:42.000
I guess it was pretty hot, living on a

00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:42.539
volcano.

00:56:42.599 --> 00:56:46.199
The air didn't feel cold to her, here on

00:56:46.199 --> 00:56:48.300
the outskirts of the jungle, but perhaps

00:56:48.300 --> 00:56:49.199
he wasn't used to it.

00:56:49.260 --> 00:56:51.000
Or perhaps he was sick.

00:56:51.059 --> 00:56:54.360
It felt strange to be so close to an

00:56:54.360 --> 00:56:55.559
unfamiliar night wing.

00:56:55.619 --> 00:56:58.920
For the 1st 6 years of her life, Sonny

00:56:58.920 --> 00:57:02.639
had known exactly 7 dragons, Clay, Tsunami

00:57:02.639 --> 00:57:05.880
Starflight, Glory, and their 3 guardians

00:57:05.880 --> 00:57:08.039
Webbs, Dune and Kestrel.

00:57:08.099 --> 00:57:11.219
Two of those 7 dragons were dead now.

00:57:11.280 --> 00:57:13.980
She knew the guardians had never been

00:57:13.980 --> 00:57:16.980
particularly kind to the dragonettes, but

00:57:16.980 --> 00:57:18.539
they were still the only parent she'd

00:57:18.539 --> 00:57:20.699
ever had, and she missed them.

00:57:20.760 --> 00:57:23.159
Her friends had never stopped to grieve

00:57:23.159 --> 00:57:24.539
for Dune and Kestrel.

00:57:24.599 --> 00:57:26.400
She wasn't even sure they were sad about

00:57:26.400 --> 00:57:27.300
their deaths at all.

00:57:27.360 --> 00:57:30.840
She'd tried not to show how it upset her

00:57:30.840 --> 00:57:34.320
but at night, curled up beside clay, when

00:57:34.320 --> 00:57:36.119
she was sure he'd sleep through it.

00:57:36.179 --> 00:57:38.519
Sometimes she'd let herself cry for

00:57:38.519 --> 00:57:38.760
them.

00:57:38.820 --> 00:57:42.300
She reached toward the sliver of obsidian

00:57:42.300 --> 00:57:44.699
but before she even touched it, Prey

00:57:44.699 --> 00:57:46.800
Hunter whimpered in his sleep, and she

00:57:46.800 --> 00:57:48.000
snatched her talons back.

00:57:48.059 --> 00:57:50.940
None of the dragons moved for a long

00:57:50.940 --> 00:57:51.480
moment.

00:57:51.539 --> 00:57:54.059
Maybe this is a bad idea.

00:57:54.119 --> 00:57:56.820
I could make things worse if I get myself

00:57:56.820 --> 00:57:57.239
caught.

00:57:57.300 --> 00:58:00.000
But if she could get the mirror away from

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:02.579
them, that would be one less weapon in

00:58:02.579 --> 00:58:05.880
their claws, they'd be flying blind, with

00:58:05.880 --> 00:58:08.460
no idea what glory was planning, and no

00:58:08.460 --> 00:58:10.019
way to know if Byrne would receive them

00:58:10.019 --> 00:58:12.719
with open wings, not to mention Sonny

00:58:12.719 --> 00:58:14.460
could probably use that mirror herself.

00:58:14.519 --> 00:58:17.940
She reached out again, and noticed the

00:58:17.940 --> 00:58:19.619
trembling that shuddered through prey

00:58:19.619 --> 00:58:20.519
hunter's scales.

00:58:20.579 --> 00:58:22.679
Maybe he wasn't cold.

00:58:22.739 --> 00:58:25.440
Maybe, it was a nightmare.

00:58:25.500 --> 00:58:28.320
Maybe he's dreaming about the terrible

00:58:28.320 --> 00:58:29.340
things he's done.

00:58:29.400 --> 00:58:31.679
Or perhaps he's dreaming about the

00:58:31.679 --> 00:58:32.820
volcano exploding.

00:58:32.880 --> 00:58:36.539
She hesitated, and then unfolded one of

00:58:36.539 --> 00:58:37.019
her wings.

00:58:37.139 --> 00:58:39.000
Spreading it gently over his back.

00:58:39.059 --> 00:58:41.880
She was too small to cover him completely

00:58:41.880 --> 00:58:44.280
but the warmth that radiated from her

00:58:44.280 --> 00:58:46.800
scales, spread as far over him as she

00:58:46.800 --> 00:58:47.159
could reach.

00:58:47.219 --> 00:58:49.860
She held her breath, trying not to touch

00:58:49.860 --> 00:58:50.039
him.

00:58:50.099 --> 00:58:53.519
Pray hunter let out a long, shuddering

00:58:53.519 --> 00:58:55.739
sigh, and then the shivering stopped.

00:58:55.800 --> 00:58:58.920
He took another deep breath, and Sonny

00:58:58.920 --> 00:59:01.440
saw the tension in his snout, jaws, and

00:59:01.440 --> 00:59:02.099
neck, relax.

00:59:02.159 --> 00:59:05.280
A ripple went through his wings, and his

00:59:05.280 --> 00:59:06.480
claws unclenched.

00:59:06.539 --> 00:59:09.059
He stopped muttering, and even his closed

00:59:09.059 --> 00:59:12.300
eyes seemed to smooth over, as if he were

00:59:12.300 --> 00:59:14.460
shifting into a deeper, calmer sleep.

00:59:14.579 --> 00:59:18.599
Sunny waited a long moment, feeling sorry

00:59:18.599 --> 00:59:20.460
for this dragon. even though she really

00:59:20.460 --> 00:59:21.059
didn't want to.

00:59:21.119 --> 00:59:23.219
She couldn't help wondering what she

00:59:23.219 --> 00:59:25.440
herself might have been like if she'd

00:59:25.440 --> 00:59:27.420
grown up on the night wing island.

00:59:27.480 --> 00:59:30.300
Desperate and sad, mean and hungry.

00:59:30.360 --> 00:59:33.659
She reached for the mirror again, and

00:59:33.659 --> 00:59:35.519
suddenly, prey hunter spoke.

00:59:35.579 --> 00:59:36.960
Please.

00:59:37.079 --> 00:59:38.940
Sonny froze.

00:59:39.000 --> 00:59:40.739
His eyes were still closed.

00:59:40.800 --> 00:59:43.920
Across the clearing, fierce teeth shifted

00:59:43.920 --> 00:59:44.880
her wings and coughed.

00:59:45.000 --> 00:59:49.619
Please, don't make me, Pray Hunter said

00:59:49.619 --> 00:59:50.460
more softly.

00:59:50.519 --> 00:59:52.500
Mother, it's awful.

00:59:52.619 --> 00:59:56.159
A stab of sympathy shot through Sonny, and

00:59:56.159 --> 00:59:59.340
she curled her tail in closer, remember

00:59:59.340 --> 01:00:02.579
what he's planning, and what he said, and

01:00:02.579 --> 01:00:03.239
what he's done.

01:00:03.300 --> 01:00:06.659
But it was hard not to imagine herself in

01:00:06.659 --> 01:00:07.260
his scales.

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:11.099
Gently, she used her front talons to

01:00:11.099 --> 01:00:12.599
slide the mirror out from under his

01:00:12.599 --> 01:00:13.139
wing.

01:00:13.139 --> 01:00:16.440
Her warmth had relaxed his grip on it, so

01:00:16.440 --> 01:00:18.960
he wasn't clutching it so tightly, and it

01:00:18.960 --> 01:00:21.059
only took a moment until it was resting

01:00:21.059 --> 01:00:22.500
coldly between her claws.

01:00:22.619 --> 01:00:26.099
The obsidian felt thin, like a layer of

01:00:26.099 --> 01:00:28.679
ice, and the edges were sharp as teeth.

01:00:28.860 --> 01:00:31.619
Sonny could see her distorted reflection

01:00:31.619 --> 01:00:32.760
in the dark glass.

01:00:32.820 --> 01:00:35.219
She took a careful step back.

01:00:35.280 --> 01:00:37.860
Then another, and folded her wings back

01:00:37.860 --> 01:00:38.099
in.

01:00:38.159 --> 01:00:41.460
Prey Hunter made a lost, mournful noise

01:00:41.460 --> 01:00:44.340
and his claws twitched, as if he were

01:00:44.340 --> 01:00:45.900
trying to pull the warmth back into him.

01:00:45.960 --> 01:00:48.659
Will they guess I'm the one who stole

01:00:48.659 --> 01:00:48.840
it?

01:00:48.900 --> 01:00:50.639
What if they come looking for me?

01:00:50.760 --> 01:00:53.400
She glanced around the clearing.

01:00:53.460 --> 01:00:56.460
A large flat gray boulder took up most of

01:00:56.460 --> 01:00:58.860
the ground between the 3 dragons, with

01:00:58.860 --> 01:01:00.960
bright yellow dandelions dotting the

01:01:00.960 --> 01:01:03.719
edges, like topaz gemstones around a

01:01:03.719 --> 01:01:04.079
pendant.

01:01:04.139 --> 01:01:06.239
I'll leave them a message.

01:01:06.300 --> 01:01:08.460
Something that won't sound like me.

01:01:08.519 --> 01:01:11.099
Maybe something that'll scare them.

01:01:11.159 --> 01:01:13.559
Her own heart was drumming frantically

01:01:13.559 --> 01:01:15.900
against her ribs like a caged bird.

01:01:15.960 --> 01:01:18.599
She wanted to get out of there before any

01:01:18.599 --> 01:01:19.199
of them woke up.

01:01:19.260 --> 01:01:21.480
But she had a strong feeling that there

01:01:21.480 --> 01:01:22.739
was something to this idea.

01:01:22.800 --> 01:01:25.800
She dipped a claw in the dark red mud

01:01:25.800 --> 01:01:28.320
that lined the river, and wrote on the

01:01:28.320 --> 01:01:30.480
boulder in tall, jagged letters.

01:01:30.539 --> 01:01:32.219
Turn back.

01:01:32.280 --> 01:01:34.260
You fly toward your death.

01:01:34.380 --> 01:01:36.659
Totally spooky.

01:01:36.719 --> 01:01:38.460
She thought with satisfaction.

01:01:38.519 --> 01:01:41.159
It even looked like maybe it could have

01:01:41.159 --> 01:01:42.000
been written in blood.

01:01:42.059 --> 01:01:45.480
That should at least creep them out, even

01:01:45.480 --> 01:01:47.280
if it doesn't send them scurrying back to

01:01:47.280 --> 01:01:47.940
the rainforest.

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:51.960
Sonny took a step back, and then suddenly

01:01:51.960 --> 01:01:54.539
strong wings let out the loudest snore

01:01:54.539 --> 01:01:57.360
yet, and fierce teeth rolled over to swat

01:01:57.360 --> 01:01:57.900
him with her wing.

01:01:58.019 --> 01:02:01.739
Shut your noisy snout, or so help me, I

01:02:01.739 --> 01:02:03.719
will rip it off with my claws, she

01:02:03.719 --> 01:02:04.139
hollered.

01:02:04.199 --> 01:02:07.679
Sonny bolted into the sky and didn't stop

01:02:07.679 --> 01:02:09.780
flying until she reached the dense green

01:02:09.780 --> 01:02:10.980
canopy of the jungle again.

01:02:11.039 --> 01:02:14.639
When she finally glanced back, there was

01:02:14.639 --> 01:02:16.739
no movement from the night wings copse of

01:02:16.739 --> 01:02:17.039
trees.

01:02:17.039 --> 01:02:19.440
Strong wings had even started snoring

01:02:19.440 --> 01:02:20.039
again.

01:02:20.280 --> 01:02:22.440
I guess she was yelling at him in her

01:02:22.440 --> 01:02:24.719
sleep, or she went right back to sleep

01:02:24.719 --> 01:02:25.800
and didn't notice me there.

01:02:25.860 --> 01:02:28.920
Sonny carefully tucked the mirror under

01:02:28.920 --> 01:02:31.559
one wing and used her talons to clamber

01:02:31.559 --> 01:02:34.019
up and along the trees until she found a

01:02:34.019 --> 01:02:36.059
spot where the leaves overlapped so

01:02:36.059 --> 01:02:38.519
thickly, it was like a small green cave

01:02:38.519 --> 01:02:39.239
around her.

01:02:39.239 --> 01:02:40.920
She studied the mirror.

01:02:40.980 --> 01:02:43.500
What had Prey Hunter done to activate

01:02:43.500 --> 01:02:43.679
it?

01:02:43.739 --> 01:02:47.639
Starflight, she said softly to the cold

01:02:47.639 --> 01:02:50.280
Abyssinian, and then she breathed a small

01:02:50.280 --> 01:02:51.900
plume of smoke across the surface.

01:02:51.960 --> 01:02:55.980
As it had before, the smoke twined and

01:02:55.980 --> 01:02:57.840
twisted around the mirror, then

01:02:57.840 --> 01:02:58.500
vanished.

01:02:58.679 --> 01:03:01.019
Sonny could feel the mirror thrumming

01:03:01.019 --> 01:03:02.460
faintly between her claws.

01:03:02.519 --> 01:03:03.900
It was sort of horrible.

01:03:03.960 --> 01:03:07.260
A sick, slithering sensation through her

01:03:07.260 --> 01:03:09.659
blood, as if it were pulling something

01:03:09.659 --> 01:03:10.860
out of Sonny's heart.

01:03:10.920 --> 01:03:14.639
A faint black tendril of smoke curled up

01:03:14.639 --> 01:03:16.800
from the center of the mirror, barely

01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:18.719
visible in the green tinted sunshine.

01:03:18.780 --> 01:03:21.900
It didn't speak, but when sunny leaned

01:03:21.900 --> 01:03:24.119
closer, she could hear the faint sound of

01:03:24.119 --> 01:03:25.860
breath going in and out.

01:03:25.920 --> 01:03:27.599
He's alive.

01:03:27.659 --> 01:03:31.500
Two pale blue wisps of smoke drifted by

01:03:31.500 --> 01:03:33.420
close to the edge of the mirror.

01:03:33.480 --> 01:03:36.239
I've never seen anything like it

01:03:36.239 --> 01:03:37.559
whispered one.

01:03:37.619 --> 01:03:41.400
The queen said this is what fire can do

01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:42.840
murmured the other.

01:03:42.960 --> 01:03:45.659
It seems almost as bad as venom, if you

01:03:45.659 --> 01:03:45.960
ask me.

01:03:46.019 --> 01:03:48.539
From their voices.

01:03:48.599 --> 01:03:50.579
Sonny guessed they were 2 of the healer

01:03:50.579 --> 01:03:52.739
rain wings she'd befriended, while she

01:03:52.739 --> 01:03:53.940
was helping take care of webs.

01:03:54.059 --> 01:03:57.539
Rainwing healers were odd, specializing

01:03:57.539 --> 01:03:59.699
mostly in saying comforting things, and

01:03:59.699 --> 01:04:00.840
offering more fruit to eat.

01:04:00.900 --> 01:04:02.760
But occasionally they were really

01:04:02.760 --> 01:04:05.039
specifically knowledgeable, like about

01:04:05.039 --> 01:04:07.500
jaguar bites, or what to do if you ate

01:04:07.500 --> 01:04:10.019
too many mangoes, or how to make salves

01:04:10.019 --> 01:04:12.179
for tails that had been used for swinging

01:04:12.179 --> 01:04:13.920
from rough branches one too many times.

01:04:13.980 --> 01:04:17.519
I'd rather be Kinkaju than him right now

01:04:17.519 --> 01:04:19.260
said the first.

01:04:19.320 --> 01:04:20.099
She's healing well.

01:04:20.159 --> 01:04:22.679
Did you see the messenger who was here

01:04:22.679 --> 01:04:23.099
before?

01:04:23.159 --> 01:04:26.940
The 2nd curl of blue smoke moved, looping

01:04:26.940 --> 01:04:28.739
around the black smoke as if checking on

01:04:28.739 --> 01:04:30.900
it, and then sliding back to the first.

01:04:31.019 --> 01:04:34.079
That big brown dragon sent a message for

01:04:34.079 --> 01:04:34.619
Sonny.

01:04:34.679 --> 01:04:36.599
I wasn't sure whether to tell him we

01:04:36.599 --> 01:04:37.139
haven't seen her.

01:04:37.199 --> 01:04:39.599
I don't want to worry the queen when she

01:04:39.599 --> 01:04:41.099
has so many night wings to deal with.

01:04:41.159 --> 01:04:44.159
I say don't start a panic.

01:04:44.219 --> 01:04:45.420
She's around somewhere.

01:04:45.480 --> 01:04:48.480
This was similar to the rain wings

01:04:48.480 --> 01:04:50.579
attitude toward their own missing dragons

01:04:50.579 --> 01:04:52.679
some of which have been gone as long as a

01:04:52.679 --> 01:04:54.360
year by the time Glory rescued them.

01:04:54.420 --> 01:04:57.840
Well, that's fine, Sonny thought.

01:04:57.900 --> 01:04:59.820
I don't need or want my friends looking

01:04:59.820 --> 01:05:00.179
for me.

01:05:00.300 --> 01:05:01.679
They have enough to do.

01:05:01.739 --> 01:05:05.340
The black smoke stirred, as if the

01:05:05.340 --> 01:05:06.840
faintest breath of wind had touched it.

01:05:06.960 --> 01:05:08.639
Sunny.

01:05:08.760 --> 01:05:10.260
Starfight whispered.

01:05:10.380 --> 01:05:13.739
But, poor Starflight.

01:05:13.800 --> 01:05:16.619
She curled her tail in around her talons

01:05:16.619 --> 01:05:17.280
and sighed.

01:05:17.340 --> 01:05:19.019
Shh.

01:05:19.079 --> 01:05:21.000
We woke him by talking about her

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:23.099
admonished the 1st healer.

01:05:23.159 --> 01:05:25.199
Let's get him another sleeping dart.

01:05:25.260 --> 01:05:28.739
Sonny cleared the mirror and held it

01:05:28.739 --> 01:05:29.880
between her claws for a moment.

01:05:29.940 --> 01:05:32.519
She disliked it more and more the longer

01:05:32.519 --> 01:05:33.119
she held it.

01:05:33.179 --> 01:05:36.599
It had a chilling wrongness to it, like

01:05:36.599 --> 01:05:39.300
the tunnels, that made her scales feel as

01:05:39.300 --> 01:05:41.460
if invisible spiders were crawling all

01:05:41.460 --> 01:05:41.880
over her.

01:05:41.940 --> 01:05:45.059
But there were things she needed to know

01:05:45.059 --> 01:05:47.940
like what the warring sand wing queens

01:05:47.940 --> 01:05:48.420
were plotting.

01:05:48.480 --> 01:05:50.760
The obsidian mirror could help her figure

01:05:50.760 --> 01:05:52.440
out if any of them was an immediate

01:05:52.440 --> 01:05:53.820
threat to Sonny's friends.

01:05:53.880 --> 01:05:57.659
I should at least try one of them, the

01:05:57.659 --> 01:05:58.739
most dangerous one.

01:05:58.800 --> 01:06:02.940
She hesitated, and then whispered, Blister

01:06:02.940 --> 01:06:04.619
to the dark glass.

01:06:04.679 --> 01:06:07.860
The pale yellow twist of smoke that rose

01:06:07.860 --> 01:06:10.079
from the center this time had the same

01:06:10.079 --> 01:06:12.179
chilling stillness that blister had.

01:06:12.239 --> 01:06:14.639
It barely even moved in the breeze.

01:06:14.699 --> 01:06:16.380
Be careful.

01:06:16.440 --> 01:06:18.059
It hissed suddenly.

01:06:18.119 --> 01:06:20.159
And Sunny flinched away from the mirror.

01:06:20.219 --> 01:06:22.860
It was unsettling to hear Blister's voice

01:06:22.860 --> 01:06:24.960
as if she were on the next branch over.

01:06:25.079 --> 01:06:26.880
Close it up.

01:06:26.940 --> 01:06:27.960
Is he ready to go?

01:06:28.019 --> 01:06:29.099
All right.

01:06:29.159 --> 01:06:31.800
Give him his gold, and tell him I'll be

01:06:31.800 --> 01:06:32.699
there in a moment with final

01:06:32.699 --> 01:06:33.539
instructions.

01:06:33.599 --> 01:06:36.420
The smoke dipped for a moment, then

01:06:36.420 --> 01:06:38.579
turned is another small twister touched

01:06:38.579 --> 01:06:38.820
down.

01:06:38.880 --> 01:06:40.500
Anything?

01:06:40.559 --> 01:06:43.320
No sign of any sea wings, Your Majesty

01:06:43.320 --> 01:06:44.579
said the new arrival.

01:06:44.639 --> 01:06:46.019
We waited half the day.

01:06:46.079 --> 01:06:49.320
Blister hissed, low and long.

01:06:49.380 --> 01:06:51.780
I'll win this war without them then.

01:06:51.840 --> 01:06:53.159
She growled.

01:06:53.219 --> 01:06:56.519
Burn will be dead within a fortnight, and

01:06:56.519 --> 01:06:59.159
then I'll kill Blaze with my own talons

01:06:59.159 --> 01:07:01.500
and the sea wings will get nothing when

01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:03.179
they come slithering out of the ocean

01:07:03.179 --> 01:07:04.559
begging for forgiveness.

01:07:04.619 --> 01:07:07.739
They'll find my claws, and the entire

01:07:07.739 --> 01:07:09.719
force of the sandwing army waiting

01:07:09.719 --> 01:07:10.199
instead.

01:07:10.260 --> 01:07:13.619
Coral has no idea what vengeance can

01:07:13.619 --> 01:07:14.280
really look like.

01:07:14.340 --> 01:07:17.579
Don't touch that, she snapped abruptly.

01:07:17.699 --> 01:07:20.280
Sorry, your majesty, what?

01:07:20.400 --> 01:07:24.360
It's my plan to end this war once and for

01:07:24.360 --> 01:07:27.599
all, Blister said, in a dark voice

01:07:27.599 --> 01:07:30.780
without the sea wings or the night

01:07:30.780 --> 01:07:31.440
wings.

01:07:31.500 --> 01:07:32.880
So stay away from it.

01:07:32.940 --> 01:07:35.460
Any word from our spies in the ice

01:07:35.460 --> 01:07:35.880
kingdom?

01:07:35.940 --> 01:07:38.579
No sign of the Dragonettes yet?

01:07:38.639 --> 01:07:41.760
Perhaps, I know, Blister snapped.

01:07:41.820 --> 01:07:43.139
They could be somewhere else.

01:07:43.199 --> 01:07:46.079
There was the sound of paper crackling.

01:07:46.139 --> 01:07:48.599
I've been considering the possibilities.

01:07:48.659 --> 01:07:51.059
Hiding in the rainforest, perhaps?

01:07:51.119 --> 01:07:54.360
Sunny felt a chill down her spine.

01:07:54.420 --> 01:07:57.719
Or perhaps they're dead, said the soldier

01:07:57.780 --> 01:07:59.940
especially if they tried going to the

01:07:59.940 --> 01:08:00.599
rainforest.

01:08:00.659 --> 01:08:02.280
From what I've heard about that place.

01:08:02.400 --> 01:08:06.659
Hmm, blister mused, dead.

01:08:06.719 --> 01:08:08.940
They'd never do anything so convenient

01:08:08.940 --> 01:08:11.639
for me, even with a night wing assassin

01:08:11.639 --> 01:08:13.980
after them, supposedly, if anything

01:08:13.980 --> 01:08:15.780
Morrow Seer says can be trusted.

01:08:15.840 --> 01:08:18.180
Speaking of dragons, I'm going to

01:08:18.180 --> 01:08:20.159
dismember as soon as I get my claws on

01:08:20.159 --> 01:08:20.399
them.

01:08:20.460 --> 01:08:23.220
She doesn't know he's dead.

01:08:23.340 --> 01:08:24.840
How could she?

01:08:24.899 --> 01:08:27.479
Sonny gripped the branch below her

01:08:27.479 --> 01:08:29.639
feeling terror shudder through her

01:08:29.639 --> 01:08:29.999
scales.

01:08:30.060 --> 01:08:32.460
At least she's not searching the

01:08:32.460 --> 01:08:33.180
rainforest yet.

01:08:33.239 --> 01:08:36.000
It doesn't matter, said Blister.

01:08:36.060 --> 01:08:37.859
Her voice suddenly brisk.

01:08:37.920 --> 01:08:40.380
I'm done with prophecies.

01:08:40.439 --> 01:08:42.359
I mean, I'll still kill the dragonettes

01:08:42.359 --> 01:08:42.839
when I find them.

01:08:42.960 --> 01:08:45.060
But 1st, I have a war to win.

01:08:45.119 --> 01:08:48.300
My new plan will take care of burn, and

01:08:48.300 --> 01:08:50.340
then the stronghold will fall, and the

01:08:50.340 --> 01:08:51.960
throne will be mine.

01:08:52.020 --> 01:08:55.319
There was a chilling rattling sound.

01:08:55.380 --> 01:08:57.600
And a twist of smoke seemed to get a

01:08:57.600 --> 01:08:58.199
little darker.

01:08:58.260 --> 01:09:00.119
How?

01:09:00.119 --> 01:09:01.380
began the soldier.

01:09:01.439 --> 01:09:04.199
But just then, Sonny heard a roar from

01:09:04.199 --> 01:09:07.199
the night wings clearing, Uh-oh.

01:09:07.319 --> 01:09:09.419
She wanted to know what blister's plan

01:09:09.419 --> 01:09:11.819
was, but she needed to know how the 3

01:09:11.819 --> 01:09:14.099
night wings were reacting, and if she was

01:09:14.099 --> 01:09:16.379
in danger right now, she cleared the

01:09:16.379 --> 01:09:19.379
mirror quickly, whispered, fierce teeth

01:09:19.379 --> 01:09:21.839
to it, then breathed smoke across it

01:09:21.839 --> 01:09:22.319
again.

01:09:22.319 --> 01:09:25.919
Immediately, 3 curls of black smoke

01:09:25.919 --> 01:09:28.199
popped up on the glass, rushing around

01:09:28.199 --> 01:09:30.299
one another like small tornadoes.

01:09:30.359 --> 01:09:32.099
How could you lose it?

01:09:32.159 --> 01:09:34.619
Fierce teeth's voice snarled.

01:09:34.680 --> 01:09:36.420
I didn't lose it.

01:09:36.479 --> 01:09:37.979
Pray Hunter snapped.

01:09:38.039 --> 01:09:39.239
Someone stole it.

01:09:39.359 --> 01:09:42.179
Right out from under your snout.

01:09:42.300 --> 01:09:43.739
Fierce teeth growled.

01:09:43.800 --> 01:09:45.060
How exactly?

01:09:45.180 --> 01:09:46.859
I don't know.

01:09:46.920 --> 01:09:48.359
Pray Hunter yelled.

01:09:48.479 --> 01:09:52.919
I do, said a trembling voice, that barely

01:09:52.919 --> 01:09:54.119
sounded like strong wings.

01:09:54.180 --> 01:09:56.819
It was the dark stalker.

01:09:56.880 --> 01:09:59.579
Sunny tilted her head toward the mirror.

01:09:59.640 --> 01:10:02.100
What's the dark stalker?

01:10:02.220 --> 01:10:05.039
What could be scary enough to terrify a

01:10:05.039 --> 01:10:06.600
dragon as big as strong wings?

01:10:06.659 --> 01:10:09.539
The other 2 night wings didn't respond

01:10:09.539 --> 01:10:10.619
for a long moment.

01:10:10.680 --> 01:10:13.319
Finally, fierce teeth hissed.

01:10:13.380 --> 01:10:15.779
That's just a ghost story for Little

01:10:15.779 --> 01:10:16.619
Dragonettes.

01:10:16.680 --> 01:10:19.380
There's no dark stalker, or if there ever

01:10:19.380 --> 01:10:21.359
was, we killed him centuries ago.

01:10:21.420 --> 01:10:26.640
No, he's real, Strongwing said, edging

01:10:26.640 --> 01:10:27.479
toward hysteria.

01:10:27.539 --> 01:10:29.819
Everyone knows he's still out there

01:10:29.819 --> 01:10:32.039
somewhere, and now he's found us.

01:10:32.100 --> 01:10:33.479
Look at this message.

01:10:33.539 --> 01:10:34.859
We're going to die.

01:10:34.920 --> 01:10:37.560
It could have been someone who wants us

01:10:37.560 --> 01:10:40.920
to think, he's the dark stalker, Pray

01:10:40.920 --> 01:10:41.880
Hunter said dubiously.

01:10:41.939 --> 01:10:44.399
But who else would know we had the

01:10:44.399 --> 01:10:44.880
mirror?

01:10:44.939 --> 01:10:47.399
Who else would know that we're flying to

01:10:47.399 --> 01:10:47.760
our death?

01:10:47.819 --> 01:10:50.640
Snap out of it, strong wings?

01:10:50.760 --> 01:10:52.079
Fierce teeth barked.

01:10:52.140 --> 01:10:54.000
Someone is trying to scare us, that's

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:54.180
all.

01:10:54.239 --> 01:10:55.560
You know the story.

01:10:55.680 --> 01:10:59.279
The dark stalker, if he did exist. died a

01:10:59.279 --> 01:10:59.760
long time ago.

01:10:59.819 --> 01:11:01.260
No.

01:11:01.319 --> 01:11:03.359
He couldn't die.

01:11:03.420 --> 01:11:05.399
Strong wings whispered.

01:11:05.460 --> 01:11:08.579
They buried him, but they always knew

01:11:08.579 --> 01:11:10.560
he'd come back one day.

01:11:10.680 --> 01:11:14.159
Sunny had never heard of this mythical

01:11:14.159 --> 01:11:14.460
dragon.

01:11:14.520 --> 01:11:17.100
It must be a night wing legend.

01:11:17.220 --> 01:11:18.420
Lucky for me.

01:11:18.479 --> 01:11:21.359
She hadn't expected to tap into an old

01:11:21.359 --> 01:11:22.199
superstition.

01:11:22.260 --> 01:11:24.960
Maybe it was that sandwing.

01:11:25.020 --> 01:11:27.659
Fierce Teeth said, then immediately let

01:11:27.659 --> 01:11:29.340
out a dismissive snort.

01:11:29.399 --> 01:11:32.340
No, that stunted salamander wouldn't have

01:11:32.340 --> 01:11:33.420
the teeth for something like this.

01:11:33.479 --> 01:11:35.880
She must have gone back and told someone

01:11:35.880 --> 01:11:37.020
we had the mirror.

01:11:37.079 --> 01:11:38.939
I bet this was death bringer.

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:41.279
Seems like something he would do, from

01:11:41.279 --> 01:11:42.060
what I've heard of him.

01:11:42.119 --> 01:11:45.300
Sonny was obscurely flattered and

01:11:45.300 --> 01:11:46.319
offended at the same time.

01:11:46.380 --> 01:11:48.359
She flicked her tongue at the dark

01:11:48.359 --> 01:11:48.720
glass.

01:11:48.779 --> 01:11:51.779
A death bringer would just kill us.

01:11:51.899 --> 01:11:53.460
Argued Pray Hunter.

01:11:53.520 --> 01:11:55.739
Strongwings is right about one thing.

01:11:55.800 --> 01:11:58.439
This is what the dog stalker does

01:11:58.439 --> 01:12:00.060
according to the stories.

01:12:00.180 --> 01:12:03.060
He plays with his prey for days, making

01:12:03.060 --> 01:12:05.100
sure they're nearly paralyzed with terror

01:12:05.100 --> 01:12:06.060
before he strikes.

01:12:06.180 --> 01:12:10.619
Yes, exactly, Strongwing said.

01:12:10.680 --> 01:12:12.960
He'll come back the next time we sleep

01:12:12.960 --> 01:12:16.859
and kill just one of us, or, So let's not

01:12:16.859 --> 01:12:19.020
be paralyzed with terror.

01:12:19.079 --> 01:12:20.640
Fierce teeth snarled.

01:12:20.699 --> 01:12:21.359
Let's go.

01:12:21.479 --> 01:12:23.880
The kingdom of sand is on the other side

01:12:23.880 --> 01:12:24.720
of those mountains.

01:12:24.779 --> 01:12:27.119
We can be there in a few days if we stop

01:12:27.119 --> 01:12:28.859
moaning and clutching our tails.

01:12:28.920 --> 01:12:30.119
Come on.

01:12:30.239 --> 01:12:33.359
Her smoke tendril was nearly interwoven

01:12:33.359 --> 01:12:35.520
with strong wings. as if she were trying

01:12:35.520 --> 01:12:37.260
to heave them into the sky with brute

01:12:37.260 --> 01:12:37.680
force.

01:12:37.800 --> 01:12:39.899
But the message...

01:12:39.899 --> 01:12:41.640
We can't go back.

01:12:41.699 --> 01:12:43.079
Fierce Teeth said.

01:12:43.140 --> 01:12:46.199
Glory will kill us more definitely than

01:12:46.199 --> 01:12:48.060
any old night wing animus ghost.

01:12:48.119 --> 01:12:49.380
And if she doesn't.

01:12:49.439 --> 01:12:51.479
We'll be the rain wings prisoners.

01:12:51.539 --> 01:12:54.359
I'll take my chances in the desert, even

01:12:54.359 --> 01:12:55.079
without that mirror.

01:12:55.199 --> 01:12:57.899
The argument didn't go on much longer.

01:12:57.960 --> 01:13:00.600
Soon the sound of wing beats thumped

01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:02.039
across the smooth obsidian.

01:13:02.100 --> 01:13:05.159
Sonny tilted the smoke together, and

01:13:05.159 --> 01:13:07.680
breathed fire across it again until there

01:13:07.680 --> 01:13:10.079
was nothing but silence, and darkness on

01:13:10.079 --> 01:13:10.920
the face of the mirror.

01:13:11.039 --> 01:13:14.399
The slithering inside of her faded, but

01:13:14.399 --> 01:13:16.560
she felt more tired and sick than she had

01:13:16.560 --> 01:13:17.159
in a while.

01:13:17.220 --> 01:13:19.979
I hope I don't have to use this thing too

01:13:19.979 --> 01:13:20.699
often.

01:13:20.760 --> 01:13:23.039
So I'd better try to keep an eye on

01:13:23.039 --> 01:13:23.220
them.

01:13:23.279 --> 01:13:26.340
She ducked through the leaves and flew

01:13:26.340 --> 01:13:28.380
straight up until she slipped through the

01:13:28.380 --> 01:13:30.600
whispering green canopy, straight into

01:13:30.600 --> 01:13:31.800
blinding sunlight.

01:13:32.279 --> 01:13:35.279
On the western horizon, already no bigger

01:13:35.279 --> 01:13:37.619
than claws, she could see the 3 black

01:13:37.619 --> 01:13:39.420
shapes winging away toward the

01:13:39.420 --> 01:13:39.960
mountains.

01:13:40.079 --> 01:13:42.899
She followed, feeling better and stronger

01:13:42.899 --> 01:13:44.819
with each moment of sun on her scales.

01:13:44.880 --> 01:13:49.800
The kingdom of sand, the desert, just on

01:13:49.800 --> 01:13:51.300
the other side of those mountains.

01:13:51.420 --> 01:13:53.100
I'm going home.

01:13:53.159 --> 01:13:57.720
Chapter 5.

01:13:58.020 --> 01:14:01.979
Sunny followed the night wings for 3 days

01:14:01.979 --> 01:14:04.260
as they navigated the foothills, and then

01:14:04.260 --> 01:14:06.479
the snowier heights of the mountain crags

01:14:06.479 --> 01:14:09.000
they slept in the shadow of Jade Mountain

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:11.159
listening to the wind howling around the

01:14:11.159 --> 01:14:11.880
twin peaks.

01:14:11.939 --> 01:14:14.640
She only had to use the mirror once more

01:14:14.640 --> 01:14:17.039
when she lost sight of them, and it

01:14:17.039 --> 01:14:18.300
helped her catch up to them again.

01:14:18.359 --> 01:14:21.000
She would have loved to sneak back into

01:14:21.000 --> 01:14:22.800
their camp and leave more scary

01:14:22.800 --> 01:14:23.460
messages.

01:14:23.520 --> 01:14:26.220
But she knew they'd take turns staying

01:14:26.220 --> 01:14:27.779
awake to keep watch after losing the

01:14:27.779 --> 01:14:28.199
mirror.

01:14:28.260 --> 01:14:30.659
And she resisted the temptation to use

01:14:30.659 --> 01:14:33.180
the mirror on her friends, or on blister

01:14:33.180 --> 01:14:35.220
again, although she kept worrying about

01:14:35.220 --> 01:14:36.359
blister's new plan.

01:14:36.420 --> 01:14:39.600
Still, she wanted to avoid that sick

01:14:39.600 --> 01:14:41.579
slidery feeling as much as possible.

01:14:41.640 --> 01:14:44.880
From the mountaintops, they flew down

01:14:44.880 --> 01:14:47.159
through densely forested foothills, and

01:14:47.159 --> 01:14:49.800
off in a distance, ahead of them, Sunny

01:14:49.800 --> 01:14:51.840
began to see something that shimmered

01:14:51.840 --> 01:14:54.300
white and hazy across the horizon.

01:14:54.359 --> 01:14:58.439
The desert, she thought, with a prickle

01:14:58.439 --> 01:14:59.159
of anticipation.

01:14:59.220 --> 01:15:01.979
She'd been there once before, when the

01:15:01.979 --> 01:15:03.539
dragonettes found the tunnel from the

01:15:03.539 --> 01:15:05.520
rainforest into the kingdom of sand.

01:15:05.579 --> 01:15:08.460
They'd had to chase mangrove all the way

01:15:08.460 --> 01:15:10.319
to the borderlands of the Ice Kingdom.

01:15:10.380 --> 01:15:13.380
So she'd spent 2 days flying over the

01:15:13.380 --> 01:15:16.020
desert, but hardly any time down on the

01:15:16.020 --> 01:15:18.180
sand, where her talons really wanted to

01:15:18.180 --> 01:15:18.359
be.

01:15:18.479 --> 01:15:21.239
And no time at all looking for my

01:15:21.239 --> 01:15:21.600
parents.

01:15:21.659 --> 01:15:24.720
Her thoughts kept circling back to that

01:15:24.720 --> 01:15:27.840
as she flew, with no one to talk to, and

01:15:27.840 --> 01:15:29.100
nothing else to distract her from

01:15:29.100 --> 01:15:30.359
worrying about the prophecy.

01:15:30.420 --> 01:15:33.479
Her friends had all found some kind of

01:15:33.479 --> 01:15:34.380
family by now.

01:15:34.439 --> 01:15:36.960
Even if some of it was disappointing

01:15:36.960 --> 01:15:39.359
family, and no one was quite what they'd

01:15:39.359 --> 01:15:39.779
expected.

01:15:39.840 --> 01:15:43.140
Clay's mother was awful, but his brothers

01:15:43.140 --> 01:15:45.239
and sisters were a lot like him, according

01:15:45.239 --> 01:15:45.840
to Clay.

01:15:45.899 --> 01:15:48.539
Tsunami's mother was the queen of the sea

01:15:48.539 --> 01:15:51.899
wings, who had tried to imprison them, but

01:15:51.899 --> 01:15:54.779
tsunami had 2 little sisters too, anemone

01:15:54.779 --> 01:15:55.619
and Aucklet.

01:15:55.680 --> 01:15:58.500
Glory had no way to figure out who her

01:15:58.500 --> 01:16:00.720
parents were, thanks to the way rain

01:16:00.720 --> 01:16:03.359
wings kept their eggs all together, but

01:16:03.359 --> 01:16:06.359
she'd found a brother, Jambu, even if he

01:16:06.359 --> 01:16:09.539
was a bit silly, and also grandeur, who

01:16:09.539 --> 01:16:11.579
was perhaps a great grandmother, or great

01:16:11.579 --> 01:16:12.720
aunt, or something like that.

01:16:12.720 --> 01:16:15.720
Poor Starflight had really had it the

01:16:15.720 --> 01:16:18.060
worst of all, between mastermind for a

01:16:18.060 --> 01:16:19.979
dad and fierce teeth as his sister.

01:16:20.039 --> 01:16:22.319
But at least they knew.

01:16:22.380 --> 01:16:25.020
At least they'd found someone.

01:16:25.079 --> 01:16:27.239
They all had dragons who wanted them in

01:16:27.239 --> 01:16:27.720
some way.

01:16:27.779 --> 01:16:30.840
Why did my parents leave me?

01:16:30.899 --> 01:16:34.199
She had almost nothing to go on if she

01:16:34.199 --> 01:16:36.539
ever wanted to look for her family.

01:16:36.600 --> 01:16:39.359
All Kestrel had said was, Dune found

01:16:39.359 --> 01:16:42.539
Sonny's egg in the desert, hidden near

01:16:42.539 --> 01:16:43.979
the Scorpion Den.

01:16:43.979 --> 01:16:46.140
The Scorpion Den.

01:16:46.199 --> 01:16:48.060
I don't even know what that is.

01:16:48.119 --> 01:16:51.060
She'd seen it marked on the map, but she

01:16:51.060 --> 01:16:52.500
didn't remember reading about it in any

01:16:52.500 --> 01:16:52.979
scrolls.

01:16:53.039 --> 01:16:54.720
Oh.

01:16:54.840 --> 01:16:57.600
Her wings missed a beat as she finally

01:16:57.600 --> 01:16:59.760
remembered where she'd heard about Jade

01:16:59.760 --> 01:17:00.119
Mountain.

01:17:00.239 --> 01:17:02.939
It was something Kestrel said the last

01:17:02.939 --> 01:17:03.600
time we saw her.

01:17:03.659 --> 01:17:05.699
When you realize you need me.

01:17:05.760 --> 01:17:08.039
You can send me a message through the

01:17:08.039 --> 01:17:09.300
dragon of Jade Mountain.

01:17:09.359 --> 01:17:12.420
She twisted to look back at the fanged

01:17:12.420 --> 01:17:12.840
mountain.

01:17:12.899 --> 01:17:14.880
So a dragon lived there.

01:17:14.939 --> 01:17:17.399
One who dealt with at least some of the

01:17:17.399 --> 01:17:20.100
talons of peace, that could be useful to

01:17:20.100 --> 01:17:20.699
keep in mind.

01:17:20.760 --> 01:17:24.539
Although, who would live somewhere so

01:17:24.539 --> 01:17:25.260
sinister?

01:17:25.380 --> 01:17:29.100
She wondered which tribe it was from, and

01:17:29.100 --> 01:17:30.779
why he or she lived alone.

01:17:30.840 --> 01:17:34.260
When she turned back around, she saw the

01:17:34.260 --> 01:17:36.600
distant shapes of the night wings diving

01:17:36.600 --> 01:17:37.979
toward the forest below them.

01:17:38.039 --> 01:17:39.840
Resting again?

01:17:39.840 --> 01:17:41.340
When we're so close?

01:17:41.460 --> 01:17:43.859
We can't be more than an hour's flight

01:17:43.859 --> 01:17:44.760
from the desert now.

01:17:44.819 --> 01:17:47.460
They had only flown for half the night

01:17:47.460 --> 01:17:49.800
before stopping to sleep, and then risen

01:17:49.800 --> 01:17:51.539
with the sunrise to fly again a few hours

01:17:51.539 --> 01:17:51.779
ago.

01:17:51.840 --> 01:17:55.140
Now the sun had cleared the eastern

01:17:55.140 --> 01:17:58.319
horizon, but the day was barely begun, and

01:17:58.319 --> 01:17:59.399
they already needed a break.

01:17:59.460 --> 01:18:02.579
They seriously have no stamina.

01:18:02.699 --> 01:18:05.399
She rolled her eyes and folded her wings

01:18:05.399 --> 01:18:07.020
to drop down into the forest as well.

01:18:07.079 --> 01:18:10.500
Wind flurried green leaves brushed

01:18:10.500 --> 01:18:13.020
against her scales, and a riot of gray

01:18:13.020 --> 01:18:15.000
squirrels scattered along the branches as

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:17.640
she landed, her talons sinking into the

01:18:17.640 --> 01:18:18.180
soft grass.

01:18:18.300 --> 01:18:20.939
In the distance, she could hear the night

01:18:20.939 --> 01:18:23.340
wings roaring grumpily, and she guessed

01:18:23.340 --> 01:18:24.840
they were having another unsuccessful

01:18:24.840 --> 01:18:25.199
hunt.

01:18:25.260 --> 01:18:28.680
For a trio of menacing killers, they were

01:18:28.680 --> 01:18:31.020
actually surprisingly bad at catching

01:18:31.020 --> 01:18:31.739
anything to eat.

01:18:31.800 --> 01:18:34.800
Sunny wasn't the world's best hunter

01:18:34.800 --> 01:18:35.220
herself.

01:18:35.279 --> 01:18:36.600
But she didn't need much.

01:18:36.659 --> 01:18:39.479
She'd always eaten less than her friends

01:18:39.479 --> 01:18:40.859
a lizard a day would be enough for her.

01:18:40.979 --> 01:18:43.979
Kestrel used to grumble that that was

01:18:43.979 --> 01:18:46.020
probably why Sonny was so stunted and

01:18:46.020 --> 01:18:48.359
scrawny, but then Dune would shake his

01:18:48.359 --> 01:18:50.520
head and insist that it was normal for

01:18:50.520 --> 01:18:52.020
sand wings to be light eaters.

01:18:52.140 --> 01:18:54.300
Kestrel and Dune.

01:18:54.359 --> 01:18:56.100
Our dead guardians.

01:18:56.159 --> 01:18:59.520
If only she'd had more time to ask Dune

01:18:59.520 --> 01:19:00.779
about where her egg came from.

01:19:00.840 --> 01:19:03.539
He'd always been evasive when the subject

01:19:03.539 --> 01:19:05.939
came up, but if she'd known her friends

01:19:05.939 --> 01:19:08.760
were planning an escape, if they'd

01:19:08.760 --> 01:19:11.399
trusted me enough to tell me about it, she

01:19:11.399 --> 01:19:13.199
thought with a frown, she could have

01:19:13.199 --> 01:19:13.979
pressed him harder.

01:19:14.039 --> 01:19:16.380
Sunny swiveled her head around

01:19:16.380 --> 01:19:16.920
listening.

01:19:17.039 --> 01:19:19.500
There was an odd noise in this forest.

01:19:19.560 --> 01:19:23.699
Actually, there were several odd noises

01:19:23.699 --> 01:19:27.060
like thumps, and murmurs, and a chattery

01:19:27.060 --> 01:19:29.399
kind of bird song, almost as though

01:19:29.399 --> 01:19:30.899
squirrels were trying to imitate their

01:19:30.899 --> 01:19:31.920
winged neighbors.

01:19:32.039 --> 01:19:35.220
But it sounded as though it was coming

01:19:35.220 --> 01:19:37.859
from under the ground.

01:19:37.920 --> 01:19:41.399
She crouched and pressed one ear to the

01:19:41.399 --> 01:19:41.939
warm earth.

01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:45.000
There's definitely something under here.

01:19:45.060 --> 01:19:47.039
Groundhogs?

01:19:47.100 --> 01:19:48.300
Rabbits?

01:19:48.359 --> 01:19:51.060
She didn't think any normal rodents made

01:19:51.060 --> 01:19:52.380
noises quite like this.

01:19:52.439 --> 01:19:55.140
And from what she could tell, it wasn't a

01:19:55.140 --> 01:19:56.579
small warren underneath her.

01:19:56.640 --> 01:19:58.920
The sounds seemed to be coming from

01:19:58.920 --> 01:20:00.239
fairly far away as well.

01:20:00.300 --> 01:20:04.020
Softly, she paced through the forest

01:20:04.020 --> 01:20:05.880
stopping occasionally to listen.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:08.939
She kept an eye out for the 3 night wings

01:20:08.939 --> 01:20:10.439
but they weren't hard to avoid.

01:20:10.500 --> 01:20:13.439
First, there was the roaring and crashing

01:20:13.439 --> 01:20:16.380
around, and then after a while, snoring

01:20:16.380 --> 01:20:18.180
that shook the top branches of the

01:20:18.180 --> 01:20:19.260
trees.

01:20:19.319 --> 01:20:21.779
Sonny worked her way cautiously westward

01:20:21.779 --> 01:20:23.399
in the direction of the desert.

01:20:23.460 --> 01:20:26.399
Small brown and red birds chorused from

01:20:26.399 --> 01:20:28.979
the trees, occasionally pausing as they

01:20:28.979 --> 01:20:31.140
saw her approach, and then starting again

01:20:31.140 --> 01:20:33.659
after a moment, as if they realized she

01:20:33.659 --> 01:20:34.680
was nothing to worry about.

01:20:34.739 --> 01:20:38.100
Bumblebees and dragonflies buzzed and

01:20:38.100 --> 01:20:39.960
hummed and flitted around her talons.

01:20:40.020 --> 01:20:43.199
In the mild morning breeze, Sonny could

01:20:43.199 --> 01:20:46.619
smell apples, and mint leaves, and

01:20:46.619 --> 01:20:49.979
something else too, like old burnt wood.

01:20:50.039 --> 01:20:51.899
She couldn't hear the sounds from under

01:20:51.899 --> 01:20:54.300
the ground anymore, but the burnt smell

01:20:54.300 --> 01:20:54.960
drew her on.

01:20:55.079 --> 01:20:57.659
Up ahead, she could see a break in the

01:20:57.659 --> 01:20:57.899
trees.

01:20:57.960 --> 01:21:00.479
She stepped out into the bright sunlight

01:21:00.479 --> 01:21:01.260
and stopped.

01:21:01.319 --> 01:21:03.420
Her eyes momentarily full of light.

01:21:03.479 --> 01:21:07.079
There was a hole blasted in the forest.

01:21:07.140 --> 01:21:10.680
Something had been here once, something

01:21:10.680 --> 01:21:12.239
that stretched for more than a mile

01:21:12.239 --> 01:21:14.460
within the forest, bigger than the

01:21:14.460 --> 01:21:15.960
dragonette's home under the mountain.

01:21:16.020 --> 01:21:19.859
But it was gone now, all burned to black

01:21:19.859 --> 01:21:20.699
ashes.

01:21:20.760 --> 01:21:23.640
Where Sonny stood at the edge of it.

01:21:23.699 --> 01:21:25.800
The forest was trying to rise again.

01:21:25.859 --> 01:21:29.159
Ashes drifted like dead leaves over her

01:21:29.159 --> 01:21:31.560
claws, but she could see small green

01:21:31.560 --> 01:21:33.300
shoots wriggling through here and there.

01:21:33.359 --> 01:21:36.420
She spread her wings and took to the air

01:21:36.420 --> 01:21:37.560
hoping for a better look.

01:21:37.619 --> 01:21:40.500
The burnt area stretched in jagged

01:21:40.500 --> 01:21:42.960
slashes through the trees, and ended at

01:21:42.960 --> 01:21:44.939
the border with the rocky foothills that

01:21:44.939 --> 01:21:45.720
led to the desert.

01:21:45.779 --> 01:21:48.720
From above, she could see that the hole

01:21:48.720 --> 01:21:51.659
in the forest was many wingspans across

01:21:51.659 --> 01:21:53.760
and black as a night wings scales.

01:21:53.819 --> 01:21:56.579
It looked like a dark gap in a piece of

01:21:56.579 --> 01:21:58.859
jewelry where a gemstone had been

01:21:58.859 --> 01:22:00.060
violently gouged out.

01:22:00.119 --> 01:22:02.159
She circled overhead.

01:22:02.220 --> 01:22:05.399
Everything inside the hole looked twisted

01:22:05.399 --> 01:22:08.819
and blasted into dark ashes, but as Sonny

01:22:08.819 --> 01:22:11.039
studied the wreckage, she realized that

01:22:11.039 --> 01:22:13.079
it wasn't just trees that had been burned

01:22:13.079 --> 01:22:13.319
here.

01:22:13.380 --> 01:22:16.439
Some of the ghostly shapes that remained

01:22:16.439 --> 01:22:18.960
looked like buildings.

01:22:19.020 --> 01:22:21.779
But these buildings were too small for

01:22:21.779 --> 01:22:22.439
dragons.

01:22:22.500 --> 01:22:26.039
Sunny landed next to one of the ruins, and

01:22:26.039 --> 01:22:27.600
stared at it in confusion for a moment.

01:22:27.659 --> 01:22:30.420
Even she was too big to fit through the

01:22:30.420 --> 01:22:33.000
stone doorways that leaned silently out

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:33.779
of the ashes.

01:22:33.840 --> 01:22:37.500
But why would any dragon build houses so

01:22:37.500 --> 01:22:37.739
small?

01:22:37.800 --> 01:22:39.899
She walked around it.

01:22:39.960 --> 01:22:42.960
Her wings stirring up small tornadoes of

01:22:42.960 --> 01:22:45.659
ash flakes, and saw that in the center of

01:22:45.659 --> 01:22:47.760
the burnt area was a kind of open

01:22:47.760 --> 01:22:49.020
square.

01:22:49.079 --> 01:22:51.420
She could feel hard cracked stones

01:22:51.420 --> 01:22:53.699
meeting her claws under the layers of

01:22:53.699 --> 01:22:54.060
ash.

01:22:54.119 --> 01:22:56.939
In the middle of the square, she found a

01:22:56.939 --> 01:22:59.880
collapsed pile of round rocks, and tipped

01:22:59.880 --> 01:23:02.399
sideways among those was a blackened

01:23:02.399 --> 01:23:04.560
metal bell about the size of Sonny's

01:23:04.560 --> 01:23:04.680
head.

01:23:04.739 --> 01:23:08.880
Somebody definitely built this, were they

01:23:08.880 --> 01:23:10.560
keeping some kind of small animal here?

01:23:10.619 --> 01:23:13.380
She turned to look at another of the

01:23:13.380 --> 01:23:16.020
small stone doorways, and found a shape

01:23:16.020 --> 01:23:17.520
sticking out of the wreckage beside it.

01:23:17.579 --> 01:23:21.180
When she clawed it out, she realized it

01:23:21.180 --> 01:23:23.880
was a piece of stone, roughly carved into

01:23:23.880 --> 01:23:27.420
a shape with 2 legs, no wings, and

01:23:27.420 --> 01:23:29.100
holding something pointy over its head.

01:23:29.159 --> 01:23:34.199
Oh, Sonny inhaled sharply, getting a nose

01:23:34.199 --> 01:23:35.640
full of old soot smell.

01:23:35.699 --> 01:23:37.500
Scavengers.

01:23:37.619 --> 01:23:41.039
The statue, if that's what it was, looked

01:23:41.039 --> 01:23:42.840
a bit like a drawing from one of the old

01:23:42.840 --> 01:23:45.420
scrolls about scavengers who attacked

01:23:45.420 --> 01:23:47.939
dragons for their treasure, waving sharp

01:23:47.939 --> 01:23:49.619
little toothpick claw things called

01:23:49.619 --> 01:23:50.699
swords.

01:23:50.760 --> 01:23:53.279
Did scavengers build this place?

01:23:53.279 --> 01:23:56.460
Can they do things like make bells and

01:23:56.460 --> 01:23:57.899
carve statues?

01:23:57.899 --> 01:24:01.260
Sunny knew scavengers lived in dens, but

01:24:01.260 --> 01:24:02.699
she hadn't thought they could build real

01:24:02.699 --> 01:24:03.600
buildings like this.

01:24:03.659 --> 01:24:06.600
She always imagined them clustering in

01:24:06.600 --> 01:24:09.720
caves or digging out holes to live in, or

01:24:09.720 --> 01:24:11.520
maybe leaning long sticks together to

01:24:11.520 --> 01:24:12.899
create shelters at most.

01:24:12.899 --> 01:24:16.319
Here, there was clearly advanced masonry

01:24:16.319 --> 01:24:19.140
deliberate foundation work, and a sort of

01:24:19.140 --> 01:24:21.600
organized street plan as far as Sonny

01:24:21.600 --> 01:24:21.899
could tell.

01:24:21.960 --> 01:24:24.000
Plus the statue.

01:24:24.119 --> 01:24:27.359
It was crude, but wasn't it art?

01:24:27.420 --> 01:24:30.239
What kind of prey made art?

01:24:30.359 --> 01:24:33.300
Maybe I misunderstanding all of this.

01:24:33.359 --> 01:24:36.239
Maybe dragons built this place and kept

01:24:36.239 --> 01:24:37.680
scavengers here for some reason.

01:24:37.739 --> 01:24:40.380
And then burned it all down?

01:24:40.439 --> 01:24:42.000
Why would they do that?

01:24:42.060 --> 01:24:45.479
She lifted into the sky, feeling

01:24:45.479 --> 01:24:46.739
unsettled.

01:24:46.800 --> 01:24:50.039
The dragonettes had studied scavengers in

01:24:50.039 --> 01:24:52.380
their scrolls, but Webbs and Kestrel had

01:24:52.380 --> 01:24:53.819
never brought any back to their mountain

01:24:53.819 --> 01:24:56.340
caves for eating or practice hunting.

01:24:56.399 --> 01:24:59.220
Sunny had seen a few small scavengers in

01:24:59.220 --> 01:25:01.979
Queen Scarlet's palace, scurrying around

01:25:01.979 --> 01:25:04.319
under the dragon's feet at a banquet for

01:25:04.319 --> 01:25:05.460
the visiting sand wings.

01:25:05.520 --> 01:25:08.880
But she'd been up in a giant bird cage on

01:25:08.880 --> 01:25:11.699
display as a gift for burn, so she hadn't

01:25:11.699 --> 01:25:12.420
gotten a very close look.

01:25:12.479 --> 01:25:15.600
Scavengers were the ones who'd started

01:25:15.600 --> 01:25:18.840
the Dragon War by killing Queen Oasis and

01:25:18.840 --> 01:25:21.479
stealing all her treasure, leaving burn

01:25:21.479 --> 01:25:23.699
blaze, and blister to fight over the

01:25:23.699 --> 01:25:25.140
throne and the empty treasury.

01:25:25.199 --> 01:25:27.239
Sonny didn't know much else about

01:25:27.239 --> 01:25:28.020
scavengers.

01:25:28.079 --> 01:25:30.840
She knew they liked shiny things.

01:25:30.899 --> 01:25:33.840
She'd always imagined scavengers as sort

01:25:33.840 --> 01:25:37.439
of fierce magpies or squirrels, bigger

01:25:37.439 --> 01:25:39.180
than either of those, but not much

01:25:39.180 --> 01:25:39.539
smarter.

01:25:39.659 --> 01:25:41.819
They couldn't have very much of a brain

01:25:41.819 --> 01:25:43.739
if they thought attacking dragons was a

01:25:43.739 --> 01:25:44.399
good idea, right?

01:25:44.460 --> 01:25:47.699
She glanced down at the destroyed village

01:25:47.699 --> 01:25:50.100
once more, then turned back to find a

01:25:50.100 --> 01:25:51.659
spot where she could hide and wait for

01:25:51.659 --> 01:25:52.319
the night wings.

01:25:52.439 --> 01:25:55.500
Maybe there's more to scavengers than we

01:25:55.500 --> 01:25:55.920
were taught.

01:25:55.979 --> 01:25:57.840
But what happened here?

01:25:57.899 --> 01:26:01.199
Who burned down this scavenger den?

01:26:01.260 --> 01:26:02.220
And why?

01:26:02.340 --> 01:26:06.840
Chapter 6.

01:26:06.899 --> 01:26:11.340
Heat blazed across Sonny's scales.

01:26:11.399 --> 01:26:14.399
She burrowed into the sand, feeling the

01:26:14.399 --> 01:26:16.560
tiny particles drift across her talons

01:26:16.560 --> 01:26:17.039
and tail.

01:26:17.100 --> 01:26:20.220
The obsidian mirror caught the sunshine

01:26:20.220 --> 01:26:21.840
as if it were trying to suck all the

01:26:21.840 --> 01:26:24.600
light into itself, and the black wisps of

01:26:24.600 --> 01:26:26.760
smoke on its surface looked like small

01:26:26.760 --> 01:26:28.020
sandstorms.

01:26:28.079 --> 01:26:30.659
Why wouldn't we go straight to burn

01:26:30.659 --> 01:26:31.619
stronghold?

01:26:31.680 --> 01:26:33.720
Fierce Teeth's voice demanded.

01:26:33.779 --> 01:26:37.319
Because she'll have us slaughter the

01:26:37.319 --> 01:26:38.399
moment she sees us coming.

01:26:38.460 --> 01:26:40.500
Pray Hunter said impatiently.

01:26:40.560 --> 01:26:43.260
Burn is a kill 1st.

01:26:43.319 --> 01:26:45.119
Ask questions later, kind of dragon.

01:26:45.180 --> 01:26:48.239
It makes sense to start at the Scorpion

01:26:48.239 --> 01:26:48.659
den.

01:26:48.779 --> 01:26:50.159
Strong Wings agreed.

01:26:50.220 --> 01:26:52.439
We can find someone there to take a

01:26:52.439 --> 01:26:54.000
message to Bern that we want to see her.

01:26:54.060 --> 01:26:56.100
Sonny closed her eyes.

01:26:56.159 --> 01:26:58.260
The scorpion den.

01:26:58.319 --> 01:27:00.600
That might be where my parents live.

01:27:00.659 --> 01:27:03.779
I thought the scorpion den was full of

01:27:03.779 --> 01:27:06.119
lowlifes in criminals, said fierce

01:27:06.119 --> 01:27:06.539
teeth.

01:27:06.600 --> 01:27:09.239
It is, said Prey Hunter.

01:27:09.300 --> 01:27:10.560
It is?

01:27:10.680 --> 01:27:11.819
thought Sonny.

01:27:11.880 --> 01:27:13.859
Is that what my parents are?

01:27:13.920 --> 01:27:17.279
But they're the kind of criminals who

01:27:17.279 --> 01:27:19.140
know how to get things done from

01:27:19.140 --> 01:27:21.659
everything I've heard, said Strongwings.

01:27:21.720 --> 01:27:24.300
That's exactly what we need right now.

01:27:24.359 --> 01:27:28.140
Besides, the Scorpion Den isn't far, just

01:27:28.140 --> 01:27:29.100
over those dunes.

01:27:29.159 --> 01:27:32.399
Sonny sat up and narrowed her eyes

01:27:32.399 --> 01:27:33.779
against the bright glare of the sun.

01:27:33.899 --> 01:27:37.020
The night wings were far ahead of her, but

01:27:37.020 --> 01:27:38.340
she thought she could see a dark shape

01:27:38.340 --> 01:27:40.560
against the sand off in the distance

01:27:40.560 --> 01:27:42.659
which might be the scorpion den.

01:27:42.779 --> 01:27:46.140
All right, all right, fierce teeth

01:27:46.140 --> 01:27:46.680
grumbled.

01:27:46.739 --> 01:27:48.539
Waste of time, if you ask me.

01:27:48.600 --> 01:27:51.539
Sonny cleared the mirror, feeling

01:27:51.539 --> 01:27:53.159
excitement prickle through her scales.

01:27:53.220 --> 01:27:55.920
She knew it was unlikely that she'd find

01:27:55.920 --> 01:27:57.659
out something about her past in the

01:27:57.659 --> 01:27:59.699
Scorpion Den, but it was still the

01:27:59.699 --> 01:28:01.619
closest she'd ever been to her parents.

01:28:01.739 --> 01:28:04.800
Even if they were criminals, she still

01:28:04.800 --> 01:28:05.699
wanted to know who they were.

01:28:05.760 --> 01:28:10.079
Also, a detour to the Scorpion Den would

01:28:10.079 --> 01:28:11.819
give her more time to slow down the night

01:28:11.819 --> 01:28:12.239
wings.

01:28:12.300 --> 01:28:14.340
She still hadn't come up with any plans

01:28:14.340 --> 01:28:15.960
to stop them from telling Bern

01:28:15.960 --> 01:28:16.439
everything.

01:28:16.500 --> 01:28:19.260
In the distance.

01:28:19.319 --> 01:28:21.359
She saw the tiny black shapes lift into

01:28:21.359 --> 01:28:21.899
the sky.

01:28:21.899 --> 01:28:24.239
Cautiously, she followed them.

01:28:24.300 --> 01:28:27.180
There was really nowhere to hide in the

01:28:27.180 --> 01:28:29.220
desert, unless she burrowed under the

01:28:29.220 --> 01:28:31.500
sand, so she was staying as far back as

01:28:31.500 --> 01:28:31.800
possible.

01:28:31.859 --> 01:28:34.800
But it was hard to stop her wings from

01:28:34.800 --> 01:28:37.199
beating faster and faster as they drew

01:28:37.199 --> 01:28:38.699
closer to the scorpion den.

01:28:38.760 --> 01:28:41.399
Sonny could see that it was a walled city

01:28:41.399 --> 01:28:44.279
full of winding alleyways, ramshackle

01:28:44.279 --> 01:28:47.220
stone buildings, tattered canopies, and

01:28:47.220 --> 01:28:49.260
dilapidated tents and colors that had

01:28:49.260 --> 01:28:51.359
been faded by the sun over a long period

01:28:51.359 --> 01:28:51.899
of time.

01:28:51.960 --> 01:28:55.079
And it seethed with dragons.

01:28:55.140 --> 01:28:58.199
Scales glittered from every shadow and

01:28:58.199 --> 01:29:00.300
venomous tails slithered around corners.

01:29:00.359 --> 01:29:03.539
She was so preoccupied staring at the

01:29:03.539 --> 01:29:05.460
town that she had to stop herself

01:29:05.460 --> 01:29:08.520
abruptly in midair when she realized that

01:29:08.520 --> 01:29:11.579
the 3 night wings had not gone inside, but

01:29:11.579 --> 01:29:13.439
were standing outside the tall gates at

01:29:13.439 --> 01:29:14.159
the single entrance.

01:29:14.220 --> 01:29:16.739
It looked as though they were arguing

01:29:16.739 --> 01:29:19.079
with a muscular sand wing guard, who

01:29:19.079 --> 01:29:21.119
stood with her wings folded back and her

01:29:21.119 --> 01:29:22.380
tail raised menacingly.

01:29:22.439 --> 01:29:26.220
Sonny dropped quickly to the sand, hoping

01:29:26.220 --> 01:29:27.000
she hadn't been seen.

01:29:27.060 --> 01:29:29.579
She flattened herself against the dune

01:29:29.579 --> 01:29:31.920
even though she knew her scales were not

01:29:31.920 --> 01:29:33.659
quite the right color for camouflage.

01:29:33.720 --> 01:29:36.659
Now that she was still, she could hear

01:29:36.659 --> 01:29:38.340
the dragon's voices shouting.

01:29:38.399 --> 01:29:41.399
You have no right to stop us.

01:29:41.520 --> 01:29:43.140
Fierce teeth roared.

01:29:43.199 --> 01:29:45.300
Can't you see that we're night wings?

01:29:45.359 --> 01:29:47.939
Yeah, answered the guard.

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:49.319
So read my mind.

01:29:49.380 --> 01:29:51.539
The part that says, go at your tails.

01:29:51.600 --> 01:29:56.340
We have business in the scorpion din, Pray

01:29:56.340 --> 01:29:57.060
Hunter insisted.

01:29:57.119 --> 01:30:00.359
No one gets inside without a contribution

01:30:00.359 --> 01:30:01.439
to the outlaws.

01:30:01.500 --> 01:30:03.300
The guard said firmly.

01:30:03.359 --> 01:30:06.239
The out claws.

01:30:06.300 --> 01:30:07.619
Said Prey Hunter.

01:30:07.680 --> 01:30:09.239
That's what you call yourselves.

01:30:09.300 --> 01:30:10.680
You must be joking.

01:30:10.739 --> 01:30:12.779
Are you asking for treasure?

01:30:12.840 --> 01:30:14.460
Fierce teeth demanded.

01:30:14.520 --> 01:30:16.079
Of course we don't have treasure.

01:30:16.140 --> 01:30:17.399
Our home was just...

01:30:17.399 --> 01:30:20.159
Surely you can make an exception for us.

01:30:20.279 --> 01:30:22.859
Strong wings interjected, cutting her

01:30:22.859 --> 01:30:23.039
off.

01:30:23.100 --> 01:30:26.279
I mean, we're night wings.

01:30:26.340 --> 01:30:28.800
And said the guard.

01:30:28.859 --> 01:30:30.420
There was a pause.

01:30:30.479 --> 01:30:34.199
Sonny grinned, imagining the apoplectic

01:30:34.199 --> 01:30:35.880
fit fierce teeth was probably having.

01:30:35.939 --> 01:30:40.079
We could give you a prophecy.

01:30:40.140 --> 01:30:42.359
Prey Hunter suggested after a moment.

01:30:42.420 --> 01:30:46.380
Ha, the guard said, sounding moderately

01:30:46.380 --> 01:30:46.979
more interested.

01:30:47.039 --> 01:30:48.600
That would be funny.

01:30:48.720 --> 01:30:51.779
Kibley, tell Thorn we have 3 night wings

01:30:51.779 --> 01:30:53.220
offering their pathetic services.

01:30:53.279 --> 01:30:57.359
I think you mean prophetic services

01:30:57.359 --> 01:30:58.859
Fierce Teeth said.

01:30:58.920 --> 01:31:02.220
Uh-huh, said the guard skeptically.

01:31:02.279 --> 01:31:04.619
There was a long silence as everyone

01:31:04.619 --> 01:31:05.039
waited.

01:31:05.100 --> 01:31:08.220
Sunny wriggled higher up on her dune

01:31:08.220 --> 01:31:10.260
hoping for a view of the city gates, but

01:31:10.260 --> 01:31:12.779
a long slope of sand dotted with prickly

01:31:12.779 --> 01:31:14.340
spheres of cacti blocked her way.

01:31:14.399 --> 01:31:17.699
What can I offer the guard to get inside

01:31:17.699 --> 01:31:18.840
the scorpion den?

01:31:18.899 --> 01:31:20.039
She wondered.

01:31:20.100 --> 01:31:22.560
She glanced down at the obsidian mirror.

01:31:22.619 --> 01:31:24.479
It was the only thing she had.

01:31:24.539 --> 01:31:27.300
Was it worth giving up her one advantage

01:31:27.300 --> 01:31:28.260
over the night wings?

01:31:28.319 --> 01:31:31.140
On the other talon, she knew she'd be

01:31:31.140 --> 01:31:33.180
happy to have its sinister weight out of

01:31:33.180 --> 01:31:33.779
her claws.

01:31:33.840 --> 01:31:37.079
But on the 3rd talon, she didn't know who

01:31:37.079 --> 01:31:38.699
would end up with their claws on this

01:31:38.699 --> 01:31:41.340
potentially dangerous weapon, what might

01:31:41.340 --> 01:31:42.779
the out claws do with it?

01:31:42.840 --> 01:31:44.340
Hmm.

01:31:44.460 --> 01:31:47.460
Moreover, even if she didn't offer it to

01:31:47.460 --> 01:31:49.920
them, what was to stop a band of outlaws

01:31:49.920 --> 01:31:50.939
from just taking it?

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:53.760
Sonny thought for a moment, then quickly

01:31:53.760 --> 01:31:55.920
dug a hole in the sand next to one of the

01:31:55.920 --> 01:31:58.380
cactus balls and buried the mirror.

01:31:58.439 --> 01:32:01.020
Of course, there wasn't anything here to

01:32:01.020 --> 01:32:03.539
help her distinguish one brownish rolling

01:32:03.539 --> 01:32:04.739
sand dune from the next.

01:32:04.800 --> 01:32:07.800
She'd have to cross all her claws and

01:32:07.800 --> 01:32:10.260
hope she'd be able to find it again, but

01:32:10.260 --> 01:32:12.659
a dangerous mirror nobody could find was

01:32:12.659 --> 01:32:14.520
better than a dangerous mirror floating

01:32:14.520 --> 01:32:16.140
around the scorpion den, surely.

01:32:16.260 --> 01:32:18.720
She lifted her head as the guard below

01:32:18.720 --> 01:32:19.079
spoke.

01:32:19.140 --> 01:32:21.600
All right, he said.

01:32:21.659 --> 01:32:23.039
Thorn wants to see you.

01:32:23.100 --> 01:32:23.939
Don't ask me why.

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:26.880
Follow Kibli, and no funny business.

01:32:26.939 --> 01:32:30.300
Sonny waited as long as she could bear it

01:32:30.300 --> 01:32:32.460
then scrambled up and started over the

01:32:32.460 --> 01:32:32.880
dune.

01:32:32.939 --> 01:32:36.180
A sand wing was standing there, no more

01:32:36.180 --> 01:32:38.939
than 3 steps away, staring straight at

01:32:38.939 --> 01:32:40.920
her, as if he'd been waiting for her.

01:32:40.979 --> 01:32:43.680
His side was pocked and dented with old

01:32:43.680 --> 01:32:47.100
scars, and he had 6 claws on each foreleg

01:32:47.100 --> 01:32:48.239
instead of five.

01:32:48.300 --> 01:32:51.060
She had no idea where he'd come from, or

01:32:51.060 --> 01:32:53.039
how he'd snuck up on her so quickly and

01:32:53.039 --> 01:32:53.520
quietly.

01:32:53.579 --> 01:32:55.979
Oh, she yelped.

01:32:56.039 --> 01:32:59.279
That means you too, he said calmly.

01:32:59.340 --> 01:33:01.319
Me too, what?

01:33:01.439 --> 01:33:02.520
Sonny stammered.

01:33:02.579 --> 01:33:04.979
He tilted his head and studied her

01:33:04.979 --> 01:33:07.800
curiously, registering the odd color of

01:33:07.800 --> 01:33:10.079
her scales and eyes, and no doubt

01:33:10.079 --> 01:33:12.000
noticing her venomless tail as well.

01:33:12.060 --> 01:33:15.119
You're to come before the outlaws as

01:33:15.119 --> 01:33:15.300
well.

01:33:15.359 --> 01:33:17.579
Thorn wants to know why you're following

01:33:17.579 --> 01:33:18.840
those scum dwellers.

01:33:18.899 --> 01:33:21.119
He jerked his head in the direction of

01:33:21.119 --> 01:33:22.739
the den and the night wings.

01:33:22.800 --> 01:33:25.319
Sonny had never heard anyone refer to

01:33:25.319 --> 01:33:27.119
night wings with that much disrespect

01:33:27.119 --> 01:33:30.420
before, except perhaps tsunami or glory.

01:33:30.479 --> 01:33:33.720
I'm, I'm not following anybody.

01:33:33.779 --> 01:33:36.239
Sonny said, folding her wings back.

01:33:36.300 --> 01:33:38.760
She could hear how unconvincing she

01:33:38.760 --> 01:33:39.180
sounded.

01:33:39.239 --> 01:33:40.319
He shrugged.

01:33:40.439 --> 01:33:43.500
Lie to me all you want, but I wouldn't

01:33:43.500 --> 01:33:45.000
recommend trying it with thorn.

01:33:45.060 --> 01:33:47.699
He flicked his tail, and she flinched

01:33:47.699 --> 01:33:48.000
away.

01:33:48.060 --> 01:33:49.560
Come.

01:33:49.619 --> 01:33:51.840
It was not a request.

01:33:51.899 --> 01:33:54.180
At least he wasn't threatening to chain

01:33:54.180 --> 01:33:56.640
her up, and at least going with him would

01:33:56.640 --> 01:33:58.260
mean getting into the Scorpion den

01:33:58.260 --> 01:33:59.699
without the problem of payment.

01:33:59.760 --> 01:34:03.479
Fine, she said, lifting her chin.

01:34:03.539 --> 01:34:05.100
Take me to Thorn.

01:34:05.220 --> 01:34:09.000
They flew down to the city gates, and the

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:10.680
guard nodded impassively as they went

01:34:10.680 --> 01:34:13.140
past her, straight into a crooked stone

01:34:13.140 --> 01:34:15.479
alleyway with steps leading up and down

01:34:15.479 --> 01:34:18.359
sharp, spicy cooking smells filled the

01:34:18.359 --> 01:34:20.760
air, along with a sense of smoke and

01:34:20.760 --> 01:34:22.500
crowds of overheated dragons.

01:34:22.619 --> 01:34:24.720
The streets around them were lined with

01:34:24.720 --> 01:34:27.060
rickety stalls and tents, and voices

01:34:27.060 --> 01:34:28.380
began pressing in on Sonny.

01:34:28.500 --> 01:34:32.279
Crocodile stew, roasted scorpion, bag of

01:34:32.279 --> 01:34:32.640
crickets.

01:34:32.699 --> 01:34:35.579
Bet you'd like some gold for them golden

01:34:35.579 --> 01:34:36.000
scales.

01:34:36.060 --> 01:34:38.760
Stuck up on bright stained cactus.

01:34:38.819 --> 01:34:39.960
You never know when you might need it.

01:34:40.020 --> 01:34:42.420
Need anyone killed, little lady?

01:34:42.479 --> 01:34:44.880
Here, take my card.

01:34:44.939 --> 01:34:48.420
A small flat piece of metal inscribed

01:34:48.420 --> 01:34:50.520
with a name was pressed into Sonny's

01:34:50.520 --> 01:34:52.739
talons, and the sand wing who'd given it

01:34:52.739 --> 01:34:54.960
to her, vanished almost immediately.

01:34:55.020 --> 01:34:57.840
Sonny blinked and glanced up at the

01:34:57.840 --> 01:34:58.859
dragon escorting her.

01:34:58.920 --> 01:35:00.539
Whose is it?

01:35:00.659 --> 01:35:03.060
he asked, plucking it out of her claws.

01:35:03.119 --> 01:35:06.840
Ah, you don't want him, too expensive

01:35:06.840 --> 01:35:07.800
barely competent.

01:35:07.859 --> 01:35:10.560
He tossed the card into another stall as

01:35:10.560 --> 01:35:13.140
they went by, and a snout poked out of a

01:35:13.140 --> 01:35:14.640
pile of carpets to growl at them.

01:35:14.699 --> 01:35:16.439
Ouch!

01:35:16.500 --> 01:35:19.319
Sonny yelped. as someone rushed past and

01:35:19.319 --> 01:35:20.159
stepped on her tail.

01:35:20.220 --> 01:35:22.380
She tried to sidestep a pair of

01:35:22.380 --> 01:35:24.659
quarreling dragons and got smacked in the

01:35:24.659 --> 01:35:25.859
face by a sandy wing.

01:35:25.920 --> 01:35:28.439
These streets are so narrow.

01:35:28.560 --> 01:35:30.659
And there are so many of them.

01:35:30.720 --> 01:35:33.359
They must accidentally scratch each other

01:35:33.359 --> 01:35:34.380
with their tails all the time.

01:35:34.439 --> 01:35:37.560
She looked more closely at the stalls

01:35:37.560 --> 01:35:40.020
around her, and realized that many of

01:35:40.020 --> 01:35:41.699
them sold the cactus that was the

01:35:41.699 --> 01:35:44.520
antidote to sandwing venom, as far as she

01:35:44.520 --> 01:35:46.619
could see, it was nearly as popular as

01:35:46.619 --> 01:35:48.659
the giant camel hide pouches of water

01:35:48.659 --> 01:35:51.359
being sold by every other merchant, or

01:35:51.359 --> 01:35:53.579
the tiny blue dragons and shiny black

01:35:53.579 --> 01:35:55.859
spheres, that also seemed to share all

01:35:55.859 --> 01:35:57.420
the tables with other merchandise.

01:35:57.479 --> 01:36:01.380
A wooden signboard caught her eye. 3

01:36:01.380 --> 01:36:03.899
dragons faces carved under the words

01:36:03.899 --> 01:36:05.039
wanted.

01:36:05.159 --> 01:36:07.859
Sonny twisted to try and stare at their

01:36:07.859 --> 01:36:09.479
faces as her guard hurried her past.

01:36:09.539 --> 01:36:12.060
She could have sworn one of them was

01:36:12.060 --> 01:36:12.479
Dune.

01:36:12.600 --> 01:36:15.420
And one of the others was.

01:36:15.479 --> 01:36:16.680
But surely it couldn't be.

01:36:16.739 --> 01:36:19.859
Her guard steered her through the tangles

01:36:19.859 --> 01:36:22.439
of dragons, keeping one wing firmly

01:36:22.439 --> 01:36:23.460
settled against her back.

01:36:23.520 --> 01:36:26.100
Other dragons jumped out of his way when

01:36:26.100 --> 01:36:28.260
they spotted him, or ducked their heads

01:36:28.260 --> 01:36:30.779
as he went by, or slipped into shadowy

01:36:30.779 --> 01:36:31.800
corners, hissing.

01:36:31.859 --> 01:36:35.760
Soon Sonny realized that the same wooden

01:36:35.760 --> 01:36:38.939
wanted sign was posted everywhere, hung

01:36:38.939 --> 01:36:42.000
from walls, pinned to tent flaps, and

01:36:42.000 --> 01:36:43.619
nailed to the stall boards.

01:36:43.680 --> 01:36:46.199
She got a chance to peer at one more

01:36:46.199 --> 01:36:48.300
closely when they paused, to let a card

01:36:48.300 --> 01:36:50.399
of gold painted boxes clatter by.

01:36:50.460 --> 01:36:53.460
It really does look like Morrisier.

01:36:53.520 --> 01:36:57.000
Marosier, Dune, and a Nightwing I've

01:36:57.000 --> 01:36:58.680
never seen before, but why?

01:36:58.739 --> 01:37:00.659
And who's looking for them?

01:37:00.779 --> 01:37:03.840
There was small print below the pictures

01:37:03.840 --> 01:37:05.579
but Sonny didn't get to read it before

01:37:05.579 --> 01:37:06.779
her guard hurried her on.

01:37:06.840 --> 01:37:10.260
Nearly all the dragons she saw were sand

01:37:10.260 --> 01:37:13.020
wings, although she also spotted a couple

01:37:13.020 --> 01:37:16.979
of scarlet sky wings and even, once, the

01:37:16.979 --> 01:37:19.739
pale blue scales of an ice wing, who must

01:37:19.739 --> 01:37:21.119
have been miserable in this heat.

01:37:21.180 --> 01:37:24.600
She also noticed a lot of war wounds.

01:37:24.659 --> 01:37:27.720
Dragons with missing talons, mangled

01:37:27.720 --> 01:37:30.960
wings, clawed up snouts, or ripped ears

01:37:30.960 --> 01:37:33.000
many of them huddling in the spaces

01:37:33.000 --> 01:37:36.060
between the stalls, skinny and wretched.

01:37:36.119 --> 01:37:38.880
Although she was sure the Scorpion Den

01:37:38.880 --> 01:37:41.039
was a dangerous place to live, she

01:37:41.039 --> 01:37:42.779
guessed that a lot of dragons came here

01:37:42.779 --> 01:37:45.359
to hide from the war, either before they

01:37:45.359 --> 01:37:47.579
could be pressed into service, or after

01:37:47.579 --> 01:37:49.680
they'd been so badly injured that they

01:37:49.680 --> 01:37:50.880
couldn't bear to fight anymore.

01:37:50.880 --> 01:37:54.420
One Sandwing limped up to them, and did

01:37:54.420 --> 01:37:56.579
an odd half salute to Sonny's guard.

01:37:56.640 --> 01:37:59.460
Going off duty, sir.

01:37:59.520 --> 01:38:02.939
He paused and squinted at Sonny, and she

01:38:02.939 --> 01:38:05.100
realized that he had a long scratch

01:38:05.100 --> 01:38:07.739
across one of his eyes that had also torn

01:38:07.739 --> 01:38:08.579
up part of his nose.

01:38:08.640 --> 01:38:11.100
There was something vaguely familiar

01:38:11.100 --> 01:38:13.140
about him, but she was sure she would

01:38:13.140 --> 01:38:14.520
have remembered that scratch.

01:38:14.579 --> 01:38:16.319
Addict.

01:38:16.380 --> 01:38:18.840
Quit reporting to me all the time, the

01:38:18.840 --> 01:38:19.319
guard said.

01:38:19.380 --> 01:38:21.420
That's not how the outlaws work.

01:38:21.479 --> 01:38:24.359
Also, I told you to stop calling me, sir.

01:38:24.479 --> 01:38:27.180
Yes, right, right.

01:38:27.239 --> 01:38:30.119
The dragon coughed, clearly swallowing

01:38:30.119 --> 01:38:30.779
another sir.

01:38:30.899 --> 01:38:33.539
Ah, who's your guest?

01:38:33.600 --> 01:38:36.300
Sonny sidled closer to her escort.

01:38:36.359 --> 01:38:38.399
Wishing addicts would stop staring at

01:38:38.399 --> 01:38:38.640
her.

01:38:38.760 --> 01:38:41.399
Her guard seemed to sense this.

01:38:41.460 --> 01:38:43.680
He casually spread his big wings to

01:38:43.680 --> 01:38:44.520
shield her from view.

01:38:44.579 --> 01:38:47.819
Just a visitor for Thorn, he said.

01:38:47.880 --> 01:38:49.140
Carry on.

01:38:49.199 --> 01:38:52.319
Addicts bobbed his head and shuffled off

01:38:52.319 --> 01:38:53.039
into the crowd.

01:38:53.100 --> 01:38:57.000
Some of these former soldiers have a hard

01:38:57.000 --> 01:38:58.800
time breaking their military habits.

01:38:58.859 --> 01:39:02.159
The big sandwink said to her, but addicts

01:39:02.159 --> 01:39:02.579
is harmless.

01:39:02.640 --> 01:39:03.479
Don't worry.

01:39:03.539 --> 01:39:06.779
Sonny twisted to look back, and saw that

01:39:06.779 --> 01:39:08.699
the limping sand wing had stopped in the

01:39:08.699 --> 01:39:10.619
shade of a stall that seemed to be

01:39:10.619 --> 01:39:12.060
selling poisons.

01:39:12.119 --> 01:39:14.880
His black eyes stared through her, and

01:39:14.880 --> 01:39:16.619
even when she ducked behind her guard's

01:39:16.619 --> 01:39:18.659
wings again, and after they had crossed

01:39:18.659 --> 01:39:21.300
several more alleys, she still fell to

01:39:21.300 --> 01:39:23.579
prickling, creeping feeling along her

01:39:23.579 --> 01:39:25.560
spine, as if his gaze were following

01:39:25.560 --> 01:39:25.920
her.

01:39:25.979 --> 01:39:29.279
They wound their way toward the center of

01:39:29.279 --> 01:39:31.800
the city, stooping under torn canopies

01:39:31.800 --> 01:39:34.260
and tripping over uneven cobblestones

01:39:34.260 --> 01:39:36.960
Sunny could smell something new up ahead

01:39:36.960 --> 01:39:40.199
like exploded fruit, and she caught a

01:39:40.199 --> 01:39:42.600
glimpse of dark green through the gaps

01:39:42.600 --> 01:39:44.939
ahead of her, incongruous against the

01:39:44.939 --> 01:39:47.399
sand colored buildings, faded orange

01:39:47.399 --> 01:39:50.460
tents, and red or black brick walls.

01:39:50.520 --> 01:39:52.920
A dragonette suddenly stumbled in front

01:39:52.920 --> 01:39:55.199
of Sonny, holding out its front claws.

01:39:55.260 --> 01:39:59.760
Hungry He bleated, his pale yellow scales

01:39:59.760 --> 01:40:02.520
were slathered with dirt, and he was tiny

01:40:02.520 --> 01:40:04.800
with bony ribs sticking out along his

01:40:04.800 --> 01:40:07.859
chest, his black eyes caught Sonny, and

01:40:07.859 --> 01:40:09.600
she stared down at him helplessly.

01:40:09.659 --> 01:40:12.060
I'm sorry, she said.

01:40:12.119 --> 01:40:13.500
I don't have anything.

01:40:13.560 --> 01:40:16.979
The dragon beside her leaned forward, and

01:40:16.979 --> 01:40:18.600
caught the dragonette before he could run

01:40:18.600 --> 01:40:20.939
off again, casually pinning the little

01:40:20.939 --> 01:40:22.859
one's tail to the ground with one talon.

01:40:22.979 --> 01:40:26.819
Don't hurt him, Sonny cried, but the

01:40:26.819 --> 01:40:27.960
guard didn't even look at her.

01:40:28.020 --> 01:40:30.479
Where's your guardian, squirt?

01:40:30.539 --> 01:40:32.039
He asked the dragonette.

01:40:32.100 --> 01:40:35.579
Sorry, sorry, sorry, cried a female

01:40:35.579 --> 01:40:37.739
sandwing. hurrying out of a nearby

01:40:37.739 --> 01:40:38.100
alley.

01:40:38.159 --> 01:40:40.380
I would never have let him bother you

01:40:40.380 --> 01:40:40.619
sir.

01:40:40.680 --> 01:40:41.460
Please forgive us.

01:40:41.579 --> 01:40:43.920
She grabbed the dragonette and clutched

01:40:43.920 --> 01:40:44.399
him to her.

01:40:44.460 --> 01:40:45.479
He drooped.

01:40:45.539 --> 01:40:47.520
No energy left to wriggle away.

01:40:47.579 --> 01:40:51.899
You must be new here, said the 6 clawed

01:40:51.899 --> 01:40:53.399
dragon, squinting at her.

01:40:53.460 --> 01:40:55.380
He shouldn't be starving like that.

01:40:55.439 --> 01:40:58.199
Dragonette's up to 8 years old, get a

01:40:58.199 --> 01:41:00.180
free meal every morning after sunrise at

01:41:00.180 --> 01:41:00.479
the pool.

01:41:00.600 --> 01:41:03.119
Start sending him, and he'll be the size

01:41:03.119 --> 01:41:04.140
of a real dragon soon.

01:41:04.199 --> 01:41:07.079
The sand wings shivered and ducked her

01:41:07.079 --> 01:41:07.319
head.

01:41:07.380 --> 01:41:09.840
But, sir, she whispered.

01:41:09.960 --> 01:41:11.579
I heard that was a trick.

01:41:11.699 --> 01:41:13.859
He sighed impatiently.

01:41:13.920 --> 01:41:15.119
Let me guess.

01:41:15.180 --> 01:41:17.699
We feed them, and then grab them to turn

01:41:17.699 --> 01:41:18.960
them into out claws.

01:41:19.020 --> 01:41:19.439
Am I right?

01:41:19.500 --> 01:41:22.979
She flinched, and her wings folded closer

01:41:22.979 --> 01:41:23.939
around the dragonette.

01:41:24.000 --> 01:41:26.880
Listen, we're not out to abduct a bunch

01:41:26.880 --> 01:41:29.100
of scrawny youngsters who be more trouble

01:41:29.100 --> 01:41:29.760
than they're worth.

01:41:29.819 --> 01:41:32.279
Thorn just wants to make sure no more

01:41:32.279 --> 01:41:34.380
dragonettes die of hunger in the scorpion

01:41:34.380 --> 01:41:34.680
den.

01:41:34.739 --> 01:41:36.060
It's not complicated.

01:41:36.119 --> 01:41:39.600
Yes, sir, the sand wing whispered.

01:41:39.720 --> 01:41:42.899
Look, send him tomorrow morning, or I'll

01:41:42.899 --> 01:41:44.939
come after you myself, he said.

01:41:45.000 --> 01:41:48.000
She nodded and scuttled away, keeping the

01:41:48.000 --> 01:41:49.319
dragonette under her wing.

01:41:49.560 --> 01:41:53.340
Some dragons, muttered Sonny's guard.

01:41:53.399 --> 01:41:54.539
Is that true?

01:41:54.659 --> 01:41:55.800
Sonny asked.

01:41:55.859 --> 01:41:59.880
The, um, outlaws feed all the dragonettes

01:41:59.880 --> 01:42:00.960
in the scorpion den?

01:42:01.079 --> 01:42:03.359
He shifted his wings up and down and

01:42:03.359 --> 01:42:03.899
scowled.

01:42:03.960 --> 01:42:05.399
We try to.

01:42:05.460 --> 01:42:08.220
Dragons don't change easily, though

01:42:08.340 --> 01:42:10.979
especially in a place like this, and

01:42:10.979 --> 01:42:12.539
especially when someone's trying to help

01:42:12.539 --> 01:42:12.779
them.

01:42:12.840 --> 01:42:16.500
Brainless worms, he muttered, turning to

01:42:16.500 --> 01:42:17.159
stalk away again.

01:42:17.220 --> 01:42:20.399
Sonny wasn't sure that she would trust a

01:42:20.399 --> 01:42:21.479
gift from this dragon either.

01:42:21.539 --> 01:42:23.579
What's your name?

01:42:23.640 --> 01:42:25.979
She asked, as she caught up to walk

01:42:25.979 --> 01:42:26.520
beside him.

01:42:26.579 --> 01:42:30.060
He looked down at her, his black tongue

01:42:30.060 --> 01:42:32.760
flicking in and out. 6 claws.

01:42:32.819 --> 01:42:36.539
Oh, Sunny said, glancing at his odd

01:42:36.539 --> 01:42:38.579
talons, and then, before she could stop

01:42:38.579 --> 01:42:40.979
herself, your parents were feeling pretty

01:42:40.979 --> 01:42:41.340
creative.

01:42:41.399 --> 01:42:44.220
He barked a laugh that made several

01:42:44.220 --> 01:42:46.260
dragons around them leap into the nearest

01:42:46.260 --> 01:42:47.579
hiding place in terror.

01:42:47.640 --> 01:42:50.460
Sunlight glinted off his light, yellowish

01:42:50.460 --> 01:42:52.619
brown scales as he held up one of his

01:42:52.619 --> 01:42:55.500
front legs and examined the 6 wickedly

01:42:55.500 --> 01:42:56.340
sharp claws there.

01:42:56.399 --> 01:42:57.960
I guess so.

01:42:58.020 --> 01:42:59.100
Yours?

01:42:59.220 --> 01:43:01.439
I'm Sonny, she said.

01:43:01.500 --> 01:43:03.000
I never met my parents.

01:43:03.060 --> 01:43:05.699
She chanced to sideways look at his

01:43:05.699 --> 01:43:06.180
face.

01:43:06.239 --> 01:43:07.500
But there was no reaction there.

01:43:07.560 --> 01:43:10.500
He was old enough to be her father, and

01:43:10.500 --> 01:43:12.479
from the way he walked and talked, she

01:43:12.479 --> 01:43:14.220
guessed he'd been in the scorpion den for

01:43:14.220 --> 01:43:14.520
a while.

01:43:14.579 --> 01:43:17.819
Plus, he had those 6 claws.

01:43:17.880 --> 01:43:19.920
Maybe peculiar defects ran in the

01:43:19.920 --> 01:43:20.220
family.

01:43:20.279 --> 01:43:23.100
Maybe he hadn't commented on her tail yet

01:43:23.100 --> 01:43:25.500
because he'd seen other dragons with the

01:43:25.500 --> 01:43:27.899
same flaw, dragons related to him.

01:43:27.960 --> 01:43:30.960
Or maybe I'm totally desperate.

01:43:31.020 --> 01:43:34.380
They stepped down a set of 5 stone stairs

01:43:34.380 --> 01:43:37.020
and their talons sank into sand.

01:43:37.079 --> 01:43:40.140
Sonny tore her gaze away from 6 claws, and

01:43:40.140 --> 01:43:41.819
saw that the shadows of tents and

01:43:41.819 --> 01:43:43.800
canopies had been replaced by the

01:43:43.800 --> 01:43:46.079
sweeping shade of large palm fronds.

01:43:46.199 --> 01:43:49.260
There was an oasis in the middle of the

01:43:49.260 --> 01:43:50.039
scorpion den.

01:43:50.100 --> 01:43:54.600
Well, that makes sense, Sonny realized

01:43:54.600 --> 01:43:56.520
why else would dragons build a city

01:43:56.520 --> 01:43:56.699
here?

01:43:56.760 --> 01:43:59.939
She could see a rippling pool of greenish

01:43:59.939 --> 01:44:01.739
blue water in the middle of the sand in

01:44:01.739 --> 01:44:02.340
the palms.

01:44:02.399 --> 01:44:05.340
She could also see multiple well armed

01:44:05.340 --> 01:44:07.500
dangerous looking dragons patrolling

01:44:07.500 --> 01:44:08.579
around the outskirts of it.

01:44:08.640 --> 01:44:11.579
Are those all out claws?

01:44:11.640 --> 01:44:12.239
She asked.

01:44:12.300 --> 01:44:14.760
You guard the water in the scorpion den?

01:44:14.819 --> 01:44:16.319
In the desert.

01:44:16.380 --> 01:44:19.380
She who controls the water, controls

01:44:19.380 --> 01:44:19.680
everything.

01:44:19.739 --> 01:44:21.539
Six claws said.

01:44:21.600 --> 01:44:26.939
And hear that she is thorn, sunny guest.

01:44:27.000 --> 01:44:29.460
Six claws nodded toward a large white

01:44:29.460 --> 01:44:31.380
tent, set up beside the water.

01:44:31.500 --> 01:44:35.100
The walls billowed like swans, wings, and

01:44:35.100 --> 01:44:37.079
venomous tail points stuck out under the

01:44:37.079 --> 01:44:39.840
edges here and there, to particularly

01:44:39.840 --> 01:44:41.760
mean looking sand wings guarded the

01:44:41.760 --> 01:44:43.979
entrance, where a flap had been rolled up

01:44:43.979 --> 01:44:46.140
to allow dragons to pass through.

01:44:46.199 --> 01:44:49.260
As they approached, Sunny spotted a flash

01:44:49.260 --> 01:44:51.539
of black scales through the doorway and

01:44:51.539 --> 01:44:53.159
ducked behind 6 claws.

01:44:53.220 --> 01:44:55.380
He peered over his shoulder at her.

01:44:55.500 --> 01:44:56.399
Yes.

01:44:56.460 --> 01:44:59.340
I don't want them to see me, she

01:44:59.340 --> 01:44:59.880
whispered.

01:44:59.939 --> 01:45:01.560
The Night Wings?

01:45:01.560 --> 01:45:02.340
he asked.

01:45:02.399 --> 01:45:05.579
The ones you were not following?

01:45:05.640 --> 01:45:06.899
She nodded.

01:45:06.960 --> 01:45:07.920
Why?

01:45:07.979 --> 01:45:11.340
Sonny had a pretty strong feeling that it

01:45:11.340 --> 01:45:13.199
wouldn't be wise to reveal her connection

01:45:13.199 --> 01:45:15.779
to the prophecy, even if the outlaws

01:45:15.779 --> 01:45:17.520
didn't immediately sell her to burn.

01:45:17.579 --> 01:45:19.920
Someone else in the scorpion den was sure

01:45:19.920 --> 01:45:21.180
to pounce on that opportunity.

01:45:21.239 --> 01:45:24.600
They tried to kill me, she said.

01:45:24.659 --> 01:45:26.039
That was basically true.

01:45:26.100 --> 01:45:28.439
Six claws looked amused.

01:45:28.500 --> 01:45:31.319
Here's some free advice When a dragon

01:45:31.319 --> 01:45:34.140
tries to kill you, fly the opposite way.

01:45:34.199 --> 01:45:38.520
I am keeping an eye on them, she said

01:45:38.520 --> 01:45:39.119
bristling.

01:45:39.180 --> 01:45:41.039
I need to know what they're planning.

01:45:41.100 --> 01:45:43.260
That's up to Thorn now.

01:45:43.319 --> 01:45:44.279
He said.

01:45:44.340 --> 01:45:46.739
Come along and stay behind me.

01:45:46.800 --> 01:45:49.680
Sonny's heart thumped as they approached

01:45:49.680 --> 01:45:50.279
the tent.

01:45:50.340 --> 01:45:51.779
Should she try to run?

01:45:51.840 --> 01:45:55.020
Wasn't it possible, even likely?

01:45:55.079 --> 01:45:57.060
that Thorn and the Night Wings would team

01:45:57.060 --> 01:45:58.199
up to sell her to burn?

01:45:58.260 --> 01:46:00.420
Thorn was the leader of a gang of

01:46:00.420 --> 01:46:01.260
criminals after all.

01:46:01.319 --> 01:46:04.380
Sonny wouldn't get far in this city

01:46:04.380 --> 01:46:06.779
though, not with the outlaws after her.

01:46:06.840 --> 01:46:09.840
Even in a place full of sandwings, she'd

01:46:09.840 --> 01:46:11.699
stick out like a fire on a dark night.

01:46:11.760 --> 01:46:14.100
She tried to keep the memory of the

01:46:14.100 --> 01:46:16.439
hungry dragonette in her head as she

01:46:16.439 --> 01:46:18.479
ducked under the soft white flap of the

01:46:18.479 --> 01:46:18.720
tent.

01:46:18.840 --> 01:46:21.420
A leader of criminals who fed small

01:46:21.420 --> 01:46:22.979
dragons didn't sound so bad.

01:46:23.039 --> 01:46:25.619
Maybe Thorn could be reasoned with.

01:46:25.680 --> 01:46:29.100
The 3 night wings were seated in a row on

01:46:29.100 --> 01:46:31.439
a bright orange carpet, woven with

01:46:31.439 --> 01:46:33.359
alternating purple and white claw

01:46:33.359 --> 01:46:33.840
shapes.

01:46:33.899 --> 01:46:36.600
A skylight in the tent ceiling was

01:46:36.600 --> 01:46:38.279
positioned to shine a ray of sunlight

01:46:38.279 --> 01:46:40.920
down on them, beaming bright and hot

01:46:40.920 --> 01:46:42.119
straight into their faces.

01:46:42.180 --> 01:46:45.300
Sunny had a feeling that was deliberate.

01:46:45.359 --> 01:46:48.000
They were surrounded on all sides by sand

01:46:48.000 --> 01:46:48.539
wings.

01:46:48.600 --> 01:46:51.359
Many of them rippling with scars or

01:46:51.359 --> 01:46:53.640
missing teeth, as if they had fought hard

01:46:53.640 --> 01:46:55.739
for a place in this tent, and weren't

01:46:55.739 --> 01:46:57.000
planning to move anytime soon.

01:46:57.060 --> 01:47:00.779
The only clear spot was at the far end of

01:47:00.779 --> 01:47:03.539
the tent, where a pile of woven sky blue

01:47:03.539 --> 01:47:05.220
rugs was arranged on a dais.

01:47:05.340 --> 01:47:07.979
After a few moments, the sound of

01:47:07.979 --> 01:47:10.619
laughter came from outside, and 5 more

01:47:10.619 --> 01:47:12.479
sand wings pushed their way into the

01:47:12.479 --> 01:47:12.720
tent.

01:47:12.779 --> 01:47:15.960
Sunny could tell which one was thorn

01:47:15.960 --> 01:47:16.500
immediately.

01:47:16.560 --> 01:47:19.739
Although she was smaller than the others

01:47:19.739 --> 01:47:21.180
and she wasn't wearing more treasure than

01:47:21.180 --> 01:47:21.720
anybody else.

01:47:21.779 --> 01:47:25.020
A solitary gold bracelet circled one of

01:47:25.020 --> 01:47:27.659
her upper forearms, a chain of flying

01:47:27.659 --> 01:47:29.579
dragons made from twisted wires.

01:47:29.640 --> 01:47:32.579
Around her neck, hung a simple copper

01:47:32.579 --> 01:47:35.520
chain with a moonstone pendant, an odd

01:47:35.520 --> 01:47:37.319
jewel to find in the desert, Sonny

01:47:37.319 --> 01:47:37.560
thought.

01:47:37.619 --> 01:47:41.279
Her scales were sandy yellow, and dappled

01:47:41.279 --> 01:47:43.260
with a pattern of small brown speckles

01:47:43.260 --> 01:47:45.060
down her back and along her wings.

01:47:45.119 --> 01:47:48.659
She looked young, probably barely 20

01:47:48.659 --> 01:47:50.520
years old if Sonny had to guess.

01:47:50.640 --> 01:47:53.579
Most dragons grew quickly for the 1st 7

01:47:53.579 --> 01:47:55.920
years of their lives, and then a little

01:47:55.920 --> 01:47:57.060
bit each year after that.

01:47:57.119 --> 01:47:59.939
So the oldest dragons were usually the

01:47:59.939 --> 01:48:03.239
largest, like Marosier, and Byrne, and

01:48:03.239 --> 01:48:03.899
Grandeur.

01:48:03.960 --> 01:48:07.260
But Thorn was wiry and compact, and

01:48:07.260 --> 01:48:09.000
looked as if she might stay that way no

01:48:09.000 --> 01:48:10.079
matter how long she lived.

01:48:10.140 --> 01:48:13.319
What was it that made her seem so clearly

01:48:13.319 --> 01:48:14.279
the leader of this group?

01:48:14.340 --> 01:48:16.920
She was laughing with the others as they

01:48:16.920 --> 01:48:19.079
came in, but she walked a step ahead of

01:48:19.079 --> 01:48:21.659
them, her wings half open and tilted

01:48:21.659 --> 01:48:23.760
forward, as if she had somewhere to be

01:48:23.760 --> 01:48:26.520
and her eyes scanning the room as if she

01:48:26.520 --> 01:48:27.420
were searching for something.

01:48:27.479 --> 01:48:30.420
She radiated an intense energy.

01:48:30.479 --> 01:48:32.939
Even Sonny caught herself wanting to

01:48:32.939 --> 01:48:34.500
follow her wherever she went next.

01:48:34.560 --> 01:48:37.739
The laughter dropped from Thorn's eyes

01:48:37.739 --> 01:48:40.199
when she spotted the 3 night wings.

01:48:40.260 --> 01:48:42.539
She curled her tail up threateningly

01:48:42.539 --> 01:48:45.180
before stalking around them and climbing

01:48:45.180 --> 01:48:45.899
onto the dais.

01:48:45.960 --> 01:48:48.479
Sonny was glad not to be the one under

01:48:48.479 --> 01:48:49.079
that glare.

01:48:49.199 --> 01:48:51.600
Night wings.

01:48:51.659 --> 01:48:53.399
Thorn said darkly.

01:48:53.460 --> 01:48:55.140
Well, well, well.

01:48:55.199 --> 01:48:57.720
We haven't had any of you visit our find

01:48:57.720 --> 01:48:59.579
sitting about 7 years.

01:48:59.640 --> 01:49:01.079
Why would we?

01:49:01.140 --> 01:49:02.939
Fierce teeth challenge.

01:49:03.000 --> 01:49:05.039
We're only here now because we want to

01:49:05.039 --> 01:49:06.119
make a deal with burn.

01:49:06.180 --> 01:49:09.960
We need someone to take her a message.

01:49:10.020 --> 01:49:11.640
Strong wings added.

01:49:11.699 --> 01:49:13.439
Thorn leaned forward.

01:49:13.500 --> 01:49:15.659
That's irrelevant to me.

01:49:15.720 --> 01:49:17.760
Where is Morrow Seer?

01:49:17.819 --> 01:49:20.279
All 3 night wings looked startled.

01:49:20.399 --> 01:49:23.159
You know, Morris, here?

01:49:23.279 --> 01:49:24.420
Prey Hunter stammered.

01:49:24.539 --> 01:49:28.260
Unfortunately, Thorn growled.

01:49:28.319 --> 01:49:31.020
Tell me where he is, and I'll seriously

01:49:31.020 --> 01:49:32.760
consider not killing you.

01:49:32.880 --> 01:49:36.180
Prey Hunter flared his wings, and several

01:49:36.180 --> 01:49:38.399
outlaws took a menacing step toward him.

01:49:38.460 --> 01:49:41.520
You can't kill us, he protested.

01:49:41.579 --> 01:49:42.840
We're night wings.

01:49:42.899 --> 01:49:46.739
I assure you, Night Wings died just as

01:49:46.739 --> 01:49:49.680
easily as any other dragon, Thorn said.

01:49:49.739 --> 01:49:51.659
Would you like a demonstration?

01:49:51.720 --> 01:49:55.859
No, no, no, Strongwing said hurriedly.

01:49:55.920 --> 01:49:57.479
We'll tell you what we know.

01:49:57.539 --> 01:50:00.779
In exchange for a messenger to burn.

01:50:00.840 --> 01:50:02.220
Fierce teeth interjected.

01:50:02.279 --> 01:50:05.100
In exchange for your lives.

01:50:05.220 --> 01:50:07.260
Thorn countered calmly.

01:50:07.319 --> 01:50:10.079
I'm not sending any of my outlaws into

01:50:10.079 --> 01:50:10.920
that death pit.

01:50:10.979 --> 01:50:13.199
Most of them are here expressly because

01:50:13.199 --> 01:50:14.520
they're trying to avoid her.

01:50:14.579 --> 01:50:17.460
But, Pierce Teeth started.

01:50:17.579 --> 01:50:19.560
Morris Sears did.

01:50:19.619 --> 01:50:21.300
Prey Hunter blurted out.

01:50:21.359 --> 01:50:23.460
He died just a few days ago.

01:50:23.520 --> 01:50:25.800
There was a terrible silence.

01:50:25.859 --> 01:50:28.439
One of the dragons who'd come in last

01:50:28.439 --> 01:50:31.319
took a step toward Thorn, reaching out

01:50:31.319 --> 01:50:33.779
tentatively, her expression a surprising

01:50:33.779 --> 01:50:35.579
mix of horror and sympathy.

01:50:35.640 --> 01:50:39.420
Thorn's face contorted into a fury, like

01:50:39.420 --> 01:50:41.039
nothing Sonny had ever seen before.

01:50:41.100 --> 01:50:44.640
With a cry of rage, she leaped off the

01:50:44.640 --> 01:50:47.220
dais, seized prey hunter by the throat

01:50:47.220 --> 01:50:49.500
and flung him to the ground, where she

01:50:49.500 --> 01:50:51.659
pinned him with her claws, and swung her

01:50:51.659 --> 01:50:52.560
tail over his heart.

01:50:52.680 --> 01:50:56.340
Fierce teeth and strong wings didn't have

01:50:56.340 --> 01:50:58.739
time to react before outlaws were there

01:50:58.739 --> 01:50:59.520
holding them back.

01:50:59.579 --> 01:51:01.439
It wasn't necessary, though.

01:51:01.500 --> 01:51:03.420
Sonny could see that they were too

01:51:03.420 --> 01:51:05.159
terrified to do anything to help Prey

01:51:05.159 --> 01:51:05.579
Hunter.

01:51:05.640 --> 01:51:07.979
Say that again.

01:51:08.039 --> 01:51:10.619
Thorn hissed in Prey Hunter's face.

01:51:10.680 --> 01:51:12.539
He's dead.

01:51:12.600 --> 01:51:14.159
Prey Hunter stammered.

01:51:14.220 --> 01:51:15.479
Isn't that good news?

01:51:15.539 --> 01:51:17.819
It sounded like you hated him.

01:51:17.880 --> 01:51:18.960
Aren't you glad he's dead?

01:51:19.020 --> 01:51:22.739
He can't be dead, Thorn said.

01:51:22.800 --> 01:51:25.619
Tell me the truth, you lying bag of

01:51:25.619 --> 01:51:25.979
bones.

01:51:26.039 --> 01:51:28.439
Tell me how to get to your secret home

01:51:28.439 --> 01:51:31.380
and where Marosir is, and what he did

01:51:31.380 --> 01:51:31.920
to...

01:51:32.159 --> 01:51:34.199
She cut herself off abruptly.

01:51:34.260 --> 01:51:38.220
I can't tell you any of that, Prey Hunter

01:51:38.220 --> 01:51:38.699
whined.

01:51:38.760 --> 01:51:41.579
We're not allowed to, but I promise you

01:51:41.579 --> 01:51:42.960
Morris here is dead.

01:51:43.020 --> 01:51:45.420
Really, really, really did.

01:51:45.539 --> 01:51:47.039
No.

01:51:47.159 --> 01:51:48.720
Thorn shouted.

01:51:48.779 --> 01:51:51.479
A burst of flame shot out of her mouth

01:51:51.479 --> 01:51:53.819
scorching a spot beside Prey Hunter's

01:51:53.819 --> 01:51:54.000
neck.

01:51:54.119 --> 01:51:57.600
He screamed with fear, and 2 outlaws

01:51:57.600 --> 01:51:59.640
jumped forward to beat out the flames on

01:51:59.640 --> 01:52:01.739
the carpet before the fire reached the

01:52:01.739 --> 01:52:02.159
tent.

01:52:02.279 --> 01:52:05.340
At the same moment, Prey Hunter convulsed

01:52:05.340 --> 01:52:07.800
and lashed out, slicing at Thorn's

01:52:07.800 --> 01:52:09.180
underbelly with his sharp talons.

01:52:09.239 --> 01:52:12.779
Moon's blasted crocodile spawn.

01:52:12.840 --> 01:52:16.020
Six claws roared, knocking dragons aside

01:52:16.020 --> 01:52:17.340
as he leaped at Prey Hunter.

01:52:17.399 --> 01:52:20.340
Another sandwing, a male dragonette

01:52:20.340 --> 01:52:23.100
around Sunny's age, also darted forward

01:52:23.100 --> 01:52:25.079
from the other side, but they weren't

01:52:25.079 --> 01:52:25.439
fast enough.

01:52:25.500 --> 01:52:28.619
Thorn's tail stabbed down into the night

01:52:28.619 --> 01:52:31.199
wing's heart, and with a shriek of pain

01:52:31.199 --> 01:52:33.239
Prey Hunter collapsed underneath her

01:52:33.239 --> 01:52:34.380
dead.

01:52:34.380 --> 01:52:38.699
Chapter 7.

01:52:38.760 --> 01:52:42.060
Sonny stared at the night wing's body.

01:52:42.119 --> 01:52:44.399
His wings lying crookedly on either side

01:52:44.399 --> 01:52:46.979
of him, his snout contorted into a final

01:52:46.979 --> 01:52:48.119
twist of despair.

01:52:48.180 --> 01:52:52.140
He was a bad dragon, she told herself.

01:52:52.199 --> 01:52:54.359
The world is better off this way.

01:52:54.420 --> 01:52:57.600
My friends are safer now that he's dead.

01:52:57.659 --> 01:52:59.579
But he had a horrible life.

01:52:59.640 --> 01:53:01.739
The other half of her argued.

01:53:01.800 --> 01:53:03.600
Maybe he could have changed.

01:53:03.659 --> 01:53:06.479
Maybe there was a better dragon inside

01:53:06.479 --> 01:53:08.880
him somewhere, if someone had bothered to

01:53:08.880 --> 01:53:09.720
try and bring it out.

01:53:09.779 --> 01:53:13.199
Thorn stepped away from the body, taking

01:53:13.199 --> 01:53:13.859
a deep breath.

01:53:13.920 --> 01:53:17.100
Six claws put one talon on her shoulder

01:53:17.100 --> 01:53:19.979
and she gave him a rueful look, as if she

01:53:19.979 --> 01:53:21.539
hadn't wanted to kill prey hunter after

01:53:21.539 --> 01:53:21.720
all.

01:53:21.779 --> 01:53:25.439
She might not have, if he hadn't lashed

01:53:25.439 --> 01:53:27.420
out at her, or maybe she had to.

01:53:27.479 --> 01:53:30.119
Either way, to make sure the other night

01:53:30.119 --> 01:53:33.300
wings know how serious, and dangerous she

01:53:33.300 --> 01:53:33.539
is.

01:53:33.600 --> 01:53:36.060
It's all right, Gibli.

01:53:36.119 --> 01:53:36.899
Thank you.

01:53:36.960 --> 01:53:39.659
Thorn said to the dragonette who'd run

01:53:39.659 --> 01:53:40.319
forward to help her.

01:53:40.380 --> 01:53:42.539
He stood on the other side of the body

01:53:42.539 --> 01:53:44.760
looking as though he'd very much like to

01:53:44.760 --> 01:53:46.199
stab it again, just to be sure.

01:53:46.260 --> 01:53:51.119
Let's try this again, Thorn said.

01:53:51.239 --> 01:53:53.699
Turning to fierce teeth and strong wings

01:53:53.699 --> 01:53:56.220
the 2 black dragons had their heads down

01:53:56.220 --> 01:53:58.140
and their wings pressed in close to their

01:53:58.140 --> 01:53:59.100
bodies.

01:53:59.159 --> 01:54:01.619
Thorn stopped, eye to eye with fierce

01:54:01.619 --> 01:54:01.920
teeth.

01:54:02.039 --> 01:54:05.640
Tell me how to find Morosir.

01:54:05.760 --> 01:54:09.300
Fierce teeth hesitated, only for a moment

01:54:09.300 --> 01:54:11.699
then said, It's an island.

01:54:11.819 --> 01:54:15.239
Fierce teeth, strong wings hissed.

01:54:15.300 --> 01:54:16.619
What?

01:54:16.739 --> 01:54:17.939
She snapped at him.

01:54:18.000 --> 01:54:19.380
What does it matter anymore?

01:54:19.439 --> 01:54:20.699
It's all destroyed anyway.

01:54:20.760 --> 01:54:23.819
She returned her scowling gaze to Thorn.

01:54:23.880 --> 01:54:27.119
We lived on an island north of the

01:54:27.119 --> 01:54:29.100
continent, but the whole place was just

01:54:29.100 --> 01:54:30.359
wiped out by a volcano.

01:54:30.420 --> 01:54:32.520
Marosir was killed by it.

01:54:32.579 --> 01:54:35.880
That's the truth, so sorry if you don't

01:54:35.880 --> 01:54:36.180
like it.

01:54:36.239 --> 01:54:38.579
She lifted her chin defiantly.

01:54:38.640 --> 01:54:41.939
Thorn's claws twitched, and her eyes

01:54:41.939 --> 01:54:42.600
narrowed.

01:54:42.659 --> 01:54:46.739
I can't let Starflight's sister die, Sonny

01:54:46.739 --> 01:54:46.979
thought.

01:54:47.039 --> 01:54:50.100
No matter how terrible she is, not if I

01:54:50.100 --> 01:54:50.520
can stop it.

01:54:50.579 --> 01:54:53.880
She knew it was foolish to expose herself

01:54:53.880 --> 01:54:56.159
here, but it felt like clearly the right

01:54:56.159 --> 01:54:56.939
thing to do.

01:54:57.000 --> 01:54:59.100
That was what being in the prophecy was

01:54:59.100 --> 01:54:59.460
all about.

01:54:59.520 --> 01:55:02.100
And if she wanted to keep believing in it

01:55:02.100 --> 01:55:04.380
she had to keep acting worthy of it.

01:55:04.439 --> 01:55:07.079
It's true, she called.

01:55:07.140 --> 01:55:09.479
She pushed her way through the sand wings

01:55:09.479 --> 01:55:10.979
who blinked at her in confusion.

01:55:11.039 --> 01:55:12.539
It's true.

01:55:12.659 --> 01:55:13.739
Don't hurt her.

01:55:13.800 --> 01:55:16.380
She stumbled onto the sand in front of

01:55:16.380 --> 01:55:18.659
Thorn, half a wingspan from the night

01:55:18.659 --> 01:55:20.100
wings who'd tried to kill her.

01:55:20.159 --> 01:55:21.720
You!

01:55:21.779 --> 01:55:23.159
Fierce teeth cried.

01:55:23.220 --> 01:55:26.340
I was there, on the Nightwing Island

01:55:26.340 --> 01:55:28.260
Sonny said, ignoring her.

01:55:28.319 --> 01:55:31.020
Thorn's black eyes were pinning her to

01:55:31.020 --> 01:55:34.260
the sand, like an exotic insect, studying

01:55:34.260 --> 01:55:35.939
every bizarrely golden scale.

01:55:36.000 --> 01:55:39.359
There was a volcano, and it wiped out the

01:55:39.359 --> 01:55:41.640
night wings home, and killed Maro Seer.

01:55:41.699 --> 01:55:45.659
I'm sorry, she added, and she was

01:55:45.659 --> 01:55:47.399
although she wasn't quite sure why.

01:55:47.460 --> 01:55:49.260
Who?

01:55:49.319 --> 01:55:52.560
In the blazes, are you, Thorn asked.

01:55:52.619 --> 01:55:55.439
This is the one who was following them.

01:55:55.500 --> 01:55:58.739
Six claws said, nodding at the black

01:55:58.739 --> 01:55:59.340
dragons.

01:55:59.399 --> 01:56:02.520
Fierce teeth scowled, Strong wings just

01:56:02.520 --> 01:56:03.180
looked shocked.

01:56:03.300 --> 01:56:06.840
Ah, said Thorn, tilting her head.

01:56:06.899 --> 01:56:07.920
Really?

01:56:07.979 --> 01:56:11.460
So you're not here to see me about the

01:56:11.460 --> 01:56:11.939
reward.

01:56:12.000 --> 01:56:14.279
What reward?

01:56:14.340 --> 01:56:15.840
Sonny shook her head.

01:56:15.899 --> 01:56:18.060
I'm just trying to stop them before they

01:56:18.060 --> 01:56:21.180
hurt my friends, she said, and then added

01:56:21.180 --> 01:56:22.979
with a rush of hope, please don't let

01:56:22.979 --> 01:56:25.079
them send a messenger to burn, it'll put

01:56:25.079 --> 01:56:26.399
a lot of dragons in danger.

01:56:26.460 --> 01:56:28.260
Really?

01:56:28.319 --> 01:56:29.699
Thorn said.

01:56:29.819 --> 01:56:32.039
She twisted to look at the night wings.

01:56:32.100 --> 01:56:34.020
What do you have to say about that?

01:56:34.079 --> 01:56:38.100
We have information we know Bern will pay

01:56:38.100 --> 01:56:38.939
handsomely for.

01:56:39.000 --> 01:56:42.000
Strong Wing said, glaring at Sonny.

01:56:42.060 --> 01:56:43.199
Not only us.

01:56:43.260 --> 01:56:45.840
I'm sure she'll reward anyone who helps

01:56:45.840 --> 01:56:48.119
us get to her, and she'll pay even more

01:56:48.119 --> 01:56:50.220
if you throw in this puny dragonette.

01:56:50.279 --> 01:56:53.159
Thorn regarded Sonny skeptically.

01:56:53.220 --> 01:56:54.659
Why?

01:56:54.720 --> 01:56:57.539
Sonny shook her head, but of course that

01:56:57.539 --> 01:56:58.500
wasn't going to stop him.

01:56:58.560 --> 01:57:01.619
She's one of the dragonettes in the

01:57:01.619 --> 01:57:04.020
prophecy, he said triumphantly.

01:57:04.079 --> 01:57:07.260
Every dragon in the tent seemed to sit up

01:57:07.260 --> 01:57:07.560
at once.

01:57:07.619 --> 01:57:10.020
A few leaped to their feet and slipped

01:57:10.020 --> 01:57:11.100
out the front entrance.

01:57:11.159 --> 01:57:12.600
Sonny noticed uneasily.

01:57:12.659 --> 01:57:15.180
Most of the others started whispering to

01:57:15.180 --> 01:57:15.420
each other.

01:57:15.479 --> 01:57:18.779
She caught snippets like, why so small?

01:57:18.899 --> 01:57:21.180
And that's why that soldier?

01:57:21.239 --> 01:57:26.460
And, but her tail, and, no wonder, burn.

01:57:26.520 --> 01:57:29.340
One dragon, with a missing eye shifted

01:57:29.340 --> 01:57:31.739
closer to peer at her, and Sonny tucked

01:57:31.739 --> 01:57:33.479
her tail closer around her talons

01:57:33.479 --> 01:57:34.380
shivering.

01:57:34.439 --> 01:57:38.039
And we know where the others are.

01:57:38.159 --> 01:57:39.720
Strong wings went on.

01:57:39.840 --> 01:57:42.840
Fierce teeth smacked him in a snout with

01:57:42.840 --> 01:57:43.260
her tail.

01:57:43.380 --> 01:57:45.659
Shut up, she snarled.

01:57:45.720 --> 01:57:48.300
All of Thorn's burning energy was now

01:57:48.300 --> 01:57:49.500
fixed on Sonny.

01:57:49.560 --> 01:57:52.560
She took a step closer, then circled

01:57:52.560 --> 01:57:53.880
Sonny, inspecting her.

01:57:53.939 --> 01:57:57.300
Sonny tried to look brave and calm, even

01:57:57.300 --> 01:57:59.699
as Thorn picked up her harmless tail and

01:57:59.699 --> 01:58:01.680
flipped it curiously between her claws.

01:58:01.739 --> 01:58:05.640
Hmm, said the leader of the outlaws.

01:58:05.760 --> 01:58:08.699
You're a little unusual.

01:58:08.760 --> 01:58:11.520
I know, Sonny said.

01:58:11.579 --> 01:58:12.779
It's all right, though.

01:58:12.840 --> 01:58:13.560
I don't mind.

01:58:13.619 --> 01:58:15.239
It's just the way I hatched.

01:58:15.300 --> 01:58:19.439
On the brightest night, Thorn said, 6

01:58:19.439 --> 01:58:20.159
years ago.

01:58:20.220 --> 01:58:23.340
It was not exactly a question, but Sonny

01:58:23.340 --> 01:58:24.180
answered it anyway.

01:58:24.239 --> 01:58:25.319
Yes.

01:58:25.380 --> 01:58:28.439
Thorn walked around Sunny one more time

01:58:28.439 --> 01:58:31.199
her talons sending up small clouds of

01:58:31.199 --> 01:58:33.779
sand between the gaps and the carpets, and

01:58:33.779 --> 01:58:36.119
then stopped beside her. frowning at the

01:58:36.119 --> 01:58:36.539
night wings.

01:58:36.600 --> 01:58:39.659
One more question for you cowardly

01:58:39.659 --> 01:58:40.079
lizards.

01:58:40.140 --> 01:58:42.180
Can you tell me anything about a night

01:58:42.180 --> 01:58:43.979
wing named Stone Mover?

01:58:44.100 --> 01:58:46.560
Strong Wings snorted.

01:58:46.680 --> 01:58:50.159
He took off 6 or 7 years ago, and no

01:58:50.159 --> 01:58:51.119
one's heard from him since.

01:58:51.180 --> 01:58:52.979
The queen was furious.

01:58:53.039 --> 01:58:57.180
This answer didn't seem to make Thorn any

01:58:57.180 --> 01:58:59.100
happier than anything else they'd said.

01:58:59.220 --> 01:59:02.460
She hissed quietly, then turned to 6

01:59:02.460 --> 01:59:02.880
claws.

01:59:02.939 --> 01:59:06.000
Put them somewhere unpleasant.

01:59:06.060 --> 01:59:07.079
She ordered.

01:59:07.140 --> 01:59:08.880
I'll decide what to do with them later.

01:59:08.939 --> 01:59:12.359
You, she said to Sonny, come with me.

01:59:12.420 --> 01:59:15.180
They left on a tide of murmuring

01:59:15.180 --> 01:59:15.840
dragons.

01:59:15.899 --> 01:59:18.180
Sonny felt the same way she had when she

01:59:18.180 --> 01:59:20.520
was in that cage in the Sky Palace, hung

01:59:20.520 --> 01:59:21.899
up for everyone to stare at.

01:59:22.020 --> 01:59:24.300
She stayed close to Thorn's tail.

01:59:24.359 --> 01:59:27.539
The back wall turned out to divide the

01:59:27.539 --> 01:59:29.699
tent in two, and when they ducked through

01:59:29.699 --> 01:59:32.159
a flap, Sonny found herself in a smaller

01:59:32.159 --> 01:59:34.619
area with fewer rugs, where there were a

01:59:34.619 --> 01:59:37.079
couple of low black tables, a trunk

01:59:37.079 --> 01:59:39.479
packed with scrolls, and 2 startling

01:59:39.479 --> 01:59:41.039
pictures pinned to the walls.

01:59:41.159 --> 01:59:44.100
Sonny gasped when she saw them.

01:59:44.159 --> 01:59:48.720
One was Maroser, drawn in dark ink

01:59:48.720 --> 01:59:50.579
glowering the way he always did.

01:59:50.640 --> 01:59:53.520
The paper was large and pockmarked with

01:59:53.520 --> 01:59:54.180
tiny holes.

01:59:54.239 --> 01:59:57.300
Like someone's been throwing rather sharp

01:59:57.300 --> 01:59:59.100
things at it, Sonny thought.

01:59:59.159 --> 02:00:01.680
The other picture was slightly smaller

02:00:01.680 --> 02:00:03.960
but had received the same treatment

02:00:03.960 --> 02:00:06.840
staring out at her, looking much younger

02:00:06.840 --> 02:00:09.239
than she remembered him, was Dune.

02:00:09.300 --> 02:00:12.479
Sonny touched the paper lightly with one

02:00:12.479 --> 02:00:12.840
claw.

02:00:12.960 --> 02:00:14.520
Wow.

02:00:14.579 --> 02:00:15.720
She said.

02:00:15.779 --> 02:00:19.319
He still has the scars, but he looks much

02:00:19.319 --> 02:00:19.680
healthier.

02:00:19.739 --> 02:00:22.140
This must be back when he was still

02:00:22.140 --> 02:00:24.180
getting the sun and heat of sandwing

02:00:24.180 --> 02:00:26.640
needs before he went into hiding under

02:00:26.640 --> 02:00:27.899
the mountain to take care of us.

02:00:27.960 --> 02:00:29.819
You know him?

02:00:29.880 --> 02:00:32.100
Thorn asked from behind one of the

02:00:32.100 --> 02:00:32.460
tables.

02:00:32.520 --> 02:00:35.220
She sounded casual, but there was

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:36.899
something ferociously intense in her

02:00:36.899 --> 02:00:37.140
eyes.

02:00:37.199 --> 02:00:40.439
Sonny wondered how much to admit, but

02:00:40.439 --> 02:00:42.479
before she had to answer, the flaps

02:00:42.479 --> 02:00:44.460
rustled, and the same dragonette from

02:00:44.460 --> 02:00:46.140
before shoved his way in.

02:00:46.199 --> 02:00:48.479
He was bigger than Sonny, but now that

02:00:48.479 --> 02:00:50.279
she could see him more clearly, she

02:00:50.279 --> 02:00:51.899
guessed he was perhaps a year younger.

02:00:51.960 --> 02:00:55.140
A dark amber earring glowed in one ear

02:00:55.140 --> 02:00:58.199
and a small rakish scar zigzagged across

02:00:58.199 --> 02:00:58.619
his nose.

02:00:58.680 --> 02:01:01.739
Kibley, thorn warned.

02:01:01.800 --> 02:01:03.239
This is a private discussion.

02:01:03.300 --> 02:01:05.699
I'm not leaving you alone with no

02:01:05.699 --> 02:01:08.520
stranger, Kibley said, shooting a look

02:01:08.520 --> 02:01:09.899
full of daggers, it's Sonny.

02:01:09.960 --> 02:01:11.939
All prophecy like or not.

02:01:12.000 --> 02:01:14.220
Thorn looked amused.

02:01:14.340 --> 02:01:17.399
Your loyalty is charming, but I think I

02:01:17.399 --> 02:01:18.899
can handle this dragonette as well as you

02:01:18.899 --> 02:01:19.079
can.

02:01:19.199 --> 02:01:22.979
It's better to have backup, he insisted.

02:01:23.039 --> 02:01:25.260
He twitched his tail forward to rest on

02:01:25.260 --> 02:01:26.220
the sand in front of him.

02:01:26.279 --> 02:01:28.500
I promise I'll be quiet.

02:01:28.560 --> 02:01:31.739
Well, that I do have to see.

02:01:31.800 --> 02:01:33.779
She said, rolling her eyes.

02:01:33.840 --> 02:01:36.060
All right, you.

02:01:36.119 --> 02:01:36.539
What was your name?

02:01:36.600 --> 02:01:38.159
Sonny.

02:01:38.220 --> 02:01:41.340
Thorn crossed to the trunk of scrolls

02:01:41.340 --> 02:01:44.579
which sat on another sky blue rug, wiping

02:01:44.579 --> 02:01:46.439
her front talons on the fabric to shake

02:01:46.439 --> 02:01:48.899
off the sand, Thorn leaned in and picked

02:01:48.899 --> 02:01:50.220
up a sheaf of loose pages.

02:01:50.340 --> 02:01:53.220
Sunny, she echoed.

02:01:53.279 --> 02:01:54.899
Before you say anything else.

02:01:54.960 --> 02:01:56.939
You're really not here for the reward?

02:01:57.060 --> 02:01:59.699
I don't know anything about a reward

02:01:59.699 --> 02:02:01.020
Sonny promised.

02:02:01.079 --> 02:02:03.180
Kibley made a scornful noise.

02:02:03.239 --> 02:02:05.880
Without commenting, Thorn handed her one

02:02:05.880 --> 02:02:06.659
of the pages.

02:02:06.779 --> 02:02:09.000
The thick, yellowish paper crinkled

02:02:09.000 --> 02:02:10.619
stiffly between her claws.

02:02:10.680 --> 02:02:13.560
Reward, reward, reward.

02:02:13.619 --> 02:02:16.739
For any information leading to the

02:02:16.739 --> 02:02:19.199
whereabouts of 2 night wings, once seen

02:02:19.199 --> 02:02:21.359
around the Scorpion Den, known as

02:02:21.359 --> 02:02:23.579
Marosier and Stone Mover.

02:02:23.640 --> 02:02:26.399
For any information regarding the present

02:02:26.399 --> 02:02:28.800
location of a scarred sand wing named

02:02:28.800 --> 02:02:31.560
Dune, last seen frequenting the night

02:02:31.560 --> 02:02:32.640
market 7 years ago.

02:02:32.699 --> 02:02:36.300
For any dragonette hatched in the last 6

02:02:36.300 --> 02:02:38.159
years with unusual features.

02:02:38.220 --> 02:02:41.100
Come before Thorn at the Outlaw pool with

02:02:41.100 --> 02:02:43.079
anything, your safety guaranteed.

02:02:43.199 --> 02:02:46.380
Reward, reward, reward.

02:02:46.439 --> 02:02:49.739
Smaller drawings of Marosir and Dune

02:02:49.739 --> 02:02:51.960
accompanied the words, along with another

02:02:51.960 --> 02:02:54.239
drawing of a subdued looking night wing

02:02:54.239 --> 02:02:55.739
she guessed was stone mover.

02:02:55.800 --> 02:02:58.140
She glanced at the other papers that

02:02:58.140 --> 02:03:00.119
Thorn was holding, and saw similar

02:03:00.119 --> 02:03:02.039
pronouncements with slightly different

02:03:02.039 --> 02:03:05.939
words, 5 years ago, or, in the last 3

02:03:05.939 --> 02:03:08.760
years, for instance, this wasn't a new

02:03:08.760 --> 02:03:10.319
search or a new reward.

02:03:10.380 --> 02:03:13.140
This was the latest update of an ongoing

02:03:13.140 --> 02:03:13.439
hunt.

02:03:13.500 --> 02:03:16.199
Sonny put the paper down slowly.

02:03:16.260 --> 02:03:18.720
Pieces were starting to come together in

02:03:18.720 --> 02:03:21.960
her mind. bubbling in a funny, hopeful

02:03:21.960 --> 02:03:22.619
confused way.

02:03:22.680 --> 02:03:24.840
You didn't know about this?

02:03:24.899 --> 02:03:26.279
Thorn asked.

02:03:26.340 --> 02:03:27.720
Sunny shook her head.

02:03:27.779 --> 02:03:30.840
I haven't been in the kingdom of sand in

02:03:30.840 --> 02:03:31.680
the last 6 years.

02:03:31.739 --> 02:03:35.100
She took a deep breath, then let it all

02:03:35.100 --> 02:03:35.880
spill out of her.

02:03:36.000 --> 02:03:39.239
My egg was found out in the desert, alone

02:03:39.239 --> 02:03:41.520
by a dragon named Dune.

02:03:41.579 --> 02:03:43.380
That dragon.

02:03:43.439 --> 02:03:46.140
She pointed to the picture on the wall as

02:03:46.140 --> 02:03:47.520
Thorn inhaled sharply.

02:03:47.579 --> 02:03:50.699
He took me to be raised by the talons of

02:03:50.699 --> 02:03:52.920
peace, along with the other dragonets of

02:03:52.920 --> 02:03:53.340
destiny.

02:03:53.399 --> 02:03:56.279
After all, I fit the prophecy.

02:03:56.399 --> 02:04:00.119
She hesitated, then added, and my parents

02:04:00.119 --> 02:04:01.199
clearly didn't want me.

02:04:01.260 --> 02:04:04.260
She raised her head and met Thorn's

02:04:04.260 --> 02:04:04.560
eyes.

02:04:04.619 --> 02:04:07.140
The leader of the out claws dropped the

02:04:07.140 --> 02:04:09.779
rest of the papers, stepped forward and

02:04:09.779 --> 02:04:11.880
seized Sonny's front talons in hers.

02:04:11.939 --> 02:04:15.539
He didn't find you, she growled.

02:04:15.600 --> 02:04:16.619
He stole you.

02:04:16.680 --> 02:04:18.840
He knew where I'd hidden you for your own

02:04:18.840 --> 02:04:21.180
safety, and he betrayed me.

02:04:21.239 --> 02:04:23.399
Sonny felt as though she couldn't

02:04:23.399 --> 02:04:23.760
breathe.

02:04:23.819 --> 02:04:27.180
The claws wrapped around hers, the dark

02:04:27.180 --> 02:04:28.380
eyes fixed on her.

02:04:28.380 --> 02:04:30.720
These were the only real things in the

02:04:30.720 --> 02:04:31.079
tent.

02:04:31.140 --> 02:04:33.659
Everything else was blurring and sliding

02:04:33.659 --> 02:04:33.960
away.

02:04:34.020 --> 02:04:35.760
This is it.

02:04:35.880 --> 02:04:37.439
She thought wonderingly.

02:04:37.560 --> 02:04:40.380
This is the moment we all dreamed about.

02:04:40.439 --> 02:04:42.479
All those years under the mountain.

02:04:42.539 --> 02:04:46.140
I wanted you, Thorn said fiercely.

02:04:46.199 --> 02:04:48.239
You were the only thing I wanted.

02:04:48.300 --> 02:04:50.399
I've done everything I could to find

02:04:50.399 --> 02:04:50.640
you.

02:04:50.699 --> 02:04:54.960
Not fulfilling the prophecy, but finding

02:04:54.960 --> 02:04:55.800
our parents.

02:04:55.920 --> 02:04:58.380
Thorn gripped her claws tighter.

02:04:58.439 --> 02:05:01.739
Sunny, you're my daughter.

02:05:01.800 --> 02:05:06.000
Chapter 8.

02:05:06.060 --> 02:05:10.079
Sunny Scales felt as if they were fizzing

02:05:10.079 --> 02:05:11.939
and humming and trying to leap right off

02:05:11.939 --> 02:05:12.180
her.

02:05:12.239 --> 02:05:15.000
She flung herself into Thorn's wings

02:05:15.000 --> 02:05:17.220
which folded around her like sunbeams.

02:05:17.279 --> 02:05:20.640
Hey, Kibley barked, jumping up.

02:05:20.699 --> 02:05:22.319
It's all right.

02:05:22.380 --> 02:05:24.479
Sit down, Thorn said.

02:05:24.539 --> 02:05:27.300
She rested her head on top of Sonny's and

02:05:27.300 --> 02:05:28.319
pulled her in more tightly.

02:05:28.380 --> 02:05:32.039
I knew you didn't really abandon me, Sonny

02:05:32.039 --> 02:05:34.199
said, although she wasn't sure how much

02:05:34.199 --> 02:05:35.460
she'd ever really known that.

02:05:35.520 --> 02:05:39.720
I knew I'd find you one day, said Thorn.

02:05:39.779 --> 02:05:41.640
I didn't take over this city for

02:05:41.640 --> 02:05:42.000
nothing.

02:05:42.060 --> 02:05:44.579
Never thought you'd just come strolling

02:05:44.579 --> 02:05:46.979
into my tent, though, chasing a trio of

02:05:46.979 --> 02:05:47.880
night wings, no less.

02:05:47.939 --> 02:05:50.039
She leaned back and smiled.

02:05:50.100 --> 02:05:52.319
Funny, brave little dragon.

02:05:52.380 --> 02:05:56.819
It was warm, warm, warm here in her

02:05:56.819 --> 02:05:59.340
mother's wings, as warm as Sonny had

02:05:59.340 --> 02:06:00.479
always wanted to be.

02:06:01.079 --> 02:06:03.720
Hang on, Kibley interjected.

02:06:03.779 --> 02:06:06.779
Thorn, begging your pardon, but how do

02:06:06.779 --> 02:06:07.140
you know?

02:06:07.140 --> 02:06:08.699
She could be anybody.

02:06:08.760 --> 02:06:09.899
She could be playing you.

02:06:09.960 --> 02:06:11.579
She could be a con artist.

02:06:11.640 --> 02:06:14.819
I've met enough con artists in the last 6

02:06:14.819 --> 02:06:18.180
years, Thorn said calmly, swaggering in

02:06:18.180 --> 02:06:19.859
here, hoping to cheat me out of the

02:06:19.859 --> 02:06:20.340
reward.

02:06:20.460 --> 02:06:22.199
This is my daughter.

02:06:22.260 --> 02:06:24.420
Where's my father?

02:06:24.479 --> 02:06:25.619
Sonny asked.

02:06:25.680 --> 02:06:28.979
It's, It's not Dune, is it?

02:06:29.039 --> 02:06:33.420
Bright smashing suns, no, Thorn said.

02:06:33.479 --> 02:06:35.579
What a horrifying thought.

02:06:35.640 --> 02:06:35.760
No.

02:06:35.880 --> 02:06:37.979
She shot a glance at Kibley.

02:06:38.039 --> 02:06:40.560
He's not around anymore.

02:06:40.619 --> 02:06:42.779
We can talk about that later.

02:06:42.840 --> 02:06:46.079
But speaking of Dune, if you can point me

02:06:46.079 --> 02:06:46.439
Adam.

02:06:46.500 --> 02:06:48.479
He's on this needs to be violently

02:06:48.479 --> 02:06:49.979
dismembered list I have.

02:06:50.039 --> 02:06:53.100
He's already dead, Sonny said.

02:06:53.159 --> 02:06:55.260
But he wasn't so bad, really.

02:06:55.319 --> 02:06:57.600
He died trying to protect us.

02:06:57.720 --> 02:06:59.520
Successfully?

02:06:59.579 --> 02:07:00.600
Thorn asked.

02:07:00.659 --> 02:07:05.220
Well, not very successfully, Sonny

02:07:05.220 --> 02:07:07.920
admitted, we kind of all got captured by

02:07:07.920 --> 02:07:09.960
the Sky Wing Queen, but we're all right

02:07:09.960 --> 02:07:10.199
now.

02:07:10.260 --> 02:07:12.300
Thorn growled.

02:07:12.359 --> 02:07:14.340
Teeth of the Viper.

02:07:14.399 --> 02:07:16.859
I cannot believe my enemies have all died

02:07:16.859 --> 02:07:18.720
before I could rip their heads off

02:07:18.720 --> 02:07:19.199
myself.

02:07:19.260 --> 02:07:21.659
Kibli, give me those drawings.

02:07:21.720 --> 02:07:24.600
The dragonette unpinned the drawings of

02:07:24.600 --> 02:07:27.479
Marosir and Dune from the wall, and Thorn

02:07:27.479 --> 02:07:30.000
kept one wing around Sonny as she tore

02:07:30.000 --> 02:07:31.199
them into tiny shreds.

02:07:31.319 --> 02:07:33.180
Feel better?

02:07:33.239 --> 02:07:33.899
Sunny asked.

02:07:33.960 --> 02:07:37.380
Yes, Thorn said, hugging her close

02:07:37.380 --> 02:07:37.680
again.

02:07:37.739 --> 02:07:40.079
Would you like me to have those night

02:07:40.079 --> 02:07:41.100
wings killed for you?

02:07:41.220 --> 02:07:44.579
No, no, Sonny said quickly.

02:07:44.640 --> 02:07:47.279
One of them is the sister of a friend of

02:07:47.279 --> 02:07:47.520
mine.

02:07:47.579 --> 02:07:49.140
She hesitated.

02:07:49.199 --> 02:07:51.720
I kind of wish you hadn't killed the

02:07:51.720 --> 02:07:52.380
other one.

02:07:52.439 --> 02:07:54.659
I know, Thorn said.

02:07:54.779 --> 02:07:57.359
She lifted her talons, checking them for

02:07:57.359 --> 02:07:57.539
blood.

02:07:57.659 --> 02:08:00.840
It's not my favorite part of the role, but

02:08:00.840 --> 02:08:02.159
if you want to lead dragons.

02:08:02.220 --> 02:08:03.779
You have to show them your claws

02:08:03.779 --> 02:08:04.680
sometimes, Beetle.

02:08:04.739 --> 02:08:06.600
Beetle?

02:08:06.720 --> 02:08:07.800
Sonny echoed.

02:08:07.859 --> 02:08:10.020
Thorn gave her an affectionate grin.

02:08:10.140 --> 02:08:12.479
That was my pet name for you when you

02:08:12.479 --> 02:08:14.340
were still in your egg, she said.

02:08:14.399 --> 02:08:16.560
That's what I've been calling you in my

02:08:16.560 --> 02:08:17.399
head all these years.

02:08:17.460 --> 02:08:19.560
But I like Sonny.

02:08:19.619 --> 02:08:21.779
Dune must have been paying attention when

02:08:21.779 --> 02:08:23.399
I talked about possible names for you.

02:08:23.520 --> 02:08:25.439
Her face darkened.

02:08:25.560 --> 02:08:28.859
So you were friends, Sonny prompted.

02:08:28.920 --> 02:08:30.239
I thought so.

02:08:30.300 --> 02:08:32.819
Her mother looked up at the tent ceiling

02:08:32.819 --> 02:08:33.420
for a moment.

02:08:33.479 --> 02:08:35.100
Her eyes glittering.

02:08:35.159 --> 02:08:38.939
I have so many questions, Sonny said

02:08:38.939 --> 02:08:39.420
softly.

02:08:39.479 --> 02:08:42.300
How did you know I would look weird?

02:08:42.359 --> 02:08:44.520
Why did you have to hide my egg for

02:08:44.520 --> 02:08:44.880
safety?

02:08:44.939 --> 02:08:47.279
What do the night wings have to do with

02:08:47.279 --> 02:08:47.520
anything?

02:08:47.579 --> 02:08:50.819
So do I. said Thorn.

02:08:50.880 --> 02:08:52.380
I want to know everything about

02:08:52.380 --> 02:08:54.359
everything you've done for the last 6

02:08:54.359 --> 02:08:56.340
years, and we should celebrate.

02:08:56.399 --> 02:08:58.680
Let me send all my brigands about their

02:08:58.680 --> 02:09:01.199
duties, and I'll tell armadillo to plan a

02:09:01.199 --> 02:09:01.560
party.

02:09:01.619 --> 02:09:04.260
Free roasted lizards and camel milk for

02:09:04.260 --> 02:09:05.760
the whole scorpion den tonight.

02:09:05.819 --> 02:09:07.079
She grinned.

02:09:07.140 --> 02:09:09.659
Wait, Sonny said.

02:09:09.720 --> 02:09:10.920
I don't need a party.

02:09:10.979 --> 02:09:12.600
Perhaps not.

02:09:12.659 --> 02:09:15.779
But it'll accomplish 3 things, Thorn said

02:09:15.779 --> 02:09:16.859
briskly.

02:09:16.920 --> 02:09:18.659
First, it'll relieve the tension out

02:09:18.659 --> 02:09:18.840
there.

02:09:18.899 --> 02:09:21.479
All those dragons, wondering what'll

02:09:21.479 --> 02:09:23.399
happen with a prophecy dragonette in our

02:09:23.399 --> 02:09:23.699
midst.

02:09:23.760 --> 02:09:26.520
Second, it'll let everyone know you're my

02:09:26.520 --> 02:09:28.380
daughter, so they'll treat you with

02:09:28.380 --> 02:09:30.239
respect and not just curiosity.

02:09:30.359 --> 02:09:33.840
And third, it'll make it very clear that

02:09:33.840 --> 02:09:36.180
you're under outlaw protection, which

02:09:36.180 --> 02:09:37.260
you're going to need in this city.

02:09:37.319 --> 02:09:39.960
Oh, Sunny said.

02:09:40.020 --> 02:09:42.359
For a moment, she'd worried that her

02:09:42.359 --> 02:09:44.880
mother was like Blaze, just looking for

02:09:44.880 --> 02:09:45.960
any excuse for a party.

02:09:46.020 --> 02:09:48.600
It was reassuring to realize she had

02:09:48.600 --> 02:09:50.220
smart reasons for what she was doing.

02:09:50.279 --> 02:09:53.520
A commotion erupted in the main tent

02:09:53.520 --> 02:09:55.619
dragons yelling, something being knocked

02:09:55.619 --> 02:09:55.859
over.

02:09:55.920 --> 02:09:58.920
Thorn whirled around with her tail high

02:09:58.920 --> 02:10:01.500
alert for any danger, but when a sand

02:10:01.500 --> 02:10:03.359
wing burst through the flaps and threw

02:10:03.359 --> 02:10:05.640
himself at her feet, she relaxed and

02:10:05.640 --> 02:10:06.779
waved Kibley back.

02:10:06.840 --> 02:10:08.159
What is it?

02:10:08.220 --> 02:10:09.119
Thorn asked.

02:10:09.239 --> 02:10:12.779
Reports of a dragon bite viper, he

02:10:12.779 --> 02:10:13.380
gasped.

02:10:13.439 --> 02:10:14.819
Senior the orphanage.

02:10:14.880 --> 02:10:16.079
Are we sure?

02:10:16.140 --> 02:10:19.079
Thorn demanded, grabbing a long spear

02:10:19.079 --> 02:10:21.180
made of 3 strands of metal twisted

02:10:21.180 --> 02:10:23.460
together, and split into several sharp

02:10:23.460 --> 02:10:24.359
points at the end.

02:10:24.420 --> 02:10:27.180
Have any outlaws confirmed that it's

02:10:27.180 --> 02:10:27.539
really there?

02:10:27.600 --> 02:10:28.920
No.

02:10:28.979 --> 02:10:32.039
He said, panting, but someone panicked

02:10:32.039 --> 02:10:34.079
and set the nearest stalls on fire.

02:10:34.140 --> 02:10:36.659
The orphanage will go up in flames.

02:10:36.720 --> 02:10:38.340
If we don't put it out fast.

02:10:38.460 --> 02:10:40.859
And so will the rest of the city.

02:10:40.920 --> 02:10:42.060
Thorn said.

02:10:42.119 --> 02:10:43.560
Sonny, I'm sorry.

02:10:43.619 --> 02:10:44.939
I have to take care of this.

02:10:45.060 --> 02:10:48.180
Of course, Sonny said, jumping up.

02:10:48.239 --> 02:10:49.319
Can I help?

02:10:49.380 --> 02:10:50.100
What can I do?

02:10:50.220 --> 02:10:53.340
You can stay here safely, so I don't have

02:10:53.340 --> 02:10:53.819
to worry about you.

02:10:53.939 --> 02:10:55.199
Thorn said.

02:10:55.260 --> 02:10:58.319
Please, Dragon Bite Vipers are not to be

02:10:58.319 --> 02:10:58.920
trifled with.

02:10:58.979 --> 02:11:00.600
I'll be back as soon as I can.

02:11:00.659 --> 02:11:03.899
She snatched up a bag by the outer flap

02:11:03.899 --> 02:11:06.300
and ducked out of the tent, gone before

02:11:06.300 --> 02:11:07.859
the messenger could scramble to his feet

02:11:07.859 --> 02:11:08.460
and follow her.

02:11:08.520 --> 02:11:11.699
Sonny and Kibley stared at each other for

02:11:11.699 --> 02:11:12.539
a few long moments.

02:11:12.600 --> 02:11:14.939
Sonny wondered if she should be upset

02:11:14.939 --> 02:11:16.800
that her mother had brushed aside her

02:11:16.800 --> 02:11:17.460
offer of help.

02:11:17.520 --> 02:11:20.340
But honestly, she wasn't sure she'd have

02:11:20.340 --> 02:11:20.819
been much use.

02:11:20.880 --> 02:11:23.159
As the excitement of meeting her mother

02:11:23.159 --> 02:11:23.819
wore off.

02:11:23.880 --> 02:11:25.920
Her wings began to feel like heavy

02:11:25.920 --> 02:11:28.260
boulders, leaning against her sides.

02:11:28.319 --> 02:11:30.659
Her head was woozy from the strange

02:11:30.659 --> 02:11:33.119
smells and noises of the scorpion den.

02:11:33.180 --> 02:11:36.180
What's a dragon bite viper?

02:11:36.239 --> 02:11:37.560
Sonny finally asked.

02:11:37.680 --> 02:11:39.119
Really?

02:11:39.239 --> 02:11:40.380
Kibley said.

02:11:40.439 --> 02:11:42.300
It's the most dangerous thing in the

02:11:42.300 --> 02:11:45.420
desert, probably in all Eperia, but we

02:11:45.420 --> 02:11:46.800
get them more than most tribes.

02:11:46.859 --> 02:11:49.500
It's the only snake in the world that can

02:11:49.500 --> 02:11:50.399
kill a dragon.

02:11:50.460 --> 02:11:52.680
There's a snake that can do that?

02:11:52.800 --> 02:11:53.939
Sonny said.

02:11:54.000 --> 02:11:56.279
She shuddered from her horns to her

02:11:56.279 --> 02:11:56.939
wingtips.

02:11:57.000 --> 02:11:58.319
Creepy.

02:11:58.380 --> 02:12:00.899
He nodded, and she tilted her head at

02:12:00.899 --> 02:12:01.079
him.

02:12:01.199 --> 02:12:03.479
Is Thorn your mother too?

02:12:03.539 --> 02:12:04.260
she asked.

02:12:04.319 --> 02:12:07.680
Ha, he said, startled.

02:12:07.739 --> 02:12:10.199
He touched his snout self-consciously

02:12:10.199 --> 02:12:12.300
where a few brown speckles stood out

02:12:12.300 --> 02:12:14.579
against his light yellow scales, much

02:12:14.579 --> 02:12:18.060
like the ones all over thorn, moons, no.

02:12:18.119 --> 02:12:20.279
She saved me from my mother.

02:12:20.340 --> 02:12:23.399
Besides, the way I understand it, there's

02:12:23.399 --> 02:12:25.680
only ever been one egg for Thorn, and

02:12:25.680 --> 02:12:26.159
that's you.

02:12:26.220 --> 02:12:28.979
If you are who you say you are.

02:12:29.039 --> 02:12:30.600
Nobody else?

02:12:30.720 --> 02:12:31.680
Sonny asked.

02:12:31.739 --> 02:12:34.619
I don't have any brothers or sisters.

02:12:34.680 --> 02:12:36.420
He shook his head.

02:12:36.479 --> 02:12:37.739
You're better off.

02:12:37.800 --> 02:12:40.619
Mine are a pair of dumb snorting hippo

02:12:40.619 --> 02:12:42.479
heads, who'd rather stab me with their

02:12:42.479 --> 02:12:44.460
tails than share so much as a fig with

02:12:44.460 --> 02:12:44.640
me.

02:12:44.699 --> 02:12:47.640
Joke's on them, now that I'm an out

02:12:47.640 --> 02:12:48.239
claw.

02:12:48.359 --> 02:12:51.359
Kibli puffed his spines up and made a

02:12:51.359 --> 02:12:52.260
ferocious face.

02:12:52.319 --> 02:12:54.840
And you better not be messing with Thorn

02:12:54.840 --> 02:12:55.260
either.

02:12:55.319 --> 02:12:58.500
There's plenty of out claws lined up

02:12:58.500 --> 02:13:00.539
behind me, who'll make you sorry if you

02:13:00.539 --> 02:13:00.720
are.

02:13:00.779 --> 02:13:03.720
I wouldn't know how to mess with her

02:13:03.720 --> 02:13:04.680
Sonny said.

02:13:04.739 --> 02:13:05.939
I promise.

02:13:06.000 --> 02:13:07.319
I'm really very nice.

02:13:07.380 --> 02:13:10.920
Hmm, Kibley said, skeptically.

02:13:10.979 --> 02:13:14.100
There was a tan camel hair pillow next to

02:13:14.100 --> 02:13:16.020
one of the black tables that looked

02:13:16.020 --> 02:13:18.239
softer than anything Sonny had slept on

02:13:18.239 --> 02:13:21.119
in the last several days, and she hadn't

02:13:21.119 --> 02:13:23.520
slept much, waking up frequently to make

02:13:23.520 --> 02:13:25.380
sure the night wings hadn't flown onward

02:13:25.380 --> 02:13:25.800
without her.

02:13:25.800 --> 02:13:28.859
She curled up on the cool sand, and

02:13:28.859 --> 02:13:30.779
rested her head and front talons on the

02:13:30.779 --> 02:13:31.079
pillow.

02:13:31.199 --> 02:13:34.380
Kibley kept his dark eyes on her, his

02:13:34.380 --> 02:13:36.420
brow furrowed, as if he hadn't quite

02:13:36.420 --> 02:13:38.039
decided whether to trust her yet.

02:13:38.100 --> 02:13:41.939
So, what do the outlaws do?

02:13:41.939 --> 02:13:42.960
Sonny asked.

02:13:43.020 --> 02:13:45.960
He fluffed his wings, scattering sand in

02:13:45.960 --> 02:13:46.560
all directions.

02:13:46.619 --> 02:13:47.939
Everything.

02:13:48.000 --> 02:13:50.640
We keep the scorpion den from becoming a

02:13:50.640 --> 02:13:53.039
mess of blood and teeth, which it used to

02:13:53.039 --> 02:13:55.439
be, with everyone fighting all the time

02:13:55.439 --> 02:13:57.239
till we sorted them all out.

02:13:57.300 --> 02:14:00.420
And we make sure those what has too much

02:14:00.420 --> 02:14:02.640
are convinced to pass them along to them

02:14:02.640 --> 02:14:03.060
with nothing.

02:14:03.119 --> 02:14:05.640
And what do you do with the pool?

02:14:05.699 --> 02:14:08.039
Sonny was genuinely curious.

02:14:08.100 --> 02:14:10.920
But for some reason, Kibli's answers seem

02:14:10.920 --> 02:14:12.720
to be fading in and out.

02:14:12.779 --> 02:14:15.600
We're the boss of it, he explained

02:14:15.600 --> 02:14:16.199
proudly.

02:14:16.260 --> 02:14:18.960
That way, we can get water to all the

02:14:18.960 --> 02:14:21.000
little dragons and the sick dragons and

02:14:21.000 --> 02:14:23.159
the wounded from the war, when they're

02:14:23.159 --> 02:14:24.840
not too scared to come around and ask for

02:14:24.840 --> 02:14:25.380
it anyways.

02:14:25.439 --> 02:14:28.380
We can be very intimidating.

02:14:28.439 --> 02:14:31.619
He added, with a satisfied nod.

02:14:31.800 --> 02:14:32.880
Mm-hmm.

02:14:32.939 --> 02:14:35.760
Sonny said, her eyelids drooping.

02:14:35.819 --> 02:14:38.039
Are you falling asleep in the middle of

02:14:38.039 --> 02:14:39.600
my fascinating explanation?

02:14:39.659 --> 02:14:42.359
Kibley demanded, sounding outraged.

02:14:42.420 --> 02:14:46.260
No, Sonny mumbled, inaccurately.

02:14:46.319 --> 02:14:48.779
And if he said anything else, she didn't

02:14:48.779 --> 02:14:49.079
hear it.

02:14:49.140 --> 02:14:53.760
She woke up in darkness to the sounds of

02:14:53.760 --> 02:14:56.159
dragons roaring and carousing outside the

02:14:56.159 --> 02:14:59.760
tent, a small oil lamp, gleaming bronze

02:14:59.760 --> 02:15:02.819
was set beside her, and 6 claws sat

02:15:02.819 --> 02:15:05.159
beside it, chewing on something that had

02:15:05.159 --> 02:15:07.500
been skewered on a stick and burned to a

02:15:07.500 --> 02:15:07.859
crisp.

02:15:07.920 --> 02:15:10.619
He dipped his head to her as she sat up

02:15:10.619 --> 02:15:11.220
and yawned.

02:15:11.279 --> 02:15:13.739
Your mother said not to wake you.

02:15:13.800 --> 02:15:18.060
The shiver that sent down sunny spine. was

02:15:18.060 --> 02:15:19.920
both lovely and unsettling.

02:15:19.979 --> 02:15:21.899
My mother.

02:15:22.020 --> 02:15:23.640
You could have.

02:15:23.699 --> 02:15:25.619
I always feel like I'm missing something

02:15:25.619 --> 02:15:27.659
when I'm sleeping, Sonny said

02:15:27.659 --> 02:15:28.199
stretching.

02:15:28.260 --> 02:15:29.579
Where is she?

02:15:29.640 --> 02:15:32.399
Still trying to put out all the fires and

02:15:32.399 --> 02:15:33.300
restore order.

02:15:33.359 --> 02:15:35.939
He flipped one wing at the noises beyond

02:15:35.939 --> 02:15:37.199
the white billowing walls.

02:15:37.260 --> 02:15:39.300
There was something solid about his

02:15:39.300 --> 02:15:41.699
presence, as though of course he would be

02:15:41.699 --> 02:15:44.340
there, waiting patiently, whenever she

02:15:44.340 --> 02:15:45.239
woke up and needed him.

02:15:45.300 --> 02:15:47.819
Sunny could imagine that her mother would

02:15:47.819 --> 02:15:48.899
be able to rely on him.

02:15:48.960 --> 02:15:51.659
She wondered again if there was any

02:15:51.659 --> 02:15:52.979
chance he might be her father.

02:15:53.039 --> 02:15:57.300
Thorn had said, not around, but maybe

02:15:57.300 --> 02:16:00.180
that just meant not attached anymore.

02:16:00.239 --> 02:16:02.340
Or maybe there was a reason she was

02:16:02.340 --> 02:16:03.539
keeping it a secret from the other

02:16:03.539 --> 02:16:04.319
outlaws.

02:16:04.380 --> 02:16:07.979
Most significantly, knowing he had

02:16:07.979 --> 02:16:10.739
hatched with his unusual 6th clause, might

02:16:10.739 --> 02:16:12.720
be enough to make Thorn think Sonny would

02:16:12.720 --> 02:16:13.979
have something odd about her too.

02:16:14.039 --> 02:16:16.739
What happened with the Viper?

02:16:16.800 --> 02:16:17.819
Sonny asked.

02:16:17.880 --> 02:16:19.140
Is everyone all right?

02:16:19.199 --> 02:16:22.079
Six Claws stopped chewing and looked at

02:16:22.079 --> 02:16:22.319
her?

02:16:22.380 --> 02:16:25.439
We didn't find the Viper yet, but we've

02:16:25.439 --> 02:16:28.140
contained the fire, for the most part, and

02:16:28.140 --> 02:16:29.819
nobody was bitten, so far.

02:16:29.880 --> 02:16:32.639
So we're either very lucky or quite

02:16:32.639 --> 02:16:35.219
unlucky if there's really a viper out

02:16:35.219 --> 02:16:35.399
there.

02:16:35.459 --> 02:16:38.519
He considered her for a moment then added

02:16:38.519 --> 02:16:39.839
thanks for asking.

02:16:39.899 --> 02:16:43.260
Oh, Sonny said, flustered.

02:16:43.319 --> 02:16:44.520
She'd been worried.

02:16:44.579 --> 02:16:45.899
Of course she'd asked.

02:16:45.959 --> 02:16:47.039
Of course.

02:16:47.100 --> 02:16:50.399
Six Claws tossed away his stick and

02:16:50.399 --> 02:16:52.020
rubbed sand over his talons.

02:16:52.079 --> 02:16:55.680
Ready to be presented to the out claws, he

02:16:55.680 --> 02:16:56.100
asked her.

02:16:56.159 --> 02:17:00.120
Not even remotely, Sonny confessed.

02:17:00.180 --> 02:17:03.299
He chuckled in a rumbling way, and lifted

02:17:03.299 --> 02:17:04.979
the flap, so she could step through the

02:17:04.979 --> 02:17:08.340
tent and out onto the shifting sands, pale

02:17:08.340 --> 02:17:10.260
in the light of the 3 moons overhead.

02:17:10.319 --> 02:17:13.440
The bright orange and yellow flames of

02:17:13.440 --> 02:17:15.780
torches flickered all around the oasis

02:17:15.780 --> 02:17:17.879
reflecting in a dance across the pool.

02:17:17.940 --> 02:17:20.819
There were too many dragons for sunny to

02:17:20.819 --> 02:17:23.100
count, especially in the wavering shadows

02:17:23.100 --> 02:17:25.920
and most of them were moving, chasing one

02:17:25.920 --> 02:17:28.020
another across the sand, calling out

02:17:28.020 --> 02:17:31.260
insults or threats or jokes, laughing and

02:17:31.260 --> 02:17:32.520
tossing drinks at each other.

02:17:32.579 --> 02:17:35.100
As she blinked around, looking for

02:17:35.100 --> 02:17:36.059
thorn.

02:17:36.120 --> 02:17:37.860
One of the sand wings toppled into the

02:17:37.860 --> 02:17:40.319
pool with a splash, and 3 others jumped

02:17:40.319 --> 02:17:42.659
to hauler out, idiots.

02:17:42.719 --> 02:17:45.299
Six claws said with affection, and

02:17:45.299 --> 02:17:45.959
started forward.

02:17:46.020 --> 02:17:49.799
That's far enough, said a voice in the

02:17:49.799 --> 02:17:52.680
darkness behind the tent, 6 claws.

02:17:52.739 --> 02:17:53.940
Stop where you are.

02:17:54.000 --> 02:17:56.940
Six Claws swung around with a hiss.

02:17:57.059 --> 02:17:59.759
I take orders from Thorn, and no one

02:17:59.759 --> 02:17:59.999
else.

02:18:00.059 --> 02:18:04.019
Oh, it's not an order, said the other

02:18:04.019 --> 02:18:04.439
dragon.

02:18:04.500 --> 02:18:07.260
He stepped forward, so the torchlight

02:18:07.260 --> 02:18:09.420
could catch on his yellow scales, and

02:18:09.420 --> 02:18:11.520
then he recognized the sand wing they'd

02:18:11.520 --> 02:18:12.780
run into on the streets earlier.

02:18:12.840 --> 02:18:15.780
Atics, the one with a scratch who looked

02:18:15.780 --> 02:18:16.200
familiar.

02:18:16.260 --> 02:18:18.719
It's a suggestion.

02:18:18.780 --> 02:18:20.520
I think you'll really want to listen to.

02:18:20.639 --> 02:18:24.179
Six Claws took a menacing step toward him

02:18:24.179 --> 02:18:25.979
and addicts flicked his tail.

02:18:26.040 --> 02:18:28.500
Two more beefy dragons appeared behind

02:18:28.500 --> 02:18:28.799
him.

02:18:28.860 --> 02:18:31.139
They had a small dragonette pinned

02:18:31.139 --> 02:18:33.959
between them, perhaps 2 years old, with

02:18:33.959 --> 02:18:36.719
nearly white scales, and a tail barb that

02:18:36.719 --> 02:18:37.920
still wasn't fully developed.

02:18:37.979 --> 02:18:40.440
She squeaked nervously as they dragged

02:18:40.440 --> 02:18:41.040
her forward.

02:18:41.040 --> 02:18:45.180
The question really, said addicts.

02:18:45.239 --> 02:18:46.559
Is which daughter do you care about

02:18:46.559 --> 02:18:46.860
more?

02:18:46.979 --> 02:18:50.459
The alleged long lost egg that Thorn has

02:18:50.459 --> 02:18:51.180
been searching for?

02:18:51.180 --> 02:18:53.159
Or yours?

02:18:53.280 --> 02:18:57.420
Sonny glanced up at 6 Claws and saw the

02:18:57.420 --> 02:18:59.280
fury and fear contorting his face.

02:18:59.340 --> 02:19:02.520
He sank his talons into the sand, raising

02:19:02.520 --> 02:19:05.219
his tail beyond him, in the shadows.

02:19:05.280 --> 02:19:08.340
She saw 4 more sand wings slide out from

02:19:08.340 --> 02:19:10.500
behind the tent to stand menacingly

02:19:10.500 --> 02:19:12.059
between them and the pool.

02:19:12.120 --> 02:19:15.540
Ostrich, 6 claws growled.

02:19:15.659 --> 02:19:17.100
His eyes fixed on his daughter.

02:19:17.159 --> 02:19:18.780
Don't be scared.

02:19:18.840 --> 02:19:20.459
I won't let them hurt you.

02:19:20.520 --> 02:19:22.739
Don't make a mistake here.

02:19:22.799 --> 02:19:24.599
Addicts warned him.

02:19:24.659 --> 02:19:27.719
My friends' tails are much closer to your

02:19:27.719 --> 02:19:29.219
dragon net than you are to me.

02:19:29.280 --> 02:19:32.760
If you attack or even shout for help

02:19:32.760 --> 02:19:34.739
she'll be dead in an instant.

02:19:34.739 --> 02:19:37.799
But this doesn't have to get all violent

02:19:37.799 --> 02:19:38.940
6 claws.

02:19:39.000 --> 02:19:41.159
We want the dragonette of destiny.

02:19:41.219 --> 02:19:43.499
It's a simple fair trade.

02:19:43.620 --> 02:19:47.280
There was no dragon bite viper, was

02:19:47.280 --> 02:19:47.579
there?

02:19:47.639 --> 02:19:49.319
6 Claus said.

02:19:49.379 --> 02:19:51.719
You said that fire to draw Thorn away.

02:19:51.780 --> 02:19:54.120
Do you know how many dragonettes you

02:19:54.120 --> 02:19:54.600
could have killed?

02:19:54.659 --> 02:19:57.420
Yes, said addicts.

02:19:57.479 --> 02:19:58.920
Don't make it one more.

02:19:58.979 --> 02:20:02.940
Six Claws growled again, and Sonny saw

02:20:02.940 --> 02:20:04.680
his eyes dart from her to his daughter.

02:20:04.739 --> 02:20:07.920
He loves her so much, she thought.

02:20:07.979 --> 02:20:09.959
That's what I always wanted.

02:20:10.020 --> 02:20:13.860
That's what I might have now, with Thorn

02:20:13.860 --> 02:20:17.159
family, and answers, and a place to

02:20:17.159 --> 02:20:17.579
belong.

02:20:17.639 --> 02:20:19.739
But only if I deserve it.

02:20:19.860 --> 02:20:22.319
I can't take it at the expense of another

02:20:22.319 --> 02:20:22.739
family.

02:20:22.799 --> 02:20:26.520
It's all right, she said to 6 Claws.

02:20:26.579 --> 02:20:27.840
Make the trade.

02:20:27.899 --> 02:20:28.920
You have to.

02:20:28.979 --> 02:20:30.000
I'll be fine.

02:20:30.059 --> 02:20:32.940
She glanced up at the palm leaves that

02:20:32.940 --> 02:20:34.020
blocked the view of the stars.

02:20:34.079 --> 02:20:36.840
Addicts had smartly cornered them in a

02:20:36.840 --> 02:20:38.639
pocket of shadow where they couldn't be

02:20:38.639 --> 02:20:40.200
spotted from across the pool.

02:20:40.379 --> 02:20:42.059
What do you want her for?

02:20:42.120 --> 02:20:43.799
Six Claws asked.

02:20:43.860 --> 02:20:47.159
Burn wants the dragonettes pretty badly.

02:20:47.280 --> 02:20:48.840
Addick said.

02:20:48.899 --> 02:20:51.540
She'll take me back if I show up with one

02:20:51.540 --> 02:20:51.959
of them.

02:20:52.020 --> 02:20:54.360
Back into her army?

02:20:54.420 --> 02:20:56.100
Six claws demanded.

02:20:56.159 --> 02:20:57.239
Why would you want that?

02:20:57.299 --> 02:20:58.799
You could be safe here.

02:20:58.920 --> 02:21:01.620
The war never comes to the Scorpion den.

02:21:01.680 --> 02:21:05.340
Attic shifted, firelight gleaming in his

02:21:05.340 --> 02:21:05.940
dark eyes.

02:21:06.000 --> 02:21:09.180
I was thrown out of her army, but my

02:21:09.180 --> 02:21:09.959
family wasn't.

02:21:10.020 --> 02:21:12.479
There are dragons there I need to get

02:21:12.479 --> 02:21:12.899
back to.

02:21:12.959 --> 02:21:17.159
Ah, sad, Sonny thought.

02:21:17.219 --> 02:21:19.680
And then her brain added, in a voice much

02:21:19.680 --> 02:21:23.040
like tsunamis, Sonny, by all the moons

02:21:23.040 --> 02:21:25.020
quit feeling sorry for dragons who want

02:21:25.020 --> 02:21:26.520
to abduct you and sell you off.

02:21:26.639 --> 02:21:30.000
She glanced down at the 6 wickedly curved

02:21:30.000 --> 02:21:32.459
claws that were carving gouges in the

02:21:32.459 --> 02:21:33.299
sand beside her.

02:21:33.360 --> 02:21:36.239
She had a bad feeling that Six Claws was

02:21:36.239 --> 02:21:38.100
planning to fight, which couldn't

02:21:38.100 --> 02:21:39.719
possibly go well for either him or

02:21:39.719 --> 02:21:40.379
ostrich.

02:21:40.500 --> 02:21:43.739
Six claws, she said firmly.

02:21:43.799 --> 02:21:46.020
I said, make the trade.

02:21:46.079 --> 02:21:47.520
My mother will understand.

02:21:47.579 --> 02:21:50.819
She wanted to jump forward herself and

02:21:50.819 --> 02:21:52.559
wrench the little dragonette out of their

02:21:52.559 --> 02:21:53.340
claws.

02:21:53.399 --> 02:21:56.340
Ostrich was trembling so badly that Sonny

02:21:56.340 --> 02:21:57.840
could hear her teeth clicking together.

02:21:57.959 --> 02:22:02.520
But Thorn, 6 Claws said, twisting around

02:22:02.520 --> 02:22:04.200
to glance back at the flickering lights

02:22:04.200 --> 02:22:04.979
by the pool.

02:22:05.040 --> 02:22:08.280
Doesn't have to know, Atic said.

02:22:08.340 --> 02:22:10.200
Tell her this one ran off.

02:22:10.260 --> 02:22:12.840
Woke up, decided she didn't want a

02:22:12.840 --> 02:22:15.000
criminal thug for a mother, and flew for

02:22:15.000 --> 02:22:15.420
the hills.

02:22:15.479 --> 02:22:19.020
Don't tell her that, Sonny protested

02:22:19.020 --> 02:22:19.680
indignantly.

02:22:19.739 --> 02:22:21.899
She smacked her tail against the sand.

02:22:21.959 --> 02:22:23.760
That's so mean.

02:22:24.059 --> 02:22:24.600
I wouldn't do that.

02:22:24.659 --> 02:22:26.819
If he tells her the truth.

02:22:26.940 --> 02:22:29.280
Thorn is likely to get herself killed

02:22:29.280 --> 02:22:32.159
trying to rescue you, Atic said.

02:22:32.219 --> 02:22:33.479
Would you prefer that?

02:22:33.540 --> 02:22:36.719
No, but at least come up with something

02:22:36.719 --> 02:22:39.600
believable, Sonny said spiritedly.

02:22:39.659 --> 02:22:41.520
She looked up at 6 claws.

02:22:41.579 --> 02:22:43.739
You can tell her I had to go back to my

02:22:43.739 --> 02:22:45.840
friends to let them know they're safe

02:22:45.840 --> 02:22:47.100
from the night wings.

02:22:47.159 --> 02:22:48.899
Tell her I'll be back.

02:22:48.959 --> 02:22:52.079
Six Claws stared at her, his face

02:22:52.079 --> 02:22:52.860
unreadable.

02:22:52.920 --> 02:22:54.780
Addicts flicked his tongue.

02:22:54.840 --> 02:22:56.159
You won't be.

02:22:56.280 --> 02:22:58.500
You don't know that.

02:22:58.559 --> 02:22:59.399
Sonny said.

02:22:59.459 --> 02:23:01.500
Now release ostrich and I'll go with

02:23:01.500 --> 02:23:01.680
you.

02:23:01.739 --> 02:23:04.200
She was starting to worry that the little

02:23:04.200 --> 02:23:06.299
dragonette would have a heart attack and

02:23:06.299 --> 02:23:06.959
collapse right there.

02:23:07.020 --> 02:23:12.479
No, Atic said, she flies with us until we

02:23:12.479 --> 02:23:15.299
have an hour's head start, and then I'll

02:23:15.299 --> 02:23:15.780
send her back.

02:23:15.899 --> 02:23:19.500
That made practical sense, although Sunny

02:23:19.500 --> 02:23:21.479
didn't want to drag ostrich any further

02:23:21.479 --> 02:23:24.180
into danger, but if they left ostrich

02:23:24.180 --> 02:23:26.579
behind, Six Claws and the others would

02:23:26.579 --> 02:23:28.379
chase them down before they could reach

02:23:28.379 --> 02:23:29.700
Burns stronghold.

02:23:29.760 --> 02:23:32.219
All right, then let's go.

02:23:32.280 --> 02:23:33.479
She said.

02:23:33.540 --> 02:23:35.520
Even more than ostrich.

02:23:35.579 --> 02:23:37.920
She was worried about what 6 claws might

02:23:37.920 --> 02:23:38.100
do.

02:23:38.219 --> 02:23:40.559
She didn't think he'd stand a chance

02:23:40.559 --> 02:23:42.360
against 7 big dragons.

02:23:42.420 --> 02:23:45.059
And what if he is my father?

02:23:45.120 --> 02:23:47.340
And ostrich is my half sister?

02:23:47.399 --> 02:23:50.280
I don't want them to die before I get to

02:23:50.280 --> 02:23:50.639
know them.

02:23:50.700 --> 02:23:54.659
It wasn't until they were aloft, winging

02:23:54.659 --> 02:23:56.819
north through the cold desert night

02:23:56.819 --> 02:23:58.920
toward the stronghold of one of the most

02:23:58.920 --> 02:24:01.799
dangerous dragons empirea, that the

02:24:01.799 --> 02:24:04.379
thought occurred to Sonny, that she might

02:24:04.379 --> 02:24:05.579
be the one who was about to die.

02:24:05.700 --> 02:24:12.360
Part two, Burns Stronghold.

02:24:12.479 --> 02:24:15.540
Chapter 9.

02:24:15.600 --> 02:24:18.479
The outer walls of the palace were

02:24:18.479 --> 02:24:19.319
dripping with blood.

02:24:19.379 --> 02:24:22.079
Sonny had read the scrolls about the sand

02:24:22.079 --> 02:24:24.600
wing stronghold, and she'd seen it from

02:24:24.600 --> 02:24:26.819
afar, but nothing could have prepared her

02:24:26.819 --> 02:24:28.920
for the smell of the decapitated dragon

02:24:28.920 --> 02:24:31.319
heads that studded the top of the walls

02:24:31.319 --> 02:24:34.079
or the gruesome stains on the stone below

02:24:34.079 --> 02:24:34.620
them.

02:24:34.680 --> 02:24:36.840
They were still more than a mile away

02:24:36.840 --> 02:24:39.299
when the horrible rotting smell 1st

02:24:39.299 --> 02:24:42.059
reached her, making her choke, and nearly

02:24:42.059 --> 02:24:43.079
driving her out of the sky.

02:24:43.139 --> 02:24:46.260
Attics caught her as she faltered toward

02:24:46.260 --> 02:24:46.559
the sand.

02:24:46.620 --> 02:24:50.819
Shallow breaths, he advised, you get used

02:24:50.819 --> 02:24:51.180
to it.

02:24:51.239 --> 02:24:52.739
Do you?

02:24:52.799 --> 02:24:54.059
Really?

02:24:54.120 --> 02:24:55.139
Sonny asked.

02:24:55.200 --> 02:24:58.079
He shrugged, which, as far as she could

02:24:58.079 --> 02:24:59.340
tell, meant, no.

02:24:59.399 --> 02:25:01.739
Ostrich had been released during the

02:25:01.739 --> 02:25:04.319
night, shooting one last terrified look

02:25:04.319 --> 02:25:06.479
at Sonny before bolting back toward the

02:25:06.479 --> 02:25:08.340
distant fires of the Scorpion Den.

02:25:08.399 --> 02:25:10.500
Sonny thought that addicts had

02:25:10.500 --> 02:25:12.239
deliberately freed the dragonette while

02:25:12.239 --> 02:25:13.620
the den was still visible behind them.

02:25:13.680 --> 02:25:16.260
Optimistically, she thought perhaps he

02:25:16.260 --> 02:25:18.120
was concerned for ostrich's safety.

02:25:18.180 --> 02:25:20.879
It seemed kind not to make her find her

02:25:20.879 --> 02:25:21.780
way in total darkness.

02:25:21.840 --> 02:25:24.540
She could almost hear her friends

02:25:24.540 --> 02:25:25.500
laughing at her inner head.

02:25:25.620 --> 02:25:27.479
That's right, sonny.

02:25:27.540 --> 02:25:29.459
Your kidnapper is a real sweetheart.

02:25:29.520 --> 02:25:32.040
He's handing you over to burn out of the

02:25:32.040 --> 02:25:32.879
goodness of his heart, too.

02:25:32.940 --> 02:25:36.180
But if he was doing this for his family

02:25:36.180 --> 02:25:37.799
for someone he cared about.

02:25:37.860 --> 02:25:41.340
Sonny glanced over the scarred dragon and

02:25:41.340 --> 02:25:43.079
thought, there's more to his story.

02:25:43.139 --> 02:25:45.479
There's always more to everyone's story.

02:25:45.540 --> 02:25:47.579
If you bother to find out what it is.

02:25:47.700 --> 02:25:50.579
The sun had cleared the mountains when

02:25:50.579 --> 02:25:52.860
they came to the sentries, a pair of sand

02:25:52.860 --> 02:25:55.979
wings carrying long spears, relentless

02:25:55.979 --> 02:25:58.200
heat beat down from the cloudless sky

02:25:58.200 --> 02:26:00.120
making the smell much worse.

02:26:00.180 --> 02:26:03.420
Sonny's wings ached from flying so long

02:26:03.420 --> 02:26:04.079
without stopping.

02:26:04.139 --> 02:26:06.719
She could see the brownish yellow walls

02:26:06.719 --> 02:26:09.360
of the stronghold up ahead, stained and

02:26:09.360 --> 02:26:11.520
crusted with a dark red and black gore

02:26:11.520 --> 02:26:12.899
that dripped from the grisly

02:26:12.899 --> 02:26:13.500
decorations.

02:26:13.559 --> 02:26:16.020
It was a vast palace.

02:26:16.079 --> 02:26:18.600
Far larger than she had realized when

02:26:18.600 --> 02:26:19.739
she'd seen it from a distance.

02:26:19.799 --> 02:26:22.500
The ramparts seemed to stretch across the

02:26:22.500 --> 02:26:25.079
horizon, and Sunny guessed that 2 or 3

02:26:25.079 --> 02:26:27.840
scorpion dens could fit inside, or about

02:26:27.840 --> 02:26:30.120
a 1000 of the caves she'd grown up in.

02:26:30.180 --> 02:26:33.239
Hold it, said one of the sentries

02:26:33.299 --> 02:26:35.040
swinging the spear toward them.

02:26:35.100 --> 02:26:37.799
He squinted, Addicts?

02:26:37.860 --> 02:26:40.559
Ho there, said addicts.

02:26:40.620 --> 02:26:42.959
He waved a claw, and the dragons behind

02:26:42.959 --> 02:26:45.420
him all paused, beating the air and

02:26:45.420 --> 02:26:46.860
craning to see past his wings.

02:26:46.920 --> 02:26:50.159
Picked up some friends somewhere, I see

02:26:50.159 --> 02:26:52.379
said the sentry, half jokingly.

02:26:52.440 --> 02:26:54.540
Are you invading or what's all this?

02:26:54.659 --> 02:26:58.200
Brought a present for the queen, said

02:26:58.200 --> 02:26:58.799
addicts.

02:26:58.860 --> 02:27:00.959
He flicked his tail at Sonny, and she

02:27:00.959 --> 02:27:01.680
hissed at him.

02:27:01.739 --> 02:27:03.420
Recognize this one?

02:27:03.479 --> 02:27:06.360
Both sentries drew in a quick breath.

02:27:06.420 --> 02:27:10.020
From the party in the sky kingdom, said

02:27:10.020 --> 02:27:10.440
one of them.

02:27:10.559 --> 02:27:12.540
Scarlet was going to give her to Queen

02:27:12.540 --> 02:27:13.020
Bern.

02:27:13.079 --> 02:27:16.079
That's where I've seen addicts before

02:27:16.079 --> 02:27:19.260
Sonny realized, bowing and scraping

02:27:19.260 --> 02:27:21.299
behind burn as she examined me like a

02:27:21.299 --> 02:27:24.180
deformed gemstone before he got his

02:27:24.180 --> 02:27:24.540
scar.

02:27:24.659 --> 02:27:28.739
And now I've found her, and I'm giving

02:27:28.739 --> 02:27:31.739
her to the queen, said addicts smugly.

02:27:31.799 --> 02:27:34.139
The sentry looked skeptically at their

02:27:34.139 --> 02:27:34.979
entourage.

02:27:35.040 --> 02:27:38.340
And you need 7 dragons to transport this

02:27:38.340 --> 02:27:39.540
midget creature safely.

02:27:39.659 --> 02:27:42.180
I'm terrifying when you get to know me.

02:27:42.239 --> 02:27:43.799
Sonny volunteered.

02:27:43.860 --> 02:27:45.959
She heard a couple of the dragons behind

02:27:45.959 --> 02:27:48.299
her chuckle, but addicts shot them a

02:27:48.299 --> 02:27:50.280
stern look, and they subsided.

02:27:50.459 --> 02:27:53.100
Wait, said the other sentry.

02:27:53.159 --> 02:27:56.700
Doesn't that mean she's, I mean, she's

02:27:56.700 --> 02:27:59.579
one of yes, Atic said.

02:27:59.639 --> 02:28:01.860
So stop delaying and let us through.

02:28:01.979 --> 02:28:02.520
All right?

02:28:02.579 --> 02:28:06.299
The sentries flapped aside, both of them

02:28:06.299 --> 02:28:08.459
examining Sonny intently as she and her

02:28:08.459 --> 02:28:09.719
escort flew past them.

02:28:09.780 --> 02:28:12.120
In all of Sonny's fantasies about

02:28:12.120 --> 02:28:13.860
fulfilling the prophecy and saving

02:28:13.860 --> 02:28:14.579
Pyria.

02:28:14.639 --> 02:28:16.860
She never imagined there'd be quite so

02:28:16.860 --> 02:28:17.819
much staring.

02:28:17.879 --> 02:28:20.639
And she certainly hadn't counted on

02:28:20.639 --> 02:28:22.440
getting locked up as often as she already

02:28:22.440 --> 02:28:22.799
had been.

02:28:22.860 --> 02:28:26.520
As they swooped down toward the thick

02:28:26.520 --> 02:28:28.860
forbidding walls of Burns stronghold

02:28:28.860 --> 02:28:31.079
Sonny thought with a shudder that this

02:28:31.079 --> 02:28:32.879
might be the worst prison so far.

02:28:32.940 --> 02:28:36.540
Scarlet's palace had had gladiator fights

02:28:36.540 --> 02:28:38.280
but at least she hadn't kept the

02:28:38.280 --> 02:28:39.899
dismembered parts of her enemies on

02:28:39.899 --> 02:28:40.500
display.

02:28:40.559 --> 02:28:43.680
And it isn't exactly easy to cut off a

02:28:43.680 --> 02:28:44.399
dragon's head.

02:28:44.459 --> 02:28:47.819
Sonny remembered Starflight saying, even

02:28:47.819 --> 02:28:48.719
if it's already dead.

02:28:48.780 --> 02:28:52.020
They'd been reading in the steady cave

02:28:52.020 --> 02:28:54.239
he'd rolled out the scroll and tapped the

02:28:54.239 --> 02:28:56.879
drawing of the stronghold, you have to be

02:28:56.879 --> 02:28:58.379
pretty brutal to get through the scales

02:28:58.379 --> 02:28:59.100
and everything else.

02:28:59.159 --> 02:29:02.639
Sunny also remembered that the outer

02:29:02.639 --> 02:29:04.920
walls had been added by burn after Queen

02:29:04.920 --> 02:29:05.760
Oasis died.

02:29:05.819 --> 02:29:09.719
They look solid and thick and imposing.

02:29:09.780 --> 02:29:12.719
But useless for keeping out dragons who

02:29:12.719 --> 02:29:13.139
can fly.

02:29:13.200 --> 02:29:15.899
The only creatures they'd really keep out

02:29:15.899 --> 02:29:18.299
for certain are scavengers.

02:29:18.840 --> 02:29:21.239
A scavenger had killed Burns' mother

02:29:21.239 --> 02:29:21.659
after all.

02:29:21.719 --> 02:29:23.879
Is Burne afraid of them?

02:29:24.000 --> 02:29:27.120
From what Sonny had seen of her, it was

02:29:27.120 --> 02:29:28.680
hard to imagine that Bern was afraid of

02:29:28.680 --> 02:29:28.860
anything.

02:29:28.979 --> 02:29:32.340
Attics led the way as they spiraled down

02:29:32.340 --> 02:29:35.040
onto the hot white stones of an enormous

02:29:35.040 --> 02:29:37.979
courtyard that encircled the old palace.

02:29:38.040 --> 02:29:39.659
Long, squat buildings had been

02:29:39.659 --> 02:29:41.340
constructed along the inner side of the

02:29:41.340 --> 02:29:41.819
walls.

02:29:41.940 --> 02:29:43.799
They appeared to be extra barracks for

02:29:43.799 --> 02:29:44.159
soldiers.

02:29:44.219 --> 02:29:47.280
Small gatherings of armed sand wings were

02:29:47.280 --> 02:29:49.139
visible in each direction, either

02:29:49.139 --> 02:29:51.600
cleaning weapons, sparring or sleeping.

02:29:51.659 --> 02:29:55.079
In the center of the courtyard, opposite

02:29:55.079 --> 02:29:57.600
the palace entrance, stood an odd kind of

02:29:57.600 --> 02:30:01.440
monument, a tall black obelisk, surrounded

02:30:01.440 --> 02:30:03.420
by a circle of sand wider than a large

02:30:03.420 --> 02:30:04.920
dragon's wingspan.

02:30:04.979 --> 02:30:07.680
Words were carved into the sides, with

02:30:07.680 --> 02:30:09.780
the letters all painted in gold, but

02:30:09.780 --> 02:30:11.100
Sonny couldn't read them from where she

02:30:11.100 --> 02:30:11.340
was.

02:30:11.399 --> 02:30:14.639
The old palace within the walls was a lot

02:30:14.639 --> 02:30:16.379
more elegant than the parts Burne had

02:30:16.379 --> 02:30:16.620
added.

02:30:16.680 --> 02:30:19.799
There were slender towers, and windows as

02:30:19.799 --> 02:30:22.260
tall as dragons, and high pavilion

02:30:22.260 --> 02:30:24.479
landing platforms topped with domes and

02:30:24.479 --> 02:30:24.959
spires.

02:30:25.020 --> 02:30:28.079
Shapes were carved all over the stone

02:30:28.079 --> 02:30:32.159
lizards, and desert birds and suns, mostly

02:30:32.159 --> 02:30:34.139
as far as sunny could see at 1st glance.

02:30:34.200 --> 02:30:37.139
It made the palace look for a moment as

02:30:37.139 --> 02:30:39.479
though it was crawling with life, or

02:30:39.479 --> 02:30:41.819
shimmering with heat, an unsettling

02:30:41.819 --> 02:30:44.579
illusion of motion, probably intended to

02:30:44.579 --> 02:30:45.719
make visitors uncomfortable.

02:30:45.780 --> 02:30:48.659
The doors were open to the huge front

02:30:48.659 --> 02:30:51.000
entrance of the palace, and Sonny

02:30:51.000 --> 02:30:53.280
realized with a start that a dragon was

02:30:53.280 --> 02:30:55.260
standing just on the edge of the sunlight

02:30:55.260 --> 02:30:57.180
staring at her from the shadow.

02:30:57.239 --> 02:31:01.200
Her heart plunged as she thought, burn.

02:31:01.260 --> 02:31:03.959
And then the dragon moved, and she

02:31:03.959 --> 02:31:05.940
glimpsed black diamond shapes on the

02:31:05.940 --> 02:31:06.479
scales.

02:31:06.540 --> 02:31:08.940
With an even stronger burst of fear, she

02:31:08.940 --> 02:31:11.700
thought, blister, how could blister be

02:31:11.700 --> 02:31:11.879
here?

02:31:11.940 --> 02:31:14.639
And then the dragon stepped into the

02:31:14.639 --> 02:31:17.819
light, and she realized he was male, and

02:31:17.819 --> 02:31:19.500
not one of the 3 sandwing sisters after

02:31:19.500 --> 02:31:19.739
all.

02:31:19.799 --> 02:31:23.159
He still looked horribly like ballister

02:31:23.159 --> 02:31:23.280
though.

02:31:23.340 --> 02:31:26.520
He had the same narrow face and lidded

02:31:26.520 --> 02:31:29.040
dark eyes, the same black patterns on his

02:31:29.040 --> 02:31:30.299
pale yellow scales.

02:31:30.360 --> 02:31:33.600
His poisonous tail barb slithered along

02:31:33.600 --> 02:31:35.819
the stones behind him, and his sharp

02:31:35.819 --> 02:31:38.040
claws made a tapping sound as he advanced

02:31:38.040 --> 02:31:38.459
toward them.

02:31:38.520 --> 02:31:41.579
He wore a cluster of keys and pouches and

02:31:41.579 --> 02:31:44.100
bells, on chains around his neck that

02:31:44.100 --> 02:31:45.840
clinked and jingled slightly as he

02:31:45.840 --> 02:31:46.139
walked.

02:31:46.200 --> 02:31:49.260
Some of them were plain iron, while

02:31:49.260 --> 02:31:50.879
others flashed with jewels or gold

02:31:50.879 --> 02:31:51.479
plating.

02:31:51.540 --> 02:31:54.059
Addicts bowed his head respectfully.

02:31:54.120 --> 02:31:58.860
Smolder, he said, I brought a gift for

02:31:58.860 --> 02:32:00.059
Queen Burn.

02:32:00.120 --> 02:32:02.760
I see, Smolder said.

02:32:02.819 --> 02:32:04.500
Sonny felt a little better.

02:32:04.620 --> 02:32:07.920
His voice didn't have the oozing, creeping

02:32:07.920 --> 02:32:09.600
sinister quality of blister's voice.

02:32:09.659 --> 02:32:13.620
He sounded just normal, like one of her

02:32:13.620 --> 02:32:13.860
friends.

02:32:13.979 --> 02:32:15.959
Who are you?

02:32:16.020 --> 02:32:19.079
he asked her, and she liked that too, that

02:32:19.079 --> 02:32:21.120
he spoke directly to her instead of over

02:32:21.120 --> 02:32:23.159
her head, as though she was nothing but a

02:32:23.159 --> 02:32:23.639
piece of treasure.

02:32:23.700 --> 02:32:26.340
My name's Sonny, she answered.

02:32:26.399 --> 02:32:27.479
Who are you?

02:32:27.540 --> 02:32:29.040
I'm...

02:32:29.040 --> 02:32:30.600
The brother.

02:32:30.659 --> 02:32:31.920
Smolder said.

02:32:31.979 --> 02:32:34.260
And something in his expression said he

02:32:34.260 --> 02:32:36.000
had many thoughts about that, but

02:32:36.000 --> 02:32:37.319
wouldn't risk going into detail.

02:32:37.379 --> 02:32:39.299
Burns brother?

02:32:39.360 --> 02:32:40.440
The only one?

02:32:40.500 --> 02:32:41.520
Sonny asked.

02:32:41.579 --> 02:32:43.500
Trying to remember what she'd read about

02:32:43.500 --> 02:32:44.940
the Sandwing Royal Family.

02:32:45.000 --> 02:32:48.180
There used to be 3 of us, but the other 2

02:32:48.180 --> 02:32:50.639
made the wrong dragon's mad, he

02:32:50.639 --> 02:32:51.120
grimaced.

02:32:51.180 --> 02:32:54.239
The wrong dragons, meaning your sister's

02:32:54.239 --> 02:32:55.260
sunny guest.

02:32:55.319 --> 02:32:57.540
So you're on burn side?

02:32:57.659 --> 02:32:59.459
I'm here, aren't I?

02:32:59.520 --> 02:33:00.540
He said.

02:33:00.600 --> 02:33:02.579
And it occurred to her that that wasn't

02:33:02.579 --> 02:33:03.959
much of an enthusiastic yes.

02:33:04.079 --> 02:33:07.020
Where is Queen Burn?

02:33:07.079 --> 02:33:08.760
Addicts cut in abruptly.

02:33:08.819 --> 02:33:12.360
She is not at home at the moment, Smolder

02:33:12.360 --> 02:33:12.719
said.

02:33:12.780 --> 02:33:15.120
He spread one wing and beckoned Sonny

02:33:15.120 --> 02:33:15.959
toward the main entrance.

02:33:16.020 --> 02:33:18.780
She's out looking for a certain quintet

02:33:18.780 --> 02:33:19.920
of young dragons.

02:33:19.979 --> 02:33:22.979
Sunny stopped, looking up at him with a

02:33:22.979 --> 02:33:23.280
shiver.

02:33:23.340 --> 02:33:26.100
If Bern was searching for her friends

02:33:26.100 --> 02:33:28.379
instead of fighting battles, she must

02:33:28.379 --> 02:33:29.579
really want to destroy them.

02:33:29.639 --> 02:33:32.100
Wait, Atic said.

02:33:32.219 --> 02:33:33.420
I want to see her.

02:33:33.479 --> 02:33:36.059
I mean, this is my prisoner.

02:33:36.120 --> 02:33:38.340
She's one of the ones in the prophecy.

02:33:38.399 --> 02:33:39.899
I know.

02:33:39.959 --> 02:33:42.000
I'll take it from here, Smolder said

02:33:42.000 --> 02:33:42.479
firmly.

02:33:42.540 --> 02:33:44.340
You can wait in the barracks until she

02:33:44.340 --> 02:33:44.639
returns.

02:33:44.760 --> 02:33:46.799
He nodded at the courtyard.

02:33:46.860 --> 02:33:49.680
Don't worry, you'll get all your pardons

02:33:49.680 --> 02:33:50.879
and your reinstatement.

02:33:50.940 --> 02:33:53.639
He flared his wing across Denny's back

02:33:53.639 --> 02:33:55.260
and ushered her forward again.

02:33:55.319 --> 02:33:58.379
But my reward.

02:33:58.500 --> 02:34:01.979
Addix's voice trailed off as Sonny and

02:34:01.979 --> 02:34:03.299
Smolder stepped out of the bright

02:34:03.299 --> 02:34:05.459
sunlight into the cool shadows of a vast

02:34:05.459 --> 02:34:08.040
hall, big enough for a 100 dragons.

02:34:08.159 --> 02:34:11.760
Far overhead, large fans shaped like

02:34:11.760 --> 02:34:14.579
dragon wings beat the air, and Sonny

02:34:14.579 --> 02:34:16.440
spotted a few small dragons pulling on

02:34:16.440 --> 02:34:17.520
ropes to keep them moving.

02:34:17.579 --> 02:34:21.000
Tapestries woven in blues and golds and

02:34:21.000 --> 02:34:23.639
white covered the walls, echoing some of

02:34:23.639 --> 02:34:25.079
the same patterns in the stonework

02:34:25.079 --> 02:34:28.260
outside, and airy white curtains billowed

02:34:28.260 --> 02:34:29.159
the long windows.

02:34:29.159 --> 02:34:31.559
A heavy table ran down the middle of the

02:34:31.559 --> 02:34:34.799
hall, loaded with food, and sunny harder

02:34:34.799 --> 02:34:35.520
stomach grumble.

02:34:35.579 --> 02:34:38.940
Take anything you like, Smolder said.

02:34:39.000 --> 02:34:40.680
No, thank you.

02:34:40.739 --> 02:34:42.360
Sonny answered politely.

02:34:42.420 --> 02:34:44.940
It seemed unlikely that the entire table

02:34:44.940 --> 02:34:47.100
of food was poisoned, but she didn't

02:34:47.100 --> 02:34:48.719
intend to make killing her any easier

02:34:48.719 --> 02:34:49.860
than it already would be.

02:34:49.920 --> 02:34:52.860
She tilted her head to study the tapestry

02:34:52.860 --> 02:34:55.860
closest to her, and realized that the odd

02:34:55.860 --> 02:34:58.620
pattern of rust colored spots on it was

02:34:58.620 --> 02:35:00.540
actually dried spatters of blood.

02:35:00.600 --> 02:35:04.020
The food is for the soldiers, Smolders

02:35:04.020 --> 02:35:05.399
said, sounding amused.

02:35:05.459 --> 02:35:07.379
I promise it's safe to eat.

02:35:07.440 --> 02:35:10.319
I'm not hungry, Sunny said.

02:35:10.379 --> 02:35:13.200
Um, when do you think Burnham will be

02:35:13.200 --> 02:35:13.379
back?

02:35:13.440 --> 02:35:16.260
Smolder shifted his wings in a shrug.

02:35:16.319 --> 02:35:17.700
I never know.

02:35:17.760 --> 02:35:20.159
She prefers not to discuss her plans.

02:35:20.219 --> 02:35:22.979
He lifted his claws and studied them

02:35:22.979 --> 02:35:25.500
thoughtfully, shaking out sand that was

02:35:25.500 --> 02:35:26.459
caught between the scales.

02:35:26.520 --> 02:35:30.059
The real question is, what to do with

02:35:30.059 --> 02:35:30.180
you?

02:35:30.299 --> 02:35:31.979
On the one talent.

02:35:32.040 --> 02:35:34.500
I assume she'd rather find you alive when

02:35:34.500 --> 02:35:37.260
she gets back, so she can kill you, or

02:35:37.260 --> 02:35:38.940
interrogate you and then kill you

02:35:38.940 --> 02:35:39.540
herself.

02:35:39.659 --> 02:35:41.459
On the other talent?

02:35:41.520 --> 02:35:44.340
If I lock you up and you somehow escape

02:35:44.340 --> 02:35:47.520
which I'm sure you'll try to do, I'll be

02:35:47.520 --> 02:35:49.379
in far worse trouble than if I just kill

02:35:49.379 --> 02:35:53.399
you right now, but on the 3rd talent, if

02:35:53.399 --> 02:35:55.680
I successfully keep you captive, she

02:35:55.680 --> 02:35:56.940
should be quite pleased.

02:35:56.940 --> 02:35:58.559
It's a risk, though.

02:35:58.620 --> 02:36:01.079
You're guaranteed not to escape if I kill

02:36:01.079 --> 02:36:01.319
you.

02:36:01.379 --> 02:36:04.500
But on the 4th talon, Sonny said

02:36:04.500 --> 02:36:05.040
hurriedly.

02:36:05.100 --> 02:36:07.440
How will Bern find my friends if she

02:36:07.440 --> 02:36:09.840
can't ask me questions or use me as a

02:36:09.840 --> 02:36:10.200
hostage?

02:36:10.200 --> 02:36:12.479
Think about how valuable I am alive.

02:36:12.540 --> 02:36:16.680
Hmm, Smolders said, with a little smile.

02:36:16.799 --> 02:36:19.620
A tiny brown mouse crept out from under

02:36:19.620 --> 02:36:21.600
the table and made a dash for the nearest

02:36:21.600 --> 02:36:22.020
wall.

02:36:22.020 --> 02:36:25.079
Smolder flicked his tail toward it, but

02:36:25.079 --> 02:36:26.819
stopped at the last minute and let the

02:36:26.819 --> 02:36:28.440
mouse vanish into one of the cracks.

02:36:28.440 --> 02:36:29.940
He looked back at Sonny.

02:36:30.000 --> 02:36:32.700
All right, you talked me into it.

02:36:32.760 --> 02:36:34.319
You can live for now.

02:36:34.379 --> 02:36:36.719
But I'd appreciate it if you'd keep your

02:36:36.719 --> 02:36:38.819
escape attempts as feeble and ineffective

02:36:38.819 --> 02:36:39.540
as possible.

02:36:39.600 --> 02:36:42.479
He started toward a doorway at the far

02:36:42.479 --> 02:36:44.280
end of the hall and Sonny followed

02:36:44.280 --> 02:36:45.780
wondering if that was supposed to be

02:36:45.780 --> 02:36:45.959
funny.

02:36:46.020 --> 02:36:49.200
Smolder had this odd way of talking that

02:36:49.200 --> 02:36:50.940
kind of made everything he said sound

02:36:50.940 --> 02:36:53.940
like a joke, but then Sonny's life and

02:36:53.940 --> 02:36:56.100
death didn't seem particularly hilarious

02:36:56.100 --> 02:36:57.540
at least if you asked her.

02:36:57.600 --> 02:37:00.659
There were 5 doors leading off the main

02:37:00.659 --> 02:37:03.420
hall, plus a staircase that led up to a

02:37:03.420 --> 02:37:04.799
balcony with 2 more doorways.

02:37:04.860 --> 02:37:07.799
Sunny considered trying to memorize the

02:37:07.799 --> 02:37:09.899
layout of the palace, but as soon as they

02:37:09.899 --> 02:37:11.819
stepped through into the dark, winding

02:37:11.819 --> 02:37:12.600
passage beyond.

02:37:12.719 --> 02:37:14.940
She knew it would be hopeless.

02:37:15.000 --> 02:37:17.159
The corridors of the old palace

02:37:17.159 --> 02:37:19.860
crisscrossed and twisted almost as often

02:37:19.860 --> 02:37:22.379
and confusingly as the streets of the

02:37:22.379 --> 02:37:24.420
Scorpion Den, and they were sometimes

02:37:24.420 --> 02:37:26.579
barely wide enough for 2 dragons to

02:37:26.579 --> 02:37:27.600
squeeze past each other.

02:37:27.659 --> 02:37:30.719
Short flights of steps kept taking them

02:37:30.719 --> 02:37:33.600
up to new levels, and then down again, and

02:37:33.600 --> 02:37:35.100
every other turn brought them to a spot

02:37:35.100 --> 02:37:37.379
that looked exactly like something they'd

02:37:37.379 --> 02:37:38.159
just passed.

02:37:38.219 --> 02:37:41.040
Sonny almost wondered if Smolder was

02:37:41.040 --> 02:37:43.200
messing with her head, except that he

02:37:43.200 --> 02:37:44.760
seemed to be calculating something under

02:37:44.760 --> 02:37:47.040
his breath, and barely paid attention to

02:37:47.040 --> 02:37:47.639
her as they walked.

02:37:47.760 --> 02:37:51.059
The stone floors were worn smooth with

02:37:51.059 --> 02:37:53.219
the passage of many dragons, and the

02:37:53.219 --> 02:37:55.440
walls and ceiling were flat, and usually

02:37:55.440 --> 02:37:56.280
bare as well.

02:37:56.340 --> 02:37:58.500
So Sonny felt as if she was walking

02:37:58.500 --> 02:38:01.020
through long, narrow boxes.

02:38:01.079 --> 02:38:03.899
It was eerie and claustrophobic, with no

02:38:03.899 --> 02:38:06.420
space to fly, except for the occasional

02:38:06.420 --> 02:38:08.100
glimpses of sunlight from the upper

02:38:08.100 --> 02:38:10.860
levels, and 3 times they passed open

02:38:10.860 --> 02:38:13.440
sunlit courtyards, where dragons were

02:38:13.440 --> 02:38:15.239
lying with their wings spread wide

02:38:15.239 --> 02:38:16.500
soaking in the heat.

02:38:16.559 --> 02:38:19.139
I haven't seen any treasure.

02:38:19.200 --> 02:38:20.639
Sunny realized.

02:38:20.700 --> 02:38:24.479
No gold talon prints, no pearl studded

02:38:24.479 --> 02:38:26.579
pools, not even anything like the

02:38:26.579 --> 02:38:28.440
beautiful flowers that decorate the rain

02:38:28.440 --> 02:38:30.540
wing village, unless you count the

02:38:30.540 --> 02:38:31.139
tapestries.

02:38:31.139 --> 02:38:33.840
I wonder if that's because the sand wing

02:38:33.840 --> 02:38:35.579
treasure is really all gone.

02:38:35.639 --> 02:38:38.700
Or perhaps sparkly things aren't burned

02:38:38.700 --> 02:38:39.420
style.

02:38:39.479 --> 02:38:42.600
She spotted a few carved statues of sand

02:38:42.600 --> 02:38:44.879
wings here and there, most of them with

02:38:44.879 --> 02:38:46.920
their wings tilted back, as if they were

02:38:46.920 --> 02:38:47.639
about to take flight.

02:38:47.700 --> 02:38:50.520
After their experience in the kingdom of

02:38:50.520 --> 02:38:51.059
the sea.

02:38:51.120 --> 02:38:53.520
Sonny had to admit that all statues made

02:38:53.520 --> 02:38:54.239
her a bit nervous.

02:38:54.360 --> 02:38:56.760
Any of them could be animas touched

02:38:56.760 --> 02:38:58.979
enchanted to do something sinister.

02:38:59.040 --> 02:39:01.739
I think I should put you in the weird

02:39:01.739 --> 02:39:02.819
Ling collection.

02:39:02.879 --> 02:39:06.059
Smolder said after a while, as if they'd

02:39:06.059 --> 02:39:07.440
been discussing her placement the entire

02:39:07.440 --> 02:39:07.860
walk.

02:39:07.920 --> 02:39:10.739
It's as safe as the dungeon, but more

02:39:10.739 --> 02:39:11.159
comfortable.

02:39:11.219 --> 02:39:13.739
Also, more psychologically

02:39:13.739 --> 02:39:14.579
destabilizing.

02:39:14.639 --> 02:39:16.079
What?

02:39:16.139 --> 02:39:17.040
Sonny said.

02:39:17.100 --> 02:39:19.500
The idea that you might actually belong

02:39:19.500 --> 02:39:20.340
somewhere like that?

02:39:20.399 --> 02:39:23.399
Smolder said, it's driven a few dragons

02:39:23.399 --> 02:39:23.819
insane.

02:39:23.879 --> 02:39:26.520
Oh, Sunny said.

02:39:26.579 --> 02:39:27.840
Sounds charming.

02:39:27.899 --> 02:39:30.840
Smolder Rumble chuckled and turned a

02:39:30.840 --> 02:39:32.940
corner, finally leading her out of the

02:39:32.940 --> 02:39:34.440
labyrinth into one of the inner

02:39:34.440 --> 02:39:34.979
courtyards.

02:39:35.100 --> 02:39:37.979
This one was surrounded on 3 sides by

02:39:37.979 --> 02:39:40.440
colonnades and balconies, with a pit of

02:39:40.440 --> 02:39:41.159
sand in the middle.

02:39:41.219 --> 02:39:43.920
Sunny slid her claws through the sand as

02:39:43.920 --> 02:39:45.959
she followed him, thinking, what if this

02:39:45.959 --> 02:39:48.600
is the last time I ever feel sand under

02:39:48.600 --> 02:39:49.079
my talons?

02:39:49.200 --> 02:39:52.079
The far wall of the courtyard was

02:39:52.079 --> 02:39:52.620
curved.

02:39:52.680 --> 02:39:55.139
And when Sonny looked up, she realized

02:39:55.139 --> 02:39:57.239
that it was actually a windowless tower

02:39:57.239 --> 02:40:00.239
of red sandstone soaring up toward the

02:40:00.239 --> 02:40:00.420
sky.

02:40:00.479 --> 02:40:02.879
It had grooves stretching the whole

02:40:02.879 --> 02:40:06.239
length of it, like claw marks, and bands

02:40:06.239 --> 02:40:08.819
of carvings, all of hideous dragon

02:40:08.819 --> 02:40:09.360
faces.

02:40:09.420 --> 02:40:12.120
There were no holes in the tower apart

02:40:12.120 --> 02:40:14.340
from one door at the bottom, and Sonny

02:40:14.340 --> 02:40:16.319
was seized with a fierce, desperate

02:40:16.319 --> 02:40:18.239
longing to stay as far away from it as

02:40:18.239 --> 02:40:18.659
possible.

02:40:18.719 --> 02:40:21.840
But of course, this was where Smolder was

02:40:21.840 --> 02:40:24.360
taking her, and of course, she had no

02:40:24.360 --> 02:40:24.659
choice.

02:40:24.719 --> 02:40:28.260
He unlocked the door with a plain silver

02:40:28.260 --> 02:40:30.780
key from a chain around his neck, picked

02:40:30.780 --> 02:40:32.100
up a bucket of water that had been

02:40:32.100 --> 02:40:34.379
waiting outside, and led her into the

02:40:34.379 --> 02:40:35.100
dark interior.

02:40:35.159 --> 02:40:38.219
At 1st she thought her eyes were dazzled

02:40:38.219 --> 02:40:41.040
by the sun, but as they adjusted, she

02:40:41.040 --> 02:40:42.959
realized that the flashes of light around

02:40:42.959 --> 02:40:45.719
her came from small mirrors embedded in

02:40:45.719 --> 02:40:47.760
the walls, which caught the reflections

02:40:47.760 --> 02:40:50.579
of bronze oil lamps, dangling at various

02:40:50.579 --> 02:40:52.440
heights on long wires from the ceiling

02:40:52.440 --> 02:40:53.639
far above.

02:40:53.819 --> 02:40:56.879
A winding ramp led from the floor around

02:40:56.879 --> 02:40:59.639
and around, up to the top of the tower.

02:40:59.700 --> 02:41:03.719
And here was Burns notorious, disturbing

02:41:03.719 --> 02:41:05.159
collection on display.

02:41:05.159 --> 02:41:08.040
Spaced at intervals along the ramp were

02:41:08.040 --> 02:41:10.680
the exhibits, Sonny caught glimpses of

02:41:10.680 --> 02:41:15.059
claws, and misshapen tales, and thought

02:41:15.059 --> 02:41:15.780
with a shudder.

02:41:15.840 --> 02:41:17.639
I'm one of them now.

02:41:17.700 --> 02:41:21.000
Right at the bottom of the ramp was a

02:41:21.000 --> 02:41:23.700
wingless white dragon, its mouth twisted

02:41:23.700 --> 02:41:25.379
open in a roar of fury.

02:41:25.440 --> 02:41:28.680
Sonny jumped back, nearly knocking

02:41:28.680 --> 02:41:31.379
smolder over before she realized the

02:41:31.379 --> 02:41:32.280
dragon was dead.

02:41:32.340 --> 02:41:35.219
And then that was actually worse, because

02:41:35.219 --> 02:41:38.340
it clearly had been alive once, before

02:41:38.340 --> 02:41:41.399
Bern slid it open, let the life pour out

02:41:41.399 --> 02:41:43.739
and then stuffed it so she could display

02:41:43.739 --> 02:41:43.920
it.

02:41:43.979 --> 02:41:46.020
Is that going to be me?

02:41:46.079 --> 02:41:49.559
Instead of saving the world, am I going

02:41:49.559 --> 02:41:51.180
to end up stuffed and mounted on a

02:41:51.180 --> 02:41:51.840
pedestal?

02:41:51.899 --> 02:41:54.540
The fear that flooded through her made

02:41:54.540 --> 02:41:56.879
her want to lie down, cover her head with

02:41:56.879 --> 02:41:59.100
her wings and scream for days.

02:41:59.159 --> 02:42:01.200
Trust in the prophecy.

02:42:01.260 --> 02:42:03.239
She told herself fiercely.

02:42:03.299 --> 02:42:04.559
I can't die here.

02:42:04.620 --> 02:42:07.200
The dragons of Pyria are counting on me.

02:42:07.319 --> 02:42:10.620
But Maro Seer's voice was still there

02:42:10.620 --> 02:42:14.639
whispering, The prophecy isn't real.

02:42:14.760 --> 02:42:18.120
And as hard as she tried, Sonny couldn't

02:42:18.120 --> 02:42:19.799
quite find that faith that had once

02:42:19.799 --> 02:42:21.000
chased out every fear.

02:42:21.059 --> 02:42:24.780
The white dragon wasn't entirely wingless

02:42:24.780 --> 02:42:25.620
she realized.

02:42:25.680 --> 02:42:28.620
It had little stubs on its back that had

02:42:28.620 --> 02:42:29.940
never grown into wings.

02:42:30.000 --> 02:42:32.219
There was something eerily sleek and

02:42:32.219 --> 02:42:33.239
snake like about it.

02:42:33.299 --> 02:42:36.719
The most truly horrifying part was the

02:42:36.719 --> 02:42:37.559
look on its face.

02:42:37.620 --> 02:42:39.840
Isn't it creepy?

02:42:39.899 --> 02:42:42.899
Smolder said in her ear, and she jumped

02:42:42.899 --> 02:42:43.139
again.

02:42:43.200 --> 02:42:46.260
Someone brought him to burn 10 years ago

02:42:46.260 --> 02:42:48.719
claiming he was the forbidden offspring

02:42:48.719 --> 02:42:51.540
of a sand wing and an ice wing, which is

02:42:51.540 --> 02:42:53.340
the right thing to say to her. even if it

02:42:53.340 --> 02:42:55.500
wasn't true, and who knows if it was

02:42:55.500 --> 02:42:58.920
because she has, let's just say, some

02:42:58.920 --> 02:43:01.680
pretty strong opinions about tribe purity

02:43:01.680 --> 02:43:03.840
and not contaminating sand wing blood

02:43:03.840 --> 02:43:05.399
with cross tribe breeding.

02:43:05.459 --> 02:43:08.579
Oh, Sonny said faintly.

02:43:08.639 --> 02:43:11.399
She thought of Starflight, who felt a

02:43:11.399 --> 02:43:12.659
1000000 miles away right now.

02:43:12.719 --> 02:43:15.299
On her list of reasons why they probably

02:43:15.299 --> 02:43:16.139
wouldn't work out.

02:43:16.200 --> 02:43:17.700
She hadn't thought to include

02:43:17.700 --> 02:43:20.159
contaminating sandwing blood.

02:43:20.280 --> 02:43:22.020
Smelder.

02:43:22.079 --> 02:43:24.600
A voice bellowed suddenly from overhead.

02:43:24.659 --> 02:43:26.340
I hear you down there.

02:43:26.399 --> 02:43:28.500
If you don't bring me more water right

02:43:28.500 --> 02:43:32.280
now, I swear, I will catch that scavenger

02:43:32.280 --> 02:43:34.200
of yours and eat her.

02:43:34.260 --> 02:43:37.379
Sonny's heart plunged through the floor.

02:43:37.440 --> 02:43:39.600
She stared at smolder in shock.

02:43:39.659 --> 02:43:41.219
She knew that voice.

02:43:41.340 --> 02:43:45.299
Queen Scarlet of the Sky Wings was alive

02:43:45.299 --> 02:43:47.760
and she was Burns prisoner too.

02:43:47.819 --> 02:43:52.079
Chapter 10.

02:43:52.440 --> 02:43:55.440
Queen Scarlet is here?

02:43:55.559 --> 02:43:58.739
Sonny whispered to Smolder. everyone's

02:43:58.739 --> 02:43:59.159
looking for her.

02:43:59.219 --> 02:44:01.799
There are dragons who think we're holding

02:44:01.799 --> 02:44:02.340
her captive.

02:44:02.399 --> 02:44:05.219
He scratched his nose with one claw

02:44:05.219 --> 02:44:05.879
inside.

02:44:06.000 --> 02:44:09.180
My sister likes to keep a close eye on

02:44:09.180 --> 02:44:09.659
her.

02:44:09.840 --> 02:44:12.120
Things, he said.

02:44:12.180 --> 02:44:14.579
The sky wing queen is a bit of a problem

02:44:14.579 --> 02:44:16.979
right now, although mostly she's a

02:44:16.979 --> 02:44:19.200
problem for me, the unlucky dragon

02:44:19.200 --> 02:44:19.739
sitter.

02:44:19.799 --> 02:44:22.319
He glanced up at the dark ceiling way

02:44:22.319 --> 02:44:24.120
above them, then peered around the

02:44:24.120 --> 02:44:25.020
floor.

02:44:25.079 --> 02:44:27.540
Flower, he shouted suddenly.

02:44:27.600 --> 02:44:29.040
Flower?

02:44:29.100 --> 02:44:31.319
He lifted a small bell from around his

02:44:31.319 --> 02:44:33.600
neck and rang it. letting the tinkling

02:44:33.600 --> 02:44:35.340
noise echo across the dark space.

02:44:35.399 --> 02:44:38.280
Something pitter pattered on the ramp

02:44:38.280 --> 02:44:40.739
above them, and after a moment, Sonny

02:44:40.739 --> 02:44:42.719
picked out a tiny figure scurrying down.

02:44:42.840 --> 02:44:46.260
That's not a dragon, she thought with

02:44:46.260 --> 02:44:46.680
surprise.

02:44:46.739 --> 02:44:51.239
It was a scavenger, alive and upright and

02:44:51.239 --> 02:44:53.579
chattering like a squirrel, bold as you

02:44:53.579 --> 02:44:55.319
please, right in the middle of the sand

02:44:55.319 --> 02:44:56.100
wing palace.

02:44:56.159 --> 02:44:58.680
It jumped down the last level to the

02:44:58.680 --> 02:45:00.600
floor and darted over to smolder.

02:45:00.659 --> 02:45:04.200
For a grim, worrying moment, Sonny

02:45:04.200 --> 02:45:05.940
expected him to rip the scavenger's head

02:45:05.940 --> 02:45:08.219
off, or offer the whole creature to her

02:45:08.219 --> 02:45:09.059
for dinner or something.

02:45:09.120 --> 02:45:13.139
Instead, the sandwing prince rested his

02:45:13.139 --> 02:45:15.120
front talons on the floor, and the

02:45:15.120 --> 02:45:16.680
scavenger clambered right onto one of

02:45:16.680 --> 02:45:19.620
them, sat down, and resumed chattering a

02:45:19.620 --> 02:45:21.780
little louder, along with some vigorous

02:45:21.780 --> 02:45:22.620
paw waving.

02:45:22.680 --> 02:45:27.299
Oh my gosh, Sonny said, momentarily

02:45:27.299 --> 02:45:28.920
distracted from Queen Scarlet.

02:45:28.979 --> 02:45:30.659
It's so cute.

02:45:30.719 --> 02:45:33.659
The scavenger looked kind of like a

02:45:33.659 --> 02:45:36.120
bigger, less hairy version of the sloths

02:45:36.120 --> 02:45:37.020
in the rainforest.

02:45:37.079 --> 02:45:39.540
It ran on its back 2 legs with easy

02:45:39.540 --> 02:45:42.239
balance, and its slender paws had no

02:45:42.239 --> 02:45:42.840
claws on them.

02:45:42.899 --> 02:45:45.479
A thatch of dark fur covered the top of

02:45:45.479 --> 02:45:47.879
its head and ran down like a mane onto

02:45:47.879 --> 02:45:48.540
its shoulders.

02:45:48.600 --> 02:45:51.420
It had a square of white fabric tied

02:45:51.420 --> 02:45:53.879
around itself that looked suspiciously as

02:45:53.879 --> 02:45:55.319
though it had been hacked off one of the

02:45:55.319 --> 02:45:58.079
main hall curtains, plus a sort of pouch

02:45:58.079 --> 02:45:59.340
bag made of the same material.

02:45:59.399 --> 02:46:02.100
I know, isn't she?

02:46:02.100 --> 02:46:03.360
said Smolder.

02:46:03.479 --> 02:46:04.979
That's what I've been saying.

02:46:05.040 --> 02:46:06.959
I have to watch her carefully though.

02:46:07.020 --> 02:46:09.540
Several dragons would be perfectly happy

02:46:09.540 --> 02:46:11.100
to eat her if they caught her alone.

02:46:11.159 --> 02:46:14.399
This is one place I figure she's safe.

02:46:14.459 --> 02:46:17.520
He lifted her up to his snout, and the

02:46:17.520 --> 02:46:19.440
scavenger leaned forward to bump noses

02:46:19.440 --> 02:46:20.219
with him.

02:46:20.280 --> 02:46:21.840
Where did you get her?

02:46:21.959 --> 02:46:22.920
Sonny asked.

02:46:22.979 --> 02:46:24.840
And why do you call her flower?

02:46:24.899 --> 02:46:27.659
Smolder reached around and set this

02:46:27.659 --> 02:46:29.579
scavenger on the back of his neck, where

02:46:29.579 --> 02:46:31.559
she grabbed onto his spikes and balanced

02:46:31.559 --> 02:46:32.700
as he started up the ramp.

02:46:32.760 --> 02:46:35.819
Sonny trailed behind him, wondering if

02:46:35.819 --> 02:46:37.079
this might be a good time to make a run

02:46:37.079 --> 02:46:37.440
for it.

02:46:37.500 --> 02:46:39.899
But she was pretty sure the tower door

02:46:39.899 --> 02:46:40.739
had locked behind them.

02:46:40.799 --> 02:46:44.280
We had some scavenger visitors about 20

02:46:44.280 --> 02:46:44.760
years ago.

02:46:44.819 --> 02:46:46.739
You may have heard about that.

02:46:46.799 --> 02:46:49.379
Smolder said in his sarcastic voice.

02:46:49.500 --> 02:46:53.879
This is the one who didn't escape. 20

02:46:53.879 --> 02:46:54.780
years ago?

02:46:54.840 --> 02:46:57.299
It took Sonny a moment to realize what he

02:46:57.299 --> 02:46:57.780
must mean.

02:46:57.840 --> 02:47:01.379
Wait, visitors plural?

02:47:01.440 --> 02:47:02.520
Sonny asked.

02:47:02.579 --> 02:47:04.920
I thought it was just one scavenger who

02:47:04.920 --> 02:47:06.540
killed the queen and stole the treasure.

02:47:06.600 --> 02:47:09.540
They passed a fish tank, glowing with a

02:47:09.540 --> 02:47:11.459
greenish light that seemed to be coming

02:47:11.459 --> 02:47:13.020
from the sea creatures themselves.

02:47:13.079 --> 02:47:15.719
There were fish with bulging eyes and

02:47:15.719 --> 02:47:18.600
extra flippers, seahorses with fangs

02:47:18.600 --> 02:47:22.139
snails that oozed purple ichor, and an

02:47:22.139 --> 02:47:23.879
octopus kind of thing with at least 20

02:47:23.879 --> 02:47:26.399
arms that was busily occupied with

02:47:26.399 --> 02:47:28.620
crushing up seashells and dropping them

02:47:28.620 --> 02:47:30.120
into its black beak of a mouth.

02:47:30.180 --> 02:47:35.520
Nope, said Smolder. 3 scavengers. 2

02:47:35.520 --> 02:47:36.540
escaped with a treasure.

02:47:36.600 --> 02:47:38.280
But we caught this one trying to hide

02:47:38.280 --> 02:47:39.780
just outside the palace.

02:47:39.840 --> 02:47:42.120
Burn was going to put her head on a spike

02:47:42.120 --> 02:47:44.700
on the wall and eat the rest, but I

02:47:44.700 --> 02:47:45.840
decided I wanted to keep her.

02:47:45.899 --> 02:47:49.020
And at the time, I had other dragons to

02:47:49.020 --> 02:47:49.559
back me up.

02:47:49.680 --> 02:47:52.920
He took a deep breath and folded his

02:47:52.920 --> 02:47:54.840
wings back into a tent over the scavenger

02:47:54.840 --> 02:47:57.000
for a moment before tucking them into his

02:47:57.000 --> 02:47:57.420
side again.

02:47:57.479 --> 02:48:00.840
Blister argued that a scavenger head on a

02:48:00.840 --> 02:48:02.219
spike wouldn't impress anyone.

02:48:02.280 --> 02:48:04.920
In fact, it would just remind everyone of

02:48:04.920 --> 02:48:06.180
mother's embarrassing death.

02:48:06.239 --> 02:48:07.739
He went on.

02:48:07.799 --> 02:48:10.799
Blaise thought flour was cued too, and

02:48:10.799 --> 02:48:12.180
wanted to see if we could get another

02:48:12.180 --> 02:48:14.159
scavenger and breed them to make more

02:48:14.159 --> 02:48:14.639
pets.

02:48:14.700 --> 02:48:17.159
And my brother said I should get to have

02:48:17.159 --> 02:48:19.319
one thing I wanted, now that mother

02:48:19.319 --> 02:48:21.239
wasn't around to keep making me unhappy.

02:48:21.299 --> 02:48:24.959
He paused, and Sonny glanced up at him.

02:48:25.020 --> 02:48:27.000
She got the feeling it wouldn't be a good

02:48:27.000 --> 02:48:29.159
idea to ask any questions about Oasis.

02:48:29.219 --> 02:48:31.079
Smolder!

02:48:31.139 --> 02:48:33.899
Queen Scarlet bellowed again, and a burst

02:48:33.899 --> 02:48:35.639
of fire lit out the tower from an upper

02:48:35.639 --> 02:48:35.879
level.

02:48:35.940 --> 02:48:37.739
Coming.

02:48:37.799 --> 02:48:40.440
He called politely, then carried on

02:48:40.440 --> 02:48:42.000
talking to Sonny as if there were really

02:48:42.000 --> 02:48:42.840
no hurry at all.

02:48:42.899 --> 02:48:45.780
Anyway, they voted to let me keep her.

02:48:45.840 --> 02:48:47.819
And by now, burn is used to her.

02:48:47.879 --> 02:48:50.760
I was going to call her stabby.

02:48:50.819 --> 02:48:52.860
She was pretty fierce with this little

02:48:52.860 --> 02:48:54.899
sword she was carrying before we took it

02:48:54.899 --> 02:48:55.260
off her.

02:48:55.319 --> 02:48:57.540
But then she found a tapestry with some

02:48:57.540 --> 02:48:59.520
flowers on it and kept pointing to them

02:48:59.520 --> 02:49:01.500
and then to herself.

02:49:01.559 --> 02:49:02.879
So I think she wants me to call her

02:49:02.879 --> 02:49:03.479
flower.

02:49:03.540 --> 02:49:06.540
Although all her chattering noises sound

02:49:06.540 --> 02:49:07.079
the same to me.

02:49:07.139 --> 02:49:10.379
Sunny glanced at another glass exhibit

02:49:10.379 --> 02:49:13.020
case as they walked by, and then really

02:49:13.020 --> 02:49:13.979
wished she hadn't.

02:49:14.040 --> 02:49:17.760
Inside were lots of parts of dragons

02:49:17.760 --> 02:49:21.239
webbed sea wing talons, a few tongues

02:49:21.239 --> 02:49:24.540
with 3 forks instead of two, half a wing

02:49:24.540 --> 02:49:27.000
that was speckled purple and gray, unlike

02:49:27.000 --> 02:49:29.879
any dragons she'd ever seen, a coil of

02:49:29.879 --> 02:49:32.280
tail with strange lichens growing on it

02:49:32.280 --> 02:49:34.739
and a number of oddly bent teeth and

02:49:34.739 --> 02:49:35.219
claws.

02:49:35.280 --> 02:49:38.579
She shuddered and dragged her focus back

02:49:38.579 --> 02:49:39.840
to smolder and flower.

02:49:39.899 --> 02:49:42.540
I've never heard of an animal choosing

02:49:42.540 --> 02:49:44.399
its own name before. she said.

02:49:44.459 --> 02:49:46.559
But then, I've never heard of anyone

02:49:46.559 --> 02:49:48.479
keeping a scavenger as a pet either.

02:49:48.540 --> 02:49:52.020
The only pets, she stopped, and clapped

02:49:52.020 --> 02:49:53.579
her front talons over her mouth in

02:49:53.579 --> 02:49:54.059
horror.

02:49:54.120 --> 02:49:57.180
She'd nearly mentioned the rain wings and

02:49:57.180 --> 02:49:59.340
their pet sloths, which could have given

02:49:59.340 --> 02:50:00.840
away exactly where her friends were.

02:50:00.899 --> 02:50:04.920
Stupid, stupid, stupid, sonny.

02:50:04.979 --> 02:50:06.780
She scolded herself.

02:50:06.840 --> 02:50:08.459
Be more careful about what you say.

02:50:08.520 --> 02:50:14.280
The only pets smolder echoed, giving her

02:50:14.280 --> 02:50:14.879
a curious look.

02:50:14.940 --> 02:50:17.940
The only pets I've ever heard of are kept

02:50:17.940 --> 02:50:20.700
by scavengers, Sonny said quickly.

02:50:20.760 --> 02:50:24.780
Ah, yes, said Smoulder, and for the 1st

02:50:24.780 --> 02:50:26.459
time, his voice was affectionate instead

02:50:26.459 --> 02:50:27.239
of sardonic.

02:50:27.299 --> 02:50:30.180
Flower likes mice, and she's always

02:50:30.180 --> 02:50:31.860
feeding any birds that dare to come down

02:50:31.860 --> 02:50:32.639
into the courtyards.

02:50:32.760 --> 02:50:35.760
He lifted one of his claws, and the

02:50:35.760 --> 02:50:37.979
scavenger patted it, as if to reassure

02:50:37.979 --> 02:50:38.700
him she was still there.

02:50:38.760 --> 02:50:40.559
Does she?

02:50:40.620 --> 02:50:42.299
Understand you?

02:50:42.360 --> 02:50:43.500
Sonny asked.

02:50:43.559 --> 02:50:47.760
Of course not, but she's very clever, he

02:50:47.760 --> 02:50:48.000
said.

02:50:48.059 --> 02:50:50.280
I trained her to come when I ring this

02:50:50.280 --> 02:50:52.139
bell, and I taught her to draw.

02:50:52.200 --> 02:50:54.000
So she can draw pictures of anything she

02:50:54.000 --> 02:50:54.239
needs.

02:50:54.299 --> 02:50:56.459
She can draw?

02:50:56.520 --> 02:50:58.860
Sonny said, fascinated.

02:50:58.920 --> 02:51:01.559
She'd learned to write and draw with a

02:51:01.559 --> 02:51:03.059
paintbrush that was more than half this

02:51:03.059 --> 02:51:05.399
scavenger's thighs with what?

02:51:05.459 --> 02:51:08.879
She made herself this adorable tiny

02:51:08.879 --> 02:51:09.540
paintbrush.

02:51:09.600 --> 02:51:11.040
She likes to make things.

02:51:11.100 --> 02:51:13.079
Smolder said proudly.

02:51:13.139 --> 02:51:15.360
She's also made all these cute little

02:51:15.360 --> 02:51:16.500
costumes for herself.

02:51:16.559 --> 02:51:17.520
Don't ask me why.

02:51:17.579 --> 02:51:20.280
It's like how birds build nests, I think

02:51:20.280 --> 02:51:23.579
all instinct, but really endearing.

02:51:23.639 --> 02:51:25.860
Although Burne complains that she's worse

02:51:25.860 --> 02:51:28.079
than moths, leaving holes in all our

02:51:28.079 --> 02:51:28.500
curtains.

02:51:28.559 --> 02:51:31.559
I'd call it resourceful, if anyone asked

02:51:31.559 --> 02:51:31.799
me.

02:51:31.860 --> 02:51:33.600
Resourceful?

02:51:33.659 --> 02:51:37.260
I'll say, Sonny thought, remembering the

02:51:37.260 --> 02:51:38.940
burnt out village as well.

02:51:39.000 --> 02:51:41.159
She gave the scavenger an appraising look

02:51:41.159 --> 02:51:43.860
and the scavenger stared back at her with

02:51:43.860 --> 02:51:46.920
those dragon like brown eyes, deeper and

02:51:46.920 --> 02:51:47.940
wiser than you'd expect.

02:51:48.000 --> 02:51:51.059
What's going on in that tiny head?

02:51:51.120 --> 02:51:52.379
Sonny wondered?

02:51:52.500 --> 02:51:54.659
Her brain can't be any bigger than a

02:51:54.659 --> 02:51:56.819
grapefruit, but maybe it works in

02:51:56.819 --> 02:51:58.139
mysterious ways.

02:51:58.200 --> 02:52:00.659
Maybe scavengers are cleverer than they

02:52:00.659 --> 02:52:00.899
seem.

02:52:00.959 --> 02:52:04.440
Another dragon suddenly loomed out of the

02:52:04.440 --> 02:52:06.659
shadows, but Sonny was able to stop

02:52:06.659 --> 02:52:08.340
herself from flinching away this time.

02:52:08.459 --> 02:52:11.819
It was another stuffed specimen, this

02:52:11.819 --> 02:52:14.819
time a mud wing, with striated red lines

02:52:14.819 --> 02:52:16.440
along his outstretched wings.

02:52:16.500 --> 02:52:19.979
He had no claws, no teeth, and a puzzled

02:52:19.979 --> 02:52:20.459
expression.

02:52:20.520 --> 02:52:23.819
Three moons, Sonny said.

02:52:23.879 --> 02:52:25.139
What happened to him?

02:52:25.200 --> 02:52:28.500
The seller said his egg was animus

02:52:28.500 --> 02:52:31.920
touched, Smolder said, or rather, animus

02:52:31.920 --> 02:52:34.079
cursed, some kind of vengeance thing

02:52:34.079 --> 02:52:34.379
maybe?

02:52:34.440 --> 02:52:36.780
Who would want a dragonette without claws

02:52:36.780 --> 02:52:37.200
or teeth?

02:52:37.260 --> 02:52:38.340
How could he live?

02:52:38.399 --> 02:52:40.620
He was destined to end up here

02:52:40.620 --> 02:52:40.979
eventually.

02:52:41.040 --> 02:52:42.659
Like me.

02:52:42.719 --> 02:52:44.940
Sonny thought despite herself.

02:52:45.000 --> 02:52:46.379
Weird looking.

02:52:46.440 --> 02:52:48.180
No other use for me.

02:52:48.239 --> 02:52:49.559
Stop that.

02:52:49.620 --> 02:52:51.959
You have a real destiny.

02:52:52.020 --> 02:52:54.959
She tilted her head at the sad, stuffed

02:52:54.959 --> 02:52:55.739
dragon.

02:52:55.799 --> 02:52:57.180
Animus touched?

02:52:57.239 --> 02:52:59.579
Could that be what happened to my egg?

02:52:59.639 --> 02:53:02.579
Did some dragon do this to me before I

02:53:02.579 --> 02:53:03.479
was hatched?

02:53:03.540 --> 02:53:04.500
Deliberately?

02:53:04.559 --> 02:53:05.819
But who?

02:53:05.879 --> 02:53:07.319
And why?

02:53:07.379 --> 02:53:09.959
Her mind flashed back to the questions

02:53:09.959 --> 02:53:12.180
Thorn had asked the night wings.

02:53:12.299 --> 02:53:14.340
She was looking for a night wing named

02:53:14.340 --> 02:53:15.360
Stone Mover.

02:53:15.420 --> 02:53:18.239
That sure sounded like an animus name.

02:53:18.239 --> 02:53:20.700
What if he did something to my egg?

02:53:20.760 --> 02:53:23.760
She was so preoccupied with this question

02:53:23.760 --> 02:53:25.979
that when they came within sight of an

02:53:25.979 --> 02:53:28.139
orange dragon, she assumed it was another

02:53:28.139 --> 02:53:30.479
stuffed specimen and barely glanced at

02:53:30.479 --> 02:53:30.600
it.

02:53:30.719 --> 02:53:33.479
But then the dragon lunged at them with a

02:53:33.479 --> 02:53:36.180
furious hiss, and smolder backed up in a

02:53:36.180 --> 02:53:38.399
hurry, nearly knocking Sonny off the

02:53:38.399 --> 02:53:39.120
winding ramp.

02:53:39.180 --> 02:53:41.700
She dug her talons into the cracks in the

02:53:41.700 --> 02:53:43.799
stone as her heart tried to leap out of

02:53:43.799 --> 02:53:44.219
her chest.

02:53:44.280 --> 02:53:47.520
Smolder.

02:53:47.579 --> 02:53:49.739
Queen Scarlet hissed.

02:53:49.799 --> 02:53:50.819
Finally.

02:53:50.940 --> 02:53:54.360
Coils of smoke wreathed around her horns

02:53:54.360 --> 02:53:55.979
but they couldn't hide what was

02:53:55.979 --> 02:53:58.319
underneath, how the side of the sky

02:53:58.319 --> 02:54:00.420
wing's face was melted into a hideous

02:54:00.420 --> 02:54:03.000
dark mess, revealing a glimpse of her

02:54:03.000 --> 02:54:05.399
jawbone underneath, and pulling one of

02:54:05.399 --> 02:54:07.139
her yellow eyes down and out of

02:54:07.139 --> 02:54:08.700
proportion with the rest of her face.

02:54:08.760 --> 02:54:11.520
The rubies that had been embedded in her

02:54:11.520 --> 02:54:14.639
scales, were gone above that eye, and so

02:54:14.639 --> 02:54:17.040
were all her earlier adornments, the

02:54:17.040 --> 02:54:19.920
golden chain mail, the medallions, the

02:54:19.920 --> 02:54:22.260
rings on her claws, the rubies on her

02:54:22.260 --> 02:54:24.840
wings, the only jewels left were the tiny

02:54:24.840 --> 02:54:26.879
rubies above her good eye, which

02:54:26.879 --> 02:54:28.860
glittered malevolently in the dim light.

02:54:28.920 --> 02:54:32.639
The last time they'd been face to face, it

02:54:32.639 --> 02:54:34.079
had been through the bars of a cage.

02:54:34.139 --> 02:54:37.440
Sonny had been the prisoner, and Scarlett

02:54:37.440 --> 02:54:39.059
had been one of the most beautiful

02:54:39.059 --> 02:54:40.799
powerful dragons in Pyria.

02:54:40.860 --> 02:54:44.520
No wonder she hates us, Sonny thought.

02:54:44.579 --> 02:54:47.100
But glory did this to her to save the

02:54:47.100 --> 02:54:47.399
rest of us.

02:54:47.459 --> 02:54:49.799
We'd all be dead by now otherwise.

02:54:49.860 --> 02:54:54.299
Here's your water, Smolder said, setting

02:54:54.299 --> 02:54:56.700
the pail down on a claw scratched X on

02:54:56.700 --> 02:54:57.000
the floor.

02:54:57.059 --> 02:55:00.840
The queen snatched the pail, and Sonny

02:55:00.840 --> 02:55:03.000
realized that the ex marked the very

02:55:03.000 --> 02:55:03.780
limit of her reach.

02:55:03.840 --> 02:55:06.299
Heavy chains kept her from moving any

02:55:06.299 --> 02:55:06.540
farther.

02:55:06.600 --> 02:55:10.200
On the other side of the X, littering the

02:55:10.200 --> 02:55:13.020
floor around Scarlet's claws, were shards

02:55:13.020 --> 02:55:15.180
of shattered glass, and puddles of

02:55:15.180 --> 02:55:16.379
glowing green slime.

02:55:16.440 --> 02:55:18.899
Here and there in the puddles lay the

02:55:18.899 --> 02:55:20.459
corpses of peculiar insects.

02:55:20.520 --> 02:55:22.620
Sonny could see oddly bulging

02:55:22.620 --> 02:55:25.500
caterpillars, nine legged hairy spiders

02:55:25.500 --> 02:55:27.719
and a bright blue dragonfly whose back

02:55:27.719 --> 02:55:29.700
bristled with sharp needle spines.

02:55:29.819 --> 02:55:32.879
When are you going to clean this up?

02:55:32.940 --> 02:55:35.159
Scarlet snapped at smolder.

02:55:35.219 --> 02:55:37.500
Her snout dripping as she came up for air

02:55:37.500 --> 02:55:38.219
from the bucket.

02:55:38.280 --> 02:55:41.760
There's slime on my beautiful tail, and I

02:55:41.760 --> 02:55:43.620
keep finding bits of horrible bugs in

02:55:43.620 --> 02:55:44.760
between my scales.

02:55:44.819 --> 02:55:46.139
He snorted.

02:55:46.260 --> 02:55:48.959
Perhaps, you should have thought of that

02:55:48.959 --> 02:55:51.420
before smashing up your host's prized

02:55:51.420 --> 02:55:52.379
collection.

02:55:52.440 --> 02:55:55.079
He nodded at something lumpy, glittering

02:55:55.079 --> 02:55:56.280
in the shadows behind her.

02:55:56.340 --> 02:55:58.799
Burn is going to be especially upset

02:55:58.799 --> 02:56:00.059
about her night wing.

02:56:00.120 --> 02:56:02.100
They're not exactly easy to replace.

02:56:02.159 --> 02:56:05.639
Sonny realized that Scarlet must have

02:56:05.639 --> 02:56:07.920
been chained up near a stuffed night wing

02:56:07.920 --> 02:56:10.379
which she had then clawed and shredded in

02:56:10.379 --> 02:56:11.579
a fit of rage.

02:56:11.639 --> 02:56:12.840
Sonny shuddered.

02:56:12.899 --> 02:56:14.700
Scarlet lashed her tail.

02:56:14.760 --> 02:56:17.700
I'll get to the rest of her toys too.

02:56:17.760 --> 02:56:19.440
Once I'm free.

02:56:19.500 --> 02:56:21.659
Scarlet.

02:56:21.719 --> 02:56:23.639
Smolder said patiently.

02:56:23.700 --> 02:56:25.979
We are not keeping you prisoner.

02:56:26.040 --> 02:56:27.840
We're keeping you safe.

02:56:27.959 --> 02:56:30.780
If you were in your own kingdom right now

02:56:30.780 --> 02:56:31.200
you'd be dead.

02:56:31.319 --> 02:56:33.659
You're in no condition to fight Ruby for

02:56:33.659 --> 02:56:34.139
the throne.

02:56:34.200 --> 02:56:37.440
That's Queen Scarlet to you.

02:56:37.500 --> 02:56:39.299
She said fiercely.

02:56:39.360 --> 02:56:42.360
Her gaze moved to Sonny, and then she

02:56:42.360 --> 02:56:43.860
swiveled her head to stare with her good

02:56:43.860 --> 02:56:44.100
eye.

02:56:44.159 --> 02:56:46.680
Sonny took an involuntary step back

02:56:46.680 --> 02:56:47.459
behind smolder.

02:56:47.520 --> 02:56:49.500
I know her.

02:56:49.559 --> 02:56:51.299
Scarlet growled.

02:56:51.360 --> 02:56:53.639
That dragon is mine.

02:56:53.700 --> 02:56:56.760
I am not, Sonny retorted.

02:56:56.819 --> 02:56:58.440
I'm not anybody's.

02:56:58.559 --> 02:57:02.100
I know where your rain wing friend is.

02:57:02.219 --> 02:57:05.760
The queen snarled, pacing to the end of

02:57:05.760 --> 02:57:07.319
her chains and glaring at Sonny.

02:57:07.379 --> 02:57:10.799
As soon as I am free, she is dead.

02:57:10.860 --> 02:57:14.040
Then I hope you stay locked in here

02:57:14.040 --> 02:57:15.840
forever, Sonny snapped.

02:57:15.899 --> 02:57:18.600
I have friends too.

02:57:18.659 --> 02:57:20.579
Scarlet hissed.

02:57:20.639 --> 02:57:22.379
I won't be here much longer.

02:57:22.440 --> 02:57:26.040
Sonny looked up at Smolder, but his

02:57:26.040 --> 02:57:27.840
expression was more tired than worried.

02:57:27.899 --> 02:57:30.659
Come along, he said to Sonny.

02:57:30.719 --> 02:57:32.340
We have to fly around her.

02:57:32.399 --> 02:57:34.739
I know it's inconvenient, but I'm not

02:57:34.739 --> 02:57:36.479
taking responsibility for unchaining

02:57:36.479 --> 02:57:36.780
her.

02:57:36.840 --> 02:57:39.299
Burn can move her when she gets here, if

02:57:39.299 --> 02:57:39.959
she wants to.

02:57:40.020 --> 02:57:42.780
He spread his wings and soared over

02:57:42.780 --> 02:57:45.540
scarlet to the next level up, with flour

02:57:45.540 --> 02:57:47.579
clinging tightly to his neck.

02:57:47.639 --> 02:57:50.340
Sonny followed, a bit nervously, her

02:57:50.340 --> 02:57:52.260
wings brushing the walls as she tried to

02:57:52.260 --> 02:57:54.000
stay as far out of scarlet to reach as

02:57:54.000 --> 02:57:54.360
possible.

02:57:54.420 --> 02:57:57.780
They landed close to the top of the tower

02:57:57.780 --> 02:58:00.360
where the light was dimmest, and Sonny

02:58:00.360 --> 02:58:02.459
saw with a sinking heart that there were

02:58:02.459 --> 02:58:05.159
chains just like scarlet's here, waiting

02:58:05.159 --> 02:58:05.639
for her.

02:58:05.700 --> 02:58:08.700
They lay collapsed on the ground like

02:58:08.700 --> 02:58:11.100
dead snakeskins, and they clanked

02:58:11.100 --> 02:58:12.600
horribly as smolder picked them up.

02:58:12.659 --> 02:58:15.719
Sonny curled her tail around her talons

02:58:15.719 --> 02:58:18.540
and looked at them for a moment, breathing

02:58:18.540 --> 02:58:19.799
deeply to calm herself.

02:58:19.860 --> 02:58:22.680
She looked up, and met Smolder's eyes.

02:58:22.799 --> 02:58:25.379
Do I really have to stay here?

02:58:25.440 --> 02:58:27.000
She asked quietly.

02:58:27.059 --> 02:58:30.780
Smolder hesitated, with a chain draped

02:58:30.780 --> 02:58:31.860
across his front talons.

02:58:31.920 --> 02:58:34.739
Flower looked from him to Sonny, then

02:58:34.739 --> 02:58:35.459
slipped off his back.

02:58:35.579 --> 02:58:38.639
To Sonny's surprise, the little scavenger

02:58:38.639 --> 02:58:40.920
came right up and patted Sonny on the

02:58:40.920 --> 02:58:41.520
side of her neck.

02:58:41.579 --> 02:58:43.440
She didn't have to be able to talk.

02:58:43.559 --> 02:58:46.680
The gesture said clearly, don't worry

02:58:46.680 --> 02:58:47.760
you'll be all right.

02:58:47.819 --> 02:58:50.700
As clearly as if the scavenger had had a

02:58:50.700 --> 02:58:52.860
tail to twine around Sonny's.

02:58:52.920 --> 02:58:55.260
It's not like I have much choice.

02:58:55.319 --> 02:58:58.440
Smolder said, I can't imagine what else

02:58:58.440 --> 02:58:58.979
to do with you.

02:58:59.040 --> 02:59:01.079
It's just...

02:59:01.079 --> 02:59:03.780
Really dark, Sunny said.

02:59:03.840 --> 02:59:06.360
Her scales were practically crying out

02:59:06.360 --> 02:59:08.520
for the sunlight right beyond these walls

02:59:08.520 --> 02:59:10.739
but more than that, the thing she

02:59:10.739 --> 02:59:12.840
couldn't bring herself to say, was that

02:59:12.840 --> 02:59:14.579
she could already tell that being in here

02:59:14.579 --> 02:59:17.879
too long would carve out her soul, one

02:59:17.879 --> 02:59:20.760
miserable moment at a time, until she'd

02:59:20.760 --> 02:59:22.620
be as empty and hopeless as one of the

02:59:22.620 --> 02:59:23.700
stuffed dragons.

02:59:23.760 --> 02:59:26.579
I know, Smolders said.

02:59:26.639 --> 02:59:29.459
And Sonny sensed the 1st hint of possible

02:59:29.459 --> 02:59:31.260
compassion in his voice.

02:59:31.319 --> 02:59:33.059
She wondered if it was partly because

02:59:33.059 --> 02:59:34.440
Flower felt sorry for her.

02:59:34.500 --> 02:59:37.920
Tell you what, he said after a pause.

02:59:37.979 --> 02:59:41.100
I'll think about it tonight and see if I

02:59:41.100 --> 02:59:41.940
can come up with something else

02:59:41.940 --> 02:59:42.360
tomorrow.

02:59:42.479 --> 02:59:45.180
If not, I'll take you out for a bit at

02:59:45.180 --> 02:59:45.659
midday.

02:59:45.719 --> 02:59:47.639
At least let you stretch your wings in

02:59:47.639 --> 02:59:48.000
the sun.

02:59:48.059 --> 02:59:50.459
As long as you promise not to escape.

02:59:50.520 --> 02:59:51.239
Deal?

02:59:51.360 --> 02:59:54.059
Sure, Sunny said.

02:59:54.120 --> 02:59:55.020
Thank you.

02:59:55.079 --> 02:59:57.899
It wasn't much, but it sounded like the

02:59:57.899 --> 02:59:58.860
best she could hope for.

02:59:58.920 --> 03:00:02.159
He clamped the chains around her ankles

03:00:02.159 --> 03:00:03.840
locking them with another one of the keys

03:00:03.840 --> 03:00:04.620
around his neck.

03:00:04.680 --> 03:00:07.920
Sonny turned her head away, unwilling to

03:00:07.920 --> 03:00:09.899
watch herself made a prisoner yet again

03:00:09.899 --> 03:00:12.420
and spotted a large box tucked against

03:00:12.420 --> 03:00:14.940
the wall not far away, at the very end of

03:00:14.940 --> 03:00:15.899
the spiraling ramp.

03:00:15.959 --> 03:00:17.639
What's that?

03:00:17.639 --> 03:00:18.540
she asked.

03:00:18.600 --> 03:00:21.959
Something new for Burns collection

03:00:21.959 --> 03:00:24.360
Smolders said, glancing up at it.

03:00:24.420 --> 03:00:27.360
The dragon who came by to sell it claims

03:00:27.360 --> 03:00:29.639
it's something rare and priceless, and

03:00:29.639 --> 03:00:31.860
that Byrne will definitely want it, but

03:00:31.860 --> 03:00:33.600
that it might die as soon as we open the

03:00:33.600 --> 03:00:33.780
box.

03:00:33.840 --> 03:00:36.540
So I'm leaving it closed until burn gets

03:00:36.540 --> 03:00:37.979
here, and she can decide what to do with

03:00:37.979 --> 03:00:38.159
it.

03:00:38.219 --> 03:00:40.440
You don't even know what it is?

03:00:40.500 --> 03:00:41.579
Sonny asked.

03:00:41.639 --> 03:00:43.440
What if it's an empty box?

03:00:43.500 --> 03:00:48.059
Then I'll get yelled at, Smolder said, but

03:00:48.059 --> 03:00:50.280
he'll get hunted down and killed, so I

03:00:50.280 --> 03:00:51.059
doubt he'd risk it.

03:00:51.120 --> 03:00:53.879
Dragons have tried to trick burn before

03:00:53.879 --> 03:00:57.059
sowing odd animal parts together, dying

03:00:57.059 --> 03:01:00.120
normal insects, strange colors, and it

03:01:00.120 --> 03:01:02.459
has always proven to be a very bad idea.

03:01:02.520 --> 03:01:05.399
Besides, he haggled so hard over the

03:01:05.399 --> 03:01:07.559
price, he nearly refused to give it to

03:01:07.559 --> 03:01:07.739
me.

03:01:07.799 --> 03:01:10.020
It must be something pretty unusual.

03:01:10.079 --> 03:01:13.379
Also, it keeps making this strange, high

03:01:13.379 --> 03:01:14.940
pitched hissing noise.

03:01:15.000 --> 03:01:18.239
He gave her a sharp look as he snapped

03:01:18.239 --> 03:01:21.180
the last chain on, don't get any ideas

03:01:21.180 --> 03:01:22.920
from Scarlet's bed behavior.

03:01:22.979 --> 03:01:25.500
My sister has reasons to keep the sky

03:01:25.500 --> 03:01:26.579
wing queen alive.

03:01:26.639 --> 03:01:29.159
She has a lot more reasons to make you

03:01:29.159 --> 03:01:29.639
dead.

03:01:29.700 --> 03:01:31.559
So don't add to them.

03:01:31.680 --> 03:01:35.159
Sonny nodded, not trusting herself to

03:01:35.159 --> 03:01:35.399
speak.

03:01:35.459 --> 03:01:37.620
This was the nightmare.

03:01:37.680 --> 03:01:39.899
The situation she and her friends had

03:01:39.899 --> 03:01:40.500
always feared.

03:01:40.620 --> 03:01:44.159
She was in Burns clutches now, and she

03:01:44.159 --> 03:01:45.780
couldn't think of any possible way she

03:01:45.780 --> 03:01:46.139
might escape.

03:01:46.200 --> 03:01:50.760
I'll be back before you know it, Smolders

03:01:50.760 --> 03:01:51.000
said.

03:01:51.059 --> 03:01:53.280
He dipped his wing toward the scavenger.

03:01:53.340 --> 03:01:54.659
Up flower.

03:01:54.719 --> 03:01:56.940
The little creature looked up at Sonny

03:01:56.940 --> 03:01:58.920
with her thoughtful brown eyes, then

03:01:58.920 --> 03:02:01.020
patted Sonny's side again and sat down.

03:02:01.079 --> 03:02:03.840
Smolder tipped his head sideways and

03:02:03.840 --> 03:02:04.440
peered at her.

03:02:04.500 --> 03:02:06.719
Flower, come along.

03:02:06.780 --> 03:02:09.540
He rang his bell and held out his claws.

03:02:09.659 --> 03:02:12.600
Flowers shook her head firmly and put one

03:02:12.600 --> 03:02:14.579
paw on one of Sonny's front talons.

03:02:14.639 --> 03:02:18.360
She wants to stay with you, Smolder

03:02:18.360 --> 03:02:18.600
said.

03:02:18.659 --> 03:02:19.979
That's funny.

03:02:20.040 --> 03:02:22.559
Flower is usually extremely cautious

03:02:22.559 --> 03:02:24.239
around any dragon who's not me.

03:02:24.299 --> 03:02:26.520
He narrowed his eyes at Sonny.

03:02:26.579 --> 03:02:29.159
If I leave her with you, will you be

03:02:29.159 --> 03:02:29.760
careful with her?

03:02:29.819 --> 03:02:32.399
No knocking her off the ramp, no stepping

03:02:32.399 --> 03:02:35.579
on her, indefinitely, no eating her.

03:02:35.639 --> 03:02:38.700
I wouldn't eat her, Sonny protested.

03:02:38.760 --> 03:02:41.819
I barely even like meat, except sometimes

03:02:41.819 --> 03:02:44.219
a lizard here or there, and I think she's

03:02:44.219 --> 03:02:44.760
being really sweet.

03:02:44.819 --> 03:02:47.579
There was something comforting about the

03:02:47.579 --> 03:02:49.319
idea of having someone with her in this

03:02:49.319 --> 03:02:53.040
dark tower, apart from Queen Scarlet, even

03:02:53.040 --> 03:02:54.239
if it was a scavenger.

03:02:54.239 --> 03:02:57.899
Whoa, Smolder said fidgeting.

03:02:57.959 --> 03:02:59.760
If you promise to be careful.

03:02:59.819 --> 03:03:02.219
Flower, are you sure?

03:03:02.280 --> 03:03:05.639
Flower kept her paw unsunny, and stared

03:03:05.639 --> 03:03:06.600
back at him without moving.

03:03:06.659 --> 03:03:09.420
All right, he sighed.

03:03:09.479 --> 03:03:10.680
See you soon.

03:03:10.799 --> 03:03:13.739
He lifted off the edge and flew in a

03:03:13.739 --> 03:03:15.360
gentle spiral down to the bottom of the

03:03:15.360 --> 03:03:15.719
tower.

03:03:15.780 --> 03:03:18.840
Sonny leaned out, and saw the shaft of

03:03:18.840 --> 03:03:20.639
sunlight that spilled into the room as he

03:03:20.639 --> 03:03:22.799
opened the door, and then saw it

03:03:22.799 --> 03:03:24.959
disappear again as the door slammed

03:03:24.959 --> 03:03:25.559
behind him.

03:03:25.620 --> 03:03:27.899
The weight around her ankles felt

03:03:27.899 --> 03:03:29.340
suddenly even heavier.

03:03:29.399 --> 03:03:32.219
She rested her head on her front talons

03:03:32.219 --> 03:03:34.739
with a sigh, curling her tail in close.

03:03:34.860 --> 03:03:37.379
Flower immediately tucked herself into

03:03:37.379 --> 03:03:39.840
the curve of sunny side, reached into her

03:03:39.840 --> 03:03:41.940
bag, and pulled out a scrap of scroll

03:03:41.940 --> 03:03:43.739
paper and a lumpy stick of charcoal.

03:03:43.799 --> 03:03:46.979
In the dim light, she started to sketch

03:03:46.979 --> 03:03:49.979
and sunny, peering over her shoulder, saw

03:03:49.979 --> 03:03:52.020
a dragon's face appearing in rapid

03:03:52.020 --> 03:03:52.620
strokes.

03:03:52.680 --> 03:03:54.239
Her face, in fact.

03:03:54.299 --> 03:03:57.959
That's amazing, Seni said.

03:03:58.020 --> 03:04:00.239
How could an animal create art like

03:04:00.239 --> 03:04:00.420
that?

03:04:00.540 --> 03:04:03.239
Flower glanced up and did something with

03:04:03.239 --> 03:04:05.159
her mouth that looked exactly like a

03:04:05.159 --> 03:04:05.879
dragon smile.

03:04:05.940 --> 03:04:09.360
Sunny found herself smiling back, despite

03:04:09.360 --> 03:04:10.319
her fear and her worry.

03:04:10.379 --> 03:04:12.360
At least she wasn't alone.

03:04:12.420 --> 03:04:15.120
Little Sandwing.

03:04:15.299 --> 03:04:17.639
Queen Scarlet's voice hissed softly from

03:04:17.639 --> 03:04:18.059
below her.

03:04:18.120 --> 03:04:20.879
Using burn is what you have to worry

03:04:20.879 --> 03:04:21.659
about right now.

03:04:21.719 --> 03:04:23.219
She's not.

03:04:23.280 --> 03:04:24.719
I am.

03:04:24.780 --> 03:04:26.819
I'll be free soon.

03:04:26.940 --> 03:04:28.260
Free.

03:04:28.319 --> 03:04:31.200
And I'll be coming for all my enemies.

03:04:31.260 --> 03:04:34.379
Think about that while you try to fall

03:04:34.379 --> 03:04:34.799
asleep.

03:04:34.860 --> 03:04:37.620
What I'm going to do to your friends when

03:04:37.620 --> 03:04:39.180
I get my claws on them.

03:04:39.239 --> 03:04:43.200
How messy and thrilling it's going to

03:04:43.200 --> 03:04:43.440
be.

03:04:43.559 --> 03:04:46.979
Sunny closed her eyes and covered her

03:04:46.979 --> 03:04:49.500
ears, but the whispers continued inside

03:04:49.500 --> 03:04:50.100
her head.

03:04:50.159 --> 03:04:52.799
What if burn comes tomorrow?

03:04:52.860 --> 03:04:54.959
What if she kills me right away?

03:04:55.079 --> 03:04:57.899
What if I never get to find out the truth

03:04:57.899 --> 03:04:59.700
about my mother and my egg?

03:04:59.760 --> 03:05:02.040
Never get to spend more time with her.

03:05:02.100 --> 03:05:04.799
What if the prophecy is fake?

03:05:04.920 --> 03:05:07.500
What if I really have no destiny?

03:05:07.500 --> 03:05:09.479
Other than to end up here.

03:05:09.540 --> 03:05:13.020
What if nobody is going to end the war or

03:05:13.020 --> 03:05:13.680
save the world?

03:05:13.739 --> 03:05:18.600
And worst of all, what if I never see my

03:05:18.600 --> 03:05:19.139
friends again?

03:05:19.200 --> 03:05:23.579
Chapter 11.

03:05:23.879 --> 03:05:28.920
Somehow, eventually, Sonny slept, which

03:05:28.920 --> 03:05:30.659
she knew because she woke up to find

03:05:30.659 --> 03:05:33.180
Flower tugging gently on her tail and

03:05:33.180 --> 03:05:34.620
smolder, unlocking her chains.

03:05:34.739 --> 03:05:38.579
She sat up slowly and stretched her wings

03:05:38.579 --> 03:05:40.620
which still ached from all the flying

03:05:40.620 --> 03:05:42.120
she'd done in the last several days.

03:05:42.180 --> 03:05:44.579
What's happening?

03:05:44.639 --> 03:05:46.200
She asked Smolder.

03:05:46.260 --> 03:05:50.159
Oh, I thought we'd go for a walk, he said

03:05:50.159 --> 03:05:51.420
wryly.

03:05:51.479 --> 03:05:52.559
Sonny squinted at him.

03:05:52.620 --> 03:05:53.639
Are you joking?

03:05:53.700 --> 03:05:55.260
Or is that just your voice?

03:05:55.319 --> 03:05:57.180
Can other dragons tell when you're

03:05:57.180 --> 03:05:57.540
joking?

03:05:57.600 --> 03:05:59.100
Because I can't figure it out.

03:05:59.159 --> 03:06:01.559
He threw back his head and laughed.

03:06:01.620 --> 03:06:04.559
I have heard that before, he admitted.

03:06:04.620 --> 03:06:06.360
There was someone who used to tease me

03:06:06.360 --> 03:06:06.780
about it.

03:06:06.840 --> 03:06:08.819
She told me she was going to assume that

03:06:08.819 --> 03:06:11.159
everything I said was a joke. since that

03:06:11.159 --> 03:06:12.059
would simplify things.

03:06:12.120 --> 03:06:14.579
You can do that too, if you like.

03:06:14.639 --> 03:06:16.920
All right, Sonny said.

03:06:16.979 --> 03:06:19.319
Smolder wasn't exactly the sinister

03:06:19.319 --> 03:06:21.059
prison guard she would have expected from

03:06:21.059 --> 03:06:22.139
Burns brother.

03:06:22.200 --> 03:06:24.899
She much preferred this oddness instead

03:06:24.899 --> 03:06:26.399
even when it wasn't settling.

03:06:26.459 --> 03:06:30.000
The last chain clattered to the floor, and

03:06:30.000 --> 03:06:32.399
Smolder held out one talon, so Flower

03:06:32.399 --> 03:06:33.780
could climb up onto his back again.

03:06:33.840 --> 03:06:36.899
Make sure to steer clear of scarlet.

03:06:36.959 --> 03:06:39.180
He reminded Sonny, who didn't need

03:06:39.180 --> 03:06:39.719
reminding.

03:06:39.780 --> 03:06:41.940
She's in a foul mood today.

03:06:42.000 --> 03:06:44.100
I heard that.

03:06:44.159 --> 03:06:46.139
Scarlet roared.

03:06:46.200 --> 03:06:49.559
Smolder rolled his eyes at Sonny and dove

03:06:49.559 --> 03:06:50.159
off the edge.

03:06:50.219 --> 03:06:52.799
She followed, catching a glimpse of the

03:06:52.799 --> 03:06:54.899
smoking orange queen as they whisked

03:06:54.899 --> 03:06:55.139
past.

03:06:55.260 --> 03:06:58.500
Scarlet sent a blast of flames into the

03:06:58.500 --> 03:06:59.459
air right behind them.

03:06:59.520 --> 03:07:02.100
Sunny felt the heat crackle along the

03:07:02.100 --> 03:07:04.559
scales of her tail, and saw Flower press

03:07:04.559 --> 03:07:06.120
herself closer to Smolder's back.

03:07:06.180 --> 03:07:09.180
Outside, it was early morning.

03:07:09.239 --> 03:07:12.059
Barely sunrise, then he realized.

03:07:12.120 --> 03:07:14.280
Smolder didn't leave me locked up very

03:07:14.280 --> 03:07:14.579
long.

03:07:14.639 --> 03:07:16.979
He didn't even wait until midday to come

03:07:16.979 --> 03:07:17.280
get me.

03:07:17.340 --> 03:07:20.040
Maybe he's secretly kinder than he wants

03:07:20.040 --> 03:07:20.459
me to think.

03:07:20.579 --> 03:07:23.280
The light slanted low across the

03:07:23.280 --> 03:07:25.920
courtyard, and small brown birds hopped

03:07:25.920 --> 03:07:27.959
along the top of the walls, gossiping

03:07:27.959 --> 03:07:28.379
cheerily.

03:07:28.500 --> 03:07:31.739
The air smelled like roasting lizards, and

03:07:31.739 --> 03:07:33.600
the sand was still cool under her claws

03:07:33.600 --> 03:07:35.639
as she followed, smoldered to an archway

03:07:35.639 --> 03:07:36.000
on the left.

03:07:36.059 --> 03:07:38.159
Where are we going?

03:07:38.219 --> 03:07:39.059
She asked.

03:07:39.120 --> 03:07:42.059
I have been investigating a mystery for

03:07:42.059 --> 03:07:45.120
the last 20 years or so, said Smoulder.

03:07:45.180 --> 03:07:47.579
Occasionally, I ask other dragons what

03:07:47.579 --> 03:07:48.000
they think.

03:07:48.059 --> 03:07:51.360
Invariably, they disappoint me, but you

03:07:51.360 --> 03:07:54.719
seem unusual, more unusual than most, so

03:07:54.719 --> 03:07:55.799
I figured I'd try again.

03:07:55.860 --> 03:07:57.239
Ever hopeful.

03:07:57.299 --> 03:08:00.000
That's me. 20 years?

03:08:00.059 --> 03:08:01.139
Sonny said.

03:08:01.200 --> 03:08:03.420
I hope it's not a very urgent mystery.

03:08:03.540 --> 03:08:08.040
Smolder chuckled, then said, well, it

03:08:08.040 --> 03:08:10.500
rather is, but it's been resolutely

03:08:10.500 --> 03:08:12.120
impossible to solve nonetheless.

03:08:12.180 --> 03:08:15.059
He led the way through a room of pillars

03:08:15.059 --> 03:08:16.979
all of them carved with swirls that

03:08:16.979 --> 03:08:19.379
looked like dragon tails and into a long

03:08:19.379 --> 03:08:21.840
hallway lined with sparkling rust colored

03:08:21.840 --> 03:08:23.459
tiles in a spiraling pattern.

03:08:23.579 --> 03:08:26.219
Sunny brushed one of the tiles with her

03:08:26.219 --> 03:08:28.139
wing, thinking that it was the 1st

03:08:28.139 --> 03:08:29.639
beautiful thing she'd seen in this

03:08:29.639 --> 03:08:30.000
palace.

03:08:30.059 --> 03:08:33.600
The hallway slanted down and down and

03:08:33.600 --> 03:08:35.819
down until Sonny was sure they were

03:08:35.819 --> 03:08:38.340
underground, and finally it ended in a

03:08:38.340 --> 03:08:40.379
room with 4 locked doors.

03:08:40.440 --> 03:08:43.920
Smolder walked to each door and opened

03:08:43.920 --> 03:08:45.780
them with large brass keys from around

03:08:45.780 --> 03:08:48.659
his neck, revealing 4 rooms of roughly

03:08:48.659 --> 03:08:51.899
equal size, with thick stone walls and

03:08:51.899 --> 03:08:53.100
plain gray stone floors.

03:08:53.159 --> 03:08:55.860
All of them were completely empty.

03:08:55.920 --> 03:08:58.559
The rumors about the sand wing treasure

03:08:58.559 --> 03:09:01.680
were never entirely accurate, he said as

03:09:01.680 --> 03:09:03.780
he did this, twisting the keys in his

03:09:03.780 --> 03:09:04.139
claws.

03:09:04.200 --> 03:09:06.299
We were very wealthy, yes.

03:09:06.360 --> 03:09:08.579
But we weren't quite stupid enough to

03:09:08.579 --> 03:09:09.540
keep it all in one place.

03:09:09.600 --> 03:09:12.360
Almost that stupid, but not quite.

03:09:12.420 --> 03:09:15.360
We kept only our most prized possessions

03:09:15.360 --> 03:09:17.520
in our treasure rooms, along with a

03:09:17.520 --> 03:09:19.799
backup stash of rubies, diamonds, and

03:09:19.799 --> 03:09:21.780
gold in case we ever needed it.

03:09:21.840 --> 03:09:25.379
So it wasn't our entire wealth, or a

03:09:25.379 --> 03:09:26.819
palace full of treasure that went

03:09:26.819 --> 03:09:27.059
missing.

03:09:27.120 --> 03:09:30.840
Only the contents of these 4 rooms, but

03:09:30.840 --> 03:09:32.579
they contained quite a lot.

03:09:32.639 --> 03:09:35.879
He held up a talent for flour to climb

03:09:35.879 --> 03:09:38.040
onto, then set her carefully on the floor

03:09:38.040 --> 03:09:39.239
in front of the treasure rooms.

03:09:39.360 --> 03:09:41.819
She looked even smaller next to the

03:09:41.819 --> 03:09:42.420
massive rooms.

03:09:42.540 --> 03:09:45.780
Sonny realized the flower was probably

03:09:45.780 --> 03:09:47.700
small enough to squeeze under the doors.

03:09:47.760 --> 03:09:51.059
The scavenger put her tiny paws on her

03:09:51.059 --> 03:09:53.579
hips, tossed her head for her back, and

03:09:53.579 --> 03:09:55.260
looked for all the world like she was

03:09:55.260 --> 03:09:57.180
bored at this dragon game.

03:09:57.239 --> 03:09:59.340
So here's what I'd like to know.

03:09:59.459 --> 03:10:03.180
Smolder said, how did 3 scavengers about

03:10:03.180 --> 03:10:04.200
this size?

03:10:04.260 --> 03:10:06.780
Two, actually, once they lost this one

03:10:06.780 --> 03:10:10.020
managed to carry 4 rooms worth of

03:10:10.020 --> 03:10:11.520
treasure off into the desert.

03:10:11.639 --> 03:10:14.579
Sunny studied the little scavenger in

03:10:14.579 --> 03:10:15.000
front of her.

03:10:15.059 --> 03:10:16.799
It was actually a very good question.

03:10:16.860 --> 03:10:19.559
Flour was only about as tall as a full

03:10:19.559 --> 03:10:20.760
grown dragon's head.

03:10:20.819 --> 03:10:24.059
She had no wings, and miniature

03:10:24.059 --> 03:10:25.079
practically useless pause.

03:10:25.139 --> 03:10:29.940
Well, maybe not that useless, she thought

03:10:29.940 --> 03:10:31.979
remembering the sketch of her face from

03:10:31.979 --> 03:10:32.520
the night before.

03:10:32.579 --> 03:10:35.579
Could they have built something to carry

03:10:35.579 --> 03:10:35.819
it?

03:10:35.879 --> 03:10:38.579
she said, crouching to examine flowers

03:10:38.579 --> 03:10:41.159
pause, the scavenger squeaked at her.

03:10:41.219 --> 03:10:43.680
I saw the ruins of one of their villages

03:10:43.680 --> 03:10:44.399
on my way here.

03:10:44.459 --> 03:10:48.120
Their dens look like real houses, and

03:10:48.120 --> 03:10:49.860
there was an iron bell in the wreckage

03:10:49.860 --> 03:10:50.100
too.

03:10:50.219 --> 03:10:52.260
So they're good at making things.

03:10:52.319 --> 03:10:54.959
Maybe they made some kind of wagon to

03:10:54.959 --> 03:10:55.379
carry it in.

03:10:55.500 --> 03:10:58.440
A wagon, would have left tracks across

03:10:58.440 --> 03:11:00.719
the sand, Smolder pointed out.

03:11:00.780 --> 03:11:03.540
The only tracks we found were hoofprints

03:11:03.540 --> 03:11:06.299
3 horses galloping flat out.

03:11:06.360 --> 03:11:08.819
You tell me how they could do that, with

03:11:08.819 --> 03:11:10.680
more than 2 bags of gold on their backs

03:11:10.680 --> 03:11:12.360
let alone all of this.

03:11:12.420 --> 03:11:15.659
Oh, you found prints?

03:11:15.780 --> 03:11:18.360
Sonny said, stepping into the 1st room

03:11:18.360 --> 03:11:19.379
and peering around.

03:11:19.440 --> 03:11:21.659
Didn't you follow them?

03:11:21.719 --> 03:11:24.540
She moved to the 2nd room, which was the

03:11:24.540 --> 03:11:27.000
same as the first, except perhaps with a

03:11:27.000 --> 03:11:27.959
little more sand on the floor.

03:11:28.020 --> 03:11:31.440
Follow them, said Smolder.

03:11:31.500 --> 03:11:33.600
If only we'd thought of that.

03:11:33.719 --> 03:11:36.239
Aha, Sonny said.

03:11:36.299 --> 03:11:37.979
That was definitely sarcasm.

03:11:38.040 --> 03:11:40.440
He gave her a crooked smile.

03:11:40.559 --> 03:11:43.500
Well, look, there was a lot of confusion

03:11:43.500 --> 03:11:45.299
when we 1st found the queen's body.

03:11:45.360 --> 03:11:47.940
We all heard her roaring in the middle of

03:11:47.940 --> 03:11:48.540
the night.

03:11:48.600 --> 03:11:50.399
It must have woken every dragon for

03:11:50.399 --> 03:11:50.760
miles.

03:11:50.819 --> 03:11:53.219
That's what brought us outside the palace

03:11:53.219 --> 03:11:54.899
thinking something terrible had

03:11:54.899 --> 03:11:55.200
happened.

03:11:55.319 --> 03:11:58.139
All we found at 1st was mother, lying

03:11:58.139 --> 03:11:59.399
there, dead.

03:11:59.459 --> 03:12:01.379
Had one of our daughters killed her.

03:12:01.440 --> 03:12:03.899
Why not in a proper duel?

03:12:03.959 --> 03:12:06.479
Who else would dare kill the sand wing

03:12:06.479 --> 03:12:06.899
queen?

03:12:06.899 --> 03:12:08.399
Who else could?

03:12:08.459 --> 03:12:10.260
And why wouldn't they admit to it?

03:12:10.319 --> 03:12:12.780
The 1st clue we found was this little

03:12:12.780 --> 03:12:15.059
creature, trying to hide by burying

03:12:15.059 --> 03:12:15.899
herself in a dune.

03:12:15.959 --> 03:12:19.079
She was injured and, of course, had no

03:12:19.079 --> 03:12:21.420
treasure on her, apart from a cute little

03:12:21.420 --> 03:12:22.440
claw sword thing.

03:12:22.559 --> 03:12:25.260
Smolder reached into the bag around his

03:12:25.260 --> 03:12:28.139
neck, and somewhat startlingly produced a

03:12:28.139 --> 03:12:28.620
banana.

03:12:28.680 --> 03:12:31.500
He handed it to Flower, who sat down and

03:12:31.500 --> 03:12:33.059
began peeling it with expert little

03:12:33.059 --> 03:12:34.799
twitches of her slender paws.

03:12:34.860 --> 03:12:38.459
That's when we realized scavengers were

03:12:38.459 --> 03:12:38.760
involved.

03:12:38.819 --> 03:12:41.040
So we knew they must have come here to

03:12:41.040 --> 03:12:41.639
steal treasure.

03:12:41.700 --> 03:12:44.100
Burn was so furious.

03:12:44.159 --> 03:12:47.579
We finally found the horse tracks, Smolder

03:12:47.579 --> 03:12:49.680
went on, but they had at least 2 hours

03:12:49.680 --> 03:12:50.459
head start by then.

03:12:50.520 --> 03:12:52.860
We caught up shortly before they reached

03:12:52.860 --> 03:12:55.620
their forest home, and then Byrne decided

03:12:55.620 --> 03:12:58.260
we should let them reach their forest

03:12:58.260 --> 03:12:58.559
home.

03:12:58.620 --> 03:13:01.979
His eyes were dark, watching flower.

03:13:02.040 --> 03:13:04.200
Once they let us ride to it.

03:13:04.260 --> 03:13:06.299
We burned it to the ground.

03:13:06.360 --> 03:13:08.219
Yikes.

03:13:08.280 --> 03:13:09.420
Sonny said.

03:13:09.479 --> 03:13:12.360
That's a lot of scavengers to wipe out

03:13:12.360 --> 03:13:14.219
just because 3 of them did something

03:13:14.219 --> 03:13:14.760
stupid.

03:13:14.819 --> 03:13:18.420
Burn said we had to stamp out the vermin

03:13:18.420 --> 03:13:19.920
before they began to think they could do

03:13:19.920 --> 03:13:22.020
something like that again, Smolder

03:13:22.020 --> 03:13:24.059
pointed out, as if he guessed what she

03:13:24.059 --> 03:13:24.540
was thinking.

03:13:24.600 --> 03:13:27.239
So after you burned the village.

03:13:27.299 --> 03:13:29.700
We searched for the treasure in the

03:13:29.700 --> 03:13:30.120
ashes.

03:13:30.180 --> 03:13:32.040
No sign of it anywhere.

03:13:32.100 --> 03:13:35.159
Not a single jewel or gold nugget.

03:13:35.219 --> 03:13:37.860
We tried hunting down a few scavengers

03:13:37.860 --> 03:13:40.200
who'd escaped the fire, but some of them

03:13:40.200 --> 03:13:42.120
must have slipped through our claws, and

03:13:42.120 --> 03:13:44.159
one of those must have the treasure, even

03:13:44.159 --> 03:13:46.020
now, 20 years later.

03:13:46.079 --> 03:13:49.319
Sunny started pacing from room to room.

03:13:49.379 --> 03:13:51.659
Something wasn't right about this story.

03:13:51.719 --> 03:13:53.879
A lot of things weren't quite right about

03:13:53.879 --> 03:13:55.260
this story.

03:13:55.319 --> 03:13:56.340
That much treasure?

03:13:56.399 --> 03:13:58.379
How could it disappear into thin air?

03:13:58.440 --> 03:14:01.680
How could scavengers make it disappear

03:14:01.680 --> 03:14:02.340
into thin air?

03:14:02.399 --> 03:14:05.520
She stopped and looked down at flower

03:14:05.520 --> 03:14:05.819
again.

03:14:05.879 --> 03:14:07.979
The brown eyes looked back at her

03:14:07.979 --> 03:14:08.579
curiously.

03:14:08.639 --> 03:14:12.299
Are you sure the scavengers killed Queen

03:14:12.299 --> 03:14:13.020
Oasis?

03:14:13.079 --> 03:14:14.459
Sonny asked.

03:14:14.520 --> 03:14:16.860
It wasn't maybe just really bad luck that

03:14:16.860 --> 03:14:18.420
they were there at the same time as some

03:14:18.420 --> 03:14:19.020
other killer?

03:14:19.079 --> 03:14:21.239
Smolder nodded.

03:14:21.299 --> 03:14:24.780
I thought of that, but it was a scavenger

03:14:24.780 --> 03:14:28.500
sized spear in mother's eye, and this

03:14:28.500 --> 03:14:29.819
part is a little weird.

03:14:29.879 --> 03:14:32.159
They cut off her tail barb and took it

03:14:32.159 --> 03:14:32.520
with them.

03:14:32.579 --> 03:14:35.459
We never found that either, but there was

03:14:35.459 --> 03:14:37.920
a trail of venom drops and dragon blood

03:14:37.920 --> 03:14:39.000
beside the horse tracks.

03:14:39.059 --> 03:14:41.639
Sonny wrangled our snout.

03:14:41.700 --> 03:14:43.559
Why would they do that?

03:14:43.620 --> 03:14:46.379
Why do scavengers do any of the

03:14:46.379 --> 03:14:47.700
inexplicable things they do?

03:14:47.760 --> 03:14:50.940
Smolder tossed another banana to flower.

03:14:51.000 --> 03:14:53.280
Sonny wonder if the scavenger had any

03:14:53.280 --> 03:14:54.479
idea they were talking about her.

03:14:54.540 --> 03:14:58.979
Hmm, she said, studying the rooms.

03:14:59.040 --> 03:15:01.620
Now that she was here, looking at the

03:15:01.620 --> 03:15:03.840
space, and at a scavenger at the same

03:15:03.840 --> 03:15:06.360
time, the original story sounded more and

03:15:06.360 --> 03:15:09.000
more ludicrous, it was crazy enough that

03:15:09.000 --> 03:15:10.979
scavengers had managed to kill a dragon

03:15:10.979 --> 03:15:13.319
queen, but then they also stole all her

03:15:13.319 --> 03:15:15.540
treasure without getting caught and

03:15:15.540 --> 03:15:16.020
eaten?

03:15:16.079 --> 03:15:18.659
Her wings twitched with a sudden idea.

03:15:18.719 --> 03:15:22.079
Maybe the question wasn't, how did they

03:15:22.079 --> 03:15:23.579
transport all that treasure?

03:15:23.639 --> 03:15:26.819
Maybe the real question was, what else

03:15:26.819 --> 03:15:27.719
could have happened to it?

03:15:27.780 --> 03:15:30.360
Wait, she said.

03:15:30.420 --> 03:15:32.340
When did you check these rooms?

03:15:32.399 --> 03:15:35.100
When did you see how much was missing?

03:15:35.159 --> 03:15:36.540
Oh.

03:15:36.659 --> 03:15:39.299
Smolder breathed a plume of smoke and

03:15:39.299 --> 03:15:39.959
squinted at her.

03:15:40.020 --> 03:15:42.659
When we returned from burning the den.

03:15:42.780 --> 03:15:44.940
I remember flying back and thinking that

03:15:44.940 --> 03:15:46.379
the scavengers couldn't have gotten much

03:15:46.379 --> 03:15:48.239
if we couldn't find any trace of it.

03:15:48.299 --> 03:15:50.879
And then Byrne led the way down here to

03:15:50.879 --> 03:15:53.520
do an inventory, and we found everything

03:15:53.520 --> 03:15:54.059
gone.

03:15:54.180 --> 03:15:57.000
I never figured out how flower unlocked

03:15:57.000 --> 03:15:57.719
the doors either.

03:15:57.780 --> 03:16:00.719
Sunny lashed her tail so hard.

03:16:00.780 --> 03:16:03.299
It smacked into one of the doors, sending

03:16:03.299 --> 03:16:05.219
a shiver of pain through her scales.

03:16:05.280 --> 03:16:08.940
That's it then, she said excitedly.

03:16:09.000 --> 03:16:11.100
Someone else took it while you were out

03:16:11.100 --> 03:16:12.239
hunting the scavengers.

03:16:12.299 --> 03:16:14.639
Who didn't go with you to chase the

03:16:14.639 --> 03:16:16.020
scavengers and burn the den?

03:16:16.079 --> 03:16:19.440
Lots of dragons, Smolder said.

03:16:19.500 --> 03:16:21.600
He frowned thoughtfully at the open

03:16:21.600 --> 03:16:22.020
doors.

03:16:22.079 --> 03:16:25.379
Blister and Blaze both stayed here.

03:16:25.440 --> 03:16:28.440
Then, of course, it was one of them, Sunny

03:16:28.440 --> 03:16:28.979
said.

03:16:29.040 --> 03:16:31.079
The scavengers probably didn't even get

03:16:31.079 --> 03:16:32.940
anything before Oasis caught them.

03:16:33.059 --> 03:16:34.379
They don't have your treasure.

03:16:34.440 --> 03:16:36.600
One of your sisters does.

03:16:36.719 --> 03:16:39.239
Smolder was already shaking his head.

03:16:39.299 --> 03:16:43.200
No, he said, no, that's not possible.

03:16:43.260 --> 03:16:46.139
It must be scavengers, or this war would

03:16:46.139 --> 03:16:46.680
be over already.

03:16:46.739 --> 03:16:50.280
Sonny met Flower's eyes, then looked back

03:16:50.280 --> 03:16:50.700
at him.

03:16:50.760 --> 03:16:52.260
Over?

03:16:52.319 --> 03:16:53.520
How do you figure?

03:16:53.579 --> 03:16:56.760
There's, I'm not supposed to talk about

03:16:56.760 --> 03:16:56.940
it.

03:16:57.000 --> 03:16:59.040
You can't do that.

03:16:59.100 --> 03:17:01.559
Sonny said, flaring her wings.

03:17:01.620 --> 03:17:03.780
You can't tell me half of something and

03:17:03.780 --> 03:17:04.739
then not tell me the rest.

03:17:04.860 --> 03:17:08.280
He wrinkled a snout, looking faintly

03:17:08.280 --> 03:17:08.819
amused again.

03:17:08.879 --> 03:17:12.540
You are my prisoner, remember?

03:17:12.600 --> 03:17:13.319
He said.

03:17:13.379 --> 03:17:16.979
It's a royal sand wing secret, I'm

03:17:16.979 --> 03:17:17.280
afraid.

03:17:17.340 --> 03:17:20.280
Oh, aren't you fancy?

03:17:20.280 --> 03:17:21.360
Sonny said.

03:17:21.479 --> 03:17:23.219
All right, I'll figure it out.

03:17:23.280 --> 03:17:27.000
Don't do that, Smolder said, with a hint

03:17:27.000 --> 03:17:27.840
of alarm in his voice.

03:17:27.899 --> 03:17:31.020
A royal secret involving your treasure

03:17:31.020 --> 03:17:33.360
that would end at the war if someone had

03:17:33.360 --> 03:17:34.500
their claws on it already.

03:17:34.559 --> 03:17:36.719
Oh, Sonny said.

03:17:36.780 --> 03:17:38.940
I bet it's something animas touched.

03:17:39.000 --> 03:17:39.659
Is that it?

03:17:39.719 --> 03:17:40.799
That must be it.

03:17:40.860 --> 03:17:43.620
Ooh, is it some kind of enchanted

03:17:43.620 --> 03:17:46.020
treasure that's like, oh, if you're

03:17:46.020 --> 03:17:47.459
holding this, you're the sand wing

03:17:47.459 --> 03:17:47.819
queen.

03:17:47.940 --> 03:17:51.059
So a scavenger must have it, because if a

03:17:51.059 --> 03:17:53.579
dragon had it, she'd be queen and the war

03:17:53.579 --> 03:17:54.059
would be over.

03:17:54.120 --> 03:17:55.680
Interesting.

03:17:55.739 --> 03:17:59.219
Smolders stared at her with unfathomable

03:17:59.219 --> 03:18:01.020
black eyes for a long moment.

03:18:01.079 --> 03:18:03.659
That's not it?

03:18:03.719 --> 03:18:06.239
Sonny finally asked nervously.

03:18:06.299 --> 03:18:09.600
That was unsettling, he said.

03:18:09.659 --> 03:18:12.540
It was just logic, Sonny said.

03:18:12.600 --> 03:18:14.399
My friend Starfight would have figured it

03:18:14.399 --> 03:18:14.819
out faster.

03:18:14.879 --> 03:18:17.520
She stopped and curled her tail around

03:18:17.520 --> 03:18:18.360
her talons.

03:18:18.420 --> 03:18:22.379
If only Starflight were here, or Clay, or

03:18:22.379 --> 03:18:22.920
any of them.

03:18:22.979 --> 03:18:27.360
Well, he said, I suppose you're likely to

03:18:27.360 --> 03:18:28.739
be dead by the end of the week anyway.

03:18:28.799 --> 03:18:31.079
Just remember that if you tell anybody

03:18:31.079 --> 03:18:32.219
we'll have to kill them too.

03:18:32.280 --> 03:18:34.260
Aren't you cheerful?

03:18:34.260 --> 03:18:35.940
Sonny said crossly.

03:18:36.000 --> 03:18:37.260
What is it anyway?

03:18:37.319 --> 03:18:39.420
The Sandwing Scepter?

03:18:39.479 --> 03:18:40.620
He shook his head.

03:18:40.739 --> 03:18:42.659
I'm not telling you that.

03:18:42.719 --> 03:18:45.420
The Lazulite Dragon?

03:18:45.479 --> 03:18:47.940
Sonny racked her brain, trying to

03:18:47.940 --> 03:18:49.500
remember what famous pieces of treasure

03:18:49.500 --> 03:18:51.000
were mentioned in the scrolls.

03:18:51.120 --> 03:18:52.559
Stop guessing.

03:18:52.620 --> 03:18:54.600
The Eye of Onyx.

03:18:54.659 --> 03:18:55.680
Sonny said.

03:18:55.739 --> 03:18:57.780
And from his expression, she knew that

03:18:57.780 --> 03:18:58.139
was it.

03:18:58.200 --> 03:19:00.659
His face wasn't quite the emotionless

03:19:00.659 --> 03:19:02.219
mask the blisters was.

03:19:02.280 --> 03:19:05.579
Well, that's why the scavengers must have

03:19:05.579 --> 03:19:06.000
the treasure.

03:19:06.059 --> 03:19:08.940
Smolder said quickly, as if hoping she

03:19:08.940 --> 03:19:09.600
hadn't noticed.

03:19:09.659 --> 03:19:12.659
If Booster or Blaze had it, one of them

03:19:12.659 --> 03:19:14.219
would be queen instead of hiding in

03:19:14.219 --> 03:19:14.700
another kingdom.

03:19:14.760 --> 03:19:17.159
If any sandwing had it.

03:19:17.219 --> 03:19:18.780
They'd be ruling the desert already.

03:19:18.899 --> 03:19:20.940
Sonny shrugged.

03:19:21.000 --> 03:19:23.760
So the scavengers managed to get

03:19:23.760 --> 03:19:26.100
something and happened to get the most

03:19:26.100 --> 03:19:26.819
important thing.

03:19:26.879 --> 03:19:29.520
Someone else still took the rest of it.

03:19:29.579 --> 03:19:31.020
I bet you anything.

03:19:31.079 --> 03:19:32.819
Hmm.

03:19:32.879 --> 03:19:35.100
Smolder narrowed his eyes.

03:19:35.159 --> 03:19:38.100
Smoke billowed from his nose, writhing

03:19:38.100 --> 03:19:38.819
around his horns.

03:19:38.940 --> 03:19:42.000
In that case, we'd still have to find the

03:19:42.000 --> 03:19:43.500
scavengers and what they stole.

03:19:43.559 --> 03:19:46.379
Sunny didn't have an answer for that.

03:19:46.440 --> 03:19:49.440
She had a feeling find the scavengers

03:19:49.440 --> 03:19:52.379
meant burn down more dens, and it made

03:19:52.379 --> 03:19:53.879
her feel sorry for the squishy little

03:19:53.879 --> 03:19:56.219
creatures, especially if they were all as

03:19:56.219 --> 03:19:57.420
cute and clever as flower.

03:19:57.479 --> 03:20:01.500
Smolder, a voice called smolder.

03:20:01.559 --> 03:20:04.920
Talons scrabbled on stone as the

03:20:04.920 --> 03:20:07.260
snubnosed sandwing came pelting down the

03:20:07.260 --> 03:20:08.159
long sloping hall.

03:20:08.219 --> 03:20:10.319
He started calling out as he ran toward

03:20:10.319 --> 03:20:12.360
them, his voice traveling across the

03:20:12.360 --> 03:20:12.719
distance.

03:20:12.780 --> 03:20:14.879
We're under attack.

03:20:14.940 --> 03:20:15.780
He yelled.

03:20:15.840 --> 03:20:16.440
Help!

03:20:16.500 --> 03:20:18.120
Turtle Sandstorm is already dead.

03:20:18.180 --> 03:20:19.440
No one knows what to do.

03:20:19.500 --> 03:20:20.399
It's chaos.

03:20:20.459 --> 03:20:21.299
We're all going to die.

03:20:21.360 --> 03:20:24.239
He skidded the last several steps toward

03:20:24.239 --> 03:20:26.280
them, and nearly tumbled into one of the

03:20:26.280 --> 03:20:27.000
treasure rooms.

03:20:27.059 --> 03:20:29.040
Sunny jumped out of the way of his

03:20:29.040 --> 03:20:29.879
flailing tail.

03:20:29.940 --> 03:20:31.860
Who's attacking?

03:20:31.979 --> 03:20:34.979
Smolder said sharply, grabbing the

03:20:34.979 --> 03:20:36.479
messenger and steering him back up the

03:20:36.479 --> 03:20:39.180
hallway with one brisk motion, ice wings

03:20:39.180 --> 03:20:39.840
or sea wings?

03:20:39.899 --> 03:20:41.219
I don't know.

03:20:41.280 --> 03:20:42.420
It happened so fast.

03:20:42.479 --> 03:20:44.219
It was like they rose straight out of the

03:20:44.219 --> 03:20:44.520
sand.

03:20:44.579 --> 03:20:48.540
Maybe it's Queen Scarlet's friends, Sonny

03:20:48.540 --> 03:20:51.059
said anxiously, scooping up flour and

03:20:51.059 --> 03:20:51.959
hurrying behind them.

03:20:52.020 --> 03:20:54.600
Smolder gave her a look, as if he'd

03:20:54.600 --> 03:20:55.319
forgotten she was there.

03:20:55.379 --> 03:20:56.819
Remember?

03:20:56.879 --> 03:20:58.620
She said someone was coming to rescue

03:20:58.620 --> 03:20:58.799
her.

03:20:58.920 --> 03:21:00.299
What if this is them?

03:21:00.420 --> 03:21:03.180
The messenger let out a horrified

03:21:03.180 --> 03:21:03.719
squeak.

03:21:03.780 --> 03:21:06.479
Then we're definitely all going to die.

03:21:06.540 --> 03:21:08.280
Stop that.

03:21:08.340 --> 03:21:11.100
Smolder said, giving him a quick shake.

03:21:11.159 --> 03:21:13.680
There are enough sandwing soldiers here

03:21:13.680 --> 03:21:14.760
to fight off any invasion.

03:21:14.879 --> 03:21:17.879
He held out his talons and Sonny passed

03:21:17.879 --> 03:21:18.600
flour to him.

03:21:18.659 --> 03:21:21.899
Smolder said his pet gently in a side

03:21:21.899 --> 03:21:23.100
room with no windows.

03:21:23.219 --> 03:21:27.600
Stay, he said sternly, pointing a claw at

03:21:27.600 --> 03:21:28.500
the little scavenger.

03:21:28.559 --> 03:21:31.559
Flower put her paws on her hips and

03:21:31.559 --> 03:21:33.899
chattered something indignant at him, but

03:21:33.899 --> 03:21:35.399
he ignored her and swept on up the

03:21:35.399 --> 03:21:36.059
corridor.

03:21:36.120 --> 03:21:38.399
I don't have time to lock you up again

03:21:38.399 --> 03:21:41.399
right now, Smolder said to Sonny, but I'm

03:21:41.399 --> 03:21:41.879
still watching you.

03:21:41.940 --> 03:21:44.280
If you try to escape while we're fighting

03:21:44.280 --> 03:21:46.020
you'll end up back in that tower, and

03:21:46.020 --> 03:21:47.159
you're never coming out again.

03:21:47.219 --> 03:21:48.840
I get it.

03:21:48.899 --> 03:21:49.920
You're menacing.

03:21:49.979 --> 03:21:51.719
Sunny shouted at him.

03:21:51.780 --> 03:21:53.579
Now, what are you going to do about Queen

03:21:53.579 --> 03:21:54.299
Scarlet?

03:21:54.360 --> 03:21:56.520
You should send more guards to watch her

03:21:56.520 --> 03:21:57.420
right now.

03:21:57.479 --> 03:21:59.879
She's the one you should worry about

03:21:59.879 --> 03:22:00.540
escaping.

03:22:00.600 --> 03:22:03.540
At least I won't murder everyone on my

03:22:03.540 --> 03:22:03.959
way out.

03:22:04.020 --> 03:22:07.559
Smolders, stern expression wavered for a

03:22:07.559 --> 03:22:09.239
moment as he looked down at her.

03:22:09.299 --> 03:22:11.879
I think I should be offended that you're

03:22:11.879 --> 03:22:13.739
obviously more afraid of my prisoner than

03:22:13.739 --> 03:22:15.180
you are of me, he said.

03:22:15.239 --> 03:22:17.520
But I suppose I'll worry about that

03:22:17.520 --> 03:22:17.760
later.

03:22:17.819 --> 03:22:21.120
You, he shouted, at a pair of guards

03:22:21.120 --> 03:22:22.139
running by.

03:22:22.200 --> 03:22:24.360
Find 4 more soldiers and take them to

03:22:24.360 --> 03:22:26.940
guard Burns Weirdling Tower with your

03:22:26.940 --> 03:22:27.540
lives.

03:22:27.600 --> 03:22:28.379
You understand?

03:22:28.440 --> 03:22:31.739
They nodded, about faced, and took off

03:22:31.739 --> 03:22:32.459
toward the tower.

03:22:32.520 --> 03:22:36.180
Thank you, Sunny said, more than a little

03:22:36.180 --> 03:22:38.100
surprised that he'd actually listened to

03:22:38.100 --> 03:22:38.399
her.

03:22:38.459 --> 03:22:41.819
Now they could hear roars and snarls and

03:22:41.819 --> 03:22:44.100
the clash of claws outside, along with

03:22:44.100 --> 03:22:46.260
the sound of shouts and running talons

03:22:46.260 --> 03:22:47.219
all over the palace.

03:22:47.280 --> 03:22:51.120
Watch her, Smolder said to the messenger

03:22:51.120 --> 03:22:52.079
pointing to Sonny.

03:22:52.139 --> 03:22:55.620
An unearthly shriek tore through the

03:22:55.620 --> 03:22:58.139
morning air, and smolder hurtled into the

03:22:58.139 --> 03:23:00.600
nearest courtyard, then up into the air.

03:23:00.659 --> 03:23:03.780
The black diamonds on his wings flared

03:23:03.780 --> 03:23:06.420
like crows taking flight as he soared

03:23:06.420 --> 03:23:09.000
higher, then banked sideways and shot

03:23:09.000 --> 03:23:09.959
toward the outer wall.

03:23:10.020 --> 03:23:13.020
Sonny ran into the courtyard behind him

03:23:13.020 --> 03:23:14.100
and spread her wings.

03:23:14.159 --> 03:23:15.360
Wait!

03:23:15.420 --> 03:23:16.739
the messenger protested.

03:23:16.799 --> 03:23:18.000
Where do you think you're going?

03:23:18.059 --> 03:23:21.719
To see what's happening, Sunny said, I

03:23:21.719 --> 03:23:23.219
want to know who's winning, don't you?

03:23:23.280 --> 03:23:27.540
Because if it's Scarlet's friends, then I

03:23:27.540 --> 03:23:28.260
need to get out of here.

03:23:28.319 --> 03:23:30.540
No matter what smolder thinks I've

03:23:30.540 --> 03:23:31.260
promised him.

03:23:31.319 --> 03:23:34.379
Um, the messenger said.

03:23:34.440 --> 03:23:37.379
Twisting his tail between his talons, but

03:23:37.379 --> 03:23:38.940
I'm not sure.

03:23:39.000 --> 03:23:40.139
Come on.

03:23:40.200 --> 03:23:43.260
Sonny launched herself into the sky and

03:23:43.260 --> 03:23:44.760
heard the scramble of his claws behind

03:23:44.760 --> 03:23:45.659
her as he followed.

03:23:45.719 --> 03:23:48.540
She aimed for the highest point of the

03:23:48.540 --> 03:23:51.239
palace that she could see, a spire with

03:23:51.239 --> 03:23:53.100
an open pavilion platform at the top.

03:23:53.159 --> 03:23:55.620
The corners of the roof were carved like

03:23:55.620 --> 03:23:58.319
dragon wings open in flight, and wind

03:23:58.319 --> 03:24:00.360
chimes on each side glittered and

03:24:00.360 --> 03:24:01.979
whispered in the faint breeze.

03:24:02.040 --> 03:24:05.100
In a few moments, her claws touched down

03:24:05.100 --> 03:24:07.500
on white stone, and she took a fluttering

03:24:07.500 --> 03:24:10.260
step for balance, spread out before her

03:24:10.260 --> 03:24:12.719
to the south of the stronghold was the

03:24:12.719 --> 03:24:13.500
battle.

03:24:13.559 --> 03:24:16.979
Sonny squinted, her eyes adjusting to the

03:24:16.979 --> 03:24:19.379
light of the rising sun as she searched

03:24:19.379 --> 03:24:22.079
for distinctive colors, perhaps the blues

03:24:22.079 --> 03:24:24.719
and greens of sea wings, or the white and

03:24:24.719 --> 03:24:27.180
pale blue of ice wings, as smolder

03:24:27.180 --> 03:24:29.819
expected, or perhaps the reds and oranges

03:24:29.819 --> 03:24:32.100
of loyal sky wings come to rescue their

03:24:32.100 --> 03:24:32.760
queen.

03:24:32.819 --> 03:24:34.979
There is something strange about this

03:24:34.979 --> 03:24:35.280
battle.

03:24:35.399 --> 03:24:38.040
Sunny couldn't see any unusual colors

03:24:38.040 --> 03:24:41.100
down there, nothing but the tan, pale

03:24:41.100 --> 03:24:43.440
yellow, and off-white scales of sand

03:24:43.440 --> 03:24:44.219
wings.

03:24:44.280 --> 03:24:46.799
Sand wings fighting sand wings.

03:24:46.920 --> 03:24:49.319
Was it blisters army attacking?

03:24:49.379 --> 03:24:51.600
But it didn't look like a hole invading

03:24:51.600 --> 03:24:52.139
force.

03:24:52.200 --> 03:24:55.139
In fact, if Sonny had to guess, she'd say

03:24:55.139 --> 03:24:56.760
there were only about 30 dragons

03:24:56.760 --> 03:24:59.159
attacking the stronghold, against about

03:24:59.159 --> 03:25:00.360
100 defenders.

03:25:00.420 --> 03:25:03.420
And then she saw a flash of sunlight

03:25:03.420 --> 03:25:05.940
catch on a gold arm bracelet, and she

03:25:05.940 --> 03:25:07.379
leaned forward with a gasp.

03:25:07.440 --> 03:25:09.360
That's Thorn.

03:25:09.420 --> 03:25:12.479
Now that she'd spotted her, it was

03:25:12.479 --> 03:25:15.299
unmistakable, the wiry, pale yellow

03:25:15.299 --> 03:25:16.979
dragon was deep in the thick of the

03:25:16.979 --> 03:25:19.500
fighting, slashing at sandwing soldiers

03:25:19.500 --> 03:25:21.959
with her talons, and stabbing her tail as

03:25:21.959 --> 03:25:24.479
she rose into the air, then dropped below

03:25:24.479 --> 03:25:27.120
2 warriors, then hurtled up to smash into

03:25:27.120 --> 03:25:27.420
another.

03:25:27.479 --> 03:25:30.719
Sonny scanned the rest of the attackers

03:25:30.719 --> 03:25:34.139
and picked out 6 claws, then Kibley

03:25:34.139 --> 03:25:35.579
fighting as close to Thorn as they

03:25:35.579 --> 03:25:35.760
could.

03:25:35.819 --> 03:25:39.360
This wasn't another army, or one of the

03:25:39.360 --> 03:25:40.440
sandwing sisters.

03:25:40.500 --> 03:25:42.959
The stronghold was being attacked by the

03:25:42.959 --> 03:25:43.799
outlaws.

03:25:43.860 --> 03:25:47.819
My mother came to get me, Sonny thought

03:25:47.819 --> 03:25:49.680
her scales humming with joy.

03:25:49.739 --> 03:25:52.200
Six claws must have told her the truth

03:25:52.200 --> 03:25:54.180
instead of the lie we came up with.

03:25:54.239 --> 03:25:56.760
But then she took another look at the

03:25:56.760 --> 03:25:58.440
battle, and her heart sank.

03:25:58.500 --> 03:26:02.280
Five sand wing soldiers lay dead on the

03:26:02.280 --> 03:26:04.319
sand, but the outlaws were still

03:26:04.319 --> 03:26:06.239
outnumbered almost 4 to one.

03:26:06.299 --> 03:26:09.120
Smolder with shouting orders as he shoved

03:26:09.120 --> 03:26:11.520
soldiers into formations, tightening the

03:26:11.520 --> 03:26:14.100
defenses, so a bristling wall of spears

03:26:14.100 --> 03:26:16.559
was ready to ram the scattered attacking

03:26:16.559 --> 03:26:16.979
dragons.

03:26:17.100 --> 03:26:20.760
One wave of sand wings piled into 6 claws

03:26:20.760 --> 03:26:23.459
who staggered back with a roar, losing

03:26:23.459 --> 03:26:25.860
height, so his bloodied tail swept the

03:26:25.860 --> 03:26:26.579
sand below him.

03:26:26.639 --> 03:26:30.180
Sunny watched in horror, as 7 soldiers

03:26:30.180 --> 03:26:32.639
encircled Thorn, cutting her off from her

03:26:32.639 --> 03:26:33.120
allies.

03:26:33.180 --> 03:26:37.500
The outlaws came to rescue me, and it's

03:26:37.500 --> 03:26:39.420
going to get them all killed.

03:26:39.479 --> 03:26:43.020
Chapter 12.

03:26:43.440 --> 03:26:47.040
Sunny paced from one end of the pavilion

03:26:47.040 --> 03:26:48.719
to the other, her heart pounding.

03:26:48.780 --> 03:26:51.420
Her eyes hurt from staring at the battle

03:26:51.420 --> 03:26:53.159
as if she'd been trying to change the

03:26:53.159 --> 03:26:55.079
outcome with the power of her eyeballs.

03:26:55.139 --> 03:26:57.600
Don't die trying to rescue me.

03:26:57.659 --> 03:27:00.059
Please, please, please don't die.

03:27:00.120 --> 03:27:03.479
It was almost killing her to watch as her

03:27:03.479 --> 03:27:06.059
mother dodged flames and claws and deadly

03:27:06.059 --> 03:27:06.600
tails.

03:27:06.659 --> 03:27:09.840
A giant sand wing slammed into Thorn's

03:27:09.840 --> 03:27:11.819
chest and tried to drive her down onto

03:27:11.819 --> 03:27:12.420
the sand.

03:27:12.479 --> 03:27:15.239
Thorn slashed at his snout and darted

03:27:15.239 --> 03:27:17.760
away, but another soldier attacked from

03:27:17.760 --> 03:27:20.040
behind her, stabbing his venomous tail

03:27:20.040 --> 03:27:21.840
down toward the center of her spine.

03:27:21.899 --> 03:27:25.139
Sunny shrieked with fear, and the

03:27:25.139 --> 03:27:26.879
messenger behind her nearly fell off the

03:27:26.879 --> 03:27:27.239
spire.

03:27:27.360 --> 03:27:28.680
What?

03:27:28.799 --> 03:27:29.819
He yelped.

03:27:29.879 --> 03:27:30.659
What is it?

03:27:30.719 --> 03:27:31.319
Who's dead?

03:27:31.379 --> 03:27:34.739
At the last moment, Kibli barreled into

03:27:34.739 --> 03:27:36.059
the soldier and knocked him away.

03:27:37.020 --> 03:27:38.639
Sonny wasn't sure her mother had even

03:27:38.639 --> 03:27:41.639
noticed how close that had been, she's

03:27:41.639 --> 03:27:43.799
not careful enough, Sonny thought

03:27:43.799 --> 03:27:46.319
anxiously, standing up on her back legs

03:27:46.319 --> 03:27:47.459
and flapping her wings.

03:27:47.520 --> 03:27:49.319
What's happening?

03:27:49.440 --> 03:27:52.079
The messenger said plaintively, craning

03:27:52.079 --> 03:27:52.739
to see around her.

03:27:52.860 --> 03:27:55.440
It's my mother, Sonny said.

03:27:55.500 --> 03:27:57.059
She's here to rescue me.

03:27:57.120 --> 03:28:00.420
The sandwing scrunged his snout at her.

03:28:00.479 --> 03:28:01.620
Are you sure?

03:28:01.739 --> 03:28:03.420
That doesn't sound like any mother I

03:28:03.420 --> 03:28:03.899
know.

03:28:03.959 --> 03:28:07.979
Well, that's just sad, Sonny said. trying

03:28:07.979 --> 03:28:09.659
to listen to him and watch the battle at

03:28:09.659 --> 03:28:10.200
the same time.

03:28:10.260 --> 03:28:12.059
Even your own mother?

03:28:12.120 --> 03:28:14.940
The other dragon made a noise that

03:28:14.940 --> 03:28:16.860
sounded half chuckle, half snort.

03:28:16.920 --> 03:28:19.860
My parents sent me to Burns Army to

03:28:19.860 --> 03:28:20.459
toughen me up.

03:28:20.520 --> 03:28:23.760
They said this way, I'd end up as brave

03:28:23.760 --> 03:28:26.399
as a real soldier or else dead, and

03:28:26.399 --> 03:28:27.780
either of those would be an improvement.

03:28:27.840 --> 03:28:29.700
What's your name?

03:28:29.760 --> 03:28:31.139
Sonny asked.

03:28:31.200 --> 03:28:34.799
Down below in the battle, 6 claws seized

03:28:34.799 --> 03:28:36.659
2 soldiers and smashed their heads

03:28:36.659 --> 03:28:39.239
together, then whirled to slash another

03:28:39.239 --> 03:28:40.319
one's throat with his tail.

03:28:40.440 --> 03:28:42.600
The messenger hesitated.

03:28:42.659 --> 03:28:44.760
Am I allowed to tell you that?

03:28:44.819 --> 03:28:46.379
Why not?

03:28:46.440 --> 03:28:47.879
My name is Sonny.

03:28:47.940 --> 03:28:50.280
I know, he said.

03:28:50.340 --> 03:28:51.540
All right.

03:28:51.600 --> 03:28:53.459
My name is Camel.

03:28:53.520 --> 03:28:56.340
Sonny flicked her wings open and shut

03:28:56.340 --> 03:28:58.379
brushing against the wind chimes.

03:28:58.500 --> 03:29:01.200
Camels seemed like a normal nervous

03:29:01.200 --> 03:29:03.420
dragon, someone she could be friends with

03:29:03.420 --> 03:29:04.200
in another life.

03:29:04.260 --> 03:29:06.420
Maybe he'd listen to reason.

03:29:06.479 --> 03:29:09.120
Do you have any dragonettes?

03:29:09.239 --> 03:29:09.659
she asked.

03:29:09.780 --> 03:29:13.319
Not yet, but my partner and I have 3 eggs

03:29:13.319 --> 03:29:15.959
hatching next month, he said proudly.

03:29:16.020 --> 03:29:18.899
So you can be a different kind of parent

03:29:18.899 --> 03:29:22.319
than yours were, Sonny said, the kind

03:29:22.319 --> 03:29:24.719
that takes care of his dragonettes, the

03:29:24.719 --> 03:29:26.459
kind who would attack a stronghold full

03:29:26.459 --> 03:29:28.200
of soldiers to protect them?

03:29:28.500 --> 03:29:29.459
She added hopefully.

03:29:29.579 --> 03:29:32.280
She didn't know much about parents in

03:29:32.280 --> 03:29:34.260
general, but she knew what she would do

03:29:34.260 --> 03:29:36.420
if she had dragonettes, and any of them

03:29:36.420 --> 03:29:37.020
were in danger.

03:29:37.079 --> 03:29:40.920
Hmm, said Camel, looking even more

03:29:40.920 --> 03:29:41.399
anxious.

03:29:41.459 --> 03:29:44.280
He swished his tail and gazed down at the

03:29:44.280 --> 03:29:44.639
battle.

03:29:44.700 --> 03:29:47.280
The blood on the sand, the sprawled

03:29:47.280 --> 03:29:49.200
bodies, the flashing claws.

03:29:49.260 --> 03:29:52.139
Maybe this isn't the right approach for

03:29:52.139 --> 03:29:54.000
this dragon, Sonny thought.

03:29:54.120 --> 03:29:58.139
All I'm saying, she continued, is that I

03:29:58.139 --> 03:29:59.819
can't stand here and watch my mother die

03:29:59.819 --> 03:30:00.840
trying to save me.

03:30:00.899 --> 03:30:03.299
Please, please let me go help her.

03:30:03.360 --> 03:30:06.899
She leaned toward the wide open blue sky

03:30:06.899 --> 03:30:09.420
imagining how she would dive in and drag

03:30:09.420 --> 03:30:11.100
all the soldiers away from Thorn.

03:30:11.219 --> 03:30:14.760
Oh, Camel said uncomfortably.

03:30:14.819 --> 03:30:17.340
Oh, no, no, I can't do that.

03:30:17.399 --> 03:30:19.559
If Burne finds out, she might take my

03:30:19.559 --> 03:30:20.040
eggs away.

03:30:20.100 --> 03:30:22.260
That wouldn't be good parenting, would

03:30:22.260 --> 03:30:22.440
it?

03:30:22.500 --> 03:30:24.239
Sunny sighed.

03:30:24.299 --> 03:30:27.420
I guess not, she admitted fairly.

03:30:27.479 --> 03:30:30.239
But maybe I can stop the fighting, so

03:30:30.239 --> 03:30:31.200
nobody else has to die.

03:30:31.260 --> 03:30:34.860
Camel hesitated again, looking down at

03:30:34.860 --> 03:30:37.020
the battle, and Sonny wondered if his

03:30:37.020 --> 03:30:38.459
partner was one of the ones out there

03:30:38.459 --> 03:30:38.879
fighting.

03:30:38.940 --> 03:30:40.559
How?

03:30:40.620 --> 03:30:41.639
He asked.

03:30:41.700 --> 03:30:44.040
I mean, you're not.

03:30:44.280 --> 03:30:46.799
He glanced at her harmless tale and away

03:30:46.799 --> 03:30:47.459
again quickly.

03:30:47.520 --> 03:30:52.559
Not exactly scary, not exactly big, not

03:30:52.559 --> 03:30:53.700
even a little bit useful.

03:30:53.819 --> 03:30:56.280
He was kind of right.

03:30:56.340 --> 03:30:58.620
What did she think she could really do if

03:30:58.620 --> 03:30:59.280
she joined in?

03:30:59.340 --> 03:31:01.860
Is there another way to stop them?

03:31:01.979 --> 03:31:03.420
A sunny way?

03:31:03.479 --> 03:31:06.659
She stared down at the battling dragons

03:31:06.659 --> 03:31:09.360
racking her brain, and then something

03:31:09.360 --> 03:31:10.979
moved under the sand.

03:31:11.040 --> 03:31:14.700
Sunny leaned forward, staring intently.

03:31:14.760 --> 03:31:18.059
Not far from one of the fallen soldiers, a

03:31:18.059 --> 03:31:20.340
patch of sand rippled as though something

03:31:20.340 --> 03:31:21.600
were buried underneath it.

03:31:21.659 --> 03:31:24.479
Something or someone.

03:31:24.540 --> 03:31:27.659
Sunny had the horrible feeling for a

03:31:27.659 --> 03:31:30.120
moment, that the ghost of Queen Oasis

03:31:30.120 --> 03:31:32.280
herself, was about to come bursting out

03:31:32.280 --> 03:31:34.079
of the sand to attack the dragons.

03:31:34.200 --> 03:31:37.020
But the head that popped out was not as

03:31:37.020 --> 03:31:37.799
sand wings.

03:31:37.860 --> 03:31:40.319
It was followed by shoulders and wings

03:31:40.319 --> 03:31:42.479
that glowed coppery orange in the bright

03:31:42.479 --> 03:31:43.020
sunlight.

03:31:43.079 --> 03:31:45.420
The dragon wriggled the rest of the way

03:31:45.420 --> 03:31:47.879
free, and began swarming across the sand

03:31:47.879 --> 03:31:49.559
toward the stronghold walls.

03:31:49.620 --> 03:31:51.659
Sonny gasped.

03:31:51.719 --> 03:31:54.299
She recognized those scales.

03:31:54.360 --> 03:31:57.059
Like hers, they were a color unique to

03:31:57.059 --> 03:31:59.520
only one dragon in Pyria, as far as

03:31:59.520 --> 03:32:00.000
anyone knew.

03:32:00.059 --> 03:32:01.979
It was peril.

03:32:02.040 --> 03:32:05.459
It had to be, Peril, the Sky Wing who had

03:32:05.459 --> 03:32:07.379
helped them escape from Queen Scarlet's

03:32:07.379 --> 03:32:07.739
palace.

03:32:07.799 --> 03:32:11.159
Well, 1st she had pretended to help them

03:32:11.159 --> 03:32:13.979
escape, And then she'd betrayed them, and

03:32:13.979 --> 03:32:16.559
then she'd nearly killed Clay, but in the

03:32:16.559 --> 03:32:17.760
end, she'd done the right thing.

03:32:17.879 --> 03:32:19.799
Although sometimes it was hard to

03:32:19.799 --> 03:32:20.280
remember that.

03:32:20.340 --> 03:32:23.579
But without her, the dragonettes and

03:32:23.579 --> 03:32:25.680
Kestrel might have been trapped in the

03:32:25.680 --> 03:32:28.379
Sky Palace until Scarlet figured out a

03:32:28.379 --> 03:32:29.940
thrilling death for each of them.

03:32:30.000 --> 03:32:34.020
Sunny's heart sank, thinking of Kestrel

03:32:34.020 --> 03:32:36.840
and how she'd died under blisters, claws

03:32:36.840 --> 03:32:37.680
and the kingdom of the sea.

03:32:37.739 --> 03:32:40.620
How would peril react to the news of her

03:32:40.620 --> 03:32:41.159
mother's death?

03:32:41.219 --> 03:32:44.459
But more important, what was she doing

03:32:44.459 --> 03:32:44.700
here?

03:32:44.760 --> 03:32:47.219
And why was she clearly trying to sneak

03:32:47.219 --> 03:32:48.180
into the palace?

03:32:48.239 --> 03:32:51.420
Peril reached the walls and glanced back

03:32:51.420 --> 03:32:53.399
at the battle, but the fighting was too

03:32:53.399 --> 03:32:54.719
fierce for anyone to notice her.

03:32:54.780 --> 03:32:57.600
She spread her wings and launched herself

03:32:57.600 --> 03:33:00.000
over the wall, landed neatly in the

03:33:00.000 --> 03:33:01.920
courtyard, and darted into the palace.

03:33:01.979 --> 03:33:05.819
Sonny inhaled sharply as an awful thought

03:33:05.819 --> 03:33:07.260
struck her.

03:33:07.319 --> 03:33:08.159
Surely not.

03:33:08.219 --> 03:33:10.979
Did you see that orange dragon?

03:33:11.040 --> 03:33:12.360
She asked Camel.

03:33:12.420 --> 03:33:13.500
I have to follow her.

03:33:13.559 --> 03:33:15.600
Come with me, so it's not like I'm

03:33:15.600 --> 03:33:16.139
escaping from you.

03:33:16.200 --> 03:33:18.899
Um, camel said.

03:33:18.959 --> 03:33:20.340
But wait, shouldn't I?

03:33:20.459 --> 03:33:22.379
Sonny didn't hear the end of that

03:33:22.379 --> 03:33:22.920
sentence.

03:33:22.979 --> 03:33:25.920
She was already in the air, and winging

03:33:25.920 --> 03:33:27.479
toward the courtyard that held the weird

03:33:27.479 --> 03:33:29.940
link tower, she could see the dark red

03:33:29.940 --> 03:33:31.920
crown of it looming over the rooftops.

03:33:31.979 --> 03:33:35.340
Her talons came down with a thump in the

03:33:35.340 --> 03:33:37.799
sand pit, and she glanced around at the

03:33:37.799 --> 03:33:40.319
tower door, but it was still closed, and

03:33:40.319 --> 03:33:42.000
she hoped, locked.

03:33:42.059 --> 03:33:44.760
Not that a lock on a wooden door would be

03:33:44.760 --> 03:33:47.219
much use at stopping peril into her fiery

03:33:47.219 --> 03:33:47.700
talons.

03:33:47.760 --> 03:33:50.520
The 6 sand winged soldiers arranged

03:33:50.520 --> 03:33:52.379
outside wouldn't be able to stop her

03:33:52.379 --> 03:33:52.799
either.

03:33:52.860 --> 03:33:55.680
They looked curiously at Sonny, but held

03:33:55.680 --> 03:33:56.340
their positions.

03:33:56.399 --> 03:33:59.700
Camel flapped down behind her and landed

03:33:59.700 --> 03:34:02.159
on the wall, as far from the tower as he

03:34:02.159 --> 03:34:03.959
could get without losing sight of Sonny.

03:34:04.020 --> 03:34:06.899
She waited a moment, trying to calm down

03:34:06.899 --> 03:34:07.500
her heartbeat.

03:34:07.620 --> 03:34:09.360
Maybe I'm wrong.

03:34:09.420 --> 03:34:11.639
Maybe peril isn't here to rescue

03:34:11.639 --> 03:34:12.299
Scarlet.

03:34:12.360 --> 03:34:14.219
I mean, why would she?

03:34:14.280 --> 03:34:17.520
But then she heard talons clattering over

03:34:17.520 --> 03:34:19.680
stone, and peril came running into the

03:34:19.680 --> 03:34:20.219
courtyard.

03:34:20.340 --> 03:34:23.219
The Sky Wing skidded to a stop when she

03:34:23.219 --> 03:34:24.059
saw Sonny.

03:34:24.120 --> 03:34:26.940
Her flame blue eyes went wide through the

03:34:26.940 --> 03:34:28.500
wisps of smoke that rose from her

03:34:28.500 --> 03:34:28.860
scales.

03:34:28.920 --> 03:34:33.360
Hi, peril, Sonny said, hoping she sounded

03:34:33.360 --> 03:34:35.879
more friendly than terrified, peril

03:34:35.879 --> 03:34:36.780
twitched nervously.

03:34:36.840 --> 03:34:39.659
She said not to let you guys stop me.

03:34:39.719 --> 03:34:42.059
Peril glanced around the courtyard

03:34:42.059 --> 03:34:44.219
peering into the shadows with a hopeful

03:34:44.219 --> 03:34:48.600
expression, is, um, I mean, are you all

03:34:48.600 --> 03:34:48.899
here?

03:34:48.959 --> 03:34:52.440
No, sorry, Sonny said.

03:34:52.500 --> 03:34:54.780
She knew who peril was really looking

03:34:54.780 --> 03:34:54.959
for.

03:34:55.020 --> 03:34:57.780
Clay's not here, but he worries about

03:34:57.780 --> 03:34:58.020
you.

03:34:58.079 --> 03:34:59.639
Did he say that?

03:34:59.700 --> 03:35:01.139
Parel asked.

03:35:01.200 --> 03:35:04.020
She touched her front talons together, the

03:35:04.020 --> 03:35:06.059
same way she had after Clay had taken her

03:35:06.059 --> 03:35:08.520
talons in his when they had said goodbye

03:35:08.520 --> 03:35:09.899
Sonny remembered.

03:35:09.899 --> 03:35:11.700
That he worries about me?

03:35:11.760 --> 03:35:12.899
What did he say exactly?

03:35:12.959 --> 03:35:17.219
Um, Sonny said, trying to remember the

03:35:17.219 --> 03:35:19.139
last time Clay had mentioned peril.

03:35:19.200 --> 03:35:22.079
They'd been a little busy lately, escaping

03:35:22.079 --> 03:35:24.180
from the sea wings and invading the night

03:35:24.180 --> 03:35:26.579
wing island and running from volcanoes

03:35:26.579 --> 03:35:28.920
but he had said something about her one

03:35:28.920 --> 03:35:31.500
night in the rainforest after Starflight

03:35:31.500 --> 03:35:32.040
had disappeared.

03:35:32.100 --> 03:35:34.559
Clay and Sonny had been curled together

03:35:34.559 --> 03:35:36.840
near Kinkaju, the little rain wing

03:35:36.840 --> 03:35:38.399
dragonette who'd been injured in the

03:35:38.399 --> 03:35:40.559
contest where glory became queen.

03:35:40.559 --> 03:35:43.260
She was asleep, and it was Sonny's turn

03:35:43.260 --> 03:35:43.739
to watch her.

03:35:43.799 --> 03:35:45.540
Clay was keeping her company.

03:35:45.600 --> 03:35:49.139
He said, I wonder where peril is right

03:35:49.139 --> 03:35:50.760
now, Sonny said.

03:35:50.819 --> 03:35:52.440
I hope she's all right.

03:35:52.500 --> 03:35:54.540
There's that new queen in the Sky

03:35:54.540 --> 03:35:55.020
Kingdom.

03:35:55.079 --> 03:35:58.920
And I said, Ruby, and he said, right

03:35:58.920 --> 03:35:59.340
her.

03:35:59.399 --> 03:36:01.680
I hope she's taking care of peril and not

03:36:01.680 --> 03:36:02.520
making her fight anymore.

03:36:02.579 --> 03:36:06.000
Carol waited for a moment and then said

03:36:06.000 --> 03:36:07.739
That's it?

03:36:07.799 --> 03:36:11.040
Well, then his stomach started growling

03:36:11.040 --> 03:36:12.420
and he had to go look for something to

03:36:12.420 --> 03:36:15.239
eat, Sonny said, but he wants to see you

03:36:15.239 --> 03:36:15.659
again.

03:36:15.719 --> 03:36:16.440
I'm sure of it.

03:36:16.500 --> 03:36:19.319
I bet you've had all kinds of adventures

03:36:19.319 --> 03:36:22.020
together, peril said, a little bitterly.

03:36:22.079 --> 03:36:25.799
It's been really scary, Sonny said.

03:36:25.860 --> 03:36:28.440
It seems like every dragon we meet either

03:36:28.440 --> 03:36:30.420
wants to kill us or lock us up.

03:36:30.479 --> 03:36:33.120
She glanced around at the tower inside.

03:36:33.180 --> 03:36:35.219
Case in point.

03:36:35.280 --> 03:36:38.700
Peril looked down at her talons, the

03:36:38.700 --> 03:36:40.739
sunlight gleamed on the gold veins in her

03:36:40.739 --> 03:36:41.100
wings.

03:36:41.159 --> 03:36:43.020
What about you?

03:36:43.079 --> 03:36:44.100
Sonny asked.

03:36:44.219 --> 03:36:46.680
Um, have you...

03:36:46.860 --> 03:36:48.600
She didn't know how to finish that

03:36:48.600 --> 03:36:49.139
sentence.

03:36:49.200 --> 03:36:51.540
Have you stopped killing dragons?

03:36:51.600 --> 03:36:54.059
Have you found a safe way to live around

03:36:54.059 --> 03:36:54.420
others?

03:36:54.540 --> 03:36:57.059
Have you by any chance come here to

03:36:57.059 --> 03:36:59.280
rescue a dragon who really wants to kill

03:36:59.280 --> 03:36:59.579
me?

03:36:59.639 --> 03:37:04.139
The answer is, she's not, Pearl said

03:37:04.139 --> 03:37:04.620
sharply.

03:37:04.680 --> 03:37:07.500
Ruby is not taking care of me.

03:37:07.559 --> 03:37:10.139
She ordered me out of the Sky Kingdom as

03:37:10.139 --> 03:37:10.860
soon as she took over.

03:37:10.920 --> 03:37:14.040
She said if I ever set claws in the sky

03:37:14.040 --> 03:37:16.860
palace again, she'd find a way to kill me

03:37:16.860 --> 03:37:17.639
and I'd better believe it.

03:37:17.760 --> 03:37:20.159
She said I was dangerous and

03:37:20.159 --> 03:37:22.079
unpredictable, and she didn't want me

03:37:22.079 --> 03:37:22.860
near her subjects.

03:37:22.920 --> 03:37:27.120
Her voice broke, and she coughed, ducking

03:37:27.120 --> 03:37:28.379
under one wing.

03:37:28.440 --> 03:37:29.760
Oh, peril.

03:37:29.819 --> 03:37:32.520
I'm so sorry, Sonny said.

03:37:32.579 --> 03:37:34.319
Don't feel sorry for me.

03:37:34.379 --> 03:37:36.780
Peril lifted her head and frowned.

03:37:36.899 --> 03:37:38.700
I am dangerous.

03:37:38.760 --> 03:37:41.159
That's like the whole entire point of

03:37:41.159 --> 03:37:41.340
me.

03:37:41.399 --> 03:37:43.139
That's not true.

03:37:43.200 --> 03:37:44.459
Sonny said.

03:37:44.520 --> 03:37:46.260
You can be whatever you want to be.

03:37:46.319 --> 03:37:51.120
I mean, I could say, well, I have no barb

03:37:51.120 --> 03:37:51.719
on my tail.

03:37:51.780 --> 03:37:54.540
I guess I'm just harmless and useless and

03:37:54.540 --> 03:37:56.219
should sit in the corner covering my head

03:37:56.219 --> 03:37:57.299
whenever there's a fight.

03:37:57.360 --> 03:38:00.299
But I don't want to be useless, and I'm

03:38:00.299 --> 03:38:00.959
not going to do that.

03:38:01.020 --> 03:38:03.360
Not if dragons I care about are in

03:38:03.360 --> 03:38:03.659
danger.

03:38:03.719 --> 03:38:06.840
She glanced at the sky. wondering

03:38:06.840 --> 03:38:09.059
anxiously how the battle was going, and

03:38:09.059 --> 03:38:10.620
whether Thorn was still all right.

03:38:10.680 --> 03:38:14.100
Um, speaking of which, I could really use

03:38:14.100 --> 03:38:14.819
your help right now.

03:38:14.879 --> 03:38:17.219
Peril shook herself.

03:38:17.280 --> 03:38:18.840
Copper scales flashing.

03:38:18.899 --> 03:38:20.520
I can't help you.

03:38:20.579 --> 03:38:22.799
I have to rescue Scarlett while everyone

03:38:22.799 --> 03:38:24.420
is distracted with that battle outside.

03:38:24.479 --> 03:38:28.079
Sunny felt a cold, shiver fear run

03:38:28.079 --> 03:38:28.860
through her scales.

03:38:28.920 --> 03:38:31.680
She had still hoped maybe that wasn't why

03:38:31.680 --> 03:38:32.520
peril was here.

03:38:32.579 --> 03:38:34.139
But why?

03:38:34.139 --> 03:38:35.100
she cried.

03:38:35.159 --> 03:38:37.620
I've been waiting days for a chance like

03:38:37.620 --> 03:38:39.540
this, when I could get her out without

03:38:39.540 --> 03:38:41.700
fighting anyone, Pearl said.

03:38:41.760 --> 03:38:44.040
So you can tell Clay, I'm trying really

03:38:44.040 --> 03:38:45.360
hard not to kill anyone.

03:38:45.420 --> 03:38:48.479
She hesitated, looking at the guards

03:38:48.479 --> 03:38:50.819
behind Sunny, between her and the tower.

03:38:50.940 --> 03:38:54.540
I'm trying, she said again.

03:38:54.600 --> 03:38:57.840
No, I mean, why would you help her?

03:38:57.899 --> 03:38:59.219
Sonny asked.

03:38:59.280 --> 03:39:00.959
After everything she did to you.

03:39:01.079 --> 03:39:04.500
The breeze picked up into a quiet wind

03:39:04.500 --> 03:39:07.260
scattering grains of sand across Sonny's

03:39:07.260 --> 03:39:09.899
claws, and bringing her the heavy, scaly

03:39:09.899 --> 03:39:11.940
smell of fear from the sand wings behind

03:39:11.940 --> 03:39:14.579
her, they hadn't moved from their spots

03:39:14.579 --> 03:39:16.920
but they stood tensed and ready with

03:39:16.920 --> 03:39:17.459
their weapons.

03:39:17.520 --> 03:39:20.219
Sonny guessed at least some of them knew

03:39:20.219 --> 03:39:22.559
who Perel was from visits to the sky

03:39:22.559 --> 03:39:23.760
kingdom with burn.

03:39:23.819 --> 03:39:27.239
I know Scarlet's not perfect, Peril

03:39:27.239 --> 03:39:27.600
said.

03:39:27.659 --> 03:39:30.600
Understatement of the year, Sonny

03:39:30.600 --> 03:39:30.899
thought.

03:39:30.959 --> 03:39:33.180
But she didn't kill me when she could

03:39:33.180 --> 03:39:33.479
have.

03:39:33.540 --> 03:39:36.479
When anyone else would have, when I was a

03:39:36.479 --> 03:39:38.940
dragonette, and she didn't throw me out

03:39:38.940 --> 03:39:40.860
she treated me like I was special.

03:39:40.920 --> 03:39:45.120
She lied to you, Sonny pointed out, about

03:39:45.120 --> 03:39:47.700
Kestrel, and about the black rocks she

03:39:47.700 --> 03:39:49.260
said you had to eat so you could never

03:39:49.260 --> 03:39:52.319
leave her, she was using you, not taking

03:39:52.319 --> 03:39:52.860
care of you.

03:39:52.920 --> 03:39:55.559
She took better care of me than my mother

03:39:55.559 --> 03:39:55.860
did.

03:39:55.920 --> 03:39:57.479
Peril flared.

03:39:57.540 --> 03:40:00.600
And from what I saw of her, Kestrel isn't

03:40:00.600 --> 03:40:02.340
the nicest dragon in the world either

03:40:02.340 --> 03:40:02.700
right?

03:40:02.760 --> 03:40:04.920
She hesitated again.

03:40:04.979 --> 03:40:07.799
Then said tentatively, have you seen

03:40:07.799 --> 03:40:08.520
Kestrel?

03:40:08.579 --> 03:40:10.260
Do you know where she is?

03:40:10.319 --> 03:40:13.559
I wonder, I've been wondering if I should

03:40:13.559 --> 03:40:15.059
have gone with her when she asked me to.

03:40:15.120 --> 03:40:17.700
Sonny's heart sank.

03:40:17.760 --> 03:40:19.979
She didn't want to deliver this news.

03:40:20.040 --> 03:40:22.440
But I can't lie to her.

03:40:22.500 --> 03:40:25.500
Literally 20 seconds after I just accused

03:40:25.500 --> 03:40:26.879
Scarlet of so much lying.

03:40:27.000 --> 03:40:30.120
I don't know how she'll react, but I have

03:40:30.120 --> 03:40:30.899
to tell her the truth.

03:40:30.959 --> 03:40:34.139
Peril, she said softly.

03:40:34.200 --> 03:40:38.459
I'm really sorry, but Kestrel's dead.

03:40:38.520 --> 03:40:42.239
Carol stared at her for a long moment, her

03:40:42.239 --> 03:40:45.180
odd eyes glowing blue and black, and then

03:40:45.180 --> 03:40:48.180
slowly, like a mountain crumbling, she

03:40:48.180 --> 03:40:50.100
collapsed to the stones and covered her

03:40:50.100 --> 03:40:51.899
face with her talons.

03:40:51.959 --> 03:40:54.120
No, no, no, she said.

03:40:54.180 --> 03:40:55.739
I sent her away.

03:40:55.799 --> 03:40:57.479
I said we'd find each other again.

03:40:57.600 --> 03:40:59.040
I know.

03:40:59.100 --> 03:41:02.100
Sonny said, wishing she could wrap her

03:41:02.100 --> 03:41:04.799
wings around peril the way Clay had, but

03:41:04.799 --> 03:41:06.780
Clay was the only dragon she knew who

03:41:06.780 --> 03:41:08.040
could touch peril without dying.

03:41:08.100 --> 03:41:09.659
I know.

03:41:09.719 --> 03:41:12.120
Oh, peril, I'm so sorry.

03:41:12.180 --> 03:41:15.299
Listen, she said desperately.

03:41:15.360 --> 03:41:18.239
Her anxiety about the battle outside, was

03:41:18.239 --> 03:41:20.459
making every scale on her wings feel like

03:41:20.459 --> 03:41:21.840
jumping off and flying away.

03:41:21.959 --> 03:41:24.180
Listen, I'm like you.

03:41:24.239 --> 03:41:26.579
I thought my mother didn't want me either

03:41:26.579 --> 03:41:28.799
but I just found out that's not true.

03:41:28.860 --> 03:41:30.600
Just like you.

03:41:30.659 --> 03:41:33.840
My mother wanted me, the way Kestrel

03:41:33.840 --> 03:41:36.959
wanted you, except I'm so afraid she's

03:41:36.959 --> 03:41:38.520
going to die before I get to know her.

03:41:38.579 --> 03:41:40.680
And that's why I need your help.

03:41:40.799 --> 03:41:42.540
Please, peril.

03:41:42.600 --> 03:41:44.879
She's attacking the palace right now

03:41:44.879 --> 03:41:46.799
trying to rescue me, and you could save

03:41:46.799 --> 03:41:47.040
her.

03:41:47.100 --> 03:41:48.180
I'm sorry.

03:41:48.239 --> 03:41:50.520
I know it's awful to throw all that at

03:41:50.520 --> 03:41:52.680
you at once, but I really need you.

03:41:52.739 --> 03:41:55.799
Peril pressed her talons into the stone

03:41:55.799 --> 03:41:56.520
and sat up.

03:41:56.579 --> 03:41:59.879
She took a deep breath, exhaling smoke

03:41:59.879 --> 03:42:01.260
and a cloud around her wings.

03:42:01.319 --> 03:42:04.920
Finally, she looked down at Sonny, with

03:42:04.920 --> 03:42:06.479
an expression as though she was trying to

03:42:06.479 --> 03:42:09.000
find any small part of herself in Sonny's

03:42:09.000 --> 03:42:09.180
eyes.

03:42:09.239 --> 03:42:12.180
Tell me more, she said.

03:42:12.239 --> 03:42:14.879
Her legs trembled, as if they might not

03:42:14.879 --> 03:42:17.040
keep holding her up, but she listened

03:42:17.040 --> 03:42:19.079
intently as Sonny explained about Thorn

03:42:19.079 --> 03:42:20.219
and the outlaws.

03:42:20.280 --> 03:42:23.760
All right, she said at last when Sonny

03:42:23.760 --> 03:42:24.479
paused for breath.

03:42:24.540 --> 03:42:26.280
I'll stop the battle.

03:42:26.340 --> 03:42:28.860
But then I'm setting Scarlet free, so

03:42:28.860 --> 03:42:30.059
don't try to get in my way.

03:42:30.180 --> 03:42:33.959
But that's the deal, Pearl said

03:42:33.959 --> 03:42:34.620
stubbornly.

03:42:34.680 --> 03:42:36.420
I've already lost one mother.

03:42:36.479 --> 03:42:39.540
Scarlet is what's left, so she's the best

03:42:39.540 --> 03:42:39.959
I can do.

03:42:40.079 --> 03:42:43.500
Sonny curled her tail around her talons.

03:42:43.559 --> 03:42:46.559
She was very worried about this plan, but

03:42:46.559 --> 03:42:47.879
there wasn't time to keep arguing.

03:42:47.940 --> 03:42:49.200
And what could she say?

03:42:49.319 --> 03:42:52.079
Having no mother would be better than

03:42:52.079 --> 03:42:52.920
having that mother.

03:42:52.979 --> 03:42:55.620
What did she know about it, really?

03:42:55.739 --> 03:42:58.620
Thank you, she said instead.

03:42:58.680 --> 03:43:00.959
I trust you, she added.

03:43:01.020 --> 03:43:03.659
She wasn't sure she really did, but she

03:43:03.659 --> 03:43:04.139
wanted to.

03:43:04.200 --> 03:43:06.479
I know you can do it without hurting

03:43:06.479 --> 03:43:06.780
anyone.

03:43:06.840 --> 03:43:10.860
Um, Camel said, and happily from above

03:43:10.860 --> 03:43:11.159
them.

03:43:11.219 --> 03:43:13.440
I really think I shouldn't let this

03:43:13.440 --> 03:43:13.860
happen.

03:43:13.920 --> 03:43:17.819
You can't stop her, Sonny said to him, as

03:43:17.819 --> 03:43:18.959
peril shot into the sky.

03:43:19.020 --> 03:43:21.659
And your job is to watch me.

03:43:21.719 --> 03:43:22.739
That all Smolder said.

03:43:22.799 --> 03:43:24.059
I'm not going anywhere.

03:43:24.120 --> 03:43:24.420
See?

03:43:24.479 --> 03:43:27.479
Well, except back up to the pavilion to

03:43:27.479 --> 03:43:27.719
watch.

03:43:27.780 --> 03:43:28.620
Come on.

03:43:28.739 --> 03:43:31.440
She followed Peril up and watched the

03:43:31.440 --> 03:43:33.659
shimmering copper scales flash toward the

03:43:33.659 --> 03:43:34.680
battle outside the walls.

03:43:34.739 --> 03:43:38.459
From the high pavilion, Sonny could see 2

03:43:38.459 --> 03:43:41.159
more corpses lying below the battle, but

03:43:41.159 --> 03:43:43.139
after a heart stopping moment, she

03:43:43.139 --> 03:43:45.600
realized that neither one was thorn or 6

03:43:45.600 --> 03:43:48.360
claws, she stared at the battle intently

03:43:48.360 --> 03:43:50.639
until she finally spotted her mother

03:43:50.639 --> 03:43:52.979
grappling claw to claw with a soldier.

03:43:53.040 --> 03:43:56.280
Smolder was there too, not far from

03:43:56.280 --> 03:43:58.680
Kibley, shouting orders and darting

03:43:58.680 --> 03:44:00.059
around the formations.

03:44:00.120 --> 03:44:02.459
He was one of the 1st to spot peril as

03:44:02.459 --> 03:44:03.059
she approached.

03:44:03.120 --> 03:44:05.760
Sonny could tell because he froze very

03:44:05.760 --> 03:44:07.979
suddenly, staring in the direction of the

03:44:07.979 --> 03:44:08.459
sky wing.

03:44:08.520 --> 03:44:11.159
The soldiers around him turned to see

03:44:11.159 --> 03:44:11.940
what he was looking at.

03:44:12.000 --> 03:44:14.340
Three of them took one look at peril

03:44:14.340 --> 03:44:17.340
shrieked, and fled into the desert. their

03:44:17.340 --> 03:44:19.319
shadows flickering rapidly across the

03:44:19.319 --> 03:44:21.239
dunes, until they vanished in the

03:44:21.239 --> 03:44:23.879
direction of the scorpion den, Sonny

03:44:23.879 --> 03:44:26.040
guessed they had been to Burns Palace, and

03:44:26.040 --> 03:44:27.360
seen what peril could do.

03:44:27.420 --> 03:44:31.379
She'd never seen what peril could do, not

03:44:31.379 --> 03:44:32.159
to another dragon.

03:44:32.219 --> 03:44:34.799
She'd been trapped in her cage while all

03:44:34.799 --> 03:44:36.600
her friends were in the arena at the Sky

03:44:36.600 --> 03:44:38.520
Palace, so she'd missed all the

03:44:38.520 --> 03:44:38.760
fighting.

03:44:38.879 --> 03:44:40.799
But Claya told her about it.

03:44:40.860 --> 03:44:44.219
The melting scales, the black talon

03:44:44.219 --> 03:44:46.559
prints burning into her victims, the

03:44:46.559 --> 03:44:49.139
scorched smell, and it sounded

03:44:49.139 --> 03:44:50.040
terrifying.

03:44:50.100 --> 03:44:52.079
She hoped she wasn't about to see it

03:44:52.079 --> 03:44:52.319
now.

03:44:52.379 --> 03:44:56.040
Gradually, the outlaws stopped fighting

03:44:56.040 --> 03:44:58.559
too, and fell back. until there was a

03:44:58.559 --> 03:45:00.540
wide circle of dragons around the clear

03:45:00.540 --> 03:45:02.579
space of sky where peril hovered.

03:45:02.639 --> 03:45:05.700
Sonny's sharp ears caught some of what

03:45:05.700 --> 03:45:07.680
peril was saying to them, but not all of

03:45:07.680 --> 03:45:07.860
it.

03:45:07.920 --> 03:45:10.440
Something about taking over the fortress

03:45:10.440 --> 03:45:12.120
something else about surrendering.

03:45:12.120 --> 03:45:15.719
She saw a smolder start forward, as if he

03:45:15.719 --> 03:45:17.100
were going to argue with peril.

03:45:17.159 --> 03:45:20.520
Oh, please don't, she thought anxiously.

03:45:20.579 --> 03:45:22.860
It was strange to admit it, but she

03:45:22.860 --> 03:45:23.579
actually liked him.

03:45:23.639 --> 03:45:26.940
She definitely didn't want him to die, or

03:45:26.940 --> 03:45:28.260
get his scales melted.

03:45:28.319 --> 03:45:31.319
But several sandwing soldiers grabbed him

03:45:31.319 --> 03:45:33.659
and pulled him back, shaking their heads

03:45:33.659 --> 03:45:34.860
and pointing to the smoke.

03:45:34.920 --> 03:45:37.020
There rose clearly from Pearl's wings.

03:45:37.139 --> 03:45:40.680
Thorn said something, imperil gestured

03:45:40.680 --> 03:45:41.639
toward the stronghold.

03:45:41.639 --> 03:45:44.819
With a sort of grateful bow, Thorn flew

03:45:44.819 --> 03:45:47.579
past her, followed by all her outlaws.

03:45:47.639 --> 03:45:49.079
Hooray!

03:45:49.139 --> 03:45:51.780
Sonny cried, flapping her wings with

03:45:51.780 --> 03:45:52.200
excitement.

03:45:52.319 --> 03:45:54.360
Brace you to the courtyard, camel.

03:45:54.420 --> 03:45:57.000
She leaped off the tower and soared down

03:45:57.000 --> 03:45:59.399
toward the stones, where she'd 1st landed

03:45:59.399 --> 03:46:00.120
in the stronghold.

03:46:00.180 --> 03:46:03.840
Thorn had just sat down and was turning

03:46:03.840 --> 03:46:06.000
to issue orders to her dragons, when

03:46:06.000 --> 03:46:07.979
Sunny catapulted to a stop in front of

03:46:07.979 --> 03:46:09.719
her, and threw her wings around her

03:46:09.719 --> 03:46:10.620
mother.

03:46:10.680 --> 03:46:13.860
By all the snakes, her mother yelped

03:46:13.860 --> 03:46:14.879
Sonny.

03:46:15.000 --> 03:46:17.520
She lifted Sonny off her talons and spun

03:46:17.520 --> 03:46:18.299
her around.

03:46:18.360 --> 03:46:19.559
Never mind.

03:46:19.620 --> 03:46:22.319
She shouted at the outlaws over Sonny's

03:46:22.319 --> 03:46:22.680
shoulder.

03:46:22.739 --> 03:46:23.579
Found her.

03:46:23.700 --> 03:46:27.180
Sonny felt giddy and weightless, like a

03:46:27.180 --> 03:46:29.639
tent with its pegs pulled up, flying

03:46:29.639 --> 03:46:30.780
loose in a sandstorm.

03:46:30.840 --> 03:46:32.579
You came to get me.

03:46:32.639 --> 03:46:34.260
She said breathlessly.

03:46:34.319 --> 03:46:37.500
Of course I did, Beetle, her mother said

03:46:37.500 --> 03:46:39.000
stepping back and looking around.

03:46:39.120 --> 03:46:41.399
Six claws told me everything.

03:46:41.459 --> 03:46:43.379
I spent 7 years looking for you.

03:46:43.440 --> 03:46:45.899
I wasn't about to lose you after only 10

03:46:45.899 --> 03:46:46.739
minutes of conversation.

03:46:46.799 --> 03:46:49.379
She grinned with all her teeth.

03:46:49.440 --> 03:46:52.139
Besides, I've always wanted to invade

03:46:52.139 --> 03:46:53.219
Burns stronghold.

03:46:53.280 --> 03:46:54.659
I take it she is not here.

03:46:54.780 --> 03:46:58.559
Luckily, Sonny said, I doubt she'd have

03:46:58.559 --> 03:47:00.299
surrendered as graciously as Smolder

03:47:00.299 --> 03:47:00.600
did.

03:47:00.659 --> 03:47:03.180
We should do the tour quick before she

03:47:03.180 --> 03:47:03.780
comes back then.

03:47:03.840 --> 03:47:06.780
Thorn said cheerfully, as if she hadn't

03:47:06.780 --> 03:47:08.520
been scales away from death a few moments

03:47:08.520 --> 03:47:08.819
earlier.

03:47:08.879 --> 03:47:11.040
What do you think that is?

03:47:11.159 --> 03:47:14.040
She put one wing over Sonny's shoulders

03:47:14.040 --> 03:47:16.500
and steered her toward the black obelisk

03:47:16.620 --> 03:47:17.399
Sonny had noticed before.

03:47:17.520 --> 03:47:20.879
Their claws sank into the sand around the

03:47:20.879 --> 03:47:23.760
monument, which was white and clean, as

03:47:23.760 --> 03:47:24.899
if it were swept every day.

03:47:24.959 --> 03:47:27.420
As they got closer.

03:47:27.479 --> 03:47:29.040
Sonny could read the words carved and

03:47:29.040 --> 03:47:30.540
painted in gold on the side of the

03:47:30.540 --> 03:47:31.260
pillar.

03:47:31.319 --> 03:47:35.219
Here lies Queen Oasis, mother of Queen

03:47:35.219 --> 03:47:35.819
Bern.

03:47:35.879 --> 03:47:38.459
Her bones now belong to the sands of

03:47:38.459 --> 03:47:39.059
time.

03:47:39.120 --> 03:47:43.139
Yikes, Sonny said, suddenly realizing

03:47:43.139 --> 03:47:46.079
what it meant, she scrambled sideways, off

03:47:46.079 --> 03:47:48.120
the sand, pulling Thorn along with her.

03:47:48.180 --> 03:47:52.200
Queen Oasis is buried under there, right

03:47:52.200 --> 03:47:52.680
below us.

03:47:52.739 --> 03:47:56.639
Probably where she died, Thorn guessed.

03:47:56.700 --> 03:47:58.680
Looking up at the walls Burne had added

03:47:58.680 --> 03:47:59.520
after she took over.

03:47:59.579 --> 03:48:02.040
This would have been right outside the

03:48:02.040 --> 03:48:04.020
original palace, where the scavengers

03:48:04.020 --> 03:48:04.500
attacked her.

03:48:04.559 --> 03:48:06.899
She peered at the inscription again.

03:48:06.959 --> 03:48:09.420
That's more poetic than I would have

03:48:09.420 --> 03:48:10.260
expected from Bern.

03:48:10.319 --> 03:48:11.459
Very impressive.

03:48:11.520 --> 03:48:14.520
The sound of wing beats overhead made

03:48:14.520 --> 03:48:16.680
them both look up as the sand wing

03:48:16.680 --> 03:48:18.120
soldiers came flapping back into the

03:48:18.120 --> 03:48:18.659
courtyard.

03:48:18.719 --> 03:48:21.659
With them were peril and smolder, who

03:48:21.659 --> 03:48:23.399
spiraled down to land beside Thorn.

03:48:23.459 --> 03:48:27.180
I'm going to be in so much trouble.

03:48:27.239 --> 03:48:29.700
Smolder said to Sonny with a sigh.

03:48:29.760 --> 03:48:31.979
Burn might actually kill me this time.

03:48:32.100 --> 03:48:34.319
Losing you and Scarlet in one fill

03:48:34.319 --> 03:48:34.979
swoop.

03:48:35.040 --> 03:48:37.440
That's probably worse than anything my

03:48:37.440 --> 03:48:38.340
brothers ever did.

03:48:38.399 --> 03:48:41.459
I'm sorry, Sonny said.

03:48:41.520 --> 03:48:45.059
Sorry enough to stay our prisoner, Smolder

03:48:45.059 --> 03:48:45.659
asked hopefully.

03:48:45.780 --> 03:48:48.719
Who is this hilarious dragon?

03:48:48.780 --> 03:48:49.860
Thorn asked her.

03:48:49.979 --> 03:48:53.879
This is Smolder, Burns brother, Sonny

03:48:53.879 --> 03:48:54.180
said.

03:48:54.239 --> 03:48:56.760
Smolder, this is Thorn, my mother.

03:48:56.879 --> 03:48:59.760
She's the leader of the out claws, and

03:48:59.760 --> 03:49:00.780
this is peril.

03:49:00.840 --> 03:49:03.659
Thorn half bowed again to peril.

03:49:03.719 --> 03:49:06.600
Our lucky angel, she said.

03:49:06.719 --> 03:49:08.879
Pearl nodded, looking a bit

03:49:08.879 --> 03:49:09.540
uncomfortable.

03:49:09.600 --> 03:49:11.579
Sonny guessed she wasn't used to

03:49:11.579 --> 03:49:13.620
gratitude, and that she'd certainly never

03:49:13.620 --> 03:49:14.940
been called an angel before.

03:49:15.000 --> 03:49:18.959
Perhaps I should move to the scorpion

03:49:18.959 --> 03:49:19.379
den.

03:49:19.440 --> 03:49:21.180
Smolder said gloomily.

03:49:21.239 --> 03:49:22.920
Thorn, was it?

03:49:22.979 --> 03:49:24.000
Hmm.

03:49:24.059 --> 03:49:26.940
He gave her a thoughtful look, as if he'd

03:49:26.940 --> 03:49:27.719
heard of her somewhere before.

03:49:27.780 --> 03:49:30.959
I need to kill the dragon who betrayed me

03:49:30.959 --> 03:49:32.100
Thorn announced.

03:49:32.159 --> 03:49:33.420
His name is Addix.

03:49:33.479 --> 03:49:34.379
Please produce him.

03:49:34.500 --> 03:49:36.420
Oh no, don't.

03:49:36.420 --> 03:49:37.739
Sonny blurted.

03:49:37.799 --> 03:49:40.079
I mean, don't kill him, please.

03:49:40.139 --> 03:49:44.219
He only, he just, he had his reasons, and

03:49:44.219 --> 03:49:46.020
look, I'm all right, aren't I?

03:49:46.139 --> 03:49:48.840
Her mother tilted her head at Sonny

03:49:48.840 --> 03:49:50.700
looking surprised and concerned.

03:49:50.760 --> 03:49:52.620
Don't you want to punish him?

03:49:52.680 --> 03:49:54.000
Aren't you angry?

03:49:54.059 --> 03:49:55.680
Am I?

03:49:55.739 --> 03:49:58.739
Sunny glanced at the barracks of soldiers

03:49:58.739 --> 03:49:59.879
beyond Smolder.

03:49:59.940 --> 03:50:02.280
Somewhere in there, addicts had been

03:50:02.280 --> 03:50:04.559
reunited with his family, and somewhere

03:50:04.559 --> 03:50:06.780
in there, he was probably hiding right

03:50:06.780 --> 03:50:09.000
now, knowing what might happen to him

03:50:09.000 --> 03:50:09.299
next.

03:50:09.360 --> 03:50:12.659
Punishing him won't make anything better

03:50:12.659 --> 03:50:13.739
Sonny said.

03:50:13.799 --> 03:50:15.899
It'll probably just make someone else

03:50:15.899 --> 03:50:18.479
angry and vengeful and lead to more awful

03:50:18.479 --> 03:50:18.719
things.

03:50:18.780 --> 03:50:20.579
I'm really all right.

03:50:20.639 --> 03:50:22.620
Let's leave him and get out of here.

03:50:22.680 --> 03:50:25.799
Thorn brushed Sonny's wing with hers and

03:50:25.799 --> 03:50:26.159
nodded.

03:50:26.219 --> 03:50:28.620
All right, if that's what you want.

03:50:28.680 --> 03:50:30.360
Mercy is yours to grant.

03:50:30.420 --> 03:50:32.879
I have one more question for this dragon

03:50:32.879 --> 03:50:33.059
though.

03:50:33.120 --> 03:50:34.739
She turned to smolder.

03:50:34.799 --> 03:50:36.659
You've lived here a long time.

03:50:36.719 --> 03:50:38.579
Can you tell me if you have any night

03:50:38.579 --> 03:50:39.420
wing prisoners?

03:50:39.479 --> 03:50:41.459
Smolder shook his head.

03:50:41.520 --> 03:50:45.059
No, I'm afraid my sister doesn't keep

03:50:45.059 --> 03:50:46.020
most of her prisoners.

03:50:46.079 --> 03:50:47.760
Alive, I mean.

03:50:47.819 --> 03:50:51.180
You had one night wing, though, Sonny

03:50:51.180 --> 03:50:51.540
offered.

03:50:51.600 --> 03:50:53.459
In Burns collection, didn't you?

03:50:53.520 --> 03:50:55.620
The stuffed one that Scarlet destroyed?

03:50:55.680 --> 03:50:57.239
What?

03:50:57.299 --> 03:50:58.319
Thorn said.

03:50:58.379 --> 03:50:59.879
Her wings went very still.

03:50:59.940 --> 03:51:01.620
What do you mean?

03:51:01.680 --> 03:51:02.700
Stuffed.

03:51:02.819 --> 03:51:05.399
It's sort of a hobby for burn.

03:51:05.459 --> 03:51:08.040
Smolder said, with an embarrassed

03:51:08.040 --> 03:51:08.459
expression.

03:51:08.520 --> 03:51:11.040
If she finds a dragon she wants for her

03:51:11.040 --> 03:51:13.379
collection, she'll usually kill him and

03:51:13.379 --> 03:51:14.280
stuff him herself.

03:51:14.340 --> 03:51:15.479
I know.

03:51:15.540 --> 03:51:17.040
It sounds pretty horrible.

03:51:17.100 --> 03:51:21.059
It is horrible, Sonny told him bluntly.

03:51:21.120 --> 03:51:22.860
It's one of the worst things I've ever

03:51:22.860 --> 03:51:24.360
heard, ever.

03:51:24.420 --> 03:51:26.700
Where?

03:51:26.760 --> 03:51:29.459
Thorn said to smolder, in a cold voice.

03:51:29.520 --> 03:51:32.100
Show me this murdered night wing.

03:51:32.219 --> 03:51:33.360
Right now.

03:51:33.420 --> 03:51:37.860
Chapter 13.

03:51:38.100 --> 03:51:41.459
As Smolder led them through the labyrinth

03:51:41.459 --> 03:51:43.680
of the palace again, Sonny noticed that

03:51:43.680 --> 03:51:45.659
Parel kept her wings pressed as close to

03:51:45.659 --> 03:51:46.500
her body as she could.

03:51:46.559 --> 03:51:50.159
Afraid of setting something on fire, she

03:51:50.159 --> 03:51:52.680
guessed, feeling sorry for the sky wing.

03:51:52.739 --> 03:51:55.079
Mother, she whispered.

03:51:55.139 --> 03:51:57.420
Why do we care about this night wing?

03:51:57.479 --> 03:51:59.639
Hopefully, we don't.

03:51:59.700 --> 03:52:01.620
Her mother answered cryptically.

03:52:01.680 --> 03:52:04.139
They crossed the sand pit to the tower.

03:52:04.200 --> 03:52:07.020
The 6 sand wing guards jumped aside with

03:52:07.020 --> 03:52:08.399
a relieved expression when they saw

03:52:08.399 --> 03:52:08.940
smolder.

03:52:09.000 --> 03:52:11.579
Sonny heard peril take a deep breath.

03:52:11.639 --> 03:52:13.739
Time for her to face Scarlet.

03:52:13.860 --> 03:52:15.000
She realized.

03:52:15.059 --> 03:52:17.819
And us too, since we'll have to get past

03:52:17.819 --> 03:52:19.379
her to see the night wing.

03:52:19.440 --> 03:52:22.260
They could hear Scarlet roaring as soon

03:52:22.260 --> 03:52:23.159
as they opened the door.

03:52:23.219 --> 03:52:24.899
Who's down there?

03:52:24.959 --> 03:52:27.719
Smolder, I hear your stupid keys

03:52:27.719 --> 03:52:28.500
clanking.

03:52:28.559 --> 03:52:29.219
If you.

03:52:29.879 --> 03:52:31.920
She cut off abruptly, and Sonny looked

03:52:31.920 --> 03:52:32.100
up.

03:52:32.159 --> 03:52:34.860
She could see yellow eyes glinting

03:52:34.860 --> 03:52:36.840
through the smoke, as Scarlet peered down

03:52:36.840 --> 03:52:37.200
at them.

03:52:37.260 --> 03:52:40.260
The silence that followed as they wound

03:52:40.260 --> 03:52:42.600
their way up the ramp was more unsettling

03:52:42.600 --> 03:52:43.260
than the shouting.

03:52:43.319 --> 03:52:45.180
What was Scarlet thinking?

03:52:45.239 --> 03:52:47.340
What would she do when they reached her?

03:52:47.399 --> 03:52:51.239
The former queen of the sky wings sat

03:52:51.239 --> 03:52:53.819
with her tail curled around her talons

03:52:53.819 --> 03:52:54.840
glaring fiercely at them.

03:52:54.899 --> 03:52:58.079
Smolder stopped in front of her, but she

03:52:58.079 --> 03:53:00.479
ignored him, fixing her malevolent gaze

03:53:00.479 --> 03:53:01.680
on peril instead.

03:53:01.739 --> 03:53:04.799
What are you doing?

03:53:04.860 --> 03:53:06.239
She growled.

03:53:06.299 --> 03:53:08.159
Rescuing you?

03:53:08.219 --> 03:53:10.979
Pearl muttered, staying behind, Sonny.

03:53:11.100 --> 03:53:13.860
This is an odd way to go about it.

03:53:13.979 --> 03:53:17.100
Scarlet swept your tail in an arc

03:53:17.100 --> 03:53:19.319
knocking glass shards over the edge to

03:53:19.319 --> 03:53:21.000
shatter on the floor far below.

03:53:21.059 --> 03:53:23.520
Such an interesting group of friends

03:53:23.520 --> 03:53:24.840
you've brought with you.

03:53:24.899 --> 03:53:27.420
Where is the night wing?

03:53:27.479 --> 03:53:28.799
Thorn demanded.

03:53:28.860 --> 03:53:32.280
Smolder pointed wordlessly at the shadowy

03:53:32.280 --> 03:53:33.420
lumps behind Scarlet.

03:53:33.479 --> 03:53:35.340
Don't go near her.

03:53:35.399 --> 03:53:38.159
Sonny warned her mother, as Thorn started

03:53:38.159 --> 03:53:38.520
forward.

03:53:38.579 --> 03:53:40.139
She's really dangerous.

03:53:40.260 --> 03:53:41.879
That's true.

03:53:41.940 --> 03:53:43.860
Scarlet hissed.

03:53:43.920 --> 03:53:46.559
Thorn paused, then faced the prisoner.

03:53:46.620 --> 03:53:49.319
Show me the Nightwing's face.

03:53:49.379 --> 03:53:51.479
Looking for someone?

03:53:51.600 --> 03:53:53.940
Scarlett said, sounding amused.

03:53:54.000 --> 03:53:56.399
Now, why would I help you?

03:53:56.459 --> 03:54:00.659
Because I'm telling you to, Peril

03:54:00.659 --> 03:54:01.680
interjected abruptly.

03:54:01.739 --> 03:54:04.020
Do it if you want me to get you out of

03:54:04.020 --> 03:54:04.200
here.

03:54:04.319 --> 03:54:07.739
Queen Scarlet rose up on her back legs

03:54:07.739 --> 03:54:09.719
spreading her wings so she looked

03:54:09.719 --> 03:54:11.639
majestically powerful despite her

03:54:11.639 --> 03:54:12.239
disfigurement.

03:54:12.299 --> 03:54:15.600
It sounds to me, like you've forgotten

03:54:15.600 --> 03:54:16.559
who your queen is.

03:54:16.620 --> 03:54:18.840
She snarled at peril.

03:54:18.899 --> 03:54:22.319
It sounds to me like you forgot who has

03:54:22.319 --> 03:54:23.940
the scale melting talons here.

03:54:24.059 --> 03:54:25.860
Pearl snapped back.

03:54:25.979 --> 03:54:29.340
Scarlet hissed, and more smoke poured

03:54:29.340 --> 03:54:30.959
from her snout to envelop her horns.

03:54:31.020 --> 03:54:32.819
Don't you threaten me.

03:54:32.879 --> 03:54:34.920
I don't take orders from anyone.

03:54:34.979 --> 03:54:39.180
Then you can rot here, Pearl said hotly

03:54:39.180 --> 03:54:40.979
turning around so fast.

03:54:41.040 --> 03:54:42.780
The Sonny had to jump out of the way of

03:54:42.780 --> 03:54:43.079
her tail.

03:54:43.200 --> 03:54:46.799
She'd only taken 3 steps when Scarlet

03:54:46.799 --> 03:54:47.940
cried, wait.

03:54:48.059 --> 03:54:49.440
Wait.

03:54:49.500 --> 03:54:52.860
Peril stopped, breathing deeply. but

03:54:52.860 --> 03:54:53.399
didn't turn around.

03:54:53.459 --> 03:54:55.739
The night wing.

03:54:55.799 --> 03:54:58.440
Thorn said, with quiet authority

03:54:58.440 --> 03:54:59.219
pointing.

03:54:59.280 --> 03:55:02.700
Scarlet growled deep in her throat, then

03:55:02.700 --> 03:55:04.680
picked up something from behind her, and

03:55:04.680 --> 03:55:06.059
threw it as hard as she could at

03:55:06.059 --> 03:55:06.540
smolder.

03:55:06.600 --> 03:55:09.719
He caught it, and then tossed it to Thorn

03:55:09.719 --> 03:55:10.319
with a yelp.

03:55:10.440 --> 03:55:12.479
It was the night wing's head.

03:55:12.540 --> 03:55:15.239
Thorn looked down at the dragon head in

03:55:15.239 --> 03:55:17.280
her talons with an expression of pure

03:55:17.280 --> 03:55:19.739
horror, but it quickly melted into

03:55:19.739 --> 03:55:19.979
relief.

03:55:20.040 --> 03:55:22.860
She gently set the head down on the stone

03:55:22.860 --> 03:55:23.819
and stepped back.

03:55:23.879 --> 03:55:26.399
Is, is everything?

03:55:26.459 --> 03:55:27.719
Sonny asked.

03:55:27.780 --> 03:55:30.360
A stranger, Thorn said.

03:55:30.420 --> 03:55:31.860
Nothing to worry about.

03:55:31.920 --> 03:55:34.020
She rubbed her forearms.

03:55:34.079 --> 03:55:35.879
Let's go back to the sunshine.

03:55:36.000 --> 03:55:38.700
Peril.

03:55:38.760 --> 03:55:41.340
Scarlet said, a low rumble in her

03:55:41.340 --> 03:55:41.700
throat.

03:55:41.760 --> 03:55:43.620
Where are you going?

03:55:43.680 --> 03:55:47.340
I'll be back to let you out once Sonny is

03:55:47.340 --> 03:55:50.159
far away from here, peril said, looking

03:55:50.159 --> 03:55:51.659
over her shoulder at the imprisoned

03:55:51.659 --> 03:55:52.079
queen.

03:55:52.139 --> 03:55:54.180
Don't try to argue with me.

03:55:54.299 --> 03:55:56.399
I know what you want to do to her, and I

03:55:56.399 --> 03:55:57.180
won't let you.

03:55:57.239 --> 03:56:00.360
She set off down the ramp as fast as she

03:56:00.360 --> 03:56:02.639
could, and Sonny followed, feeling

03:56:02.639 --> 03:56:04.860
grateful and anxious in equal parts.

03:56:04.920 --> 03:56:08.459
I know what you want, and it's not going

03:56:08.459 --> 03:56:08.879
to work.

03:56:08.940 --> 03:56:10.920
Scarlett shouted after her.

03:56:10.979 --> 03:56:13.500
He's never going to love you.

03:56:13.559 --> 03:56:15.600
You can keep trying to save his friends

03:56:15.600 --> 03:56:18.239
but no one will ever love you except me.

03:56:18.299 --> 03:56:20.700
I'm the only one who accepts you the way

03:56:20.700 --> 03:56:21.000
you are.

03:56:21.059 --> 03:56:23.579
You'll always be a monster to everyone

03:56:23.579 --> 03:56:23.879
else.

03:56:23.940 --> 03:56:27.899
Peril threw the door open, leaving scorch

03:56:27.899 --> 03:56:30.000
marks on the wood, and dashed out of the

03:56:30.000 --> 03:56:30.360
tower.

03:56:30.420 --> 03:56:33.659
Sonny caught up to her outside, where the

03:56:33.659 --> 03:56:35.639
sky wing was curled up small in the

03:56:35.639 --> 03:56:37.620
middle of the sand, rubbing her claws

03:56:37.620 --> 03:56:37.920
together.

03:56:37.979 --> 03:56:41.879
She's wrong, Sonny said to peril's back.

03:56:41.940 --> 03:56:43.500
She hesitated.

03:56:43.559 --> 03:56:46.079
Glancing back at Smolder and Thorn as

03:56:46.079 --> 03:56:47.459
Smolder relocked the tower.

03:56:47.459 --> 03:56:49.920
Don't let her make you hate yourself.

03:56:49.979 --> 03:56:52.799
I can't promise you anything about clay

03:56:52.799 --> 03:56:56.520
but I think, I mean, if I know him at all

03:56:56.520 --> 03:56:59.040
I can tell you the way to his heart is by

03:56:59.040 --> 03:56:59.760
helping his friends.

03:56:59.879 --> 03:57:03.719
Although, I cannot picture him with you.

03:57:03.780 --> 03:57:07.440
The kindest dragon empyrea, and someone

03:57:07.440 --> 03:57:08.879
who's killed, who knows how many

03:57:08.879 --> 03:57:09.479
dragons?

03:57:09.540 --> 03:57:11.399
How could you ever deserve him?

03:57:11.459 --> 03:57:14.340
She didn't say any of that out loud

03:57:14.340 --> 03:57:14.579
though?

03:57:14.639 --> 03:57:17.399
If she was being perfectly honest, she'd

03:57:17.399 --> 03:57:18.899
have to admit to herself that she'd never

03:57:18.899 --> 03:57:20.579
think anyone was worthy of clay.

03:57:20.700 --> 03:57:23.579
Peril sniffed and then nodded.

03:57:23.639 --> 03:57:27.540
And I don't think you're a monster, Sonny

03:57:27.540 --> 03:57:30.899
added, thinking, you've been monstrous

03:57:30.899 --> 03:57:32.520
but maybe you can change.

03:57:32.579 --> 03:57:34.739
I have to believe you can change.

03:57:34.799 --> 03:57:37.620
You're a dragon, like anyone else.

03:57:37.680 --> 03:57:39.959
You can remake yourself however you want

03:57:39.959 --> 03:57:40.200
to.

03:57:40.319 --> 03:57:42.299
Peril snorted.

03:57:42.360 --> 03:57:43.920
Easy for you to say.

03:57:43.979 --> 03:57:47.040
Not really, Sonny thought.

03:57:47.100 --> 03:57:50.040
My friends think they know who I am too

03:57:50.040 --> 03:57:52.500
no matter how much I try to show them.

03:57:52.559 --> 03:57:53.399
I' more than that.

03:57:53.459 --> 03:57:56.700
You don't have to set scarlet free.

03:57:56.760 --> 03:57:58.260
Sonny reminded her.

03:57:58.319 --> 03:58:00.000
You could come with me instead.

03:58:00.059 --> 03:58:03.659
Pearl tossed her head, folding her wings

03:58:03.659 --> 03:58:03.959
back.

03:58:04.020 --> 03:58:05.940
Don't worry about me.

03:58:06.000 --> 03:58:07.079
I'm fine.

03:58:07.200 --> 03:58:10.139
Which means I don't want any more

03:58:10.139 --> 03:58:12.540
sympathy right now, Sonny thought.

03:58:12.600 --> 03:58:15.540
She turned back toward the tower as her

03:58:15.540 --> 03:58:16.860
mother and smolder approached.

03:58:16.979 --> 03:58:19.620
I think we have something that belongs to

03:58:19.620 --> 03:58:19.799
you.

03:58:19.920 --> 03:58:22.020
Smolder was saying to Thorn.

03:58:22.079 --> 03:58:23.579
If you don't mind waiting.

03:58:23.639 --> 03:58:25.079
I'll go check Burns library.

03:58:25.139 --> 03:58:28.260
Thorn gave him a suspicious look, and he

03:58:28.260 --> 03:58:28.680
chuckled.

03:58:28.739 --> 03:58:31.860
Or you can come along, but it's rather a

03:58:31.860 --> 03:58:32.459
mess is all.

03:58:32.579 --> 03:58:34.379
He glanced at peril.

03:58:34.440 --> 03:58:36.299
Lots of papers everywhere.

03:58:36.360 --> 03:58:38.760
I'll wait here.

03:58:38.819 --> 03:58:40.559
Parel said sadly.

03:58:40.680 --> 03:58:43.260
She drew her tail in close to herself

03:58:43.260 --> 03:58:45.719
leaving a moon shaped swath in the sand.

03:58:45.780 --> 03:58:49.379
Lead on, Thorn said to Smolder.

03:58:49.440 --> 03:58:51.899
Sonny joined them, and they headed into

03:58:51.899 --> 03:58:53.879
yet another twisting set of corridors.

03:58:53.940 --> 03:58:56.280
These ones lined with flickering diamond

03:58:56.280 --> 03:58:58.440
shaped mirrors that caught the sunlight

03:58:58.440 --> 03:59:00.299
from small holes in the roof and walls.

03:59:00.360 --> 03:59:03.659
Mother, Sonny said as they walked.

03:59:03.719 --> 03:59:04.979
What's going on?

03:59:05.040 --> 03:59:07.200
I thought you hated Night Wings.

03:59:07.260 --> 03:59:08.879
Why did you think you might care about

03:59:08.879 --> 03:59:09.299
that one?

03:59:09.360 --> 03:59:13.139
Thorn stopped and waited until Smolder

03:59:13.139 --> 03:59:15.120
was far ahead, picking through his keys

03:59:15.120 --> 03:59:17.639
with a bright, brassy jingling sound.

03:59:17.819 --> 03:59:20.159
I don't hate all night wings.

03:59:20.219 --> 03:59:21.959
Thorn said quietly.

03:59:22.020 --> 03:59:25.379
I mean, I'm not fond of them, and I don't

03:59:25.379 --> 03:59:27.600
trust them as a rule, but I'm looking for

03:59:27.600 --> 03:59:30.479
one in particular, an animus dragon named

03:59:30.479 --> 03:59:31.260
Stone Mover.

03:59:31.379 --> 03:59:33.780
Because he did something to my egg?

03:59:33.840 --> 03:59:35.159
Sonny guessed.

03:59:35.219 --> 03:59:36.000
Is that why?

03:59:36.059 --> 03:59:38.159
Not exactly.

03:59:38.219 --> 03:59:41.879
Well, I guess in a manner of speaking

03:59:41.879 --> 03:59:43.200
Thorn said.

03:59:43.319 --> 03:59:45.600
Glancing up at the skylights with an odd

03:59:45.600 --> 03:59:48.899
half smile, Sonny stared at her, she had

03:59:48.899 --> 03:59:50.579
a pretty good idea what that look meant.

03:59:50.639 --> 03:59:53.639
He isn't, she whispered.

03:59:53.700 --> 03:59:56.219
You wondered why you don't look like a

03:59:56.219 --> 03:59:58.440
regular sandwing, Thorn said.

03:59:58.500 --> 04:00:03.239
So, it's because Sonny's claws trembled

04:00:03.239 --> 04:00:06.000
with shock of all the theories she'd ever

04:00:06.000 --> 04:00:06.540
imagined.

04:00:06.600 --> 04:00:09.719
Yes, this one had crossed her mind, but

04:00:09.719 --> 04:00:11.700
of all the tribes she'd wondered about

04:00:11.700 --> 04:00:12.659
never this one.

04:00:12.780 --> 04:00:15.420
Never, never this one.

04:00:15.479 --> 04:00:18.360
Yes, sonny, said Thorn.

04:00:18.420 --> 04:00:20.819
Her voice falling like drops of water

04:00:20.819 --> 04:00:22.379
into the stillness between them.

04:00:22.379 --> 04:00:25.020
It's because you're half night wing.

04:00:25.079 --> 04:00:29.399
Chapter 14.

04:00:29.579 --> 04:00:33.780
But the night wings are awful, Sonny

04:00:33.780 --> 04:00:34.620
cried.

04:00:34.680 --> 04:00:35.940
I don't want to be anything like them.

04:00:36.000 --> 04:00:38.940
So don't be. her mother said.

04:00:39.059 --> 04:00:41.399
She started walking again, and Sunny

04:00:41.399 --> 04:00:42.299
hurried to keep up.

04:00:42.360 --> 04:00:44.340
No one's making you be awful.

04:00:44.459 --> 04:00:46.500
And didn't you say you're friends with

04:00:46.500 --> 04:00:46.739
one?

04:00:46.799 --> 04:00:50.340
Starflight is different, Sonny said.

04:00:50.399 --> 04:00:53.100
So was Stone Mover, said Thorn.

04:00:53.159 --> 04:00:54.899
At least, I thought so.

04:00:54.959 --> 04:00:56.639
It's been a long time.

04:00:56.700 --> 04:01:00.540
Sunny's scales seemed suddenly too large

04:01:00.540 --> 04:01:01.860
or maybe too small.

04:01:01.920 --> 04:01:04.620
Everything felt wrong, as if she was

04:01:04.620 --> 04:01:05.819
wearing someone else's wings.

04:01:05.940 --> 04:01:09.959
Half night wing by all the moons.

04:01:10.020 --> 04:01:11.879
Please tell me about him.

04:01:11.940 --> 04:01:13.379
I want to know everything.

04:01:13.440 --> 04:01:15.059
I mean, I think I do.

04:01:15.120 --> 04:01:15.959
Do I?

04:01:16.020 --> 04:01:18.479
How did you fall in love with a night

04:01:18.479 --> 04:01:19.860
wing of all the tribes?

04:01:19.920 --> 04:01:22.799
Thorn folded her wings back and ducked

04:01:22.799 --> 04:01:23.700
under a low archway.

04:01:23.760 --> 04:01:27.479
Eight years ago, I met a dragon, out in

04:01:27.479 --> 04:01:28.860
the sands not far from here, actually.

04:01:28.920 --> 04:01:31.739
His scales were like the desert sky at

04:01:31.739 --> 04:01:34.379
night, and he was always nervous in a

04:01:34.379 --> 04:01:36.899
sweet, worried way, like no other dragon

04:01:36.899 --> 04:01:37.559
I'd ever met.

04:01:37.620 --> 04:01:40.979
Remember, I grew up in the Scorpion Den.

04:01:41.040 --> 04:01:43.440
There you have to be tough and cutthroat

04:01:43.440 --> 04:01:45.180
all the time, or you're dead.

04:01:45.239 --> 04:01:48.600
I liked the way Stone Mover fidgeted, and

04:01:48.600 --> 04:01:49.979
the questions he was always asking.

04:01:50.040 --> 04:01:52.620
And I liked that he wasn't pretending to

04:01:52.620 --> 04:01:54.479
be scarier and meaner than he really

04:01:54.479 --> 04:01:55.260
was.

04:01:55.319 --> 04:01:58.079
It was just himself, and he was very

04:01:58.079 --> 04:01:58.440
smart.

04:01:58.500 --> 04:02:02.159
He sounds a lot like Starflight, Sonny

04:02:02.159 --> 04:02:02.399
said.

04:02:02.459 --> 04:02:04.500
She wondered if that meant anything.

04:02:04.559 --> 04:02:07.379
If she was like her mother, did that mean

04:02:07.379 --> 04:02:09.059
she would end up in love with a dragon

04:02:09.059 --> 04:02:10.200
who was like her father?

04:02:10.260 --> 04:02:11.879
Was that her type?

04:02:12.000 --> 04:02:13.979
Was that her destiny?

04:02:14.040 --> 04:02:16.440
Her and Starflight together?

04:02:16.500 --> 04:02:19.440
She had many thoughts about that, but no

04:02:19.440 --> 04:02:20.579
idea how to sort them out.

04:02:20.639 --> 04:02:25.079
He gave me this, Thorn said, touching the

04:02:25.079 --> 04:02:26.159
moonstone around her neck.

04:02:26.280 --> 04:02:29.280
I asked him why he was here, and he said

04:02:29.280 --> 04:02:30.600
he was trying to save his tribe.

04:02:30.659 --> 04:02:32.520
I liked that too.

04:02:32.579 --> 04:02:33.959
She went on.

04:02:34.020 --> 04:02:36.719
He really, really cared about saving his

04:02:36.719 --> 04:02:37.379
tribe.

04:02:37.440 --> 04:02:40.379
I'd never seen loyalty before because

04:02:40.379 --> 04:02:42.239
there was nothing like the outlaws back

04:02:42.239 --> 04:02:44.280
then, not in the scorpion den.

04:02:44.340 --> 04:02:46.319
He said he was doing something essential

04:02:46.319 --> 04:02:47.760
that nobody else could do.

04:02:47.819 --> 04:02:50.819
Oh, Sonny gasped.

04:02:50.879 --> 04:02:51.959
The tunnels.

04:02:52.020 --> 04:02:53.879
He must be the animus who built the

04:02:53.879 --> 04:02:54.299
tunnels.

04:02:54.360 --> 04:02:56.700
Thorn looked at her curiously.

04:02:56.760 --> 04:02:57.959
You know about that?

04:02:58.020 --> 04:03:01.680
Wait, tunnels, as in multiple tunnels?

04:03:01.739 --> 04:03:04.319
Two of them, Sonny said.

04:03:04.379 --> 04:03:06.840
As far as I know, those are the only ones

04:03:06.840 --> 04:03:07.920
I've been through anyway.

04:03:07.979 --> 04:03:12.360
You have been around, Thorn said. with a

04:03:12.360 --> 04:03:13.739
hint of admiration in her voice.

04:03:13.799 --> 04:03:16.200
I only knew about one tunnel.

04:03:16.260 --> 04:03:19.260
He was here every day for a while, trying

04:03:19.260 --> 04:03:21.420
to pick the right spot and working of the

04:03:21.420 --> 04:03:22.379
energy to create it.

04:03:22.440 --> 04:03:24.840
So I kept coming back to bother him.

04:03:24.899 --> 04:03:27.719
And finally, I guess he fell for me too.

04:03:27.780 --> 04:03:31.020
Who wouldn't, Sonny thought.

04:03:31.079 --> 04:03:34.739
But, she said, didn't anyone care that

04:03:34.739 --> 04:03:36.180
you were from 2 different tribes?

04:03:36.239 --> 04:03:38.940
If Bern thinks it's wrong?

04:03:39.000 --> 04:03:40.979
I'm guessing she's not the only dragon

04:03:40.979 --> 04:03:41.879
who feels that way.

04:03:41.940 --> 04:03:44.819
What if it were me and Starflight?

04:03:44.879 --> 04:03:48.000
She realized she didn't really know what

04:03:48.000 --> 04:03:49.860
dragons in the outside world thought

04:03:49.860 --> 04:03:51.420
about intertribe relationships.

04:03:51.479 --> 04:03:54.780
It had never come up in any scrolls, and

04:03:54.780 --> 04:03:56.159
the guardians under the mountain had

04:03:56.159 --> 04:03:58.260
never talked about it, but they never

04:03:58.260 --> 04:04:00.180
talked about families or love at all.

04:04:00.239 --> 04:04:04.319
No one knew, except Six Claws and my

04:04:04.319 --> 04:04:06.600
friend Armadillo, Thorn admitted.

04:04:06.659 --> 04:04:09.659
Stone Mover was my secret.

04:04:09.719 --> 04:04:11.459
Of course, I didn't have a whole lot of

04:04:11.459 --> 04:04:12.360
other friends back then.

04:04:12.420 --> 04:04:16.920
If they knew now, Sonny said slowly, would

04:04:16.920 --> 04:04:18.059
you lose the outlaws?

04:04:18.180 --> 04:04:20.879
Thorn stepped in front of Sonny?

04:04:20.940 --> 04:04:22.680
and put up her wings to stop her in

04:04:22.680 --> 04:04:22.979
place.

04:04:23.040 --> 04:04:24.659
Listen to me.

04:04:24.719 --> 04:04:25.620
She said.

04:04:25.680 --> 04:04:28.139
I don't tell everyone about my past

04:04:28.139 --> 04:04:30.600
because I like my privacy, and there

04:04:30.600 --> 04:04:32.040
isn't much of that when you lead a band

04:04:32.040 --> 04:04:32.819
of outlaws.

04:04:32.879 --> 04:04:35.579
But I'm not ashamed of you, or of where

04:04:35.579 --> 04:04:36.540
you came from.

04:04:36.600 --> 04:04:38.520
If other dragons have a problem with it

04:04:38.520 --> 04:04:39.780
that's their problem.

04:04:39.840 --> 04:04:42.180
It's not against the law to be with a

04:04:42.180 --> 04:04:43.440
dragon from another tribe.

04:04:43.500 --> 04:04:46.739
It just hardly ever happens, that's all.

04:04:46.799 --> 04:04:50.399
Usually each tribe keeps to itself, which

04:04:50.399 --> 04:04:53.639
makes you rare, but not illegal, or taboo

04:04:53.639 --> 04:04:55.739
or horrifying, or anything like that.

04:04:55.799 --> 04:04:58.559
Don't ever let any dragon make you feel

04:04:58.559 --> 04:04:59.639
like you shouldn't exist.

04:04:59.700 --> 04:05:00.479
You understand?

04:05:00.600 --> 04:05:02.639
Sonny nodded.

04:05:02.700 --> 04:05:04.860
She thought Dragon should be allowed to

04:05:04.860 --> 04:05:07.079
love whoever they fell in love with, but

04:05:07.079 --> 04:05:08.459
at the same time, she couldn't help

04:05:08.459 --> 04:05:10.379
thinking, look at me though.

04:05:10.440 --> 04:05:14.639
No natural weapons, no powers, scales

04:05:14.639 --> 04:05:16.500
that mean I don't fit into any tribe.

04:05:16.559 --> 04:05:19.260
I'm kind of a walking argument for

04:05:19.260 --> 04:05:21.719
avoiding intertribe relationships, aren't

04:05:21.719 --> 04:05:21.840
I?

04:05:21.959 --> 04:05:24.540
Her mother looked as if she could read

04:05:24.540 --> 04:05:26.040
Sonny's thoughts on her face.

04:05:26.100 --> 04:05:28.860
She brushed her front talons over Sunny's

04:05:28.860 --> 04:05:30.959
head and horns and cupped her snout.

04:05:31.020 --> 04:05:33.420
Sonny, you are perfect.

04:05:33.479 --> 04:05:34.620
The way you are.

04:05:34.680 --> 04:05:37.680
So what happened to stone mover.

04:05:37.739 --> 04:05:38.700
Sonny asked.

04:05:38.760 --> 04:05:40.739
She didn't want to think about her weird

04:05:40.739 --> 04:05:42.899
looks anymore, at least for a little

04:05:42.899 --> 04:05:43.139
while.

04:05:43.200 --> 04:05:44.879
He disappeared.

04:05:44.940 --> 04:05:48.239
Thorn let go of her, and blew out a

04:05:48.239 --> 04:05:49.739
breath with hints of fire in it.

04:05:49.799 --> 04:05:52.260
I came back one day and he was gone.

04:05:52.319 --> 04:05:55.200
Morrow seer was there instead.

04:05:55.319 --> 04:05:58.260
He said it was my fault, whatever had

04:05:58.260 --> 04:06:00.479
happened to Stone Mover, and never to

04:06:00.479 --> 04:06:01.860
look for him or try to speak to him

04:06:01.860 --> 04:06:02.159
again.

04:06:02.219 --> 04:06:05.639
Pompous, worm faced, snobhead camel

04:06:05.639 --> 04:06:06.120
turd.

04:06:06.239 --> 04:06:07.799
Mother!

04:06:07.860 --> 04:06:10.079
Sonny said, nearly shocked into

04:06:10.079 --> 04:06:10.500
laughing.

04:06:10.559 --> 04:06:14.040
That's what he was, Thorn growled.

04:06:14.100 --> 04:06:15.479
Morrow seer.

04:06:15.540 --> 04:06:18.120
I dream about wringing his neck all the

04:06:18.120 --> 04:06:18.420
time.

04:06:18.479 --> 04:06:21.780
She sighed, and her claws scratched

04:06:21.780 --> 04:06:23.040
across the stone as if they were

04:06:23.040 --> 04:06:24.059
frustrated too.

04:06:24.120 --> 04:06:26.879
We didn't like him much either, Sonny

04:06:26.879 --> 04:06:27.899
admitted.

04:06:27.899 --> 04:06:28.559
So that was it?

04:06:28.680 --> 04:06:31.500
Didn't you ever see Stone Mover again?

04:06:31.559 --> 04:06:34.500
No, but of course that wasn't it.

04:06:34.620 --> 04:06:37.319
Thorn said, turning to walk on again.

04:06:37.379 --> 04:06:39.420
I looked for him everywhere.

04:06:39.479 --> 04:06:41.879
I went through the tunnel, but it led to

04:06:41.879 --> 04:06:43.920
the rainforest. isn't that odd?

04:06:43.979 --> 04:06:46.079
I thought it would lead to their hidden

04:06:46.079 --> 04:06:48.899
kingdom, but no, I searched the whole

04:06:48.899 --> 04:06:51.000
place, but there were no night wings

04:06:51.000 --> 04:06:51.299
there.

04:06:51.360 --> 04:06:54.420
Only some very sweet, rather bewildered

04:06:54.420 --> 04:06:55.139
rain wings.

04:06:55.200 --> 04:06:56.639
Very confusing.

04:06:56.700 --> 04:06:58.739
I never understood how that would save

04:06:58.739 --> 04:06:59.280
his tribe.

04:06:59.340 --> 04:07:02.700
I'll explain it to you later, Sonny

04:07:02.700 --> 04:07:02.940
said.

04:07:03.000 --> 04:07:04.260
Did he know about me?

04:07:04.319 --> 04:07:05.639
No.

04:07:05.700 --> 04:07:06.840
Thorn said.

04:07:06.899 --> 04:07:09.899
We were fighting, a little bit, when I

04:07:09.899 --> 04:07:12.360
found out I was with Egg, I planned to

04:07:12.360 --> 04:07:14.760
tell him once he apologized, but he'd

04:07:14.760 --> 04:07:17.879
gotten very strange and cold, so maybe he

04:07:17.879 --> 04:07:18.420
wasn't going to.

04:07:18.479 --> 04:07:21.899
That's what happens to animus dragons

04:07:21.899 --> 04:07:22.739
Sonny said.

04:07:22.799 --> 04:07:25.620
Whenever they use their magic, they lose

04:07:25.620 --> 04:07:27.299
a little bit of their soul or something

04:07:27.299 --> 04:07:27.719
like that.

04:07:27.780 --> 04:07:31.200
They get meaner and colder and a little

04:07:31.200 --> 04:07:31.739
more crazy.

04:07:31.799 --> 04:07:33.899
From what I've heard anyway.

04:07:34.020 --> 04:07:36.659
Thorn stopped again and stared down at

04:07:36.659 --> 04:07:38.819
her, worry filling her dark eyes.

04:07:38.879 --> 04:07:40.860
I didn't know that.

04:07:40.920 --> 04:07:42.659
That's what was happening to him?

04:07:42.719 --> 04:07:44.700
I wonder if he knew.

04:07:44.760 --> 04:07:46.379
He must have known.

04:07:46.440 --> 04:07:48.420
Why didn't he tell me?

04:07:48.479 --> 04:07:50.760
She flicked her tail thoughtfully

04:07:50.760 --> 04:07:52.379
furrowing her brow.

04:07:52.440 --> 04:07:55.260
So then, Sonny prompted her.

04:07:55.319 --> 04:07:57.780
So then I was afraid the night wings

04:07:57.780 --> 04:07:59.219
would come after your egg if they knew

04:07:59.219 --> 04:07:59.819
about it.

04:07:59.879 --> 04:08:02.159
That's why I buried it in the desert.

04:08:02.280 --> 04:08:04.799
That's why I asked Dune to help me look

04:08:04.799 --> 04:08:05.159
after it.

04:08:05.219 --> 04:08:08.159
I had no idea he was with the talons of

04:08:08.159 --> 04:08:08.459
peace.

04:08:08.520 --> 04:08:11.100
And even if I had known, I wouldn't have

04:08:11.100 --> 04:08:12.479
guessed that would make him steal my

04:08:12.479 --> 04:08:12.780
egg.

04:08:12.840 --> 04:08:13.920
Would you?

04:08:13.979 --> 04:08:18.059
Here we are, Smolder called, and they

04:08:18.059 --> 04:08:20.040
realized he'd stopped in the tunnel ahead

04:08:20.040 --> 04:08:21.659
next to a dark wooden door.

04:08:21.780 --> 04:08:24.600
He selected a delicate gold key and

04:08:24.600 --> 04:08:27.059
unlocked it, then had to shove hard to

04:08:27.059 --> 04:08:27.600
get the door open.

04:08:27.659 --> 04:08:31.020
Sonny realized why as they squeezed

04:08:31.020 --> 04:08:31.739
inside behind him.

04:08:31.799 --> 04:08:35.040
He wasn't kidding about the mess, piles

04:08:35.040 --> 04:08:36.899
of scrolls had toppled over to block the

04:08:36.899 --> 04:08:39.000
door, and there were papers and glass

04:08:39.000 --> 04:08:41.700
paper weights, and small carved onyx

04:08:41.700 --> 04:08:43.799
lizards scattered all across the small

04:08:43.799 --> 04:08:44.459
square room.

04:08:44.579 --> 04:08:47.459
If there had ever been any system of

04:08:47.459 --> 04:08:49.440
organization, there was no way to tell

04:08:49.440 --> 04:08:49.979
now.

04:08:50.040 --> 04:08:54.719
This is not Burn's favorite place, Smolder

04:08:54.719 --> 04:08:57.479
said, stepping around the piles gingerly

04:08:57.479 --> 04:08:59.700
and still knocking over several more with

04:08:59.700 --> 04:09:00.059
his tail.

04:09:00.180 --> 04:09:03.239
I can't guarantee she's ever been in here

04:09:03.239 --> 04:09:05.760
in fact, and our mother wasn't the most

04:09:05.760 --> 04:09:07.680
organized dragon in the world either.

04:09:07.739 --> 04:09:10.200
I tried once to put it all in order.

04:09:10.260 --> 04:09:13.319
As you can see, I was wildly successful.

04:09:13.440 --> 04:09:18.120
Hmm, Sonny and Thorn said, the same non

04:09:17.280 --> 04:09:18.959
committal noise at the same time.

04:09:19.020 --> 04:09:22.139
Smolder gave them an amused look.

04:09:22.200 --> 04:09:25.860
And while I was organizing, I discovered

04:09:25.860 --> 04:09:27.719
that we have a system for intercepting

04:09:27.719 --> 04:09:29.700
messages that go across the kingdom of

04:09:29.700 --> 04:09:30.059
sand.

04:09:30.180 --> 04:09:32.819
Well, Queen Oasis had a system.

04:09:32.879 --> 04:09:35.760
Again, I'm not sure Byrne knows or cares

04:09:35.760 --> 04:09:38.399
about it, but we have dragons who pose as

04:09:38.399 --> 04:09:40.680
messengers, and other dragons who are

04:09:40.680 --> 04:09:43.860
instructed to attack real messengers, and

04:09:43.860 --> 04:09:45.959
so a fair percentage of the letters sent

04:09:45.959 --> 04:09:47.940
in our realm come here instead.

04:09:48.000 --> 04:09:50.819
Presumably so that we can scan them for

04:09:50.819 --> 04:09:53.159
hints of rebellion, or assassination

04:09:53.159 --> 04:09:56.520
schemes, which, clearly, we are keeping

04:09:56.520 --> 04:09:57.780
careful track of around here.

04:09:57.840 --> 04:10:01.260
He waved his claws at the disaster strewn

04:10:01.260 --> 04:10:01.799
library.

04:10:01.860 --> 04:10:04.139
I guess that's how it seems like my

04:10:04.139 --> 04:10:05.159
mother always knew everything.

04:10:05.219 --> 04:10:08.280
I keep it going in case we need it one

04:10:08.280 --> 04:10:10.620
day, even though no one has time to

04:10:10.620 --> 04:10:11.159
review all this.

04:10:11.280 --> 04:10:14.879
In any case, I thought I saw one marked

04:10:14.879 --> 04:10:18.959
Thorn, which I carefully filed somewhere

04:10:18.959 --> 04:10:20.280
useful, I'm sure.

04:10:20.340 --> 04:10:23.520
Smolder dug his talent into a pile of

04:10:23.520 --> 04:10:26.100
scrolls, and Sonny realized with a start

04:10:26.100 --> 04:10:28.620
that there was a desk there, underneath

04:10:28.620 --> 04:10:29.819
the drifts of paper.

04:10:29.879 --> 04:10:32.219
Help me look, he suggested.

04:10:32.340 --> 04:10:35.700
Thorn and Sonny waded in and began

04:10:35.700 --> 04:10:38.219
peering at scrolls and mini scrolls, and

04:10:38.219 --> 04:10:40.500
thick papyrus notes with scrawls of black

04:10:40.500 --> 04:10:43.440
ink on them, Sonny's wings toppled over a

04:10:43.440 --> 04:10:46.379
stack of thin, scraped stone tablets that

04:10:46.379 --> 04:10:47.940
turned out to have messages carved on

04:10:47.940 --> 04:10:48.420
them as well.

04:10:48.420 --> 04:10:50.819
Are you sure about this?

04:10:50.879 --> 04:10:52.260
Thorn asked.

04:10:52.319 --> 04:10:54.420
After they'd searched for a few minutes.

04:10:54.479 --> 04:10:56.459
Maybe you remembered wrong.

04:10:56.520 --> 04:10:58.020
Or maybe it wasn't anything important.

04:10:58.079 --> 04:10:59.940
Maybe.

04:11:00.059 --> 04:11:03.299
Smolder said, lifting a bowl filled with

04:11:03.299 --> 04:11:05.219
dried leaves and peering at the papers

04:11:05.219 --> 04:11:05.639
underneath.

04:11:05.700 --> 04:11:08.760
I'm pretty sure I remember it looked

04:11:08.760 --> 04:11:09.420
important though.

04:11:09.479 --> 04:11:12.059
Sonny wished she had time to read

04:11:12.059 --> 04:11:14.340
everything in here, or a way to bring it

04:11:14.340 --> 04:11:15.659
all back to Starflight.

04:11:15.959 --> 04:11:17.520
So many scrolls.

04:11:17.579 --> 04:11:21.780
So many scraps of dragons, lives, moments

04:11:21.780 --> 04:11:24.659
and messages, caught in between scent and

04:11:24.659 --> 04:11:25.260
never received.

04:11:25.319 --> 04:11:27.600
I wonder if the world would be different

04:11:27.600 --> 04:11:29.879
if some of these letters had gotten to

04:11:29.879 --> 04:11:31.260
where they were supposed to go.

04:11:31.319 --> 04:11:34.319
Claws scrabbled on the stone in the hall

04:11:34.319 --> 04:11:36.659
outside, and smolder went to the doorway

04:11:36.659 --> 04:11:37.500
to poke his head out.

04:11:37.620 --> 04:11:39.360
What is it?

04:11:39.420 --> 04:11:42.000
He called, as 2 guards rushed by.

04:11:42.059 --> 04:11:44.579
A wing approaching from the northeast.

04:11:44.639 --> 04:11:46.920
One of them called back, might be

04:11:46.920 --> 04:11:47.219
burned.

04:11:47.340 --> 04:11:50.579
Sonny's head snapped up, and she flapped

04:11:50.579 --> 04:11:51.299
her wings at her mother.

04:11:51.360 --> 04:11:53.040
We have to get out of here.

04:11:53.100 --> 04:11:58.860
Oh, great moons, at last, Smolder said.

04:11:58.979 --> 04:12:00.780
Sorry about this, you two.

04:12:00.899 --> 04:12:02.760
Sorry about what?

04:12:02.760 --> 04:12:05.879
Sonny asked, turning toward him just as

04:12:05.879 --> 04:12:08.219
he jumped out of the room and slammed the

04:12:08.219 --> 04:12:08.700
door on them.

04:12:08.760 --> 04:12:11.760
No, Thorn roared.

04:12:11.879 --> 04:12:15.299
Sonny leaped over the scrolls and grabbed

04:12:15.299 --> 04:12:17.219
the door handle, but she could hear the

04:12:17.219 --> 04:12:18.420
key turning in the lock already.

04:12:18.479 --> 04:12:21.719
She threw herself against the wood, but

04:12:21.719 --> 04:12:23.520
it was solid and only bruised her

04:12:23.520 --> 04:12:23.760
shoulder.

04:12:23.819 --> 04:12:26.879
Smolder, don't do this.

04:12:27.000 --> 04:12:28.860
She shouted through the door.

04:12:28.920 --> 04:12:30.479
Don't give us to burn.

04:12:30.540 --> 04:12:31.200
Please.

04:12:31.319 --> 04:12:35.100
I can't let you waltz out of here, he

04:12:35.100 --> 04:12:35.399
said.

04:12:35.459 --> 04:12:37.079
His voice faint and muffled.

04:12:37.139 --> 04:12:39.360
I saw what Byrne did to my brothers.

04:12:39.420 --> 04:12:41.040
I know how to stay alive.

04:12:41.100 --> 04:12:43.260
Like I said, I'm sorry.

04:12:43.319 --> 04:12:45.600
Sonny pounded on the door.

04:12:45.659 --> 04:12:48.059
At least give us a fair chance to fight

04:12:48.059 --> 04:12:48.360
her.

04:12:48.420 --> 04:12:49.200
Smolder.

04:12:49.319 --> 04:12:52.620
But she could hear his tail slithering

04:12:52.620 --> 04:12:53.399
away into the palace.

04:12:53.459 --> 04:12:55.739
He was gone.

04:12:55.799 --> 04:12:58.319
Leaving her and her mother locked in

04:12:58.319 --> 04:13:00.840
trapped, and waiting for burn.

04:13:00.899 --> 04:13:05.159
Chapter 15.

04:13:05.579 --> 04:13:09.659
Thorn picked up an onyx lizard and hurled

04:13:09.659 --> 04:13:11.100
it across the library.

04:13:11.159 --> 04:13:14.459
Blood, red eggs, and fireballs, she

04:13:14.459 --> 04:13:15.000
shouted.

04:13:15.059 --> 04:13:17.100
I'm going to flay that dragon alive.

04:13:17.159 --> 04:13:19.860
Won't your out claws save us?

04:13:19.920 --> 04:13:22.500
Sonny asked, waiting through the papers

04:13:22.500 --> 04:13:23.159
to the desk.

04:13:23.219 --> 04:13:26.159
She ran her talons all over it, but there

04:13:26.159 --> 04:13:28.020
were no drawers, and no place for a

04:13:28.020 --> 04:13:28.920
hidden extra key.

04:13:29.040 --> 04:13:31.860
If they're smart, they'll fly for the

04:13:31.860 --> 04:13:33.360
hills the moment they hear the burn is

04:13:33.360 --> 04:13:34.860
coming. said Thorn.

04:13:34.920 --> 04:13:37.139
They'll expect me to run and meet them at

04:13:37.139 --> 04:13:38.100
the Scorpion Den.

04:13:38.159 --> 04:13:39.600
Act smart.

04:13:39.659 --> 04:13:42.059
Stay alive, stick together but don't be

04:13:42.059 --> 04:13:42.360
an idiot.

04:13:42.420 --> 04:13:43.979
Those are our basic rules.

04:13:44.040 --> 04:13:46.500
She picked up a scroll and ripped it

04:13:46.500 --> 04:13:47.459
furiously down the middle.

04:13:47.520 --> 04:13:51.600
All right, so we do that, Sonny said.

04:13:51.719 --> 04:13:53.340
We figure a way out of here.

04:13:53.399 --> 04:13:54.360
I know we can.

04:13:54.420 --> 04:13:57.420
She twisted to look around the library

04:13:57.420 --> 04:13:59.280
searching for anything she could use to

04:13:59.280 --> 04:13:59.819
pick the lock.

04:13:59.940 --> 04:14:02.700
Not that she had any idea how to do that

04:14:02.700 --> 04:14:05.100
but she'd read about someone doing it in

04:14:05.100 --> 04:14:05.819
a scroll once.

04:14:05.879 --> 04:14:09.239
There were no windows, so no way to call

04:14:09.239 --> 04:14:09.780
out for help.

04:14:09.840 --> 04:14:12.719
The light came from a small chandelier of

04:14:12.719 --> 04:14:14.399
hanging oil lamps high above them.

04:14:14.459 --> 04:14:17.639
The ceiling was tall, but made of solid

04:14:17.639 --> 04:14:18.120
stone.

04:14:18.180 --> 04:14:20.459
The door was the only way out.

04:14:20.520 --> 04:14:24.059
What about your sky wing friend, Thorn

04:14:24.059 --> 04:14:24.360
said.

04:14:24.420 --> 04:14:26.340
Might she guess what's happened and come

04:14:26.340 --> 04:14:26.879
looking for us?

04:14:26.940 --> 04:14:29.700
Sonny shifted her wings and shook her

04:14:29.700 --> 04:14:29.879
head.

04:14:29.940 --> 04:14:31.739
I doubt it.

04:14:31.799 --> 04:14:34.139
If she hears burn is coming, I'm sure

04:14:34.139 --> 04:14:35.819
she'll free Scarlet and run too.

04:14:35.879 --> 04:14:38.520
She stepped back and stared at the door.

04:14:38.579 --> 04:14:40.500
The wooden door.

04:14:40.559 --> 04:14:43.739
But if she could burn down this door, we

04:14:43.739 --> 04:14:44.940
should be able to do the same thing

04:14:44.940 --> 04:14:45.479
right?

04:14:45.540 --> 04:14:47.280
Wait.

04:14:47.340 --> 04:14:49.860
Thorn cried, as Sonny drew in a breath.

04:14:49.920 --> 04:14:52.139
She spread her claws at the mess around

04:14:52.139 --> 04:14:52.440
them.

04:14:52.500 --> 04:14:53.879
It's not safe.

04:14:54.000 --> 04:14:56.459
If you set the door on fire, it could

04:14:56.459 --> 04:14:58.680
spread to the papers in here, the whole

04:14:58.680 --> 04:15:00.420
room could be in flames in a heartbeat

04:15:00.420 --> 04:15:02.520
and we'd burn to death before we made it

04:15:02.520 --> 04:15:02.700
out.

04:15:02.760 --> 04:15:05.579
That was a horribly good point.

04:15:05.639 --> 04:15:08.520
Sonny guessed that that had occurred to

04:15:08.520 --> 04:15:09.239
smolder as well.

04:15:09.299 --> 04:15:11.579
He was more cunning than he looked.

04:15:11.639 --> 04:15:14.040
Perhaps as cunning as blister.

04:15:14.100 --> 04:15:16.200
He'd also cleverly found a way to

04:15:16.200 --> 04:15:17.340
separate them from peril.

04:15:17.399 --> 04:15:20.100
Well, Sonny said.

04:15:20.159 --> 04:15:22.799
I suspect I'd rather burn to death than

04:15:22.799 --> 04:15:25.799
end up stuffed in burns collection, but I

04:15:25.799 --> 04:15:26.639
think I can do it carefully.

04:15:26.700 --> 04:15:29.399
I'm pretty good at aiming small flames.

04:15:29.459 --> 04:15:31.079
Let me try, all right?

04:15:31.139 --> 04:15:34.139
Thorn hesitated, then nodded.

04:15:34.200 --> 04:15:35.579
Sonny was pleased.

04:15:35.639 --> 04:15:37.979
She was pretty sure her friends wouldn't

04:15:37.979 --> 04:15:39.299
have trusted her to do anything this

04:15:39.299 --> 04:15:39.780
risky.

04:15:39.840 --> 04:15:43.020
She swept papers away from the door with

04:15:43.020 --> 04:15:45.299
her tail until it was surrounded by a

04:15:45.299 --> 04:15:47.219
half circle of clear stone floor.

04:15:47.280 --> 04:15:50.219
Then she leaned forward, opened her mouth

04:15:50.219 --> 04:15:53.459
and hissed, letting fire build up in the

04:15:53.459 --> 04:15:54.059
back of her throat.

04:15:54.120 --> 04:15:57.659
It felt fierce and hot, like she'd

04:15:57.659 --> 04:16:00.059
swallowed the sun, and she never liked

04:16:00.059 --> 04:16:00.840
using it for long.

04:16:00.899 --> 04:16:02.879
Aiming carefully.

04:16:02.940 --> 04:16:05.700
She breathed a small jet of flame in an

04:16:05.700 --> 04:16:06.659
arc around the lock.

04:16:06.719 --> 04:16:09.780
The thick wood turned black where the

04:16:09.780 --> 04:16:12.360
fire touched it, and smoke curled from

04:16:12.360 --> 04:16:13.319
the gash left behind.

04:16:13.379 --> 04:16:15.600
Nothing burst into flames.

04:16:15.659 --> 04:16:16.799
Not yet, anyway.

04:16:16.860 --> 04:16:20.639
Sunny did the same thing again, trying to

04:16:20.639 --> 04:16:23.760
trace the same line over and over, 4 more

04:16:23.760 --> 04:16:26.159
times, until she saw a glimmer of light

04:16:26.159 --> 04:16:27.000
on the other side.

04:16:27.120 --> 04:16:29.819
She jammed her claws into the blackened

04:16:29.819 --> 04:16:32.579
wood and twisted them around, digging and

04:16:32.579 --> 04:16:35.040
slashing, until the whole lock came loose

04:16:35.040 --> 04:16:36.420
and thumped into her talons.

04:16:36.479 --> 04:16:40.559
I did it, she whispered to her mother, as

04:16:40.559 --> 04:16:42.059
the door swung a few inches open.

04:16:42.120 --> 04:16:45.600
Sonny turned and found her mother holding

04:16:45.600 --> 04:16:47.940
a folded square of thick papyrus paper

04:16:47.940 --> 04:16:51.299
with the word thorn, scrawled across the

04:16:51.299 --> 04:16:52.260
front in black ink.

04:16:52.319 --> 04:16:56.100
There is a letter for me, said Thorn

04:16:56.100 --> 04:16:56.760
curiously.

04:16:56.819 --> 04:16:58.979
He wasn't lying about that part.

04:16:59.040 --> 04:17:00.239
How odd.

04:17:00.360 --> 04:17:02.760
She flipped it over and opened it.

04:17:02.819 --> 04:17:07.500
Mother, we really have to go, Sonny said

04:17:07.500 --> 04:17:09.840
but her voice trailed off as she saw the

04:17:09.840 --> 04:17:11.100
expression on her mother's face.

04:17:11.159 --> 04:17:13.020
Mother?

04:17:13.079 --> 04:17:13.920
Thorn?

04:17:13.979 --> 04:17:18.059
It's from him, Thorn said, glancing up at

04:17:18.059 --> 04:17:18.479
Sonny.

04:17:18.540 --> 04:17:19.979
From your father.

04:17:20.040 --> 04:17:23.399
Listen, dearest Thorn.

04:17:23.459 --> 04:17:24.959
I can't keep doing this.

04:17:25.020 --> 04:17:27.600
I can't use my powers for the night wings

04:17:27.600 --> 04:17:29.579
any longer, or I'll lose myself

04:17:29.579 --> 04:17:30.120
completely.

04:17:30.239 --> 04:17:33.959
So I'm running away, and I'd like you to

04:17:33.959 --> 04:17:34.440
come too.

04:17:34.500 --> 04:17:36.780
Meet me at Jade Mountain.

04:17:36.840 --> 04:17:38.879
I'll wait for you as long as I have to.

04:17:38.940 --> 04:17:40.440
I love you.

04:17:40.500 --> 04:17:42.239
Stone mover.

04:17:42.299 --> 04:17:44.280
Her voice trailed off.

04:17:44.340 --> 04:17:47.579
Jade Mountain, Sonny cried.

04:17:47.639 --> 04:17:49.680
There's supposed to be a dragon who lives

04:17:49.680 --> 04:17:49.979
there.

04:17:50.040 --> 04:17:52.020
Maybe it's Stone Mover.

04:17:52.079 --> 04:17:54.479
Oh, maybe he's still waiting for you

04:17:54.479 --> 04:17:55.860
after all these years.

04:17:55.920 --> 04:17:57.360
Isn't that romantic?

04:17:57.420 --> 04:18:01.200
That frog faced blob of camel spit.

04:18:01.319 --> 04:18:04.079
Thorn shouted abruptly, making Sonny

04:18:04.079 --> 04:18:04.379
jump.

04:18:04.440 --> 04:18:06.360
She crumpled the paper in her front

04:18:06.360 --> 04:18:08.760
talons, threw it to the ground, and

04:18:08.760 --> 04:18:11.219
smashed it with one of her feet, all

04:18:11.219 --> 04:18:11.700
these years.

04:18:11.760 --> 04:18:12.780
He's alive.

04:18:12.840 --> 04:18:14.159
He's not a prisoner.

04:18:14.219 --> 04:18:16.500
And he's known exactly where I was this

04:18:16.500 --> 04:18:18.959
whole time, but he never once came to

04:18:18.959 --> 04:18:21.000
look for me or tried to contact me.

04:18:21.120 --> 04:18:24.120
Well, Sonny faltered.

04:18:24.180 --> 04:18:26.459
Maybe he thought you got his letter, but

04:18:26.459 --> 04:18:27.600
didn't want to be with him.

04:18:27.659 --> 04:18:31.920
So send me another letter, Thorn cried.

04:18:32.040 --> 04:18:33.719
Try a little harder.

04:18:33.780 --> 04:18:35.340
Don't be at your boa head.

04:18:35.399 --> 04:18:38.399
She stomped past Sonny and into the hall

04:18:38.399 --> 04:18:39.899
checking in both directions.

04:18:39.959 --> 04:18:41.879
Come on, let's run for it.

04:18:41.940 --> 04:18:43.379
I saw a courtyard this way.

04:18:43.500 --> 04:18:46.500
They bolted down the long stone corridor

04:18:46.500 --> 04:18:49.020
and swerved to the right at the end.

04:18:49.079 --> 04:18:50.940
Sunny could see a patch of blue sky up

04:18:50.940 --> 04:18:53.819
ahead beyond a wall of dark red columns.

04:18:53.879 --> 04:18:56.340
She started to unfold her wings as she

04:18:56.340 --> 04:18:56.700
ran.

04:18:56.760 --> 04:18:58.620
The prisoners.

04:18:58.680 --> 04:19:00.239
A voice shouted behind her.

04:19:00.299 --> 04:19:02.159
Prisoners escaping.

04:19:02.219 --> 04:19:04.379
Sonny's heart plunged.

04:19:04.440 --> 04:19:07.079
Uh-oh, Thorn muttered.

04:19:07.139 --> 04:19:09.180
They skidded up to the courtyard and

04:19:09.180 --> 04:19:11.459
found several sandwing soldiers milling

04:19:11.459 --> 04:19:13.799
about there, preparing their weapons as

04:19:13.799 --> 04:19:15.899
if they were getting ready for battle.

04:19:15.959 --> 04:19:18.000
The soldiers all turned and stared at

04:19:18.000 --> 04:19:18.239
them.

04:19:18.299 --> 04:19:20.100
Go!

04:19:20.159 --> 04:19:22.440
Thorn shouted, flaring her wings.

04:19:22.440 --> 04:19:25.200
Startled, Sunny hurtled into the sky.

04:19:25.260 --> 04:19:28.319
One of the soldiers roared and leaped

04:19:28.319 --> 04:19:28.680
after her.

04:19:28.739 --> 04:19:31.620
She felt the wind of his talons slashing

04:19:31.620 --> 04:19:32.639
just short of her tail.

04:19:32.700 --> 04:19:35.459
She twisted away and looked back in time

04:19:35.459 --> 04:19:37.559
to see her mother blast the soldier in

04:19:37.559 --> 04:19:39.420
the face with a burst of flames.

04:19:39.479 --> 04:19:42.780
He shrieked and plummeted to the ground.

04:19:42.840 --> 04:19:45.719
The other soldiers were slower to react

04:19:45.719 --> 04:19:48.840
and faster to catch on fire, when Thorn

04:19:48.840 --> 04:19:50.459
blasted the rest of them as well.

04:19:50.520 --> 04:19:53.520
She soared up out of the shrieking and

04:19:53.520 --> 04:19:56.040
mayhem and smoke, and circled Sonny.

04:19:56.100 --> 04:19:57.540
What are you waiting for?

04:19:57.659 --> 04:19:58.620
She called.

04:19:58.680 --> 04:20:01.079
Thorn banked around and headed for the

04:20:01.079 --> 04:20:01.979
main courtyard.

04:20:02.040 --> 04:20:03.719
Sonny followed close behind her.

04:20:03.780 --> 04:20:07.440
I hope they'll be all right, Sonny said

04:20:07.440 --> 04:20:09.120
glancing back at the flames.

04:20:09.180 --> 04:20:12.540
I hope we'll be all right, Thorn said.

04:20:12.600 --> 04:20:13.739
Oh, no.

04:20:13.799 --> 04:20:15.540
Moon liquors.

04:20:15.600 --> 04:20:17.760
Six claws, you idiot.

04:20:17.819 --> 04:20:21.299
She swerved suddenly sideways, and Sonny

04:20:21.299 --> 04:20:23.639
saw what she was aiming for, a cluster of

04:20:23.639 --> 04:20:25.559
battling sand wings on the stones below

04:20:25.559 --> 04:20:28.680
with 6 Claws and Kibley in the center of

04:20:28.680 --> 04:20:28.920
it.

04:20:28.979 --> 04:20:31.680
She heard 6 claws roar.

04:20:31.739 --> 04:20:33.059
Where is Thorn?

04:20:33.180 --> 04:20:35.700
And then Thorn snatched a loose brick

04:20:35.700 --> 04:20:37.860
from the nearest wall and lobbed it past

04:20:37.860 --> 04:20:40.200
his head, clocking the dragon behind him

04:20:40.200 --> 04:20:40.860
in the snout.

04:20:40.920 --> 04:20:44.040
I'm right here, snails for brains.

04:20:44.100 --> 04:20:45.000
She bellowed.

04:20:45.059 --> 04:20:46.200
Let's go.

04:20:46.319 --> 04:20:50.159
Without a moment's hesitation, Six Claws

04:20:50.159 --> 04:20:52.620
and Kibli and 20 other dragons leaped

04:20:52.620 --> 04:20:55.079
aloft, kicking off their opponents, and

04:20:55.079 --> 04:20:57.120
swinging their deadly tails wildly behind

04:20:57.120 --> 04:20:57.420
them.

04:20:57.479 --> 04:21:01.559
Where the others, Thorn called to 6 claws

04:21:01.559 --> 04:21:04.079
as they all veered south, flying as fast

04:21:04.079 --> 04:21:04.559
as they could.

04:21:04.620 --> 04:21:06.479
Fled already.

04:21:06.540 --> 04:21:09.540
Six claws said tersely, cowards.

04:21:09.600 --> 04:21:13.139
Following orders, Thorn reminded him, as

04:21:13.139 --> 04:21:15.719
you should have done, we weren't leaving

04:21:15.719 --> 04:21:17.760
without you, he growled.

04:21:17.819 --> 04:21:20.399
Yeah, Kibley piped up.

04:21:20.459 --> 04:21:22.559
I didn't trust that smolder dragon.

04:21:22.620 --> 04:21:23.700
I knew there'd be trouble.

04:21:23.760 --> 04:21:24.780
Didn't I say so?

04:21:24.840 --> 04:21:26.459
Can't trust a royal.

04:21:26.520 --> 04:21:27.600
That's what I always say.

04:21:27.659 --> 04:21:30.840
Because you've met so many royal dragons

04:21:30.840 --> 04:21:31.739
in your life, have you?

04:21:31.799 --> 04:21:33.420
Six claws demanded.

04:21:33.479 --> 04:21:36.360
Thorn shook her head, but didn't argue

04:21:36.360 --> 04:21:38.100
saving their breath for flying.

04:21:38.159 --> 04:21:41.819
Sunny risked a glance back, but nobody

04:21:41.819 --> 04:21:42.540
was chasing them yet.

04:21:42.600 --> 04:21:44.940
She guessed the stronghold was

04:21:44.940 --> 04:21:47.879
disorganized chaos right now, with no one

04:21:47.879 --> 04:21:49.319
sure whether they were still in a

04:21:49.319 --> 04:21:52.020
surrendered stalemate, whether peril was

04:21:52.020 --> 04:21:53.639
still lurking around to kill them all

04:21:53.639 --> 04:21:56.579
whether it was really burn on her way, or

04:21:56.579 --> 04:21:58.079
whether Smolder was still in charge.

04:21:58.139 --> 04:22:01.500
She could see the wing of dragons in the

04:22:01.500 --> 04:22:04.500
distance, approaching the stronghold, too

04:22:04.500 --> 04:22:06.959
close, only minutes away from finding out

04:22:06.959 --> 04:22:08.879
what had happened, and she was pretty

04:22:08.879 --> 04:22:11.340
sure the hulking shape in the lead was

04:22:11.340 --> 04:22:12.540
truly burn.

04:22:12.600 --> 04:22:16.500
Her eyes scanned the horizon, had peril

04:22:16.500 --> 04:22:17.159
made it out safely?

04:22:17.280 --> 04:22:20.700
Or would peril always be safe, because no

04:22:20.700 --> 04:22:22.440
one could get near her with talons like

04:22:22.440 --> 04:22:22.799
hers.

04:22:22.920 --> 04:22:26.520
She spotted 2 small shapes winging away

04:22:26.520 --> 04:22:29.219
to the north, glinting orange and gold in

04:22:29.219 --> 04:22:29.819
the sunlight.

04:22:29.879 --> 04:22:33.360
Peril and Queen Scarlet, now free.

04:22:33.420 --> 04:22:35.340
Sonny shuddered.

04:22:35.340 --> 04:22:37.680
If Queen Scarlet really did know where

04:22:37.680 --> 04:22:40.139
the dragonets were, how long did they

04:22:40.139 --> 04:22:41.340
have before she came for them?

04:22:41.399 --> 04:22:44.459
What kind of revenge had she planned?

04:22:44.520 --> 04:22:46.559
All those nights in the horrible tower?

04:22:46.680 --> 04:22:49.920
A feeling of dread climbed into her chest

04:22:49.920 --> 04:22:51.059
and squeezed.

04:22:51.120 --> 04:22:52.979
For a moment, she couldn't breathe.

04:22:53.040 --> 04:22:58.680
Clay, tsunami, glory, and poor wounded

04:22:58.680 --> 04:22:59.280
Starflight.

04:22:59.399 --> 04:23:03.299
Mother, she called, beating her wings to

04:23:03.299 --> 04:23:04.139
catch up to Thorn.

04:23:04.200 --> 04:23:06.959
Thorn grinned toothily at her.

04:23:07.020 --> 04:23:09.120
I've been called lots of things in my

04:23:09.120 --> 04:23:11.579
life, but that's the strangest and the

04:23:11.579 --> 04:23:12.479
best at the same time.

04:23:12.540 --> 04:23:15.719
Sonny brushed her mother's wingtip with

04:23:15.719 --> 04:23:15.959
her own.

04:23:16.020 --> 04:23:18.959
I have to return to my friends, she

04:23:18.959 --> 04:23:19.260
said.

04:23:19.319 --> 04:23:20.579
I need to warn them.

04:23:20.700 --> 04:23:23.100
I'm afraid they're in danger, now that

04:23:23.100 --> 04:23:24.239
Queen Scarlet is free.

04:23:24.299 --> 04:23:27.059
Probably, Thorn agreed.

04:23:27.120 --> 04:23:28.319
She hesitated.

04:23:28.379 --> 04:23:30.540
Couldn't I send a messenger instead?

04:23:30.659 --> 04:23:32.879
I wanted to bring you back to the

04:23:32.879 --> 04:23:33.719
Scorpion Den.

04:23:33.780 --> 04:23:36.540
I still haven't heard about your life, and

04:23:36.540 --> 04:23:37.860
what you've been doing all these years.

04:23:37.920 --> 04:23:40.979
I know, Sunny said.

04:23:41.040 --> 04:23:43.020
She wished she could stay with her mother

04:23:43.020 --> 04:23:46.319
with those warm, strong wings close by to

04:23:46.319 --> 04:23:46.799
keep her safe.

04:23:46.860 --> 04:23:50.280
For the 1st time, she could imagine life

04:23:50.280 --> 04:23:52.739
without the prophecy, she could be a

04:23:52.739 --> 04:23:55.260
normal dragon, living in the scorpion den

04:23:55.260 --> 04:23:57.059
with her mother, instead of worrying

04:23:57.059 --> 04:23:58.139
about saving the whole world.

04:23:58.260 --> 04:24:01.920
But prophecy or not, her friends were her

04:24:01.920 --> 04:24:04.920
real life, her whole life, she couldn't

04:24:04.920 --> 04:24:05.639
leave them in danger.

04:24:05.700 --> 04:24:08.040
But this is really important.

04:24:08.100 --> 04:24:11.639
I'll come back to you soon, or you could

04:24:11.639 --> 04:24:12.059
come with me?

04:24:12.120 --> 04:24:14.520
Thorn sighed and shook her head.

04:24:14.579 --> 04:24:16.979
There might be retaliation from the

04:24:16.979 --> 04:24:17.579
stronghold.

04:24:17.639 --> 04:24:20.340
I have to fortify the den, prepare my

04:24:20.340 --> 04:24:22.559
dragons, make sure everyone's safe.

04:24:22.620 --> 04:24:24.180
That was true.

04:24:24.239 --> 04:24:28.079
Thorn had risked a lot, bringing her out

04:24:28.079 --> 04:24:29.639
claws into this dangerous rescue

04:24:29.639 --> 04:24:30.780
mission.

04:24:30.840 --> 04:24:32.399
Sonny touched her wing to begin.

04:24:32.459 --> 04:24:34.680
Thank you for coming to get me.

04:24:34.739 --> 04:24:37.920
Always, Thorn said fiercely.

04:24:37.979 --> 04:24:41.579
I'll see you soon, Sonny said, tilting

04:24:41.579 --> 04:24:42.299
her wings.

04:24:42.360 --> 04:24:44.639
Sonny, Thorn called.

04:24:44.700 --> 04:24:46.139
Be careful.

04:24:46.200 --> 04:24:49.079
I will, Sonny called back.

04:24:49.139 --> 04:24:51.120
Already soaring toward the mountains.

04:24:51.180 --> 04:24:55.020
No, I mean, Thorn swooped out of the

04:24:55.020 --> 04:24:57.059
formation for a moment, catching up to

04:24:57.059 --> 04:24:58.680
her. and circling her in the air.

04:24:58.739 --> 04:25:01.739
I mean, if you go see your father.

04:25:01.799 --> 04:25:03.420
I know you're thinking about it.

04:25:03.479 --> 04:25:07.020
She nodded at the line of mountains, where

04:25:07.020 --> 04:25:09.360
the jagged peak of Jade Mountain towered

04:25:09.360 --> 04:25:10.260
darkly over the rest.

04:25:10.319 --> 04:25:12.959
Be careful with Stone Mover.

04:25:13.079 --> 04:25:14.879
If all that is true about being an

04:25:14.879 --> 04:25:15.420
animus.

04:25:15.479 --> 04:25:18.239
Well, I saw him do a lot of magic.

04:25:18.299 --> 04:25:21.239
We don't know how much soul he has left.

04:25:21.299 --> 04:25:23.520
Are you going to go see him?

04:25:23.579 --> 04:25:24.899
Sonny asked.

04:25:24.959 --> 04:25:28.979
Someday, Thorn said, with a small flicker

04:25:28.979 --> 04:25:29.879
of anger in her eyes.

04:25:29.940 --> 04:25:33.180
Apparently he's in no hurry, so I'll take

04:25:33.180 --> 04:25:34.260
care of my dragons first.

04:25:34.319 --> 04:25:38.280
I should do that too, Sonny said, with my

04:25:38.280 --> 04:25:39.120
dragons, I mean.

04:25:39.180 --> 04:25:41.100
Thorn smiled at her.

04:25:41.159 --> 04:25:42.780
See you soon, daughter.

04:25:42.840 --> 04:25:46.680
Sunny watched as the outlaws soared away

04:25:46.680 --> 04:25:49.200
across the desert, all their wing beats

04:25:49.200 --> 04:25:51.479
together, stirring up small sandstorms

04:25:51.479 --> 04:25:51.840
below them.

04:25:51.899 --> 04:25:54.360
Then she oriented herself toward the

04:25:54.360 --> 04:25:56.760
mountains again and flew, beating her

04:25:56.760 --> 04:25:58.139
wings as fast as they would move.

04:25:58.200 --> 04:26:00.959
She couldn't use the tunnel to the

04:26:00.959 --> 04:26:01.559
rainforest.

04:26:01.620 --> 04:26:04.319
She couldn't risk the trip past Burns

04:26:04.319 --> 04:26:05.459
stronghold to get to it.

04:26:05.520 --> 04:26:08.579
It would be safer, if longer, to go over

04:26:08.579 --> 04:26:10.979
the mountains, but she should have a head

04:26:10.979 --> 04:26:13.559
start on Pearl and Scarlet, who had flown

04:26:13.559 --> 04:26:15.299
the other way, and who didn't know about

04:26:15.299 --> 04:26:15.840
the tunnels.

04:26:15.899 --> 04:26:18.299
I hope, she thought.

04:26:18.360 --> 04:26:20.459
I don't think there's any way they could

04:26:20.459 --> 04:26:20.819
know.

04:26:20.879 --> 04:26:23.760
Her breath seemed to come more easily

04:26:23.760 --> 04:26:26.459
with every wing beat, even as the forest

04:26:26.459 --> 04:26:28.020
and the mountains came closer and

04:26:28.020 --> 04:26:28.379
closer.

04:26:28.440 --> 04:26:31.440
She was leaving the desert, but she was

04:26:31.440 --> 04:26:33.120
going back to her friends at last.

04:26:33.180 --> 04:26:37.799
Chapter 16.

04:26:38.040 --> 04:26:41.040
The plan was to go straight to the

04:26:41.040 --> 04:26:41.700
rainforest.

04:26:41.760 --> 04:26:44.879
As tempted as Sonny was by the idea of

04:26:44.879 --> 04:26:46.920
meeting her father, she was more worried

04:26:46.920 --> 04:26:47.520
about her friends.

04:26:47.579 --> 04:26:50.040
She needed to get back and warn them

04:26:50.040 --> 04:26:50.819
fast.

04:26:50.879 --> 04:26:53.520
But the weather had other plans.

04:26:53.579 --> 04:26:57.299
A gale force wind howled down the

04:26:57.299 --> 04:26:59.579
mountains that night, carrying with it

04:26:59.579 --> 04:27:01.379
the worst storm Sonny had ever been

04:27:01.379 --> 04:27:01.860
caught in.

04:27:01.920 --> 04:27:05.040
Not that she'd encountered many living in

04:27:05.040 --> 04:27:05.940
caves her whole life.

04:27:06.000 --> 04:27:08.700
But there was that one hurricane in the

04:27:08.700 --> 04:27:10.739
kingdom of the sea, and Sonny was pretty

04:27:10.739 --> 04:27:12.059
sure this was worse.

04:27:12.120 --> 04:27:15.420
Or maybe it only felt worse, because she

04:27:15.420 --> 04:27:17.700
was alone and caught outside with no

04:27:17.700 --> 04:27:20.579
shelter, and rapidly becoming very, very

04:27:20.579 --> 04:27:21.059
wet.

04:27:21.120 --> 04:27:24.899
The rain pelted in her eyes and dragged

04:27:24.899 --> 04:27:27.059
down her wings, while the wind kept

04:27:27.059 --> 04:27:29.700
trying to slam her into the cliffs, and

04:27:29.700 --> 04:27:32.520
the whole time, thunder roared, as though

04:27:32.520 --> 04:27:34.079
the clouds were playing drums on the

04:27:34.079 --> 04:27:35.100
mountaintops.

04:27:35.159 --> 04:27:37.920
Lightning cracked terrifyingly close to

04:27:37.920 --> 04:27:40.559
her wings, and Sonny thought, I won't be

04:27:40.559 --> 04:27:42.659
able to save anyone if I end up as a

04:27:42.659 --> 04:27:43.860
fiery heap in a ravine.

04:27:43.920 --> 04:27:46.739
She veered toward the peak of Jade

04:27:46.739 --> 04:27:49.139
Mountain, the one solid thing she could

04:27:49.139 --> 04:27:50.700
identify in the driving storm.

04:27:50.760 --> 04:27:52.559
Will he be there?

04:27:52.620 --> 04:27:54.840
Will he want to meet me?

04:27:54.899 --> 04:27:58.920
Will he be scary, or awful, or

04:27:58.920 --> 04:27:59.459
dangerous?

04:27:59.520 --> 04:28:01.440
Will he be like Orca?

04:28:01.500 --> 04:28:04.139
The crazy animus seawing who killed all

04:28:04.139 --> 04:28:05.340
those dragonettes?

04:28:05.399 --> 04:28:08.639
She wished she had clay or tsunami with

04:28:08.639 --> 04:28:08.819
her.

04:28:08.879 --> 04:28:11.159
That would have been better if she could

04:28:11.159 --> 04:28:13.559
have gone back to the rainforest 1st and

04:28:13.559 --> 04:28:15.719
gotten one of them to come along, so she

04:28:15.719 --> 04:28:17.459
didn't have to meet her mysterious

04:28:17.459 --> 04:28:19.799
powerful, potentially homicidal father

04:28:19.799 --> 04:28:20.219
alone.

04:28:20.280 --> 04:28:24.120
But the storm drove her on, as if it had

04:28:24.120 --> 04:28:26.639
talons of its own, dragging her up the

04:28:26.639 --> 04:28:28.200
mountain with shrieking fury.

04:28:28.260 --> 04:28:32.520
Soaking wet, exhausted, and shivering

04:28:32.520 --> 04:28:35.579
with anxiety, Sunny finally crash landed

04:28:35.579 --> 04:28:37.620
in a cave high up on the mountain's south

04:28:37.620 --> 04:28:37.979
side.

04:28:38.040 --> 04:28:41.459
She stumbled to a stop, scraping her

04:28:41.459 --> 04:28:43.979
scales painfully on the rocky floor, and

04:28:43.979 --> 04:28:45.540
shook out her wings in a flurry of

04:28:45.540 --> 04:28:46.020
droplets.

04:28:46.079 --> 04:28:49.680
It was dark inside, and Sonny thought it

04:28:49.680 --> 04:28:51.540
was unlikely that she'd have accidentally

04:28:51.540 --> 04:28:53.639
wandered into the exact cave where her

04:28:53.639 --> 04:28:54.299
father lived.

04:28:54.360 --> 04:28:57.059
Surely there were other caves all over

04:28:57.059 --> 04:28:59.579
the mountain, but the darkness made her

04:28:59.579 --> 04:29:02.219
uneasy, and cautiously she breathed out a

04:29:02.219 --> 04:29:03.420
plume of fire.

04:29:03.479 --> 04:29:04.620
Nothing.

04:29:04.680 --> 04:29:07.680
An empty stone cavern loomed around her

04:29:07.680 --> 04:29:10.260
not that different from the ones she'd

04:29:10.260 --> 04:29:11.100
grown up in.

04:29:11.159 --> 04:29:14.040
She breathed more fire, letting it warm

04:29:14.040 --> 04:29:16.500
her from the inside, and searched the

04:29:16.500 --> 04:29:18.899
cave until she found a thick branch that

04:29:18.899 --> 04:29:20.399
had been swept inside by the storm.

04:29:20.520 --> 04:29:23.940
She set it ablaze, and held it up to use

04:29:23.940 --> 04:29:24.540
as a torch.

04:29:24.600 --> 04:29:27.899
The flickering light revealed a gap in

04:29:27.899 --> 04:29:29.219
the rocks in the back corner.

04:29:29.280 --> 04:29:32.340
When she investigated, she found a sort

04:29:32.340 --> 04:29:34.739
of natural tunnel that seemed to lead

04:29:34.739 --> 04:29:37.260
farther into the mountain to a cave

04:29:37.260 --> 04:29:39.000
system that probably ran all the way

04:29:39.000 --> 04:29:39.420
through it.

04:29:39.479 --> 04:29:42.899
Sunny hesitated, leaning against the

04:29:42.899 --> 04:29:43.500
stone wall.

04:29:43.559 --> 04:29:46.319
Should she rest here and fly on in the

04:29:46.319 --> 04:29:46.559
morning?

04:29:46.620 --> 04:29:49.799
Maybe she could leave unnoticed, and come

04:29:49.799 --> 04:29:51.120
back when she had reinforcements.

04:29:51.180 --> 04:29:54.180
But how could I get this close to my

04:29:54.180 --> 04:29:56.520
father and not try to see him?

04:29:56.579 --> 04:30:00.420
She thought of peril and kestrel, and how

04:30:00.420 --> 04:30:02.100
peril had thought they'd have more time

04:30:02.100 --> 04:30:03.059
to get to know each other.

04:30:03.120 --> 04:30:05.639
You never know what might happen.

04:30:05.700 --> 04:30:07.979
That decided her.

04:30:08.040 --> 04:30:10.799
Holding out the torch, she slipped into

04:30:10.799 --> 04:30:12.899
the gap and started down the rocky slope

04:30:12.899 --> 04:30:13.260
beyond.

04:30:13.319 --> 04:30:16.680
She wandered for what felt like a long

04:30:16.680 --> 04:30:19.319
time, marking the walls with her claws

04:30:19.319 --> 04:30:20.760
whenever she came to a fork in the

04:30:20.760 --> 04:30:21.120
tunnels.

04:30:21.180 --> 04:30:24.719
She found caves dripping with stalactites

04:30:24.719 --> 04:30:27.719
clambered over rocks like giant bubbles

04:30:27.719 --> 04:30:30.180
flew over a dark pool with no ripples

04:30:30.180 --> 04:30:32.459
where her torch reflected eerily across

04:30:32.459 --> 04:30:33.540
the glassy surface.

04:30:33.600 --> 04:30:37.139
It felt familiar, being underground like

04:30:37.139 --> 04:30:37.379
this.

04:30:37.440 --> 04:30:40.620
She wondered if other dragons, especially

04:30:40.620 --> 04:30:43.379
other sand wings, would be more unnerved

04:30:43.379 --> 04:30:44.159
by these surroundings.

04:30:44.219 --> 04:30:47.219
But this was so similar to the small

04:30:47.219 --> 04:30:48.840
enclosed world she grew up in.

04:30:48.899 --> 04:30:51.780
She almost expected to turn a corner and

04:30:51.780 --> 04:30:54.239
find the steady cave, with a map spread

04:30:54.239 --> 04:30:56.819
against one wall and scrolls piled in the

04:30:56.819 --> 04:30:59.159
corner, and her friends arguing over who

04:30:59.159 --> 04:31:00.959
would play Blaze when they acted out the

04:31:00.959 --> 04:31:01.739
history of the war.

04:31:01.799 --> 04:31:05.399
And then, she stopped in a narrow

04:31:05.399 --> 04:31:07.500
passageway with a low, craggy ceiling.

04:31:07.559 --> 04:31:09.780
Was that breathing?

04:31:09.840 --> 04:31:12.600
She held her own breath and listened.

04:31:12.719 --> 04:31:15.299
It sounds like breathing.

04:31:15.360 --> 04:31:20.459
Air rasped quietly somewhere, in and out

04:31:20.459 --> 04:31:22.500
as if something large were sitting

04:31:22.500 --> 04:31:25.739
concealed in shadows, not too far away

04:31:25.739 --> 04:31:27.780
maybe even watching her.

04:31:27.840 --> 04:31:32.100
Sunny's scales crawled, and she clutched

04:31:32.100 --> 04:31:33.299
the torch closer.

04:31:33.360 --> 04:31:34.860
Do not panic.

04:31:34.979 --> 04:31:36.360
Listen.

04:31:36.420 --> 04:31:39.959
After a long moment, she realized that

04:31:39.959 --> 04:31:41.760
the breathing was even and rhythmic.

04:31:41.819 --> 04:31:43.920
That's not the sound of something

04:31:43.920 --> 04:31:44.940
lurking.

04:31:45.000 --> 04:31:47.459
That's the sound of a dragon sleeping.

04:31:47.520 --> 04:31:50.579
She crept up a passageway toward the

04:31:50.579 --> 04:31:50.819
noise.

04:31:50.879 --> 04:31:53.219
I think it's this way.

04:31:53.280 --> 04:31:56.819
Sharp edges of rocks caught on her tail

04:31:56.819 --> 04:31:59.219
and stabbed at her feet as she climbed

04:31:59.219 --> 04:32:01.860
closer, and closer.

04:32:01.920 --> 04:32:05.579
The torchlight flickered suddenly, dipping

04:32:05.579 --> 04:32:08.040
and swaying, and then Sonny felt it as

04:32:08.040 --> 04:32:10.920
well, a gust of wind, whistling down the

04:32:10.920 --> 04:32:12.059
tunnel from far away.

04:32:12.120 --> 04:32:15.899
She lifted the torch higher, and saw that

04:32:15.899 --> 04:32:17.940
the tunnel widened into a cave only a few

04:32:17.940 --> 04:32:19.260
paces ahead.

04:32:19.319 --> 04:32:23.340
At first, as she edged closer, the cave

04:32:23.340 --> 04:32:25.440
looked empty, but then the firelight

04:32:25.440 --> 04:32:27.540
reflected off something black and glossy

04:32:27.540 --> 04:32:29.100
in the shadows against the back wall.

04:32:29.159 --> 04:32:34.319
Scales, black scales, rising and falling

04:32:34.319 --> 04:32:34.920
in sleep.

04:32:35.040 --> 04:32:36.899
It was a night wing for sure.

04:32:36.959 --> 04:32:40.319
Sunny stopped and stared at the

04:32:40.319 --> 04:32:41.280
slumbering dragon.

04:32:41.340 --> 04:32:43.260
Is that my father?

04:32:43.379 --> 04:32:46.860
He was bigger than thorn, but not

04:32:46.860 --> 04:32:49.680
enormous, nowhere near the size of morrow

04:32:49.680 --> 04:32:50.760
seer or burn.

04:32:50.819 --> 04:32:54.299
Deep lines were etched into his face, so

04:32:54.299 --> 04:32:56.520
he looked as if he were in pain, even in

04:32:56.520 --> 04:32:56.940
his sleep.

04:32:56.940 --> 04:32:59.700
His talons were curled awkwardly into

04:32:59.700 --> 04:33:02.159
stiff shapes, and his tail flopped

04:33:02.159 --> 04:33:03.959
heavily along the ground behind him

04:33:03.959 --> 04:33:06.959
barely moving as he breathed, as though

04:33:06.959 --> 04:33:07.799
it were made of stone.

04:33:07.860 --> 04:33:11.580
Sonny took a quick breath in, and then

04:33:11.580 --> 04:33:13.020
stepped closer.

04:33:13.080 --> 04:33:14.700
It wasn't just his tail.

04:33:14.759 --> 04:33:18.359
Other parts of the dragon, his back legs

04:33:18.359 --> 04:33:21.059
his shoulders, the edges of his wings

04:33:21.059 --> 04:33:23.459
looked heavier and thicker than a normal

04:33:23.459 --> 04:33:24.839
dragon's scales.

04:33:24.959 --> 04:33:28.259
Like he's actually turning into stone.

04:33:28.380 --> 04:33:29.520
Is that possible?

04:33:29.580 --> 04:33:33.119
She lifted the torch. and peered at the

04:33:33.119 --> 04:33:34.859
section of tail closest to her.

04:33:34.919 --> 04:33:37.739
The black scales looked like dark pebbles

04:33:37.739 --> 04:33:40.079
here, sinking into the skin beneath.

04:33:40.139 --> 04:33:43.919
She was so preoccupied, studying this odd

04:33:43.919 --> 04:33:46.139
phenomenon, that it took her a moment to

04:33:46.139 --> 04:33:48.659
realize that the dragon's eyes had opened

04:33:48.659 --> 04:33:50.580
and he was staring back at her.

04:33:50.639 --> 04:33:54.240
Oh, she gasped, jumping back.

04:33:54.299 --> 04:33:55.259
I'm sorry.

04:33:55.319 --> 04:33:56.580
I didn't.

04:33:56.639 --> 04:33:59.340
I mean, I didn't mean to wake you.

04:33:59.400 --> 04:34:01.680
I was, The storm.

04:34:01.740 --> 04:34:06.240
I don't bite, he said in a deep, serious

04:34:06.240 --> 04:34:06.840
voice.

04:34:06.900 --> 04:34:09.479
Oh, Sonny said again.

04:34:09.540 --> 04:34:11.759
Well, that's good.

04:34:11.819 --> 04:34:14.819
You mean, you don't bite other dragons

04:34:14.819 --> 04:34:15.000
right?

04:34:15.119 --> 04:34:15.839
Like me?

04:34:15.900 --> 04:34:18.240
Are you being reassuring?

04:34:18.360 --> 04:34:19.799
He blinked slowly at her.

04:34:19.860 --> 04:34:22.319
I don't bite.

04:34:22.380 --> 04:34:24.119
Other dragons.

04:34:24.180 --> 04:34:28.020
Great. said Sonny, not feeling very

04:34:28.020 --> 04:34:28.680
reassured.

04:34:28.740 --> 04:34:31.259
It was unsettling how he hadn't moved a

04:34:31.259 --> 04:34:33.060
muscle of his body as he spoke to her.

04:34:33.119 --> 04:34:36.779
Even his jaws seemed to hinge very slowly

04:34:36.779 --> 04:34:37.859
open for him to talk.

04:34:37.919 --> 04:34:40.499
So, hi.

04:34:40.560 --> 04:34:42.060
I'm Sonny.

04:34:42.180 --> 04:34:43.619
He didn't answer.

04:34:43.680 --> 04:34:47.520
She waited a moment, then said, are you

04:34:47.520 --> 04:34:48.360
stone mover?

04:34:48.419 --> 04:34:51.239
That seemed to surprise him a little.

04:34:51.299 --> 04:34:53.459
If the tiny flicker of movement in his

04:34:53.459 --> 04:34:54.360
brow meant anything.

04:34:54.720 --> 04:34:55.919
Yes.

04:34:56.040 --> 04:34:58.619
It is my father.

04:34:58.680 --> 04:35:00.540
It's really him.

04:35:00.599 --> 04:35:03.419
He's still alive, and right here in front

04:35:03.419 --> 04:35:03.839
of me.

04:35:03.959 --> 04:35:07.439
And he doesn't look crazy and homicidal.

04:35:07.500 --> 04:35:10.500
He just looks sad.

04:35:10.619 --> 04:35:13.079
Stone mover blinked again.

04:35:13.139 --> 04:35:16.500
How did the Talons find out my name?

04:35:16.560 --> 04:35:19.979
I'm not from the talons, she said.

04:35:20.040 --> 04:35:21.479
Do the talons come here?

04:35:21.540 --> 04:35:22.680
Oh, right.

04:35:22.740 --> 04:35:24.959
Kestrel said we could send her a message

04:35:24.959 --> 04:35:25.619
through you.

04:35:25.680 --> 04:35:28.020
I guess that would be useful when you're

04:35:28.020 --> 04:35:29.819
an underground movement and never know

04:35:29.819 --> 04:35:30.959
where you'll have to hide.

04:35:31.020 --> 04:35:33.360
True, he said.

04:35:33.479 --> 04:35:36.779
After all, I am not going anywhere.

04:35:36.900 --> 04:35:41.279
Oh, Sunny said, glancing at his scales.

04:35:41.340 --> 04:35:44.040
Because what happened to you?

04:35:44.099 --> 04:35:48.659
You are nosier than the talons, he

04:35:48.659 --> 04:35:50.819
observed, but without any anger in his

04:35:50.819 --> 04:35:50.999
voice.

04:35:51.119 --> 04:35:54.659
It is my animus curse.

04:35:54.720 --> 04:35:56.159
Really?

04:35:56.279 --> 04:35:57.359
Sonny said.

04:35:57.419 --> 04:35:59.339
This happened to you when you used your

04:35:59.339 --> 04:35:59.759
magic?

04:35:59.819 --> 04:36:03.720
I thought you'd lose your, you know, soul

04:36:03.720 --> 04:36:06.479
or something, not this.

04:36:06.540 --> 04:36:09.419
She waved her claws at the petrified

04:36:09.419 --> 04:36:10.680
scales weighing him down.

04:36:10.740 --> 04:36:15.720
I turned the magic on itself, he said.

04:36:15.779 --> 04:36:18.959
The curse appears in my scales now

04:36:19.020 --> 04:36:21.540
instead of taking my soul.

04:36:21.599 --> 04:36:25.919
He sighed through his nose, a sad, windy

04:36:25.919 --> 04:36:27.299
sound with drifts of smoke.

04:36:27.299 --> 04:36:30.359
Too late, anyway.

04:36:30.419 --> 04:36:32.279
Too late for what?

04:36:32.340 --> 04:36:33.540
Sonny asked.

04:36:33.599 --> 04:36:35.699
My soul.

04:36:35.759 --> 04:36:39.119
He managed to turn his head a fraction

04:36:39.119 --> 04:36:41.399
toward her, with an eerie, creaking

04:36:41.399 --> 04:36:41.819
sound.

04:36:41.880 --> 04:36:44.459
His dark eyes were as still and

04:36:44.459 --> 04:36:47.099
unreadable as the underground cave like.

04:36:47.159 --> 04:36:50.040
The things I have done.

04:36:50.099 --> 04:36:53.639
You mean like building the tunnels?

04:36:53.700 --> 04:36:54.720
Sonny said.

04:36:54.779 --> 04:36:56.879
And now there was a definite flash of

04:36:56.879 --> 04:36:59.579
surprise all the way through his eyes.

04:36:59.639 --> 04:37:02.220
Then it faded, and his eyes narrowed, as

04:37:02.220 --> 04:37:04.259
he examined her from horns to talons.

04:37:04.319 --> 04:37:06.840
It might have been scary once, his

04:37:06.840 --> 04:37:09.119
expression, except that the rest of him

04:37:09.119 --> 04:37:11.099
was so pathetic and sad.

04:37:11.159 --> 04:37:12.779
He could hardly even move.

04:37:12.840 --> 04:37:15.419
Sonny didn't feel afraid of him at all.

04:37:15.479 --> 04:37:17.220
Who?

04:37:17.279 --> 04:37:18.839
Oh, you?

04:37:18.839 --> 04:37:19.559
he asked.

04:37:19.619 --> 04:37:23.579
I'm, Well, this felt awkward.

04:37:23.639 --> 04:37:25.500
Just throwing it out there mid

04:37:25.500 --> 04:37:27.840
conversation, but how else could she tell

04:37:27.840 --> 04:37:28.139
him?

04:37:28.200 --> 04:37:31.020
Was there an easy, not shocking way to

04:37:31.020 --> 04:37:31.919
break this kind of news?

04:37:31.979 --> 04:37:36.419
Okay, the truth is, I'm your daughter.

04:37:36.479 --> 04:37:38.340
Thorn is my mother.

04:37:38.400 --> 04:37:42.419
I only just found her just, wow, just

04:37:42.419 --> 04:37:42.900
yesterday.

04:37:42.959 --> 04:37:46.380
No, 2 days ago, and she told me about you

04:37:46.380 --> 04:37:50.159
and Sunny talked on, not sure what to

04:37:50.159 --> 04:37:52.020
think of the expressions darting across

04:37:52.020 --> 04:37:55.500
Stone Mover's face, confusion, suspicion

04:37:55.500 --> 04:37:57.659
hope, dismay.

04:37:57.720 --> 04:37:59.040
Maybe anger?

04:37:59.099 --> 04:38:00.959
And I wanted to meet you.

04:38:01.080 --> 04:38:04.619
I hope that's, I hope you, Well, I know

04:38:04.619 --> 04:38:06.360
it's weird because she never got a chance

04:38:06.360 --> 04:38:11.279
to tell you about me, so, We had eggs, he

04:38:11.279 --> 04:38:11.819
rasped.

04:38:11.880 --> 04:38:16.560
You had me, Sonny said, an egg, one

04:38:16.560 --> 04:38:17.279
dragonette.

04:38:17.340 --> 04:38:18.540
Just me.

04:38:18.599 --> 04:38:21.359
She looked down at her talons.

04:38:21.419 --> 04:38:24.419
Mother wanted to tell you, but she never

04:38:24.419 --> 04:38:24.959
got your note.

04:38:25.020 --> 04:38:27.240
She didn't know you were here until she

04:38:27.240 --> 04:38:28.080
found it yesterday.

04:38:28.139 --> 04:38:30.240
She's been looking everywhere for you.

04:38:30.360 --> 04:38:33.360
Her father sighed through his nose and

04:38:33.360 --> 04:38:34.139
closed his eyes.

04:38:34.259 --> 04:38:38.039
I thought she'd given up on me.

04:38:38.159 --> 04:38:42.240
She might have now, Sunny said, trying to

04:38:42.240 --> 04:38:43.500
prompt more of a response.

04:38:43.560 --> 04:38:45.240
Why didn't he care more?

04:38:45.299 --> 04:38:47.279
Why hadn't he tried harder?

04:38:47.340 --> 04:38:49.500
She felt a wave of sympathy for her

04:38:49.500 --> 04:38:49.740
mother.

04:38:49.799 --> 04:38:52.080
Why didn't you go look for her?

04:38:52.139 --> 04:38:54.299
I'm not.

04:38:54.360 --> 04:38:58.259
The right dragon for Thorn, he said.

04:38:58.319 --> 04:39:00.900
Perhaps I never was.

04:39:01.020 --> 04:39:04.680
She obviously thought you were, Sonny

04:39:04.680 --> 04:39:05.220
pointed out.

04:39:05.279 --> 04:39:07.259
She really worried about you.

04:39:07.380 --> 04:39:09.360
He sighed again.

04:39:09.419 --> 04:39:13.439
He sighs a lot, Sonny thought, wishing

04:39:13.439 --> 04:39:14.999
she could poke something into his nose to

04:39:14.999 --> 04:39:15.539
make him stop.

04:39:15.659 --> 04:39:18.779
There's nothing I can do.

04:39:18.840 --> 04:39:21.720
I did all the wrong things.

04:39:21.840 --> 04:39:25.380
A long, long time ago.

04:39:25.500 --> 04:39:28.680
And nothing can change that.

04:39:28.740 --> 04:39:31.860
Something suddenly scrabbled in the dark

04:39:31.860 --> 04:39:34.380
nearby, and Sunny nearly leaped onto

04:39:34.380 --> 04:39:35.759
Stone Mover's back in terror.

04:39:35.819 --> 04:39:38.700
But when she swung the torch around and

04:39:38.700 --> 04:39:41.159
then down, the light reflected off tiny

04:39:41.159 --> 04:39:43.619
little eyes and pointed ears, and wet

04:39:43.619 --> 04:39:44.520
russet fur.

04:39:44.700 --> 04:39:46.139
It was a fox.

04:39:46.200 --> 04:39:48.720
Sauntering into their cave as bold as

04:39:48.720 --> 04:39:48.959
anything.

04:39:49.020 --> 04:39:52.020
Sunny realized it had come down another

04:39:52.020 --> 04:39:54.419
passageway, and she could feel the wind

04:39:54.419 --> 04:39:56.220
coming from that direction as well.

04:39:56.279 --> 04:39:59.639
The passage must lead to an exit out to

04:39:59.639 --> 04:40:00.360
the mountainside.

04:40:00.419 --> 04:40:03.659
The fox carried a dead squirrel in its

04:40:03.659 --> 04:40:06.240
jaws, and it gave Sonny a scornful look

04:40:06.240 --> 04:40:08.459
as if it certainly didn't expect her to

04:40:08.459 --> 04:40:10.439
dare pick a fight with someone as tough

04:40:10.439 --> 04:40:10.799
as him.

04:40:10.860 --> 04:40:14.400
Shoo, Sonny said sternly.

04:40:14.459 --> 04:40:16.259
Go find yourself another cave.

04:40:16.319 --> 04:40:18.060
Oh.

04:40:18.180 --> 04:40:22.380
This is dinner, Stone Mover said.

04:40:22.439 --> 04:40:25.860
He hinged his jaw open, and to Sonny's

04:40:25.860 --> 04:40:28.139
wonder, the fox trotted over and dropped

04:40:28.139 --> 04:40:29.639
the squirrel right into his mouth.

04:40:29.700 --> 04:40:32.520
It stepped back and gave Sonny another

04:40:32.520 --> 04:40:34.799
haughty look as Stone Mover began to

04:40:34.799 --> 04:40:35.040
chew.

04:40:35.159 --> 04:40:40.200
Wow, Sonny said, are foxes intelligent

04:40:40.200 --> 04:40:40.560
too?

04:40:40.560 --> 04:40:42.060
Like scavengers?

04:40:42.119 --> 04:40:44.459
What if all animals are smarter than we

04:40:44.459 --> 04:40:44.880
think they are?

04:40:45.000 --> 04:40:48.180
Is there going to be any prey left that I

04:40:48.180 --> 04:40:49.319
won't feel bad about eating?

04:40:49.380 --> 04:40:51.599
How did you train it to do that?

04:40:51.720 --> 04:40:55.139
Stone mover waited until he'd swallowed

04:40:55.139 --> 04:40:57.779
and then he said, I didn't.

04:40:57.840 --> 04:40:59.580
I enchanted him.

04:40:59.639 --> 04:41:01.979
Sonny frowned at the fox.

04:41:02.040 --> 04:41:05.340
You mean with animus magic?

04:41:05.400 --> 04:41:07.979
That only works on things, not animals.

04:41:08.040 --> 04:41:12.119
Turns out, it works on animals.

04:41:12.180 --> 04:41:13.979
Said Stone Mover.

04:41:14.040 --> 04:41:17.340
If you're desperate, and try hard

04:41:17.340 --> 04:41:17.700
enough.

04:41:17.759 --> 04:41:20.759
She folded her wings in and shivered.

04:41:20.819 --> 04:41:22.139
That's creepy.

04:41:22.200 --> 04:41:26.819
Dinner doesn't mind, he replied, and it

04:41:26.819 --> 04:41:28.259
took her a moment to figure it out.

04:41:28.380 --> 04:41:31.020
You call the fox dinner?

04:41:31.020 --> 04:41:31.799
she said.

04:41:31.860 --> 04:41:33.479
Why not?

04:41:33.540 --> 04:41:36.599
His shoulder moved an infinitesimal

04:41:36.599 --> 04:41:38.580
amount, the smallest of shrugs.

04:41:38.639 --> 04:41:43.020
Because that's peculiar, she said, and

04:41:43.020 --> 04:41:44.939
really creepy for him if he knew what you

04:41:44.939 --> 04:41:45.240
were saying.

04:41:45.299 --> 04:41:48.779
I didn't think about it, he said.

04:41:48.840 --> 04:41:51.720
I've never introduced him to anyone

04:41:51.720 --> 04:41:52.139
before.

04:41:52.200 --> 04:41:56.459
Anyway, I only enchanted him to bring me

04:41:56.459 --> 04:41:57.779
food every few days.

04:41:57.840 --> 04:42:01.979
He still has a fine ordinary life as a

04:42:01.979 --> 04:42:02.639
fox.

04:42:02.700 --> 04:42:03.540
I'm sure.

04:42:03.599 --> 04:42:07.139
As if in answer to this, dinner shook

04:42:07.139 --> 04:42:09.299
himself vigorously, scattering water all

04:42:09.299 --> 04:42:11.340
over sunny, and then trotted out of the

04:42:11.340 --> 04:42:11.759
cave again.

04:42:11.819 --> 04:42:17.400
I mean, Stone Mover concluded, I had to

04:42:17.400 --> 04:42:20.040
do something, or I would have starved.

04:42:20.099 --> 04:42:21.599
Hmm.

04:42:21.659 --> 04:42:22.799
Sonny said.

04:42:22.860 --> 04:42:25.080
She didn't like the thought of any dragon

04:42:25.080 --> 04:42:27.060
using magic to command a living thing.

04:42:27.180 --> 04:42:29.880
Would animus magic work on something

04:42:29.880 --> 04:42:30.959
bigger than a fox?

04:42:31.020 --> 04:42:34.080
She didn't want to follow that thought to

04:42:34.080 --> 04:42:35.099
its possible conclusion.

04:42:35.159 --> 04:42:37.919
I can't believe.

04:42:38.099 --> 04:42:39.599
I have a daughter.

04:42:39.720 --> 04:42:42.900
Stone Mover said, and Sonny felt a little

04:42:42.900 --> 04:42:45.419
warmer toward him, hearing the sadness in

04:42:45.419 --> 04:42:45.720
his voice.

04:42:45.779 --> 04:42:48.240
I used to dream.

04:42:48.299 --> 04:42:52.020
I would think about what our dragonettes

04:42:52.020 --> 04:42:52.860
might look like.

04:42:52.979 --> 04:42:57.060
If Thorn and I ever, but I thought it was

04:42:57.060 --> 04:42:57.419
too late.

04:42:57.479 --> 04:42:59.939
I bet you didn't picture me.

04:43:00.000 --> 04:43:01.680
Sonny said ruefully.

04:43:01.740 --> 04:43:05.159
I don't have the sandwing tail barb, and

04:43:05.159 --> 04:43:07.080
I also don't have any cool nightwing

04:43:07.080 --> 04:43:08.220
powers.

04:43:08.279 --> 04:43:09.659
I always thought maybe I looked weird

04:43:09.659 --> 04:43:12.779
because of the prophecy somehow, but he

04:43:12.779 --> 04:43:13.860
would have sat up if he could.

04:43:13.919 --> 04:43:14.819
She could tell.

04:43:14.880 --> 04:43:17.159
His head twitched a little closer to

04:43:17.159 --> 04:43:17.400
her.

04:43:17.459 --> 04:43:19.919
His breath smelled like squirrel

04:43:19.919 --> 04:43:21.479
prophecy.

04:43:21.599 --> 04:43:24.659
About the dragonette saving the world and

04:43:24.659 --> 04:43:25.560
stopping the war?

04:43:25.619 --> 04:43:28.680
Sonny said, you know, you must know.

04:43:28.799 --> 04:43:30.419
Yes.

04:43:30.540 --> 04:43:31.799
He mused.

04:43:31.860 --> 04:43:34.139
I'm one of them, she said.

04:43:34.259 --> 04:43:36.779
Hidden alone from the rival queens.

04:43:36.840 --> 04:43:37.680
That's me.

04:43:37.740 --> 04:43:39.419
It's kind of a long story.

04:43:39.479 --> 04:43:43.139
But he started, and paused.

04:43:43.200 --> 04:43:46.680
And then Sonny was scared, because the

04:43:46.680 --> 04:43:48.779
look in his eyes was the look of news she

04:43:48.779 --> 04:43:50.700
knew she didn't want, and it was

04:43:50.700 --> 04:43:53.580
righteousness and pity, and truth is the

04:43:53.580 --> 04:43:55.439
important thing, and she didn't want it.

04:43:55.500 --> 04:43:57.180
She didn't want him to say it.

04:43:57.240 --> 04:44:01.799
Stop, don't, she blurted, but at the same

04:44:01.799 --> 04:44:04.619
time, he said, But don't you know?

04:44:04.680 --> 04:44:08.099
The prophecy isn't real.

04:44:08.159 --> 04:44:12.840
Chapter 17.

04:44:13.080 --> 04:44:15.540
Hmm...

04:44:15.659 --> 04:44:18.540
Stone mover said, studying her

04:44:18.540 --> 04:44:19.080
expression.

04:44:19.139 --> 04:44:21.180
You did know.

04:44:21.240 --> 04:44:23.279
You know it's fake.

04:44:23.340 --> 04:44:27.599
Well, I've heard that, Sonny said.

04:44:27.659 --> 04:44:29.880
The walls felt as if they were tilting in

04:44:29.880 --> 04:44:30.360
toward her.

04:44:30.419 --> 04:44:33.180
She curled her claws and twitched her

04:44:33.180 --> 04:44:34.560
tail, avoiding his eyes.

04:44:34.619 --> 04:44:37.979
That's what Maro seer said, but why

04:44:37.979 --> 04:44:38.639
should we trust him?

04:44:38.700 --> 04:44:42.119
Stone Mover managed to look faintly

04:44:42.119 --> 04:44:42.599
amused.

04:44:42.659 --> 04:44:47.159
Morusir wouldn't make himself seem any

04:44:47.159 --> 04:44:50.040
less powerful if he could ever avoid it.

04:44:50.099 --> 04:44:53.279
He must have been forced to tell you the

04:44:53.279 --> 04:44:55.740
truth, for some reason.

04:44:55.799 --> 04:44:59.939
He was manipulating us, like always, Sonny

04:44:59.939 --> 04:45:01.979
said, but just because I don't like him

04:45:01.979 --> 04:45:03.599
doesn't mean that prophecy couldn't be

04:45:03.599 --> 04:45:03.779
real.

04:45:03.840 --> 04:45:06.599
Oh little dragon.

04:45:06.720 --> 04:45:09.840
Stone Mover said, and she got the feeling

04:45:09.840 --> 04:45:11.279
he'd already forgotten her name.

04:45:11.340 --> 04:45:13.259
I promise you.

04:45:13.380 --> 04:45:15.540
The prophecy is not real.

04:45:15.599 --> 04:45:18.479
I was there when they came up with it.

04:45:18.540 --> 04:45:21.299
I was also there when the night wing

04:45:21.299 --> 04:45:23.400
scribes were ordered to write more about

04:45:23.400 --> 04:45:25.619
our so called powers.

04:45:25.680 --> 04:45:29.279
Building them up in every scroll, every

04:45:29.279 --> 04:45:29.939
story.

04:45:29.939 --> 04:45:33.060
Queen battle winner planned that

04:45:33.060 --> 04:45:33.720
carefully.

04:45:33.779 --> 04:45:37.020
But no night wing is at any power to see

04:45:37.020 --> 04:45:40.439
the future, or read minds, in over a 100

04:45:40.439 --> 04:45:40.740
years.

04:45:40.799 --> 04:45:42.419
If anyone ever did.

04:45:42.479 --> 04:45:45.659
That is the truth.

04:45:45.720 --> 04:45:49.080
Sonny wanted to throw things, and yell

04:45:49.080 --> 04:45:50.639
like her mother did when she was angry.

04:45:50.700 --> 04:45:52.680
Nightwings.

04:45:52.740 --> 04:45:53.819
She growled.

04:45:53.880 --> 04:45:56.520
You guys make it really, really hard to

04:45:56.520 --> 04:45:56.939
like you.

04:45:57.000 --> 04:45:58.799
Why are you telling me this?

04:45:58.860 --> 04:46:01.619
You obviously haven't told the talons or

04:46:01.619 --> 04:46:02.340
everyone would know.

04:46:02.400 --> 04:46:07.200
Because I suspect I am dying.

04:46:07.319 --> 04:46:10.979
He said with a dry cough, and someone

04:46:10.979 --> 04:46:11.759
should know.

04:46:11.819 --> 04:46:13.919
If not my own daughter.

04:46:13.979 --> 04:46:15.299
Then who?

04:46:15.419 --> 04:46:18.479
Well, hooray, Sonny said.

04:46:18.540 --> 04:46:19.680
Lucky me.

04:46:19.740 --> 04:46:22.560
She tucked her tail around her talons and

04:46:22.560 --> 04:46:24.060
hunched her wings up.

04:46:24.119 --> 04:46:26.520
After a moment, she said, really?

04:46:26.580 --> 04:46:28.439
Are you really dying?

04:46:28.500 --> 04:46:31.020
I'm always dying.

04:46:31.139 --> 04:46:34.319
He answered, which also made Sonny want

04:46:34.319 --> 04:46:35.580
to poke him in the nose.

04:46:35.639 --> 04:46:37.860
She honestly had no idea why her mother

04:46:37.860 --> 04:46:39.540
had ever liked this dragon.

04:46:39.599 --> 04:46:42.180
But at least he's telling me the truth.

04:46:42.299 --> 04:46:44.759
That's more than I can say for most of

04:46:44.759 --> 04:46:46.380
the grown up dragons I've ever known.

04:46:46.439 --> 04:46:49.380
She tried to push down the bitterness she

04:46:49.380 --> 04:46:51.599
felt about night wings and all their

04:46:51.599 --> 04:46:52.080
lies.

04:46:52.139 --> 04:46:55.200
She tried to look at just stone mover, her

04:46:55.200 --> 04:46:58.439
father, and see him as his own dragon, not

04:46:58.439 --> 04:46:59.099
one of a tribe.

04:46:59.159 --> 04:47:01.020
He's really sad.

04:47:01.139 --> 04:47:05.340
Imagine, if I had been born with Anima's

04:47:05.340 --> 04:47:07.619
powers, into a terrible place like the

04:47:07.619 --> 04:47:08.459
Nightwing Island.

04:47:08.580 --> 04:47:10.860
The queen must have used him from the

04:47:10.860 --> 04:47:12.240
moment they found out what he could do.

04:47:12.299 --> 04:47:14.580
He never had a choice about what to do

04:47:14.580 --> 04:47:15.060
with his life.

04:47:15.119 --> 04:47:17.819
Maybe nobody does.

04:47:17.880 --> 04:47:20.400
Even though I want to end the war so

04:47:20.400 --> 04:47:20.880
badly.

04:47:20.939 --> 04:47:22.799
Maybe there's nothing I can do.

04:47:22.919 --> 04:47:26.159
The prophecy was really fake.

04:47:26.220 --> 04:47:28.740
Her life was really a lie.

04:47:28.799 --> 04:47:31.380
She was really not special.

04:47:31.500 --> 04:47:34.139
And she was really not destined to save

04:47:34.139 --> 04:47:34.560
the world.

04:47:34.619 --> 04:47:38.040
She looked at her father, whose eyes had

04:47:38.040 --> 04:47:38.400
closed.

04:47:38.459 --> 04:47:41.159
His breathing was starting to slow down

04:47:41.159 --> 04:47:42.840
as if he were falling asleep again.

04:47:42.959 --> 04:47:45.479
Can I stay here tonight?

04:47:45.540 --> 04:47:46.380
she asked.

04:47:46.439 --> 04:47:50.279
Please do, he said quietly.

04:47:50.340 --> 04:47:53.459
Sunny blew out the torch, and curled up

04:47:53.459 --> 04:47:55.139
in a ball in the warmest corner of the

04:47:55.139 --> 04:47:58.080
cave, across from Stone Mover's petrified

04:47:58.080 --> 04:47:58.619
scales.

04:47:58.680 --> 04:48:01.560
She rested her chin on her front talons

04:48:01.560 --> 04:48:03.720
feeling like her own scales were made of

04:48:03.720 --> 04:48:06.779
stone too, heavy, and exhausting to lug

04:48:06.779 --> 04:48:07.740
around.

04:48:07.799 --> 04:48:10.080
She wished she could wake up back in the

04:48:10.080 --> 04:48:11.939
cave under the mountain 2 months ago

04:48:11.939 --> 04:48:14.880
before any of this had happened, when she

04:48:14.880 --> 04:48:16.979
still believed in the prophecy, their

04:48:16.979 --> 04:48:20.400
destiny, a wonderful future, and perfect

04:48:20.400 --> 04:48:22.080
parents waiting out there for all of

04:48:22.080 --> 04:48:22.319
them.

04:48:22.319 --> 04:48:26.459
Her eyes closed, and her sadness drifted

04:48:26.459 --> 04:48:27.119
away into sleep.

04:48:27.180 --> 04:48:31.139
Sunny was back in the stronghold

04:48:31.139 --> 04:48:33.599
wandering through Burns Weirdling

04:48:33.599 --> 04:48:36.659
collection, except instead of a tower, it

04:48:36.659 --> 04:48:38.220
had become an endless maze of

04:48:38.220 --> 04:48:39.900
increasingly creepy oddities.

04:48:39.959 --> 04:48:42.779
Every time she turned a corner, a new

04:48:42.779 --> 04:48:44.700
disturbing thing lurched toward her.

04:48:44.759 --> 04:48:47.819
She realized Flower was sitting on her

04:48:47.819 --> 04:48:50.340
shoulder, holding onto her neck like one

04:48:50.340 --> 04:48:52.799
of the rainforest sloths and chattering

04:48:52.799 --> 04:48:53.880
quietly to herself.

04:48:53.939 --> 04:48:57.360
This was comforting only for a moment, and

04:48:57.360 --> 04:48:59.580
then a headless gray dragon suddenly

04:48:59.580 --> 04:49:01.380
loomed out of his shadowy doorway

04:49:01.380 --> 04:49:03.900
tottering at her, and splattering blood

04:49:03.900 --> 04:49:05.340
from its claws.

04:49:05.400 --> 04:49:08.279
Sonny leaped aside, pressing her back

04:49:08.279 --> 04:49:10.139
against the wall, she closed her eyes.

04:49:10.200 --> 04:49:13.080
Stop, stop.

04:49:13.139 --> 04:49:14.040
Don't be scared.

04:49:14.099 --> 04:49:15.479
This is just a dream.

04:49:15.540 --> 04:49:18.540
You're safe now, far away from Bern.

04:49:18.659 --> 04:49:21.959
She imagined the bright rolling sand of

04:49:21.959 --> 04:49:24.060
the desert, trying to change her dreams

04:49:24.060 --> 04:49:25.680
surroundings by force of will.

04:49:25.740 --> 04:49:27.299
After a few moments.

04:49:27.360 --> 04:49:29.580
She felt the warmth of sunlight on her

04:49:29.580 --> 04:49:31.139
face, and she opened her eyes.

04:49:31.259 --> 04:49:33.180
It had worked.

04:49:33.240 --> 04:49:36.419
She was standing on the desert sand, and

04:49:36.419 --> 04:49:38.400
right in front of her was a scavenger.

04:49:38.520 --> 04:49:41.340
Sunny started back with a yelp of

04:49:41.340 --> 04:49:43.680
surprise, and so did the scavenger.

04:49:43.740 --> 04:49:46.139
But it didn't turn and run, and it didn't

04:49:46.139 --> 04:49:46.500
scream.

04:49:46.560 --> 04:49:49.200
It just stood there and blinked at her

04:49:49.200 --> 04:49:51.419
with enormous brown eyes.

04:49:51.479 --> 04:49:53.459
She reached up to her shoulder.

04:49:53.520 --> 04:49:55.380
Flower was still there.

04:49:55.439 --> 04:49:58.020
This scavenger in front of her was not

04:49:58.020 --> 04:49:58.799
flower.

04:49:58.860 --> 04:50:00.479
Sonny had never seen it before.

04:50:00.540 --> 04:50:03.720
Ah, Sonny thought.

04:50:03.779 --> 04:50:04.680
It's so cute.

04:50:04.740 --> 04:50:08.099
She guessed it was female, like flower

04:50:08.099 --> 04:50:10.139
although this one seemed smaller and

04:50:10.139 --> 04:50:10.680
younger.

04:50:10.740 --> 04:50:12.119
Seeing flower.

04:50:12.180 --> 04:50:14.099
That's probably why she was dreaming

04:50:14.099 --> 04:50:16.259
about scavengers, although it was

04:50:16.259 --> 04:50:18.180
surprising to dream up one she'd never

04:50:18.180 --> 04:50:18.599
seen before.

04:50:18.659 --> 04:50:21.659
A long, dark mane flowed from the

04:50:21.659 --> 04:50:23.580
scavenger's head down to the middle of

04:50:23.580 --> 04:50:26.279
her back, and she had the same adorable

04:50:26.279 --> 04:50:28.139
little nose and monkey features as

04:50:28.139 --> 04:50:31.080
Smolders pet, including the long, thin

04:50:31.080 --> 04:50:33.000
clever paws with no claws on the end.

04:50:33.000 --> 04:50:36.119
Sonny tilted her head at the scavenger's

04:50:36.119 --> 04:50:36.419
paws.

04:50:36.479 --> 04:50:37.619
Wait.

04:50:37.680 --> 04:50:39.299
She was holding something.

04:50:39.360 --> 04:50:41.939
Something about the size of an orange

04:50:41.939 --> 04:50:44.279
which caught the desert sunlight with a

04:50:44.279 --> 04:50:45.240
shimmer of blue.

04:50:45.299 --> 04:50:48.000
While Starflight had been trapped with a

04:50:48.000 --> 04:50:49.860
night wings, he'd found a way to

04:50:49.860 --> 04:50:51.599
communicate with his friends by dropping

04:50:51.599 --> 04:50:54.240
into their dreams, using an old animus

04:50:54.240 --> 04:50:56.759
touched sapphire called a dream visitor.

04:50:56.819 --> 04:50:58.860
Apparently, there were 3 of them out

04:50:58.860 --> 04:51:00.060
there in the world somewhere.

04:51:00.119 --> 04:51:02.279
And he had found one on the Nightwing

04:51:02.279 --> 04:51:02.639
Island.

04:51:02.700 --> 04:51:05.580
Glory had explained it to Sonny and Clay

04:51:05.580 --> 04:51:08.459
and tsunami, rolling her eyes, as if she

04:51:08.459 --> 04:51:09.779
couldn't believe they'd forgotten that

04:51:09.779 --> 04:51:12.479
one sentence in one scroll they'd studied

04:51:12.479 --> 04:51:12.959
years ago.

04:51:13.080 --> 04:51:15.599
Sometimes she could be as bad as

04:51:15.599 --> 04:51:17.580
Starfight, although nobody would ever

04:51:17.580 --> 04:51:18.479
dare tell her that.

04:51:18.540 --> 04:51:21.720
Sunny took a step toward the scavenger

04:51:21.720 --> 04:51:23.580
but she didn't even flinch back.

04:51:23.639 --> 04:51:26.819
Instead, she took a step towards Sonny

04:51:26.819 --> 04:51:28.380
holding out her free paw.

04:51:28.439 --> 04:51:30.840
She pointed at Flower and chattered

04:51:30.840 --> 04:51:31.319
something.

04:51:31.439 --> 04:51:33.360
Am I not dreaming?

04:51:33.479 --> 04:51:35.159
Is this real?

04:51:35.220 --> 04:51:37.979
Could a scavenger possibly have a dream

04:51:37.979 --> 04:51:38.580
visitor?

04:51:38.700 --> 04:51:41.340
How would it have gotten a dragon Jewel

04:51:41.340 --> 04:51:41.639
like that?

04:51:41.700 --> 04:51:45.119
She inhaled sharply, flaring her wings.

04:51:45.240 --> 04:51:48.720
The only possible way, by stealing it

04:51:48.720 --> 04:51:51.599
from the queen of the sand wings 20 years

04:51:51.599 --> 04:51:51.840
ago.

04:51:51.900 --> 04:51:54.180
Where did you get that?

04:51:54.180 --> 04:51:57.119
she asked, flicking her tail at the jewel

04:51:57.119 --> 04:51:58.319
in the scavenger's paw?

04:51:58.439 --> 04:52:01.080
The scavenger looked down at the dream

04:52:01.080 --> 04:52:01.680
visitor.

04:52:01.740 --> 04:52:04.319
Her eyes widened, and the desert sand

04:52:04.319 --> 04:52:06.000
behind her suddenly went blurry.

04:52:06.060 --> 04:52:08.340
Sonny caught a glimpse of black shapes

04:52:08.340 --> 04:52:10.680
around her. towering against a background

04:52:10.680 --> 04:52:12.060
of trees and moonlight.

04:52:12.119 --> 04:52:15.419
With a muffled yelp, the scavenger gave

04:52:15.419 --> 04:52:17.819
Sonny a fierce look, clutched the

04:52:17.819 --> 04:52:19.979
sapphire to her chest, and vanished.

04:52:20.040 --> 04:52:22.799
Wait, Sonny shouted.

04:52:22.860 --> 04:52:24.119
I need that treasure.

04:52:24.180 --> 04:52:26.400
She pounced on the spot where the

04:52:26.400 --> 04:52:28.860
scavenger had been, digging frantically

04:52:28.860 --> 04:52:31.439
in the sand, but of course, it was gone

04:52:31.439 --> 04:52:34.200
popping out of her dream as abruptly as

04:52:34.200 --> 04:52:36.599
it had popped in, and there was no way to

04:52:36.599 --> 04:52:36.959
get her back.

04:52:37.020 --> 04:52:39.240
The scavenger was the one who had the

04:52:39.240 --> 04:52:41.459
dream visitor, and therefore controlled

04:52:41.459 --> 04:52:43.020
where she went and who she saw.

04:52:43.139 --> 04:52:45.659
But why would she visit me?

04:52:45.720 --> 04:52:47.159
And how?

04:52:47.220 --> 04:52:49.619
I thought you could only visit the dreams

04:52:49.619 --> 04:52:51.240
of dragons you've met before.

04:52:51.299 --> 04:52:53.159
Or seen.

04:52:53.220 --> 04:52:55.500
She must have seen me somewhere.

04:52:55.560 --> 04:52:57.720
Sometime while we were traveling around

04:52:57.720 --> 04:53:00.240
Pyria, although I'm sure I didn't see

04:53:00.240 --> 04:53:00.540
her.

04:53:00.659 --> 04:53:04.380
Sunny sat down, sweeping her claws

04:53:04.380 --> 04:53:05.099
through the sand.

04:53:05.159 --> 04:53:08.880
So if I can figure out where, maybe I can

04:53:08.880 --> 04:53:09.299
find her.

04:53:09.360 --> 04:53:12.240
And the stolen sandwing treasure.

04:53:12.299 --> 04:53:15.299
She closed her eyes and concentrated

04:53:15.299 --> 04:53:17.520
trying to bring back those blurry dark

04:53:17.520 --> 04:53:19.439
shapes that she'd glimpsed behind the

04:53:19.439 --> 04:53:21.000
scavenger just for a moment.

04:53:21.119 --> 04:53:24.479
They'd looked familiar, and there had

04:53:24.479 --> 04:53:25.259
been trees too.

04:53:25.319 --> 04:53:28.319
So it wasn't the kingdom of the sea, or

04:53:28.319 --> 04:53:29.279
the sky kingdom.

04:53:29.340 --> 04:53:31.860
Were there scavengers in the rainforest?

04:53:31.919 --> 04:53:34.680
The trees didn't look tall enough.

04:53:34.740 --> 04:53:37.799
Sonny's eyes snapped open.

04:53:37.799 --> 04:53:40.619
The forest between the mountains and the

04:53:40.619 --> 04:53:43.080
desert, where I saw the ruins of the old

04:53:43.080 --> 04:53:44.040
scavenger den.

04:53:44.159 --> 04:53:47.759
The little scavenger was in the ruins.

04:53:47.880 --> 04:53:51.000
Which means now I know where to start

04:53:51.000 --> 04:53:51.479
looking.

04:53:51.540 --> 04:53:56.099
Part three.

04:53:56.159 --> 04:53:58.020
The Eye of Onyx.

04:53:58.080 --> 04:54:01.080
Chapter 18.

04:54:01.259 --> 04:54:04.500
It was still raining when Sonny woke up

04:54:04.500 --> 04:54:05.099
the next morning.

04:54:05.159 --> 04:54:07.680
She could hear the pitter patter at the

04:54:07.680 --> 04:54:09.959
far end of the passageway, and the breeze

04:54:09.959 --> 04:54:12.000
that gusted toward them smelled damp and

04:54:12.000 --> 04:54:12.540
fresh.

04:54:12.599 --> 04:54:15.240
But it came along with dim morning light

04:54:15.240 --> 04:54:17.880
and the wind wasn't as cold or fierce as

04:54:17.880 --> 04:54:18.900
it had been the night before.

04:54:18.959 --> 04:54:21.779
She felt sure that the worst of the storm

04:54:21.779 --> 04:54:22.319
had passed.

04:54:22.380 --> 04:54:25.979
She stood up and stretched, reaching her

04:54:25.979 --> 04:54:28.139
wings as wide and high as they would go

04:54:28.139 --> 04:54:30.060
and pressing her talons out in front of

04:54:30.060 --> 04:54:30.240
her.

04:54:30.299 --> 04:54:33.180
Everything felt less awful again

04:54:33.180 --> 04:54:33.540
somehow.

04:54:33.599 --> 04:54:36.000
Her father was still asleep.

04:54:36.060 --> 04:54:39.119
Sonny hesitated, half tempted to leave

04:54:39.119 --> 04:54:41.220
without saying goodbye, but she couldn't

04:54:41.220 --> 04:54:41.759
do that to him.

04:54:41.819 --> 04:54:43.979
Stone mover?

04:54:44.040 --> 04:54:46.860
She picked up the burnt stick she'd used

04:54:46.860 --> 04:54:49.200
for a torch, and nudged a part of his

04:54:49.200 --> 04:54:51.060
shoulder that didn't look entirely made

04:54:51.060 --> 04:54:51.599
of stone yet.

04:54:51.720 --> 04:54:54.540
Mm, he answered.

04:54:54.599 --> 04:54:57.000
His eyes slowly peeled open.

04:54:57.060 --> 04:54:59.700
I have to go, she said.

04:54:59.759 --> 04:55:01.799
Already.

04:55:01.860 --> 04:55:03.299
He sighed.

04:55:03.360 --> 04:55:05.459
This time long and smoky.

04:55:05.520 --> 04:55:07.139
So she had to step back to breathe.

04:55:07.200 --> 04:55:09.540
Can't you stay?

04:55:09.599 --> 04:55:11.520
It's really.

04:55:11.939 --> 04:55:14.340
Quiet. here.

04:55:14.400 --> 04:55:18.060
Really lonely, you mean, she thought.

04:55:18.119 --> 04:55:20.700
I'm sorry, she said.

04:55:20.759 --> 04:55:23.880
Then added with a burst of excitement, I

04:55:23.880 --> 04:55:25.259
think I've figured out how to end the

04:55:25.259 --> 04:55:25.619
war.

04:55:25.680 --> 04:55:28.439
I mean, I think I found a clue sort of.

04:55:28.500 --> 04:55:30.299
At least, I have an idea.

04:55:30.419 --> 04:55:33.240
Stone Mover's eyes were dark and

04:55:33.240 --> 04:55:33.659
puzzled.

04:55:33.720 --> 04:55:36.060
But, he said.

04:55:36.119 --> 04:55:37.560
But why?

04:55:37.619 --> 04:55:40.319
The prophecy isn't real.

04:55:40.380 --> 04:55:41.400
Remember?

04:55:41.459 --> 04:55:44.700
That doesn't matter, she said.

04:55:44.759 --> 04:55:47.040
I'm not doing it because a prophecy told

04:55:47.040 --> 04:55:47.459
me to.

04:55:47.520 --> 04:55:50.099
If I can stop the war, I think I should.

04:55:50.159 --> 04:55:52.380
It would be nice if someone else would

04:55:52.380 --> 04:55:54.180
take care of it, but maybe that's what

04:55:54.180 --> 04:55:55.139
everyone else is hoping.

04:55:55.200 --> 04:55:57.540
And maybe someone just has to do it.

04:55:57.599 --> 04:56:00.900
Hmm. said Stone Mover.

04:56:00.959 --> 04:56:04.919
Somehow, I suspect, it won't be that

04:56:04.919 --> 04:56:05.159
easy.

04:56:05.220 --> 04:56:07.500
Maybe it will be.

04:56:07.560 --> 04:56:09.060
Sonny said brightly.

04:56:09.119 --> 04:56:11.880
I'll find the eye of Onyx, and give it to

04:56:11.880 --> 04:56:13.680
one of the queens, and that's all it'll

04:56:13.680 --> 04:56:13.860
take.

04:56:13.919 --> 04:56:17.520
Oh, said Stone Mover.

04:56:17.580 --> 04:56:19.319
That'll never work.

04:56:19.380 --> 04:56:22.259
I thought you might say that, Sonny

04:56:22.259 --> 04:56:22.560
said.

04:56:22.619 --> 04:56:25.259
Don't worry, I'll come back and tell you

04:56:25.259 --> 04:56:27.479
all about it when it totally does work.

04:56:27.540 --> 04:56:30.479
She smiled at him, and she thought she

04:56:30.479 --> 04:56:32.580
saw the slightest movement of a maybe

04:56:32.580 --> 04:56:34.740
smile twitching around the corners of his

04:56:34.740 --> 04:56:34.919
mouth.

04:56:34.979 --> 04:56:39.419
I wish, he said, then stopped.

04:56:39.540 --> 04:56:42.299
I don't even know where to begin with

04:56:42.299 --> 04:56:43.799
wishing, Sonny thought.

04:56:43.860 --> 04:56:46.380
I wish the talons hadn't taken me?

04:56:46.439 --> 04:56:49.139
No, because then I wouldn't have grown up

04:56:49.139 --> 04:56:49.979
with my friends.

04:56:50.040 --> 04:56:52.860
I wish I'd been born looking like a real

04:56:52.860 --> 04:56:53.700
sandwing.

04:56:53.759 --> 04:56:56.459
No, because then I wouldn't be me.

04:56:56.520 --> 04:56:58.380
And I wouldn't want to be anyone else.

04:56:58.439 --> 04:57:01.799
Maybe I wish the prophecy were real.

04:57:01.860 --> 04:57:04.680
I wish I knew for sure that this would

04:57:04.680 --> 04:57:04.860
work.

04:57:04.919 --> 04:57:07.380
Sunny shook out her wings.

04:57:07.500 --> 04:57:10.080
Just wish me luck, she said.

04:57:10.139 --> 04:57:10.979
I'll see you soon.

04:57:11.040 --> 04:57:14.159
She could sense Stone Mover watching her

04:57:14.159 --> 04:57:16.259
gloomily as she headed up the passage

04:57:16.259 --> 04:57:18.779
toward the light and the quiet rain.

04:57:18.840 --> 04:57:20.939
She wondered what her mother would think

04:57:20.939 --> 04:57:23.639
of him now, how much he had changed since

04:57:23.639 --> 04:57:24.540
they knew each other.

04:57:24.599 --> 04:57:27.419
None of my friends got to know both of

04:57:27.419 --> 04:57:27.959
their parents.

04:57:28.020 --> 04:57:30.240
I'm lucky they're both still alive.

04:57:30.299 --> 04:57:32.580
And I'm lucky they're not that bad.

04:57:32.639 --> 04:57:35.099
But now that I've met both of them.

04:57:35.159 --> 04:57:37.319
I know which one I want to be like.

04:57:37.380 --> 04:57:40.619
I'm not going to sit in a cave and mope

04:57:40.619 --> 04:57:42.419
because things aren't the way I want them

04:57:42.419 --> 04:57:42.720
to be.

04:57:42.779 --> 04:57:44.759
I'm going to go make them happen.

04:57:44.819 --> 04:57:47.580
The way Thorn started the outlaws and

04:57:47.580 --> 04:57:48.180
searched for me.

04:57:48.240 --> 04:57:50.939
If she had given up, how would we ever

04:57:50.939 --> 04:57:51.599
have found each other?

04:57:51.659 --> 04:57:54.900
She'd have been just another dragon in

04:57:54.900 --> 04:57:55.799
the scorpion den?

04:57:55.860 --> 04:57:57.779
And maybe our paths would never have

04:57:57.779 --> 04:57:58.139
crossed.

04:57:58.259 --> 04:58:01.500
The passage ended in a shallow cave

04:58:01.500 --> 04:58:03.240
overlooking the mountain range below.

04:58:03.299 --> 04:58:06.240
The sun was rising in the east, which was

04:58:06.240 --> 04:58:08.639
also the direction of the rainforest, but

04:58:08.639 --> 04:58:10.200
the forest with the scavenger was to the

04:58:10.200 --> 04:58:10.619
west.

04:58:10.680 --> 04:58:12.479
Do I have time?

04:58:12.540 --> 04:58:15.060
What if Scarlet gets to the rainforest

04:58:15.060 --> 04:58:15.720
before I do?

04:58:15.779 --> 04:58:19.619
Sonny hesitated, with her claws gripping

04:58:19.619 --> 04:58:22.139
the ledge, and her wings outspread?

04:58:22.200 --> 04:58:24.060
Maybe Scarlett had been bluffing about

04:58:24.060 --> 04:58:25.979
knowing where the dragonettes were.

04:58:26.040 --> 04:58:27.599
How would she guess they were in the

04:58:27.599 --> 04:58:29.880
rainforest, if no one else had found them

04:58:29.880 --> 04:58:30.060
there?

04:58:30.119 --> 04:58:32.340
Maybe she was only trying to scare

04:58:32.340 --> 04:58:32.880
Sonny.

04:58:32.939 --> 04:58:35.880
Well, she did a good job of that.

04:58:35.939 --> 04:58:39.119
Too bad I don't have the obsidian mirror

04:58:39.119 --> 04:58:39.479
anymore.

04:58:39.540 --> 04:58:41.939
It'd be useful to know what Scarlet is

04:58:41.939 --> 04:58:42.119
doing.

04:58:42.180 --> 04:58:44.819
Maybe I should go warn my friends and

04:58:44.819 --> 04:58:45.479
then come back.

04:58:45.540 --> 04:58:48.240
But what if the scavenger leaves the

04:58:48.240 --> 04:58:48.720
ruins?

04:58:48.779 --> 04:58:51.299
This could be my only chance to find the

04:58:51.299 --> 04:58:52.919
eye of onyx and stop the war.

04:58:52.979 --> 04:58:56.340
It was a detour, but she had to risk it.

04:58:56.400 --> 04:58:59.819
She leaned forward and plummeted down the

04:58:59.819 --> 04:59:02.220
mountainside, soaring west toward the

04:59:02.220 --> 04:59:05.159
scavenger ruins, and, she hoped, the

04:59:05.159 --> 04:59:05.759
missing treasure.

04:59:05.819 --> 04:59:09.900
The burnt village was easy to spot from

04:59:09.900 --> 04:59:13.139
the air, a dark gash, stark and black

04:59:13.139 --> 04:59:15.720
against the surrounding greenery, sunny

04:59:15.720 --> 04:59:18.119
spiraled toward it, studying the trees

04:59:18.119 --> 04:59:20.340
with our sharp eyes, and looking for any

04:59:20.340 --> 04:59:21.840
movement that might be a scavenger.

04:59:21.900 --> 04:59:25.500
Nothing so far, but it was late afternoon

04:59:25.500 --> 04:59:27.419
and Sonny wasn't even sure whether

04:59:27.419 --> 04:59:29.880
scavengers were normally nocturnal or

04:59:29.880 --> 04:59:31.259
preferred the day.

04:59:31.319 --> 04:59:34.500
She landed lightly in a cloud of ash that

04:59:34.500 --> 04:59:35.759
smelled like a wood fire.

04:59:35.819 --> 04:59:39.060
The ruins were still and deserted, and

04:59:39.060 --> 04:59:40.619
Sonny wondered uneasily if she had been

04:59:40.619 --> 04:59:40.799
wrong.

04:59:40.860 --> 04:59:43.439
What if the scavenger wasn't here?

04:59:43.500 --> 04:59:45.720
Or what if she'd been here, but was now

04:59:45.720 --> 04:59:47.459
gone, and Sunny had missed her?

04:59:47.520 --> 04:59:49.860
Think positive.

04:59:49.979 --> 04:59:54.299
She paced the entire perimeter of the den

04:59:54.299 --> 04:59:56.040
searching every structure with even half

04:59:56.040 --> 04:59:58.919
a wall still standing, every noise made

04:59:58.919 --> 05:00:01.500
her freeze and listen, her head cocked to

05:00:01.500 --> 05:00:03.840
the side, but it was always squirrels in

05:00:03.840 --> 05:00:05.939
the nearby trees, where other little

05:00:05.939 --> 05:00:07.979
creatures scurrying in the underbrush

05:00:07.979 --> 05:00:10.380
which reminded her that she was hungry.

05:00:10.439 --> 05:00:13.139
So she caught a mouse and ate it, sitting

05:00:13.139 --> 05:00:15.240
on the old bell platform at the center of

05:00:15.240 --> 05:00:15.659
the village.

05:00:15.720 --> 05:00:19.860
Well, there was no one here now, but that

05:00:19.860 --> 05:00:21.180
didn't mean she should give up.

05:00:21.240 --> 05:00:23.220
Maybe the scavenger would return later

05:00:23.220 --> 05:00:26.279
except she probably wouldn't if she

05:00:26.279 --> 05:00:28.080
spotted a dragon prowling through the

05:00:28.080 --> 05:00:31.500
ruins, but then again, if she'd stolen

05:00:31.500 --> 05:00:33.540
the treasure from the sand wings, that

05:00:33.540 --> 05:00:35.819
meant she had to be fairly bold and

05:00:35.819 --> 05:00:36.659
reasonably stupid.

05:00:36.779 --> 05:00:40.560
Still, Sonny decided to hide, just in

05:00:40.560 --> 05:00:40.740
case.

05:00:40.799 --> 05:00:43.919
She found a tree with thick, overlapping

05:00:43.919 --> 05:00:46.740
leaves and wide branches, and settled

05:00:46.740 --> 05:00:48.779
into the crook of the trunk, keeping a

05:00:48.779 --> 05:00:50.099
sharp eye on the burnt village.

05:00:50.159 --> 05:00:52.259
From here, she had a good view of most of

05:00:52.259 --> 05:00:54.060
it, and she spent the rest of the day

05:00:54.060 --> 05:00:55.740
watching and waiting.

05:00:55.799 --> 05:00:59.639
By nightfall, as one of the moons climbed

05:00:59.639 --> 05:01:02.159
cheerily up the sky, Sonny had begun to

05:01:02.159 --> 05:01:05.340
doubt herself again, I should just go, I

05:01:05.340 --> 05:01:06.240
don't have time to sit here.

05:01:06.299 --> 05:01:08.220
I have to get to my friends in the

05:01:08.220 --> 05:01:08.759
rainforest.

05:01:08.819 --> 05:01:12.720
Besides, if she comes during the night, I

05:01:12.720 --> 05:01:15.240
won't be able to see her anyway, if only

05:01:15.240 --> 05:01:17.099
I could see in the dark like tsunami.

05:01:17.159 --> 05:01:20.759
She dug her claws into the bark, forcing

05:01:20.759 --> 05:01:21.779
herself to be patient.

05:01:21.840 --> 05:01:24.720
If the Eye of Onyx was nearby, it was

05:01:24.720 --> 05:01:25.380
worth waiting for.

05:01:25.439 --> 05:01:28.319
Once she had that, she'd have a way to

05:01:28.319 --> 05:01:28.919
end the war.

05:01:28.979 --> 05:01:32.340
Which won't stop Scarlet from wanting to

05:01:32.340 --> 05:01:33.419
kill us, of course.

05:01:33.479 --> 05:01:36.180
She stared hard at the village.

05:01:36.240 --> 05:01:39.119
Now a shadowy mass of odd lumps and

05:01:39.119 --> 05:01:41.580
pointy shapes, overlaid with a silvery

05:01:41.580 --> 05:01:42.060
moonlight.

05:01:42.180 --> 05:01:43.619
Was that?

05:01:43.740 --> 05:01:46.080
Something was moving in the forest

05:01:46.080 --> 05:01:47.099
outside the ruins.

05:01:47.159 --> 05:01:50.279
A small light bobbed up and down, not far

05:01:50.279 --> 05:01:53.040
from the ground, blinking in and out as

05:01:53.040 --> 05:01:54.599
it went behind trees and bushes.

05:01:54.659 --> 05:01:57.659
Now her ears could pick out the sound of

05:01:57.659 --> 05:01:58.259
footsteps.

05:01:58.319 --> 05:01:59.819
They were very quiet.

05:01:59.939 --> 05:02:03.060
But here and there a twig snapped, and

05:02:03.060 --> 05:02:05.459
she recognized the noise of paws brushing

05:02:05.459 --> 05:02:05.939
through leaves.

05:02:06.000 --> 05:02:07.860
Softly.

05:02:07.919 --> 05:02:10.560
She unwound her tail from the branch and

05:02:10.560 --> 05:02:11.700
slithered down the trunk.

05:02:11.759 --> 05:02:14.099
She crept silently through the dark

05:02:14.099 --> 05:02:16.979
village toward the light as it left the

05:02:16.979 --> 05:02:18.959
trees and floated toward a set of

05:02:18.959 --> 05:02:20.400
collapsed stone stairs.

05:02:20.459 --> 05:02:22.380
If Sunny remembered right from her

05:02:22.380 --> 05:02:23.819
earlier tour of the ruins.

05:02:23.880 --> 05:02:25.560
There were 2 of them.

05:02:25.619 --> 05:02:29.279
Two scavengers, one of them with short

05:02:29.279 --> 05:02:31.560
fluffy hair, but the other one's hair was

05:02:31.560 --> 05:02:34.139
long and she moved in a quick, confident

05:02:34.139 --> 05:02:34.380
way.

05:02:34.439 --> 05:02:37.560
Sonny was short, was the same scavenger

05:02:37.560 --> 05:02:38.099
from her dream.

05:02:38.159 --> 05:02:41.279
She waited until they climbed onto the

05:02:41.279 --> 05:02:42.599
steps and sat down.

05:02:42.659 --> 05:02:45.599
They were warbling in low tones that

05:02:45.599 --> 05:02:47.220
sounded like some of the rainforest

05:02:47.220 --> 05:02:49.319
monkeys, and the one with the long hair

05:02:49.319 --> 05:02:52.080
sometimes waved her paws, as if she were

05:02:52.080 --> 05:02:53.099
drawing a picture in the air.

05:02:53.159 --> 05:02:56.700
Flower did the same thing, Sunny

05:02:56.700 --> 05:02:57.360
remembered.

05:02:57.419 --> 05:03:00.599
Now, the trick would be to approach them

05:03:00.599 --> 05:03:02.459
and get the treasure without scaring them

05:03:02.459 --> 05:03:04.319
off, and without getting attacked.

05:03:04.380 --> 05:03:07.020
They didn't look like they were carrying

05:03:07.020 --> 05:03:09.119
any sharp little weapons, but you never

05:03:09.119 --> 05:03:10.979
knew with scavengers, according to the

05:03:10.979 --> 05:03:11.459
scrolls.

05:03:11.520 --> 05:03:14.580
And if these 2 had stolen the treasure

05:03:14.580 --> 05:03:17.880
that meant they'd killed Queen Oasis, so

05:03:17.880 --> 05:03:19.080
they could be very dangerous.

05:03:19.139 --> 05:03:22.319
She paused in the shadows for a moment

05:03:22.319 --> 05:03:25.500
considering, and finally decided a direct

05:03:25.500 --> 05:03:26.639
approach was the only option.

05:03:26.700 --> 05:03:31.259
Don't run away, she said, stepping out in

05:03:31.259 --> 05:03:33.060
front of them and spreading her wings.

05:03:33.180 --> 05:03:36.119
Both scavengers yelled with fright, and

05:03:36.119 --> 05:03:37.259
promptly tried to run away.

05:03:37.319 --> 05:03:40.380
Sonny leaped into the air and landed in

05:03:40.380 --> 05:03:41.700
front of the scavenger from her dream.

05:03:41.759 --> 05:03:43.380
That was the one she wanted.

05:03:43.439 --> 05:03:48.060
I said, don't run away, Sonny barked, even

05:03:48.060 --> 05:03:49.680
though she knew the scavenger couldn't

05:03:49.680 --> 05:03:50.220
understand her.

05:03:50.279 --> 05:03:52.259
Hey, come back.

05:03:52.380 --> 05:03:54.959
She flung her tail out, and tripped the

05:03:54.959 --> 05:03:56.520
little creature as it bolted in another

05:03:56.520 --> 05:03:56.880
direction.

05:03:56.939 --> 05:04:00.060
I won't eat you, I promise.

05:04:00.119 --> 05:04:02.819
She pounced, and managed to trap the

05:04:02.819 --> 05:04:04.439
scavenger between her front talons.

05:04:04.500 --> 05:04:07.259
The 2nd scavenger suddenly came running

05:04:07.259 --> 05:04:09.299
out of the ruins and threw something at

05:04:09.299 --> 05:04:09.540
her.

05:04:09.599 --> 05:04:11.880
This turned out to be the tiny lamp

05:04:11.880 --> 05:04:14.099
they'd been carrying, which bounced off

05:04:14.099 --> 05:04:16.380
Sunny's scales, but left a stinging burn

05:04:16.380 --> 05:04:17.040
where it hit.

05:04:17.099 --> 05:04:18.900
Ouch.

05:04:18.959 --> 05:04:20.220
Sonny roared.

05:04:20.279 --> 05:04:21.240
All right.

05:04:21.299 --> 05:04:23.279
I might eat you if you keep doing that.

05:04:23.340 --> 05:04:26.459
She swept her tail around and knocked the

05:04:26.459 --> 05:04:28.799
2nd scavenger over, then picked up the

05:04:28.799 --> 05:04:30.900
1st scavenger and hopped a step back

05:04:30.900 --> 05:04:31.680
growling.

05:04:31.740 --> 05:04:34.740
The scavenger between her claws was

05:04:34.740 --> 05:04:36.419
kicking and wriggling, and being

05:04:36.419 --> 05:04:37.259
generally impossible.

05:04:37.319 --> 05:04:39.959
Sonny was trying really hard to hold it

05:04:39.959 --> 05:04:42.119
gently, but it was like hanging on to a

05:04:42.119 --> 05:04:42.599
moonbeam.

05:04:42.720 --> 05:04:45.119
And the other scavenger was already

05:04:45.119 --> 05:04:47.400
struggling back upright, probably to

05:04:47.400 --> 05:04:48.060
attack her again.

05:04:48.119 --> 05:04:51.119
Sonny looked around and spotted a

05:04:51.119 --> 05:04:52.799
building that hadn't burned as badly as

05:04:52.799 --> 05:04:53.639
the rest of them.

05:04:53.880 --> 05:04:56.819
Two of the walls still stood, forming a

05:04:56.819 --> 05:04:58.619
corner made of heavy round stones.

05:04:58.680 --> 05:05:02.040
The walls were as tall as Seni's head, too

05:05:02.040 --> 05:05:03.900
tall for a little scavenger to jump off

05:05:03.900 --> 05:05:06.180
unless they were more like frogs than

05:05:06.180 --> 05:05:06.959
Sonny thought they were.

05:05:07.080 --> 05:05:10.319
She deposited the 1st scavenger on top of

05:05:10.319 --> 05:05:13.439
the wall, then whipped around, seized the

05:05:13.439 --> 05:05:15.479
2nd scavenger, and stuck him up there as

05:05:15.479 --> 05:05:15.720
well.

05:05:15.779 --> 05:05:18.479
They both made little yelping sounds and

05:05:18.479 --> 05:05:19.380
clung to the stones.

05:05:19.439 --> 05:05:22.200
There, Sonny said.

05:05:22.259 --> 05:05:24.000
Now you can't run away.

05:05:24.060 --> 05:05:26.759
She sat down and folded her wings back.

05:05:26.819 --> 05:05:29.819
So, where is the treasure?

05:05:29.880 --> 05:05:32.459
Their big eyes stared back at her.

05:05:32.520 --> 05:05:35.459
Sunny reached for a branch, set it on

05:05:35.459 --> 05:05:37.200
fire, and stuck it upright in the ground

05:05:37.200 --> 05:05:38.400
so she could see them better.

05:05:38.520 --> 05:05:41.400
The scavenger from her dream pointed at

05:05:41.400 --> 05:05:43.500
Sonny, and chattered something at the

05:05:43.500 --> 05:05:44.279
other scavenger.

05:05:44.340 --> 05:05:47.099
If she were my pet, I could give her a

05:05:47.099 --> 05:05:48.540
name, Sonny thought.

05:05:48.659 --> 05:05:52.080
Maybe something like holler for all that

05:05:52.080 --> 05:05:52.979
noise she was making.

05:05:53.040 --> 05:05:56.040
And the other one could be fluffy for his

05:05:56.040 --> 05:05:56.220
hair.

05:05:56.279 --> 05:06:00.180
She smiled, holler and fluffy, totally

05:06:00.180 --> 05:06:00.720
cute.

05:06:00.779 --> 05:06:03.419
But also maybe totally responsible for

05:06:03.419 --> 05:06:05.639
this whole war if they were the ones who

05:06:05.639 --> 05:06:06.599
stole the treasure.

05:06:06.779 --> 05:06:09.119
They looked a little small to be treasure

05:06:09.119 --> 05:06:12.000
thieves, but then all scavengers were too

05:06:12.000 --> 05:06:13.259
small to be trying something that

05:06:13.259 --> 05:06:14.459
idiotic.

05:06:14.520 --> 05:06:17.400
The dream visitor, Sonny said.

05:06:17.459 --> 05:06:19.680
Cupping her front talons together as if

05:06:19.680 --> 05:06:20.700
she were holding a jewel.

05:06:20.759 --> 05:06:22.860
The one you had in my dream?

05:06:22.979 --> 05:06:24.299
Where is it?

05:06:24.419 --> 05:06:26.159
She tilted her head.

05:06:26.220 --> 05:06:29.700
Holler and Fluffy started arguing, or at

05:06:29.700 --> 05:06:31.139
least it certainly looked that way

05:06:31.139 --> 05:06:33.659
raising their voices and barking at each

05:06:33.659 --> 05:06:34.860
other, waving their paws.

05:06:34.919 --> 05:06:38.340
Sunny watched this for a moment, then

05:06:38.340 --> 05:06:40.500
stuck her claw between them and said, all

05:06:40.500 --> 05:06:42.180
right, you're adorable, but that's

05:06:42.180 --> 05:06:42.299
enough.

05:06:42.419 --> 05:06:45.180
Dream visitor, treasure?

05:06:45.240 --> 05:06:46.080
Now?

05:06:46.139 --> 05:06:49.080
She rested her open talons between them.

05:06:49.139 --> 05:06:52.680
Holler hesitated, looking at Fluffy, and

05:06:52.680 --> 05:06:54.360
then reached into a pocket of the fabric

05:06:54.360 --> 05:06:55.500
that was draped around her.

05:06:55.560 --> 05:06:57.720
She pulled out the sapphire and dropped

05:06:57.720 --> 05:06:58.979
it into Sonny's palm.

05:06:59.040 --> 05:07:02.159
Whoa, Sonny said.

05:07:02.220 --> 05:07:03.900
She hadn't actually expected that to

05:07:03.900 --> 05:07:04.380
work.

05:07:04.439 --> 05:07:06.479
She raised the jewel to her eye and

05:07:06.479 --> 05:07:06.959
studied it.

05:07:07.080 --> 05:07:09.419
It certainly looked like the animus

05:07:09.419 --> 05:07:10.740
touched gems from the scroll.

05:07:10.799 --> 05:07:14.040
Thank you, Sonny said to Holler.

05:07:14.099 --> 05:07:15.299
Where's the rest?

05:07:15.360 --> 05:07:17.639
Holler blinked at her.

05:07:17.700 --> 05:07:20.279
Um, Sonny said.

05:07:20.340 --> 05:07:22.259
She took the jewel and put it on the

05:07:22.259 --> 05:07:24.540
ground, then drew a large circle around

05:07:24.540 --> 05:07:27.419
it in the ashes, and mimed adding more

05:07:27.419 --> 05:07:28.319
jewels to the circle.

05:07:28.380 --> 05:07:31.259
Then she spread her wings around it, and

05:07:31.259 --> 05:07:33.000
waved at the imaginary pile of treasure.

05:07:33.060 --> 05:07:36.419
The rest of the treasure that you stole

05:07:36.419 --> 05:07:37.979
where this came from?

05:07:38.099 --> 05:07:40.740
She picked up the dream visitor and waved

05:07:40.740 --> 05:07:41.040
it again.

05:07:41.099 --> 05:07:44.400
Fluffy indicated the imaginary treasure

05:07:44.400 --> 05:07:46.080
embarked something at Holler.

05:07:46.619 --> 05:07:48.900
Holler ignored him, pointed over Sunny's

05:07:48.900 --> 05:07:51.119
shoulder, and said something to her in

05:07:51.119 --> 05:07:52.799
what really sounded like an imperious

05:07:52.799 --> 05:07:55.439
tone of voice, if it wasn't too crazy to

05:07:55.439 --> 05:07:57.240
think about scavengers trying to order

05:07:57.240 --> 05:07:58.200
dragons around.

05:07:58.319 --> 05:08:01.020
Sonny narrowed her eyes at Holler.

05:08:01.080 --> 05:08:02.880
Now that she had a moment to think about

05:08:02.880 --> 05:08:05.459
it, she could see that both scavengers

05:08:05.459 --> 05:08:06.599
were smaller than flour.

05:08:06.659 --> 05:08:09.659
They didn't seem entirely full grown.

05:08:09.720 --> 05:08:12.360
Scavengers reached their full size before

05:08:12.360 --> 05:08:13.799
20 years, didn't they?

05:08:13.860 --> 05:08:15.900
So if the treasure had been stolen 20

05:08:15.900 --> 05:08:18.419
years ago, surely it couldn't have been

05:08:18.419 --> 05:08:19.439
these 2 who took it.

05:08:19.500 --> 05:08:23.040
But there was the dream visitor, real and

05:08:23.040 --> 05:08:24.240
heavy in her claws.

05:08:24.299 --> 05:08:27.119
Fluffy began chattering vigorously at

05:08:27.119 --> 05:08:27.540
Sonny.

05:08:27.599 --> 05:08:29.700
Holler grabbed his shoulder and tried to

05:08:29.700 --> 05:08:31.319
stop him, but he fended her off.

05:08:31.380 --> 05:08:33.959
He pointed at the imaginary pile of

05:08:33.959 --> 05:08:36.360
treasure, and then at himself, and then

05:08:36.360 --> 05:08:36.959
at Sonny.

05:08:37.020 --> 05:08:39.540
That, me, ew.

05:08:39.599 --> 05:08:41.939
And then he mimed picking something up

05:08:41.939 --> 05:08:42.959
and giving it to Sonny.

05:08:43.080 --> 05:08:45.900
Is he offering to bring me the treasure?

05:08:46.020 --> 05:08:48.180
Sunny's hopes rose.

05:08:48.240 --> 05:08:50.880
Holler stamped her foot and snapped at

05:08:50.880 --> 05:08:53.040
him, he put his paws on his hips and

05:08:53.040 --> 05:08:53.639
yapped back.

05:08:53.700 --> 05:08:57.180
I have an excellent idea, Sonny

05:08:57.180 --> 05:08:57.659
announced.

05:08:57.720 --> 05:08:59.819
She gently scooped her claws around

05:08:59.819 --> 05:09:02.159
Fluffy and lifted him off the wall onto

05:09:02.159 --> 05:09:03.419
the ground.

05:09:03.479 --> 05:09:05.580
He yelled and flapped around a bit until

05:09:05.580 --> 05:09:07.860
she let him go and stepped back, and then

05:09:07.860 --> 05:09:09.540
he stopped, watching her warily.

05:09:09.599 --> 05:09:13.319
You go get the rest of the treasure, and

05:09:13.319 --> 05:09:15.599
when you come give it to me, you can have

05:09:15.599 --> 05:09:16.259
Hollerback.

05:09:16.319 --> 05:09:18.900
Sonny tapped holler lightly on the head.

05:09:19.020 --> 05:09:21.180
This took a while to sink in.

05:09:21.240 --> 05:09:24.360
Sonny pointed to the forest, held up the

05:09:24.360 --> 05:09:26.759
dream visitor, pointed to Fluffy and

05:09:26.759 --> 05:09:28.979
Holler, in several different combinations

05:09:28.979 --> 05:09:31.139
until finally Fluffy took a few steps

05:09:31.139 --> 05:09:33.779
toward the trees, calling up to holler

05:09:33.779 --> 05:09:36.540
she yapped back at him, and he bobbed his

05:09:36.540 --> 05:09:38.639
fluffy, shaggy head, then hurried off

05:09:38.639 --> 05:09:39.180
into the darkness.

05:09:39.240 --> 05:09:41.639
I hope this works.

05:09:41.700 --> 05:09:43.020
Sonny said to Holler.

05:09:43.080 --> 05:09:44.939
I'm not actually going to eat you or

05:09:44.939 --> 05:09:45.419
anything.

05:09:45.479 --> 05:09:46.740
Even if he doesn't come back.

05:09:46.799 --> 05:09:49.080
Yibble, yibble, yibble.

05:09:49.139 --> 05:09:51.299
Holler said to Sonny, or at least that's

05:09:51.299 --> 05:09:51.900
what it sounded like.

05:09:51.959 --> 05:09:55.560
You're very cute, but you're all a lot of

05:09:55.560 --> 05:09:57.240
trouble, Sonny said.

05:09:57.299 --> 05:09:58.619
Yibble.

05:09:58.680 --> 05:09:59.880
Yibble yibble.

05:09:59.939 --> 05:10:02.340
Holler shouted, pointing over Sonny's

05:10:02.340 --> 05:10:02.880
shoulder again.

05:10:02.939 --> 05:10:05.939
Or maybe she was pointing at Sonny's

05:10:05.939 --> 05:10:07.860
shoulder, where Flower had been sitting

05:10:07.860 --> 05:10:09.000
in Sonny's dream.

05:10:09.060 --> 05:10:12.599
Oh, Sonny said, thinking of Glory's

05:10:12.599 --> 05:10:13.020
sloth.

05:10:13.080 --> 05:10:14.220
Do you want a ride?

05:10:14.279 --> 05:10:15.419
Are you sure?

05:10:15.479 --> 05:10:17.400
Sonny flicked her tail.

05:10:17.459 --> 05:10:18.720
You won't be scared?

05:10:18.779 --> 05:10:20.580
You bull?

05:10:20.639 --> 05:10:21.659
Holler demanded.

05:10:21.720 --> 05:10:25.380
All right, Sonny said, scooping her up.

05:10:25.439 --> 05:10:27.720
Holler shrieked, with a little more

05:10:27.720 --> 05:10:29.400
terror than Sunny thought was necessary

05:10:29.400 --> 05:10:31.740
considering she'd asked for this.

05:10:31.799 --> 05:10:34.860
As Sonny set her on her shoulder, Holler

05:10:34.860 --> 05:10:36.779
grabbed Sonny's neck and balanced herself

05:10:36.779 --> 05:10:39.180
across her scales, making startled

05:10:39.180 --> 05:10:40.020
yelping noises.

05:10:40.080 --> 05:10:44.340
Hold on tight, Sonny said, swinging her

05:10:44.340 --> 05:10:45.840
head around to check that Holler was

05:10:45.840 --> 05:10:46.740
firmly in place.

05:10:46.799 --> 05:10:49.139
She spread her wings and leaped into the

05:10:49.139 --> 05:10:49.319
sky.

05:10:49.380 --> 05:10:52.919
It was a clear starry night.

05:10:52.979 --> 05:10:55.560
All the clouds from yesterday's storm had

05:10:55.560 --> 05:10:57.840
blown away, and 2 of the moons were half

05:10:57.840 --> 05:10:59.099
full in the sky overhead.

05:10:59.159 --> 05:11:01.919
The rustling leaves below them looked

05:11:01.919 --> 05:11:03.599
like waves rippling on the sea.

05:11:03.659 --> 05:11:07.560
Sunny soared up in a long arc, swooped

05:11:07.560 --> 05:11:09.720
down across the forest, and veered back

05:11:09.720 --> 05:11:10.259
around again.

05:11:10.319 --> 05:11:13.380
The scavenger was quiet on her back, which

05:11:13.380 --> 05:11:14.819
was much preferable to shrieking.

05:11:14.880 --> 05:11:18.479
I hope Fluffy understood me, Sonny

05:11:18.479 --> 05:11:18.720
thought.

05:11:18.779 --> 05:11:21.240
I hope he hasn't gone to get a pack of

05:11:21.240 --> 05:11:23.040
other scavengers with pointy things.

05:11:23.099 --> 05:11:25.979
Imagine, if he really does come back with

05:11:25.979 --> 05:11:28.319
a missing treasure, I could be moments

05:11:28.319 --> 05:11:30.360
away from holding the eye of onyx.

05:11:30.419 --> 05:11:34.020
The eye of onyx, and power over the whole

05:11:34.020 --> 05:11:35.099
kingdom of sand.

05:11:35.159 --> 05:11:39.299
Sunny shivered from horns to tail, and

05:11:39.299 --> 05:11:40.860
felt the scavenger clutch her neck

05:11:40.860 --> 05:11:41.220
tighter.

05:11:41.279 --> 05:11:44.700
Whoever holds the eye could be queen.

05:11:44.759 --> 05:11:46.259
Even I could be queen.

05:11:46.319 --> 05:11:48.599
That would be one way to end the war.

05:11:48.659 --> 05:11:51.840
None of the 3 sisters wins, and I take

05:11:51.840 --> 05:11:52.560
the throne.

05:11:52.619 --> 05:11:55.139
Sonny, Queen of the Sandwings.

05:11:55.200 --> 05:11:58.500
Of course, that would leave 3 dragons

05:11:58.500 --> 05:12:01.080
with a single unified mission, kill me.

05:12:01.139 --> 05:12:04.619
It was scary, but it gave her an eerie

05:12:04.619 --> 05:12:05.639
thrill to think about too.

05:12:05.700 --> 05:12:08.459
What if that was her real destiny?

05:12:08.459 --> 05:12:10.139
To rule the sand wings?

05:12:10.259 --> 05:12:13.619
She glanced down at the forest and saw a

05:12:13.619 --> 05:12:15.360
movement near the torch she had lit.

05:12:15.419 --> 05:12:16.380
Fluffy was back.

05:12:16.500 --> 05:12:18.840
She tucked in her wings and dove toward

05:12:18.840 --> 05:12:21.000
the ruins, landing with a thump right in

05:12:21.000 --> 05:12:21.419
front of him.

05:12:21.479 --> 05:12:24.119
Fluffy jumped back with a yell.

05:12:24.180 --> 05:12:27.060
His eyes widened when he saw holler on

05:12:27.060 --> 05:12:29.159
Sonny's shoulder, and he launched into

05:12:29.159 --> 05:12:31.619
another shouting fit, practically hopping

05:12:31.619 --> 05:12:32.040
up and down.

05:12:32.099 --> 05:12:34.740
Holler slid off Sonny's back and joined

05:12:34.740 --> 05:12:34.919
in.

05:12:34.979 --> 05:12:37.680
Sunny wasn't interested in their little

05:12:37.680 --> 05:12:38.819
monkey squabble, though.

05:12:38.880 --> 05:12:41.279
She was interested in the bulging canvas

05:12:41.279 --> 05:12:42.779
sack that Fluffy was clutching.

05:12:42.840 --> 05:12:45.180
Reaching over Holler's head.

05:12:45.240 --> 05:12:47.220
She deftly lifted the sack out of his

05:12:47.220 --> 05:12:47.520
paws.

05:12:47.639 --> 05:12:50.220
She turned toward the firelight and

05:12:50.220 --> 05:12:52.619
fidgeting with excitement, emptied the

05:12:52.619 --> 05:12:54.119
contents of the sack onto the ground.

05:12:54.180 --> 05:12:58.020
Gold coins and jewels tumbled out and

05:12:58.020 --> 05:13:00.240
bounced through the ashes, clinking and

05:13:00.240 --> 05:13:01.619
clattering into a small pile.

05:13:01.680 --> 05:13:04.680
Most of the jewels were tiny, none as big

05:13:04.680 --> 05:13:06.840
as the dream visitor, and barely worth

05:13:06.840 --> 05:13:07.319
stealing.

05:13:07.380 --> 05:13:09.959
The biggest object was a statue of a

05:13:09.959 --> 05:13:12.360
dragon carved from blue stone, with

05:13:12.360 --> 05:13:13.439
emeralds for eyes.

05:13:13.500 --> 05:13:16.860
The Lazolite dragon, Sunny Guest

05:13:16.860 --> 05:13:18.299
remembering the scrolls about the missing

05:13:18.299 --> 05:13:18.659
treasure.

05:13:18.720 --> 05:13:21.779
She sifted through the pile, her heart

05:13:21.779 --> 05:13:22.319
sinking.

05:13:22.380 --> 05:13:25.080
She knew the answer at 1st glance, but

05:13:25.080 --> 05:13:27.299
she dug through it all, examining every

05:13:27.299 --> 05:13:29.580
coin, just to be sure she was right.

05:13:29.639 --> 05:13:31.560
She was.

05:13:31.619 --> 05:13:34.259
The Eye of Onyx was not there.

05:13:34.319 --> 05:13:38.819
Chapter 19.

05:13:39.000 --> 05:13:43.319
This isn't all of it, Sonny cried

05:13:43.380 --> 05:13:45.360
whipping around to face the scavengers.

05:13:45.419 --> 05:13:47.580
Where's the eye?

05:13:47.639 --> 05:13:48.240
Why isn't it here?

05:13:48.360 --> 05:13:51.479
They stopped chattering immediately, and

05:13:51.479 --> 05:13:53.459
jumped away from her, holding their paws

05:13:53.459 --> 05:13:53.939
up in the air.

05:13:54.060 --> 05:13:56.819
Fluffy pointed at the sack and Yibble

05:13:56.819 --> 05:13:57.779
yibbled frantically.

05:13:57.840 --> 05:13:59.700
You must have it.

05:13:59.759 --> 05:14:01.020
Where else could it be?

05:14:01.080 --> 05:14:03.779
Sonny started pacing back and forth.

05:14:03.840 --> 05:14:05.939
She could feel smoke rising from her

05:14:05.939 --> 05:14:07.680
snout, and she knew she was probably

05:14:07.680 --> 05:14:09.959
scaring the scavengers, but they didn't

05:14:09.959 --> 05:14:10.500
run away.

05:14:10.619 --> 05:14:12.720
I need the eye of onyx.

05:14:12.779 --> 05:14:14.759
It's my one chance to end the war.

05:14:14.819 --> 05:14:17.099
She stopped and faced them again.

05:14:17.159 --> 05:14:19.680
How am I supposed to end the war without

05:14:19.680 --> 05:14:19.979
it?

05:14:20.040 --> 05:14:21.720
Yibble?

05:14:21.779 --> 05:14:23.159
Holler said tentatively.

05:14:23.220 --> 05:14:24.659
Yibble.

05:14:24.779 --> 05:14:25.919
Yibble?

05:14:25.979 --> 05:14:29.340
Well said, Sonny said to her, that's very

05:14:29.340 --> 05:14:29.819
helpful.

05:14:29.939 --> 05:14:32.700
She sat down and frowned crossly at the

05:14:32.700 --> 05:14:33.840
pathetic pile of treasure.

05:14:33.959 --> 05:14:35.639
Ribble.

05:14:35.700 --> 05:14:36.360
Yibble?

05:14:36.479 --> 05:14:37.860
Fluffy said to holler.

05:14:37.919 --> 05:14:40.799
Herbal yobble, she snapped back.

05:14:40.860 --> 05:14:44.279
Someone else must have it, Sonny said

05:14:44.279 --> 05:14:45.360
thinking aloud.

05:14:45.419 --> 05:14:48.060
If you had it, you'd have brought it to

05:14:48.060 --> 05:14:49.560
me, because you were worried about

05:14:49.560 --> 05:14:50.040
Holler.

05:14:50.099 --> 05:14:52.020
You wouldn't keep the one thing I need.

05:14:52.080 --> 05:14:54.659
When I'm sure scavengers prefer shiny

05:14:54.659 --> 05:14:57.299
little things like all of this, so you

05:14:57.299 --> 05:14:59.819
don't have the eye of onyx, which means

05:14:59.819 --> 05:15:03.000
it's, Somewhere else in Pyria.

05:15:03.060 --> 05:15:06.779
She sighed, and then stopped herself mid

05:15:06.180 --> 05:15:08.220
size so she wouldn't sound like stone

05:15:08.220 --> 05:15:08.580
mover.

05:15:08.639 --> 05:15:12.119
Her 1st theory was probably right, and

05:15:12.119 --> 05:15:13.860
some other dragon had stolen most of the

05:15:13.860 --> 05:15:14.220
treasure.

05:15:14.279 --> 05:15:17.279
Perhaps they had the eye of onyx and

05:15:17.279 --> 05:15:19.439
didn't realize what it was, or what it

05:15:19.439 --> 05:15:19.860
could do.

05:15:19.919 --> 05:15:22.619
But that didn't help Sonny, who had no

05:15:22.619 --> 05:15:24.119
way to track down the real thief.

05:15:24.180 --> 05:15:27.119
She felt something touch her talent and

05:15:27.119 --> 05:15:27.659
looked down.

05:15:27.720 --> 05:15:29.880
Holler was standing in the curve of

05:15:29.880 --> 05:15:32.400
Sonny's wing, patting her talon in a way

05:15:32.400 --> 05:15:35.880
that seemed to say, don't worry, and it's

05:15:35.880 --> 05:15:36.540
not the end of the world.

05:15:36.599 --> 05:15:40.979
You're brave and cute, Sonny told her.

05:15:41.040 --> 05:15:42.779
I wish I could keep you.

05:15:42.840 --> 05:15:44.700
If glory can have a sloth.

05:15:44.759 --> 05:15:46.439
I don't see why I can't have a scavenger

05:15:46.439 --> 05:15:46.799
or two.

05:15:46.919 --> 05:15:49.740
She glanced at Fluffy, who was edging

05:15:49.740 --> 05:15:51.959
closer. glancing up at her warily.

05:15:52.020 --> 05:15:53.880
But it's too dangerous.

05:15:53.880 --> 05:15:55.979
I'd feel terrible if one of you got

05:15:55.979 --> 05:15:56.220
hurt.

05:15:56.279 --> 05:15:59.040
She gave Holler a thoughtful look.

05:15:59.099 --> 05:16:02.040
These small, breakable scavengers were

05:16:02.040 --> 05:16:04.319
brave enough to fight or ride a dragon

05:16:04.319 --> 05:16:06.060
who could eat them in 3 bites.

05:16:06.119 --> 05:16:08.159
Could I be that brave?

05:16:08.220 --> 05:16:12.659
Like, for instance, could I try to stop a

05:16:12.659 --> 05:16:12.959
war?

05:16:13.020 --> 05:16:16.500
Even if I don't have a magical jewel, or

05:16:16.500 --> 05:16:19.200
a mystical prophecy to back me up, even

05:16:19.200 --> 05:16:21.180
if my friends decide not to help.

05:16:21.240 --> 05:16:22.319
Could I still do it?

05:16:22.380 --> 05:16:25.020
Isn't it important enough?

05:16:25.080 --> 05:16:26.580
Why shouldn't I try?

05:16:26.700 --> 05:16:29.759
So what if there's no foretold destiny

05:16:29.759 --> 05:16:30.599
saying I have to?

05:16:30.659 --> 05:16:32.400
Shouldn't I do it anyway?

05:16:32.459 --> 05:16:34.139
Just because I want to?

05:16:34.200 --> 05:16:35.819
But how?

05:16:35.939 --> 05:16:38.279
She tapped her claws on the ground

05:16:38.279 --> 05:16:38.939
thinking.

05:16:39.060 --> 05:16:41.340
Eeble rubble snob?

05:16:41.400 --> 05:16:42.240
Holler said.

05:16:42.299 --> 05:16:44.400
She pointed to Sunny's shoulder again.

05:16:44.459 --> 05:16:46.200
Sorry, Holler.

05:16:46.259 --> 05:16:47.819
I don't have time to take you for another

05:16:47.819 --> 05:16:50.040
ride, Sonny said regretfully.

05:16:50.099 --> 05:16:51.900
I have to go.

05:16:51.959 --> 05:16:54.419
She shook out her wings and reached to

05:16:54.419 --> 05:16:55.860
scoop all the treasure back into the

05:16:55.860 --> 05:16:56.099
sack.

05:16:56.220 --> 05:16:58.380
She was a little bit tempted to let the

05:16:58.380 --> 05:17:00.479
scavengers keep it, but she had a feeling

05:17:00.479 --> 05:17:02.939
she could find some use for it, giving it

05:17:02.939 --> 05:17:04.259
back to the sand wings, perhaps.

05:17:04.319 --> 05:17:07.319
I'm going to find my friends and see if

05:17:07.319 --> 05:17:07.740
they'll help me.

05:17:07.799 --> 05:17:10.020
She informed Fluffy and Holler.

05:17:10.080 --> 05:17:13.319
And then, then I've got a war to stop.

05:17:13.439 --> 05:17:16.319
She patted them each gently on their

05:17:16.319 --> 05:17:18.000
heads before gathering her wings to take

05:17:18.000 --> 05:17:18.599
off.

05:17:18.779 --> 05:17:20.939
As she sailed into the sky, she looked

05:17:20.939 --> 05:17:22.500
back and saw them waving.

05:17:22.619 --> 05:17:24.299
She wondered if she'd ever see them

05:17:24.299 --> 05:17:24.479
again.

05:17:24.540 --> 05:17:27.000
Maybe she could come back and look for

05:17:27.000 --> 05:17:28.020
them after the war was over.

05:17:28.080 --> 05:17:31.380
The weather was with her this time, and

05:17:31.380 --> 05:17:32.639
she flew through the mountains much

05:17:32.639 --> 05:17:34.860
faster than she had on the way out, when

05:17:34.860 --> 05:17:36.419
she'd had to stop every time the night

05:17:36.419 --> 05:17:37.740
wings rested or ate.

05:17:37.740 --> 05:17:40.380
She always ate light, so it didn't take

05:17:40.380 --> 05:17:41.520
long for her to pause.

05:17:41.580 --> 05:17:43.799
Catch anita squirrel or a lizard once a

05:17:43.799 --> 05:17:44.759
day and keep flying.

05:17:44.880 --> 05:17:47.639
So it was only 2 days later when she

05:17:47.639 --> 05:17:49.380
cleared the mountains and saw the

05:17:49.380 --> 05:17:51.720
rainforest ahead of her, illuminated by

05:17:51.720 --> 05:17:53.340
the rising sun beyond it.

05:17:53.400 --> 05:17:55.740
It looked so vast and green and

05:17:55.740 --> 05:17:56.279
peaceful.

05:17:56.340 --> 05:17:59.040
Sonny found herself caught by a moment of

05:17:59.040 --> 05:18:01.619
longing, a wish that she could just dive

05:18:01.619 --> 05:18:03.060
into those leaves and stay there

05:18:03.060 --> 05:18:03.419
forever.

05:18:03.540 --> 05:18:06.479
There would be enough to do, helping

05:18:06.479 --> 05:18:08.819
glory rule the rainforest and organize

05:18:08.819 --> 05:18:09.540
the night wings.

05:18:09.599 --> 05:18:11.759
It was beautiful, and there was always

05:18:11.759 --> 05:18:14.040
enough food, and the rain wings were

05:18:14.040 --> 05:18:15.900
easygoing dragons to share a tree with.

05:18:15.959 --> 05:18:18.659
The war would come here eventually.

05:18:18.720 --> 05:18:20.340
She told herself.

05:18:20.400 --> 05:18:22.500
Even the rain wings aren't safe.

05:18:22.560 --> 05:18:24.900
We already know that from what the night

05:18:24.900 --> 05:18:27.419
wings did to them, and between Scarlet

05:18:27.419 --> 05:18:30.060
and the 3 sisters looking for us, we

05:18:30.060 --> 05:18:31.740
probably aren't safe anywhere either.

05:18:31.799 --> 05:18:34.080
No hiding in caves.

05:18:34.139 --> 05:18:36.180
That's my promise to myself.

05:18:36.240 --> 05:18:37.680
No hiding at all.

05:18:37.740 --> 05:18:40.619
When the world is all wrong, I'm going to

05:18:40.619 --> 05:18:42.060
be a dragon who does something about it.

05:18:42.119 --> 05:18:45.119
Her nerves started to get the better of

05:18:45.119 --> 05:18:46.979
her the closer she got to the rain wing

05:18:46.979 --> 05:18:47.520
village, though.

05:18:47.580 --> 05:18:50.939
She kept picturing her friends' faces

05:18:50.939 --> 05:18:54.779
doubtful, kind, but condescending, all

05:18:54.779 --> 05:18:54.959
really?

05:18:55.020 --> 05:18:58.919
You, Sonny, and that is sweet, but now

05:18:58.919 --> 05:18:59.520
let's be serious.

05:18:59.639 --> 05:19:02.880
Her stomach was doing flips and spirals

05:19:02.880 --> 05:19:04.619
by the time she spotted the tree houses

05:19:04.619 --> 05:19:06.599
on the outskirts in the early afternoon

05:19:06.599 --> 05:19:08.939
and she was almost tempted to turn around

05:19:08.939 --> 05:19:10.139
and fly away again.

05:19:10.200 --> 05:19:12.240
What if they're mad at me?

05:19:12.299 --> 05:19:14.580
She suddenly thought, with another

05:19:14.580 --> 05:19:15.479
stomach lurch.

05:19:15.540 --> 05:19:17.939
What if everyone's furious at me for

05:19:17.939 --> 05:19:18.299
running off?

05:19:18.360 --> 05:19:21.119
It had occurred to her to use the dream

05:19:21.119 --> 05:19:23.279
visitor while she was traveling, but

05:19:23.279 --> 05:19:24.419
she'd decided against it.

05:19:24.479 --> 05:19:26.819
She wanted to explain everything to her

05:19:26.819 --> 05:19:27.959
friends face to face.

05:19:28.020 --> 05:19:30.959
A movement distracted her from her

05:19:30.959 --> 05:19:31.380
thoughts.

05:19:31.380 --> 05:19:33.900
Something shifting out of the corner of

05:19:33.900 --> 05:19:36.060
her eye, but when she looked, she

05:19:36.060 --> 05:19:37.979
couldn't see anything but dangling vines

05:19:37.979 --> 05:19:39.299
and bright orange flowers.

05:19:39.360 --> 05:19:42.000
Immediately she ducked and rolled.

05:19:42.060 --> 05:19:44.819
So the tranquilizer dart shot right past

05:19:44.819 --> 05:19:46.680
her and thudded into a tree trunk

05:19:46.680 --> 05:19:48.900
startling several shiny blue frogs.

05:19:48.959 --> 05:19:53.099
It's me, Sonny shouted, twisting to wave

05:19:53.099 --> 05:19:54.479
her claws with the leaves around her.

05:19:54.540 --> 05:19:56.220
It's sunny.

05:19:56.279 --> 05:19:57.720
I'm Queen Glory's friend.

05:19:57.779 --> 05:20:00.419
She held out her talons and spread her

05:20:00.419 --> 05:20:02.700
wings wide, hoping one of the hidden rain

05:20:02.700 --> 05:20:03.900
wings would remember her.

05:20:03.959 --> 05:20:06.779
A face materialized on a nearby branch.

05:20:06.840 --> 05:20:09.360
His scales shifting from brown and green

05:20:09.360 --> 05:20:10.319
to dark purple.

05:20:10.380 --> 05:20:12.840
The dragon blinked a few times, looking

05:20:12.840 --> 05:20:15.240
more wary than most rain wings Sonny had

05:20:15.240 --> 05:20:15.599
ever met.

05:20:15.659 --> 05:20:18.599
The queen was looking for a little gold

05:20:18.599 --> 05:20:21.479
dragon, said a voice behind Sonny, and

05:20:21.479 --> 05:20:24.060
another dragon emerged, this one shifting

05:20:24.060 --> 05:20:25.799
to the Clementine orange of the flowers.

05:20:25.860 --> 05:20:27.599
This could be her.

05:20:27.659 --> 05:20:29.939
Shouldn't we knock her out anyway?

05:20:30.000 --> 05:20:31.799
asked the purple dragon.

05:20:31.860 --> 05:20:32.880
Just to be safe.

05:20:32.939 --> 05:20:34.740
You know, the queen keeps telling us to

05:20:34.740 --> 05:20:35.400
be more careful.

05:20:35.459 --> 05:20:39.000
She means about the night wings. said the

05:20:39.000 --> 05:20:40.200
orange dragon blithely.

05:20:40.259 --> 05:20:42.299
This one's not a night wing.

05:20:42.360 --> 05:20:43.020
I sure she's fine.

05:20:43.080 --> 05:20:45.240
On the one talon.

05:20:45.299 --> 05:20:46.860
Sonny certainly didn't want to be shot

05:20:46.860 --> 05:20:47.459
with a dart.

05:20:47.520 --> 05:20:49.799
She wanted to be wide awake when she saw

05:20:49.799 --> 05:20:50.340
her friends again.

05:20:50.400 --> 05:20:53.639
On the other talon, she was afraid she

05:20:53.639 --> 05:20:56.040
could imagine this exact conversation if

05:20:56.040 --> 05:20:59.400
say, a smoldering, vengeful sky wing

05:20:59.400 --> 05:21:01.080
happened to show up in the rainforest

05:21:01.080 --> 05:21:01.799
looking for them.

05:21:01.919 --> 05:21:04.439
Oh, she's not a night wing?

05:21:04.500 --> 05:21:06.419
Well, then, let's take her straight to

05:21:06.419 --> 05:21:07.319
the dragonets.

05:21:07.380 --> 05:21:07.919
No worries.

05:21:07.979 --> 05:21:11.639
I am Glory's friend, she promised them.

05:21:11.700 --> 05:21:13.439
There's nothing to worry about Scarlet

05:21:13.439 --> 05:21:13.680
later.

05:21:13.740 --> 05:21:15.240
I need to see her.

05:21:15.360 --> 05:21:17.340
The queen.

05:21:17.459 --> 05:21:18.540
Let's see.

05:21:18.599 --> 05:21:21.060
She might be in the audience tree house

05:21:21.060 --> 05:21:22.799
said the orange dragon thoughtfully.

05:21:22.860 --> 05:21:25.860
Or the healer's hut, said the purple

05:21:25.860 --> 05:21:26.520
dragon.

05:21:26.580 --> 05:21:27.599
She's there a lot.

05:21:27.659 --> 05:21:30.900
Or visiting the night wing camp, or

05:21:30.900 --> 05:21:32.400
checking on the progress of the school.

05:21:32.520 --> 05:21:35.580
Or reviewing, all right, Sunny

05:21:35.580 --> 05:21:36.419
interrupted.

05:21:36.479 --> 05:21:37.799
I'll just look for her.

05:21:37.860 --> 05:21:39.240
Thank you.

05:21:39.299 --> 05:21:42.060
They both flicked their tails and bobbed

05:21:42.060 --> 05:21:44.220
their heads, and their scales immediately

05:21:44.220 --> 05:21:46.380
began shifting back to camouflage as

05:21:46.380 --> 05:21:47.580
Sonny flew on.

05:21:47.639 --> 05:21:50.939
The healer's hut, she decided, so I can

05:21:50.939 --> 05:21:51.779
see Starflight.

05:21:51.840 --> 05:21:54.959
But before she got there, she spotted the

05:21:54.959 --> 05:21:57.000
mahogany brown scales of a mud wing

05:21:57.000 --> 05:21:58.319
stretched out on one of the sleeping

05:21:58.319 --> 05:21:59.220
platforms.

05:21:59.279 --> 05:22:00.900
Clay!

05:22:00.959 --> 05:22:02.279
She yelped happily.

05:22:02.340 --> 05:22:04.919
She barreled up to him, and nearly flung

05:22:04.919 --> 05:22:06.779
her wings around him before she realized

05:22:06.779 --> 05:22:08.099
it wasn't clay at all.

05:22:08.159 --> 05:22:11.159
It was some other mudwing dragonette, who

05:22:11.159 --> 05:22:12.900
jumped back with a startled expression

05:22:12.900 --> 05:22:14.759
and hid something behind his wings.

05:22:14.819 --> 05:22:19.080
Whoa, Sonny said, skidding to a stop on

05:22:19.080 --> 05:22:19.380
the wood.

05:22:19.439 --> 05:22:20.580
Who are you?

05:22:20.700 --> 05:22:22.619
Who are you?

05:22:22.680 --> 05:22:24.240
He responded rudely.

05:22:24.299 --> 05:22:27.119
Sonny usually liked everybody, at least

05:22:27.119 --> 05:22:29.400
at first, but something about this dragon

05:22:29.400 --> 05:22:31.020
immediately rubbed her the wrong way.

05:22:31.080 --> 05:22:33.599
Where's clay?

05:22:33.599 --> 05:22:34.020
she asked.

05:22:34.080 --> 05:22:35.700
How should I know?

05:22:35.759 --> 05:22:36.900
He demanded.

05:22:36.959 --> 05:22:40.259
Sonny frowned at him, then turned to fly

05:22:40.259 --> 05:22:40.560
away.

05:22:40.619 --> 05:22:43.080
If he didn't want to be helpful, she

05:22:43.080 --> 05:22:44.099
didn't need to bother with him.

05:22:44.220 --> 05:22:46.799
Hey, he called.

05:22:46.860 --> 05:22:47.580
Come back.

05:22:47.700 --> 05:22:49.740
Sonny ignored him.

05:22:49.799 --> 05:22:52.259
She had noticed the angle of the sunlight

05:22:52.259 --> 05:22:54.659
and realized that it was the rain wing

05:22:54.659 --> 05:22:56.580
suntime, when most of them would be

05:22:56.580 --> 05:22:58.380
sleeping high up in the treetops

05:22:58.380 --> 05:23:00.540
recharging their scales.

05:23:00.599 --> 05:23:02.880
She wondered if Glory was up there too, or

05:23:02.880 --> 05:23:04.439
if she ever let herself sleep.

05:23:04.500 --> 05:23:07.500
Just then, she spotted the healer's hut

05:23:07.500 --> 05:23:10.020
and coming out of it, opening his wings

05:23:10.020 --> 05:23:13.139
to fly was clay, definitely clay this

05:23:13.139 --> 05:23:15.900
time, every wonderful brown scale of

05:23:15.900 --> 05:23:16.020
him.

05:23:16.080 --> 05:23:19.439
Sunny dove into his wings, nearly

05:23:19.439 --> 05:23:21.299
knocking him backward, except that he was

05:23:21.299 --> 05:23:22.200
big enough to catch her.

05:23:22.259 --> 05:23:25.560
He made an oof noise, and then realized

05:23:25.560 --> 05:23:26.099
who she was.

05:23:26.159 --> 05:23:29.040
Sonny, he roared.

05:23:29.099 --> 05:23:30.060
It's you.

05:23:30.119 --> 05:23:31.259
You're alive.

05:23:31.319 --> 05:23:32.159
You're all right.

05:23:32.220 --> 05:23:35.220
He seized her and swung her around, her

05:23:35.220 --> 05:23:37.020
tail flying out behind her, and then

05:23:37.020 --> 05:23:37.740
quickly put her down.

05:23:37.799 --> 05:23:39.840
Are you all right?

05:23:39.900 --> 05:23:41.400
He asked anxiously.

05:23:41.459 --> 05:23:43.860
He touched her wings and checked her

05:23:43.860 --> 05:23:44.400
talons.

05:23:44.459 --> 05:23:46.740
We thought something terrible had

05:23:46.740 --> 05:23:47.159
happened to you.

05:23:47.220 --> 05:23:50.459
We've been searching and searching.

05:23:50.520 --> 05:23:51.060
Come, come in.

05:23:51.119 --> 05:23:53.759
He dragged her into the hut before she

05:23:53.759 --> 05:23:54.479
could say anything.

05:23:54.540 --> 05:23:55.919
Starflight.

05:23:55.979 --> 05:23:56.819
Sonny's back.

05:23:56.880 --> 05:24:00.180
Two black dragons turned their heads in

05:24:00.180 --> 05:24:01.319
unison toward the door.

05:24:01.380 --> 05:24:04.380
Sonny recognized fate speaker, the night

05:24:04.380 --> 05:24:05.880
wing who had been one of the alternate

05:24:05.880 --> 05:24:08.459
dragonettes, raised by the talons in case

05:24:08.459 --> 05:24:10.439
they needed a spare set to fulfill the

05:24:10.439 --> 05:24:10.919
prophecy.

05:24:10.979 --> 05:24:13.799
She was crouched beside a nest of leaves

05:24:13.799 --> 05:24:15.840
where Starflight was lying with his wings

05:24:15.840 --> 05:24:16.500
spread out.

05:24:16.560 --> 05:24:19.919
Sunny flinched at the side of the burns

05:24:19.919 --> 05:24:22.020
all along Starflight's dark scales.

05:24:22.080 --> 05:24:24.779
Some kind of silvery ointment glistened

05:24:24.779 --> 05:24:26.939
over the wounds, and she saw a little of

05:24:26.939 --> 05:24:29.759
it on fate speakers talons as well, as if

05:24:29.759 --> 05:24:30.840
she'd been helping to put it on.

05:24:30.900 --> 05:24:35.520
Sonny, Starflight said in a hoarse voice

05:24:35.520 --> 05:24:36.779
really?

05:24:36.840 --> 05:24:39.959
Sonny realized, with a stab of guilt and

05:24:39.959 --> 05:24:42.779
horror, that Starfly's eyes were covered

05:24:42.779 --> 05:24:44.819
with a mask of leaves, carefully

05:24:44.819 --> 05:24:45.720
plastered in place.

05:24:45.779 --> 05:24:49.740
It's me. she said, hurrying over to his

05:24:49.740 --> 05:24:49.919
side.

05:24:49.979 --> 05:24:52.439
She nudged his shoulder gently with her

05:24:52.439 --> 05:24:54.599
snout, trying to share her warmth with

05:24:54.599 --> 05:24:54.840
him.

05:24:54.900 --> 05:24:56.400
I'm here.

05:24:56.459 --> 05:24:58.680
Starflight let out his breath.

05:24:58.740 --> 05:25:00.419
Are you all right?

05:25:00.479 --> 05:25:01.919
He said anxiously.

05:25:01.979 --> 05:25:04.919
Better than you are, she tried to joke.

05:25:04.979 --> 05:25:07.259
I told him you were fine.

05:25:07.319 --> 05:25:09.959
Fate speaker interjected, in a helpful

05:25:09.959 --> 05:25:10.319
voice.

05:25:10.380 --> 05:25:12.540
She patted the edge of the leaves where

05:25:12.540 --> 05:25:13.500
Starflight lay.

05:25:13.560 --> 05:25:14.880
I had a vision.

05:25:15.000 --> 05:25:17.040
I mean, it was fuzzy, but I was pretty

05:25:17.040 --> 05:25:17.759
sure you were fine.

05:25:17.819 --> 05:25:21.419
Starflight coughed awkwardly, as if he'd

05:25:21.419 --> 05:25:23.220
been trying to avoid talking about fate

05:25:23.220 --> 05:25:24.479
speakers visions for days.

05:25:24.599 --> 05:25:27.479
Sunny remembered what Stone Mover had

05:25:27.479 --> 05:25:29.939
told her, that no Nightwing had had

05:25:29.939 --> 05:25:32.400
prophetic powers or mind reading for

05:25:32.400 --> 05:25:32.939
generations.

05:25:33.000 --> 05:25:35.520
So was fate speaker lying?

05:25:35.580 --> 05:25:38.159
Or did she believe her own wild stories?

05:25:38.220 --> 05:25:40.740
She didn't seem cruel enough to deceive

05:25:40.740 --> 05:25:42.479
Starflight about whether Sonny was all

05:25:42.479 --> 05:25:45.119
right, but then Sonny didn't really know

05:25:45.119 --> 05:25:45.720
her at all.

05:25:45.779 --> 05:25:48.419
I'm sorry I wasn't here to take care of

05:25:48.419 --> 05:25:48.599
you.

05:25:48.659 --> 05:25:51.900
Senny said, touching one of Starflight's

05:25:51.900 --> 05:25:52.500
wings gently.

05:25:52.560 --> 05:25:55.919
I took care of him, fate speaker said.

05:25:55.979 --> 05:25:59.639
Sonny felt a flash of something odd, like

05:25:59.639 --> 05:26:01.500
she wanted fate speaker to shush and go

05:26:01.500 --> 05:26:01.680
away.

05:26:01.740 --> 05:26:03.360
Jealousy.

05:26:03.419 --> 05:26:06.240
But wouldn't that mean that I like

05:26:06.240 --> 05:26:07.740
Starflight the way he likes me?

05:26:07.799 --> 05:26:09.419
Did she?

05:26:09.479 --> 05:26:11.939
It would be nice if she could love him

05:26:11.939 --> 05:26:13.560
back, it would make him happy.

05:26:13.619 --> 05:26:15.419
And she did care about him.

05:26:15.479 --> 05:26:17.939
Plus, he was a real hero.

05:26:18.000 --> 05:26:21.419
He'd just saved the entire night wing

05:26:21.419 --> 05:26:22.439
tribe from extinction.

05:26:22.500 --> 05:26:25.619
We don't have time for mushy romance

05:26:25.619 --> 05:26:26.459
right now anyway.

05:26:26.520 --> 05:26:28.500
She told herself sternly.

05:26:28.560 --> 05:26:30.479
Whatever's going to happen with me in

05:26:30.479 --> 05:26:33.599
Starfight, whatever we are, we'll figure

05:26:33.599 --> 05:26:35.159
it out after we stop the war.

05:26:35.220 --> 05:26:38.220
She glanced around the room and noticed

05:26:38.220 --> 05:26:40.680
that Webbs was still there, asleep in a

05:26:40.680 --> 05:26:43.020
corner, although the venomous scratch on

05:26:43.020 --> 05:26:44.459
his tail looked almost completely

05:26:44.459 --> 05:26:45.119
healed.

05:26:45.180 --> 05:26:48.419
There were a few rain wings as well, 4

05:26:48.419 --> 05:26:49.919
with injuries that might have happened

05:26:49.919 --> 05:26:52.139
during the attack on the Nightwing Island

05:26:52.139 --> 05:26:54.779
and 2 others whose breads rattled in

05:26:54.779 --> 05:26:56.340
their skinny chests as they slept.

05:26:56.400 --> 05:26:59.520
Sunny guessed they had been prisoners, and

05:26:59.520 --> 05:27:00.659
were still recovering from their

05:27:00.659 --> 05:27:02.459
treatment at the talons of the night

05:27:02.459 --> 05:27:02.759
wings.

05:27:02.819 --> 05:27:05.340
She could see spots on their snouts and

05:27:05.340 --> 05:27:07.919
ankles, where iron bands had rubbed the

05:27:07.919 --> 05:27:08.639
scales raw.

05:27:08.700 --> 05:27:12.180
The only other dragon occupying a bed was

05:27:12.180 --> 05:27:13.979
the Sky Wing, Flame.

05:27:14.040 --> 05:27:16.560
He'd grown up with fate speaker among the

05:27:16.560 --> 05:27:18.659
talons of peace, as another possible

05:27:18.659 --> 05:27:20.400
alternate for the dragonettes.

05:27:20.459 --> 05:27:22.740
She could tell that the healers had

05:27:22.740 --> 05:27:24.840
applied the cactus milk antidote to the

05:27:24.840 --> 05:27:27.360
wound that slashed across his face, but

05:27:27.360 --> 05:27:29.340
it would still leave a nasty scar.

05:27:29.400 --> 05:27:31.799
She wondered if his face had looked that

05:27:31.799 --> 05:27:33.419
furious before he was injured.

05:27:33.540 --> 05:27:35.099
She suspected yes.

05:27:35.159 --> 05:27:37.979
He was awake, glaring around the tree

05:27:37.979 --> 05:27:40.319
house, with trails of smoke coming out of

05:27:40.319 --> 05:27:41.159
his nose and ears.

05:27:41.220 --> 05:27:43.560
So where were you?

05:27:43.619 --> 05:27:46.740
Clay asked, bumping Sonny's wing with his

05:27:46.740 --> 05:27:46.919
own.

05:27:46.979 --> 05:27:49.380
Tsunami thought maybe you'd been

05:27:49.380 --> 05:27:49.979
kidnapped.

05:27:50.040 --> 05:27:51.180
Isn't that crazy?

05:27:51.240 --> 05:27:55.200
Well, I kind of was kidnapped, Sonny

05:27:55.200 --> 05:27:56.159
admitted.

05:27:56.220 --> 05:27:58.619
Starflight and fate speaker both gasped.

05:27:58.680 --> 05:28:02.340
But I got away, except then I got caught

05:28:02.340 --> 05:28:04.860
again, and then I was a prisoner in Burns

05:28:04.860 --> 05:28:05.819
stronghold for a while.

05:28:05.880 --> 05:28:07.259
What?

05:28:07.319 --> 05:28:10.200
Starflight tried to sit up and nearly

05:28:10.200 --> 05:28:11.580
fell off his bed.

05:28:11.639 --> 05:28:13.259
Clay's eyes were wide and shocked.

05:28:13.319 --> 05:28:15.840
I'm here now, though, aren't I?

05:28:15.959 --> 05:28:16.860
Sonny said.

05:28:16.919 --> 05:28:18.299
It all turned out fine.

05:28:18.360 --> 05:28:21.840
I've taken care of myself, mostly, she

05:28:21.840 --> 05:28:25.020
added honestly, it was a little crazy, but

05:28:25.020 --> 05:28:26.639
I should tell you all at the same time

05:28:26.639 --> 05:28:28.139
where are tsunami and glory?

05:28:28.200 --> 05:28:32.159
Tsunami was drilling rain wings and

05:28:32.159 --> 05:28:34.200
evasive maneuvers, although apparently

05:28:34.200 --> 05:28:36.299
what that actually meant was a lot of

05:28:36.299 --> 05:28:39.180
yelling things like, pay attention, and

05:28:39.180 --> 05:28:42.959
leave that toucan alone, and why are you

05:28:42.959 --> 05:28:47.340
pink, stopping pink, and 3 moons, are you

05:28:47.340 --> 05:28:48.000
eating again?

05:28:48.119 --> 05:28:51.540
Sonny half hoped that meant she'd be all

05:28:51.540 --> 05:28:53.639
yelled out, but of course it didn't.

05:28:53.700 --> 05:28:56.400
Tsunami had plenty of yelling energy left

05:28:56.400 --> 05:28:57.000
for Sonny.

05:28:57.060 --> 05:28:59.520
Where have you been?

05:28:59.580 --> 05:29:00.720
she roared.

05:29:00.840 --> 05:29:03.119
Do you know how worried we've been?

05:29:03.180 --> 05:29:05.340
How could you do that to us?

05:29:05.400 --> 05:29:07.500
I was so sure the Night Wings did

05:29:07.500 --> 05:29:09.419
something to you that I nearly threw them

05:29:09.419 --> 05:29:10.380
all back to the volcano.

05:29:10.500 --> 05:29:13.080
We've had search parties out every day

05:29:13.080 --> 05:29:16.200
but not one sign of you, anywhere.

05:29:16.259 --> 05:29:18.479
Not even Deathbringer.

05:29:18.540 --> 05:29:20.880
Well, he said he smelled you over to the

05:29:20.880 --> 05:29:22.439
west, but who trusts him?

05:29:22.500 --> 05:29:23.939
Not me is who.

05:29:24.000 --> 05:29:25.680
I haven't slept in days, sonny.

05:29:25.740 --> 05:29:26.759
Days.

05:29:26.880 --> 05:29:29.520
She grabbed Sonny and wrapped her wings

05:29:29.520 --> 05:29:31.080
around her in a fierce hug.

05:29:31.139 --> 05:29:34.500
Sonny felt her own anger melting and

05:29:34.500 --> 05:29:37.139
realized she'd been furious with tsunami

05:29:37.139 --> 05:29:38.639
ever since overhearing the conversation

05:29:38.639 --> 05:29:40.259
in the obsidian mirror.

05:29:40.319 --> 05:29:43.439
She may not take me seriously, Sonny

05:29:43.439 --> 05:29:45.419
thought, but she really does love me.

05:29:45.479 --> 05:29:49.680
I'm sorry, Sonny said, muffled, into

05:29:49.680 --> 05:29:50.819
Tsunami's shoulder.

05:29:50.880 --> 05:29:52.799
But I swear I was doing important

05:29:52.799 --> 05:29:53.279
things.

05:29:53.340 --> 05:29:55.139
I'll tell you all about it.

05:29:55.259 --> 05:29:55.919
Where's glory?

05:29:55.979 --> 05:29:59.099
Checking on the night wing camp, Tsunami

05:29:59.099 --> 05:30:01.380
said, relaxing her grip on Sonny, but

05:30:01.380 --> 05:30:02.759
keeping one wing around her.

05:30:02.939 --> 05:30:05.340
She is kind of awesome with them, all

05:30:05.340 --> 05:30:07.560
scary and tough and royal, like a real

05:30:07.560 --> 05:30:07.979
queen.

05:30:08.040 --> 05:30:09.060
Do not.

05:30:09.119 --> 05:30:10.139
Tell her I said that.

05:30:10.200 --> 05:30:12.240
Sonny grinned up at her.

05:30:12.299 --> 05:30:13.500
Are they behaving?

05:30:13.560 --> 05:30:16.380
For the most part, tsunami said.

05:30:16.439 --> 05:30:18.779
They were all absolutely starving, so

05:30:18.779 --> 05:30:20.400
just giving them enough food is making

05:30:20.400 --> 05:30:22.560
them a whole lot happier and easier to

05:30:22.560 --> 05:30:22.919
deal with.

05:30:22.979 --> 05:30:25.860
Glory's letting them hunt and eat as much

05:30:25.860 --> 05:30:27.959
as they want, except for the saws.

05:30:28.020 --> 05:30:30.119
Those are off limits, apparently.

05:30:30.180 --> 05:30:32.520
I guess being a giant sucker for cute

05:30:32.520 --> 05:30:34.560
furry things is a rain wing genetic

05:30:34.560 --> 05:30:34.860
defect.

05:30:34.979 --> 05:30:36.900
I wouldn't need them either.

05:30:36.959 --> 05:30:38.340
Sonny pointed out.

05:30:38.400 --> 05:30:40.619
Well, but that makes sense.

05:30:40.680 --> 05:30:42.000
Tsunami said.

05:30:42.060 --> 05:30:43.979
You practically are a cute furry thing.

05:30:44.040 --> 05:30:47.220
Sunny debated getting riled up about this

05:30:47.220 --> 05:30:49.439
but tsunami was already turning to one of

05:30:49.439 --> 05:30:51.779
the rain wings, all of whom were staring

05:30:51.779 --> 05:30:54.060
nosily at Sunny, and ordering him to

05:30:54.060 --> 05:30:54.599
fetch glory.

05:30:54.659 --> 05:30:57.659
Tell her to meet us in the healer's hut

05:30:57.659 --> 05:30:59.819
she said, and no dawdling.

05:30:59.880 --> 05:31:01.740
If you stop to admire so much as one

05:31:01.740 --> 05:31:03.900
beetle, I will seriously bite you.

05:31:03.959 --> 05:31:07.919
All right, the rain wing said affably, and

05:31:07.919 --> 05:31:09.720
flew off in a way that probably counted

05:31:09.720 --> 05:31:12.240
as a hurry for a rain wing, but was only

05:31:12.240 --> 05:31:13.799
marginally faster than your average

05:31:13.799 --> 05:31:14.520
snail.

05:31:14.580 --> 05:31:18.119
I swear, tsunami muttered through her

05:31:18.119 --> 05:31:20.939
teeth, Sonny, you'll probably be shocked

05:31:20.939 --> 05:31:22.979
to hear this, but I don't think I'd make

05:31:22.979 --> 05:31:24.000
a very good rain wing.

05:31:24.119 --> 05:31:25.680
Sonny laughed.

05:31:25.740 --> 05:31:28.979
I missed you. she said, and meant it.

05:31:29.040 --> 05:31:31.380
It wasn't long before they were all

05:31:31.380 --> 05:31:33.060
gathered around Starflight's bed.

05:31:33.119 --> 05:31:36.119
Sonny felt a rush of joy as glory swept

05:31:36.119 --> 05:31:36.599
into the room.

05:31:36.659 --> 05:31:39.720
Here were all her friends, all together

05:31:39.720 --> 05:31:41.520
in one place like they were supposed to

05:31:41.520 --> 05:31:41.700
be.

05:31:41.759 --> 05:31:46.139
Sonny, Glory said, and the relief in her

05:31:46.139 --> 05:31:48.060
voice was matched by the bright yellow of

05:31:48.060 --> 05:31:48.599
her scales.

05:31:48.659 --> 05:31:51.360
She even reached out and squeezed Sonny's

05:31:51.360 --> 05:31:53.340
front talons, which was more affection

05:31:53.340 --> 05:31:54.779
than Sonny would have expected from her.

05:31:54.840 --> 05:31:57.840
Thank goodness you're alive, because now

05:31:57.840 --> 05:31:59.520
I can totally behead you.

05:31:59.580 --> 05:32:02.040
Starflight, what's our official policy on

05:32:02.040 --> 05:32:02.639
beheading right now?

05:32:02.700 --> 05:32:06.419
Our Constitution says no beheading Sonny

05:32:06.419 --> 05:32:07.439
he said loyally.

05:32:07.560 --> 05:32:09.180
Let's amend that.

05:32:09.240 --> 05:32:12.720
Glory said, flicking her tail to, I can

05:32:12.720 --> 05:32:14.400
behead anyone who worries me half to

05:32:14.400 --> 05:32:14.880
death like this.

05:32:15.000 --> 05:32:18.540
I know you're probably mad, Sonny said.

05:32:18.659 --> 05:32:21.299
Glory's ears and wings were starting to

05:32:21.299 --> 05:32:22.619
shade more red than yellow.

05:32:22.680 --> 05:32:26.759
Okay, definitely mad, but there were lots

05:32:26.759 --> 05:32:30.240
of stuff happened and it had better be

05:32:30.240 --> 05:32:32.700
wildly important stuff.

05:32:32.759 --> 05:32:33.959
Glory growled.

05:32:34.020 --> 05:32:36.779
You know what I don't need in my 1st week

05:32:36.779 --> 05:32:37.319
as queen.

05:32:37.380 --> 05:32:39.540
In addition to a whole new tribe of

05:32:39.540 --> 05:32:41.939
pretty much the worst, most unhealthy

05:32:41.939 --> 05:32:44.099
most annoying dragons ever.

05:32:44.220 --> 05:32:46.919
I don't need to also be freaking out

05:32:46.919 --> 05:32:49.020
because one of my best friends has

05:32:49.020 --> 05:32:49.500
disappeared.

05:32:49.560 --> 05:32:53.159
I don't need to be using my best dragons

05:32:53.159 --> 05:32:55.619
on patrols searching for you when they

05:32:55.619 --> 05:32:57.419
should be helping me run a brand new

05:32:57.419 --> 05:32:59.340
experimental 2 tribe kingdom.

05:32:59.400 --> 05:33:03.240
That's me, Deathbringer said, poking his

05:33:03.240 --> 05:33:04.020
head in from outside.

05:33:04.080 --> 05:33:05.279
Sonny jumped.

05:33:05.340 --> 05:33:07.439
She still wasn't used to seeing any night

05:33:07.439 --> 05:33:09.599
wings in the rain wing village apart from

05:33:09.599 --> 05:33:10.200
Starflight.

05:33:10.259 --> 05:33:14.099
When she says her best dragons, she's

05:33:14.099 --> 05:33:14.639
talking about me.

05:33:14.700 --> 05:33:18.959
I am not, Glory said, a little too

05:33:18.959 --> 05:33:20.639
indignantly, Sonny thought.

05:33:20.700 --> 05:33:22.619
Quit stalking me.

05:33:22.680 --> 05:33:27.119
This is not stalking, he objected. sliding

05:33:27.119 --> 05:33:28.439
into the room as if he were perfectly

05:33:28.439 --> 05:33:28.799
welcome.

05:33:28.860 --> 05:33:31.020
This is protecting you.

05:33:31.080 --> 05:33:33.479
Nobody invited you to this private

05:33:33.479 --> 05:33:34.380
conversation.

05:33:34.439 --> 05:33:36.119
Tsunami said bossily.

05:33:36.180 --> 05:33:39.000
Hey, I'm just making sure the queen is

05:33:39.000 --> 05:33:41.520
safe, he said, spreading his wings.

05:33:41.580 --> 05:33:44.700
The queen can take care of herself.

05:33:44.759 --> 05:33:46.319
Glory pointed out.

05:33:46.380 --> 05:33:49.500
Out of the 2 dragons in question, the

05:33:49.500 --> 05:33:51.180
queen happens to be the one with

05:33:51.180 --> 05:33:53.340
camouflage scales who can shoot venom.

05:33:53.400 --> 05:33:54.479
What can you do again?

05:33:54.540 --> 05:33:56.099
Sit in the dark, is that it?

05:33:56.159 --> 05:33:57.119
Guess what?

05:33:57.180 --> 05:33:58.200
I can do that too.

05:33:58.259 --> 05:34:01.860
Inky Black spilled across her scales, and

05:34:01.860 --> 05:34:03.360
she looked down her snout at him.

05:34:03.419 --> 05:34:07.139
I can stop dragons from killing you, he

05:34:07.139 --> 05:34:07.380
said.

05:34:07.439 --> 05:34:10.619
Three, assassination plot so far, Your

05:34:10.619 --> 05:34:11.159
Majesty.

05:34:11.220 --> 05:34:13.259
No one's better at stopping assassins

05:34:13.259 --> 05:34:15.419
than the world's best assassin.

05:34:15.479 --> 05:34:19.740
You poor dragon, Glory said, if only you

05:34:19.740 --> 05:34:21.119
had a shred of self-esteem.

05:34:21.180 --> 05:34:22.439
What?

05:34:22.560 --> 05:34:24.419
Sonny cried dismayed.

05:34:24.479 --> 05:34:26.400
Nightwings have tried to kill you.

05:34:26.459 --> 05:34:27.959
Three times already?

05:34:28.020 --> 05:34:30.840
So he says, Glory observed.

05:34:30.900 --> 05:34:33.000
She didn't look remotely scared or even

05:34:33.000 --> 05:34:33.540
ruffled.

05:34:33.599 --> 05:34:36.180
Apparently, he's my bodyguard now.

05:34:36.240 --> 05:34:39.240
Not that anyone asked him to be, ahem.

05:34:39.479 --> 05:34:40.319
It's true.

05:34:40.380 --> 05:34:42.720
I did have to fight my way past a whole

05:34:42.720 --> 05:34:45.360
pack of volunteers, he mused mockingly.

05:34:45.419 --> 05:34:48.299
Oh no, wait, it's just me.

05:34:48.360 --> 05:34:50.939
The only dragon who cares if you live or

05:34:50.939 --> 05:34:51.119
die.

05:34:51.180 --> 05:34:53.639
He's just trying to make his list look

05:34:53.639 --> 05:34:54.360
longer than mine.

05:34:54.419 --> 05:34:55.919
Glory said to Sonny.

05:34:56.040 --> 05:34:58.139
We're keeping track of who has saved 2

05:34:58.139 --> 05:34:58.740
more often.

05:34:58.799 --> 05:35:00.779
I say it doesn't count if you have to

05:35:00.779 --> 05:35:02.819
save me from your own dragon murdering

05:35:02.819 --> 05:35:03.119
self.

05:35:03.180 --> 05:35:05.400
And he says, I shouldn't get credit for

05:35:05.400 --> 05:35:07.500
sending him away before the ice wings got

05:35:07.500 --> 05:35:07.680
him.

05:35:07.799 --> 05:35:10.619
Sunny couldn't help and notice that

05:35:10.619 --> 05:35:12.419
Deathbringer was apparently allowed to

05:35:12.419 --> 05:35:14.939
know where the rain wing village was and

05:35:14.939 --> 05:35:16.139
to roam around it freely.

05:35:16.200 --> 05:35:19.020
So whatever she said about him, glory

05:35:19.020 --> 05:35:21.299
really must trust him, certainly more

05:35:21.299 --> 05:35:22.319
than any other night wing.

05:35:22.439 --> 05:35:25.740
If you 2 are quite finished jabbing at

05:35:25.740 --> 05:35:27.959
each other, tsunami said, rolling her

05:35:27.959 --> 05:35:30.060
eyes, I'd like to hear what Sonny's been

05:35:30.060 --> 05:35:30.779
doing for the last week.

05:35:30.840 --> 05:35:32.759
Me too.

05:35:32.880 --> 05:35:35.700
Clay said fervently, sidling up beside

05:35:35.700 --> 05:35:35.939
her.

05:35:36.000 --> 05:35:39.419
Sonny twined her tail around his, relieved

05:35:39.419 --> 05:35:41.099
that at least one of her friends wouldn't

05:35:41.099 --> 05:35:43.259
be mad at her, no matter what she'd done

05:35:43.259 --> 05:35:44.700
or how worried he'd been.

05:35:44.759 --> 05:35:46.860
Well, she said.

05:35:46.919 --> 05:35:49.979
I found my parents, and I met Burns

05:35:49.979 --> 05:35:53.279
brother, and I saw peril again, and Queen

05:35:53.279 --> 05:35:54.479
Scarlet is alive.

05:35:54.540 --> 05:35:57.240
Oh, and she's maybe coming here to kill

05:35:57.240 --> 05:35:59.279
us, although I hope she doesn't really

05:35:59.279 --> 05:36:01.139
know where we are, although she said she

05:36:01.139 --> 05:36:01.380
did.

05:36:01.439 --> 05:36:04.560
Glory cleared her throat quietly, but

05:36:04.560 --> 05:36:05.880
everyone turned to look at her anyway.

05:36:06.000 --> 05:36:08.819
Um, she said.

05:36:08.880 --> 05:36:13.560
So, yes, actually, she does know where we

05:36:13.560 --> 05:36:13.799
are.

05:36:13.860 --> 05:36:16.979
She squinted at the skylight, rubbing the

05:36:16.979 --> 05:36:17.459
back of her head.

05:36:17.520 --> 05:36:21.419
She, maybe you visited me in a dream with

05:36:21.419 --> 05:36:23.819
a dream visitor and saw where I was.

05:36:23.880 --> 05:36:25.500
So, yes.

05:36:25.560 --> 05:36:27.659
That seems like something worth

05:36:27.659 --> 05:36:29.759
mentioning, tsunami yelled.

05:36:29.819 --> 05:36:32.880
I was going to tell you all, Glory said

05:36:32.880 --> 05:36:35.220
huffily, but then Starflight disappeared

05:36:35.220 --> 05:36:36.959
and I became queen and I got a little

05:36:36.959 --> 05:36:38.520
busy.

05:36:38.580 --> 05:36:42.659
Anyway, Sonny interrupted, before the 2

05:36:42.659 --> 05:36:43.680
of them could start one of their

05:36:43.680 --> 05:36:44.819
interminable arguments.

05:36:44.939 --> 05:36:48.119
So she was in burned stronghold, but

05:36:48.119 --> 05:36:48.840
she's not anymore.

05:36:48.900 --> 05:36:51.720
Could you start at the beginning?

05:36:51.779 --> 05:36:53.159
Starflight asked.

05:36:53.220 --> 05:36:54.419
I'm a little confused.

05:36:54.479 --> 05:36:56.159
Me too.

05:36:56.220 --> 05:36:58.139
Fate speaker chimed in.

05:36:58.200 --> 05:37:01.740
As if anyone asked you, Sonny thought

05:37:01.740 --> 05:37:03.779
then felt incredibly guilty for thinking

05:37:03.779 --> 05:37:04.080
it.

05:37:04.139 --> 05:37:06.840
All right, Sonny said.

05:37:06.900 --> 05:37:09.540
It started with these 3 night wings

05:37:09.540 --> 05:37:10.080
grabbing me.

05:37:10.139 --> 05:37:14.459
Chapter 20.

05:37:14.759 --> 05:37:19.439
And so, Sonny finished, I decided we

05:37:19.439 --> 05:37:20.700
shouldn't wait any longer.

05:37:20.759 --> 05:37:23.400
Maybe we'll never find the Eye of Onyx

05:37:23.400 --> 05:37:25.560
but we can still choose a queen and end

05:37:25.560 --> 05:37:25.919
the war.

05:37:25.979 --> 05:37:29.279
Someone has to, and I think it should be

05:37:29.279 --> 05:37:29.520
us.

05:37:29.580 --> 05:37:32.220
She paused and looked around at her

05:37:32.220 --> 05:37:34.259
friends, whose faces ranged from

05:37:34.259 --> 05:37:37.080
disbelieving to astonished, too terribly

05:37:37.080 --> 05:37:37.380
worried.

05:37:37.439 --> 05:37:40.500
I can't believe all of that happened to

05:37:40.500 --> 05:37:43.860
you, Starflight said, in a low, shaken

05:37:43.860 --> 05:37:44.220
voice.

05:37:44.279 --> 05:37:46.619
And we weren't there to protect you

05:37:46.619 --> 05:37:49.500
Tsunami said, exchanging a glance with

05:37:49.500 --> 05:37:49.979
clay.

05:37:50.040 --> 05:37:52.799
She did all right, Glory said

05:37:52.799 --> 05:37:53.580
unexpectedly.

05:37:53.639 --> 05:37:55.919
Stealing the Obsidian mirror?

05:37:55.979 --> 05:37:57.180
That was crazy brave.

05:37:57.240 --> 05:38:00.659
Crazy and brave, I mean, and talking

05:38:00.659 --> 05:38:02.939
peril into saving Thorn.

05:38:03.000 --> 05:38:04.860
Well, that would have made me nervous.

05:38:04.919 --> 05:38:08.459
Also, confronting scavengers.

05:38:08.520 --> 05:38:11.279
Deathbringer chimed in, he gave a little

05:38:11.279 --> 05:38:12.720
shudder out to his wingtips.

05:38:12.779 --> 05:38:15.360
No, no, no, thanks, not for me.

05:38:15.419 --> 05:38:18.659
You're scared of scavengers?

05:38:18.720 --> 05:38:20.159
Glory asked amused.

05:38:20.220 --> 05:38:22.439
No, he said.

05:38:22.500 --> 05:38:23.580
I just...

05:38:23.580 --> 05:38:25.740
Give me the heebie jeebies, that's all.

05:38:25.799 --> 05:38:30.360
With their eyes and paws and faces.

05:38:30.419 --> 05:38:34.020
That's pretty cute, Glory said.

05:38:34.080 --> 05:38:37.020
The big bad assassin, terrified of itty

05:38:36.299 --> 05:38:37.799
bitty scavengers.

05:38:37.860 --> 05:38:40.979
One day, I'll throw a sword waving

05:38:40.979 --> 05:38:42.720
scavenger at you and see how tough you

05:38:42.720 --> 05:38:42.900
are.

05:38:43.020 --> 05:38:43.979
He bridled.

05:38:44.040 --> 05:38:48.000
But, Sonny, Clay interjected.

05:38:48.060 --> 05:38:49.919
We can't stop the war.

05:38:49.979 --> 05:38:52.680
The prophecy isn't true, remember?

05:38:52.740 --> 05:38:54.240
So?

05:38:54.240 --> 05:38:54.959
she said.

05:38:55.020 --> 05:38:57.720
If there had never been a prophecy, would

05:38:57.720 --> 05:38:59.040
the war have to go on forever?

05:38:59.099 --> 05:39:01.919
No, it has to end sometime.

05:39:01.979 --> 05:39:04.319
I vote right now.

05:39:04.380 --> 05:39:07.680
But it doesn't have to be us, Starflight

05:39:07.680 --> 05:39:08.040
said.

05:39:08.099 --> 05:39:10.740
Then immediately added an almost a mumble

05:39:10.740 --> 05:39:12.599
Maybe it has to be us.

05:39:12.659 --> 05:39:15.720
He reached up to the leaves on his eyes

05:39:15.720 --> 05:39:17.819
remembered they were there, and lowered

05:39:17.819 --> 05:39:18.419
his claws again.

05:39:18.479 --> 05:39:22.259
No, fate speaker said, grabbing

05:39:22.259 --> 05:39:23.580
Starflight's talons.

05:39:23.639 --> 05:39:24.840
It doesn't have to be you.

05:39:24.900 --> 05:39:27.180
It especially doesn't have to be you.

05:39:27.240 --> 05:39:28.139
You've done enough.

05:39:28.200 --> 05:39:31.259
Sonny's right, though, he said.

05:39:31.319 --> 05:39:32.639
Why shouldn't it be us?

05:39:32.759 --> 05:39:34.979
Maybe everyone else is waiting for the

05:39:34.979 --> 05:39:37.319
prophecy, and so they don't realize they

05:39:37.319 --> 05:39:38.939
could end the war themselves.

05:39:39.000 --> 05:39:40.979
And think about all the dragons who need

05:39:40.979 --> 05:39:42.060
this war to be over.

05:39:42.119 --> 05:39:45.959
My brothers and sisters, said Clay.

05:39:46.020 --> 05:39:47.700
If they're still alive.

05:39:47.819 --> 05:39:51.840
Anemone, tsunami said, so she doesn't

05:39:51.840 --> 05:39:53.580
have to use her anima's powers and lose

05:39:53.580 --> 05:39:54.299
her soul.

05:39:54.360 --> 05:39:57.360
All the sand wings, Glory added.

05:39:57.419 --> 05:40:00.599
They need a queen and a unified kingdom.

05:40:00.659 --> 05:40:02.520
So will you help me?

05:40:02.580 --> 05:40:05.400
Sonny said, picking nervously at a vine

05:40:05.400 --> 05:40:07.560
of small star shaped red flowers that

05:40:07.560 --> 05:40:08.520
snaked through the window.

05:40:08.580 --> 05:40:12.119
Well, even if we did, what's the plan?

05:40:12.180 --> 05:40:14.580
Tsunami said practically.

05:40:14.639 --> 05:40:17.880
Pick a queen, and then Sand Deathbringer

05:40:17.880 --> 05:40:18.540
to kill the other two?

05:40:18.599 --> 05:40:20.400
Yikes.

05:40:20.459 --> 05:40:22.740
Deathbringer said, flaring his wings.

05:40:22.799 --> 05:40:24.959
Give me the easy job, why don't you?

05:40:25.020 --> 05:40:29.700
Oh, if only we knew Pyria's best assassin

05:40:29.700 --> 05:40:31.619
Glory mused teasingly.

05:40:31.680 --> 05:40:35.520
No, no, Sonny said, flapping between them

05:40:35.520 --> 05:40:37.080
before they could go too far down that

05:40:37.080 --> 05:40:37.319
road.

05:40:37.439 --> 05:40:38.819
No killing.

05:40:38.880 --> 05:40:42.119
It would be almost impossible, tsunami

05:40:42.119 --> 05:40:42.540
mused.

05:40:42.599 --> 05:40:44.580
I assume dragons have tried before.

05:40:44.639 --> 05:40:47.759
What if we got an animus to enchant

05:40:47.759 --> 05:40:49.680
something, Starflight suggested.

05:40:49.740 --> 05:40:52.979
That was Blister's plan to use anemone

05:40:52.979 --> 05:40:53.939
and it was a smart one.

05:40:54.000 --> 05:40:57.060
Enchanted Spear to go kill Burn, or

05:40:57.060 --> 05:40:58.860
perhaps we could put her life essence in

05:40:58.860 --> 05:41:00.720
a tree and set it on fire, or something

05:41:00.720 --> 05:41:01.139
like that.

05:41:01.200 --> 05:41:04.560
We are not making anemone do that.

05:41:04.680 --> 05:41:06.119
Tsunami snarled.

05:41:06.180 --> 05:41:07.680
Are you serious?

05:41:07.740 --> 05:41:09.840
Can an animus dragon really do those

05:41:09.840 --> 05:41:10.139
things?

05:41:10.200 --> 05:41:11.759
Fate speaker asked.

05:41:11.819 --> 05:41:13.619
That's absolutely terrifying.

05:41:13.680 --> 05:41:16.560
It's a little more complicated than that

05:41:16.560 --> 05:41:18.659
but basically, Deathbringer answered

05:41:18.659 --> 05:41:18.900
her.

05:41:18.959 --> 05:41:21.060
And yes, it's terrifying.

05:41:21.119 --> 05:41:25.020
No, Sonny said again, we're not going to

05:41:25.020 --> 05:41:25.439
kill them.

05:41:25.500 --> 05:41:29.220
I agree with tsunami, Clay said.

05:41:29.279 --> 05:41:32.040
We can't ask Anemone to use her powers.

05:41:32.099 --> 05:41:34.139
That would be awful for her.

05:41:34.200 --> 05:41:36.419
I wasn't thinking of anemone.

05:41:36.479 --> 05:41:37.860
Starflight protested.

05:41:37.919 --> 05:41:40.500
I was thinking of Sonny's father, stone

05:41:40.500 --> 05:41:40.979
mover.

05:41:41.040 --> 05:41:43.680
He's sort of beyond hope anyway, isn't

05:41:43.680 --> 05:41:43.860
he?

05:41:43.919 --> 05:41:45.119
Is he?

05:41:45.180 --> 05:41:47.700
Sonny closed her mouth to think about

05:41:47.700 --> 05:41:47.939
that.

05:41:48.000 --> 05:41:50.340
She had a feeling that if he used his

05:41:50.340 --> 05:41:52.560
magic again, that would be it for stone

05:41:52.560 --> 05:41:55.080
mover, especially if he used it for

05:41:55.080 --> 05:41:56.880
something as massive as killing 2

05:41:56.880 --> 05:41:57.540
dragons.

05:41:57.599 --> 05:41:59.099
But would it be worth it?

05:41:59.159 --> 05:42:01.380
To save the rest of Pyria?

05:42:01.439 --> 05:42:02.520
Would he do it?

05:42:02.580 --> 05:42:05.580
Could she bring herself to ask him to do

05:42:05.580 --> 05:42:05.819
it?

05:42:05.880 --> 05:42:09.119
He was disappointing that he was still

05:42:09.119 --> 05:42:09.599
her father.

05:42:09.659 --> 05:42:11.400
Didn't she want to get to know him

05:42:11.400 --> 05:42:11.700
better?

05:42:11.759 --> 05:42:15.299
With either of those options, we'd have

05:42:15.299 --> 05:42:17.340
to pick which sister we want to be queen

05:42:17.340 --> 05:42:20.220
Glory said, and they're all terrible.

05:42:20.279 --> 05:42:22.799
Blaze seems nice.

05:42:22.860 --> 05:42:24.840
Clay said optimistically.

05:42:24.900 --> 05:42:28.380
Blaze is a dizzy idiot, who'd be dead by

05:42:28.380 --> 05:42:29.939
day too, Glory said.

05:42:30.000 --> 05:42:33.000
I say blister, she's evil, but she's

05:42:33.000 --> 05:42:35.279
smart, so she'd probably rule the kingdom

05:42:35.279 --> 05:42:35.759
fine.

05:42:35.819 --> 05:42:37.919
And if we're her allies, she'll leave us

05:42:37.919 --> 05:42:39.419
alone, I think.

05:42:39.479 --> 05:42:40.919
Well, maybe not.

05:42:40.979 --> 05:42:43.919
Okay, probably not, but at least we'd

05:42:43.919 --> 05:42:44.340
know where she was.

05:42:44.400 --> 05:42:46.979
Wait, Sonny said.

05:42:47.099 --> 05:42:48.540
I don't want to kill any of them.

05:42:48.599 --> 05:42:52.740
Burn is the least awful, tsunami argued.

05:42:52.799 --> 05:42:54.779
She's mean, but she's not scheming.

05:42:54.840 --> 05:42:56.580
We'd see her coming if she tried anything

05:42:56.580 --> 05:42:57.000
on us.

05:42:57.060 --> 05:43:01.200
Mean and brutal, Starflight reminded

05:43:01.200 --> 05:43:01.380
her.

05:43:01.439 --> 05:43:03.720
Remember the murdered dragons in her

05:43:03.720 --> 05:43:06.000
collection, and the Skywing egg she

05:43:06.000 --> 05:43:06.599
smashed?

05:43:06.659 --> 05:43:09.540
Just an egg, not even a dragonette yet.

05:43:09.599 --> 05:43:12.240
As long as she's alive, I don't think

05:43:12.240 --> 05:43:12.840
we're safe.

05:43:12.900 --> 05:43:16.560
He paused, then added, I don't think

05:43:16.560 --> 05:43:17.880
Sonny will be safe.

05:43:17.939 --> 05:43:21.000
Sonny leaned over to brush his wing with

05:43:21.000 --> 05:43:21.659
hers.

05:43:21.720 --> 05:43:24.000
So how do we decide?

05:43:24.000 --> 05:43:25.259
Clay said.

05:43:25.319 --> 05:43:29.099
Who do we choose and who, and how?

05:43:29.159 --> 05:43:31.860
I mean, are we really going to?

05:43:31.860 --> 05:43:34.439
No, Sonny said.

05:43:34.500 --> 05:43:37.259
Listen, for once, please?

05:43:37.319 --> 05:43:40.020
But tsunami, glory, fate speaker, and

05:43:40.020 --> 05:43:42.000
death bringer all started talking over

05:43:42.000 --> 05:43:44.459
her at once, arguing about the sisters

05:43:44.459 --> 05:43:45.299
and how to get rid of them.

05:43:45.419 --> 05:43:48.240
Sonny clapped her talons over her ears

05:43:48.240 --> 05:43:50.220
and shouted, stop.

05:43:50.340 --> 05:43:51.599
I said stop.

05:43:51.720 --> 05:43:54.240
Everyone blinked at her in this sudden

05:43:54.240 --> 05:43:54.599
silence.

05:43:54.720 --> 05:43:59.700
No, she said again, more firmly, we are

05:43:59.700 --> 05:44:01.560
not killing any of them.

05:44:01.619 --> 05:44:03.959
We're not using magic to do something

05:44:03.959 --> 05:44:04.680
underhanded.

05:44:04.740 --> 05:44:07.139
We are going to get all 3 of them in one

05:44:07.139 --> 05:44:09.240
place, and then we will either have a

05:44:09.240 --> 05:44:12.180
competition, like the rain wings have, or

05:44:12.180 --> 05:44:13.979
we'll let all the sand wings decide.

05:44:14.040 --> 05:44:16.439
Let the sand wings decide?

05:44:16.500 --> 05:44:18.299
tsunami said skeptically.

05:44:18.360 --> 05:44:19.259
What?

05:44:19.319 --> 05:44:22.020
Like, when we decide things together?

05:44:22.080 --> 05:44:24.299
Starflight said, understanding

05:44:24.299 --> 05:44:24.840
immediately.

05:44:24.900 --> 05:44:28.619
By voting, or talking it out, like the

05:44:28.619 --> 05:44:30.779
Night Wings or Queen Coral's Council.

05:44:30.840 --> 05:44:33.119
All the sand wings?

05:44:33.180 --> 05:44:34.139
Glory said.

05:44:34.259 --> 05:44:35.700
I don't see how that could work.

05:44:35.759 --> 05:44:37.919
They'll never agree to it.

05:44:37.979 --> 05:44:40.259
Death bringer said, shaking his head.

05:44:40.319 --> 05:44:42.240
The sisters.

05:44:42.299 --> 05:44:43.439
They haven't been in one place together

05:44:43.439 --> 05:44:44.279
in over 18 years.

05:44:44.340 --> 05:44:46.560
They certainly won't put the decision

05:44:46.560 --> 05:44:48.119
about the throne and the claws of their

05:44:48.119 --> 05:44:48.840
future subjects.

05:44:48.900 --> 05:44:51.959
Well, that's what we're going to try

05:44:51.959 --> 05:44:53.939
Sonny said stubbornly.

05:44:54.000 --> 05:44:56.099
I think we can get them all together

05:44:56.099 --> 05:44:57.900
especially if you guys help me.

05:44:57.959 --> 05:45:00.180
But if you don't, it doesn't matter.

05:45:00.299 --> 05:45:01.860
I'm doing it anyway.

05:45:01.919 --> 05:45:04.919
She settled her wings back and looked at

05:45:04.919 --> 05:45:05.939
her friends defiantly.

05:45:06.000 --> 05:45:09.180
There was a long pause.

05:45:09.240 --> 05:45:10.319
Sonny could imagine what they were

05:45:10.319 --> 05:45:12.000
thinking, what they were about to say.

05:45:12.060 --> 05:45:15.000
Oh sonny, it's a sweet idea, but it'll

05:45:15.000 --> 05:45:15.360
never work.

05:45:15.419 --> 05:45:17.520
You have too much faith in the goodness

05:45:17.520 --> 05:45:18.180
of dragons.

05:45:18.240 --> 05:45:20.880
You're so naive and ridiculous.

05:45:20.939 --> 05:45:23.040
Why don't you work on a project here in

05:45:23.040 --> 05:45:25.560
the rainforest instead, like counting

05:45:25.560 --> 05:45:26.400
bananas or something?

05:45:26.520 --> 05:45:29.279
Your crazy ideas and obsession with the

05:45:29.279 --> 05:45:30.299
prophecy is just...

05:45:30.299 --> 05:45:33.180
All right, said Clay.

05:45:33.240 --> 05:45:34.200
I'm in.

05:45:34.259 --> 05:45:36.720
Sonny's heart leaped.

05:45:36.779 --> 05:45:37.740
She beamed at him.

05:45:37.799 --> 05:45:41.580
Me too. said Starflight, struggling to

05:45:41.580 --> 05:45:42.000
his feet.

05:45:42.060 --> 05:45:43.560
It's worth a try.

05:45:43.619 --> 05:45:44.819
I want it to work.

05:45:44.880 --> 05:45:47.220
But you need to rest.

05:45:47.279 --> 05:45:48.959
Fate speaker protested.

05:45:49.020 --> 05:45:51.119
We need to be safe.

05:45:51.180 --> 05:45:54.419
Starflight said, and we won't be safe, and

05:45:54.419 --> 05:45:55.919
neither will our friends and all the

05:45:55.919 --> 05:45:58.439
dragons who count on us until the war is

05:45:58.439 --> 05:45:59.099
over.

05:45:59.159 --> 05:46:01.680
I agree, said Glory.

05:46:01.740 --> 05:46:02.939
I'll help too.

05:46:03.000 --> 05:46:05.220
Although I can't leave my dragons here

05:46:05.220 --> 05:46:07.439
for long, not with the night wings so

05:46:07.439 --> 05:46:09.180
close by and not settled yet.

05:46:09.240 --> 05:46:12.299
The Night Wings are your dragons too

05:46:12.299 --> 05:46:12.659
now.

05:46:12.720 --> 05:46:14.459
Deathbringer pointed out.

05:46:14.520 --> 05:46:16.619
Sonny caught the way he looked at glory

05:46:16.619 --> 05:46:19.799
and thought, what he really means is, I

05:46:19.799 --> 05:46:22.380
am yours, now, and forever.

05:46:22.439 --> 05:46:25.259
Is that how Starflight feels about me?

05:46:25.319 --> 05:46:29.279
She glanced at him with his sad bandaged

05:46:29.279 --> 05:46:30.900
eyes and determined expression.

05:46:30.959 --> 05:46:32.400
I don't.

05:46:32.520 --> 05:46:34.680
I don't think that's how I feel about

05:46:34.680 --> 05:46:34.979
him.

05:46:35.040 --> 05:46:38.939
I mean, I love him, but not like that.

05:46:39.000 --> 05:46:42.119
Fine, tsunami said.

05:46:42.180 --> 05:46:44.040
Fine, yes, of course I'm in.

05:46:44.099 --> 05:46:45.959
It's never going to work, but I'll do it

05:46:45.959 --> 05:46:47.040
whatever it is.

05:46:47.099 --> 05:46:49.919
So, then, what are we doing?

05:46:49.979 --> 05:46:52.919
Suddenly they were all looking at Sonny.

05:46:52.979 --> 05:46:55.259
Even Starflight's face was tilted in her

05:46:55.259 --> 05:46:55.560
direction.

05:46:55.680 --> 05:46:58.020
You wanted their attention.

05:46:58.080 --> 05:47:00.540
You wanted them to listen to you.

05:47:00.599 --> 05:47:01.560
You'd better earn this.

05:47:01.619 --> 05:47:05.040
We start by sending a message to Bern

05:47:05.040 --> 05:47:08.099
Blister, and Blaze, she said firmly.

05:47:08.220 --> 05:47:10.979
We start with blister, and we get to her

05:47:10.979 --> 05:47:12.360
through the talons of peace.

05:47:12.419 --> 05:47:16.860
Chapter 21.

05:47:17.099 --> 05:47:21.240
This is awesome, Tsunami said.

05:47:21.299 --> 05:47:22.619
I'm so excited.

05:47:22.680 --> 05:47:25.319
Going to see my very favorite dragons in

05:47:25.319 --> 05:47:26.220
all of Pyria.

05:47:26.279 --> 05:47:28.380
Are you being glory now?

05:47:28.439 --> 05:47:29.459
Sonny asked.

05:47:29.520 --> 05:47:30.720
Queen of sarcasm?

05:47:30.779 --> 05:47:32.700
I can be sarcastic too.

05:47:32.759 --> 05:47:34.619
She doesn't get to be the queen of

05:47:34.619 --> 05:47:36.840
everything, tsunami grumbled.

05:47:36.900 --> 05:47:39.240
She tilted her wings to do another sweep

05:47:39.240 --> 05:47:40.020
over the shoreline.

05:47:40.080 --> 05:47:42.540
They were on the eastern outskirts of the

05:47:42.540 --> 05:47:44.639
mud kingdom, on the edge of the kingdom

05:47:44.639 --> 05:47:45.119
of the sea.

05:47:45.180 --> 05:47:48.119
Below them, the ocean rushed up onto the

05:47:48.119 --> 05:47:50.580
beach and then back, wave upon white

05:47:50.580 --> 05:47:51.299
topped wave.

05:47:51.360 --> 05:47:54.659
The sky was gray from edge to edge, and

05:47:54.659 --> 05:47:56.220
the air was wet with something that

05:47:56.220 --> 05:47:58.200
couldn't decide if it was mist or rain.

05:47:58.259 --> 05:48:00.180
It was dreary.

05:48:00.240 --> 05:48:02.880
Sunny missed the hot, dry desert.

05:48:02.939 --> 05:48:05.099
You can even tell it was almost the

05:48:05.099 --> 05:48:05.819
middle of the day.

05:48:05.880 --> 05:48:07.799
The sun was well hidden behind those

05:48:07.799 --> 05:48:08.819
ranks of clouds.

05:48:08.880 --> 05:48:11.400
Her wings felt unpleasantly damp as she

05:48:11.400 --> 05:48:13.080
circled around behind tsunami.

05:48:13.139 --> 05:48:16.080
Where is that blasted mud wing?

05:48:16.139 --> 05:48:18.299
Tsunami muttered, scanning the beach.

05:48:18.360 --> 05:48:21.540
I wish we hadn't had to bring him, Sonny

05:48:21.540 --> 05:48:21.779
said.

05:48:21.840 --> 05:48:23.880
I'm not convinced he really knows where

05:48:23.880 --> 05:48:24.360
he's going.

05:48:24.419 --> 05:48:26.939
I wish we could have brought our mudwing

05:48:26.939 --> 05:48:27.299
instead.

05:48:27.360 --> 05:48:30.360
Our medwing doesn't know where the talons

05:48:30.360 --> 05:48:32.819
of peace camp is, tsunami pointed out

05:48:32.819 --> 05:48:34.680
ogre supposedly does.

05:48:34.740 --> 05:48:38.279
Okre was the disagreeable mud wing Sonny

05:48:38.279 --> 05:48:39.360
had met in the rainforest.

05:48:39.419 --> 05:48:41.700
It turned out he was one of the alternate

05:48:41.700 --> 05:48:44.220
dragonettes as well, so he'd grown up

05:48:44.220 --> 05:48:46.200
with the talons of peace and had agreed

05:48:46.200 --> 05:48:48.299
to go back to them and guide Sonny and

05:48:48.299 --> 05:48:48.959
tsunami there.

05:48:49.080 --> 05:48:52.439
The other 2 options, Flame and Fate

05:48:52.439 --> 05:48:54.720
Speaker, had had slightly more violent

05:48:54.720 --> 05:48:55.740
reactions.

05:48:55.799 --> 05:48:58.020
Fate speaker had declared passionately

05:48:58.020 --> 05:48:59.759
that she wouldn't leave Starflight's

05:48:59.759 --> 05:48:59.939
side.

05:49:00.060 --> 05:49:02.520
She said he needed her, which gave Sonny

05:49:02.520 --> 05:49:05.040
another jealous twinge, and added that

05:49:05.040 --> 05:49:06.720
the talents never particularly liked her

05:49:06.720 --> 05:49:07.259
anyway.

05:49:07.319 --> 05:49:10.799
Flame, on the other talon, had thrown an

05:49:10.799 --> 05:49:12.720
entire bowl of mangoes at them, and

05:49:12.720 --> 05:49:15.000
roared that he wasn't letting anyone see

05:49:15.000 --> 05:49:17.639
him with his face all destroyed, least of

05:49:17.639 --> 05:49:19.680
all the talons who'd just handed him over

05:49:19.680 --> 05:49:21.299
to the stupid night wings in the 1st

05:49:21.299 --> 05:49:21.479
place.

05:49:21.540 --> 05:49:25.319
So they were stuck with ocher, which had

05:49:25.319 --> 05:49:27.419
meant 3 days of travel with a dragonette

05:49:27.419 --> 05:49:28.979
whom Sonny liked less and less.

05:49:29.040 --> 05:49:32.400
He was like the not funny, not adorable

05:49:32.400 --> 05:49:35.279
opposite of clay, constantly hungry, but

05:49:35.279 --> 05:49:37.319
in a pushy way, instead of a sweetly

05:49:37.319 --> 05:49:38.159
embarrassed way.

05:49:38.220 --> 05:49:40.560
He'd even made himself a sack out of

05:49:40.560 --> 05:49:43.080
leaves with a handle of vines that he

05:49:43.080 --> 05:49:45.360
could hang over his neck, and he'd filled

05:49:45.360 --> 05:49:46.680
this with half the fruits in the

05:49:46.680 --> 05:49:48.779
rainforest as far as Sunny could tell.

05:49:48.840 --> 05:49:51.540
That way he could eat and fly at the same

05:49:51.540 --> 05:49:53.880
time, dripping bright yellow and purple

05:49:53.880 --> 05:49:56.340
juice all over his brown scales, and

05:49:56.340 --> 05:49:58.979
spattering the ground below them, and

05:49:58.979 --> 05:50:01.020
incidentally, refusing to share.

05:50:01.080 --> 05:50:03.119
Not that she wanted anything from a bag

05:50:03.119 --> 05:50:04.860
he'd drooled all over anyway.

05:50:04.919 --> 05:50:08.939
Besides, tsunami added, Glory still needs

05:50:08.939 --> 05:50:10.799
clay back at camp to help with the night

05:50:10.799 --> 05:50:13.439
wings, especially if Queen Scarlet is on

05:50:13.439 --> 05:50:13.680
her way.

05:50:13.740 --> 05:50:16.680
I don't understand why she hasn't come

05:50:16.680 --> 05:50:19.080
after us yet, Sonny said with a shiver.

05:50:19.139 --> 05:50:21.540
She glanced down at her own small

05:50:21.540 --> 05:50:24.060
necklace, a pouch containing the dream

05:50:24.060 --> 05:50:24.479
visitor.

05:50:24.540 --> 05:50:26.639
They'd been using it for the last few

05:50:26.639 --> 05:50:28.439
days to check in with her friends back in

05:50:28.439 --> 05:50:30.720
the rainforest, but so far everything was

05:50:30.720 --> 05:50:31.740
quiet there.

05:50:31.799 --> 05:50:34.560
It made Sonny's scales feel wriggly and

05:50:34.560 --> 05:50:37.319
oversized, not knowing where Scarlet was

05:50:37.319 --> 05:50:38.880
and what she was plotting.

05:50:38.939 --> 05:50:41.939
Tsunami followed her gaze to the dream

05:50:41.939 --> 05:50:42.840
visitor pouch.

05:50:42.900 --> 05:50:46.200
We could have avoided this whole trip, she

05:50:46.200 --> 05:50:46.860
pointed out.

05:50:46.919 --> 05:50:48.659
Sonny shook her head.

05:50:48.720 --> 05:50:49.919
It's not safe.

05:50:49.979 --> 05:50:52.860
If we used the dream visitor to contact

05:50:52.860 --> 05:50:56.580
blister, or even the talons of peace, or

05:50:56.580 --> 05:50:58.979
to check on Scarlet, they might catch a

05:50:58.979 --> 05:51:00.959
glimpse of the rainforest and realize

05:51:00.959 --> 05:51:01.560
where we are.

05:51:01.619 --> 05:51:04.080
Like I figured out where the scavenger

05:51:04.080 --> 05:51:05.639
was when she dream visited me.

05:51:05.700 --> 05:51:08.279
Or Glory said she caught a glimpse of the

05:51:08.279 --> 05:51:10.259
weird link tower behind Scarlet too.

05:51:10.319 --> 05:51:11.759
We couldn't risk it.

05:51:11.819 --> 05:51:13.319
I know.

05:51:13.380 --> 05:51:14.819
Tsunami sighed.

05:51:14.939 --> 05:51:17.939
So here we are, looking for the talents

05:51:17.939 --> 05:51:18.299
of peace.

05:51:18.360 --> 05:51:21.779
My, your favorite dragons.

05:51:21.840 --> 05:51:23.040
Sonny finished for her.

05:51:23.099 --> 05:51:26.099
I don't trust them, tsunami added.

05:51:26.220 --> 05:51:29.220
That's why you're here, Sonny agreed.

05:51:29.279 --> 05:51:30.900
Because you think otherwise they might

05:51:30.900 --> 05:51:32.580
grab me and do something nefarious.

05:51:32.639 --> 05:51:35.700
Trapping us in an underground cave for 6

05:51:35.700 --> 05:51:37.020
years comes to mind.

05:51:37.080 --> 05:51:38.340
Tsunami muttered.

05:51:38.400 --> 05:51:41.340
Sunny squinted at a dark shape winging

05:51:41.340 --> 05:51:42.299
out of the fog up ahead.

05:51:42.360 --> 05:51:44.279
That's ogre, right?

05:51:44.340 --> 05:51:47.279
And there's someone with him, tsunami

05:51:47.279 --> 05:51:47.700
said.

05:51:47.759 --> 05:51:49.500
Snapping her head up and frowning

05:51:49.500 --> 05:51:50.099
fiercely.

05:51:50.220 --> 05:51:52.380
A few someone's.

05:51:52.439 --> 05:51:54.900
As the group of dragons came closer, she

05:51:54.900 --> 05:51:56.340
humped with surprise.

05:51:56.400 --> 05:51:59.400
I've seen that dragon before, she told

05:51:59.400 --> 05:52:00.000
Sonny.

05:52:00.060 --> 05:52:02.400
The one in the lead, the sea wing with

05:52:02.400 --> 05:52:04.020
the black spirals on his gales.

05:52:04.080 --> 05:52:06.840
I saw him meeting with riptide, the very

05:52:06.840 --> 05:52:08.759
1st time I saw riptide in the kingdom of

05:52:08.759 --> 05:52:09.060
the sea.

05:52:09.180 --> 05:52:11.759
I didn't realize at the time that he was

05:52:11.759 --> 05:52:12.720
with the talons of peace.

05:52:12.779 --> 05:52:16.259
He's flashing something at us, Sonny

05:52:16.259 --> 05:52:16.680
pointed out.

05:52:16.740 --> 05:52:19.319
The sea wings glow in the dark scales

05:52:19.319 --> 05:52:20.520
were lighting up in some kind of

05:52:20.520 --> 05:52:21.000
pattern.

05:52:21.060 --> 05:52:23.220
Tsunami growled.

05:52:23.279 --> 05:52:25.860
If he's with the talons, he should know

05:52:25.860 --> 05:52:28.500
that I don't understand aquatic, since he

05:52:28.500 --> 05:52:30.240
was probably one of the squidheads who

05:52:30.240 --> 05:52:31.799
made the decision not to teach it to me.

05:52:31.860 --> 05:52:34.139
Maybe I should go over there and thump

05:52:34.139 --> 05:52:36.119
him and then pretend I misunderstood what

05:52:36.119 --> 05:52:36.479
he was saying.

05:52:36.599 --> 05:52:40.259
I think he's just suggesting we land

05:52:40.259 --> 05:52:41.459
Sonny guessed.

05:52:41.520 --> 05:52:43.439
Since all the approaching dragons were

05:52:43.439 --> 05:52:44.880
now veering down toward the beach.

05:52:44.939 --> 05:52:46.860
Well, sure.

05:52:46.919 --> 05:52:49.380
I could have figured that out, tsunami

05:52:49.380 --> 05:52:49.799
said.

05:52:49.860 --> 05:52:52.139
But he didn't have to rub my snout in a

05:52:52.139 --> 05:52:52.619
ditty.

05:52:52.680 --> 05:52:55.259
She flapped on ahead and Sonny followed.

05:52:55.319 --> 05:52:58.439
They landed on the sand, which was wet

05:52:58.439 --> 05:53:00.180
and clumpy between Sonny's claws.

05:53:00.240 --> 05:53:03.840
Across from them were ogre and 5 dragons

05:53:03.840 --> 05:53:06.779
from the talons of peace, an ice wing, a

05:53:06.779 --> 05:53:09.900
sky wing, a sand wing, and 2 sea wings

05:53:09.900 --> 05:53:12.360
one of them green with black spirals on

05:53:12.360 --> 05:53:14.700
his scales, the other sky blue with dark

05:53:14.700 --> 05:53:15.419
blue horns.

05:53:15.479 --> 05:53:17.819
Wait, Sonny thought.

05:53:17.880 --> 05:53:19.740
I know that other sea wing.

05:53:19.799 --> 05:53:23.099
Riptide, tsunami cried.

05:53:23.159 --> 05:53:25.259
The blue dragon's whole face lit up.

05:53:25.319 --> 05:53:28.439
You're alive, he said, stepping forward.

05:53:28.500 --> 05:53:31.500
That's far enough, said the other Sea

05:53:31.500 --> 05:53:34.080
Wing. flaring one wing in riptide's way.

05:53:34.139 --> 05:53:37.860
Of course I am, tsunami said to Riptide

05:53:37.860 --> 05:53:39.900
ignoring the green dragon.

05:53:39.959 --> 05:53:41.040
What are you doing with these?

05:53:41.159 --> 05:53:43.860
Sonny kicked her as hard as she could.

05:53:43.919 --> 05:53:46.319
Remember why we're here, tsunami.

05:53:46.380 --> 05:53:48.599
No insulting the dragons were asking for

05:53:48.599 --> 05:53:48.840
help.

05:53:48.900 --> 05:53:52.200
Tsunami glared at her, but she seemed to

05:53:52.200 --> 05:53:52.619
get the message.

05:53:52.680 --> 05:53:56.159
With the talons of peace, she finished.

05:53:56.279 --> 05:53:58.439
Queen Carl threw me out.

05:53:58.500 --> 05:54:02.099
Riptide said sadly, furrowing lines in

05:54:02.099 --> 05:54:03.240
the sand with his claws.

05:54:03.299 --> 05:54:06.479
She considered killing me, or imprisoning

05:54:06.479 --> 05:54:08.939
me again, but she said I'd fought bravely

05:54:08.939 --> 05:54:11.220
in the Battle of the Summer Palace, so

05:54:11.220 --> 05:54:12.360
she let me leave with my life.

05:54:12.419 --> 05:54:14.520
I didn't know where else to go.

05:54:14.580 --> 05:54:16.860
I thought the talons might know where you

05:54:16.860 --> 05:54:19.560
were, but he trailed off.

05:54:19.619 --> 05:54:21.659
But we had no idea.

05:54:21.720 --> 05:54:24.659
Said the other Seawing, in a clipped, cold

05:54:24.659 --> 05:54:25.979
voice.

05:54:26.040 --> 05:54:27.599
Tsunami gave him an incredulous look.

05:54:27.659 --> 05:54:30.540
You're not seriously mad at us, are you?

05:54:30.599 --> 05:54:33.659
Because no, I am mad at you.

05:54:33.720 --> 05:54:34.500
That's how this works.

05:54:34.560 --> 05:54:36.959
This is Nautilus.

05:54:37.020 --> 05:54:40.020
Riptide interjected quickly, the leader

05:54:40.020 --> 05:54:41.040
of the talons of peace.

05:54:41.159 --> 05:54:45.479
For now, growled the Sky Wing, flicking

05:54:45.479 --> 05:54:47.159
her red tail back and forth, and

05:54:47.159 --> 05:54:49.020
glowering through a trail of smoke.

05:54:49.080 --> 05:54:51.060
Do you have the other dragonettes?

05:54:51.180 --> 05:54:53.639
She choked her head at ocher, who was

05:54:53.639 --> 05:54:55.259
munching his way through a banana, and

05:54:55.259 --> 05:54:57.599
eyeing the seashells around his claws, as

05:54:57.599 --> 05:54:59.099
if he was wondering whether they might be

05:54:59.099 --> 05:54:59.639
edible too.

05:54:59.700 --> 05:55:03.360
We don't have them, tsunami said.

05:55:03.419 --> 05:55:06.299
But we know where 2 of them are, Sonny

05:55:06.299 --> 05:55:06.720
added.

05:55:06.779 --> 05:55:08.580
Our friends help them get away from the

05:55:08.580 --> 05:55:09.119
night wings.

05:55:09.180 --> 05:55:11.459
They didn't want to come back here though

05:55:11.459 --> 05:55:12.540
tsunami said.

05:55:12.599 --> 05:55:13.380
We offered.

05:55:13.439 --> 05:55:15.779
The Skywings scowled at her.

05:55:15.840 --> 05:55:17.279
Which two?

05:55:17.400 --> 05:55:19.439
Is Viper one of them?

05:55:19.500 --> 05:55:21.060
demanded the Sandwing.

05:55:21.119 --> 05:55:22.799
Uh-oh.

05:55:22.860 --> 05:55:23.880
Sunny thought.

05:55:23.939 --> 05:55:26.279
She shook her head, but before she could

05:55:26.279 --> 05:55:28.619
answer, the ice wing hissed, there's a

05:55:28.619 --> 05:55:29.580
dragon coming this way.

05:55:29.639 --> 05:55:33.299
They all turned and saw someone flying

05:55:33.299 --> 05:55:35.220
over the cliffs around the beach, high

05:55:35.220 --> 05:55:35.880
above their heads.

05:55:35.939 --> 05:55:39.060
The sun caught on red scales, and all the

05:55:39.060 --> 05:55:40.560
dragons on the sand tensed.

05:55:40.619 --> 05:55:42.720
Is it a Skywing Scout?

05:55:42.779 --> 05:55:45.240
One of Ruby's soldiers, or someone

05:55:45.240 --> 05:55:46.200
working for Bern?

05:55:46.259 --> 05:55:48.599
Or Queen Scarlet?

05:55:48.659 --> 05:55:51.360
Sonny thought worriedly, before she

05:55:51.360 --> 05:55:53.700
realized this dragon was smaller and a

05:55:53.700 --> 05:55:54.299
different color.

05:55:54.419 --> 05:55:56.819
He was also clearly heading toward them

05:55:56.819 --> 05:55:58.560
as if he'd been watching them for a

05:55:58.560 --> 05:55:58.740
while.

05:55:58.799 --> 05:56:02.639
That looks like flame, said the Skywing

05:56:02.639 --> 05:56:03.180
squinting.

05:56:03.240 --> 05:56:04.560
But it can't be.

05:56:04.619 --> 05:56:06.180
What's wrong with his face?

05:56:06.240 --> 05:56:08.759
It might be flame.

05:56:08.819 --> 05:56:11.279
Sonny said, glancing at tsunami.

05:56:11.340 --> 05:56:12.540
He could have followed us.

05:56:12.599 --> 05:56:14.520
Maybe he changed his mind about coming

05:56:14.520 --> 05:56:14.759
back.

05:56:14.819 --> 05:56:17.700
Maybe he just didn't want to fly with us

05:56:17.700 --> 05:56:20.520
tsunami said, or with him anyway.

05:56:20.580 --> 05:56:22.860
She flipped her tail at ochre.

05:56:22.919 --> 05:56:25.500
Flame called the Sky Wing.

05:56:25.560 --> 05:56:26.639
Flame.

05:56:26.700 --> 05:56:29.400
The dragonette was soaring down toward

05:56:29.400 --> 05:56:30.000
the sand now.

05:56:30.060 --> 05:56:32.459
When he heard his name, he faltered in

05:56:32.459 --> 05:56:34.500
mid-flight and nearly crash landed on the

05:56:34.500 --> 05:56:34.799
dunes.

05:56:34.860 --> 05:56:39.000
Mother, he called back, wobbling upright

05:56:39.000 --> 05:56:39.299
again.

05:56:39.360 --> 05:56:42.419
The Sky Wing shoved past Sunny and

05:56:42.419 --> 05:56:44.520
Tsunami, and caught Flame as he dropped

05:56:44.520 --> 05:56:45.119
toward her.

05:56:45.180 --> 05:56:47.279
She let out a roar at the side of his

05:56:47.279 --> 05:56:47.759
face.

05:56:47.759 --> 05:56:49.619
What happened to you?

05:56:49.740 --> 05:56:50.520
Who did this?

05:56:50.580 --> 05:56:52.860
She wrapped her wings around him and

05:56:52.860 --> 05:56:53.520
pulled him close.

05:56:53.580 --> 05:56:57.540
Flame seemed to collapse into her, burying

05:56:57.540 --> 05:56:58.439
his head in her neck.

05:56:58.500 --> 05:57:01.860
Sonny heard muffled sobbing, and felt a

05:57:01.860 --> 05:57:03.779
wrenching stab of pity for the sky wing

05:57:03.779 --> 05:57:04.380
dragonette.

05:57:04.439 --> 05:57:07.259
She'd only ever seen his mean, prickly

05:57:07.259 --> 05:57:09.419
grouchy side, but clearly he could be

05:57:09.419 --> 05:57:10.740
someone else with someone who really

05:57:10.740 --> 05:57:11.400
cared about him.

05:57:11.459 --> 05:57:15.599
I miss my mother, she thought, wishing

05:57:15.599 --> 05:57:17.819
she had large, warm wings wrapped around

05:57:17.819 --> 05:57:18.779
her right then.

05:57:18.840 --> 05:57:21.479
I guess I've always missed her, but I

05:57:21.479 --> 05:57:22.979
miss her even more now that I know her.

05:57:23.040 --> 05:57:26.520
Thorn was so far away, on the other side

05:57:26.520 --> 05:57:27.119
of the continent.

05:57:27.180 --> 05:57:29.700
Sonny folded back her wings and lifted

05:57:29.700 --> 05:57:30.299
her chin.

05:57:30.360 --> 05:57:31.860
I'll see her again soon.

05:57:31.919 --> 05:57:34.259
As soon as this war is over.

05:57:34.319 --> 05:57:36.599
That's avalanche.

05:57:36.659 --> 05:57:39.900
Riptide said quietly to tsunami, nodding

05:57:39.900 --> 05:57:40.680
at flames, mother.

05:57:40.740 --> 05:57:43.560
She's a spy, so she normally lives in the

05:57:43.560 --> 05:57:46.020
Sky Palace, and she left Flame here to

05:57:46.020 --> 05:57:46.799
keep him out of the war.

05:57:46.860 --> 05:57:48.240
He hesitated.

05:57:48.299 --> 05:57:51.419
She was away when Maru Seer came and took

05:57:51.419 --> 05:57:52.380
the dragonettes.

05:57:52.439 --> 05:57:54.599
She was furious when she came back and

05:57:54.599 --> 05:57:55.200
found him gone.

05:57:55.259 --> 05:57:57.540
She nearly killed Nautilus.

05:57:57.599 --> 05:58:00.959
Nautilus shifted uneasily on his talons.

05:58:01.020 --> 05:58:03.779
Some dragons don't understand the things

05:58:03.779 --> 05:58:07.439
we have to do for peace, he said, but not

05:58:07.439 --> 05:58:08.939
in a way that sounded like he meant it.

05:58:09.000 --> 05:58:12.419
Do. Do I want to know what happened to

05:58:12.419 --> 05:58:12.779
the others?

05:58:12.779 --> 05:58:13.619
he asked.

05:58:13.680 --> 05:58:15.720
Fate speaker is fine.

05:58:15.779 --> 05:58:17.880
Sonny said, but we don't know what

05:58:17.880 --> 05:58:20.220
happened to Squid, and Viper is dead.

05:58:20.279 --> 05:58:23.040
The sand wing across from her snarled and

05:58:23.040 --> 05:58:24.240
raised his venomous tail.

05:58:24.299 --> 05:58:25.200
How?

05:58:25.259 --> 05:58:28.799
An accident in the night kingdom, tsunami

05:58:28.799 --> 05:58:29.159
answered.

05:58:29.279 --> 05:58:31.319
Piper was fighting and fell into some

05:58:31.319 --> 05:58:31.799
lava.

05:58:31.860 --> 05:58:34.020
It was her tail that did that to Flame's

05:58:34.020 --> 05:58:34.319
face.

05:58:34.380 --> 05:58:37.200
We need Morrow seer.

05:58:37.319 --> 05:58:38.520
Nautilus growled.

05:58:38.639 --> 05:58:40.500
Several of us would like to have words

05:58:40.500 --> 05:58:41.040
with him.

05:58:41.099 --> 05:58:43.500
Words and teeth and claws.

05:58:43.560 --> 05:58:46.979
And tails, added the sandwing.

05:58:47.099 --> 05:58:49.439
He looked angry, but not devastated.

05:58:49.500 --> 05:58:51.779
Sonny wondered if he was an uncle instead

05:58:51.779 --> 05:58:53.279
of Viper's father or something like

05:58:53.279 --> 05:58:53.520
that.

05:58:53.580 --> 05:58:57.119
Marosir is dead too, Sonny said.

05:58:57.180 --> 05:58:58.619
So we need your help.

05:58:58.680 --> 05:59:00.240
Oh, really?

05:59:00.240 --> 05:59:01.799
said Nautilus.

05:59:01.860 --> 05:59:03.900
Suddenly, the wonderful independent

05:59:03.900 --> 05:59:05.159
dragonettes need us.

05:59:05.279 --> 05:59:08.880
Don't be a rotting tooth, Tsunami said to

05:59:08.880 --> 05:59:09.119
him.

05:59:09.180 --> 05:59:11.220
If you want this prophecy fulfilled and

05:59:11.220 --> 05:59:13.740
this war stopped, you'll help us, so shut

05:59:13.740 --> 05:59:14.040
up.

05:59:14.159 --> 05:59:16.619
He opened and closed his mouth a few

05:59:16.619 --> 05:59:18.599
times, then settled for flashing

05:59:18.599 --> 05:59:20.639
something with his luminescent stripes

05:59:20.639 --> 05:59:22.319
that Sunny guessed she wouldn't want

05:59:22.319 --> 05:59:22.799
translated.

05:59:22.860 --> 05:59:26.340
We need to send a message to Blister, she

05:59:26.340 --> 05:59:26.700
said.

05:59:26.759 --> 05:59:28.560
You're the only ones we could think of

05:59:28.560 --> 05:59:29.759
who might be able to reach her.

05:59:29.819 --> 05:59:33.180
She's looking for you pretty seriously

05:59:33.180 --> 05:59:34.319
Riptide said.

05:59:34.439 --> 05:59:36.659
You probably just have to stand out in

05:59:36.659 --> 05:59:38.099
the open for a day and she'll land on

05:59:38.099 --> 05:59:38.279
you.

05:59:38.340 --> 05:59:40.380
Right, sure.

05:59:40.439 --> 05:59:43.200
Tsunami answered, except we're trying to

05:59:43.200 --> 05:59:45.000
do this in a not ending a dead way?

05:59:45.119 --> 05:59:47.340
Fair enough, he said.

05:59:47.400 --> 05:59:48.299
Good idea.

05:59:48.360 --> 05:59:49.439
I support that plan.

05:59:49.500 --> 05:59:52.259
What do you want us to tell her?

05:59:52.380 --> 05:59:53.580
Nautilus asked.

05:59:53.639 --> 05:59:55.860
If we can get in touch with her.

05:59:55.919 --> 05:59:58.680
And if we agree to do this.

05:59:58.740 --> 06:00:02.040
Sonny looked him in the eye, knowing

06:00:02.040 --> 06:00:03.900
perfectly well that he'd do anything she

06:00:03.900 --> 06:00:05.939
said if it meant a chance at peace.

06:00:06.000 --> 06:00:08.400
He may have made some terrible decisions

06:00:08.400 --> 06:00:11.099
over the last 7 years, but she believed

06:00:11.099 --> 06:00:12.900
that he did care about one thing very

06:00:12.900 --> 06:00:15.419
much, and that was ending the war.

06:00:15.479 --> 06:00:18.299
Tell her to meet us on the 10th midnight

06:00:18.299 --> 06:00:20.880
from tonight. she said, in the entrance

06:00:20.880 --> 06:00:22.740
courtyard of the stronghold in the

06:00:22.740 --> 06:00:23.459
kingdom of sand.

06:00:23.520 --> 06:00:26.819
If she doesn't show up, she forfeits her

06:00:26.819 --> 06:00:27.599
chance to be Queen.

06:00:27.720 --> 06:00:29.279
This is it?

06:00:29.340 --> 06:00:31.020
The sand wing demanded.

06:00:31.080 --> 06:00:32.880
You're fulfilling the prophecy in

06:00:32.880 --> 06:00:33.599
choosing a queen?

06:00:33.659 --> 06:00:34.740
It's blister.

06:00:34.799 --> 06:00:37.439
Come along and see, Sonny offered.

06:00:37.500 --> 06:00:38.819
Anyone who wants to?

06:00:38.880 --> 06:00:40.799
Bring all the talents of peace.

06:00:40.860 --> 06:00:43.200
If it goes the way it should, you won't

06:00:43.200 --> 06:00:44.099
be fugitives anymore.

06:00:44.159 --> 06:00:46.680
If blister shows up and everything goes

06:00:46.680 --> 06:00:49.139
as planned, then the war will be over.

06:00:49.200 --> 06:00:52.799
We'll think about it, Nautilus said.

06:00:52.860 --> 06:00:55.020
But even he had an unmistakable

06:00:55.020 --> 06:00:56.639
undercurrent of excitement in his voice.

06:00:56.759 --> 06:00:59.939
It's important to tell her, Sonny

06:00:59.939 --> 06:01:01.979
insisted, we don't know how else to reach

06:01:01.979 --> 06:01:02.220
her.

06:01:02.279 --> 06:01:06.659
We're not like friends with her, Riptide

06:01:06.659 --> 06:01:08.099
said, just so you know.

06:01:08.159 --> 06:01:10.259
It's not like the talons of peace are

06:01:10.259 --> 06:01:11.459
working with her, I swear.

06:01:11.580 --> 06:01:13.500
But you can find her?

06:01:13.500 --> 06:01:14.580
Tsunami asked.

06:01:14.639 --> 06:01:17.340
She sends one of her soldiers to the

06:01:17.340 --> 06:01:19.020
ruins of the summer palace pretty much

06:01:19.020 --> 06:01:22.200
every day, Nautilus said, hoping for a

06:01:22.200 --> 06:01:23.520
message from Queen Coral.

06:01:23.580 --> 06:01:25.020
That's how we'll reach her.

06:01:25.139 --> 06:01:27.720
Good, tsunami said.

06:01:27.779 --> 06:01:30.119
Thank you, Sonny added.

06:01:30.180 --> 06:01:31.740
She turned to tsunami.

06:01:31.799 --> 06:01:33.060
Then we'd better go.

06:01:33.180 --> 06:01:35.759
So we can send our messages to the other

06:01:35.759 --> 06:01:36.540
2 sisters.

06:01:36.599 --> 06:01:38.580
We only have 10 days now.

06:01:38.639 --> 06:01:41.700
Tsunami swept her tail through the sand

06:01:41.700 --> 06:01:43.139
and looked over at Riptide.

06:01:43.200 --> 06:01:46.200
I could come with you.

06:01:46.259 --> 06:01:49.200
He said hesitantly, as if he wasn't sure

06:01:49.200 --> 06:01:49.979
he'd be welcome.

06:01:50.040 --> 06:01:54.240
I think, tsunami said, it'd be better if

06:01:54.240 --> 06:01:56.279
you stay and make sure blister shows up

06:01:56.279 --> 06:01:56.939
at the stronghold.

06:01:57.060 --> 06:01:59.520
Then bring some of the talons of peace

06:01:59.520 --> 06:01:59.880
with you.

06:01:59.939 --> 06:02:01.740
And I'll see you there.

06:02:01.799 --> 06:02:04.799
He nodded, tilting his wings back with a

06:02:04.799 --> 06:02:05.580
hopeful expression.

06:02:05.639 --> 06:02:08.220
Alright, tsunami said.

06:02:08.279 --> 06:02:09.419
See you soon.

06:02:09.479 --> 06:02:11.580
It sounded like a promise.

06:02:11.639 --> 06:02:15.540
Bye, Ocher, Sonny said, making one last

06:02:15.540 --> 06:02:17.400
effort to be friendly to the unlikable

06:02:17.400 --> 06:02:18.060
dragon.

06:02:18.060 --> 06:02:20.159
The mud wing had gotten his claws stuck

06:02:20.159 --> 06:02:22.560
in a pineapple as he tried to peel it and

06:02:22.560 --> 06:02:23.580
was now trying to shake it off.

06:02:23.700 --> 06:02:25.439
Have a nice life.

06:02:25.500 --> 06:02:28.319
Yeah, yeah, he muttered.

06:02:28.380 --> 06:02:30.540
He accidentally whacked himself in the

06:02:30.540 --> 06:02:32.459
snout with the top of the pineapple and

06:02:32.459 --> 06:02:33.659
yelped with pain.

06:02:33.720 --> 06:02:36.299
Tsunami and Sonny rolled their eyes at

06:02:36.299 --> 06:02:38.159
each other and lifted off into the sky.

06:02:38.220 --> 06:02:41.400
They flew over Flame and his mother, still

06:02:41.400 --> 06:02:42.599
wrapped around each other on the beach.

06:02:42.659 --> 06:02:46.020
Sonny felt another jab of pity, although

06:02:46.020 --> 06:02:47.819
she knew the Sky Wing dragonette didn't

06:02:47.819 --> 06:02:48.540
want to be seen that way.

06:02:48.599 --> 06:02:51.720
She glanced back as they reached the edge

06:02:51.720 --> 06:02:53.400
of the beach, and saw that the other

06:02:53.400 --> 06:02:55.860
dragons had turned to leave, but riptide

06:02:55.860 --> 06:02:57.000
was still staring after them.

06:02:57.060 --> 06:02:58.860
Are you all right?

06:02:58.919 --> 06:03:00.900
Sonny asked tsunami.

06:03:00.959 --> 06:03:02.700
I mean, about riptide?

06:03:02.819 --> 06:03:05.040
Have you forgiven him for lying to about

06:03:05.040 --> 06:03:05.700
being a talent?

06:03:05.819 --> 06:03:08.279
Tsunami gave her a rueful look?

06:03:08.340 --> 06:03:11.040
It's complicated, she said.

06:03:11.099 --> 06:03:14.159
I hate being lied to, and the talons are

06:03:14.159 --> 06:03:16.380
the worst, but when I saw that he was

06:03:16.380 --> 06:03:19.799
alive, I was just really, really happy.

06:03:19.860 --> 06:03:21.000
Is that weird?

06:03:21.060 --> 06:03:23.639
No, Sonny said.

06:03:23.700 --> 06:03:25.080
I know what you mean.

06:03:25.139 --> 06:03:27.959
I'll see how I feel after the war is over

06:03:27.959 --> 06:03:29.099
tsunami said.

06:03:29.220 --> 06:03:31.380
When everything's a little more normal.

06:03:31.439 --> 06:03:33.900
Not that we know anything about normal or

06:03:33.900 --> 06:03:35.700
what that's supposed to look like, right?

06:03:35.759 --> 06:03:39.720
But then I think, well, we'll see.

06:03:39.779 --> 06:03:42.540
I hope blister shows up.

06:03:42.599 --> 06:03:44.880
Sonny said, as they soared up over the

06:03:44.880 --> 06:03:45.299
cliffs.

06:03:45.360 --> 06:03:47.159
I hope this works.

06:03:47.220 --> 06:03:50.759
It will, tsunami said confidently.

06:03:50.819 --> 06:03:52.740
We'll get all 3 sisters to the

06:03:52.740 --> 06:03:53.279
stronghold.

06:03:53.340 --> 06:03:55.139
I'm not worried about that.

06:03:55.200 --> 06:03:57.240
What happens once we're all there

06:03:57.240 --> 06:03:57.360
though?

06:03:57.479 --> 06:03:59.819
That part worries me quite a lot.

06:03:59.939 --> 06:04:04.500
Chapter 22.

06:04:04.680 --> 06:04:08.459
In some ways, burn and blades should have

06:04:08.459 --> 06:04:09.900
been easier to send a message to.

06:04:10.020 --> 06:04:13.020
They both had a fixed home base. burn at

06:04:13.020 --> 06:04:15.299
the stronghold, blaze in her fortress in

06:04:15.299 --> 06:04:17.639
the ice kingdom, but Sonny was not about

06:04:17.639 --> 06:04:19.740
to waltz into either place, and she

06:04:19.740 --> 06:04:21.479
didn't want to send anyone she knew to

06:04:21.479 --> 06:04:21.779
face them.

06:04:21.900 --> 06:04:25.139
She didn't trust Bern or Queen Glacier

06:04:25.139 --> 06:04:26.279
not to just kill the messenger.

06:04:26.400 --> 06:04:29.819
After a lot of arguing, though, Glory had

06:04:29.819 --> 06:04:31.200
offered a solution for Blaze.

06:04:31.259 --> 06:04:34.080
Sanda Rainwing disguised as an ice wing

06:04:34.080 --> 06:04:34.979
to pass the message along.

06:04:35.099 --> 06:04:38.880
Send me, was her actual suggestion.

06:04:38.939 --> 06:04:41.099
I could be there and back in a couple of

06:04:41.099 --> 06:04:41.340
days.

06:04:41.400 --> 06:04:43.319
Absolutely not.

06:04:43.380 --> 06:04:45.000
Deathbringer had said.

06:04:45.060 --> 06:04:46.979
You are the dragon holding this

06:04:46.979 --> 06:04:47.880
rainforest together.

06:04:47.939 --> 06:04:49.380
Two tribes depend on you.

06:04:49.500 --> 06:04:52.200
If anything happens, you're leaving chaos

06:04:52.200 --> 06:04:54.540
behind, and Blaze will probably recognize

06:04:54.540 --> 06:04:54.720
you.

06:04:54.779 --> 06:04:59.099
True, Clay had agreed, but you could send

06:04:59.099 --> 06:04:59.759
someone else.

06:04:59.819 --> 06:05:01.319
Maybe Jambu?

06:05:01.439 --> 06:05:03.180
He's been there before.

06:05:03.240 --> 06:05:04.380
Sonny pointed out.

06:05:04.439 --> 06:05:06.659
He knows where Blaze's fortress is.

06:05:06.720 --> 06:05:08.819
He's already changed his scales to look

06:05:08.819 --> 06:05:10.860
like an ice wing, so he should be able to

06:05:10.860 --> 06:05:11.340
do it again.

06:05:11.400 --> 06:05:12.959
Glory snorted.

06:05:13.020 --> 06:05:15.959
As long as he doesn't fall asleep or get

06:05:15.959 --> 06:05:17.459
distracted by something shiny.

06:05:17.520 --> 06:05:20.819
Or I could go, Deathbringer offered.

06:05:20.880 --> 06:05:22.139
I know where it is too.

06:05:22.200 --> 06:05:23.819
Absolutely not.

06:05:23.939 --> 06:05:26.639
Glory had echoed back at him, only half

06:05:26.639 --> 06:05:27.060
teasing.

06:05:27.119 --> 06:05:29.099
Remember the part where you tried to kill

06:05:29.099 --> 06:05:30.299
Blaze?

06:05:30.360 --> 06:05:32.639
You're the last dragon she'd trust.

06:05:32.700 --> 06:05:35.340
Glacier probably has soldiers prepared to

06:05:35.340 --> 06:05:36.119
kill you on site.

06:05:36.180 --> 06:05:38.340
She's probably told them to kill any

06:05:38.340 --> 06:05:40.500
night wing who comes along just in case

06:05:40.500 --> 06:05:40.919
it's you.

06:05:40.979 --> 06:05:44.279
Oh, Deathbringer said.

06:05:44.340 --> 06:05:46.740
You totally care if I live or die too.

06:05:46.799 --> 06:05:49.799
Sonny could practically see the struggle

06:05:49.799 --> 06:05:52.259
in glory's scales, as she tried to stamp

06:05:52.259 --> 06:05:54.060
out any bits of pink that were trying to

06:05:54.060 --> 06:05:54.479
sneak through.

06:05:54.540 --> 06:05:57.180
Well, sure, she said.

06:05:57.240 --> 06:05:59.159
A dead messenger wouldn't do us much good

06:05:59.159 --> 06:05:59.400
at all.

06:05:59.459 --> 06:06:03.000
Deathbringer laughed, and Sunny realized

06:06:03.000 --> 06:06:05.220
that he was deliberately provoking glory

06:06:05.220 --> 06:06:06.959
because he liked the way she shot him

06:06:06.959 --> 06:06:07.200
down.

06:06:07.259 --> 06:06:09.779
If that's what he's looking for in a

06:06:09.779 --> 06:06:12.540
dragon, she thought, he certainly picked

06:06:12.540 --> 06:06:12.959
the right one.

06:06:13.020 --> 06:06:16.200
Send Jambu and Mangrove.

06:06:16.259 --> 06:06:17.279
Sonny suggested.

06:06:17.340 --> 06:06:19.380
They both know the way, and they can keep

06:06:19.380 --> 06:06:20.220
an eye on each other.

06:06:20.279 --> 06:06:22.919
Everyone had agreed to this plan

06:06:22.919 --> 06:06:26.099
including Jambu and Mangrove, but Sonny

06:06:26.099 --> 06:06:27.959
still felt anxious as she watched the 2

06:06:27.959 --> 06:06:29.939
rain wings slip into the tunnel that led

06:06:29.939 --> 06:06:31.020
to the kingdom of sand.

06:06:31.080 --> 06:06:33.840
It was the day she and tsunami got back

06:06:33.840 --> 06:06:34.799
from the talons of peace.

06:06:34.860 --> 06:06:37.380
The flight had taken them 3 days with

06:06:37.380 --> 06:06:38.639
almost no stops.

06:06:38.700 --> 06:06:41.340
Seven to go, she thought.

06:06:41.400 --> 06:06:43.080
Be safe.

06:06:43.139 --> 06:06:45.419
Glory said to them, that's an order from

06:06:45.419 --> 06:06:45.959
your queen.

06:06:46.020 --> 06:06:50.159
Yes, Your Majesty, Jambu answered.

06:06:50.220 --> 06:06:52.439
Grinning in a way that suggested he just

06:06:52.439 --> 06:06:54.900
liked saying those words, not that he was

06:06:54.900 --> 06:06:55.319
actually listening.

06:06:55.439 --> 06:06:58.680
Steak camouflaged as much as you can. the

06:06:58.680 --> 06:07:00.479
whole way there, and you don't have to go

06:07:00.479 --> 06:07:02.819
into the fortress, or even all the way to

06:07:02.819 --> 06:07:03.360
the fortress.

06:07:03.419 --> 06:07:05.700
If you find an ice wing patrol before you

06:07:05.700 --> 06:07:08.159
get there, tell them to tell Blaze, and

06:07:08.159 --> 06:07:10.139
then you come home, right away.

06:07:10.200 --> 06:07:10.860
Understand?

06:07:10.919 --> 06:07:13.500
Yep, said Mangrove.

06:07:13.560 --> 06:07:16.259
We still understand, like we did 5

06:07:16.259 --> 06:07:18.119
minutes ago when you last explained it.

06:07:18.180 --> 06:07:20.459
And 5 minutes before that.

06:07:20.520 --> 06:07:25.500
And all right, go away, Glory said

06:07:25.500 --> 06:07:26.459
flicking her tongue out at them.

06:07:26.580 --> 06:07:29.340
Remember to tell them she has to show up

06:07:29.340 --> 06:07:31.860
Sonny called, or else she doesn't get to

06:07:31.860 --> 06:07:32.400
be queen.

06:07:32.459 --> 06:07:34.560
Make sure that part of the message gets

06:07:34.560 --> 06:07:35.400
to Glacier.

06:07:35.459 --> 06:07:38.819
She was the least sure about Blaise, who

06:07:38.819 --> 06:07:40.500
seemed perfectly happy to hide in her

06:07:40.500 --> 06:07:42.779
fortress and let other dragons do all the

06:07:42.779 --> 06:07:43.380
fighting for her.

06:07:43.439 --> 06:07:46.740
If she was going to show up, Sonny had a

06:07:46.740 --> 06:07:48.540
feeling it would be only because Queen

06:07:48.540 --> 06:07:49.619
Glacier dragged her there.

06:07:49.680 --> 06:07:52.500
As soon as their tails had disappeared

06:07:52.500 --> 06:07:53.700
Sonny turned to clay.

06:07:53.759 --> 06:07:54.959
Ready?

06:07:55.020 --> 06:07:57.540
Sure, Clay said.

06:07:57.599 --> 06:08:00.000
I mean, I've eaten breakfast.

06:08:00.060 --> 06:08:01.439
What else do I need to do?

06:08:01.500 --> 06:08:04.740
Oh, maybe some more breakfast.

06:08:04.799 --> 06:08:05.819
That's a good idea.

06:08:05.939 --> 06:08:08.880
Sonny laughed, and soon the 2 of them

06:08:08.880 --> 06:08:10.860
were aloft, soaring north through the

06:08:10.860 --> 06:08:12.479
rainforest toward the mud kingdom.

06:08:12.540 --> 06:08:15.540
Do you think anyone will listen to us?

06:08:15.599 --> 06:08:18.119
Clay asked her after they'd flown for a

06:08:18.119 --> 06:08:18.360
while.

06:08:18.419 --> 06:08:20.880
The landscape below was shifting from

06:08:20.880 --> 06:08:23.520
jungle to swamp, with shorter trees and

06:08:23.520 --> 06:08:25.439
brownish green ponds visible here and

06:08:25.439 --> 06:08:25.680
there.

06:08:25.740 --> 06:08:28.080
In the distance to their right, they

06:08:28.080 --> 06:08:29.759
could see a shimmer of water that had to

06:08:29.759 --> 06:08:30.779
be the big lake.

06:08:30.840 --> 06:08:33.299
That's where Queen Morin's palace was.

06:08:33.360 --> 06:08:36.000
They were definitely not going there.

06:08:36.060 --> 06:08:39.240
Sunny tilted her wings to the west

06:08:39.240 --> 06:08:40.439
heading for the mountains.

06:08:40.500 --> 06:08:43.319
I think someone will listen, she said.

06:08:43.380 --> 06:08:46.259
We just have to find the right someone, a

06:08:46.259 --> 06:08:49.259
mudwing patrol, I think, not Skywings or

06:08:49.259 --> 06:08:49.979
Sandwings.

06:08:50.040 --> 06:08:51.900
I bet they'll listen to you anyway.

06:08:51.959 --> 06:08:55.200
As far as she was concerned, Clay could

06:08:55.200 --> 06:08:57.779
talk anyone into anything, because anyone

06:08:57.779 --> 06:08:59.700
could see that he was sincere and wanted

06:08:59.700 --> 06:09:00.659
the best for everybody.

06:09:00.720 --> 06:09:04.139
Clay rumbled nervously deep in his throat

06:09:04.139 --> 06:09:06.479
maybe we don't have to do this.

06:09:06.540 --> 06:09:09.419
Maybe Bern will stay in her stronghold

06:09:09.419 --> 06:09:10.979
and just be there when we get there.

06:09:11.040 --> 06:09:14.400
She's more likely to go out again, looking

06:09:14.400 --> 06:09:16.860
for another battle, Sonny said.

06:09:16.919 --> 06:09:19.560
She thought for a moment, then added, or

06:09:19.560 --> 06:09:20.700
looking for us.

06:09:20.759 --> 06:09:22.979
No, we have to make sure she'll be there

06:09:22.979 --> 06:09:24.840
in 7 days, or this won't work.

06:09:24.900 --> 06:09:28.080
They found a sheltered grove of pines at

06:09:28.080 --> 06:09:29.159
the foot of the mountains where they

06:09:29.159 --> 06:09:29.759
could sleep that night.

06:09:29.880 --> 06:09:32.639
There had been surprisingly few dragons

06:09:32.639 --> 06:09:35.759
out that day, a few solitary scouts, and

06:09:35.759 --> 06:09:38.279
some 2 dragon patrols, but Sunny had

06:09:38.279 --> 06:09:39.419
decided to avoid them all.

06:09:39.540 --> 06:09:41.759
She wanted to get farther away from

06:09:41.759 --> 06:09:44.220
Morehen's palace, just in case anyone

06:09:44.220 --> 06:09:45.959
tried to drag her and Clay back there.

06:09:46.020 --> 06:09:48.900
She'd expected to see more soldiers out

06:09:48.900 --> 06:09:49.560
and about, though.

06:09:49.680 --> 06:09:52.200
It was a little unsettling how quiet the

06:09:52.200 --> 06:09:52.680
skies were.

06:09:52.740 --> 06:09:55.680
Clay was thoughtfully watching the stars

06:09:55.680 --> 06:09:57.720
as she curled up against him in the

06:09:57.720 --> 06:09:57.900
dark.

06:09:58.020 --> 06:10:00.779
Sonny, he whispered.

06:10:00.840 --> 06:10:03.479
I know I'm bad at remembering stuff, but

06:10:03.479 --> 06:10:06.840
Pyre only has 3 moons, right?

06:10:06.900 --> 06:10:09.599
Of course, she whispered back.

06:10:09.659 --> 06:10:10.979
Why?

06:10:11.040 --> 06:10:14.880
That thing over there, he said. pointing

06:10:14.880 --> 06:10:15.659
with one of his wings.

06:10:15.720 --> 06:10:18.659
It looks kind of like a moon coming this

06:10:18.659 --> 06:10:18.840
way.

06:10:18.900 --> 06:10:22.080
Sunny followed his gaze to a glowing

06:10:22.080 --> 06:10:22.799
shape in the sky.

06:10:22.860 --> 06:10:24.959
It was bigger than the other stars

06:10:24.959 --> 06:10:27.540
although not quite as big or round as a

06:10:27.540 --> 06:10:27.779
moon.

06:10:27.840 --> 06:10:30.299
She couldn't remember ever noticing it

06:10:30.299 --> 06:10:30.479
before.

06:10:30.540 --> 06:10:33.659
Freaky, she said.

06:10:33.720 --> 06:10:34.799
I wonder what it is.

06:10:34.860 --> 06:10:37.380
Not one of the regular moons.

06:10:37.439 --> 06:10:40.619
Look, you can see all the others there

06:10:40.619 --> 06:10:43.500
and there, and over there, right on the

06:10:43.500 --> 06:10:44.279
edge of the mountains.

06:10:44.340 --> 06:10:47.580
None of them were full, but 2 of them

06:10:47.580 --> 06:10:49.619
were more than halfway there, and filled

06:10:49.619 --> 06:10:50.279
the sky with light.

06:10:50.340 --> 06:10:54.000
I might fly up the mountain a ways and

06:10:54.000 --> 06:10:56.880
take a closer look, Clay said, is that

06:10:56.880 --> 06:10:57.119
all right?

06:10:57.240 --> 06:11:00.540
Sure, Sonny said, sitting up.

06:11:00.599 --> 06:11:01.259
I'll come with you.

06:11:01.319 --> 06:11:04.500
They climbed higher and higher, looking

06:11:04.500 --> 06:11:06.779
for a clear view of the sky, and finally

06:11:06.779 --> 06:11:08.520
stopped on a ledge not far from the

06:11:08.520 --> 06:11:08.819
peak.

06:11:08.880 --> 06:11:11.700
Clay seemed almost entranced by the

06:11:11.700 --> 06:11:13.020
strange new thing in the sky.

06:11:13.080 --> 06:11:16.080
And so it was Sonny who looked down, and

06:11:16.080 --> 06:11:18.360
gasped, and grabbed his arm and pointed.

06:11:18.419 --> 06:11:21.900
Clay, look, she whispered.

06:11:21.959 --> 06:11:24.959
The valley below them was dotted with

06:11:24.959 --> 06:11:27.659
fires, almost like a lake reflecting the

06:11:27.659 --> 06:11:29.759
stars above, but they could clearly see

06:11:29.759 --> 06:11:31.619
the shapes of dragons gathered around

06:11:31.619 --> 06:11:34.319
those fires, and the glint of weapons

06:11:34.319 --> 06:11:36.720
being polished and sharpened and ready

06:11:36.720 --> 06:11:37.200
for battle.

06:11:37.319 --> 06:11:40.619
That's where they all are, Sonny

06:11:40.619 --> 06:11:41.040
whispered.

06:11:41.099 --> 06:11:42.779
The mud wings are gathering for

06:11:42.779 --> 06:11:43.020
something.

06:11:43.080 --> 06:11:45.299
This must be almost their whole army.

06:11:45.419 --> 06:11:48.779
Clay stared down at them, his tail

06:11:48.779 --> 06:11:49.319
twitching.

06:11:49.380 --> 06:11:52.619
That could have been him down there, she

06:11:52.619 --> 06:11:53.159
realized.

06:11:53.220 --> 06:11:56.040
If there had been no prophecy, he'd have

06:11:56.040 --> 06:11:58.680
grown up like any ordinary mudwing, he'd

06:11:58.680 --> 06:12:00.240
have led his brothers and sisters into

06:12:00.240 --> 06:12:00.659
battle.

06:12:00.720 --> 06:12:03.360
He'd have fought and died for Queen Morin

06:12:03.360 --> 06:12:06.119
and by extension, her ally, Bern.

06:12:06.180 --> 06:12:10.139
They're planning something big, Clay said

06:12:10.139 --> 06:12:11.400
I wonder how soon.

06:12:11.459 --> 06:12:14.939
Let's go find out, Sonny suggested

06:12:14.939 --> 06:12:17.400
spreading her wings, but you.

06:12:18.000 --> 06:12:18.479
He started.

06:12:18.540 --> 06:12:21.959
I'm just a sandwing, she said, I could be

06:12:21.959 --> 06:12:22.500
your ally.

06:12:22.560 --> 06:12:25.020
In the dark, maybe no one will look twice

06:12:25.020 --> 06:12:25.500
at my tail.

06:12:25.560 --> 06:12:28.380
She curled it up in an imitation of the

06:12:28.380 --> 06:12:30.479
scorpion like way the sand wings often

06:12:30.479 --> 06:12:31.259
held their tails.

06:12:31.319 --> 06:12:34.500
After some arguing, she won the debate

06:12:34.500 --> 06:12:37.080
and they flew down to the mudwing camp as

06:12:37.080 --> 06:12:38.700
cautiously and quietly as they could

06:12:38.700 --> 06:12:38.939
move.

06:12:39.000 --> 06:12:41.400
There didn't seem to be any guards on the

06:12:41.400 --> 06:12:43.560
outskirts, and they slipped in among the

06:12:43.560 --> 06:12:44.819
campfires on silent feet.

06:12:44.880 --> 06:12:47.880
Many of the dragons around them were

06:12:47.880 --> 06:12:50.220
sleeping, although Sonny saw at least one

06:12:50.220 --> 06:12:52.020
member awake in each small group.

06:12:52.080 --> 06:12:54.419
She remembered what they'd learned about

06:12:54.419 --> 06:12:56.099
mud wings in Clay's home village.

06:12:56.159 --> 06:12:58.680
Each troop was made up of brothers and

06:12:58.680 --> 06:13:00.959
sisters, who fought alongside one another

06:13:00.959 --> 06:13:03.479
through thick and thin, led by whichever

06:13:03.479 --> 06:13:05.580
one was the biggest, their big wings.

06:13:05.639 --> 06:13:09.000
Someone here could pass a message to burn

06:13:09.000 --> 06:13:11.759
she whispered to Clay, but how do we

06:13:11.759 --> 06:13:12.180
decide who?

06:13:12.299 --> 06:13:14.400
And what if they're all going off to a

06:13:14.400 --> 06:13:15.119
battle tomorrow?

06:13:15.180 --> 06:13:16.680
Do you think we can stop them?

06:13:16.740 --> 06:13:19.799
She had to hurry to keep up with Clay's

06:13:19.799 --> 06:13:20.520
longer strides.

06:13:20.580 --> 06:13:22.560
He was pacing purposefully through the

06:13:22.560 --> 06:13:25.680
camp, studying each group of dragons, and

06:13:25.680 --> 06:13:26.939
she wasn't sure he was even really

06:13:26.939 --> 06:13:27.599
listening to her.

06:13:27.659 --> 06:13:31.860
Oh, she thought, I'm an idiot, of

06:13:31.860 --> 06:13:32.159
course.

06:13:32.220 --> 06:13:34.680
Of course, he was looking for his

06:13:34.680 --> 06:13:35.819
brothers and sisters.

06:13:35.880 --> 06:13:38.279
He'd only met them once, but they were

06:13:38.279 --> 06:13:38.939
often on his mind.

06:13:39.000 --> 06:13:41.880
He'd wondered aloud about them several

06:13:41.880 --> 06:13:43.200
times in the last few weeks.

06:13:43.259 --> 06:13:46.560
Sunny hadn't met them, so she couldn't

06:13:46.560 --> 06:13:48.900
help him search, but she stayed close on

06:13:48.900 --> 06:13:50.639
his heels as they walked and walked

06:13:50.639 --> 06:13:52.919
through the camp, which was even bigger

06:13:52.919 --> 06:13:54.299
than it had looked from up on the

06:13:54.299 --> 06:13:54.540
mountain.

06:13:54.599 --> 06:13:57.779
Here and there she spotted sand wings and

06:13:57.779 --> 06:14:00.060
sky wings as well, which made her feel

06:14:00.060 --> 06:14:01.259
less conspicuous at least.

06:14:01.380 --> 06:14:04.619
Suddenly, Clay stopped and blocked her

06:14:04.619 --> 06:14:05.340
path with his tail.

06:14:05.400 --> 06:14:08.040
He nodded at a group of 5 dragons

06:14:08.040 --> 06:14:10.139
clustered around a fire, drawing

06:14:10.139 --> 06:14:11.400
formation plans in the dirt.

06:14:11.459 --> 06:14:13.319
Is that them?

06:14:13.439 --> 06:14:15.119
Sonny asked softly.

06:14:15.180 --> 06:14:18.000
He nodded, then started forward again.

06:14:18.060 --> 06:14:19.680
Read.

06:14:19.740 --> 06:14:21.659
He whispered from the shadows.

06:14:21.720 --> 06:14:22.680
Shh.

06:14:22.740 --> 06:14:24.060
Don't call out.

06:14:24.119 --> 06:14:24.659
It clay.

06:14:24.720 --> 06:14:27.720
All 5 dragons whirled toward him as he

06:14:27.720 --> 06:14:28.860
stepped into the circle of light.

06:14:28.919 --> 06:14:32.939
Clay, yelped the smallest one quietly.

06:14:33.000 --> 06:14:35.220
He jumped over the fire and bounced

06:14:35.220 --> 06:14:37.680
around Clay, stepping on his talons a few

06:14:37.680 --> 06:14:38.459
times by accident.

06:14:38.520 --> 06:14:42.180
Hey, Omber, Clay said affectionately

06:14:42.180 --> 06:14:44.099
punching the little dragon gently on the

06:14:44.099 --> 06:14:44.400
shoulder.

06:14:44.459 --> 06:14:47.279
Everyone, this is sunny.

06:14:47.340 --> 06:14:49.139
Reed is the big wings.

06:14:49.200 --> 06:14:52.680
My sisters are Sora and Pheasant, and my

06:14:52.680 --> 06:14:53.819
3rd brother is Marsh.

06:14:53.939 --> 06:14:57.299
Hi, Sunny whispered to all of them

06:14:57.299 --> 06:14:59.340
nodding at each of the trusting brown

06:14:59.340 --> 06:15:00.119
eyed faces.

06:15:00.180 --> 06:15:02.459
It's great to finally meet you.

06:15:02.520 --> 06:15:04.380
The way they looked at clay.

06:15:04.439 --> 06:15:06.840
There was a bit of terrifying hope there

06:15:06.840 --> 06:15:08.700
as if they were expecting him to come

06:15:08.700 --> 06:15:11.040
with extra fireproof scales to protect

06:15:11.040 --> 06:15:11.400
them all.

06:15:11.520 --> 06:15:13.200
Are you all right?

06:15:13.259 --> 06:15:14.400
Reed asked.

06:15:14.459 --> 06:15:16.919
He was almost, but not quite as big as

06:15:16.919 --> 06:15:17.520
clay.

06:15:17.580 --> 06:15:19.500
And he held his head up and shoulders

06:15:19.500 --> 06:15:21.840
back, as if he was very aware that he

06:15:21.840 --> 06:15:23.040
shouldn't have been the big wings.

06:15:23.099 --> 06:15:25.919
But he too looked at clay with hope

06:15:25.919 --> 06:15:27.479
rather than envy or worry.

06:15:27.540 --> 06:15:30.240
We've been wondering, we've heard

06:15:30.240 --> 06:15:30.720
rumors.

06:15:30.779 --> 06:15:32.520
Oh, we're fine.

06:15:32.580 --> 06:15:33.720
Clay said.

06:15:33.779 --> 06:15:34.799
Indestructible.

06:15:34.860 --> 06:15:35.880
Don't you worry.

06:15:35.939 --> 06:15:38.880
He grinned at Reed, nudging his side.

06:15:38.939 --> 06:15:40.319
What is all this?

06:15:40.380 --> 06:15:41.580
Why are you here?

06:15:41.639 --> 06:15:45.659
The 5 mudwings exchanged looks, as if

06:15:45.659 --> 06:15:47.220
they weren't sure whether to answer that

06:15:47.220 --> 06:15:47.700
question.

06:15:47.819 --> 06:15:50.159
Would it be treason to their queen?

06:15:50.159 --> 06:15:52.200
Or loyalty to their brother?

06:15:52.259 --> 06:15:54.360
Reed was the one who nodded.

06:15:54.419 --> 06:15:55.619
Yes.

06:15:55.680 --> 06:15:56.580
Tell them.

06:15:56.639 --> 06:16:00.659
A huge offensive, pheasant said, her

06:16:00.659 --> 06:16:03.360
voice shaded with anxiety and fear and

06:16:03.360 --> 06:16:04.139
resignation.

06:16:04.200 --> 06:16:07.380
Wipe out as many ice wings as we can in

06:16:07.380 --> 06:16:10.259
one huge sweep, and hope we kill Blaze

06:16:10.259 --> 06:16:10.979
while we're at it.

06:16:11.040 --> 06:16:14.220
Queen Morin is leading us herself, said

06:16:14.220 --> 06:16:16.619
Reed, and Queen Ruby is supposed to bring

06:16:16.619 --> 06:16:18.180
her troops over to attack from the

06:16:18.180 --> 06:16:18.479
north.

06:16:18.540 --> 06:16:21.540
The order that came down was, we keep

06:16:21.540 --> 06:16:23.880
fighting, as long as any enemies are left

06:16:23.880 --> 06:16:24.240
alive.

06:16:24.299 --> 06:16:27.900
Take no prisoners, Zora whispered

06:16:27.900 --> 06:16:28.500
shuddering.

06:16:28.560 --> 06:16:30.000
Kill everyone.

06:16:30.060 --> 06:16:33.180
Byrne wants to end the war fast before

06:16:33.180 --> 06:16:35.520
you guys miss everything up, Umber

06:16:35.520 --> 06:16:35.819
added.

06:16:35.880 --> 06:16:37.619
That's the word going around the camp

06:16:37.619 --> 06:16:38.159
anyway.

06:16:38.220 --> 06:16:40.860
And as long as the sea wings are still in

06:16:40.860 --> 06:16:41.220
hiding.

06:16:41.279 --> 06:16:43.500
She can focus all her energy on the ice

06:16:43.500 --> 06:16:46.500
kingdom, Reed explained. on destroying

06:16:46.500 --> 06:16:46.680
them.

06:16:46.740 --> 06:16:50.279
Every last ice wing, Marsh finished

06:16:50.279 --> 06:16:51.659
unless we all die first.

06:16:51.720 --> 06:16:54.419
He stared into the flames of their

06:16:54.419 --> 06:16:54.959
campfire.

06:16:55.020 --> 06:16:58.380
The 3 moons were not enough to combat the

06:16:58.380 --> 06:16:59.939
dark that was pressing in around them

06:16:59.939 --> 06:17:02.459
like shadow wings folding over their

06:17:02.459 --> 06:17:02.759
heads.

06:17:02.819 --> 06:17:06.599
The fire flickered and spat, illuminating

06:17:06.599 --> 06:17:09.240
amber underscales and dark brown tails

06:17:09.240 --> 06:17:10.319
and waves of orange light.

06:17:10.380 --> 06:17:14.099
You can't do that, Sonny said.

06:17:14.159 --> 06:17:16.020
She could hear her voice shaking.

06:17:16.080 --> 06:17:18.659
All of you against the ice wings?

06:17:18.720 --> 06:17:20.880
You really might wipe them out.

06:17:21.000 --> 06:17:22.680
The entire tribe.

06:17:22.740 --> 06:17:27.000
And so many of you will die trying, Clay

06:17:27.000 --> 06:17:29.400
said, reaching one wing around Umber.

06:17:29.520 --> 06:17:32.159
It's so cold in the Ice Kingdom.

06:17:32.220 --> 06:17:35.819
We were there, just on the outskirts, and

06:17:35.819 --> 06:17:36.540
it was freezing.

06:17:36.599 --> 06:17:39.659
Imagine how much worse it'll be right in

06:17:39.659 --> 06:17:42.180
the heart of it or up by Glacier's

06:17:42.180 --> 06:17:42.479
palace.

06:17:42.599 --> 06:17:44.939
Hundreds of dragons will freeze to

06:17:44.939 --> 06:17:45.180
death.

06:17:45.299 --> 06:17:46.619
You might.

06:17:46.680 --> 06:17:48.180
You mustn't.

06:17:48.299 --> 06:17:51.060
He broke off, clearing his throat.

06:17:51.119 --> 06:17:54.959
Marsh and Sora shuffled closer to him, and

06:17:54.959 --> 06:17:56.759
he spread his other wing to go awkwardly

06:17:56.759 --> 06:17:57.540
around them as well.

06:17:57.599 --> 06:18:00.720
He's right, Sonny said.

06:18:00.779 --> 06:18:02.759
This is a suicide mission.

06:18:02.819 --> 06:18:04.919
Suicide or genocide?

06:18:04.979 --> 06:18:07.080
Those are your only 2 outcomes.

06:18:07.139 --> 06:18:09.599
Clay, we can't let this happen.

06:18:09.659 --> 06:18:11.580
What else can we do?

06:18:11.700 --> 06:18:13.020
Reed demanded.

06:18:13.080 --> 06:18:14.580
We're part of an army.

06:18:14.639 --> 06:18:15.900
These are our orders.

06:18:15.959 --> 06:18:18.299
Orders from our queen.

06:18:18.360 --> 06:18:21.119
You could run away, Clay said.

06:18:21.180 --> 06:18:22.259
Come with us.

06:18:22.319 --> 06:18:23.099
We'll hide you.

06:18:23.220 --> 06:18:25.979
We can, but you know that's not good

06:18:25.979 --> 06:18:27.659
enough, Seni said to him.

06:18:27.720 --> 06:18:29.819
We have to stop this from happening at

06:18:29.819 --> 06:18:30.000
all.

06:18:30.060 --> 06:18:33.479
There's 5 of us against Queen Morhen.

06:18:33.540 --> 06:18:35.939
Queen Ruby, and all of Burns army.

06:18:36.000 --> 06:18:37.439
Reed pointed out.

06:18:37.560 --> 06:18:39.000
Who's going to listen to us?

06:18:39.060 --> 06:18:42.000
I'm sure you're not the only one who are

06:18:42.000 --> 06:18:43.560
worried, Senny said.

06:18:43.619 --> 06:18:45.900
She twisted to look at the fires all

06:18:45.900 --> 06:18:47.939
around them, and wondered how many of the

06:18:47.939 --> 06:18:49.439
sleeping dragons were caught in

06:18:49.439 --> 06:18:51.000
nightmares about the battles to come.

06:18:51.060 --> 06:18:53.159
Nightmares.

06:18:53.220 --> 06:18:56.340
She touched the pouch around her throat, a

06:18:56.340 --> 06:18:57.720
possible idea was starting to come to

06:18:57.720 --> 06:18:57.900
her.

06:18:57.959 --> 06:19:00.720
When are you supposed to attack?

06:19:00.840 --> 06:19:01.740
Clay asked.

06:19:01.799 --> 06:19:03.959
We move out tomorrow morning?

06:19:04.020 --> 06:19:05.340
Pheasant answered.

06:19:05.400 --> 06:19:07.860
A few days to cross the mountains in the

06:19:07.860 --> 06:19:10.560
desert, those who make it, and then we'll

06:19:10.560 --> 06:19:11.459
be at the ice kingdom.

06:19:11.520 --> 06:19:14.040
So we have to do something about it now

06:19:14.040 --> 06:19:17.159
Sunny said, standing up and pacing around

06:19:17.159 --> 06:19:17.520
the fire.

06:19:17.580 --> 06:19:19.680
Where is Queen Mohan?

06:19:19.740 --> 06:19:20.279
Is she here?

06:19:20.340 --> 06:19:20.880
Do you know?

06:19:21.000 --> 06:19:24.299
Reed and the others looked alarmed, apart

06:19:24.299 --> 06:19:25.380
from Umber, who looked excited.

06:19:25.439 --> 06:19:29.040
You can't just go talk to the Queen, Reed

06:19:29.040 --> 06:19:29.279
said.

06:19:29.340 --> 06:19:31.380
She'll never let you get away.

06:19:31.439 --> 06:19:34.020
There are orders to capture you all if

06:19:34.020 --> 06:19:34.860
anyone sees you.

06:19:34.919 --> 06:19:36.779
Although everyone's looking for 5

06:19:36.779 --> 06:19:39.299
dragonets together, and most dragons

06:19:39.299 --> 06:19:40.319
don't know what you look like.

06:19:40.380 --> 06:19:43.319
But if you walk right into her camp, you

06:19:43.319 --> 06:19:44.700
might as well put on your own chains.

06:19:44.759 --> 06:19:47.700
We're not going to do that, Sonny

06:19:47.700 --> 06:19:48.180
promised.

06:19:48.240 --> 06:19:49.259
I have a plan.

06:19:49.319 --> 06:19:52.380
A sort of a plan, a something worth

06:19:52.380 --> 06:19:53.099
trying anyway.

06:19:53.159 --> 06:19:54.720
So which way is she?

06:19:54.840 --> 06:19:57.240
Umber flicked his tail toward the center

06:19:57.240 --> 06:19:57.840
of camp.

06:19:57.900 --> 06:20:00.659
Right in the middle of everything, he

06:20:00.659 --> 06:20:02.580
said, like a real big wings.

06:20:02.639 --> 06:20:04.799
Please don't kill her.

06:20:04.860 --> 06:20:06.599
Sora said softly.

06:20:06.659 --> 06:20:08.040
She's not a bad queen.

06:20:08.099 --> 06:20:12.419
We're not going to, Clay assured her, we

06:20:12.419 --> 06:20:14.040
would never. don't do that.

06:20:14.099 --> 06:20:17.279
We'll be back, Sonny promised them.

06:20:17.340 --> 06:20:19.799
She plunged into the darkness with Clay

06:20:19.799 --> 06:20:21.779
close behind her, weaving between the

06:20:21.779 --> 06:20:22.200
fires again.

06:20:22.259 --> 06:20:25.139
Do you really have a sort of plan?

06:20:25.200 --> 06:20:26.159
Clay asked.

06:20:26.220 --> 06:20:27.840
Because I have no plan.

06:20:27.959 --> 06:20:30.779
Except maybe a throwing up So nervous

06:20:30.779 --> 06:20:31.080
plan.

06:20:31.139 --> 06:20:35.279
I do, Sonny said, curling her claws

06:20:35.279 --> 06:20:36.479
around the dream visitor.

06:20:36.540 --> 06:20:38.279
I just have to see the queen and make

06:20:38.279 --> 06:20:39.119
sure she's sleeping.

06:20:39.180 --> 06:20:41.880
Oh, Clay said.

06:20:41.939 --> 06:20:43.380
Aha.

06:20:43.439 --> 06:20:45.900
He took the lead, adjusting their

06:20:45.900 --> 06:20:48.119
direction, and soon they saw a brightly

06:20:48.119 --> 06:20:49.919
burning circle of fires ahead of them.

06:20:49.979 --> 06:20:52.680
Wide awake guards were posted between the

06:20:52.680 --> 06:20:55.259
fires, staring alertly out of the camp

06:20:55.259 --> 06:20:56.220
and up at the sky.

06:20:56.340 --> 06:20:59.639
But beyond the guards, they could see a

06:20:59.639 --> 06:21:03.060
huge dragon, as big as morrow seer, curled

06:21:03.060 --> 06:21:03.959
in a slumbering ball.

06:21:04.020 --> 06:21:07.080
Firelight reflected off her russet scales

06:21:07.080 --> 06:21:08.939
and caught the glitter of gemstones on

06:21:08.939 --> 06:21:09.779
her ankles and head.

06:21:09.840 --> 06:21:12.900
The spines on her back moved slowly up

06:21:12.900 --> 06:21:14.159
and down as she breathed.

06:21:14.220 --> 06:21:17.459
Clustered around her were 4 other dragons

06:21:17.459 --> 06:21:20.279
all smaller than her, all glittering with

06:21:20.279 --> 06:21:21.479
gems and sleeping as well.

06:21:21.540 --> 06:21:24.180
Her brothers and sisters?

06:21:24.180 --> 06:21:25.319
Sonny guest.

06:21:25.380 --> 06:21:27.240
They stopped well out of sight of the

06:21:27.240 --> 06:21:29.279
guards, studying the royal camp.

06:21:29.340 --> 06:21:30.540
Clay nodded.

06:21:30.599 --> 06:21:31.740
I think so.

06:21:31.799 --> 06:21:33.180
He grinned.

06:21:33.240 --> 06:21:34.860
If Starflight were here.

06:21:34.919 --> 06:21:37.439
He could tell us all their names and

06:21:37.439 --> 06:21:39.779
personal histories, and what they each

06:21:39.779 --> 06:21:41.040
eat for breakfast every day.

06:21:41.099 --> 06:21:44.939
Sonny grinned back, although inside, her

06:21:44.939 --> 06:21:46.380
stomach felt as though it were trying to

06:21:46.380 --> 06:21:46.860
eat itself.

06:21:46.919 --> 06:21:50.159
I remember one thing I read, she said.

06:21:50.220 --> 06:21:52.680
It said that no mudwing queen has ever

06:21:52.680 --> 06:21:54.900
been challenged by a sister, only

06:21:54.900 --> 06:21:55.439
daughters.

06:21:55.500 --> 06:21:58.080
I didn't understand it then, but I do

06:21:58.080 --> 06:21:58.319
now.

06:21:58.380 --> 06:21:59.759
In your tribe.

06:21:59.819 --> 06:22:02.040
Brothers and sisters are always loyal to

06:22:02.040 --> 06:22:02.459
one another.

06:22:02.520 --> 06:22:05.099
A sister would never try to take the

06:22:05.099 --> 06:22:06.360
throne from her big wings.

06:22:06.419 --> 06:22:08.099
Clay nodded.

06:22:08.159 --> 06:22:11.159
That feels right to me, he said.

06:22:11.220 --> 06:22:14.220
Sonny stared at the queen, trying to

06:22:14.220 --> 06:22:16.139
memorize her features or what she could

06:22:16.139 --> 06:22:16.680
see of them.

06:22:16.740 --> 06:22:17.759
Would this work?

06:22:17.819 --> 06:22:19.860
Was she really going to risk it?

06:22:19.919 --> 06:22:23.099
The image of 100s of ice wing corpses

06:22:23.099 --> 06:22:24.119
flashed through her head.

06:22:24.180 --> 06:22:25.680
Of course I am.

06:22:25.799 --> 06:22:29.459
Struck by another idea, she studied all

06:22:29.459 --> 06:22:31.439
the queen's brothers and sisters too.

06:22:31.439 --> 06:22:33.479
She wondered how many times the dream

06:22:33.479 --> 06:22:35.580
visitor could be used in one night.

06:22:35.639 --> 06:22:39.000
All right, she said, pulling clay away.

06:22:39.060 --> 06:22:41.939
They chose the darkest patch of shadow

06:22:41.939 --> 06:22:44.580
they could find outside the camp with the

06:22:44.580 --> 06:22:45.599
mountains looming over them.

06:22:45.659 --> 06:22:48.479
Maybe you should be the one to do this

06:22:48.479 --> 06:22:51.360
she whispered to Clay, trying to pass him

06:22:51.360 --> 06:22:52.139
the dream visitor.

06:22:52.200 --> 06:22:54.840
He shook his head and pushed it back to

06:22:54.840 --> 06:22:55.020
her.

06:22:55.080 --> 06:22:58.020
You've used it before, and you'll know

06:22:58.020 --> 06:22:58.619
what to say.

06:22:58.680 --> 06:23:02.099
And if it's me, well, she might think

06:23:02.099 --> 06:23:03.060
it's a normal dream.

06:23:03.119 --> 06:23:06.419
Just another mud wing, voicing her inner

06:23:06.419 --> 06:23:07.319
anxieties or something.

06:23:07.380 --> 06:23:10.380
But if it's you, she'll know it's real.

06:23:10.500 --> 06:23:13.080
A real message from the dragonettes

06:23:13.080 --> 06:23:14.639
because nobody else looks like you.

06:23:14.700 --> 06:23:18.479
That's true, Sunny thought, and then

06:23:18.479 --> 06:23:19.080
Riley.

06:23:19.139 --> 06:23:21.840
So maybe there is a good reason to look

06:23:21.840 --> 06:23:22.680
this weird after all.

06:23:22.799 --> 06:23:25.200
You can do it, Sonny.

06:23:25.259 --> 06:23:26.340
Clay said.

06:23:26.400 --> 06:23:27.779
I'm completely sure.

06:23:27.840 --> 06:23:31.200
He twined his tail around hers, and she

06:23:31.200 --> 06:23:33.180
felt a tiny bit less terrified.

06:23:33.240 --> 06:23:35.759
Sonny cupped her talons around the dream

06:23:35.759 --> 06:23:38.279
visitor and held it to her head, closing

06:23:38.279 --> 06:23:38.759
her eyes.

06:23:38.819 --> 06:23:41.040
She'd only ever used it on her friends.

06:23:41.159 --> 06:23:43.380
Please let this work.

06:23:43.439 --> 06:23:44.880
She prayed.

06:23:44.939 --> 06:23:47.159
She thought of the huge brown dragon

06:23:47.159 --> 06:23:48.360
she'd just seen.

06:23:48.419 --> 06:23:49.979
Queen Morin.

06:23:50.040 --> 06:23:51.240
Let me in.

06:23:51.299 --> 06:23:54.599
After a long moment, she opened her eyes

06:23:54.599 --> 06:23:57.299
and found herself standing ankle deep in

06:23:57.299 --> 06:23:57.659
mud.

06:23:57.720 --> 06:24:00.659
Mud stretched around her, and endless

06:24:00.659 --> 06:24:03.180
warm swamp dotted with mangroves, and

06:24:03.180 --> 06:24:04.380
dozing crocodiles.

06:24:04.439 --> 06:24:07.740
The sun was high above them in a hazy sky

06:24:07.740 --> 06:24:09.240
and insects buzzed through the long

06:24:09.240 --> 06:24:09.959
cattails.

06:24:10.020 --> 06:24:13.619
Sonny turned in a circle and spotted

06:24:13.619 --> 06:24:15.720
Queen Mohen pacing across a dry island

06:24:15.720 --> 06:24:16.919
that stuck out of the mud.

06:24:17.040 --> 06:24:19.500
Several scrolls were scattered around her

06:24:19.500 --> 06:24:21.720
talons, many of them covered in brown

06:24:21.720 --> 06:24:24.599
spatters, and a large map of Pyria was

06:24:24.599 --> 06:24:25.439
scratched into the dirt.

06:24:25.500 --> 06:24:28.439
The queen lashed her tail and drew long

06:24:28.439 --> 06:24:30.779
lines with her claws across the mountains

06:24:30.779 --> 06:24:32.939
furrowing them through the sketched out

06:24:32.939 --> 06:24:35.040
kingdom of sand, and then slashing

06:24:35.040 --> 06:24:36.840
furiously at the corner of the map that

06:24:36.840 --> 06:24:38.459
represented the ice kingdom.

06:24:38.520 --> 06:24:41.639
She stopped, shook her head, and glanced

06:24:41.639 --> 06:24:42.360
down at the mud.

06:24:42.419 --> 06:24:45.659
With a jolt of horror, Sonny realized

06:24:45.659 --> 06:24:47.880
that there were dead bodies lying half

06:24:47.880 --> 06:24:49.979
submerged around the Queen's Island.

06:24:50.040 --> 06:24:52.259
She recognized at least one of them as

06:24:52.259 --> 06:24:54.479
one of the queen's brothers, who'd been

06:24:54.479 --> 06:24:56.279
sleeping nearby in the royal camp.

06:24:56.340 --> 06:24:58.979
This is a real nightmare.

06:24:59.040 --> 06:25:01.500
She might not be able to hear me.

06:25:01.560 --> 06:25:03.479
But Sonny had to try.

06:25:03.540 --> 06:25:06.540
She waited through the mud, which felt

06:25:06.540 --> 06:25:08.939
gloppily real against her scales and

06:25:08.939 --> 06:25:10.680
clambered up onto the island behind the

06:25:10.680 --> 06:25:11.639
mud wing queen.

06:25:11.700 --> 06:25:14.639
Mohan whirled around and stared at her.

06:25:14.700 --> 06:25:17.220
Sonny spread her talons.

06:25:17.279 --> 06:25:20.220
I'm harmless, she said, I'm here to

06:25:20.220 --> 06:25:20.700
talk.

06:25:20.759 --> 06:25:24.779
Here, now, the queen demanded.

06:25:24.840 --> 06:25:26.279
Can't you see?

06:25:26.340 --> 06:25:28.680
in the middle of a campaign, and everyone

06:25:28.680 --> 06:25:30.900
is dying, and it's all my fault, and I

06:25:30.900 --> 06:25:32.220
can't save them.

06:25:32.279 --> 06:25:34.500
She slashed her claws across the kingdom

06:25:34.500 --> 06:25:36.659
of sand, and turned to look down into the

06:25:36.659 --> 06:25:37.080
mud again.

06:25:37.139 --> 06:25:40.200
Her wings trembled, and she lowered her

06:25:40.200 --> 06:25:41.639
snout to the closest corpse.

06:25:41.700 --> 06:25:46.259
No, no, I command you not to die.

06:25:46.319 --> 06:25:50.459
This is a dream, Sonny said firmly and

06:25:50.459 --> 06:25:50.939
loudly.

06:25:51.000 --> 06:25:53.340
You're only dreaming, I promise you.

06:25:53.400 --> 06:25:55.979
The queen drew back from the corpse.

06:25:56.040 --> 06:25:58.259
Hmm, she said.

06:25:58.319 --> 06:26:01.919
It's a nightmare, Sonny said, but they're

06:26:01.919 --> 06:26:02.939
not dead.

06:26:03.000 --> 06:26:04.500
Your brothers and sisters are asleep

06:26:04.500 --> 06:26:05.700
right beside you in the camp.

06:26:05.819 --> 06:26:08.639
They're safe, at least for now.

06:26:08.700 --> 06:26:10.799
What does that mean?

06:26:10.860 --> 06:26:12.659
Queen Morhen asked.

06:26:12.720 --> 06:26:15.419
Her voice sounded less strained, and her

06:26:15.419 --> 06:26:16.319
wings were relaxing.

06:26:16.380 --> 06:26:18.299
Is that a threat?

06:26:18.360 --> 06:26:21.299
Not at all, Sonny said hastily.

06:26:21.360 --> 06:26:23.040
I want them to be safe too.

06:26:23.159 --> 06:26:25.619
I want all your subjects to be safe.

06:26:25.680 --> 06:26:27.000
That's why I'm here.

06:26:27.060 --> 06:26:30.479
The queen looked up at the sky, then

06:26:30.479 --> 06:26:33.180
around at the swamp, down at the map, and

06:26:33.180 --> 06:26:33.959
back at Sunny.

06:26:34.020 --> 06:26:36.119
This is really a dream.

06:26:36.180 --> 06:26:38.099
Then how are you here?

06:26:38.159 --> 06:26:41.159
Old magic, Sonny said.

06:26:41.220 --> 06:26:42.360
But that's not important.

06:26:42.419 --> 06:26:43.919
Do you know who I am?

06:26:43.979 --> 06:26:47.340
I have a guess, said the queen.

06:26:47.400 --> 06:26:49.380
Shouldn't there be 5 of you?

06:26:49.439 --> 06:26:52.560
There are 5 of us, Sonny said.

06:26:52.619 --> 06:26:54.360
But I'm the one here talking to you.

06:26:54.419 --> 06:26:56.819
I'm here to tell you not to attack the

06:26:56.819 --> 06:26:57.479
Ice Kingdom.

06:26:57.540 --> 06:26:58.560
Not tomorrow?

06:26:58.619 --> 06:26:59.400
Not ever.

06:26:59.459 --> 06:27:02.880
Too many dragons will die if you do, on

06:27:02.880 --> 06:27:03.540
both sides.

06:27:03.659 --> 06:27:05.700
Is that an omen?

06:27:05.759 --> 06:27:07.319
Queen Morhen asked.

06:27:07.380 --> 06:27:09.599
Did your night wing tell you that?

06:27:09.659 --> 06:27:12.119
You know it doesn't take a nightwing

06:27:12.119 --> 06:27:14.880
prophecy to see that future, Sonny said.

06:27:14.939 --> 06:27:17.040
Touching one claw lightly to the

06:27:17.040 --> 06:27:18.419
scratched up map beside her.

06:27:18.479 --> 06:27:21.540
You know how many of your dragons you'll

06:27:21.540 --> 06:27:21.720
lose.

06:27:21.840 --> 06:27:24.659
The queen drew a line in the dirt in

06:27:24.659 --> 06:27:25.080
front of her.

06:27:25.139 --> 06:27:28.080
But then the war will be over, and

06:27:28.080 --> 06:27:29.279
perhaps that'll be worth it.

06:27:29.340 --> 06:27:32.580
Bern has promised us immunity from attack

06:27:32.580 --> 06:27:34.680
for the next 100 years if we help her

06:27:34.680 --> 06:27:35.099
win.

06:27:35.159 --> 06:27:38.040
If we don't, she'll destroy us.

06:27:38.159 --> 06:27:40.740
She is a powerful enemy, Little

06:27:40.740 --> 06:27:41.400
Sandwing.

06:27:41.520 --> 06:27:44.639
A lot more powerful than you, and she's

06:27:44.639 --> 06:27:46.080
an enemy I don't intend to make.

06:27:46.080 --> 06:27:50.159
You don't have to, Sonny said, thinking

06:27:50.159 --> 06:27:52.919
that's how Bern got her mudwing alliance

06:27:52.919 --> 06:27:55.080
with intimidation and threats?

06:27:55.139 --> 06:27:58.799
So Queen Morhen joined the war to protect

06:27:58.799 --> 06:27:59.819
her dragons.

06:27:59.880 --> 06:28:03.180
It sounds backward, but I can see it.

06:28:03.240 --> 06:28:05.459
We're going to end the war.

06:28:05.459 --> 06:28:07.259
We have a message for Bern.

06:28:07.319 --> 06:28:10.860
Meet us at midnight in 7 days time in the

06:28:10.860 --> 06:28:12.360
main courtyard of her stronghold.

06:28:12.419 --> 06:28:14.939
If you can tell her to do that, instead

06:28:14.939 --> 06:28:17.580
of attacking the ice wings, we'll find a

06:28:17.580 --> 06:28:18.419
way to stop the war.

06:28:18.479 --> 06:28:20.279
And you can come too.

06:28:20.340 --> 06:28:23.099
We want everyone to see that this is the

06:28:23.099 --> 06:28:24.000
end of the fighting.

06:28:24.060 --> 06:28:26.279
No more dragons have to die.

06:28:26.400 --> 06:28:29.400
Queen Morhen tilted her head with a

06:28:29.400 --> 06:28:30.240
skeptical expression.

06:28:30.299 --> 06:28:33.779
It sounds like a tail, from one of the

06:28:33.779 --> 06:28:36.599
sea wing queen's silly romantic scrolls.

06:28:36.659 --> 06:28:38.340
What are you planning to do?

06:28:38.400 --> 06:28:40.139
You'll see.

06:28:40.200 --> 06:28:41.279
Sonny said.

06:28:41.340 --> 06:28:42.299
Just be there.

06:28:42.360 --> 06:28:45.119
Be there instead of watching your dragons

06:28:45.119 --> 06:28:46.319
die in the ice kingdom.

06:28:46.380 --> 06:28:48.419
Bring the sky wings too.

06:28:48.479 --> 06:28:50.880
Everyone who wants this war to be over.

06:28:50.939 --> 06:28:53.159
The queen nodded slowly.

06:28:53.220 --> 06:28:54.959
I'll think about it.

06:28:55.020 --> 06:28:57.540
Are you choosing burn then?

06:28:57.599 --> 06:29:00.779
We are choosing peace, Sonny said.

06:29:00.840 --> 06:29:02.099
That's the important thing.

06:29:02.220 --> 06:29:04.860
That sounds like you're avoiding the

06:29:04.860 --> 06:29:05.220
question.

06:29:05.340 --> 06:29:07.080
Morehen pointed out.

06:29:07.200 --> 06:29:08.459
Does it matter?

06:29:08.520 --> 06:29:09.599
Sonny asked.

06:29:09.659 --> 06:29:11.340
As long as the war is over?

06:29:11.459 --> 06:29:13.979
The queen thought for a long time and

06:29:13.979 --> 06:29:14.759
inside.

06:29:14.880 --> 06:29:16.139
Perhaps not.

06:29:16.259 --> 06:29:20.040
Make sure Bern is there, Sonny said.

06:29:20.099 --> 06:29:20.939
It's important.

06:29:21.000 --> 06:29:25.020
It sounds like it, said the mud wing

06:29:25.020 --> 06:29:25.380
queen.

06:29:25.439 --> 06:29:27.659
She brushed her tail over the map of

06:29:27.659 --> 06:29:30.840
Pyria, erasing it, and all the agonized

06:29:30.840 --> 06:29:32.639
claw marks she'd drawn on it.

06:29:32.700 --> 06:29:34.619
I'll see what I can do.

06:29:34.680 --> 06:29:37.200
That sounded a little ridiculous to

06:29:37.200 --> 06:29:37.740
Sonny.

06:29:37.799 --> 06:29:39.779
If the queen of the mudwings couldn't do

06:29:39.779 --> 06:29:41.759
as she'd asked, then what chance did

06:29:41.759 --> 06:29:42.240
anyone have?

06:29:42.360 --> 06:29:43.740
But she didn't say that.

06:29:43.860 --> 06:29:45.720
She bowed and stepped back.

06:29:45.779 --> 06:29:49.020
Thank you, Your Majesty, she said

06:29:49.020 --> 06:29:49.619
instead.

06:29:49.680 --> 06:29:52.259
Good luck, said the queen.

06:29:52.380 --> 06:29:55.020
You're very small to be in charge of

06:29:55.020 --> 06:29:55.680
saving the world.

06:29:55.799 --> 06:30:00.299
And weird looking, Sonny agreed, but we

06:30:00.299 --> 06:30:01.799
can do it if everyone helps.

06:30:01.860 --> 06:30:03.779
Hmm.

06:30:03.900 --> 06:30:06.900
Queen Morhen pulled her wings in close

06:30:06.900 --> 06:30:09.540
and stared down at the mud covered bodies

06:30:09.540 --> 06:30:11.099
of her brothers and sisters all around

06:30:11.099 --> 06:30:11.400
her.

06:30:11.459 --> 06:30:13.020
Maybe.

06:30:13.080 --> 06:30:15.900
As Sonny lifted the dream visitor away

06:30:15.900 --> 06:30:17.880
from her head, stepping out of the dream

06:30:17.880 --> 06:30:20.220
she thought she heard the queen whisper

06:30:20.220 --> 06:30:20.880
one last thing.

06:30:20.939 --> 06:30:22.979
I hope so.

06:30:23.040 --> 06:30:27.659
Chapter 23.

06:30:27.900 --> 06:30:31.380
Sonny was tired after visiting the

06:30:31.380 --> 06:30:33.720
queen's dream, but she made herself step

06:30:33.720 --> 06:30:35.520
into the dreams of the royal siblings

06:30:35.520 --> 06:30:35.880
next.

06:30:35.939 --> 06:30:38.819
Three brothers and one sister, all of

06:30:38.819 --> 06:30:41.459
them having similar anxiety dreams, most

06:30:41.459 --> 06:30:43.439
of them about Queen Morhen dying in some

06:30:43.439 --> 06:30:43.919
awful way.

06:30:43.979 --> 06:30:46.500
One of the brothers was having such a

06:30:46.500 --> 06:30:48.720
terrible nightmare that Sonny wasn't able

06:30:48.720 --> 06:30:49.740
to get through to him at all.

06:30:49.799 --> 06:30:52.560
But the others saw her, and they seemed

06:30:52.560 --> 06:30:53.700
to listen to what she said.

06:30:53.759 --> 06:30:56.340
They each answered that it was up to

06:30:56.340 --> 06:30:58.740
Morehen to make the decision, but Sonny

06:30:58.740 --> 06:31:00.180
had a feeling the queen would listen to

06:31:00.180 --> 06:31:02.459
her siblings more than any other advisor

06:31:02.459 --> 06:31:04.139
she might have, and if they could

06:31:04.139 --> 06:31:04.799
persuade her.

06:31:04.860 --> 06:31:07.680
Well, it was worth the chance.

06:31:07.740 --> 06:31:11.340
After that, as she and Clay were walking

06:31:11.340 --> 06:31:13.500
back through the camp, passed so many

06:31:13.500 --> 06:31:16.380
sleeping dragons, she stopped, brushing

06:31:16.380 --> 06:31:17.819
his wing with hers.

06:31:17.880 --> 06:31:20.220
We can do more, she said.

06:31:20.279 --> 06:31:23.340
Not all of them, but if even a few

06:31:23.340 --> 06:31:25.139
dragons talk about having dream messages

06:31:25.139 --> 06:31:27.060
from us, Maybe that'll make a

06:31:27.060 --> 06:31:27.360
difference.

06:31:27.419 --> 06:31:29.459
Aren't you tired?

06:31:29.520 --> 06:31:30.540
Clay asked.

06:31:30.599 --> 06:31:32.520
You look like you haven't slept in a

06:31:32.520 --> 06:31:33.060
week?

06:31:33.180 --> 06:31:35.759
There had been a lot of exhausting flying

06:31:35.759 --> 06:31:36.180
lately.

06:31:36.240 --> 06:31:38.880
More than she was used to, and all she

06:31:38.880 --> 06:31:40.919
wanted was to curl up under Clay's wing

06:31:40.919 --> 06:31:43.740
and sleep for the next month, but that

06:31:43.740 --> 06:31:44.700
was not an option.

06:31:44.759 --> 06:31:47.459
I can do it, she assured him.

06:31:47.520 --> 06:31:51.599
Let me do some too, he said, holding out

06:31:51.599 --> 06:31:52.380
his talons.

06:31:52.439 --> 06:31:54.659
You can rest while I do that.

06:31:54.720 --> 06:31:58.259
They chose sleeping dragons at random

06:31:58.259 --> 06:32:00.599
standing in the shadows nearby, and

06:32:00.599 --> 06:32:02.099
dropping lightly into their dreams.

06:32:02.159 --> 06:32:04.259
Most of them were nightmares.

06:32:04.319 --> 06:32:05.939
There were nightmares all through the

06:32:05.939 --> 06:32:06.180
camp.

06:32:06.240 --> 06:32:09.240
Sometimes Sonny could break through and

06:32:09.240 --> 06:32:11.220
show them they were dreaming, and then

06:32:11.220 --> 06:32:11.759
they would listen.

06:32:11.819 --> 06:32:13.619
She kept her messages brief.

06:32:13.680 --> 06:32:15.540
The war is almost over.

06:32:15.599 --> 06:32:16.680
No more killing.

06:32:16.740 --> 06:32:18.659
Don't go to the ice kingdom.

06:32:18.720 --> 06:32:20.279
The war will be over soon.

06:32:20.340 --> 06:32:21.479
You can help.

06:32:21.599 --> 06:32:23.819
Stop fighting, spread the word.

06:32:23.939 --> 06:32:27.060
They found Reed and the others again as

06:32:27.060 --> 06:32:28.560
early morning light was beginning to

06:32:28.560 --> 06:32:29.459
creep across the camp.

06:32:29.520 --> 06:32:33.240
Umber, Marsh, and Sora were fast asleep

06:32:33.240 --> 06:32:35.580
in a pile of tails and wings, but

06:32:35.580 --> 06:32:37.740
Pheasant and Reed were awake, watching

06:32:37.740 --> 06:32:39.240
for them with matching, anxious

06:32:39.240 --> 06:32:39.779
expressions.

06:32:39.840 --> 06:32:44.279
We did our best, Clay whispered, pressing

06:32:44.279 --> 06:32:46.139
their talons in his.

06:32:46.200 --> 06:32:48.180
Hopefully, you'll get new orders soon.

06:32:48.240 --> 06:32:51.900
But we should go before we're seen, Sonny

06:32:51.900 --> 06:32:52.139
said.

06:32:52.200 --> 06:32:54.060
Do you want to come with us?

06:32:54.119 --> 06:32:55.259
Clay asked.

06:32:55.319 --> 06:32:57.959
Reed sighed, and looked at his sleeping

06:32:57.959 --> 06:32:58.860
brothers and sister.

06:32:58.919 --> 06:33:03.720
No, I mean, I do, but we are loyal to the

06:33:03.720 --> 06:33:05.459
queen, and we don't want to be

06:33:05.459 --> 06:33:05.880
fugitives.

06:33:05.939 --> 06:33:08.639
I wish I could at least give you Umber or

06:33:08.639 --> 06:33:10.439
Marsh, but they won't leave the rest of

06:33:10.439 --> 06:33:10.619
us.

06:33:10.680 --> 06:33:12.180
We stick together.

06:33:12.240 --> 06:33:13.560
That's our way.

06:33:13.619 --> 06:33:17.099
I'm sorry, Clay said reluctantly.

06:33:17.159 --> 06:33:18.599
I wish I could stay.

06:33:18.659 --> 06:33:20.700
If you do have to fight.

06:33:20.819 --> 06:33:22.919
I wish I could be there with you.

06:33:22.979 --> 06:33:27.000
Me too, Reed admitted, in a low voice.

06:33:27.060 --> 06:33:29.700
Pheasant shook her head, but didn't say

06:33:29.700 --> 06:33:29.939
anything.

06:33:30.000 --> 06:33:33.060
She nudged the others away, and they each

06:33:33.060 --> 06:33:34.080
hugged Clay goodbye.

06:33:34.139 --> 06:33:38.400
See you soon, Sunny said, trying to sound

06:33:38.400 --> 06:33:39.720
more hopeful than she felt.

06:33:39.720 --> 06:33:42.240
Be safe, Clay said.

06:33:42.299 --> 06:33:44.159
I'm glad you have Reed.

06:33:44.279 --> 06:33:46.619
He wrapped his wings around his brother

06:33:46.619 --> 06:33:47.279
again.

06:33:47.340 --> 06:33:49.319
And then he and Sonny hurried off through

06:33:49.319 --> 06:33:51.180
the camp toward the safety of the

06:33:51.180 --> 06:33:51.599
mountains.

06:33:51.720 --> 06:33:54.599
They stayed on the ground, afraid that

06:33:54.599 --> 06:33:56.099
the guards would spot them if they flew

06:33:56.099 --> 06:33:56.880
this close to the camp.

06:33:56.939 --> 06:34:00.360
Most of the campfires were now just dying

06:34:00.360 --> 06:34:03.180
embers, but a few had been rebuilt, and

06:34:03.180 --> 06:34:04.740
the smell of roasting meat and smoke

06:34:04.740 --> 06:34:06.779
floated through the pre-dawn air.

06:34:06.840 --> 06:34:09.119
Birds fluttered and chirped in the trees

06:34:09.119 --> 06:34:11.400
at half hearted intervals, as if they

06:34:11.400 --> 06:34:12.659
weren't sure they should be awake yet.

06:34:12.720 --> 06:34:15.959
Sunny's eyes ached, and her wings had

06:34:15.959 --> 06:34:16.860
never felt heavier.

06:34:16.919 --> 06:34:19.799
They had reached the scrub brush on the

06:34:19.799 --> 06:34:22.139
hills overlooking the camp, when Sunny

06:34:22.139 --> 06:34:23.340
heard a different sound coming from

06:34:23.340 --> 06:34:25.619
behind them, not the rustling and

06:34:25.619 --> 06:34:27.659
stamping of dragons, or the clanking of

06:34:27.659 --> 06:34:28.020
weapons.

06:34:28.080 --> 06:34:30.299
She heard singing.

06:34:30.360 --> 06:34:33.659
Oh, the dragonettes are coming.

06:34:33.720 --> 06:34:36.299
Clay, she whispered.

06:34:36.360 --> 06:34:37.500
Do you hear that?

06:34:37.560 --> 06:34:39.000
Am I imagining it?

06:34:39.060 --> 06:34:41.580
He stopped and lifted his head to

06:34:41.580 --> 06:34:41.759
listen.

06:34:41.819 --> 06:34:44.759
They're coming to save the day.

06:34:44.819 --> 06:34:48.659
Voices in the camp below, more than one

06:34:48.659 --> 06:34:50.099
in different parts of the camp.

06:34:50.159 --> 06:34:52.200
The mud wings were singing.

06:34:52.200 --> 06:34:55.319
They're coming to fight, for they know

06:34:55.319 --> 06:34:55.919
what's right.

06:34:55.979 --> 06:34:59.159
It was the eerie version they'd last

06:34:59.159 --> 06:35:01.799
heard in the Sky Palace, not the usual

06:35:01.799 --> 06:35:04.139
rousing bar song that tsunami used to

06:35:04.139 --> 06:35:06.060
sing around the cave whenever she wanted

06:35:06.060 --> 06:35:07.200
to annoy the Guardians.

06:35:07.259 --> 06:35:10.259
Sutny had been trapped in her bird cage

06:35:10.259 --> 06:35:11.099
alone.

06:35:11.159 --> 06:35:13.860
On display above the banquet, Scarlet was

06:35:13.860 --> 06:35:14.700
holding for Bern.

06:35:14.759 --> 06:35:16.799
But everyone there had heard it.

06:35:16.860 --> 06:35:19.200
The sound of the prisoners singing

06:35:19.200 --> 06:35:21.180
echoing over the cliffs in the night.

06:35:21.240 --> 06:35:24.060
Sonny could remember the shivery, hopeful

06:35:24.060 --> 06:35:26.159
feeling it had given her, and she also

06:35:26.159 --> 06:35:28.080
remembered the expressions on some of the

06:35:28.080 --> 06:35:32.340
soldiers' faces, hope, dread, longing.

06:35:32.400 --> 06:35:35.520
Most of them much more complicated than

06:35:35.520 --> 06:35:37.680
the pure fury visible on Scarlet and

06:35:37.680 --> 06:35:38.099
Burn.

06:35:38.159 --> 06:35:41.520
She felt it again now, like sand

06:35:41.520 --> 06:35:43.979
trickling across her scales all the way

06:35:43.979 --> 06:35:44.639
down her spine.

06:35:44.759 --> 06:35:46.860
Those dragons singing.

06:35:46.919 --> 06:35:49.080
Those were the dragons who believed in

06:35:49.080 --> 06:35:49.319
them.

06:35:49.380 --> 06:35:51.599
They were the reason she and her friends

06:35:51.599 --> 06:35:52.319
had to do this.

06:35:52.380 --> 06:35:54.779
I hope we can do this.

06:35:54.840 --> 06:35:57.659
I really, really hope we can do this.

06:35:57.720 --> 06:36:01.319
She glanced up at Clay, who smiled at

06:36:01.319 --> 06:36:01.560
her.

06:36:01.619 --> 06:36:03.840
Just being near him made her feel like

06:36:03.840 --> 06:36:04.740
anything was possible.

06:36:04.799 --> 06:36:08.279
Clay was so real and solid, and

06:36:08.279 --> 06:36:09.779
dependable, and kind.

06:36:09.840 --> 06:36:11.159
He would always be there.

06:36:11.220 --> 06:36:14.279
Clay had kept all of them from killing

06:36:14.279 --> 06:36:15.900
each other as they grew up under the

06:36:15.900 --> 06:36:18.180
mountain, trapped with only one another

06:36:18.180 --> 06:36:19.080
and their guardians.

06:36:19.200 --> 06:36:21.720
If he hadn't been there, would they have

06:36:21.720 --> 06:36:23.220
been more like the alternates?

06:36:23.279 --> 06:36:26.099
The fake dragonettes of destiny, who'd

06:36:26.099 --> 06:36:26.759
hated one another?

06:36:26.819 --> 06:36:30.479
Kutsunami, glory, and Starflight have

06:36:30.479 --> 06:36:32.700
turned out that way, hostile and

06:36:32.700 --> 06:36:35.400
aggressive, and angry all the time, if

06:36:35.400 --> 06:36:36.840
they hadn't had clay to keep them

06:36:36.840 --> 06:36:37.139
together.

06:36:37.200 --> 06:36:39.659
Would Sonny have ended up like fate

06:36:39.659 --> 06:36:41.939
speaker, clinging to a belief in a

06:36:41.939 --> 06:36:43.500
friendship and loyalty that didn't

06:36:43.500 --> 06:36:44.040
exist?

06:36:44.220 --> 06:36:45.959
But that hadn't happened.

06:36:46.020 --> 06:36:47.700
They'd had clay.

06:36:47.759 --> 06:36:49.740
And he stopped them from fighting too

06:36:49.740 --> 06:36:52.020
much, and he made jokes when anyone was

06:36:52.020 --> 06:36:53.939
sad, and he made them care about one

06:36:53.939 --> 06:36:56.220
another, and he believed in all of them.

06:36:56.279 --> 06:36:59.580
He'd made them a family, even though they

06:36:59.580 --> 06:37:00.360
were from different tribes.

06:37:00.419 --> 06:37:03.720
He really is our big wings.

06:37:03.779 --> 06:37:07.259
Let's get back to the others, she said

06:37:07.259 --> 06:37:09.840
and he nodded, and soon they were winging

06:37:09.840 --> 06:37:11.340
their way back to the rainforest.

06:37:11.400 --> 06:37:12.959
Six more days.

06:37:13.020 --> 06:37:15.240
We can do this.

06:37:15.299 --> 06:37:18.419
She's not coming?

06:37:18.479 --> 06:37:19.680
Sonny cried.

06:37:19.740 --> 06:37:21.060
What do you mean she's not coming?

06:37:21.180 --> 06:37:24.060
A shower of raindrops pattered over her

06:37:24.060 --> 06:37:26.700
wings, sending pink and red hibiscus

06:37:26.700 --> 06:37:28.680
flowers whirling down past her toward the

06:37:28.680 --> 06:37:29.880
ground far below.

06:37:29.880 --> 06:37:33.060
Jambu shook his head, looking very

06:37:33.060 --> 06:37:34.860
literally blue from horns to tail.

06:37:34.919 --> 06:37:38.580
We tried, but every ice wing we talked to

06:37:38.580 --> 06:37:39.659
basically laughed at us.

06:37:39.720 --> 06:37:42.779
They said Blaze never leaves her fortress

06:37:42.779 --> 06:37:45.659
and she won't until Glacier lets her go

06:37:45.659 --> 06:37:47.459
which will be when burn and blister are

06:37:47.459 --> 06:37:47.639
dead.

06:37:47.700 --> 06:37:50.880
They know if she gets near one of her

06:37:50.880 --> 06:37:51.419
sisters.

06:37:51.479 --> 06:37:54.000
She's dead, Mangrove said.

06:37:54.060 --> 06:37:57.180
She doesn't stand a chance in a challenge

06:37:57.180 --> 06:37:57.479
duel.

06:37:57.540 --> 06:38:00.060
Then why do the ice wing support her?

06:38:00.119 --> 06:38:01.799
Glory said crossly.

06:38:01.860 --> 06:38:04.020
Don't they want the sandwings to have a

06:38:04.020 --> 06:38:04.740
strong queen?

06:38:04.799 --> 06:38:06.720
No, of course they don't.

06:38:06.840 --> 06:38:09.599
She answered herself. figuring it out as

06:38:09.599 --> 06:38:09.959
she spoke.

06:38:10.020 --> 06:38:12.240
The one kingdom they share a border

06:38:12.240 --> 06:38:12.599
with.

06:38:12.659 --> 06:38:14.700
Wouldn't it be great if it happened to be

06:38:14.700 --> 06:38:17.159
ruled by a vain, silly dragon, who was

06:38:17.159 --> 06:38:18.599
totally in debt to them and did

06:38:18.599 --> 06:38:21.360
everything their queen ordered, maddening

06:38:21.360 --> 06:38:22.979
for us, but sensible for them.

06:38:23.040 --> 06:38:25.439
Queen Glacier knows what she's doing.

06:38:25.500 --> 06:38:29.340
Unless she loses, like if Blaise happened

06:38:29.340 --> 06:38:31.979
to die somehow, in which case she'd have

06:38:31.979 --> 06:38:34.259
to deal with Burr right on her border, all

06:38:34.259 --> 06:38:36.000
enraged and looking for vengeance.

06:38:36.060 --> 06:38:39.299
All right, yes, I can see why she'd keep

06:38:39.299 --> 06:38:40.139
her safely locked up.

06:38:40.200 --> 06:38:41.759
Three moons.

06:38:41.880 --> 06:38:44.700
That was like watching her brain work on

06:38:44.700 --> 06:38:45.540
the outside of her head.

06:38:45.599 --> 06:38:47.880
Fate speaker said to Starflight.

06:38:47.939 --> 06:38:51.119
Well, we can't let her stay all locked up

06:38:51.119 --> 06:38:52.080
Sonny said.

06:38:52.139 --> 06:38:54.240
It's not going to work unless all 3

06:38:54.240 --> 06:38:55.860
sisters are there, right?

06:38:55.919 --> 06:38:56.639
Don't you agree?

06:38:56.700 --> 06:38:59.459
Yes, Glory said.

06:38:59.520 --> 06:39:01.799
And tsunami and Starflight nodded as

06:39:01.799 --> 06:39:02.400
well.

06:39:02.459 --> 06:39:04.560
If what you want is to forge a peace

06:39:04.560 --> 06:39:06.779
treaty, All the combatants need to be

06:39:06.779 --> 06:39:07.680
present to agree to it.

06:39:07.740 --> 06:39:10.619
Glory scratched her snout, thinking

06:39:10.619 --> 06:39:12.779
perhaps it would be enough to have Queen

06:39:12.779 --> 06:39:13.619
Glacier there.

06:39:13.740 --> 06:39:15.000
But I don't think so.

06:39:15.060 --> 06:39:17.880
Glacier would know that it would look

06:39:17.880 --> 06:39:20.099
like weakness to come in her place and

06:39:20.099 --> 06:39:22.740
let Blaze stay in hiding, safer for

06:39:22.740 --> 06:39:23.580
neither of them to show up.

06:39:23.639 --> 06:39:26.520
But doesn't Queen Glacier want to end the

06:39:26.520 --> 06:39:27.000
war too?

06:39:27.119 --> 06:39:28.139
Sonny said.

06:39:28.200 --> 06:39:29.400
I'm sure she does.

06:39:29.520 --> 06:39:31.979
I'm especially sure she would if she knew

06:39:31.979 --> 06:39:33.720
what burn and the mud wings were planning

06:39:33.720 --> 06:39:36.180
a few days ago, even if they've put off

06:39:36.180 --> 06:39:37.439
their invasion plans for now.

06:39:37.500 --> 06:39:39.540
Are we sure about that?

06:39:39.599 --> 06:39:41.099
Starflight asked.

06:39:41.159 --> 06:39:42.659
They're really not invading?

06:39:42.720 --> 06:39:45.720
It doesn't look like it, Glory said.

06:39:45.779 --> 06:39:47.279
On her shoulder.

06:39:47.340 --> 06:39:50.520
Her sloth woke up, chirruped sleepily, and

06:39:50.520 --> 06:39:52.380
tucked itself closer to her wing before

06:39:52.380 --> 06:39:53.159
closing its eyes again.

06:39:53.220 --> 06:39:56.279
We've dream visited with Clay's brother

06:39:56.279 --> 06:39:58.080
and also sent out scouts to check.

06:39:58.139 --> 06:40:01.020
It seems like that mud wing camp is in a

06:40:01.020 --> 06:40:01.619
holding pattern.

06:40:01.680 --> 06:40:04.799
No one flying off to kill ice wings, at

06:40:04.799 --> 06:40:05.279
least for now.

06:40:05.340 --> 06:40:08.279
Queen Morehen is waiting to see what

06:40:08.279 --> 06:40:10.860
happens at the stronghold, Sonny said

06:40:10.860 --> 06:40:13.799
shaking loose flowers off her wings, which

06:40:13.799 --> 06:40:16.200
means our plan really has to work, or

06:40:16.200 --> 06:40:17.759
else the invasion might still happen.

06:40:17.880 --> 06:40:20.880
Maybe if we could tell Queen Glacier that

06:40:20.880 --> 06:40:23.040
she'd let Blaze come.

06:40:23.159 --> 06:40:26.520
Maybe, tsunami said, but we can't get to

06:40:26.520 --> 06:40:28.259
the queen if she's in her ice palace.

06:40:28.319 --> 06:40:30.240
Not that it would be safe to go talk to

06:40:30.240 --> 06:40:31.319
her no matter where she is.

06:40:31.439 --> 06:40:33.959
And none of us have seen her.

06:40:34.080 --> 06:40:36.299
So we can't even dream visitor.

06:40:36.360 --> 06:40:37.619
Clay pointed out.

06:40:37.680 --> 06:40:41.700
But we can dream visit Blaze, Sonny

06:40:41.700 --> 06:40:42.000
said.

06:40:42.060 --> 06:40:43.560
I think that's what we have to do.

06:40:43.619 --> 06:40:46.080
Glory, you should do it.

06:40:46.200 --> 06:40:46.979
You really convincing.

06:40:47.040 --> 06:40:50.159
Glory looked down at the sapphire as then

06:40:50.159 --> 06:40:50.880
he passed it to her.

06:40:50.939 --> 06:40:53.279
She thought for a moment, then shook her

06:40:53.279 --> 06:40:53.639
head.

06:40:53.700 --> 06:40:55.860
No, she won't listen to me.

06:40:55.919 --> 06:40:58.259
She kept saying, I shouldn't be part of

06:40:58.259 --> 06:40:59.279
the prophecy, remember?

06:40:59.340 --> 06:41:00.779
She wouldn't take me seriously.

06:41:00.840 --> 06:41:03.599
And she's jealous of glory.

06:41:03.720 --> 06:41:05.580
Death bringer interjected.

06:41:05.639 --> 06:41:08.279
Blaze doesn't like any dragons prettier

06:41:08.279 --> 06:41:08.759
than she is.

06:41:08.819 --> 06:41:10.020
Which glory is.

06:41:10.080 --> 06:41:13.080
Not that I've noticed myself personally.

06:41:13.139 --> 06:41:13.799
It's just a fact.

06:41:13.860 --> 06:41:15.959
Enough out of you.

06:41:16.020 --> 06:41:19.319
Glory said, folding her wings in, but not

06:41:19.319 --> 06:41:21.180
before Sonny spotted the hints of pink

06:41:21.180 --> 06:41:22.380
blooming along the edges.

06:41:22.439 --> 06:41:24.840
I've already said you can be the night

06:41:24.840 --> 06:41:27.180
wing liaison, so flattery won't get you

06:41:27.180 --> 06:41:29.159
anything else, Mr. Clever Scales.

06:41:29.220 --> 06:41:32.400
It's not flattery to state the obvious. he

06:41:32.400 --> 06:41:32.639
said.

06:41:32.700 --> 06:41:35.580
It should be sunny or tsunami.

06:41:35.700 --> 06:41:38.340
Glory said, ignoring him and passing the

06:41:38.340 --> 06:41:40.380
sapphire back into Sonny's talons.

06:41:40.439 --> 06:41:42.900
Tsunami actually got wounded trying to

06:41:42.900 --> 06:41:44.700
help her. so she might be impressed by

06:41:44.700 --> 06:41:44.880
that.

06:41:44.939 --> 06:41:47.939
But then, tsunami is about as diplomatic

06:41:47.939 --> 06:41:50.400
as a starving rhinoceros, so I'd probably

06:41:50.400 --> 06:41:51.240
vote for Sonny.

06:41:51.299 --> 06:41:53.880
I beg your pardon.

06:41:53.939 --> 06:41:55.439
Tsunami objected.

06:41:55.500 --> 06:41:58.680
I can be very diplomatic when I want to

06:41:58.680 --> 06:41:59.099
be.

06:41:59.159 --> 06:42:01.500
I'm sure, Glory said.

06:42:01.560 --> 06:42:02.459
Any other votes?

06:42:02.580 --> 06:42:05.759
As each of them voted for her, Sonny felt

06:42:05.759 --> 06:42:07.200
as though her own scales might turn

06:42:07.200 --> 06:42:07.560
pink.

06:42:07.680 --> 06:42:11.400
You are all, you're such a bunch of

06:42:11.400 --> 06:42:13.139
tsunami sputtered.

06:42:13.200 --> 06:42:15.959
Frog faced blobs of camel spit?

06:42:16.020 --> 06:42:17.159
Sonny suggested.

06:42:17.220 --> 06:42:19.919
Tsunami started laughing so hard, she

06:42:19.919 --> 06:42:21.180
nearly fell off the branch.

06:42:21.240 --> 06:42:24.479
All right, fine, she said, recovering at

06:42:24.479 --> 06:42:24.659
last.

06:42:24.720 --> 06:42:27.000
I don't see how I can compete with that

06:42:27.000 --> 06:42:28.200
kind of mastery of language.

06:42:28.319 --> 06:42:30.900
But then you should use the dream visitor

06:42:30.900 --> 06:42:33.720
to talk to your mother, Sonny said, or to

06:42:33.720 --> 06:42:36.000
someone in your kingdom, some sea wings

06:42:36.000 --> 06:42:38.099
should come to the stronghold if any of

06:42:38.099 --> 06:42:39.659
them are willing to see what happens.

06:42:39.720 --> 06:42:43.560
Tsunami nodded, bumping Sonny's shoulder

06:42:43.560 --> 06:42:44.220
affectionately.

06:42:44.279 --> 06:42:45.720
I can do that.

06:42:45.779 --> 06:42:47.880
I'd like to check on anemone anyway.

06:42:47.939 --> 06:42:51.119
That night, Sonny took the dream visitor

06:42:51.119 --> 06:42:52.860
and flew to the pool by the tunnels.

06:42:52.919 --> 06:42:54.840
She chose the tunnel that led from the

06:42:54.840 --> 06:42:56.700
kingdom of sand to the rainforest.

06:42:56.819 --> 06:42:59.099
The one that led to the night kingdom

06:42:59.099 --> 06:43:01.919
smelled of burnt scales and fire, and

06:43:01.919 --> 06:43:03.000
still radiated heat.

06:43:03.119 --> 06:43:06.000
She crouched in the darkest part of the

06:43:06.000 --> 06:43:08.040
tunnel, where it was pitch black.

06:43:08.099 --> 06:43:10.080
There was nothing around her to offer a

06:43:10.080 --> 06:43:12.240
clue about where she was, even if the

06:43:12.240 --> 06:43:13.979
dream visitor gave the dreamer a glimpse

06:43:13.979 --> 06:43:16.139
of her, all she would see was blackness.

06:43:16.200 --> 06:43:18.419
Hopefully Blaze would think it was a cave

06:43:18.419 --> 06:43:19.860
in the mountains, if anything.

06:43:19.919 --> 06:43:22.619
She closed her eyes and held the blue

06:43:22.619 --> 06:43:23.819
sapphire to her head again.

06:43:23.880 --> 06:43:27.299
It hummed in a strange way, like far away

06:43:27.299 --> 06:43:29.279
chanting faintly heard through layers of

06:43:29.279 --> 06:43:29.520
rock.

06:43:29.580 --> 06:43:31.619
Blaze.

06:43:31.680 --> 06:43:34.259
Sonny pictured the beautiful sand wing.

06:43:34.319 --> 06:43:36.659
They'd only met once in the Ice Kingdom.

06:43:36.720 --> 06:43:39.599
Later, she'd overheard tsunami describing

06:43:39.599 --> 06:43:40.619
Blaze to Kinkachu.

06:43:40.680 --> 06:43:43.560
She's pretty but silly, one of those

06:43:43.560 --> 06:43:46.200
overly optimistic dragons, like Sonia

06:43:46.200 --> 06:43:48.479
sometimes, although Blaze is more self

06:43:47.880 --> 06:43:48.479
centered.

06:43:48.540 --> 06:43:51.599
This comparison had made Sonny want to

06:43:51.599 --> 06:43:53.400
shred a tree with her bare claws.

06:43:53.459 --> 06:43:57.479
She was nothing, nothing like Blaze, and

06:43:57.479 --> 06:43:59.400
if tsunami thought so, then she really

06:43:59.400 --> 06:44:01.740
must think Sunny was an idiot with no

06:44:01.740 --> 06:44:02.700
brains in her head at all.

06:44:02.759 --> 06:44:04.740
Don't think about that now.

06:44:04.860 --> 06:44:07.560
Concentrate on getting into Blaze's

06:44:07.560 --> 06:44:08.939
dreams, she thought.

06:44:09.000 --> 06:44:11.880
And then she opened her eyes and realized

06:44:11.880 --> 06:44:13.500
she was already there.

06:44:13.560 --> 06:44:16.439
She stood in the desert, claws sinking

06:44:16.439 --> 06:44:17.459
into warm sand.

06:44:17.520 --> 06:44:21.419
Blaze was flying, her polished scales

06:44:21.419 --> 06:44:23.400
shimmering in the bright hot sunlight.

06:44:23.459 --> 06:44:27.060
She shone against the clear blue sky, and

06:44:27.060 --> 06:44:29.220
beautiful jewels sparkled all along her

06:44:29.220 --> 06:44:29.639
scales.

06:44:29.700 --> 06:44:32.639
She kept circling in the air and twisting

06:44:32.639 --> 06:44:34.799
her head to look down, not far from where

06:44:34.799 --> 06:44:37.080
Sonny was, but she didn't seem to notice

06:44:37.080 --> 06:44:37.919
Sonny at first.

06:44:37.979 --> 06:44:40.799
Sonny lifted herself onto her back talons

06:44:40.799 --> 06:44:43.200
to look around, and spotted a clear pool

06:44:43.200 --> 06:44:44.400
of water not far away.

06:44:44.459 --> 06:44:47.159
Blaise was admiring herself in the

06:44:47.159 --> 06:44:48.360
perfectly still reflection.

06:44:48.419 --> 06:44:50.400
Good grief.

06:44:50.459 --> 06:44:51.779
Sonny muttered.

06:44:51.840 --> 06:44:54.000
She flared her wings and waved at the

06:44:54.000 --> 06:44:54.959
sand wing in the sky.

06:44:55.020 --> 06:44:57.479
It took a lot of flapping before Blaze

06:44:57.479 --> 06:44:59.819
finally gave a little start and veered

06:44:59.819 --> 06:45:00.900
around to stare at Sonny.

06:45:00.959 --> 06:45:03.419
Sonny beckoned, wanting to have this

06:45:03.419 --> 06:45:04.860
conversation on solid ground.

06:45:04.919 --> 06:45:08.159
Blaze landed in front of her, kicking

06:45:08.159 --> 06:45:10.319
sand up Sonny's nose without noticing

06:45:10.319 --> 06:45:11.099
she'd done so.

06:45:11.159 --> 06:45:13.080
She swished her tail around and sat

06:45:13.080 --> 06:45:13.740
gracefully.

06:45:13.799 --> 06:45:16.619
Hello, I know you, don't I?

06:45:16.680 --> 06:45:17.580
she asked.

06:45:17.700 --> 06:45:19.979
We've met, Sonny said.

06:45:20.099 --> 06:45:21.840
I'm one of the dragonettes.

06:45:21.900 --> 06:45:23.580
That was all she had to say.

06:45:23.700 --> 06:45:26.279
Dragonettes of destiny didn't sound right

06:45:26.279 --> 06:45:28.799
to her anymore, not since she'd found out

06:45:28.799 --> 06:45:30.119
the truth about the prophecy.

06:45:30.180 --> 06:45:32.639
She wondered briefly what would happen if

06:45:32.639 --> 06:45:35.040
she just told the sandwing sisters that

06:45:35.040 --> 06:45:36.060
the prophecy was false.

06:45:36.119 --> 06:45:38.939
Then they really wouldn't listen to us

06:45:38.939 --> 06:45:40.139
she thought.

06:45:40.200 --> 06:45:42.599
We'd have no chance of making this work.

06:45:42.659 --> 06:45:45.360
We have to let them believe it, at least

06:45:45.360 --> 06:45:45.900
for now.

06:45:45.959 --> 06:45:48.299
Oh, of course.

06:45:48.360 --> 06:45:51.419
The weird looking sandwing, Blaise said.

06:45:51.479 --> 06:45:52.020
Right.

06:45:52.080 --> 06:45:53.639
Which necklace do you think looks better

06:45:53.639 --> 06:45:53.880
on me?

06:45:53.939 --> 06:45:56.639
I've always liked rubies, but these

06:45:56.639 --> 06:45:58.380
emeralds are smashing too, right?

06:45:58.500 --> 06:46:01.799
She held out 2 gem studded necklaces

06:46:01.799 --> 06:46:04.860
draped sparklingly across her claws.

06:46:04.919 --> 06:46:06.659
Blaze, Sonny said.

06:46:06.779 --> 06:46:08.639
Do you want to go home?

06:46:08.700 --> 06:46:10.619
The Sandwing princess looked around

06:46:10.619 --> 06:46:11.279
blinking.

06:46:11.340 --> 06:46:12.659
Aren't I home?

06:46:12.720 --> 06:46:14.580
This is a dream.

06:46:14.700 --> 06:46:16.439
Sonny said patiently.

06:46:16.500 --> 06:46:19.319
I mean, really home, home to the

06:46:19.319 --> 06:46:21.779
stronghold in the desert, to sand and

06:46:21.779 --> 06:46:24.060
roasted lizards and warm sunshine every

06:46:24.060 --> 06:46:24.240
day.

06:46:24.299 --> 06:46:26.159
Oh my.

06:46:26.220 --> 06:46:28.919
Blaise said. a wistful sigh.

06:46:28.979 --> 06:46:31.919
I remember my rooms in the stronghold.

06:46:31.979 --> 06:46:34.740
They were so big and pretty, with tall

06:46:34.740 --> 06:46:36.240
windows on 3 walls.

06:46:36.360 --> 06:46:39.419
I really do look my best and full natural

06:46:39.419 --> 06:46:40.080
sunlight, you know.

06:46:40.139 --> 06:46:42.720
She spread her wings and swished them

06:46:42.720 --> 06:46:44.580
gracefully around, admiring them.

06:46:44.639 --> 06:46:47.279
Sonny managed not to roll her eyes.

06:46:47.400 --> 06:46:49.139
So come to us.

06:46:49.200 --> 06:46:51.659
Don't keep hiding in that cold, dark

06:46:51.659 --> 06:46:52.319
fortress.

06:46:52.380 --> 06:46:54.360
If you come to the stronghold.

06:46:54.419 --> 06:46:56.340
We'll end this war and you can go home.

06:46:56.400 --> 06:46:58.080
What?

06:46:58.139 --> 06:47:00.599
Blaise said, tilting her head.

06:47:00.659 --> 06:47:02.459
Right now?

06:47:02.520 --> 06:47:05.759
The 3rd midnight from tonight, Sonny

06:47:05.759 --> 06:47:06.119
said.

06:47:06.180 --> 06:47:07.799
Didn't anyone give you our message?

06:47:07.860 --> 06:47:11.400
No one said anything about a message, said

06:47:11.400 --> 06:47:11.939
Blaze.

06:47:12.060 --> 06:47:14.520
From the dragoness of the prophecy?

06:47:14.580 --> 06:47:16.139
How could they keep something like that

06:47:16.139 --> 06:47:16.500
for me?

06:47:16.560 --> 06:47:19.080
Well, I am offended.

06:47:19.139 --> 06:47:21.779
She thought for a moment, then

06:47:21.779 --> 06:47:22.200
brightened.

06:47:22.259 --> 06:47:25.020
Oh, so you did pick me.

06:47:25.080 --> 06:47:28.139
Well, wait, Sonny said.

06:47:28.200 --> 06:47:29.819
We haven't picked any of you yet.

06:47:29.880 --> 06:47:30.419
We.

06:47:31.319 --> 06:47:32.099
Right, of course.

06:47:32.159 --> 06:47:34.380
You haven't announced it or anything, but

06:47:34.380 --> 06:47:35.220
you're going to pick me.

06:47:35.279 --> 06:47:38.700
The only way I can go home, after all, is

06:47:38.700 --> 06:47:40.860
if my sisters are dead.

06:47:40.919 --> 06:47:42.720
Oh, how lovely.

06:47:42.779 --> 06:47:44.700
I knew you would choose me.

06:47:44.759 --> 06:47:45.840
I am very nice.

06:47:45.900 --> 06:47:47.700
And doesn't everyone want a beautiful

06:47:47.700 --> 06:47:48.540
queen.

06:47:48.599 --> 06:47:51.720
Not at all, Sonny thought.

06:47:51.779 --> 06:47:54.299
We're really looking for a peaceful

06:47:54.299 --> 06:47:55.919
outcome, she said.

06:47:55.979 --> 06:47:58.619
That's our goal, and then whoever becomes

06:47:58.619 --> 06:47:59.099
queen.

06:47:59.159 --> 06:48:01.619
I'm going to order a new bracelet to

06:48:01.619 --> 06:48:01.979
celebrate.

06:48:02.099 --> 06:48:05.040
Blaise declared. jumping up and nearly

06:48:05.040 --> 06:48:06.119
dancing around Sonny.

06:48:06.240 --> 06:48:07.979
And a crown.

06:48:08.040 --> 06:48:09.299
Of course, I need a crown.

06:48:09.360 --> 06:48:12.599
Oh, now I really have to decide rubies or

06:48:12.599 --> 06:48:13.259
emeralds.

06:48:13.380 --> 06:48:16.680
I suppose I could have 2 crowns or lots

06:48:16.680 --> 06:48:17.759
and lots of crowns.

06:48:17.819 --> 06:48:19.259
I am so excited.

06:48:19.319 --> 06:48:22.740
Blaze, stop, Sonny said desperately.

06:48:22.799 --> 06:48:24.900
The princess wasn't listening to her at

06:48:24.900 --> 06:48:27.240
all, and Sonny didn't want to lie to her

06:48:27.240 --> 06:48:29.159
or make her show up under false

06:48:29.159 --> 06:48:29.819
pretenses.

06:48:29.880 --> 06:48:32.580
The important thing is that you be there

06:48:32.580 --> 06:48:34.799
at the stronghold, and then we'll figure

06:48:34.799 --> 06:48:35.819
out who should be queen.

06:48:35.880 --> 06:48:37.500
It might not be you.

06:48:37.560 --> 06:48:38.639
Do you understand?

06:48:38.700 --> 06:48:42.299
Glacier is going to be pleased too, said

06:48:42.299 --> 06:48:44.279
Blaise, talking right over Sonny.

06:48:44.340 --> 06:48:46.680
I'll have to convince her to let me go

06:48:46.680 --> 06:48:48.659
but I can win arguments when I really

06:48:48.659 --> 06:48:49.080
want to.

06:48:49.200 --> 06:48:51.779
I'll tell her there's a new crown in it

06:48:51.779 --> 06:48:52.319
for her too.

06:48:52.380 --> 06:48:55.560
I think she looks best in sapphires

06:48:55.560 --> 06:48:56.040
naturally.

06:48:56.099 --> 06:48:57.900
So you'll be there?

06:48:57.959 --> 06:49:00.779
Sonny said, even knowing you might not be

06:49:00.779 --> 06:49:01.919
queen when it's all over.

06:49:01.979 --> 06:49:05.279
Blaze was already swanning back to the

06:49:05.279 --> 06:49:05.819
still pool.

06:49:05.880 --> 06:49:09.419
You can live in my palace if you like, she

06:49:09.419 --> 06:49:10.319
called back to Sonny.

06:49:10.380 --> 06:49:13.020
I could give you a really important job.

06:49:13.080 --> 06:49:15.180
Ooh, like helping me get dressed in the

06:49:15.180 --> 06:49:15.540
morning.

06:49:15.599 --> 06:49:18.900
Sometimes it takes me simply hours to

06:49:18.900 --> 06:49:20.159
choose the right anklet.

06:49:20.220 --> 06:49:22.979
Midnight, at the stronghold.

06:49:23.099 --> 06:49:24.779
Sonny cried after her.

06:49:24.900 --> 06:49:26.819
Three midnights from tonight.

06:49:26.880 --> 06:49:29.279
That means not tonight, not tomorrow

06:49:29.279 --> 06:49:30.840
night, but the night after that.

06:49:30.900 --> 06:49:32.340
Will you remember?

06:49:32.400 --> 06:49:33.240
Will you count right?

06:49:33.299 --> 06:49:37.919
Queen Blaze, sang the sand wing princess

06:49:37.919 --> 06:49:39.540
as she lifted into the air.

06:49:39.540 --> 06:49:41.520
Doesn't that sound pretty?

06:49:41.580 --> 06:49:43.319
Oh, dear.

06:49:43.380 --> 06:49:44.639
Sonny thought.

06:49:44.700 --> 06:49:47.099
She stepped out of the dream and stared

06:49:47.099 --> 06:49:48.540
into the blackness all around her.

06:49:48.599 --> 06:49:51.659
Will Queen Glacier listen to her?

06:49:51.720 --> 06:49:53.099
Will she be there?

06:49:53.159 --> 06:49:55.799
What if all of this falls apart and we

06:49:55.799 --> 06:49:56.099
fail?

06:49:56.159 --> 06:49:59.400
She gripped the dream visitor tightly in

06:49:59.400 --> 06:49:59.819
her claws?

06:49:59.939 --> 06:50:02.939
That's not an option.

06:50:02.939 --> 06:50:05.220
If Blaze doesn't show up, I'll fly to the

06:50:05.220 --> 06:50:06.959
Ice Kingdom and drag her back myself.

06:50:07.020 --> 06:50:10.860
In 4 days time, either the war will be

06:50:10.860 --> 06:50:13.020
over, or we'll all be dead.

06:50:13.139 --> 06:50:17.759
Chapter 24.

06:50:17.939 --> 06:50:22.200
Night had fallen, and the sky was full of

06:50:22.200 --> 06:50:22.680
dragons.

06:50:22.740 --> 06:50:26.099
That was the 1st thing Sonny noticed when

06:50:26.099 --> 06:50:27.720
she stepped out of the tunnel onto the

06:50:27.720 --> 06:50:30.419
desert sands, the air crackled with the

06:50:30.419 --> 06:50:32.279
sound of wing beats and the smell of

06:50:32.279 --> 06:50:32.520
fire.

06:50:32.639 --> 06:50:36.180
Dragons soared overhead like a 1000000

06:50:36.180 --> 06:50:39.000
bats, sinuous shapes silhouetted across

06:50:39.000 --> 06:50:39.479
the moons.

06:50:39.540 --> 06:50:41.520
It was time.

06:50:41.580 --> 06:50:42.840
This was the night.

06:50:42.900 --> 06:50:45.540
All 3 sandwing sisters would be in the

06:50:45.540 --> 06:50:47.459
same place for the 1st time since the war

06:50:47.459 --> 06:50:47.880
began.

06:50:47.939 --> 06:50:51.360
If they show up, Sonny thought.

06:50:51.419 --> 06:50:53.700
She glanced at the night sky again.

06:50:53.759 --> 06:50:55.979
It certainly seems like every other

06:50:55.979 --> 06:50:57.599
dragon empire might be here.

06:50:57.720 --> 06:51:00.659
And it was easier to see them than it

06:51:00.659 --> 06:51:02.520
should have been because of the mystery

06:51:02.520 --> 06:51:03.299
orb in the sky.

06:51:03.360 --> 06:51:05.819
It had gotten bigger and brighter every

06:51:05.819 --> 06:51:09.060
night, and now it was the same size as

06:51:09.060 --> 06:51:11.459
the other moons, 2 of which were full.

06:51:11.520 --> 06:51:14.759
Between the 3 of them filling the sky, it

06:51:14.759 --> 06:51:16.380
looked like another brightest night.

06:51:16.439 --> 06:51:19.439
A new brightest night, when there

06:51:19.439 --> 06:51:21.060
shouldn't have been one for another 94

06:51:21.060 --> 06:51:22.740
years, Sonny thought.

06:51:22.799 --> 06:51:25.439
If that's not an omen, what is?

06:51:25.500 --> 06:51:27.840
She hadn't said that to her friends

06:51:27.840 --> 06:51:28.020
though.

06:51:28.080 --> 06:51:30.479
She knew they'd roll their eyes at her

06:51:30.479 --> 06:51:33.360
and the whole idea of destiny, or omens

06:51:33.360 --> 06:51:36.659
but still, that 3rd uncanny moon in the

06:51:36.659 --> 06:51:38.939
sky made her feel somehow a little more

06:51:38.939 --> 06:51:41.099
hopeful, like maybe things would be all

06:51:41.099 --> 06:51:41.340
right.

06:51:41.400 --> 06:51:43.619
The way she used to feel when she thought

06:51:43.619 --> 06:51:44.400
about the prophecy.

06:51:44.520 --> 06:51:47.639
Sonny climbed up to the ridge overlooking

06:51:47.639 --> 06:51:50.520
the stronghold and stood between 2 cacti

06:51:50.520 --> 06:51:51.599
gazing down at it.

06:51:51.659 --> 06:51:54.959
The long black structure, all shadows in

06:51:54.959 --> 06:51:57.180
the moonlight, was vast and forbidding

06:51:57.180 --> 06:51:59.400
even from a distance, and she still had

06:51:59.400 --> 06:52:01.259
nightmares about the weirdling tower.

06:52:01.259 --> 06:52:03.599
She couldn't imagine stepping back inside

06:52:03.599 --> 06:52:04.860
there of her own free will.

06:52:04.919 --> 06:52:07.979
But that was exactly what she was about

06:52:07.979 --> 06:52:08.340
to do.

06:52:08.459 --> 06:52:11.759
The sound of shifting sand behind her

06:52:11.759 --> 06:52:14.400
signaled the arrival of her friends, and

06:52:14.400 --> 06:52:17.159
Sonny turned to see Clay, then tsunami

06:52:17.159 --> 06:52:19.740
then Starflight and fate speaker emerged

06:52:19.740 --> 06:52:20.340
from the tunnel.

06:52:20.400 --> 06:52:23.099
Fate speaker glanced around at the desert

06:52:23.099 --> 06:52:25.439
at the way the sand seemed to run all the

06:52:25.439 --> 06:52:26.639
way to the edge of the sky.

06:52:26.700 --> 06:52:27.840
She shuddered.

06:52:27.900 --> 06:52:31.380
This place is freaky, she whispered.

06:52:31.439 --> 06:52:33.540
Starflight, I don't think it's safe

06:52:33.540 --> 06:52:33.779
here.

06:52:33.840 --> 06:52:35.159
Shouldn't you stay behind?

06:52:35.220 --> 06:52:37.259
Starflight shook his head.

06:52:37.380 --> 06:52:39.419
No, I have to be here.

06:52:39.479 --> 06:52:42.540
I'm not missing this, even if I can't see

06:52:42.540 --> 06:52:42.720
it.

06:52:42.840 --> 06:52:46.080
He'd been practicing with Tamarin, the

06:52:46.080 --> 06:52:48.720
blind rain wing all week, how to fly with

06:52:48.720 --> 06:52:50.580
someone guiding him, how to sense

06:52:50.580 --> 06:52:53.520
unexpected obstacles, and most of all, how

06:52:53.520 --> 06:52:54.240
to ask for help.

06:52:54.299 --> 06:52:57.540
Sunny slid down the hill to them and

06:52:57.540 --> 06:52:59.700
brushed Starflight's wing with hers to

06:52:59.700 --> 06:53:00.720
let him know she was there.

06:53:00.779 --> 06:53:03.479
He leaned toward her, touching the

06:53:03.479 --> 06:53:04.200
bandage on his eyes.

06:53:04.259 --> 06:53:06.720
What is that?

06:53:06.840 --> 06:53:09.540
Fate speaker asked, staring up at the

06:53:09.540 --> 06:53:09.779
sky.

06:53:09.840 --> 06:53:12.659
Starflight, why is there a 4th moon?

06:53:12.720 --> 06:53:15.299
Sonny had already described it to him

06:53:15.299 --> 06:53:17.459
although his explanation didn't make all

06:53:17.459 --> 06:53:18.779
that much sense to her.

06:53:18.840 --> 06:53:21.840
I think it's more like a comet than a

06:53:21.840 --> 06:53:22.080
moon.

06:53:22.139 --> 06:53:24.360
Starflight said to fate speaker.

06:53:24.419 --> 06:53:26.700
I remember a scroll that mentioned

06:53:26.700 --> 06:53:28.619
something like that in the sky 100s of

06:53:28.619 --> 06:53:28.919
years ago.

06:53:28.979 --> 06:53:31.680
Maybe it circles around and only comes

06:53:31.680 --> 06:53:33.119
back every 1000 years or so.

06:53:33.240 --> 06:53:35.279
Have you noticed the earthquakes?

06:53:35.340 --> 06:53:37.439
I think they might be caused by the

06:53:37.439 --> 06:53:38.040
comet.

06:53:38.099 --> 06:53:40.919
The ground trembled quietly under them.

06:53:40.979 --> 06:53:43.500
The way it had several times in the last

06:53:43.500 --> 06:53:44.040
few days.

06:53:44.099 --> 06:53:47.099
Sunny dug her claws into the sand

06:53:47.099 --> 06:53:49.500
glancing up at the stars.

06:53:49.560 --> 06:53:52.319
But it's not going to, like, land on us

06:53:52.319 --> 06:53:52.979
or anything, right?

06:53:53.040 --> 06:53:55.680
Fate speaker said, because it sure looks

06:53:55.680 --> 06:53:56.520
like it's gotten bigger.

06:53:56.580 --> 06:53:58.860
I think maybe it's going to fall on us.

06:53:58.919 --> 06:54:02.520
Ooh, I think maybe I'm having a vision.

06:54:02.639 --> 06:54:04.439
Stop that.

06:54:04.500 --> 06:54:07.259
Starflight said, smacking her gently with

06:54:07.259 --> 06:54:07.680
his wing.

06:54:07.740 --> 06:54:09.840
You know those powers aren't real?

06:54:09.900 --> 06:54:12.360
Your visions are just your imagination.

06:54:12.419 --> 06:54:15.180
Fate speaker shot him a very indignant

06:54:15.180 --> 06:54:17.099
look, but he luckily couldn't see.

06:54:17.159 --> 06:54:20.459
I know that's what Stone Mover said, but

06:54:20.459 --> 06:54:21.599
I think it doesn't apply to me.

06:54:21.659 --> 06:54:24.119
My visions are totally real.

06:54:24.180 --> 06:54:26.759
And when this moon comet thing crushes us

06:54:26.759 --> 06:54:27.900
all.

06:54:27.959 --> 06:54:29.220
Everyone will be sorry for not listening

06:54:29.220 --> 06:54:29.580
to me.

06:54:29.639 --> 06:54:32.159
All right. he answered.

06:54:32.220 --> 06:54:33.119
We'll see.

06:54:33.180 --> 06:54:34.919
Where's Glory?

06:54:34.919 --> 06:54:37.560
Tsunami asked, coming back from scouting

06:54:37.560 --> 06:54:38.340
the top of the dunes.

06:54:38.400 --> 06:54:42.419
Right behind us, said Clay, and he jumped

06:54:42.419 --> 06:54:44.159
out of the way as more dragons started

06:54:44.159 --> 06:54:45.119
coming out of the tunnel.

06:54:45.180 --> 06:54:47.700
It was strange to know that all these

06:54:47.700 --> 06:54:50.099
dragons were rain wings, but to see

06:54:50.099 --> 06:54:52.380
instead, sky wings and night wings and

06:54:52.380 --> 06:54:53.040
mud wings.

06:54:53.099 --> 06:54:56.099
Glory had decided to bring 15 rain wings

06:54:56.099 --> 06:54:58.799
along to be voices for peace if necessary

06:54:58.799 --> 06:55:01.619
and to be dangerous venom spitting backup

06:55:01.619 --> 06:55:02.759
if really necessary.

06:55:02.819 --> 06:55:05.580
She decided it would be safer for her

06:55:05.580 --> 06:55:07.139
dragons if they came in disguise.

06:55:07.200 --> 06:55:09.659
Their camouflage scales making them

06:55:09.659 --> 06:55:10.919
anonymous bystanders.

06:55:10.979 --> 06:55:14.340
Those 3 tribes were the easiest disguises

06:55:14.340 --> 06:55:17.580
no poisonous tales, webbed talons, or

06:55:17.580 --> 06:55:18.840
serrated claws among them.

06:55:18.900 --> 06:55:22.139
There were 5 actual night wings as well

06:55:22.139 --> 06:55:25.500
plus Death Bringer, who'd refused to stay

06:55:25.500 --> 06:55:26.880
behind and let glory go without him.

06:55:26.939 --> 06:55:29.459
But you could be useful here.

06:55:29.520 --> 06:55:31.799
Glory had argued back in the rainforest.

06:55:31.860 --> 06:55:33.840
You could keep an eye on the night wings

06:55:33.840 --> 06:55:34.139
for me.

06:55:34.200 --> 06:55:37.200
I'd rather keep an eye on you. he

06:55:37.200 --> 06:55:39.299
retorted, and on all the dragons you're

06:55:39.299 --> 06:55:40.979
about to go chat with, who literally want

06:55:40.979 --> 06:55:41.340
to kill you.

06:55:41.459 --> 06:55:44.939
Hey, that's how you and I met, Glory

06:55:44.939 --> 06:55:45.180
said.

06:55:45.240 --> 06:55:47.040
Maybe I'll charm them out of the idea

06:55:47.040 --> 06:55:47.459
too.

06:55:47.520 --> 06:55:51.240
I'm not sure charm is quite the word I'd

06:55:51.240 --> 06:55:51.479
use.

06:55:51.540 --> 06:55:54.720
He'd mused, and gotten a swat to his nose

06:55:54.720 --> 06:55:55.439
as a thank you.

06:55:55.500 --> 06:55:58.860
But she'd let him select 5 night wings he

06:55:58.860 --> 06:56:00.299
thought were more trustworthy than the

06:56:00.299 --> 06:56:02.099
rest, so that the tribe would be

06:56:02.099 --> 06:56:03.900
represented at this gathering.

06:56:03.959 --> 06:56:05.340
Sunny thought that was probably a good

06:56:05.340 --> 06:56:07.319
idea, although she was still having

06:56:07.319 --> 06:56:09.299
trouble forgiving the black dragons for

06:56:09.299 --> 06:56:09.959
all their lies.

06:56:10.020 --> 06:56:13.319
Mangrove and grandeur had been left in

06:56:13.319 --> 06:56:15.419
charge of everyone while they were gone.

06:56:15.479 --> 06:56:18.000
The 5 Dragonettes climbed up to stand on

06:56:18.000 --> 06:56:20.639
the ridge, surveying the stronghold below

06:56:20.639 --> 06:56:22.259
and the clouds of dragons who were

06:56:22.259 --> 06:56:23.340
already descending on it.

06:56:23.400 --> 06:56:25.139
What if they start fighting?

06:56:25.259 --> 06:56:28.380
Fate speaker asked suddenly, all these

06:56:28.380 --> 06:56:30.419
dragons from different tribes who've been

06:56:30.419 --> 06:56:31.259
at war for so long?

06:56:31.319 --> 06:56:33.299
What if something happens and they start

06:56:33.299 --> 06:56:34.200
trying to kill each other?

06:56:34.319 --> 06:56:37.200
Sunny curled her tail around her talons.

06:56:37.259 --> 06:56:39.599
What an awful thought that hadn't even

06:56:39.599 --> 06:56:40.200
occurred to her.

06:56:40.259 --> 06:56:43.680
It'd be a huge battle, Deathbringer

06:56:43.680 --> 06:56:43.919
said.

06:56:44.040 --> 06:56:45.840
That might end the war itself.

06:56:45.900 --> 06:56:49.560
With 100s more dead dragons, Sonny said.

06:56:49.619 --> 06:56:51.479
No, that's not all right.

06:56:51.540 --> 06:56:53.159
We'll stop them if we have to.

06:56:53.220 --> 06:56:55.860
Right, tsunami said.

06:56:55.919 --> 06:56:57.659
By asking nicely?

06:56:57.720 --> 06:56:58.259
Is that the plan?

06:56:58.380 --> 06:57:01.619
You'd be surprised how effective asking

06:57:01.619 --> 06:57:03.479
nicely can be, Sonny said.

06:57:03.540 --> 06:57:05.759
Maybe if you ever tried it, you'd know.

06:57:05.819 --> 06:57:10.020
Yeah, Glory said with a grin, and tsunami

06:57:10.020 --> 06:57:10.919
glared at both of them.

06:57:10.979 --> 06:57:13.799
Well, let's get down there before

06:57:13.799 --> 06:57:16.080
anything happens, Clay suggested.

06:57:16.139 --> 06:57:19.979
Before we go, Sonny said, turning to her

06:57:19.979 --> 06:57:23.040
friends, I just, I just want you guys to

06:57:23.040 --> 06:57:23.759
know that I love you.

06:57:23.819 --> 06:57:26.040
And I don't regret anything that's

06:57:26.040 --> 06:57:26.340
happened.

06:57:26.400 --> 06:57:29.580
I'm not mad about the fake prophecy, or

06:57:29.580 --> 06:57:32.220
the talons stealing us, because without

06:57:32.220 --> 06:57:33.840
all of that, I wouldn't have grown up

06:57:33.840 --> 06:57:34.139
with you.

06:57:34.200 --> 06:57:36.060
And you're more important to me than

06:57:36.060 --> 06:57:36.360
anything.

06:57:36.479 --> 06:57:38.880
You are my brothers and sisters.

06:57:38.939 --> 06:57:40.619
You're my real family.

06:57:40.680 --> 06:57:43.740
So it was worth it, no matter what.

06:57:43.799 --> 06:57:48.180
Oh, Clay said, pulling her into his wings

06:57:48.180 --> 06:57:49.139
for a fierce hug.

06:57:49.259 --> 06:57:53.220
Uh-oh, Glory said, a mushy speech.

06:57:53.279 --> 06:57:54.959
We're all going to die, aren't we?

06:57:55.020 --> 06:57:57.240
She means she loves you too.

06:57:57.360 --> 06:58:00.419
Tsunami translated, dragging Sonny away

06:58:00.419 --> 06:58:02.099
from clay so she could hug her as well.

06:58:02.159 --> 06:58:05.099
And so do I. Me too.

06:58:05.159 --> 06:58:08.220
Starflight said quietly, and they all

06:58:08.220 --> 06:58:09.900
wrapped their wings around him together.

06:58:09.959 --> 06:58:12.779
Sonny felt the sinewy curve of his

06:58:12.779 --> 06:58:15.119
shoulder pressing against her snout, and

06:58:15.119 --> 06:58:16.919
smelled the herbs in the bandage on his

06:58:16.919 --> 06:58:17.159
eyes.

06:58:17.220 --> 06:58:19.319
Horse Starflight.

06:58:19.380 --> 06:58:21.779
Is that enough of an answer for him?

06:58:21.840 --> 06:58:23.159
I do love him.

06:58:23.220 --> 06:58:25.680
But, like a brother.

06:58:25.740 --> 06:58:27.479
I wish I felt more.

06:58:27.599 --> 06:58:30.299
There wasn't time to say anything else.

06:58:30.360 --> 06:58:32.099
It was almost midnight.

06:58:32.159 --> 06:58:35.099
They leaped into the sky, soaring down

06:58:35.099 --> 06:58:36.959
toward the stronghold with the rain wings

06:58:36.959 --> 06:58:38.459
and night wings streaming out behind

06:58:38.459 --> 06:58:38.700
them.

06:58:38.759 --> 06:58:42.779
From above, as they approached, Sonny

06:58:42.779 --> 06:58:44.099
could see that the courtyard looked

06:58:44.099 --> 06:58:45.180
deserted.

06:58:45.240 --> 06:58:48.119
The monument to Queen Oasis was a tower

06:58:48.119 --> 06:58:50.819
of darkness, rejecting the moonlight, and

06:58:50.819 --> 06:58:52.860
casting a long shadow across the sand

06:58:52.860 --> 06:58:53.759
circle around it.

06:58:53.819 --> 06:58:56.400
The soldiers' barracks were empty.

06:58:56.459 --> 06:58:59.459
The flat white stones stretched blankly

06:58:59.459 --> 06:59:01.860
glowing, as if they were made of the same

06:59:01.860 --> 06:59:03.119
stuff as the weird moon.

06:59:03.180 --> 06:59:06.180
Fire flickered from torches that studded

06:59:06.180 --> 06:59:08.220
the courtyard like claws.

06:59:08.279 --> 06:59:09.599
What if they don't come?

06:59:09.659 --> 06:59:13.080
The dragons who had flown into watch, were

06:59:13.080 --> 06:59:15.540
gathered all along the walls, wing to

06:59:15.540 --> 06:59:15.900
wing.

06:59:15.959 --> 06:59:18.599
They had torn out the heads on spikes, and

06:59:18.599 --> 06:59:20.459
dropped the gruesome trophies onto the

06:59:20.459 --> 06:59:22.979
sand below, making room for the 100s of

06:59:22.979 --> 06:59:23.880
spectators instead.

06:59:23.939 --> 06:59:27.000
It was hard to tell which tribe was which

06:59:27.000 --> 06:59:28.200
in the silvery moonlight.

06:59:28.259 --> 06:59:30.599
All the dragons seem to have scales of

06:59:30.599 --> 06:59:31.979
silver and black and gray.

06:59:32.040 --> 06:59:34.680
But Sonny was pretty sure she spotted sea

06:59:34.680 --> 06:59:37.139
wings sitting next to mud wings, ice

06:59:37.139 --> 06:59:40.020
wings beside sky wings, sand wings and

06:59:40.020 --> 06:59:42.599
night wings and rain wings, barely a few

06:59:42.599 --> 06:59:43.619
claws from one another.

06:59:43.680 --> 06:59:46.200
That's what I really want.

06:59:46.259 --> 06:59:47.279
Sonny thought.

06:59:47.340 --> 06:59:50.040
A pyrea where all dragons can see that

06:59:50.040 --> 06:59:52.380
we're basically the same, no matter what

06:59:52.380 --> 06:59:55.080
kinds of natural weapons we hatch with, or

06:59:55.080 --> 06:59:56.580
don't hatch with for some of us.

06:59:56.639 --> 06:59:59.340
A pyrea where it doesn't matter what

06:59:59.340 --> 07:00:01.380
tribe you're from, because you can have

07:00:01.380 --> 07:00:03.540
friends from any tribe, like us.

07:00:03.599 --> 07:00:07.200
As her gays scanned the walls, she

07:00:07.200 --> 07:00:09.900
spotted familiar sandwing scales, and her

07:00:09.900 --> 07:00:11.099
heart squeezed happily.

07:00:11.159 --> 07:00:14.400
Thorn was here, along with 6 claws and

07:00:14.400 --> 07:00:16.979
Kibley, and no doubt more out claws.

07:00:16.979 --> 07:00:19.020
Even if everything went horribly wrong

07:00:19.020 --> 07:00:22.259
Sonny had this strange, warm feeling that

07:00:22.259 --> 07:00:24.060
her mother would care about her and want

07:00:24.060 --> 07:00:26.400
to know her, whether or not she saved the

07:00:26.400 --> 07:00:26.639
world.

07:00:26.700 --> 07:00:29.639
Sonny was surprised to find herself

07:00:29.639 --> 07:00:32.099
thinking, maybe that's better than a

07:00:32.099 --> 07:00:33.840
prophecy and a great destiny.

07:00:33.900 --> 07:00:36.659
But I do still have to save the world.

07:00:36.720 --> 07:00:38.279
Right now, in fact.

07:00:38.400 --> 07:00:41.819
She was on one side of Starflight, with

07:00:41.819 --> 07:00:43.020
fate speaker on the other.

07:00:43.080 --> 07:00:45.779
They guided him down to the sand, and

07:00:45.779 --> 07:00:47.819
Sunny heard fate speaker describing the

07:00:47.819 --> 07:00:48.779
scene for him in a whisper.

07:00:48.840 --> 07:00:51.959
Clay thumped down next to her, and

07:00:51.959 --> 07:00:53.580
sneezed as sand went up his nose.

07:00:53.700 --> 07:00:56.639
Tsunami and glory arrived without

07:00:56.639 --> 07:00:58.919
Deathbringer, who had been sent to the

07:00:58.919 --> 07:01:00.599
walls along with the dragons they had

07:01:00.599 --> 07:01:01.080
brought with them.

07:01:01.139 --> 07:01:03.479
Sonny was a little surprised that

07:01:03.479 --> 07:01:04.919
Deathbringer had agreed to be that far

07:01:04.919 --> 07:01:07.380
away from glory, but she glanced at the

07:01:07.380 --> 07:01:09.479
determined look on Glory's face and

07:01:09.479 --> 07:01:11.099
figured she wouldn't have argued with

07:01:11.099 --> 07:01:11.340
that either.

07:01:11.459 --> 07:01:15.180
Glory herself was disguised as a sky wing

07:01:15.180 --> 07:01:17.580
red and gold scales rippling along her

07:01:17.580 --> 07:01:17.939
wings.

07:01:18.000 --> 07:01:19.919
Ironic, right?

07:01:19.979 --> 07:01:22.740
she'd said, lashing her crimson tail.

07:01:22.799 --> 07:01:25.080
Now at least I look like I belong in the

07:01:25.080 --> 07:01:25.560
prophecy.

07:01:25.619 --> 07:01:28.380
And judging by the murmurs coming from

07:01:28.380 --> 07:01:30.479
above them, the audience was thinking the

07:01:30.479 --> 07:01:30.779
same thing.

07:01:30.840 --> 07:01:35.099
The 5 dragonettes, Sonny thought, as

07:01:35.099 --> 07:01:36.299
Marosir foretold.

07:01:36.360 --> 07:01:37.500
Here we are.

07:01:37.560 --> 07:01:39.599
Prophecy or no prophecy.

07:01:39.659 --> 07:01:43.500
Now, where are the queens who blister and

07:01:43.500 --> 07:01:44.400
blaze and burn?

07:01:44.459 --> 07:01:47.520
A rumbling growl came from the dark

07:01:47.520 --> 07:01:50.819
entrance to the old palace, and Bern

07:01:50.819 --> 07:01:52.319
stepped out into the moonlight.

07:01:52.439 --> 07:01:57.180
Chapter 25.

07:01:57.360 --> 07:02:01.080
Three moons, sunny thought.

07:02:01.139 --> 07:02:02.939
She's even bigger than I remembered.

07:02:03.060 --> 07:02:06.900
Burn was a massive, heavy dragon, with

07:02:06.900 --> 07:02:09.180
jagged scars all over her pale yellow

07:02:09.180 --> 07:02:11.939
scales, including a particularly vicious

07:02:11.939 --> 07:02:13.860
one all along her side under her left

07:02:13.860 --> 07:02:14.279
wing.

07:02:14.340 --> 07:02:17.099
A more recent wound was slashed across

07:02:17.099 --> 07:02:20.400
her snout, oozing olive green pus and

07:02:20.400 --> 07:02:20.819
dark blood.

07:02:20.880 --> 07:02:23.939
Her black eyes glittered, and her stained

07:02:23.939 --> 07:02:25.979
claws gleamed with what looked like fresh

07:02:25.979 --> 07:02:28.439
blood as she slithered across the stones

07:02:28.439 --> 07:02:28.979
toward them.

07:02:29.040 --> 07:02:32.340
So, you came.

07:02:32.400 --> 07:02:33.779
She hissed.

07:02:33.900 --> 07:02:36.240
I thought the rumors couldn't possibly be

07:02:36.240 --> 07:02:36.479
true.

07:02:36.540 --> 07:02:40.020
She cast a seething look up at the 100s

07:02:40.020 --> 07:02:40.919
of watching dragons.

07:02:40.979 --> 07:02:43.560
I hope you have a good reason for

07:02:43.560 --> 07:02:45.299
disrupting my battle plans.

07:02:45.360 --> 07:02:49.919
This war is over, Sonny said, as loud as

07:02:49.919 --> 07:02:50.459
she could.

07:02:50.520 --> 07:02:52.680
There was a ripple of whispers along the

07:02:52.680 --> 07:02:54.900
walls as her words were passed along.

07:02:54.959 --> 07:02:59.220
Really, said Bern, because you say so.

07:02:59.279 --> 07:03:00.119
Is that it?

07:03:00.180 --> 07:03:03.900
Because we all say so, tsunami retorted.

07:03:03.959 --> 07:03:06.119
She flared her wings to include all the

07:03:06.119 --> 07:03:07.500
dragons above and around them.

07:03:07.560 --> 07:03:09.180
Interesting.

07:03:09.299 --> 07:03:12.299
Said Bern, but I see a problem.

07:03:12.360 --> 07:03:15.959
In fact, I see 2 problems, flying this

07:03:15.959 --> 07:03:16.680
way right now.

07:03:16.799 --> 07:03:20.819
Sunny World, and saw a massive dragons

07:03:20.819 --> 07:03:21.779
arriving from the east.

07:03:21.840 --> 07:03:24.959
Blister and her forces, she thought

07:03:24.959 --> 07:03:25.500
hopefully.

07:03:25.560 --> 07:03:27.900
She looked north and spotted flashing

07:03:27.900 --> 07:03:28.919
silver scales.

07:03:28.979 --> 07:03:31.319
Please let that be blaze with the ice

07:03:31.319 --> 07:03:31.740
wings.

07:03:31.799 --> 07:03:33.900
It's possible.

07:03:33.959 --> 07:03:36.720
I won't kill you, Burns said.

07:03:36.779 --> 07:03:39.360
After all, you've brought me my sisters

07:03:39.360 --> 07:03:41.459
to kill, which is more help than any

07:03:41.459 --> 07:03:42.599
other dragons have been.

07:03:42.659 --> 07:03:45.900
Then again, you're very annoying.

07:03:45.959 --> 07:03:49.619
This is not about killing, Sonny said.

07:03:49.680 --> 07:03:52.020
The sounds of wing beats we're getting

07:03:52.020 --> 07:03:54.479
closer, so she turned to watch blister

07:03:54.479 --> 07:03:56.819
land next to the Queen Oasis Monument.

07:03:56.880 --> 07:03:59.759
Blister sank her talons into the sand for

07:03:59.759 --> 07:04:01.979
a moment, shooting a deadly look up at

07:04:01.979 --> 07:04:02.700
the obelisk.

07:04:02.759 --> 07:04:05.459
Blaze and Queen Glacier landed a moment

07:04:05.459 --> 07:04:07.740
later, off to Seni's left.

07:04:07.799 --> 07:04:10.439
Blaise eyed her sisters nervously, stand

07:04:10.439 --> 07:04:12.060
close to the ice wing's side.

07:04:12.180 --> 07:04:15.540
Blisters slithered out of the sand and

07:04:15.540 --> 07:04:18.299
paced slowly between sunny and clay, her

07:04:18.299 --> 07:04:21.060
snake like gaze pinned on Byrne as she

07:04:21.060 --> 07:04:22.139
circled her older sister.

07:04:22.200 --> 07:04:27.060
You're still alive, Blister remarked. in

07:04:27.060 --> 07:04:30.000
a cold, calm voice, that's a pity.

07:04:30.060 --> 07:04:32.819
She paused and narrowed her eyes at the

07:04:32.819 --> 07:04:33.540
dragonettes.

07:04:33.599 --> 07:04:36.119
I was hoping you'd have my sisters dead

07:04:36.119 --> 07:04:36.959
before I got here.

07:04:37.020 --> 07:04:38.759
What?

07:04:38.819 --> 07:04:39.900
Burn snarled.

07:04:39.959 --> 07:04:42.479
They've chosen me as queen, not you.

07:04:42.540 --> 07:04:44.220
No way.

07:04:44.279 --> 07:04:47.159
Blaise cried, then hurriedly backed into

07:04:47.159 --> 07:04:48.779
Glacier as her sisters whipped their

07:04:48.779 --> 07:04:49.979
heads toward her.

07:04:50.040 --> 07:04:50.819
They picked me.

07:04:50.880 --> 07:04:52.200
They told me to come here.

07:04:52.259 --> 07:04:55.919
We haven't chosen any of you, Sonny said

07:04:55.919 --> 07:04:58.200
firmly, and we're definitely not killing

07:04:58.200 --> 07:04:58.799
any of you.

07:04:58.860 --> 07:05:00.779
Unless we have to.

07:05:00.840 --> 07:05:02.279
Glory observed.

07:05:02.340 --> 07:05:04.259
Feel free to provoke us.

07:05:04.319 --> 07:05:07.560
Shh, Clay said, nudging her.

07:05:07.619 --> 07:05:10.979
We are here to find a peaceful solution

07:05:10.979 --> 07:05:12.840
Sonny announced.

07:05:13.020 --> 07:05:15.720
Either you 3 decide among you, peacefully

07:05:15.720 --> 07:05:18.240
who's going to be queen, or everyone else

07:05:18.240 --> 07:05:19.439
here will decide for you?

07:05:19.500 --> 07:05:23.040
No more armies, no more dead dragons.

07:05:23.099 --> 07:05:26.279
Burn barked, a harsh, disbelieving

07:05:26.279 --> 07:05:26.580
laugh.

07:05:26.639 --> 07:05:30.180
I have a better idea, she snarled.

07:05:30.240 --> 07:05:33.540
First, I kill my sisters, and then I kill

07:05:33.540 --> 07:05:36.240
all of you, and then I stuff you, and

07:05:36.240 --> 07:05:38.040
spend the next 100 years telling your

07:05:38.040 --> 07:05:40.439
dead face about peaceful solutions.

07:05:40.560 --> 07:05:43.740
Out of the corner of her eye.

07:05:43.799 --> 07:05:45.540
Sonny saw a flurry of movement from the

07:05:45.540 --> 07:05:47.040
part of the wall where Thorn was

07:05:47.040 --> 07:05:47.580
perched.

07:05:47.639 --> 07:05:51.000
No one is going to let you do that, she

07:05:51.000 --> 07:05:53.040
said to Burne, trying to sound much

07:05:53.040 --> 07:05:54.060
braver than she felt.

07:05:54.119 --> 07:05:58.200
In fact, Blister interjected suddenly.

07:05:58.259 --> 07:06:00.659
I've already made a gesture of peace.

07:06:00.720 --> 07:06:03.540
Didn't you get my present, burn?

07:06:03.659 --> 07:06:06.959
An eerie silence fell for a moment. as

07:06:06.959 --> 07:06:08.040
Burns stared down at her.

07:06:08.159 --> 07:06:11.159
I was thinking.

07:06:11.279 --> 07:06:13.680
Blister hissed into the stillness.

07:06:13.740 --> 07:06:16.380
But this war has gone on too long.

07:06:16.439 --> 07:06:20.040
I thought if I sent you a gift, something

07:06:20.040 --> 07:06:22.319
I know you've always wanted.

07:06:22.439 --> 07:06:27.000
That perhaps we could mend fences and

07:06:27.000 --> 07:06:28.080
reunite the family.

07:06:28.139 --> 07:06:30.779
She bared her teeth at the palace

07:06:30.779 --> 07:06:33.479
entrance, and Sunny spotted smoldered

07:06:33.479 --> 07:06:35.880
just inside the doorway, where she'd 1st

07:06:35.880 --> 07:06:36.299
seen him.

07:06:36.360 --> 07:06:38.279
Aha!

07:06:38.340 --> 07:06:39.779
Burn snarled.

07:06:39.840 --> 07:06:41.400
That was from you.

07:06:41.520 --> 07:06:43.799
Smolder, bring me the box.

07:06:43.860 --> 07:06:48.540
Now, he said, don't argue with me.

07:06:48.599 --> 07:06:51.240
She growled, and he vanished into the

07:06:51.240 --> 07:06:51.659
palace.

07:06:51.720 --> 07:06:53.220
A gift?

07:06:53.279 --> 07:06:54.900
A gesture of peace?

07:06:54.959 --> 07:06:56.819
Reuniting the family?

07:06:56.880 --> 07:06:59.220
That doesn't sound like blister.

07:06:59.279 --> 07:07:01.919
Sonny flicked her tail anxiously.

07:07:01.979 --> 07:07:04.500
Or is she really willing to stand down

07:07:04.500 --> 07:07:05.759
and let burn be queen?

07:07:05.819 --> 07:07:08.880
Smolder returned a few moments later

07:07:08.880 --> 07:07:11.279
carrying the box that Sonny had seen on

07:07:11.279 --> 07:07:13.619
the top floor of the Weirdling Tower when

07:07:13.619 --> 07:07:14.639
she'd been chained up there.

07:07:14.700 --> 07:07:17.580
As he set it down in front of Bern, it

07:07:17.580 --> 07:07:19.139
let out a malevolent hiss.

07:07:19.200 --> 07:07:23.040
Bern, be careful, Sonny said.

07:07:23.159 --> 07:07:25.259
She had a horrible sinking feeling in her

07:07:25.259 --> 07:07:27.419
chest, and she really didn't like the

07:07:27.419 --> 07:07:28.560
look on Blister's face.

07:07:28.619 --> 07:07:31.500
I, I think this might be a trick.

07:07:31.560 --> 07:07:35.880
Of course it is, Burns said, especially

07:07:35.880 --> 07:07:38.040
if it's from my clever little sister.

07:07:38.099 --> 07:07:41.220
Sending me a present, thinking I'll open

07:07:41.220 --> 07:07:43.860
it without any suspicion, as if I don't

07:07:43.860 --> 07:07:46.439
recognize the hiss of the dragon bite

07:07:46.439 --> 07:07:47.340
viper when I hear it.

07:07:47.400 --> 07:07:49.380
It's not a trick.

07:07:49.439 --> 07:07:51.419
Blister said coolly.

07:07:51.479 --> 07:07:53.939
I know you've always wanted one for your

07:07:53.939 --> 07:07:54.540
collection.

07:07:54.599 --> 07:07:56.639
Dragon Bite Viper?

07:07:56.700 --> 07:07:59.159
Fate speaker whispered to Starflight.

07:07:59.220 --> 07:08:02.459
Rare and deadly, he whispered back.

07:08:02.520 --> 07:08:05.279
The only snake in Pyria, that can kill a

07:08:05.279 --> 07:08:06.360
dragon with one bite.

07:08:06.419 --> 07:08:09.240
He shifted nervously on his talons.

07:08:09.240 --> 07:08:12.180
If that's really what's in there, I hope

07:08:12.180 --> 07:08:13.619
that's not really what's in there.

07:08:13.680 --> 07:08:16.319
Well, the trick's on you.

07:08:16.380 --> 07:08:17.880
Burns said.

07:08:17.939 --> 07:08:20.580
She sank her claws into the top of the

07:08:20.580 --> 07:08:22.619
box and ripped it off with a vicious

07:08:22.619 --> 07:08:25.619
tearing sound, fast as lightning, her

07:08:25.619 --> 07:08:28.139
talons shot into the box, and lifted out

07:08:28.139 --> 07:08:30.659
a writhing, hissing rope of scaly fury.

07:08:30.720 --> 07:08:34.080
The snake's head was pinned between burns

07:08:34.080 --> 07:08:35.759
claws, so it couldn't bite her.

07:08:35.819 --> 07:08:38.459
Its whole body wriggled and lashed, like

07:08:38.459 --> 07:08:40.380
the eels attacking in the sea wing

07:08:40.380 --> 07:08:40.680
prison.

07:08:40.740 --> 07:08:44.220
I know your sick, twisted mind.

07:08:44.279 --> 07:08:45.720
You thought this would kill me.

07:08:45.840 --> 07:08:48.000
Burn snarled at blister.

07:08:48.060 --> 07:08:51.180
So it'll be very poetic when it kills you

07:08:51.180 --> 07:08:52.020
instead.

07:08:52.080 --> 07:08:54.959
She took a step toward her sister, and

07:08:54.959 --> 07:08:56.700
then stopped suddenly, looking down.

07:08:56.759 --> 07:08:59.580
Oh, Blister said.

07:08:59.639 --> 07:09:00.900
I got you too.

07:09:00.959 --> 07:09:02.580
Did I leave out that part?

07:09:02.639 --> 07:09:06.840
A 2nd dragon bite viper lunged out of the

07:09:06.840 --> 07:09:09.540
box and sank its teeth into Burns ankle.

07:09:09.599 --> 07:09:12.540
Its venomous fangs slid like shards of

07:09:12.540 --> 07:09:14.220
ice right between her scales.

07:09:14.279 --> 07:09:17.220
The screaming seemed to come from

07:09:17.220 --> 07:09:18.240
everywhere at once.

07:09:18.299 --> 07:09:20.939
Blaze was probably screaming the loudest

07:09:20.939 --> 07:09:23.580
shrieking and flapping her wings as if

07:09:23.580 --> 07:09:25.680
she were the one who'd been bitten, all

07:09:25.680 --> 07:09:26.639
along the walls.

07:09:26.700 --> 07:09:28.979
Dragons were pushing and yelling and

07:09:28.979 --> 07:09:30.840
leaning in to get a better look, or

07:09:30.840 --> 07:09:32.639
taking off into the sky to get as far

07:09:32.639 --> 07:09:34.200
away from the snakes as possible.

07:09:34.259 --> 07:09:37.380
Burn stamped one foot down on the 2nd

07:09:37.380 --> 07:09:39.840
snake, crushing it, but it was too late.

07:09:39.900 --> 07:09:43.080
Black veins were shooting up her leg and

07:09:43.080 --> 07:09:44.159
spreading through her scales.

07:09:44.279 --> 07:09:46.500
What's happening?

07:09:46.560 --> 07:09:49.319
Starfight asked, reaching out for Sonny.

07:09:49.380 --> 07:09:51.419
Sonny touched his wing with her own.

07:09:51.479 --> 07:09:55.139
There was a 2nd snake in the box, and it

07:09:55.139 --> 07:09:55.860
bit burn.

07:09:55.919 --> 07:09:59.639
This was Blister's plan, the one I

07:09:59.639 --> 07:10:01.080
overheard her talking about in the

07:10:01.080 --> 07:10:01.380
mirror.

07:10:01.439 --> 07:10:04.860
Send burn something she really wants, and

07:10:04.860 --> 07:10:06.119
figure out a way for it to kill her.

07:10:06.180 --> 07:10:09.479
Clever and evil and sinister.

07:10:09.599 --> 07:10:12.779
She looked over at blister, who was

07:10:12.779 --> 07:10:14.939
watching her sister's death throes with

07:10:14.939 --> 07:10:17.220
an enthralled, smug smile on her face.

07:10:17.279 --> 07:10:20.340
We can't let her be queen.

07:10:20.400 --> 07:10:23.040
All of Pyria would be in danger if

07:10:23.040 --> 07:10:24.180
blister were queen.

07:10:24.240 --> 07:10:25.979
But what else can we do?

07:10:26.040 --> 07:10:28.619
She's not going to accept Blaze on the

07:10:28.619 --> 07:10:29.279
throne instead.

07:10:29.340 --> 07:10:31.919
And it looks like this is the end for

07:10:31.919 --> 07:10:32.340
burn.

07:10:32.459 --> 07:10:36.119
Burn let out a furious roar, and

07:10:36.119 --> 07:10:37.979
collapsed to the ground with a crash that

07:10:37.979 --> 07:10:38.520
shook the earth.

07:10:38.639 --> 07:10:41.340
Her wings twitched and convulsed as if

07:10:41.340 --> 07:10:42.119
they were possessed.

07:10:42.180 --> 07:10:44.580
She clawed at the air, reaching for

07:10:44.580 --> 07:10:45.000
blister.

07:10:45.060 --> 07:10:48.659
I'll kill you, she snarled.

07:10:48.720 --> 07:10:50.099
I'll claw that.

07:10:50.159 --> 07:10:51.720
I'll, it hurts.

07:10:51.840 --> 07:10:52.860
Stop it.

07:10:52.919 --> 07:10:53.759
Stop the.

07:10:54.720 --> 07:10:57.060
She roared again, howling her agony at

07:10:57.060 --> 07:10:57.419
the sky.

07:10:57.479 --> 07:11:01.319
Her ankle was entirely black now, the

07:11:01.319 --> 07:11:03.119
claws curling in and shriveling.

07:11:03.180 --> 07:11:06.299
The venom marched up toward her heart

07:11:06.299 --> 07:11:07.439
fast and unstoppable.

07:11:07.560 --> 07:11:09.900
Is there anything we can do?

07:11:09.959 --> 07:11:11.099
Sonny asked.

07:11:11.159 --> 07:11:12.720
Clay, Starflight.

07:11:12.840 --> 07:11:15.180
Starflight shook his head mutely.

07:11:15.240 --> 07:11:18.540
Burn rolled onto her back, wheezing as

07:11:18.540 --> 07:11:20.759
the black tendrils looped together in the

07:11:20.759 --> 07:11:21.779
center of her chest.

07:11:21.840 --> 07:11:23.520
Her arm flopped to the ground.

07:11:23.580 --> 07:11:26.520
Her talons opened, and the 1st snake

07:11:26.520 --> 07:11:28.500
slithered loose onto the stones of the

07:11:28.500 --> 07:11:29.099
courtyard.

07:11:29.099 --> 07:11:31.020
The Viper?

07:11:31.080 --> 07:11:32.459
Blaise shrieked.

07:11:32.520 --> 07:11:33.419
It's going to kill us.

07:11:33.540 --> 07:11:37.080
Pandemonium erupted along the walls.

07:11:37.200 --> 07:11:40.259
Fly, screamed several dragons.

07:11:40.319 --> 07:11:43.080
Kill it, roared others, or it will kill

07:11:43.080 --> 07:11:43.439
us all.

07:11:43.560 --> 07:11:46.919
Blister was in the air already, hovering

07:11:46.919 --> 07:11:49.200
over them and watching gleefully as the

07:11:49.200 --> 07:11:51.299
snake shot toward the dragonettes.

07:11:51.360 --> 07:11:54.060
It moved like lightning, zigzagging

07:11:54.060 --> 07:11:56.220
across the stones faster than flight.

07:11:56.279 --> 07:11:57.840
Up, up, up.

07:11:57.900 --> 07:12:00.419
Tsunami shouted, shoving at her friends.

07:12:00.479 --> 07:12:02.220
Starflight.

07:12:02.279 --> 07:12:04.080
Fate speaker screamed.

07:12:04.139 --> 07:12:07.560
Sunny whirled, and saw Starflight stumble

07:12:07.560 --> 07:12:10.380
forward, his wings unfolding, but slowly

07:12:10.380 --> 07:12:13.439
too slowly, his talons reached out, trying

07:12:13.439 --> 07:12:14.459
to orient himself.

07:12:14.520 --> 07:12:16.439
The snake was nearly at his feet

07:12:16.439 --> 07:12:16.799
already.

07:12:16.860 --> 07:12:20.159
Sunny and fate speaker reached him at the

07:12:20.159 --> 07:12:22.740
same time, grabbing his forearms, and

07:12:22.740 --> 07:12:24.900
trying to lift him bodily into the sky

07:12:24.900 --> 07:12:27.779
but they were both small, and Starflight

07:12:27.779 --> 07:12:30.060
was heavy and confused and unwieldy.

07:12:30.119 --> 07:12:33.240
His tail thwacked the ground, and his

07:12:33.240 --> 07:12:35.880
wings nearly overbalanced them all as

07:12:35.880 --> 07:12:37.259
they tried to struggle into the air.

07:12:37.380 --> 07:12:41.040
The viper hissed, and it sounded as if it

07:12:41.040 --> 07:12:43.200
was coming from inside Sunny's skull.

07:12:43.259 --> 07:12:46.619
It's going to get one of us, Sonny

07:12:46.619 --> 07:12:48.299
realized, with a jolt of horror.

07:12:48.360 --> 07:12:49.979
Let it be me.

07:12:50.040 --> 07:12:51.419
Please don't let Starflight die.

07:12:51.479 --> 07:12:54.659
And then something hit her, like a

07:12:54.659 --> 07:12:56.099
boulder slamming into all of them.

07:12:56.159 --> 07:12:59.099
Sunny, fate speaker, and Starflight

07:12:59.099 --> 07:13:01.860
tumbled backward, a tangle of wings and

07:13:01.860 --> 07:13:04.020
tails catapulted across the courtyard.

07:13:04.080 --> 07:13:06.959
Sonny was flung loose from the others and

07:13:06.959 --> 07:13:09.479
skidded across the sand, crashing finally

07:13:09.479 --> 07:13:11.459
into the queen oasis obelisk.

07:13:11.520 --> 07:13:14.639
She shoved herself back up, dizzy and

07:13:14.639 --> 07:13:15.360
disoriented.

07:13:15.419 --> 07:13:16.860
What had happened?

07:13:16.919 --> 07:13:17.880
Had someone pushed them?

07:13:17.939 --> 07:13:19.680
Did the snake bite anyone?

07:13:19.740 --> 07:13:21.240
Was Starflight all right?

07:13:21.299 --> 07:13:23.700
Her head took a moment to clear.

07:13:23.759 --> 07:13:26.400
And then she realized there was a dragon

07:13:26.400 --> 07:13:28.740
lying on the stones, where she'd been

07:13:28.740 --> 07:13:29.759
standing a moment before.

07:13:29.880 --> 07:13:32.939
The dragon who'd slammed into them, the

07:13:32.939 --> 07:13:34.439
dragon who'd saved their lives.

07:13:34.560 --> 07:13:36.659
It was clay.

07:13:36.720 --> 07:13:41.099
Chapter 26.

07:13:41.340 --> 07:13:44.880
No, Sonny screamed.

07:13:44.939 --> 07:13:46.799
Sonny, stay back.

07:13:46.860 --> 07:13:48.900
The viper's still alive.

07:13:48.959 --> 07:13:51.299
Deathbringer yelled from overhead.

07:13:51.360 --> 07:13:54.060
She realized that he was holding glory in

07:13:54.060 --> 07:13:56.279
the air, and the rain wing queen was

07:13:56.279 --> 07:13:56.939
fighting to get away.

07:13:57.000 --> 07:14:00.540
But no one was holding her back, and she

07:14:00.540 --> 07:14:01.500
didn't care about the snake.

07:14:01.560 --> 07:14:03.540
She didn't care if she did get bitten.

07:14:03.599 --> 07:14:05.819
She wasn't going to leave clay lying

07:14:05.819 --> 07:14:06.840
there, dying.

07:14:06.900 --> 07:14:09.779
She scrambled across the courtyard and

07:14:09.779 --> 07:14:11.759
threw her wings over him, shaking him

07:14:11.759 --> 07:14:12.479
with her talons.

07:14:12.540 --> 07:14:15.240
Clay, she yelled, clay.

07:14:15.299 --> 07:14:18.360
He looked dazed, but his eyes were open.

07:14:18.419 --> 07:14:19.979
Maybe the snake had missed him.

07:14:20.040 --> 07:14:22.139
She couldn't see it anywhere.

07:14:22.200 --> 07:14:22.439
Maybe.

07:14:22.619 --> 07:14:26.459
Oh, Clay said, trying to sit up.

07:14:26.520 --> 07:14:28.319
Ow, I...

07:14:28.319 --> 07:14:29.880
My leg.

07:14:29.939 --> 07:14:32.520
Wow, that really hurts.

07:14:32.639 --> 07:14:35.580
He pressed his claws to his head and

07:14:35.580 --> 07:14:37.439
looked as if he might pass out.

07:14:37.560 --> 07:14:39.599
And then Sonny saw the wound.

07:14:39.659 --> 07:14:42.540
The fang marks in the flesh of clay's

07:14:42.540 --> 07:14:45.659
right thigh, a black starburst had

07:14:45.659 --> 07:14:47.459
already appeared around the 2 holes

07:14:47.459 --> 07:14:50.099
pulsing bigger and bigger across his warm

07:14:50.099 --> 07:14:51.060
brown scales.

07:14:51.119 --> 07:14:52.979
Clay?

07:14:53.040 --> 07:14:54.540
Sonny started to cry.

07:14:54.599 --> 07:14:55.799
Please don't die.

07:14:55.860 --> 07:15:02.040
I'm, I'm, uh, open to suggestions, he

07:15:02.040 --> 07:15:04.380
said, with a small, breathless laugh.

07:15:04.439 --> 07:15:07.020
He reached toward his leg, then flinched

07:15:07.020 --> 07:15:08.759
back, gritting his teeth in pain.

07:15:08.819 --> 07:15:12.299
Tsunami thumped down on his other side

07:15:12.299 --> 07:15:14.220
and let out a gasp at the side of the

07:15:14.220 --> 07:15:14.819
snake bite.

07:15:14.880 --> 07:15:16.740
She twisted to look at the courtyard

07:15:16.740 --> 07:15:17.099
around them.

07:15:17.220 --> 07:15:18.779
Where's the snake?

07:15:18.779 --> 07:15:19.560
she said.

07:15:19.619 --> 07:15:20.400
Where did it go?

07:15:20.459 --> 07:15:23.279
I don't know, Sonny said.

07:15:23.340 --> 07:15:25.380
She could barely see through her tears.

07:15:25.439 --> 07:15:28.319
She leaned against clay, trying to send

07:15:28.319 --> 07:15:30.540
all the warmth from her scales into him.

07:15:30.599 --> 07:15:33.479
Hey, it's all right.

07:15:33.540 --> 07:15:36.419
Clay said, although his claws were

07:15:36.419 --> 07:15:38.400
clenched, and his wings were starting to

07:15:38.400 --> 07:15:38.939
shudder.

07:15:39.000 --> 07:15:41.819
It's not such a bad destiny, sonny.

07:15:41.880 --> 07:15:45.060
I'd die to save you and Starflight over

07:15:45.060 --> 07:15:46.619
and over if I had to.

07:15:46.680 --> 07:15:49.259
His voice caught on the last few words

07:15:49.259 --> 07:15:51.240
and he stopped, breathing hard.

07:15:51.299 --> 07:15:54.000
I order you not to die.

07:15:54.060 --> 07:15:56.220
Tsunami said, grabbing his shoulder.

07:15:56.279 --> 07:15:58.380
Clay, stop.

07:15:58.439 --> 07:15:59.099
Stop it.

07:15:59.159 --> 07:16:00.540
Stop dying right now.

07:16:00.599 --> 07:16:03.180
Her normally bossy voice was full of

07:16:03.180 --> 07:16:03.599
panic.

07:16:03.659 --> 07:16:05.099
Ow!

07:16:05.159 --> 07:16:07.680
Death bringer roared from up in the sky.

07:16:07.740 --> 07:16:10.380
And a moment later, glory crash landed

07:16:10.380 --> 07:16:10.919
into Sonny.

07:16:10.979 --> 07:16:12.959
No, no, no.

07:16:13.020 --> 07:16:15.779
Glory said, looking at the growing burst

07:16:15.779 --> 07:16:16.200
of black.

07:16:16.319 --> 07:16:18.959
Her scales had turned lily green and

07:16:18.959 --> 07:16:21.840
white, the colors of fear and panic and

07:16:21.840 --> 07:16:22.139
pain.

07:16:22.200 --> 07:16:25.080
No, we have to be able to stop this.

07:16:25.139 --> 07:16:26.580
There must be something we can do.

07:16:26.639 --> 07:16:28.319
Starflight, she bellowed.

07:16:28.380 --> 07:16:30.779
Think, how do you stop a dragon bite

07:16:30.779 --> 07:16:31.560
viper's poison?

07:16:31.619 --> 07:16:34.619
The scrolls must have said something, she

07:16:34.619 --> 07:16:36.900
muttered, touching clay's scales.

07:16:36.959 --> 07:16:39.360
He winced as her claws brushed the

07:16:39.360 --> 07:16:40.200
blackened area.

07:16:40.259 --> 07:16:41.819
Why can't I remember anything?

07:16:41.880 --> 07:16:43.680
Why is it spreading so fast?

07:16:43.799 --> 07:16:47.220
Sonny looked around for the 1st time and

07:16:47.220 --> 07:16:49.560
realized that the dragons along the walls

07:16:49.560 --> 07:16:52.139
had fallen completely silent, staring at

07:16:52.139 --> 07:16:52.259
them.

07:16:52.319 --> 07:16:54.540
Blister and Blaze were watching too.

07:16:54.659 --> 07:16:57.419
One with cold interest, and the other

07:16:57.419 --> 07:16:58.020
with horror.

07:16:58.080 --> 07:17:01.380
Over by the wall, Starflight was trying

07:17:01.380 --> 07:17:03.779
to find them, stumbling forward, with his

07:17:03.779 --> 07:17:06.180
claws held out, although fate speaker was

07:17:06.180 --> 07:17:07.259
trying to drag him back.

07:17:07.319 --> 07:17:11.099
And there was something hurtling out of

07:17:11.099 --> 07:17:13.380
the sky toward them, something that

07:17:13.380 --> 07:17:17.099
blazed, fiery orange, and trailed smoke, a

07:17:17.099 --> 07:17:18.959
dragon with burning scales.

07:17:19.020 --> 07:17:20.880
Out of the way.

07:17:20.939 --> 07:17:23.759
Pearl yelled, Sonny, get everyone out of

07:17:23.759 --> 07:17:24.060
the way.

07:17:24.119 --> 07:17:28.080
Tsunami reacted first, weeping over clay

07:17:28.080 --> 07:17:30.299
to shove Sunny and Glory back.

07:17:30.360 --> 07:17:32.759
The heat from peril's scales swept over

07:17:32.759 --> 07:17:35.340
them as the sky wing hit the ground and

07:17:35.340 --> 07:17:36.419
nearly slid into clay.

07:17:36.540 --> 07:17:38.639
You can't die!

07:17:38.700 --> 07:17:40.080
Carol yelled at him.

07:17:40.139 --> 07:17:40.979
I won't let you.

07:17:41.040 --> 07:17:44.099
Don't tsunami started forward.

07:17:44.159 --> 07:17:45.000
What are you?

07:17:45.479 --> 07:17:47.759
I'm burning out the poison, peril said

07:17:47.759 --> 07:17:49.979
and she stabbed her smoldering claws

07:17:49.979 --> 07:17:51.779
straight into the center of the black

07:17:51.779 --> 07:17:53.639
starburst on Clay's leg.

07:17:53.700 --> 07:17:58.200
With a roar of crazed agony, Clay surged

07:17:58.200 --> 07:18:00.119
up as though he was trying to fly away.

07:18:00.180 --> 07:18:03.479
Tsunami, Glory, and Sonny, flung

07:18:03.479 --> 07:18:05.819
themselves at him and pinned him down, but

07:18:05.819 --> 07:18:08.220
he was bigger and stronger and fighting

07:18:08.220 --> 07:18:08.700
hard.

07:18:08.759 --> 07:18:11.459
Deathbringer, get down here.

07:18:11.520 --> 07:18:14.279
Glory yelled, and a moment later, the

07:18:14.279 --> 07:18:16.380
night wing was there, adding his weight

07:18:16.380 --> 07:18:16.799
to theirs.

07:18:16.860 --> 07:18:20.220
Sonny grabbed Clay's front talons in hers

07:18:20.220 --> 07:18:21.720
and held on for dear life.

07:18:21.779 --> 07:18:24.060
Clay, it's all right.

07:18:24.119 --> 07:18:24.720
She's helping you.

07:18:24.779 --> 07:18:27.659
But Clay was in too much pain to hear

07:18:27.659 --> 07:18:27.959
her.

07:18:28.020 --> 07:18:29.880
He jerked and thrashed.

07:18:29.939 --> 07:18:32.700
His howls digging into Sonny's heart like

07:18:32.700 --> 07:18:33.900
ice wing claws.

07:18:33.959 --> 07:18:36.900
She closed her eyes and leaned into him

07:18:36.900 --> 07:18:39.840
the awful smell of melting scales and

07:18:39.840 --> 07:18:42.419
burning flesh assailed her, as if she

07:18:42.419 --> 07:18:44.220
were burying her snout in the night wing

07:18:44.220 --> 07:18:44.639
volcano.

07:18:44.700 --> 07:18:48.360
She felt more dragons join them, holding

07:18:48.360 --> 07:18:50.700
down Clay's wings and keeping his claws

07:18:50.700 --> 07:18:51.479
away from peril.

07:18:51.540 --> 07:18:53.220
When she opened her eyes again.

07:18:53.279 --> 07:18:56.459
It was who she expected, Riptide, and

07:18:56.459 --> 07:18:59.159
Starflight, and also who she didn't.

07:18:59.220 --> 07:19:02.639
Thorn, clasping Sonny and Clay's talents

07:19:02.639 --> 07:19:03.119
between her own.

07:19:03.180 --> 07:19:07.619
Mother, she whispered with relief, resting

07:19:07.619 --> 07:19:09.299
her head against the warm sand wing

07:19:09.299 --> 07:19:09.959
scales.

07:19:09.959 --> 07:19:13.500
This should have been me, Thorn said, but

07:19:13.500 --> 07:19:14.400
I couldn't get you in time.

07:19:14.459 --> 07:19:17.700
Sonny shook her head and chanced to look

07:19:17.700 --> 07:19:18.599
at Clay's leg.

07:19:18.720 --> 07:19:21.659
Carol still had her talons buried in his

07:19:21.659 --> 07:19:23.639
scales, carving out everything that had

07:19:23.639 --> 07:19:25.500
been touched by the black venom.

07:19:25.560 --> 07:19:28.139
There was a scorched, gaping, bleeding

07:19:28.139 --> 07:19:30.659
hole in clay's thigh, and Sonny had to

07:19:30.659 --> 07:19:32.099
look away quickly before she threw up.

07:19:32.159 --> 07:19:34.919
I'm not sure he can survive this.

07:19:35.040 --> 07:19:38.459
Thorn whispered gently to Sonny, that big

07:19:38.459 --> 07:19:38.939
of a burn.

07:19:39.060 --> 07:19:42.060
He can, Sonny said fiercely.

07:19:42.119 --> 07:19:44.700
Maybe no one else could, but he can.

07:19:44.759 --> 07:19:48.299
Fireproof scales, Starflight said, across

07:19:48.299 --> 07:19:48.720
from them.

07:19:48.779 --> 07:19:53.639
Oh, I hope, Thorn said, and then she

07:19:53.639 --> 07:19:55.319
spread her wing around Sonny's back and

07:19:55.319 --> 07:19:57.060
pulled her close, falling silent.

07:19:57.180 --> 07:20:00.720
A few moments later, peril said, that's

07:20:00.720 --> 07:20:01.080
all of it.

07:20:01.200 --> 07:20:04.200
In an exhausted voice, and stepped back.

07:20:04.259 --> 07:20:06.599
I think, it better be.

07:20:06.720 --> 07:20:08.700
I don't see any more venom to you?

07:20:08.759 --> 07:20:10.080
She asked Sonny.

07:20:10.139 --> 07:20:10.860
Clay?

07:20:10.919 --> 07:20:12.659
Clay, are you all right?

07:20:12.720 --> 07:20:15.000
Clay had passed out.

07:20:15.060 --> 07:20:18.240
His wings were limp and his head lulled

07:20:18.240 --> 07:20:20.099
to the side when Riptide let go of it.

07:20:20.159 --> 07:20:22.020
Is he all right?

07:20:22.080 --> 07:20:24.479
Peril said, her voice rising.

07:20:24.540 --> 07:20:25.500
Tell me it worked.

07:20:25.560 --> 07:20:28.319
It worked, Glory said.

07:20:28.380 --> 07:20:31.020
She rested her talons on Clay's chest

07:20:31.020 --> 07:20:32.759
which was rising and falling evenly.

07:20:32.819 --> 07:20:35.939
The black venom had stopped spreading.

07:20:36.000 --> 07:20:38.459
Peril had burned it all out of him.

07:20:38.520 --> 07:20:40.979
Sonny could see his fireproof scales

07:20:40.979 --> 07:20:43.860
trying to fix themselves, warm brown

07:20:43.860 --> 07:20:46.139
smoothing over the scorched spots.

07:20:46.200 --> 07:20:48.299
But the whole peril had had to gouge out

07:20:48.299 --> 07:20:50.700
of his leg, was too big for the scales to

07:20:50.700 --> 07:20:51.119
knit over.

07:20:51.180 --> 07:20:54.060
Clay was going to be scarred, and

07:20:54.060 --> 07:20:55.319
probably limping for life.

07:20:55.380 --> 07:20:57.659
But he was alive.

07:20:57.720 --> 07:21:00.180
He'd survived the snake bite.

07:21:00.240 --> 07:21:01.740
That was all that mattered.

07:21:01.799 --> 07:21:04.919
Thank you, Sonny said to peril.

07:21:05.040 --> 07:21:07.619
She automatically reached to hug Peril

07:21:07.619 --> 07:21:09.540
but the Sky Wing jumped back before they

07:21:09.540 --> 07:21:09.900
could touch.

07:21:09.959 --> 07:21:14.099
Seriously, tsunami said, rubbing her face

07:21:14.099 --> 07:21:15.360
with her talons and sitting back.

07:21:15.419 --> 07:21:17.340
You, that.

07:21:17.520 --> 07:21:18.720
I don't know what to say.

07:21:18.779 --> 07:21:21.419
Glory had her tail curled around her

07:21:21.419 --> 07:21:23.639
talons and was holding her wings in close

07:21:23.639 --> 07:21:26.700
as wave after wave of odd colors spread

07:21:26.700 --> 07:21:27.360
through her scales.

07:21:27.479 --> 07:21:30.060
Death bringer put one wing around her

07:21:30.060 --> 07:21:32.220
gently, and she let him.

07:21:32.279 --> 07:21:35.520
Maybe, Clay mumbled.

07:21:35.580 --> 07:21:37.560
And they all leaned closer to hear him.

07:21:37.619 --> 07:21:41.580
Maybe peril is the wings of fire.

07:21:41.700 --> 07:21:44.700
He lapsed back into unconsciousness.

07:21:44.759 --> 07:21:47.880
Sonny saw the nervously delighted

07:21:47.880 --> 07:21:50.340
expression on Parel's face and felt as if

07:21:50.340 --> 07:21:51.479
her heart might explode.

07:21:51.540 --> 07:21:54.119
The night wings just made that up.

07:21:54.180 --> 07:21:57.540
Wings of fire was nothing but a pretty

07:21:57.540 --> 07:21:58.380
phrase to them.

07:21:58.439 --> 07:22:01.380
But it is something, and it's more than

07:22:01.380 --> 07:22:02.939
perils burning scales.

07:22:03.000 --> 07:22:05.159
Peril helped us because clay is

07:22:05.159 --> 07:22:05.459
wonderful.

07:22:05.520 --> 07:22:08.099
He was kind to her when no one else ever

07:22:08.099 --> 07:22:10.919
was, and he believed in her, no matter

07:22:10.919 --> 07:22:11.580
what she'd done.

07:22:11.639 --> 07:22:14.759
His heart is the real wings of fire.

07:22:14.819 --> 07:22:17.520
She glanced around at her friends.

07:22:17.580 --> 07:22:21.779
Clay's heart, tsunami's courage, glory's

07:22:21.779 --> 07:22:24.180
determination, Starflights, loyalty.

07:22:24.240 --> 07:22:27.060
I think the wings of fire are inside all

07:22:27.060 --> 07:22:29.159
of us, inside every dragon.

07:22:29.220 --> 07:22:31.979
Maybe you just have to reach inside and

07:22:31.979 --> 07:22:32.340
find it.

07:22:32.459 --> 07:22:35.819
A sinister hiss interrupted her thoughts

07:22:35.819 --> 07:22:38.580
and she whirled around as a jolt of fear

07:22:38.580 --> 07:22:39.180
ran through her.

07:22:39.240 --> 07:22:42.840
The dragon bite viper was slithering up

07:22:42.840 --> 07:22:45.299
between 2 of the stones, eyeing the group

07:22:45.299 --> 07:22:48.119
of dragonettes with a dark, cold, lidless

07:22:48.119 --> 07:22:48.840
glare.

07:22:49.020 --> 07:22:51.840
Peril leaped forward and smashed her

07:22:51.840 --> 07:22:52.919
talons down on it.

07:22:52.979 --> 07:22:55.259
The snake flailed horribly for a moment

07:22:55.259 --> 07:22:57.720
and then crumpled into a shriveled, burnt

07:22:57.720 --> 07:22:58.319
out husk.

07:22:58.380 --> 07:23:02.099
Oh, well. said blister's voice behind

07:23:02.099 --> 07:23:02.340
them.

07:23:02.400 --> 07:23:05.340
That would have been convenient, killing

07:23:05.340 --> 07:23:07.680
all my enemies with one snake, so to

07:23:07.680 --> 07:23:10.619
speak, Blister flicked her tail up, and

07:23:10.619 --> 07:23:12.299
studied them for a long moment as they

07:23:12.299 --> 07:23:12.959
turned to face her.

07:23:13.020 --> 07:23:15.540
Tsunami squared her shoulders and glared

07:23:15.540 --> 07:23:18.000
back at her, talons clenched, as if she

07:23:18.000 --> 07:23:18.659
was ready to fight.

07:23:18.720 --> 07:23:21.360
But I think I'll deal with you later

07:23:21.360 --> 07:23:22.799
Blister said.

07:23:22.860 --> 07:23:25.139
Her eyes shifted toward the hordes of

07:23:25.139 --> 07:23:27.900
gathered dragons, and Sunny realized the

07:23:27.900 --> 07:23:29.340
blister wasn't sure what they would do.

07:23:29.400 --> 07:23:31.979
If blister tried to kill the prophecy

07:23:31.979 --> 07:23:33.840
dragonettes, right here in front of

07:23:33.840 --> 07:23:35.700
everybody, would they stop her?

07:23:35.759 --> 07:23:37.139
How would they all react?

07:23:37.259 --> 07:23:41.939
For now, Blister said, I'm finally just

07:23:41.939 --> 07:23:43.919
one step away from the throne that is

07:23:43.919 --> 07:23:44.819
rightfully mine.

07:23:44.880 --> 07:23:47.819
And that step, of course.

07:23:47.939 --> 07:23:51.479
She turned to her sister, Blaise, who

07:23:51.479 --> 07:23:53.520
cowered back against the ice wing queen

07:23:53.580 --> 07:23:55.619
is killing you.

07:23:55.680 --> 07:24:00.599
Chapter 27.

07:24:00.900 --> 07:24:04.619
You don't have to kill her, Sonny

07:24:04.619 --> 07:24:07.380
protested, as Blister advanced on Blaze.

07:24:07.439 --> 07:24:10.680
Perhaps, Blister said over her shoulder

07:24:10.680 --> 07:24:12.479
but I certainly want to.

07:24:12.540 --> 07:24:14.819
Can't you fight for me?

07:24:14.880 --> 07:24:17.400
Blaise pleaded, turning to Queen

07:24:17.400 --> 07:24:17.939
Glacier.

07:24:18.000 --> 07:24:19.860
I don't want to die like this.

07:24:19.919 --> 07:24:22.740
Queen Glacier looked torn.

07:24:22.799 --> 07:24:25.319
She had to know there was no chance Blaze

07:24:25.319 --> 07:24:27.180
would survive this duel, which meant

07:24:27.180 --> 07:24:29.340
she'd get none of the promised territory

07:24:29.340 --> 07:24:30.180
for the ice wings.

07:24:30.240 --> 07:24:32.580
And she'd be left with a bordering

07:24:32.580 --> 07:24:34.919
kingdom, ruled by a queen who'd been her

07:24:34.919 --> 07:24:36.540
enemy for 18 years.

07:24:36.599 --> 07:24:39.479
But Sonny could see that Glacier wanted

07:24:39.479 --> 07:24:40.619
to be just and fair.

07:24:40.680 --> 07:24:43.319
She couldn't fight a Sandwings battle for

07:24:43.319 --> 07:24:46.139
her, not one on one, for the throne like

07:24:46.139 --> 07:24:46.380
this.

07:24:46.439 --> 07:24:49.020
The ice wing shook her head.

07:24:49.139 --> 07:24:51.000
I'm sorry, Blaze.

07:24:51.060 --> 07:24:52.619
This is your fight.

07:24:52.740 --> 07:24:55.799
She touched Blaze's wing with her own

07:24:55.799 --> 07:24:58.380
briefly, then turned and flew up to join

07:24:58.380 --> 07:25:00.180
her fellow ice dragons on the wall.

07:25:00.240 --> 07:25:03.959
Blaise faced her sister, wide eyed with

07:25:03.959 --> 07:25:04.200
fear.

07:25:04.259 --> 07:25:07.619
You can forfeit, Sonny cried.

07:25:07.680 --> 07:25:08.700
You don't have to fight.

07:25:08.759 --> 07:25:10.799
Let her be queen and live.

07:25:10.799 --> 07:25:12.659
It's too late for that.

07:25:12.659 --> 07:25:14.340
Blister snarled.

07:25:14.400 --> 07:25:16.860
She wanted to be queen badly enough to

07:25:16.860 --> 07:25:18.060
fight for it all these years.

07:25:18.119 --> 07:25:21.180
She can't back down now that it's just

07:25:21.180 --> 07:25:22.020
the 2 of us.

07:25:22.080 --> 07:25:25.560
With a swift, sudden movement, blister

07:25:25.560 --> 07:25:28.439
darted a blaze, bit down viciously on the

07:25:28.439 --> 07:25:30.540
edge of one of her wings, and darted away

07:25:30.540 --> 07:25:30.720
again.

07:25:30.779 --> 07:25:32.400
Ow!

07:25:32.459 --> 07:25:33.840
Blaise shrieked.

07:25:33.900 --> 07:25:36.000
She staggered back, staring at her wing.

07:25:36.060 --> 07:25:37.439
Three moons?

07:25:37.500 --> 07:25:38.340
It's bleeding.

07:25:38.400 --> 07:25:39.060
I'm bleeding.

07:25:39.119 --> 07:25:40.860
Oh, brother.

07:25:40.919 --> 07:25:43.560
Glory said, but there was pity in her

07:25:43.560 --> 07:25:43.979
expression.

07:25:44.099 --> 07:25:45.840
Shouldn't we stop them?

07:25:45.900 --> 07:25:47.520
Sonny asked her friends.

07:25:47.580 --> 07:25:50.340
It's royal sandwing business now

07:25:50.340 --> 07:25:53.220
Starflight said, touching the bandage

07:25:53.220 --> 07:25:54.779
around his eyes and ducking his head.

07:25:54.840 --> 07:25:57.599
They'll fight and blister will win.

07:25:57.659 --> 07:25:59.639
But the important thing is that it means

07:25:59.639 --> 07:26:00.479
the war is over.

07:26:00.540 --> 07:26:02.880
There will be a queen on the sandwing

07:26:02.880 --> 07:26:04.919
throne, and no one else has to die.

07:26:05.040 --> 07:26:08.340
Except Blaze, Glory observed.

07:26:08.400 --> 07:26:11.159
The 2 sandwings circled each other

07:26:11.159 --> 07:26:13.259
hissing and jabbing with their tails like

07:26:13.259 --> 07:26:14.099
2 scorpions.

07:26:14.159 --> 07:26:17.340
Poor Blaze, Sonny said.

07:26:17.400 --> 07:26:18.540
It doesn't seem fair.

07:26:18.599 --> 07:26:21.840
She curled into Clay's side, leaning

07:26:21.840 --> 07:26:22.680
against his scales.

07:26:22.740 --> 07:26:26.040
I wish someone else could be queen, fate

07:26:26.040 --> 07:26:26.759
speaker said.

07:26:26.819 --> 07:26:28.380
Blister is so creepy.

07:26:28.439 --> 07:26:31.560
And smart, Starflight agreed.

07:26:31.619 --> 07:26:33.900
Who knows what she'll do once the throne

07:26:33.900 --> 07:26:34.560
is really hers?

07:26:34.680 --> 07:26:37.560
He scratched his claws across the stone.

07:26:37.619 --> 07:26:40.380
With the United Sandwing Armyator claw

07:26:40.380 --> 07:26:41.700
tips and the treasure.

07:26:41.759 --> 07:26:44.520
If she's the one who stole it, She could

07:26:44.520 --> 07:26:46.680
easily be the most dangerous dragon in

07:26:46.680 --> 07:26:47.340
Pyria.

07:26:47.400 --> 07:26:49.080
Isn't there anyone else?

07:26:49.200 --> 07:26:50.459
Sonny asked.

07:26:50.520 --> 07:26:53.040
She turned and saw Smolder still standing

07:26:53.040 --> 07:26:54.599
in the shadows of the doorway.

07:26:54.599 --> 07:26:56.819
He met her eyes and started toward her

07:26:56.819 --> 07:26:58.860
carefully avoiding his sisters.

07:26:58.919 --> 07:27:01.740
I don't think so, Starflight said.

07:27:01.799 --> 07:27:04.619
None of the 3 sisters have exactly taken

07:27:04.619 --> 07:27:06.299
the time to have dragonettes.

07:27:06.360 --> 07:27:10.139
Hello, Smolder said, sliding up to them.

07:27:10.200 --> 07:27:12.240
Flower was perched on his shoulder

07:27:12.240 --> 07:27:14.400
staring around at all the dragons with

07:27:14.400 --> 07:27:16.200
her big, brown, dragon like eyes.

07:27:16.259 --> 07:27:19.139
Aren't you all dramatic troublemakers?

07:27:19.200 --> 07:27:21.240
Do you think blisters going to let me

07:27:21.240 --> 07:27:21.659
live?

07:27:21.720 --> 07:27:22.860
I'm guessing no.

07:27:22.919 --> 07:27:25.439
This would probably be a good time for me

07:27:25.439 --> 07:27:26.099
to run away.

07:27:26.159 --> 07:27:29.520
He cast a speculative glance at the sky.

07:27:29.580 --> 07:27:30.659
But to where?

07:27:30.720 --> 07:27:33.659
Could you use another outlaw, perhaps?

07:27:33.720 --> 07:27:35.279
He asked Thorn.

07:27:35.340 --> 07:27:38.340
You have some nerve, Thorn snapped.

07:27:38.400 --> 07:27:40.139
I should kill you myself or that trick

07:27:40.139 --> 07:27:42.060
you played, locking us in the library.

07:27:42.180 --> 07:27:45.720
As if I had a choice, Smolder said

07:27:45.720 --> 07:27:47.880
reproachfully, and it didn't even work.

07:27:47.939 --> 07:27:50.700
Burn was this close to killing me until

07:27:50.700 --> 07:27:52.380
she got your message about meeting her

07:27:52.380 --> 07:27:52.619
here tonight.

07:27:52.680 --> 07:27:56.220
I should be mad at him too, Sonny

07:27:56.220 --> 07:27:56.400
thought.

07:27:56.459 --> 07:27:57.599
But she couldn't be.

07:27:57.659 --> 07:27:59.040
He wasn't evil.

07:27:59.099 --> 07:28:00.479
He wasn't even mean.

07:28:00.599 --> 07:28:03.900
He was a dragon in a terrible family, in

07:28:03.900 --> 07:28:06.360
a hard situation, in danger of being put

07:28:06.360 --> 07:28:07.860
to death like his brothers at any

07:28:07.860 --> 07:28:08.040
moment.

07:28:08.099 --> 07:28:10.439
He could have killed her the moment he

07:28:10.439 --> 07:28:11.639
got his talons on her.

07:28:11.700 --> 07:28:13.080
He could have left her in the tower.

07:28:13.200 --> 07:28:15.000
Maybe she shouldn't like him.

07:28:15.060 --> 07:28:16.080
But she did anyway.

07:28:16.139 --> 07:28:19.439
Smolder pointed to his sister's dead body

07:28:19.439 --> 07:28:20.459
with a rueful expression.

07:28:20.580 --> 07:28:24.419
I must admit, I never expected to outlive

07:28:24.419 --> 07:28:24.840
her.

07:28:24.900 --> 07:28:28.200
It probably won't be by much, if that's

07:28:28.200 --> 07:28:30.779
any consolation, Thorn said bluntly.

07:28:30.840 --> 07:28:33.360
Smolder, Sonny broke in.

07:28:33.419 --> 07:28:35.639
Are there any other dragons in line for

07:28:35.639 --> 07:28:36.599
the sandwing throne?

07:28:36.659 --> 07:28:39.779
Did Queen Oasis have any sisters or other

07:28:39.779 --> 07:28:42.419
daughters, or did any of these 3 have

07:28:42.419 --> 07:28:43.020
dragonettes?

07:28:43.080 --> 07:28:45.119
Smolder shook his head?

07:28:45.240 --> 07:28:48.000
Mother was very strict and very careful.

07:28:48.060 --> 07:28:51.119
She had just the 3 daughters, so someone

07:28:51.119 --> 07:28:53.279
could inherit one day, but she didn't

07:28:53.279 --> 07:28:55.560
want a lot of challengers, so she had no

07:28:55.560 --> 07:28:56.040
more eggs.

07:28:56.099 --> 07:28:58.080
And the rest of us were not allowed to

07:28:58.080 --> 07:28:59.159
have dragonettes either.

07:28:59.279 --> 07:29:01.500
He fell silent for a moment.

07:29:01.560 --> 07:29:03.419
I was in love once.

07:29:03.479 --> 07:29:06.119
She was so angry when she found out.

07:29:06.180 --> 07:29:08.159
I don't even know what she did.

07:29:08.279 --> 07:29:10.500
But I never saw a poem again.

07:29:10.560 --> 07:29:13.860
You should have better choices, Sonny

07:29:13.860 --> 07:29:15.119
said, stamping her foot.

07:29:15.180 --> 07:29:17.279
All 3 of your sisters are terrible.

07:29:17.340 --> 07:29:21.060
Blaze let out another yowl of pain as

07:29:21.060 --> 07:29:22.799
Blister slashed her claws across her

07:29:22.799 --> 07:29:23.099
nose.

07:29:23.159 --> 07:29:25.619
Sonny had a feeling this fight could have

07:29:25.619 --> 07:29:27.840
been over already, but Blister was

07:29:27.840 --> 07:29:30.060
playing with Blaze, showing off for the

07:29:30.060 --> 07:29:30.360
audience.

07:29:30.479 --> 07:29:33.119
Why can't someone else be queen?

07:29:33.180 --> 07:29:34.619
Fate speaker asked.

07:29:34.680 --> 07:29:36.900
If glory can be queen of the night wings

07:29:36.900 --> 07:29:38.819
who says it has to be a member of the

07:29:38.819 --> 07:29:39.900
royal family?

07:29:39.959 --> 07:29:42.240
Good question, said Glory.

07:29:42.360 --> 07:29:44.580
Who else would have the authority?

07:29:44.639 --> 07:29:45.959
Starflight asked.

07:29:46.020 --> 07:29:48.119
Why would the other Sandwings listen to

07:29:48.119 --> 07:29:48.540
anyone else?

07:29:48.599 --> 07:29:51.419
If any dragon could take the throne?

07:29:51.479 --> 07:29:52.319
It'd be anarchy.

07:29:52.380 --> 07:29:54.779
There'd be challengers trying to grab it

07:29:54.779 --> 07:29:55.380
every other day.

07:29:55.439 --> 07:29:59.880
I know, Sunny said, but still, if all the

07:29:59.880 --> 07:30:02.220
royal options are awful, it seems like

07:30:02.220 --> 07:30:03.599
there should be a way to give the sand

07:30:03.599 --> 07:30:06.000
wing someone else, a better queen.

07:30:06.060 --> 07:30:08.220
Her wings drooped.

07:30:08.279 --> 07:30:10.380
After everything they'd been through.

07:30:10.439 --> 07:30:12.959
All the worry about the prophecy, and all

07:30:12.959 --> 07:30:15.060
the danger they'd been in, and all the

07:30:15.060 --> 07:30:16.500
dragons who tried to kill them.

07:30:16.560 --> 07:30:18.299
Was this how it ended?

07:30:18.360 --> 07:30:21.060
They stopped the war, but gave the

07:30:21.060 --> 07:30:22.560
sandwings an evil queen?

07:30:22.619 --> 07:30:25.439
Was she supposed to say, oh, well, good

07:30:25.439 --> 07:30:25.979
enough.

07:30:26.040 --> 07:30:29.040
Flower wriggled off smolders back and

07:30:29.040 --> 07:30:31.200
came over to pat Sonny's talons in her

07:30:31.200 --> 07:30:32.159
odd, comforting way.

07:30:32.220 --> 07:30:34.560
The little scavenger looked up at Sonny

07:30:34.560 --> 07:30:36.299
and squeaked, waving her paws.

07:30:36.360 --> 07:30:40.680
Scavengers are so crazy, tsunami said.

07:30:40.740 --> 07:30:42.779
She ducked her head to sniff at flower.

07:30:42.840 --> 07:30:43.919
Look at her.

07:30:43.979 --> 07:30:45.659
Just standing here in the middle of all

07:30:45.659 --> 07:30:46.380
these dragons.

07:30:46.439 --> 07:30:48.119
Where's her survival instinct?

07:30:48.240 --> 07:30:50.279
This is the one who stole the treasure

07:30:50.279 --> 07:30:50.459
right?

07:30:50.520 --> 07:30:52.860
Hey, Squish face.

07:30:52.919 --> 07:30:54.119
This is all your fault, you know?

07:30:54.180 --> 07:30:56.880
Flower wrapped her arms around one of

07:30:56.880 --> 07:30:59.340
Sonny's ankles and tugged, as if she was

07:30:59.340 --> 07:31:01.619
trying to drag Sonny somewhere, squeaking

07:31:01.619 --> 07:31:01.979
loudly.

07:31:02.040 --> 07:31:03.720
What?

07:31:03.779 --> 07:31:04.860
Sonny asked.

07:31:04.919 --> 07:31:06.119
She looked at Smolder.

07:31:06.180 --> 07:31:07.500
What's she trying to say?

07:31:07.560 --> 07:31:09.180
He shrugged.

07:31:09.240 --> 07:31:10.439
I never know.

07:31:10.500 --> 07:31:13.439
Flower jumped up and down, flapping her

07:31:13.439 --> 07:31:13.919
paws.

07:31:13.979 --> 07:31:16.139
Sonny tilted her head, confused.

07:31:16.200 --> 07:31:18.900
The scavenger ran over to the pit of sand

07:31:18.900 --> 07:31:22.139
flapped again, ran back to Sonny, tugged

07:31:22.139 --> 07:31:24.119
on her ankle, and ran back to the sand.

07:31:24.180 --> 07:31:27.540
To Sonny's astonishment, flower threw

07:31:27.540 --> 07:31:29.279
herself down and started to dig with her

07:31:29.279 --> 07:31:29.639
paws.

07:31:29.759 --> 07:31:33.000
What in the 3 moons?

07:31:33.000 --> 07:31:34.200
Smolder said.

07:31:34.259 --> 07:31:36.779
I'll never understand scavengers.

07:31:36.840 --> 07:31:39.900
She's trying to tell us something, Sonny

07:31:39.900 --> 07:31:40.139
said.

07:31:40.200 --> 07:31:42.540
She followed flower to the sand pit

07:31:42.540 --> 07:31:44.159
glancing up at the obelisk.

07:31:44.220 --> 07:31:46.799
Did Flower know that the dragon she'd

07:31:46.799 --> 07:31:49.080
killed or helped to kill was buried

07:31:49.080 --> 07:31:49.259
here?

07:31:49.319 --> 07:31:51.900
This is a little morbid flower.

07:31:51.959 --> 07:31:54.900
Flower whacked Sonny's front talons

07:31:54.900 --> 07:31:56.819
pointed at the sand, shouted something

07:31:56.819 --> 07:31:59.400
like, you will throbble and went back to

07:31:59.400 --> 07:31:59.759
digging.

07:31:59.819 --> 07:32:03.540
All right, Sonny said, and she started to

07:32:03.540 --> 07:32:04.080
dig too.

07:32:04.139 --> 07:32:06.119
What could she be trying to tell us?

07:32:06.180 --> 07:32:08.459
What are you doing?

07:32:08.520 --> 07:32:09.900
Glory demanded.

07:32:09.959 --> 07:32:12.180
Digging, Sonny said.

07:32:12.240 --> 07:32:14.400
She glanced up at Blaze and Blister.

07:32:14.459 --> 07:32:17.520
Blaze had 3 more bleeding wounds. and

07:32:17.520 --> 07:32:19.439
blister was pacing smugly around her.

07:32:19.500 --> 07:32:21.479
Surely the fight couldn't last much

07:32:21.479 --> 07:32:21.720
longer.

07:32:21.779 --> 07:32:23.459
Why?

07:32:23.520 --> 07:32:25.619
Tsunami asked, coming to stand next to

07:32:25.619 --> 07:32:25.860
her.

07:32:25.919 --> 07:32:29.279
Because Flower wants me to, Sonny said, I

07:32:29.279 --> 07:32:31.200
don't know, but it feels like maybe it's

07:32:31.200 --> 07:32:31.500
important.

07:32:31.560 --> 07:32:34.740
Tsunami and glory exchange glances.

07:32:34.799 --> 07:32:36.659
Sonny could guess what those looks

07:32:36.659 --> 07:32:36.959
meant.

07:32:37.020 --> 07:32:38.880
Another crazy, sunny idea.

07:32:38.939 --> 07:32:41.520
Look at her. following a scavenger's

07:32:41.520 --> 07:32:43.200
instructions, as if that makes any

07:32:43.200 --> 07:32:43.500
sense.

07:32:43.619 --> 07:32:46.500
Scoot over, tsunami said.

07:32:46.560 --> 07:32:48.779
She flexed her claws and drove them into

07:32:48.779 --> 07:32:49.139
the sand.

07:32:49.259 --> 07:32:52.500
You too, Glory said to the scavenger

07:32:52.500 --> 07:32:53.099
joining them.

07:32:53.159 --> 07:32:56.939
Tsunami and glory began to dig, wing to

07:32:56.939 --> 07:32:57.540
wing with Sonny.

07:32:57.659 --> 07:33:00.540
A moment later, she looked up and found

07:33:00.540 --> 07:33:03.180
Thorn digging busily beside her as well.

07:33:03.419 --> 07:33:05.819
She tried to hide her smile, but she

07:33:05.819 --> 07:33:06.119
couldn't.

07:33:06.180 --> 07:33:09.599
Their talons swept the sand away quickly

07:33:09.599 --> 07:33:11.939
and soon Sonny could see the gleam of

07:33:11.939 --> 07:33:13.020
white bones below them.

07:33:13.080 --> 07:33:15.540
That's Queen Oasis.

07:33:15.599 --> 07:33:18.000
Why does Flower want us to dig her up?

07:33:18.119 --> 07:33:21.599
Before long, they had the front half of

07:33:21.599 --> 07:33:23.040
the dragon's body uncovered.

07:33:23.099 --> 07:33:26.639
She was huge too, even bigger than burn.

07:33:26.700 --> 07:33:29.159
She must have been terrifying when she

07:33:29.159 --> 07:33:29.580
was alive.

07:33:29.639 --> 07:33:33.180
Flower scrambled into the hole they dug

07:33:33.180 --> 07:33:34.979
and carefully climbed around the bones

07:33:34.979 --> 07:33:37.020
until she was standing beside the

07:33:37.020 --> 07:33:38.099
dragon's skull.

07:33:38.159 --> 07:33:40.799
She tapped on the skull's jaws and looked

07:33:40.799 --> 07:33:41.520
up at Sonny.

07:33:41.580 --> 07:33:45.000
A sudden shiver went down Sunny's spine

07:33:45.000 --> 07:33:47.040
as if she knew what was about to happen

07:33:47.040 --> 07:33:48.840
although she couldn't have put it into

07:33:48.840 --> 07:33:49.500
words.

07:33:49.560 --> 07:33:52.680
She reached down and pried open the

07:33:52.680 --> 07:33:53.459
queen's mouth.

07:33:53.520 --> 07:33:57.840
Inside were 2 sacks, falling apart and

07:33:57.840 --> 07:34:00.240
full of holes, but otherwise just like

07:34:00.240 --> 07:34:01.860
the one the scavengers had given her in

07:34:01.860 --> 07:34:02.159
the forest.

07:34:02.220 --> 07:34:05.639
Behind her, she heard glory gasp.

07:34:05.700 --> 07:34:09.240
She understood what this meant. 20 years

07:34:09.240 --> 07:34:11.340
ago, the night Oasis died.

07:34:11.400 --> 07:34:13.500
Flower must have hidden some of the

07:34:13.500 --> 07:34:15.540
treasure in the dead dragon's mouth

07:34:15.540 --> 07:34:18.060
before she ran off to hide in the dunes.

07:34:18.119 --> 07:34:20.580
Maybe she thought she'd have a chance to

07:34:20.580 --> 07:34:22.740
go back and get it, or maybe she didn't

07:34:22.740 --> 07:34:23.459
want to be caught with it.

07:34:23.520 --> 07:34:26.819
Sunny carefully lifted the sacks onto the

07:34:26.819 --> 07:34:27.180
sand.

07:34:27.240 --> 07:34:30.779
Emeralds and gold coins, and tiger's eye

07:34:30.779 --> 07:34:32.400
bracelets spilled out through the holes.

07:34:32.520 --> 07:34:35.279
She sliced open the sacks with one of her

07:34:35.279 --> 07:34:35.759
claws.

07:34:35.819 --> 07:34:37.799
And there it was at last.

07:34:37.860 --> 07:34:40.500
The Eye of Onyx.

07:34:40.560 --> 07:34:45.060
Chapter 28.

07:34:45.299 --> 07:34:49.860
By all the moons, Thorn whispered.

07:34:49.919 --> 07:34:52.619
Sunny slit her talons around the black

07:34:52.619 --> 07:34:54.779
sphere and lifted it up.

07:34:54.840 --> 07:34:57.540
As she did, she realized that it was set

07:34:57.540 --> 07:35:00.299
on a chain of hammered gold links so it

07:35:00.299 --> 07:35:01.380
could be worn as a necklace.

07:35:01.439 --> 07:35:04.259
And then she took a closer look at the

07:35:04.259 --> 07:35:04.560
setting.

07:35:04.619 --> 07:35:08.759
In molded, beaten gold, on either side of

07:35:08.759 --> 07:35:11.459
the onyx stone were 2 dragon wings.

07:35:11.520 --> 07:35:13.799
They caught the firelight of the torches

07:35:13.799 --> 07:35:16.740
and glowed red, gold, orange as she held

07:35:16.740 --> 07:35:17.819
the necklace up.

07:35:17.880 --> 07:35:19.799
Wings of fire.

07:35:19.860 --> 07:35:22.139
Had somebody known?

07:35:22.200 --> 07:35:24.659
Somewhere along the line and told the

07:35:24.659 --> 07:35:25.439
night wings?

07:35:25.500 --> 07:35:27.060
Was it just a coincidence?

07:35:27.119 --> 07:35:30.659
In a way, the prophecy turned out to be

07:35:30.659 --> 07:35:31.319
real after all.

07:35:31.380 --> 07:35:34.200
Even if somebody thought they made it up

07:35:34.200 --> 07:35:37.380
it's real to me, and to all the dragons

07:35:37.380 --> 07:35:38.639
who need the war to be over.

07:35:38.700 --> 07:35:41.400
But the prophecy didn't make this happen

07:35:41.400 --> 07:35:45.000
no all powerful fate or guiding force in

07:35:45.000 --> 07:35:46.080
the universe made this happen.

07:35:46.139 --> 07:35:48.659
We made this happen.

07:35:48.720 --> 07:35:51.900
Me and my friends, and all these dragons

07:35:51.900 --> 07:35:53.400
here, and even flower.

07:35:53.459 --> 07:35:56.580
She could feel power thrumming through

07:35:56.580 --> 07:35:59.279
the sphere, like the obsidian mirror, or

07:35:59.279 --> 07:36:01.380
the dream visitor, but stronger and

07:36:01.380 --> 07:36:02.220
lighter somehow.

07:36:02.279 --> 07:36:05.099
She wondered if animus touched objects

07:36:05.099 --> 07:36:07.139
had different auras based on which dragon

07:36:07.139 --> 07:36:08.099
had enchanted them.

07:36:08.159 --> 07:36:10.979
No wonder no one has been able to take

07:36:10.979 --> 07:36:12.720
the sand wing throne all these years

07:36:12.720 --> 07:36:14.279
tsunami said.

07:36:14.340 --> 07:36:17.700
It's like Queen Oasis was still hanging

07:36:17.700 --> 07:36:18.180
on to it.

07:36:18.240 --> 07:36:21.240
Glory agreed, nudging the bones with her

07:36:21.240 --> 07:36:21.540
tail.

07:36:21.599 --> 07:36:24.060
Flower was watching them nervously from

07:36:24.060 --> 07:36:25.080
on top of the skull.

07:36:25.139 --> 07:36:28.139
Sonny held up the eye of onyx, and made a

07:36:28.139 --> 07:36:29.459
little bow toward the scavenger.

07:36:29.580 --> 07:36:31.740
Thank you, she said.

07:36:31.799 --> 07:36:33.360
This is what we needed.

07:36:33.419 --> 07:36:36.119
Sunny, tsunami said.

07:36:36.180 --> 07:36:38.520
With this, you could be queen.

07:36:38.580 --> 07:36:39.779
You'd be a great queen.

07:36:39.840 --> 07:36:41.580
It's true.

07:36:41.639 --> 07:36:42.720
Glory said.

07:36:42.779 --> 07:36:44.340
Nobody wants blister.

07:36:44.400 --> 07:36:46.439
They'd follow you if you want the

07:36:46.439 --> 07:36:46.740
throne.

07:36:46.860 --> 07:36:48.479
They were right.

07:36:48.599 --> 07:36:51.299
Sonny could sense that the magic in the

07:36:51.299 --> 07:36:53.819
sphere was not confined to royalty.

07:36:53.880 --> 07:36:55.919
Annie Sandwing who held the Eye of Onyx

07:36:55.919 --> 07:36:58.560
could command the kingdom, even Sunny

07:36:58.560 --> 07:37:00.659
with her harmless tale could be queen.

07:37:00.720 --> 07:37:03.720
Another earthquake shook the ground under

07:37:03.720 --> 07:37:04.500
her talons.

07:37:04.560 --> 07:37:08.159
And I promise not to be jealous, tsunami

07:37:08.159 --> 07:37:08.459
said.

07:37:08.520 --> 07:37:11.159
Even though this is all highly unfair

07:37:11.159 --> 07:37:13.319
because why aren't thrones just falling

07:37:13.319 --> 07:37:15.000
into my lap is what I'd like to know?

07:37:15.060 --> 07:37:19.439
Sonny imagined it, a palace, an army

07:37:19.439 --> 07:37:21.119
treasure, and power.

07:37:21.180 --> 07:37:23.939
She'd command the largest kingdom in

07:37:23.939 --> 07:37:24.599
Pyria.

07:37:24.659 --> 07:37:27.540
She could make the kingdom of sand a safe

07:37:27.540 --> 07:37:28.560
peaceful place to live.

07:37:28.619 --> 07:37:31.319
She could change the laws, and stop

07:37:31.319 --> 07:37:33.060
dragons from fighting each other all the

07:37:33.060 --> 07:37:33.299
time.

07:37:33.360 --> 07:37:36.659
She looked up at the wings and claws and

07:37:36.659 --> 07:37:37.860
teeth lining the walls.

07:37:37.919 --> 07:37:39.900
Or could she?

07:37:39.959 --> 07:37:41.700
Would she be strong enough to punish

07:37:41.700 --> 07:37:42.840
anyone who opposed her?

07:37:42.900 --> 07:37:45.240
Would she know how to defend her subjects

07:37:45.240 --> 07:37:47.580
if another tribe attacked them?

07:37:47.639 --> 07:37:49.680
Would she have to become a different kind

07:37:49.680 --> 07:37:50.279
of dragon?

07:37:50.400 --> 07:37:54.479
I don't want to be queen, Sonny

07:37:54.479 --> 07:37:55.139
realized.

07:37:55.200 --> 07:37:58.080
I don't want to fight for my throne, or

07:37:58.080 --> 07:38:00.419
worry about the size of my territory, and

07:38:00.419 --> 07:38:01.680
how much is in my treasury.

07:38:01.740 --> 07:38:04.200
I want to be with my friends.

07:38:04.259 --> 07:38:06.959
I want to teach dragonettes how to make

07:38:06.959 --> 07:38:09.360
peace and how to find other solutions

07:38:09.360 --> 07:38:10.619
instead of war.

07:38:10.680 --> 07:38:12.419
I just want to be me.

07:38:12.540 --> 07:38:14.220
Sunny.

07:38:14.279 --> 07:38:17.040
But it still didn't have to be blister.

07:38:17.159 --> 07:38:18.779
There was another choice.

07:38:18.900 --> 07:38:21.900
She could feel the eyes of every dragon

07:38:21.900 --> 07:38:22.439
on her.

07:38:22.500 --> 07:38:24.659
Even blister and blaze had stopped

07:38:24.659 --> 07:38:27.060
fighting, alerted by the silence that

07:38:27.060 --> 07:38:28.439
something significant was happening.

07:38:28.560 --> 07:38:30.720
Blisters stepped toward them with a

07:38:30.720 --> 07:38:31.020
hiss.

07:38:31.080 --> 07:38:34.439
Sonny looked right at her, then turned

07:38:34.439 --> 07:38:37.500
and gave the Eye of Onyx to Thorn.

07:38:37.560 --> 07:38:40.319
Something crackled between them as their

07:38:40.319 --> 07:38:41.400
claws touched.

07:38:41.459 --> 07:38:45.000
A tiny jolt of purple lightning, sparking

07:38:45.000 --> 07:38:46.560
along the curve of the black stone.

07:38:46.619 --> 07:38:50.939
This is the new sandwing queen, Sonny

07:38:50.939 --> 07:38:53.279
said, hearing her voice echo across the

07:38:53.279 --> 07:38:53.759
courtyard.

07:38:53.819 --> 07:38:55.560
She is our choice.

07:38:55.619 --> 07:38:57.419
She is the right choice.

07:38:57.540 --> 07:39:01.020
Murmurs and gasps rippled through the

07:39:01.020 --> 07:39:01.799
watching dragons.

07:39:01.919 --> 07:39:06.240
Fourth moons and fireballs, Thorn said

07:39:06.240 --> 07:39:07.200
awestruck.

07:39:07.259 --> 07:39:08.340
Me?

07:39:08.400 --> 07:39:09.240
Are you sure?

07:39:09.299 --> 07:39:13.200
I'm extremely, definitely sure, Sunny

07:39:13.200 --> 07:39:13.560
said.

07:39:13.619 --> 07:39:14.880
Awesome.

07:39:14.939 --> 07:39:16.619
Glory whispered.

07:39:16.680 --> 07:39:19.020
And when Sonny looked over at her, the

07:39:19.020 --> 07:39:20.639
rain wing queen winked.

07:39:20.700 --> 07:39:23.580
Beside her, tsunami was nodding too.

07:39:23.639 --> 07:39:27.779
Absolutely not, said Blister. advancing

07:39:27.779 --> 07:39:28.139
on them.

07:39:28.200 --> 07:39:29.700
That is mine.

07:39:29.759 --> 07:39:31.259
I deserve it.

07:39:31.319 --> 07:39:33.360
I took the rest of the sandwing

07:39:33.360 --> 07:39:33.659
treasure.

07:39:33.779 --> 07:39:36.180
I tricked mother into flying toward death

07:39:36.180 --> 07:39:36.479
alone.

07:39:36.540 --> 07:39:40.020
She gave the old queen's bones a scornful

07:39:40.020 --> 07:39:40.259
look.

07:39:40.319 --> 07:39:43.799
I used my brain to get out of facing burn

07:39:43.799 --> 07:39:46.619
in a challenge duel by turning our fight

07:39:46.619 --> 07:39:47.159
into a war.

07:39:47.279 --> 07:39:50.939
She hissed at the Dragonettes, her usual

07:39:50.939 --> 07:39:52.860
stillness broken into trembling anger.

07:39:52.919 --> 07:39:56.759
I am the smartest dragon in Pyria.

07:39:56.819 --> 07:39:59.759
I am the rightful sandwing queen.

07:39:59.880 --> 07:40:03.000
She flicked her tail at Burn's body, then

07:40:03.000 --> 07:40:05.819
at Blaze, who was crouched on the stones

07:40:05.819 --> 07:40:07.200
bleeding from several small wounds.

07:40:07.259 --> 07:40:11.220
Besides, it's in the prophecy, she

07:40:11.220 --> 07:40:14.279
growled, of 3 queens who blister and

07:40:14.279 --> 07:40:16.740
blaze and burn, 2 shall die.

07:40:16.860 --> 07:40:20.580
And one shall learn, Sonny quoted back at

07:40:20.580 --> 07:40:20.819
her.

07:40:20.819 --> 07:40:23.400
If she bows to a fate that is stronger

07:40:23.400 --> 07:40:25.500
and higher, she'll have the power of

07:40:25.500 --> 07:40:26.400
wings of fire.

07:40:26.459 --> 07:40:30.180
Marosir was talking about the night wings

07:40:30.180 --> 07:40:32.459
hinting that the winning queen would have

07:40:32.459 --> 07:40:34.259
to submit to the night wing tribe.

07:40:34.380 --> 07:40:36.840
But this is much better.

07:40:36.900 --> 07:40:40.740
This is your fate, to accept your new

07:40:40.740 --> 07:40:41.220
queen.

07:40:41.279 --> 07:40:43.139
She nodded at Thorn.

07:40:43.200 --> 07:40:46.380
Blister coiled her venomous tail up

07:40:46.380 --> 07:40:49.380
giving Sonny and Thorn a cold glare that

07:40:49.380 --> 07:40:51.540
was unsettlingly like the dragon bite

07:40:51.540 --> 07:40:52.080
vipers.

07:40:52.139 --> 07:40:55.080
You don't seriously think that's going to

07:40:55.080 --> 07:40:56.279
happen, do you?

07:40:56.340 --> 07:40:59.580
So fight me, Thorn said.

07:40:59.639 --> 07:41:00.540
I'm not afraid of you.

07:41:00.599 --> 07:41:02.939
I can win this throne in battle, if

07:41:02.939 --> 07:41:03.900
that's how you want to do it.

07:41:04.020 --> 07:41:06.479
She tossed her head toward Blaze.

07:41:06.599 --> 07:41:09.599
Or are you only willing to fight weak and

07:41:09.599 --> 07:41:10.919
cowering dragons?

07:41:10.919 --> 07:41:13.080
Blister's expression was hard to read.

07:41:13.139 --> 07:41:15.779
Is she afraid to fight, Thorn?

07:41:15.840 --> 07:41:18.540
Sonny wondered, or is she calculating her

07:41:18.540 --> 07:41:20.759
next move, coming up with another evil

07:41:20.759 --> 07:41:21.119
trick?

07:41:21.180 --> 07:41:25.439
I don't have to fight you, Blister said

07:41:25.439 --> 07:41:27.180
pacing closer and closer.

07:41:27.240 --> 07:41:29.639
Her obsidian eyes glittered in the

07:41:29.639 --> 07:41:30.180
moonlight.

07:41:30.299 --> 07:41:32.459
You have no right to this throne.

07:41:32.580 --> 07:41:34.799
The eye of onyx is mine.

07:41:34.860 --> 07:41:38.159
Suddenly she lunged forward, and snatched

07:41:38.159 --> 07:41:40.020
the smooth black sphere out of Thorn's

07:41:40.020 --> 07:41:40.500
talons.

07:41:40.560 --> 07:41:43.799
Orange sparks flew off the eye where

07:41:43.799 --> 07:41:45.659
blisters claws touched it.

07:41:45.720 --> 07:41:48.299
There was a hissing, crackling, spitting

07:41:48.299 --> 07:41:50.340
sound that seemed to fill the whole

07:41:50.340 --> 07:41:53.759
courtyard and expand outward, shock waves

07:41:53.759 --> 07:41:55.380
spilling over the walls and the desert

07:41:55.380 --> 07:41:55.740
beyond.

07:41:55.860 --> 07:41:59.099
Blisters, talons started shaking.

07:41:59.159 --> 07:42:01.139
It looked as if she was trying to drop

07:42:01.139 --> 07:42:02.340
the eye, but she couldn't.

07:42:02.400 --> 07:42:04.560
Lightning flickered across the black

07:42:04.560 --> 07:42:07.380
stone and then out, darting along

07:42:07.380 --> 07:42:09.779
blister's arms and up into her wings.

07:42:09.900 --> 07:42:12.900
She jerked back, nearly lifting into the

07:42:12.900 --> 07:42:15.240
air, and fell, still clutching the

07:42:15.240 --> 07:42:15.479
sphere.

07:42:15.599 --> 07:42:17.700
But she didn't scream.

07:42:17.759 --> 07:42:19.740
She never made a sound.

07:42:19.860 --> 07:42:22.439
Even as her tail smashed into the ground

07:42:22.439 --> 07:42:24.419
and her head thrashed from side to side.

07:42:24.479 --> 07:42:28.139
The lightning cracked again, faster

07:42:28.139 --> 07:42:29.880
ripping through the sand wing's body.

07:42:29.939 --> 07:42:32.759
And then blister, the dragon of their

07:42:32.759 --> 07:42:35.700
nightmares, the sister whose evil schemes

07:42:35.700 --> 07:42:39.119
had started the whole war exploded into a

07:42:39.119 --> 07:42:40.200
pile of black dust.

07:42:40.259 --> 07:42:42.180
Nobody moved.

07:42:42.240 --> 07:42:46.139
Nobody spoke for a long, long moment.

07:42:46.200 --> 07:42:50.159
And then Blaise said wonderingly, it's

07:42:50.159 --> 07:42:50.459
me?

07:42:50.520 --> 07:42:52.799
I'm the sister who survives?

07:42:52.919 --> 07:42:56.220
Thorn stepped forward, and Gingerly

07:42:56.220 --> 07:42:57.659
picked up the Eye of Onyx again.

07:42:57.720 --> 07:43:00.299
It made a little humming sound, and

07:43:00.299 --> 07:43:02.700
flickered with dark purple lines just

07:43:02.700 --> 07:43:04.319
once, then went quiet.

07:43:04.380 --> 07:43:06.479
What happened?

07:43:06.540 --> 07:43:08.099
Starflight asked.

07:43:08.159 --> 07:43:09.360
Beside him?

07:43:09.419 --> 07:43:12.240
Fate speaker shook her head, for once too

07:43:12.240 --> 07:43:13.020
shocked to speak.

07:43:13.080 --> 07:43:16.020
I think we'd better do some research

07:43:16.020 --> 07:43:18.119
about the exact enchantment on that thing

07:43:18.119 --> 07:43:21.659
Glory said, giving the eye of onyx a wary

07:43:21.659 --> 07:43:21.840
look.

07:43:21.900 --> 07:43:24.720
I can see why Oasis kept it in her

07:43:24.720 --> 07:43:26.759
treasury instead of wearing it, Thorn

07:43:26.759 --> 07:43:27.060
said.

07:43:27.119 --> 07:43:29.340
I'm a little traumatized right now.

07:43:29.400 --> 07:43:31.979
But she lifted the necklace over her head

07:43:31.979 --> 07:43:34.380
and let the chain settle around her neck

07:43:34.380 --> 07:43:37.139
with the onyx stone and the dragon wings

07:43:37.139 --> 07:43:38.459
resting in the center of her chest.

07:43:38.520 --> 07:43:41.340
They bumped against the moonstone that

07:43:41.340 --> 07:43:43.259
was already there, and Sonny thought of

07:43:43.259 --> 07:43:43.560
her father.

07:43:43.619 --> 07:43:45.840
We proved him wrong.

07:43:45.900 --> 07:43:47.520
We really did it.

07:43:47.580 --> 07:43:49.259
We ended the war.

07:43:49.319 --> 07:43:52.439
She looked up at all the dragons who were

07:43:52.439 --> 07:43:54.900
watching, from the walls, from the sky

07:43:54.900 --> 07:43:57.540
and now spilling into the courtyard, sand

07:43:57.540 --> 07:43:59.340
wings coming forward to greet their new

07:43:59.340 --> 07:44:00.060
queen.

07:44:00.119 --> 07:44:02.279
Blaze was the 1st one to reach her

07:44:02.279 --> 07:44:05.159
crouching and bowing low to Queen Thorn

07:44:05.159 --> 07:44:07.500
behind her, others followed suit.

07:44:07.799 --> 07:44:10.259
This is really strange.

07:44:10.380 --> 07:44:12.360
Thorn whispered to Sonny.

07:44:12.419 --> 07:44:13.979
I hope you're planning to help me figure

07:44:13.979 --> 07:44:14.580
this all out.

07:44:14.639 --> 07:44:18.240
I will, Sonny said, but you'll be

07:44:18.240 --> 07:44:18.900
brilliant.

07:44:18.959 --> 07:44:21.240
She caught a glimpse of smolder.

07:44:21.299 --> 07:44:23.819
Six Claws and Kibley among the bowing

07:44:23.819 --> 07:44:26.759
dragons, and she saw Queen Glacier, Queen

07:44:26.759 --> 07:44:29.099
Coral, and Queen Mohan watching from the

07:44:29.099 --> 07:44:30.900
walls, looking relieved.

07:44:30.959 --> 07:44:33.000
And I think there will be lots of other

07:44:33.000 --> 07:44:34.799
dragons willing to help you figure it out

07:44:34.799 --> 07:44:34.979
too.

07:44:35.040 --> 07:44:38.040
She realized that Clay was sitting out

07:44:38.040 --> 07:44:40.740
beside Starflight, rubbing his head, and

07:44:40.740 --> 07:44:42.659
she hurried over to him with tsunami and

07:44:42.659 --> 07:44:43.439
glory right behind her.

07:44:43.500 --> 07:44:46.619
His bewildered, worried, wonderful face

07:44:46.619 --> 07:44:51.360
alive, and all right, made her whole body

07:44:51.360 --> 07:44:53.819
feel as though it was full of light.

07:44:53.880 --> 07:44:55.020
Wow.

07:44:55.080 --> 07:44:57.180
Everything hurts.

07:44:57.240 --> 07:44:58.380
Clay said.

07:44:58.439 --> 07:45:01.080
He blinked at them, and at the sky where

07:45:01.080 --> 07:45:03.240
the sun was rising, and at the courtyard

07:45:03.240 --> 07:45:04.080
full of dragons.

07:45:04.139 --> 07:45:07.319
Oh, did I miss anything?

07:45:07.380 --> 07:45:11.880
Epilogue.

07:45:11.939 --> 07:45:13.259
One month later.

07:45:13.380 --> 07:45:16.979
It was a perfect day for flying.

07:45:17.040 --> 07:45:20.159
Trails of white clouds splashed across

07:45:20.159 --> 07:45:22.259
the bright blue sky, as if they'd been

07:45:22.259 --> 07:45:24.599
painted on in long, thin brushstrokes.

07:45:24.659 --> 07:45:27.720
The wind whisked around them, fast and

07:45:27.720 --> 07:45:30.000
breathless and playful, and the mountains

07:45:30.000 --> 07:45:32.340
below looked like sharp green gemstones

07:45:32.340 --> 07:45:33.060
in the warm sunlight.

07:45:33.119 --> 07:45:35.340
Can't you imagine it?

07:45:35.400 --> 07:45:36.959
Sonny said to her friends.

07:45:37.020 --> 07:45:38.279
Wouldn't it be perfect?

07:45:38.340 --> 07:45:41.159
They stood on one of the peaks of Jade

07:45:41.159 --> 07:45:43.619
Mountain, with all of Pyria spread out

07:45:43.619 --> 07:45:44.040
below them.

07:45:44.099 --> 07:45:47.040
From here, on a day like today, Sunny

07:45:47.040 --> 07:45:48.959
could see the white sands of the desert

07:45:48.959 --> 07:45:51.479
far off to the west, and the dark green

07:45:51.479 --> 07:45:52.860
of the rainforest to the east.

07:45:52.919 --> 07:45:55.439
She could see the ocean glittering blue

07:45:55.439 --> 07:45:57.720
in the south, and the jagged teeth of the

07:45:57.720 --> 07:45:59.819
mountains stretching in a long line north

07:45:59.819 --> 07:46:00.900
toward the sky kingdom.

07:46:00.959 --> 07:46:03.779
She opened her wings and felt the wind

07:46:03.779 --> 07:46:06.240
whoosh around her, nearly lifting her off

07:46:06.240 --> 07:46:06.959
her talons.

07:46:07.020 --> 07:46:09.720
I can see it, tsunami said.

07:46:09.779 --> 07:46:12.540
We could use the caves as classrooms, but

07:46:12.540 --> 07:46:14.040
have everyone outside as much as

07:46:14.040 --> 07:46:14.459
possible.

07:46:14.520 --> 07:46:16.439
Lots of sunshine.

07:46:16.500 --> 07:46:17.580
Gloria agreed.

07:46:17.700 --> 07:46:19.439
Mandatory sunshine.

07:46:19.500 --> 07:46:23.819
And field trips, Clay suggested, limping

07:46:23.819 --> 07:46:24.659
over the rocks to them.

07:46:24.720 --> 07:46:28.860
So every dragonette can feel mud and sand

07:46:28.860 --> 07:46:32.040
and the ocean, and snow, and also eat

07:46:32.040 --> 07:46:32.700
mangoes.

07:46:32.759 --> 07:46:34.560
He granded glory.

07:46:34.619 --> 07:46:36.479
Mandatory mangoes.

07:46:36.540 --> 07:46:38.459
And scrolls, right?

07:46:38.520 --> 07:46:39.659
Starflight said.

07:46:39.720 --> 07:46:42.540
Lots and lots of scrolls, all the scrolls

07:46:42.540 --> 07:46:43.319
in Pyria.

07:46:43.380 --> 07:46:45.419
We could have the biggest library in the

07:46:45.419 --> 07:46:45.840
world here.

07:46:45.900 --> 07:46:49.139
He paused, and even with a bandage over

07:46:49.139 --> 07:46:51.299
his eyes, they could see his face fall.

07:46:51.360 --> 07:46:54.720
Sunny twined her tail around his, knowing

07:46:54.720 --> 07:46:55.979
he felt more comfortable when he was

07:46:55.979 --> 07:46:56.939
touching another dragon.

07:46:57.000 --> 07:46:59.159
Don't worry, Starflight.

07:46:59.220 --> 07:47:01.500
Fate speaker said from his other side

07:47:01.500 --> 07:47:02.639
nudging him gently.

07:47:02.700 --> 07:47:04.979
We'll figure out a way to make scrolls

07:47:04.979 --> 07:47:06.540
that blind dragons can read too.

07:47:06.599 --> 07:47:08.880
And until then, I'll read you every

07:47:08.880 --> 07:47:11.700
single scroll we find, I promise, I'm not

07:47:11.700 --> 07:47:12.299
going anywhere.

07:47:12.360 --> 07:47:14.880
He smiled shyly in her direction.

07:47:15.000 --> 07:47:17.279
And Sonny felt another stab of guilt.

07:47:17.340 --> 07:47:19.799
They'd talked about it.

07:47:19.860 --> 07:47:22.200
Finally, once they were all safely back

07:47:22.200 --> 07:47:23.580
in the rainforest.

07:47:23.639 --> 07:47:25.740
Sonny had found him by himself for once

07:47:25.740 --> 07:47:27.959
lying in the sun on one of the leaf

07:47:27.959 --> 07:47:30.360
platforms, and she had curled up beside

07:47:30.360 --> 07:47:31.500
him until he woke up.

07:47:31.560 --> 07:47:35.700
I'm sorry, Starfight, she'd said, and

07:47:35.700 --> 07:47:36.959
he'd known right away what she was

07:47:36.959 --> 07:47:37.380
talking about.

07:47:37.439 --> 07:47:41.159
I know, he'd answered, turning his head

07:47:41.159 --> 07:47:41.639
away from her.

07:47:41.700 --> 07:47:46.860
I just, I love you, but, like a brother.

07:47:46.919 --> 07:47:50.939
She'd hesitated, then said instead, not

07:47:50.939 --> 07:47:52.500
like fate speaker loves you.

07:47:52.560 --> 07:47:55.560
He folded his wings over his face and

07:47:55.560 --> 07:47:56.880
coughed, embarrassed.

07:47:56.939 --> 07:48:00.360
It's all right if you love her too, Sonny

07:48:00.360 --> 07:48:00.659
said.

07:48:00.720 --> 07:48:01.619
You should.

07:48:01.680 --> 07:48:04.319
She's, she cares about you.

07:48:04.380 --> 07:48:06.240
And she's hilarious.

07:48:06.299 --> 07:48:09.360
He hadn't said anything for a long time.

07:48:09.419 --> 07:48:12.180
Finally, Sunny had said, I brought you

07:48:12.180 --> 07:48:12.479
something.

07:48:12.540 --> 07:48:15.119
His head lifted at the sound of the

07:48:15.119 --> 07:48:15.840
rustling scroll.

07:48:15.900 --> 07:48:18.720
Remember, Tales of the Night Wings?

07:48:18.779 --> 07:48:20.159
want me to read it to you?

07:48:20.220 --> 07:48:23.639
Ha, he'd said, actually smiling.

07:48:23.700 --> 07:48:26.040
It'll sound a little different now that

07:48:26.040 --> 07:48:27.000
we know none of it is true.

07:48:27.119 --> 07:48:29.340
Sure, please do.

07:48:29.400 --> 07:48:32.700
Here, now on the mountaintop.

07:48:32.759 --> 07:48:36.180
Sonny thought, well, she hoped that

07:48:36.180 --> 07:48:37.259
everything would be all right between

07:48:37.259 --> 07:48:37.560
them.

07:48:37.619 --> 07:48:39.479
He'd be a great teacher.

07:48:39.540 --> 07:48:42.299
He didn't need his sight to do that, and

07:48:42.299 --> 07:48:43.740
his flying was getting more confident

07:48:43.740 --> 07:48:44.279
every day.

07:48:44.340 --> 07:48:47.459
If she ever found someone she cared about

07:48:47.459 --> 07:48:48.060
that way.

07:48:48.119 --> 07:48:51.060
Well, then things might be awkward again

07:48:51.060 --> 07:48:51.540
for a while.

07:48:51.599 --> 07:48:53.819
But he had fate speaker.

07:48:53.880 --> 07:48:55.799
They'd all be all right.

07:48:55.860 --> 07:48:58.619
Do you think anyone will actually come?

07:48:58.680 --> 07:49:01.200
Tsunami asked, pacing back from the

07:49:01.200 --> 07:49:01.860
northern ridge.

07:49:01.919 --> 07:49:04.619
I mean, a school for dragonettes from all

07:49:04.619 --> 07:49:05.340
the tribes.

07:49:05.400 --> 07:49:07.259
No one's ever done anything like that

07:49:07.259 --> 07:49:07.439
before.

07:49:07.500 --> 07:49:10.380
The queens might not want their subjects

07:49:10.380 --> 07:49:12.240
to understand each other better.

07:49:12.299 --> 07:49:15.000
What if we build a school and no one

07:49:15.000 --> 07:49:15.240
comes?

07:49:15.299 --> 07:49:18.779
They'll come, Sonny said confidently.

07:49:18.840 --> 07:49:20.880
We're not the only dragons who want to

07:49:20.880 --> 07:49:21.840
avoid any more wars.

07:49:21.900 --> 07:49:23.580
This is the best way.

07:49:23.639 --> 07:49:26.939
Dragonettes who grow up together will see

07:49:26.939 --> 07:49:29.099
how alike they really are, no matter what

07:49:29.099 --> 07:49:31.319
tribe they're from, then they won't judge

07:49:31.319 --> 07:49:33.060
each other, and they'll be much less

07:49:33.060 --> 07:49:34.259
likely to kill each other.

07:49:34.319 --> 07:49:38.220
Like us, Clay said, grinning at her.

07:49:38.279 --> 07:49:40.619
Unless they're all like tsunami.

07:49:40.680 --> 07:49:41.759
Glory choked.

07:49:41.819 --> 07:49:44.340
And then, getting to know each other will

07:49:44.340 --> 07:49:46.139
make them more likely to want to kill

07:49:46.139 --> 07:49:46.439
each other.

07:49:46.500 --> 07:49:49.200
Tsunami smacked her over the head with

07:49:49.200 --> 07:49:49.680
her tail.

07:49:49.740 --> 07:49:53.099
Hey, Deathbringer shouted from overhead

07:49:53.159 --> 07:49:54.840
where he was swooping about, surveying

07:49:54.840 --> 07:49:55.319
the mountains.

07:49:55.380 --> 07:49:57.299
No hitting the queen.

07:49:57.360 --> 07:50:00.779
Yeah, Gloria said saucily to tsunami.

07:50:00.900 --> 07:50:01.979
No hitting the queen.

07:50:02.040 --> 07:50:05.580
You're only a queen, tsunami said.

07:50:05.639 --> 07:50:07.919
You might have their rain wings and night

07:50:07.919 --> 07:50:09.840
wings wrapped around your tail, but

07:50:09.840 --> 07:50:11.040
you're still not the boss of me.

07:50:11.099 --> 07:50:14.580
And neither are you, Mr. Mooney Eyes, she

07:50:14.580 --> 07:50:16.740
said to Deathbringer, as he landed beside

07:50:16.740 --> 07:50:17.040
glory.

07:50:17.159 --> 07:50:19.380
I bet I could knock you off this mountain

07:50:19.380 --> 07:50:20.220
if I wanted to.

07:50:20.279 --> 07:50:22.860
I think you're proving my point.

07:50:22.919 --> 07:50:25.919
Glory mused, and then ducked a tsunami

07:50:25.919 --> 07:50:26.880
tried to swat her again.

07:50:26.939 --> 07:50:30.479
My brothers and sisters will come, Clay

07:50:30.479 --> 07:50:33.000
said, I think, if they know I'm here.

07:50:33.060 --> 07:50:36.060
Umber was telling me he hardly knows any

07:50:36.060 --> 07:50:38.520
history, and his reading's not so great.

07:50:38.580 --> 07:50:40.200
He'd love to learn more.

07:50:40.259 --> 07:50:42.720
We should ask Webbs to be one of the

07:50:42.720 --> 07:50:44.220
teachers, Sonny said.

07:50:44.279 --> 07:50:45.659
Now that he's all recovered.

07:50:45.720 --> 07:50:48.240
I mean, whatever else you guys think of

07:50:48.240 --> 07:50:50.220
him, you have to admit he was a good

07:50:50.220 --> 07:50:51.060
history teacher.

07:50:51.119 --> 07:50:53.580
And he can't go home to the kingdom of

07:50:53.580 --> 07:50:54.000
the sea.

07:50:54.060 --> 07:50:56.880
Carl's never going to forgive him, even

07:50:56.880 --> 07:50:58.740
if she lets all the other talons come

07:50:58.740 --> 07:50:59.159
back one day.

07:50:59.220 --> 07:51:01.020
I vote yes.

07:51:01.080 --> 07:51:03.299
I'd be happy to finally get him out of my

07:51:03.299 --> 07:51:05.099
rainforest, Glory said.

07:51:05.159 --> 07:51:07.919
Much as he would clearly prefer to stay

07:51:07.919 --> 07:51:09.540
in bed eating fruit forever.

07:51:09.599 --> 07:51:12.299
She flicked her tail, turning orange

07:51:12.299 --> 07:51:13.139
around her ears.

07:51:13.200 --> 07:51:16.080
Kinkajoo and Tamron will want to come for

07:51:16.080 --> 07:51:16.319
sure.

07:51:16.380 --> 07:51:19.560
They need real teachers, not the scraps

07:51:19.560 --> 07:51:20.700
of time I have for them.

07:51:20.759 --> 07:51:22.259
I'll send some others.

07:51:22.319 --> 07:51:24.299
As long as you promise they'll still get

07:51:24.299 --> 07:51:25.560
their afternoon suntime.

07:51:25.619 --> 07:51:27.779
Don't forget mighty claws.

07:51:27.840 --> 07:51:30.360
Deathbringer suggested, and that little

07:51:30.360 --> 07:51:31.919
night wing whose mother hid her egg in

07:51:31.919 --> 07:51:32.459
the rainforest.

07:51:32.520 --> 07:51:35.939
Moon Watcher, Glory said, nodding.

07:51:36.000 --> 07:51:38.040
Poor little nervous dragonette.

07:51:38.159 --> 07:51:40.919
And my sisters, tsunami said.

07:51:40.979 --> 07:51:43.740
I bet I could get mother to send anemone

07:51:43.740 --> 07:51:44.700
and Aucklet.

07:51:44.759 --> 07:51:46.799
Although then we might have to let Queen

07:51:46.799 --> 07:51:49.259
Kroll visit, like pretty much every day.

07:51:49.319 --> 07:51:53.220
Wow, Sonny said, they all survived.

07:51:53.279 --> 07:51:55.500
All these dragons we care about.

07:51:55.560 --> 07:51:56.700
Isn't that amazing?

07:51:56.819 --> 07:52:00.240
I mean, except Dune and Kestrel.

07:52:00.360 --> 07:52:02.520
She looked down at her talons.

07:52:02.580 --> 07:52:07.200
And Viper, fate speaker added, and my

07:52:07.200 --> 07:52:09.720
father, Tsunami said quietly.

07:52:09.779 --> 07:52:12.240
Sonny reached over and twined her tail

07:52:12.240 --> 07:52:13.319
around tsunamis.

07:52:13.380 --> 07:52:15.659
The other great thing about this school

07:52:15.659 --> 07:52:16.139
idea?

07:52:16.259 --> 07:52:19.259
Sonny said after a moment, is that this

07:52:19.259 --> 07:52:20.340
way we can all stay together.

07:52:20.400 --> 07:52:23.040
I mean, if you want to.

07:52:23.099 --> 07:52:25.200
If you want to go back to your families

07:52:25.200 --> 07:52:27.180
you can, but we'll always have a place

07:52:27.180 --> 07:52:28.200
where we can be together.

07:52:28.259 --> 07:52:31.139
I'd rather be with you all than in the

07:52:31.139 --> 07:52:34.020
mud kingdom, Clay said readily, especially

07:52:34.020 --> 07:52:35.639
if I can get Umber and the others here.

07:52:35.700 --> 07:52:38.340
Same, tsunami said.

07:52:38.400 --> 07:52:41.040
I'm afraid if I go home, mother will

07:52:41.040 --> 07:52:43.139
somehow get a harness on me, or at least

07:52:43.139 --> 07:52:45.060
want to watch me every moment of the day

07:52:45.060 --> 07:52:47.700
and it'll be easier to learn aquatic here

07:52:47.700 --> 07:52:49.799
than in the Deep Palace, where there

07:52:49.799 --> 07:52:51.540
would be a 1000000 eyes on me all the

07:52:51.540 --> 07:52:54.000
time, and hardly any chances to come up

07:52:54.000 --> 07:52:54.840
to the surface to talk.

07:52:54.900 --> 07:52:56.400
She shuddered.

07:52:56.459 --> 07:52:58.979
Worse, no one could understand me.

07:52:59.040 --> 07:53:01.500
How would I boss anyone around?

07:53:01.560 --> 07:53:04.439
Sonny giggled, and tsunami shatter a

07:53:04.439 --> 07:53:04.919
grin.

07:53:04.979 --> 07:53:08.340
I have to stay in the rainforest, Glory

07:53:08.340 --> 07:53:09.959
said, but it's not far.

07:53:10.020 --> 07:53:11.340
I could visit all the time.

07:53:11.400 --> 07:53:15.060
Starflight didn't say anything, but they

07:53:15.060 --> 07:53:16.860
all knew he had no attachment to the

07:53:16.860 --> 07:53:18.720
Nightwing village that was being built in

07:53:18.720 --> 07:53:19.319
the rainforest.

07:53:19.380 --> 07:53:23.639
His father, mastermind, was in prison, or

07:53:23.639 --> 07:53:25.439
the closest thing the rain wings could

07:53:25.439 --> 07:53:27.959
come up with anyway, until glory could

07:53:27.959 --> 07:53:29.279
figure out how to try him for his

07:53:29.279 --> 07:53:29.700
crimes.

07:53:29.759 --> 07:53:32.340
And fierce teeth was still in the

07:53:32.340 --> 07:53:33.060
Scorpion den.

07:53:33.180 --> 07:53:35.400
Sonny reminded herself that she had to

07:53:35.400 --> 07:53:37.680
talk to Thorn about her and Strongwings.

07:53:37.799 --> 07:53:40.020
Once they figured out what they wanted to

07:53:40.020 --> 07:53:40.380
do with them.

07:53:40.439 --> 07:53:42.599
Oh, I know.

07:53:42.720 --> 07:53:45.299
Peril, Clay said suddenly.

07:53:45.360 --> 07:53:47.580
Peril could be one of the students.

07:53:47.639 --> 07:53:50.639
She's got nowhere else to go, and we'd

07:53:50.639 --> 07:53:51.659
know how to take care of her.

07:53:51.720 --> 07:53:54.240
Sunny caught the look that went between

07:53:54.240 --> 07:53:55.619
glory and tsunami.

07:53:55.680 --> 07:53:58.500
They all knew they owed peril clay's life

07:53:58.500 --> 07:54:00.360
but it was still hard to feel entirely

07:54:00.360 --> 07:54:01.080
safe around her.

07:54:01.139 --> 07:54:04.259
She really doesn't know where Scarlet

07:54:04.259 --> 07:54:04.560
is?

07:54:04.619 --> 07:54:05.819
Tsunami asked.

07:54:05.880 --> 07:54:07.919
Isn't that a little weird that she

07:54:07.919 --> 07:54:10.080
rescued Scarlet and then Scarlet just

07:54:10.080 --> 07:54:11.040
vanished on her?

07:54:11.099 --> 07:54:13.139
Peril's out looking for now?

07:54:13.200 --> 07:54:14.400
Clay said.

07:54:14.459 --> 07:54:17.159
She said Scarlet was appearing in her

07:54:17.159 --> 07:54:19.740
dreams all the time before the rescue, but

07:54:19.740 --> 07:54:20.819
she hasn't come back since.

07:54:20.880 --> 07:54:24.000
Maybe we could use our dream visitor to

07:54:24.000 --> 07:54:26.759
look for her, Sonny suggested, except

07:54:26.759 --> 07:54:29.279
then she'll see us too, which makes me so

07:54:29.279 --> 07:54:29.819
nervous.

07:54:29.880 --> 07:54:31.979
I wish we'd found the obsidian mirror.

07:54:32.040 --> 07:54:34.799
She'd gone back to the outskirts of the

07:54:34.799 --> 07:54:37.319
Scorpion den to look for it, but as she'd

07:54:37.319 --> 07:54:39.659
feared, every sand dune looked the same

07:54:39.659 --> 07:54:41.580
and a day of digging had turned up

07:54:41.580 --> 07:54:41.880
nothing.

07:54:41.939 --> 07:54:44.639
Either someone else had found it, which

07:54:44.639 --> 07:54:46.919
was also a worrying thought, or the

07:54:46.919 --> 07:54:48.119
desert had swallowed it up.

07:54:48.180 --> 07:54:52.080
It is disturbing, Deathbringer said

07:54:52.080 --> 07:54:53.340
frowning up at the sky.

07:54:53.400 --> 07:54:55.560
She's going to come for you sometime

07:54:55.560 --> 07:54:58.319
especially you, he said to Glory.

07:54:58.380 --> 07:55:00.240
Glory shrugged.

07:55:00.299 --> 07:55:02.880
I'll let you worry about that, she said.

07:55:02.939 --> 07:55:05.159
Oh, thanks, he said.

07:55:05.220 --> 07:55:06.299
You know I will.

07:55:06.419 --> 07:55:08.939
Fine by me. she said.

07:55:09.000 --> 07:55:11.759
And despite their sarcastic words, the

07:55:11.759 --> 07:55:13.680
look they gave each other made tsunami

07:55:13.680 --> 07:55:14.759
roll her eyes at Sonny.

07:55:14.819 --> 07:55:17.580
I wonder if they'll have dragonettes

07:55:17.580 --> 07:55:18.180
together one day.

07:55:18.240 --> 07:55:20.880
Will anyone complain that the queen of

07:55:20.880 --> 07:55:22.560
the rain wings should be with another

07:55:22.560 --> 07:55:23.819
rain wing instead?

07:55:23.880 --> 07:55:26.220
A half rain wing, half night wing

07:55:26.220 --> 07:55:27.419
dragonette?

07:55:27.479 --> 07:55:28.139
What would that look like?

07:55:28.200 --> 07:55:30.240
Everything in one dragon?

07:55:30.240 --> 07:55:32.400
Or something different, like me?

07:55:32.459 --> 07:55:35.520
Then I wouldn't be the only half tribe

07:55:35.520 --> 07:55:36.360
dragon in the world.

07:55:36.419 --> 07:55:40.619
Below them in the caves, Sonny knew her

07:55:40.619 --> 07:55:42.540
mother was having an awkward reunion with

07:55:42.540 --> 07:55:43.200
Stone Mover.

07:55:43.259 --> 07:55:46.680
They both changed so much over the last 7

07:55:46.680 --> 07:55:46.860
years.

07:55:46.979 --> 07:55:49.380
There wasn't much in common between the

07:55:49.380 --> 07:55:51.479
new queen of the sand wings, and the

07:55:51.479 --> 07:55:53.580
partly stone enchanter hermit of Jade

07:55:53.580 --> 07:55:54.119
Mountain.

07:55:54.299 --> 07:55:56.580
Sonny had been with him for the 1st few

07:55:56.580 --> 07:55:58.619
moments, but it had been way too

07:55:58.619 --> 07:55:59.040
strange.

07:55:59.099 --> 07:56:01.439
So she'd fled out here to her friends

07:56:01.439 --> 07:56:02.099
instead.

07:56:02.159 --> 07:56:05.819
Oh, she said, remembering something.

07:56:05.880 --> 07:56:07.500
One of the things we have to teach

07:56:07.500 --> 07:56:10.020
everyone is that the night wings don't

07:56:10.020 --> 07:56:11.759
have any of those powers that they've

07:56:11.759 --> 07:56:12.479
been claiming to have.

07:56:12.540 --> 07:56:14.759
We can't let everyone still be afraid of

07:56:14.759 --> 07:56:15.599
them, right?

07:56:15.659 --> 07:56:18.840
Except me, fate speaker protested.

07:56:18.900 --> 07:56:21.299
I totally so do have powers.

07:56:21.360 --> 07:56:24.479
Fade speaker, Glory said sternly.

07:56:24.540 --> 07:56:25.680
We talked about this.

07:56:25.740 --> 07:56:30.180
All right, all right, your majesty, fate

07:56:30.180 --> 07:56:33.180
speaker said, subsiding grumbly, but I

07:56:33.180 --> 07:56:35.220
swear my visions really do feel real.

07:56:35.340 --> 07:56:38.279
But that comment went away again without

07:56:38.279 --> 07:56:39.119
falling on us.

07:56:39.180 --> 07:56:40.740
Starflight pointed out.

07:56:40.799 --> 07:56:42.119
Didn't that convince you?

07:56:42.180 --> 07:56:44.700
Fate speaker had the grace to look a

07:56:44.700 --> 07:56:45.360
little embarrassed.

07:56:45.419 --> 07:56:48.840
Well, she said, it could still come

07:56:48.840 --> 07:56:49.020
back.

07:56:49.139 --> 07:56:52.439
Sunny started giggling, and after a

07:56:52.439 --> 07:56:54.540
moment, fate speaker's dramatic face

07:56:54.540 --> 07:56:56.099
cracked, and she joined in.

07:56:56.159 --> 07:56:58.619
What about our prophecy?

07:56:58.680 --> 07:57:02.040
Clay said, Won't it confuse everyone if

07:57:02.040 --> 07:57:03.659
we tell them it wasn't real after all?

07:57:03.720 --> 07:57:06.000
Sonny thought about that for a moment.

07:57:06.060 --> 07:57:09.360
Maybe we could say the Night Wings lost

07:57:09.360 --> 07:57:11.159
their powers along with their home.

07:57:11.220 --> 07:57:14.340
So that was it, the last prophecy.

07:57:14.400 --> 07:57:18.060
The last prophecy, Starflight echoed.

07:57:18.180 --> 07:57:21.479
Three moons, yes, tsunami said.

07:57:21.540 --> 07:57:22.860
That is what I vote for.

07:57:22.919 --> 07:57:24.659
No more prophecies ever again.

07:57:24.720 --> 07:57:28.020
I guess we just make it up from here

07:57:28.020 --> 07:57:31.259
Sonny said, watching the wind tug at her

07:57:31.259 --> 07:57:31.979
wings and tail.

07:57:32.099 --> 07:57:35.040
Far below them, hawks soared over the

07:57:35.040 --> 07:57:35.880
ridges and valleys.

07:57:36.000 --> 07:57:38.220
Bad news, Sonny.

07:57:38.279 --> 07:57:40.259
I'm pretty sure we've been making it up

07:57:40.259 --> 07:57:41.340
this whole time.

07:57:41.400 --> 07:57:42.540
Glory said.

07:57:42.599 --> 07:57:44.279
Sonny laughed.

07:57:44.340 --> 07:57:45.419
That's true.

07:57:45.479 --> 07:57:47.159
And things turned out all right anyway.

07:57:47.220 --> 07:57:51.299
Well, I know what I want my destiny to be

07:57:51.299 --> 07:57:52.439
Clay said.

07:57:52.560 --> 07:57:55.080
I wanted to be sleeping and being friends

07:57:55.080 --> 07:57:56.279
with you guys forever.

07:57:56.340 --> 07:57:59.099
Oh, wait, also feasting.

07:57:59.159 --> 07:58:01.380
Lots of feasting.

07:58:01.439 --> 07:58:05.159
That sounds great, Starflight said, best

07:58:05.159 --> 07:58:06.060
destiny ever.

07:58:06.180 --> 07:58:09.419
We can make that happen, Sonny said

07:58:09.419 --> 07:58:11.279
smiling, and all of them spread their

07:58:11.279 --> 07:58:13.500
wings and leaped into the wide open sky.

07:58:13.560 --> 07:58:18.779
Wings of fire will continue.

07:58:18.840 --> 07:58:21.419
The war is over.

07:58:21.479 --> 07:58:23.880
The false prophecy has been fulfilled.

07:58:23.939 --> 07:58:26.639
But the Dragonettes still have enemies.

07:58:26.700 --> 07:58:30.599
A dark evil, buried for centuries, is

07:58:30.599 --> 07:58:31.139
stirring.

07:58:31.200 --> 07:58:34.080
And a young night wing may have had the

07:58:34.080 --> 07:58:36.000
1st true prophecy in generations.

07:58:36.060 --> 07:58:39.659
Something is coming to shake the earth.

07:58:39.720 --> 07:58:42.240
Something is coming to scorch the

07:58:42.240 --> 07:58:42.540
ground.

07:58:42.599 --> 07:58:45.599
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

07:58:45.599 --> 07:58:48.360
and ice, unless the lost city of night

07:58:48.360 --> 07:58:48.959
can be found.

